/****** Object:  StoredProcedure [dbo].[owp_PostSnapshot]    Script Date: 03/08/2012 13:35:36 ******

Program:      owp_PostSnapshot           
Author:       Greg Kulawiak
Date created: 14/10/2010           
                      
 Description:   This procedure is run after a TR Snapshot refresh and recreates the 
				constraints and indexes dropped when the staging are tables are
				dropped by the TR process. The TR Snapshot then recreates the table
				and reloads them by BCP'ing data across from the source database.

                It is called as follows:
					exec owp_PostSnapshot 'Insight'
					exec owp_PostSnapshot 'OBP'
					exec owp_PostSnapshot 'SWIFT'
        *****************************************************************************************
		*																						*	
		*	NOTE:	When adding new Articles (tables) do NOT add primary key/clustered			*
		*	indexes via this procedure as this is done automatically by the Snapshot.			*
		*	These additional indexes then cause the Distribution job to fail.					*
		*																						*
		*****************************************************************************************
		
                  
Amendment History               
-----------------               
                      
Date        Who       Description       
----        ---       -----------     
14/10/2010  GK        Proc created
21/12/2010  GK        Fix for Mortgage Providers
06/01/2011  GK        Change Provider for non-Mortgage arrangements (derive using ISL)
18/01/2011  GK        Add column ARIDstr for easier downstream processing
16/03/2011  GK        PROD failure fix - 5 update statements added
17/03/2011  GK        Sums Assured added
21/03/2011  GK        Application Date added
08/03/2012	MPC		  Amended Plan Index created on sa_obp_OpportunityVersion to use
					  PlanSnapshotId which has superseded the dropped column PlanId.
					  Change triggered by DT changes scheduled for deployment on 5/4/12.
29/03/2012	MPC		  Added new Index [PlanId] to the sa_obp_PlanSnapshot table. Note
					  an earlier change to add a Clustered index on the primary key [ID]
					  was reversed as it caused the Distribution job to fail (please 
					  see the NOTE in the comment section at the top of the procedure).
30/10/2012 LN		  Added section for OpenworkSolution (OWS)
19/11/2012 LN		  Added section for ABS.
21/03/2017 CM		  Added another index to swift
10/04/2017 CM		  Added another index to swift
***************************************************************************************/
CREATE PROCEDURE [dbo].[owp_PostSnapshot]
	@SourceSystem VARCHAR(25)
WITH EXECUTE AS CALLER
AS
BEGIN
	SET NOCOUNT ON;

	IF @SourceSystem = 'swift'
	BEGIN
		BEGIN TRY
