/*********************************************************************************************************

Program:		owp_RecognitionGIPaymentshield					
Author:			Alan Groves
Date created:	20/04/2018
											
Description:
===========

This proc populates the new recognition table called "owt_Recognition" with "Value of New Business"
(VNB) points.

This proc handles the GI (Paymentshield) data. 

Note: There is a separate proc that calculates the VNB points for Swift data covering:
WEALTH - COB business i.e. pensions and investments
MORTGAGES
PROTECTION

The approach of this proc is to use the same data-set loaded by the last Paymentshield load
to calculate the VNB points in a temporary table.

The temporary table is then merged with the permanent table to make the calculated (or
re-calculated values) permanent.

Terms
-----
DA	- Distribution Allowance (the total amount paid out by the provider to Openwork)


THE CALCULATION
===============

GI
--
Note: for GI, DA and APE are the same.
= (DA X GI Retention Rate) - (DA X GI FCA Rate) 
GI Points Total = Initial


This proc is called as follows:
	declare @rc int
	exec @rc = dbo.owp_RecognitionGIPaymentshield 'Openwork', 'Recognition'
	select @rc

				
AMENDMENT HISTORY				
=================								

Date		Author		Description
----		------		-----------
03/05/2018	A Groves	Added update of column "msit_OpenworkAdviserListing.VNB_Points".
21/05/2018	A Groves	1) At Marcus Cossey's request, GI payments should only be in scope
							in their first year. Typically, this will include the first payment
							and any clawbacks/adjustments that might occur throughout that first
							year.
						2) In the case of clawbacks/adjustments, the DA is not on the data
							row. Therefore, where the payment is negative, then the "PaymentAmount"
							is used. Where the payment is positive, then the "DA" is used.
23/05/2018	A Groves	Changed value stored in "PaymentReceived" column from "pcp.DA" to
							"pcp.PaymentAmount" as the latter is used for clawbacks and adjustments.
24/05/2018	A Groves	Marcus Cossey asked for the following payments to be excluded from VNB:
						1) Where OrigCommType = 'Renewal'
						2) Where OrigStatus = 'RENEWAL'
						Note: Marcus didn't want to simply include the oldest +ve payment and all
						-ve payments in the first 12 months, as he did not want to miss out any
						MTA (mid term adjustment) credits.
05/06/2018	A Groves	New columns introduced (for the benefit of the wealth calculation):
						1) ReassignedProductGroupCode
						2) ReassignedProductGroupName
*************************************************************************************************************/

CREATE PROCEDURE [dbo].[owp_RecognitionGIPaymentshield_Backup20180613AG]
	@Client		varchar(50),
	@Module		Varchar(50)
AS

set nocount on

declare		@PhaseStart				varchar(50),
			@PhaseEnd				varchar(50),
			@PhaseError				varchar(50),
			@PhaseLog				varchar(50),
			@ProcName				varchar(100),
			@ProcessMessage			varchar(100),
			@RowCount				int,
			@OALRowCount			int,
			@ErrMsg					nvarchar(4000),
			@ErrMsgBrief			nvarchar(100),
			@ErrNum					int,
			@ErrSev					int,
			@ErrLine				int,
			@ErrState				int
			
/****************************************************************************

	Set initial parameters																
																		
****************************************************************************/

set @ProcName			= object_name(@@procid)
set @PhaseStart			= 'START'
set @PhaseEnd			= 'END'
set @PhaseError			= 'ERROR'
set @PhaseLog			= 'LOG'
set @ErrNum				= 0	

-- We want this logging irrespective of whether or not there is a rollback
exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseStart, @ProcName, null, @Module, @Client

/****************************************************************************

	Populate the table																
																		
****************************************************************************/

SET XACT_ABORT ON	-- Needed if XACT_STATE() function is used.

BEGIN TRY

	/****************************************************************************

		Calculate VNB and populate the temporary table with the results
																		
	****************************************************************************/

	select top 0 *
	into #owt_Recognition
	from owt_Recognition

	declare @OwlManager2Code nvarchar(10)
	set @OwlManager2Code = (select cde.Code from msit_MIWarehouseCodesAndDescriptions cde
				where cde.ColumnName = 'Manager2Code' and cde.Description = 'Owl Financial')
	declare @DateLastUpdated datetime = getdate()

	--AG 21/05/2018. Get the oldest payment date for each policy so that the 12 month period can be derived
	select	Policy, MIN(PaymentDate) as MinPaymentDate
	into	#EarliestPolPayments
	from	owt_PaymentshieldCommissionPayments pcp
			inner join mstt_Agents ag on ag.Code = pcp.BusinessCode
	where	ag.Manager2Code <> @OwlManager2Code		--Exclude Owl
	group	by Policy

	insert into #owt_Recognition
	(
		SourceID,
		CaseID,
		TransactionID,
		Policy,
		ProductCode,
		BusinessCode,
		PointsTotal,
		BSC,
		MBF,
		Initial,
		OngoingTotal,
		OngoingYr01,
		OngoingYr02,
		OngoingYr03,
		OngoingYr04,
		OngoingYr05,
		OngoingYr06,
		OngoingYr07,
		OngoingYr08,
		OngoingYr09,
		OngoingYr10,
		FCARate,
		RetentionRate,
		RetentionRateBroker,
		OngoingServicingRate,
		OngoingServicingSource,
		DA,
		AmountReceived,
		Premium,
		AgentSplit,
		CommissionType,
		CommissionTypeDesc,
		Month,
		FrequencyCode,
		FrequencyDesc,
		ReassignedProductGroupCode,		--AG 05/06/2018
		ReassignedProductGroupName,		--AG 05/06/2018
		RecognitionType,
		CalculationType,
		Source,
		DateInserted,
		DateLastUpdated
	)
	select	pcp.ID as SourceID,
			null as CaseID,
			null as TransactionID,
			pcp.Policy,
			pcp.HierarchyProduct as ProductCode,
			pcp.BusinessCode,
			case when pcp.PaymentAmount < 0.0		--AG 21/05/2018
				then ((pcp.PaymentAmount * GIrate.FACTOR) - (pcp.PaymentAmount * GIfca.FACTOR)) * GIrate.Multiplier 
				else ((pcp.DA * GIrate.FACTOR) - (pcp.DA * GIfca.FACTOR)) * GIrate.Multiplier 
			end as PointsTotal,
			0 as BSC,
			0 as MBF,
			case when pcp.PaymentAmount < 0.0		--AG 21/05/2018
				then ((pcp.PaymentAmount * GIrate.FACTOR) - (pcp.PaymentAmount * GIfca.FACTOR)) * GIrate.Multiplier 
				else ((pcp.DA * GIrate.FACTOR) - (pcp.DA * GIfca.FACTOR)) * GIrate.Multiplier 
			end as Initial,
			0 as OngoingTotal,
			0 as OngoingYr01,
			0 as OngoingYr02,
			0 as OngoingYr03,
			0 as OngoingYr04,
			0 as OngoingYr05,
			0 as OngoingYr06,
			0 as OngoingYr07,
			0 as OngoingYr08,
			0 as OngoingYr09,
			0 as OngoingYr10,
			GIfca.FACTOR*100.0 as FCARate,
			GIrate.FACTOR*100.0 as RetentionRate,
			0 as RetentionRateBroker,
			null as OngoingServicingRate,
			null as OngoingServicingSource,
			pcp.DA,
			pcp.PaymentAmount as AmountReceived,	--AG 23/05/2018
			pcp.Premium,
			100.0 as AgentSplit,
			null as CommissionType,
			pcp.FeeType as CommissionTypeDesc,
			pcp.Month,
			null as FrequencyCode,
			pcp.Frequency as FrequencyDesc,
			1 as ReassignedProductGroupCode,		--AG 05/06/2018
			'GI' as ReassignedProductGroupName,		--AG 05/06/2018
			'VNB' as RecognitionType,
			'GI' as CalculationType,
			pcp.Source,
			@DateLastUpdated as DateInserted,
			@DateLastUpdated as DateLastUpdated
	from	owt_PaymentshieldCommissionPayments pcp
/*			inner join (select max(FileID) as FileID
						from owt_PaymentshieldImportControl) X on pcp.CreateDate = X.FileID
*/			inner join #EarliestPolPayments epp on epp.Policy = pcp.Policy
			inner join mstt_Agents ag on ag.Code = pcp.BusinessCode
			inner join msit_Commissionstatementperiods csp on csp.month = pcp.month
			inner join msit_CommissionStatementPeriods VNBStart on convert(date,pcp.StartDate) between VNBStart.PeriodStartDate and VNBStart.PeriodEndDate
			left join owt_EliteFactors GIfca on GIfca.FeeType = 'VNB' and GIfca.category = 'GI-FCA-RATE' and csp.year between GIfca.StartYear and GIfca.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors GIrate on GIrate.FeeType = 'VNB' and GIrate.category = 'GI-RETENTION-RATE' and csp.year between GIrate.StartYear and GIrate.EndYear 
	where	ag.Manager2Code <> @OwlManager2Code		--Exclude Owl
	and		pcp.PaymentAmount <> 0 
	and		pcp.SalesMoveFlag <> 'N'				--Although <> 'N' is loaded to OA, only = 'Y' gets DA, etc. calculated.
	and		pcp.OrigCommtype <> 'Renewal'			--AG 24/05/2018
	and		pcp.OrigStatus <> 'RENEWAL'				--AG 24/05/2018
	--IC and Adj must be in 1st year of policy. Add 11 months to 01/05/2017 and you get 01/04/2018 as required.
	and		pcp.PaymentDate <= DATEADD(mm,11,epp.MinPaymentDate)	--AG 21/05/2018	
	and		VNBStart.Year >= 2017					--VNB to start from 2017
	and		csp.Year >= 2017						--Ensure in-scope payments are consistent with VNB start

	select @RowCount = @@rowcount
	set @ProcessMessage = '#owt_Recognition = ' + convert(nvarchar(10), @RowCount)
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseLog, @ProcessMessage, null, @Module, @Client
	
	/****************************************************************************

		Merge the temporary table into the permanent table
																		
	****************************************************************************/

	BEGIN TRANSACTION

	declare @SummaryOfChanges table (Change varchar(20))
	merge	dbo.owt_Recognition as trg
	using	#owt_Recognition as src
	on		trg.SourceID = src.SourceID
	and		trg.Source = src.Source
	when	matched 
	and		isnull(trg.PointsTotal,0) <> isnull(src.PointsTotal,0)
	then	update 
				set trg.CaseID = src.CaseID,
					trg.TransactionID = src.TransactionID,
					trg.Policy = src.Policy,
					trg.ProductCode = src.ProductCode,
					trg.BusinessCode = src.BusinessCode,
					trg.PointsTotal = src.PointsTotal,
					trg.BSC = src.BSC,
					trg.MBF = src.MBF,
					trg.Initial = src.Initial,
					trg.OngoingTotal = src.OngoingTotal,
					trg.OngoingYr01 = src.OngoingYr01,
					trg.OngoingYr02 = src.OngoingYr02,
					trg.OngoingYr03 = src.OngoingYr03,
					trg.OngoingYr04 = src.OngoingYr04,
					trg.OngoingYr05 = src.OngoingYr05,
					trg.OngoingYr06 = src.OngoingYr06,
					trg.OngoingYr07 = src.OngoingYr07,
					trg.OngoingYr08 = src.OngoingYr08,
					trg.OngoingYr09 = src.OngoingYr09,
					trg.OngoingYr10 = src.OngoingYr10,
					trg.FCARate = src.FCARate,
					trg.RetentionRate = src.RetentionRate,
					trg.RetentionRateBroker = src.RetentionRateBroker,
					trg.OngoingServicingRate = src.OngoingServicingRate,
					trg.OngoingServicingSource = src.OngoingServicingSource,
					trg.DA = src.DA,
					trg.AmountReceived = src.AmountReceived,
					trg.Premium = src.Premium,
					trg.AgentSplit = src.AgentSplit,
					trg.CommissionType = src.CommissionType,
					trg.CommissionTypeDesc = src.CommissionTypeDesc,
					trg.Month = src.Month,
					trg.FrequencyCode = src.FrequencyCode,
					trg.FrequencyDesc = src.FrequencyDesc,
					trg.ReassignedProductGroupCode = src.ReassignedProductGroupCode,	--AG 05/06/2018
					trg.ReassignedProductGroupName = src.ReassignedProductGroupCode,	--AG 05/06/2018
					trg.RecognitionType = src.RecognitionType,
					trg.CalculationType = src.CalculationType,
					trg.DateLastUpdated = @DateLastUpdated
	when	not matched by target 
	then	insert
			(
				SourceID,
				CaseID,
				TransactionID,
				Policy,
				ProductCode,
				BusinessCode,
				PointsTotal,
				BSC,
				MBF,
				Initial,
				OngoingTotal,
				OngoingYr01,
				OngoingYr02,
				OngoingYr03,
				OngoingYr04,
				OngoingYr05,
				OngoingYr06,
				OngoingYr07,
				OngoingYr08,
				OngoingYr09,
				OngoingYr10,
				FCARate,
				RetentionRate,
				RetentionRateBroker,
				OngoingServicingRate,
				OngoingServicingSource,
				DA,
				AmountReceived,
				Premium,
				AgentSplit,
				CommissionType,
				CommissionTypeDesc,
				Month,
				FrequencyCode,
				FrequencyDesc,
				ReassignedProductGroupCode,		--AG 05/06/2018
				ReassignedProductGroupName,		--AG 05/06/2018
				RecognitionType,
				CalculationType,
				Source,
				DateInserted,
				DateLastUpdated
			)		
			values
			(
				src.SourceID,
				src.CaseID,
				src.TransactionID,
				src.Policy,
				src.ProductCode,
				src.BusinessCode,
				src.PointsTotal,
				src.BSC,
				src.MBF,
				src.Initial,
				src.OngoingTotal,
				src.OngoingYr01,
				src.OngoingYr02,
				src.OngoingYr03,
				src.OngoingYr04,
				src.OngoingYr05,
				src.OngoingYr06,
				src.OngoingYr07,
				src.OngoingYr08,
				src.OngoingYr09,
				src.OngoingYr10,
				src.FCARate,
				src.RetentionRate,
				src.RetentionRateBroker,
				src.OngoingServicingRate,
				src.OngoingServicingSource,
				src.DA,
				src.AmountReceived,
				src.Premium,
				src.AgentSplit,
				src.CommissionType,
				src.CommissionTypeDesc,
				src.Month,
				src.FrequencyCode,
				src.FrequencyDesc,
				src.ReassignedProductGroupCode,		--AG 05/06/2018
				src.ReassignedProductGroupName,		--AG 05/06/2018
				src.RecognitionType,
				src.CalculationType,
				src.Source,
				src.DateInserted,
				src.DateLastUpdated)				
	output $action into @SummaryOfChanges;			--Merge statements must have a ;
/*	
	update	oal
		set VNB_Points = r.PointsTotal
	from	owt_PaymentshieldCommissionPayments pcp
/*			inner join (select max(FileID) as FileID
						from owt_PaymentshieldImportControl) X on pcp.CreateDate = X.FileID
*/			inner join msit_OpenworkAdviserListing oal on oal.SourceID = pcp.ID and oal.Source = 'Payshield'
			inner join owt_Recognition r 
						on r.RecognitionType = 'VNB'
						and r.SourceID = pcp.ID
						and r.Source = oal.Source		
	where	isnull(oal.VNB_Points,0) <> isnull(r.PointsTotal,0)
	
	select @OALRowCount = @@rowcount
*/
	COMMIT TRANSACTION      

	select	@RowCount = COUNT(*)
	from	@SummaryOfChanges
	where	Change = 'INSERT'

	set @ProcessMessage = 'owt_Recognition (insert) = ' + convert(nvarchar(10), @RowCount)
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseLog, @ProcessMessage, null, @Module, @Client

	select	@RowCount = COUNT(*)
	from	@SummaryOfChanges
	where	Change = 'UPDATE'

	set @ProcessMessage = 'owt_Recognition (update) = ' + convert(nvarchar(10), @RowCount)
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseLog, @ProcessMessage, null, @Module, @Client
/*
	set @ProcessMessage = 'msit_OpenworkAdviserListing (update) = ' + convert(nvarchar(10), @OALRowCount)
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseLog, @ProcessMessage, null, @Module, @Client
*/
	/****************************************************************************

		T H E   E N D
																		
	****************************************************************************/
	
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseEnd, @ProcName, null, @Module, @Client

END TRY

BEGIN CATCH 

	select @ErrNum = ERROR_NUMBER(), @ErrMsg = ERROR_MESSAGE(), @ErrSev = ERROR_SEVERITY(), @ErrLine = ERROR_LINE(), @ErrState = XACT_STATE()
	set @ErrMsg = REPLACE(@ErrMsg, '.', '') + ' (error no: ' + CAST(@ErrNum AS VARCHAR(10)) + ') on line ' + CAST(@ErrLine AS VARCHAR(10))
	
	-- Test XACT_STATE for 0, 1, or -1.
    -- If 1, the transaction is committable.
    -- If -1, the transaction is uncommittable and should be rolled back.
    -- If 0, there is no transaction and a commit or rollback operation would generate an error.

	if @ErrState = -1			-- Transaction is uncommitable
		rollback transaction

	if @ErrState = 1			
		commit transaction

	-- Error message line 1
	set @ErrMsgBrief = left(@ErrMsg,100)
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseError, @ErrMsgBrief, null, @Module, @Client
	
	-- Error message line 2 - if any text exists
	set @ErrMsgBrief = substring(@ErrMsg,101,100)
	if len(@ErrMsgBrief) > 0
		exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseError, @ErrMsgBrief, null, @Module, @Client

	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseEnd, @ProcName, null, @Module, @Client

	RAISERROR(@ErrMsg, @ErrSev , 1)

END CATCH

/****************************************************************************

			E N D															

****************************************************************************/

return @ErrNum



GO
/****** Object:  StoredProcedure [dbo].[owp_RecognitionSwift]    Script Date: 7/3/2026 3:44:25 PM ******/
SET ANSI_NULLS ON
GO
SET QUOTED_IDENTIFIER ON
GO
/*********************************************************************************************************

Program:		owp_RecognitionSwift					
Author:			Alan Groves
Date created:	11/04/2018
											
Description:
===========

This proc populates the new recognition table called "owt_Recognition" with "Value of New Business"
(VNB) points.

This proc handles all of the swift data which includes:
WEALTH - COB business i.e. pensions and investments
MORTGAGES
PROTECTION

Note: There is a separate proc that calculates the GI VNB points from the Paymentshield data.

The approach of this proc is to use the incremental PendingPaymentIDs from the overnight batch
to calculate the VNB points in a temporary table.

The temporary table is then merged with the permanent table to make the calculated (or
re-calculated values) permanent.

Terms
-----
BSC			- Business Service Charge.
MBF			- Mortgage Broker Fee.
OGS			- Ongoing Servicing.
BSC Rate	- 0.12% at the time of writing (24/04/2018). This could be changed by the business, but
				would also require some DEV work in OWS.
DF			- Discount Factor.
DA			- Distribution Allowance (the total amount paid out by the provider to Openwork)
AUM			- Assets Under Management. Basically the amount invested or the premium on investment
				cases.
Average AUM - Average amount invested annually which is equivalent to 6 months' premium.

THE CALCULATIONS
================

There are two potential parts: initial + ongoing (if ongoing applies). If BSC (applies to ongoing 
only) and MBF (applies to mortgages only) apply, then these are also included:

MORTGAGE
--------
Part 1: MBF column = (Advice Fee Amount X Broker Retention Rate) - (Advice Fee Amount X Mort FCA Rate)
Part 2: Initial column = (Proc Fee Amount X Mortgage Retention Rate) - (Proc Fee X Mort FCA Rate) 
Mortgage Points Total = Initial + MBF

PROTECTION
----------
= (DA X Protection Retention Rate) - (DA X Protection FCA Rate) 
Protection Points Total = Initial

WEALTH (COB i.e. pensions and investments)
------
Part 1: Initial column = (DA X Wealth Retention Rate) - (DA X Wealth FCA Rate)

Part 2:

****XXXX****

NOTE: Where the BSC rate is greater than the ongoing rate, then BSC gets ALL of the AVAILABLE 
ongoing.

****XXXX****

REGULAR - BSC applies:
Year 1 column = BSC Points + Non-BSC Points - FCA Points
Non-BSC Points = Ave AUM X (OGS Rate - BSC Rate) X COB Retention Rate
BSC Points = Ave AUM X BSC Rate
FCA Points = Ave AUM X OGS Rate X COB FCA Rate

REGULAR - Non-BSC: 
Year 1 column = (Ave AUM X OGS Rate X COB Retention Rate) - (Ave AUM X OGS Rate X COB FCA Rate)

SINGLE - BSC applies:
Year 1 column = (AUM X BSC Rate) + (AUM X (OGS Rate - BSC Rate) X COB Retention Rate) - (AUM X OGS Rate X COB FCA Rate) 

SINGLE - Non-BSC:
Year 1 column = (AUM X OGS Rate X COB Retention Rate) - (AUM X OGS Rate X COB FCA Rate) 

Then years 2 to 10 are calculated by applying a discount factor
Year  2 = Year 1 X  3 X DF
Year  3 = Year 1 X  5 X DF
Year  4 = Year 1 X  7 X DF
Year  5 = Year 1 X  9 X DF
Year  6 = Year 1 X 11 X DF
Year  7 = Year 1 X 13 X DF
Year  8 = Year 1 X 15 X DF
Year  9 = Year 1 X 17 X DF
Year 10 = Year 1 X 19 X DF

Wealth Points Total =	OngoingYr01 + OngoingYr02 + OngoingYr03 + OngoingYr04 + OngoingYr05 +
						OngoingYr06 + OngoingYr07 + OngoingYr08 + OngoingYr09 + OngoingYr10 +
						Initial

GI
--
See stored proc "owp_RecognitionGIPaymentshield".
 
Notes:
-----

1)	There is a BSC column on table owt_Recognition. However, BSC is already included in the ongoing
	years 1 - 10, so the BSC column does not need to be added in. In fact you will double count if 
	you attempt to do anything with it other than display it.

2)	Occasionally an investment case may receive two or more cheques which
	then go through Swift as two or more SINGLE investments on the SAME
	slice. Although the INITIAL VNB calculation will pro-rata correctly
	because it is based on the amount received, this scenario will cause
	ongoing VNB to be calculated on each of the payment records and so will 
	double count (or worse if there are more than two cheques received).
	Since de-coupling IC from ongoing i.e. they now have separate rows on
	table owt_Recognition, the issue of multiple cheques should no longer
	cause ongoing double counting.


This proc is called as follows:
	declare @rc int
	exec @rc = dbo.owp_RecognitionSwift 'Openwork', 'Recognition'
	select @rc

					
AMENDMENT HISTORY				
=================								

Date		Author		Description
----		------		-----------
26/04/2018	A Groves	Only include rows in the OGS lookups where the OngoingServiceFee > 0.0.
						Negative OGS rates are bad data and at the time of writing, there are
						39 of these.
27/04/2018	A Groves	Additional calculation and condition to handle the scenario where BSC applies
						but the OGS Rate is less than the BSC rate. Previously, this caused the
						total ongoing to be zero. However, there are two components to ongoing VNB 
						points, the BSC share and the non-BSC share. So the BSC share (which takes 
						100% when the OGS rate is less than 0.12%) should still yield ongoing points.
27/04/2018	A Groves	Single ongoing Yr01 corrected by applying outer brackets before signing the result.
03/05/2018	A Groves	Added update of column "msit_OpenworkAdviserListing.VNB_Points".
18/05/2018	A Groves	Changed mortgage calculation to use e.AMOUNT_REC instead of pt.CommInitialAmount
						as Marcus Cossey wanted the actual amount received to be used for the DA.
04/06/2018	A Groves	1) In the REGULAR section of column "OngoingYr01", the condition for cs.FrequencyCode <> 6
							was added to ensure the code differentiates to the SINGLE section.
						2) Exclude MBF from the OpenAccess table (msit_OpenworkAdviserListing) as this
							is shown on the MBF download and would otherwise incur MBF double counting.
05/06/2018	A Groves	1) Marcus Cossey advised that investments should get ongoing for years 1 to 6 and
							pensions for years 1 to 10. Previously, both lines of business got years 1 to 10.
						2) Marcus Cossey asked for split payments (i.e. where multiple cheques are processed
							for a SINGLE investment) to only claculate ongoing VNB on the oldest payment. 
11/06/2018	A Groves	1) PSD processed a protection clawback statement as fee type initial. These clawbacks
							all generated +ve instead of -ve VNB points. A tweak was added to ensure that the 
							absolute value of AMOUNT_REC is used to ensure the VNB is correctly signed. 
						2) Another unknown business rule has surfaced: Previously, only initial, clawbacks and
							adjustments on slices created new from 2017 were included. This rule only applies
							to initial. Clawbacks and adjustments can belong to a slice created at any point
							in the past. However, note that the payment (irrespective of whether it is +ve or 
							-ve), must not pre-date 2017.
13/06/2018	A Groves	Marcus asked for SellerCode and PaymentMatchedDate to be added so he need only use 
							the one table for both the adviser and enterprise leagues. PayBasisCode and 
							PayBasisDesc were also added at the same time as these are used in the calculations.
06/07/2018	A Groves	Replaced the OGS Rate lookup on the fly to using table dbo.owt_OngoingRate. This was 
							done to ensure the rate used at any point in time stays the same, so the onging VNB
							will always give the same result each time the calculation runs.
17/07/2018	A Groves	Marcus asked for the ongoing calculation to be based on the sum of premium across
							all the initial transactions where an initial fee has been paid.
19/07/2018	A Groves	Agreed with Marcus that any initial premium that isn't covered by ongoing slices
							needs to be added to the OGS calculation to ensure advisers are not under
							rewarded. The missing OGS premium is added to the oldest OGS payment.
24/07/2018	A Groves	When moving back to the original table during final testing, it was clear that the
							MERGE statement at the end needed a DELETE step as it is possible for transaction/
							payment pairs to disappear.
27/07/2018	A Groves	Corrected update of msit_OpenworkAdviserListing
							from:	isnull(oal.VNB_Points,0) <> isnull(r.PointsTotal,0)
							to:		isnull(oal.VNB_Points,0) <> isnull(r.PointsTotal - r.MBF,0)
						This stops unnecessary updates where a value for MBF exists.
*************************************************************************************************************/

CREATE PROCEDURE [dbo].[owp_RecognitionSwift]
	@Client		varchar(50),
	@Module		Varchar(50)

AS

set nocount on

declare		@PhaseStart				varchar(50),
			@PhaseEnd				varchar(50),
			@PhaseError				varchar(50),
			@PhaseLog				varchar(50),
			@ProcName				varchar(100),
			@ProcessMessage			varchar(100),
			@RowCount				int,
			@OALRowCount			int,
			@ErrMsg					nvarchar(4000),
			@ErrMsgBrief			nvarchar(100),
			@ErrNum					int,
			@ErrSev					int,
			@ErrLine				int,
			@ErrState				int,
			@DateLastUpdated		datetime,
			@OwlManager2Code		nvarchar(10)
			
/****************************************************************************

	Set initial parameters																
																		
****************************************************************************/

set @ProcName			= object_name(@@procid)
set @PhaseStart			= 'START'
set @PhaseEnd			= 'END'
set @PhaseError			= 'ERROR'
set @PhaseLog			= 'LOG'
set @ErrNum				= 0	
set @DateLastUpdated	= getdate()

set @OwlManager2Code = (select cde.Code from msit_MIWarehouseCodesAndDescriptions cde
			where cde.ColumnName = 'Manager2Code' and cde.Description = 'Owl Financial')

-- We want this logging irrespective of whether or not there is a rollback
exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseStart, @ProcName, null, @Module, @Client

/****************************************************************************

	Populate the table																
																		
****************************************************************************/

SET XACT_ABORT ON	-- Needed if XACT_STATE() function is used.

BEGIN TRY

	/****************************************************************************

		Calculate VNB and populate the temporary table with the results
		
		Note that there are oddities like LV protection payments which always
		come in pairs with one large and one much smaller amount (e.g. TransactionID 
		= 6684787.) The system treats both payments in the pair as first payments 
		and the (projected) DA associated with both is the same (because it's on 
		the policy transaction). 
		
		There is also a requirement to front-load VNB points on accrual and level
		payments. This means calculate the VNB for the full amount of the DA and 
		put it on the first payment record and then on all subsequent accrual and 
		level payments, set the VNB to zero.
		
		Thus two different sources of DA are used depending on whether we need the
		full DA amount for accruals and level or the actual amount received for all
		other scenarios including the LV split payment scenario. The two sources are:
		
		mstt_PolicyTransactions.CommInitialAmount - Full (projected) DA amount
		
		mstt_Expectation.AMOUNT_REC - The DA actually received. This handles the
										LV scenario whereby the AMOUNT_REC is 
										proportioned across the two payments received.   
																		
	****************************************************************************/

	create table #TEMP_owt_Recognition
	(
		[ID] [bigint] IDENTITY(1,1) NOT NULL,
		[SourceID] [int] NULL,
		[CaseID] [int] NULL,
		[TransactionID] [int] NULL,
		[Policy] [varchar](25) NULL,
		[ProductCode] [varchar](8) NULL,
		[BusinessCode] [varchar](7) NULL,
		[SellerCode] [varchar](7) NULL,
		[PointsTotal] [decimal](16, 4) NULL,
		[BSC] [decimal](16, 4) NULL,
		[MBF] [decimal](16, 4) NULL,
		[Initial] [decimal](16, 4) NULL,
		[OngoingTotal] [decimal](16, 4) NULL,
		[OngoingYr01] [decimal](16, 4) NULL,
		[OngoingYr02] [decimal](16, 4) NULL,
		[OngoingYr03] [decimal](16, 4) NULL,
		[OngoingYr04] [decimal](16, 4) NULL,
		[OngoingYr05] [decimal](16, 4) NULL,
		[OngoingYr06] [decimal](16, 4) NULL,
		[OngoingYr07] [decimal](16, 4) NULL,
		[OngoingYr08] [decimal](16, 4) NULL,
		[OngoingYr09] [decimal](16, 4) NULL,
		[OngoingYr10] [decimal](16, 4) NULL,
		[FCARate] [decimal](8, 4) NULL,
		[RetentionRate] [decimal](8, 4) NULL,
		[RetentionRateBroker] [decimal](8, 4) NULL,
		[OngoingServicingRate] [decimal](8, 4) NULL,
		[OngoingServicingSource] [varchar](20) NULL,
		[DA] [decimal](16, 2) NULL,
		[AmountReceived] [decimal](16, 2) NULL,
		[Premium] [decimal](16, 2) NULL,
		[AgentSplit] [decimal](8, 4) NULL,
		[CommissionType] [int] NULL,
		[CommissionTypeDesc] [varchar](50) NULL,
		[PayBasisCode] [varchar](20) NULL,
		[PayBasisDesc] [varchar](20) NULL,
		[PaymentMatchedDate] [datetime] NULL,
		[Month] [datetime] NULL,
		[FrequencyCode] [tinyint] NULL,
		[FrequencyDesc] [varchar](20) NULL,
		[ReassignedProductGroupCode] [int] NULL,
		[ReassignedProductGroupName] [varchar](50) NULL,
		[RecognitionType] [varchar](15) NULL,
		[CalculationType] [varchar](20) NULL,
		[Source] [varchar](15) NULL,
		[DateInserted] [datetime] NULL,
		[DateLastUpdated] [datetime] NULL,
		[CommissionYear] [int] NULL
	)

	/****************************************************************************

		Phase 1 - Process all but regular accrual cases with clawbacks/adjustments
		Accruals are front loaded unless their latest payment is a clawback/adjudtment
		in which case they accrue VNB points on a per payment basis and so these
		are dealt with in Phases 2 and 3.
																		
	****************************************************************************/

	insert into #TEMP_owt_Recognition
	(
		SourceID,
		CaseID,
		TransactionID,
		Policy,
		ProductCode,
		BusinessCode,
		SellerCode,						--AG 13/06/2018
		PointsTotal,
		BSC,
		MBF,
		Initial,
		OngoingTotal,
		OngoingYr01,
		OngoingYr02,
		OngoingYr03,
		OngoingYr04,
		OngoingYr05,
		OngoingYr06,
		OngoingYr07,
		OngoingYr08,
		OngoingYr09,
		OngoingYr10,
		FCARate,
		RetentionRate,
		RetentionRateBroker,
		OngoingServicingRate,
		OngoingServicingSource,
		DA,
		AmountReceived,
		Premium,
		AgentSplit,
		CommissionType,
		CommissionTypeDesc,
		PayBasisCode,					--AG 13/06/2018
		PayBasisDesc,					--AG 13/06/2018
		PaymentMatchedDate,				--AG 13/06/2018
		Month,
		FrequencyCode,
		FrequencyDesc,
		ReassignedProductGroupCode,		--AG 05/06/2018
		ReassignedProductGroupName,		--AG 05/06/2018
		RecognitionType,
		CalculationType,
		Source,
		DateInserted,
		DateLastUpdated,
		CommissionYear
	)
	select	cs.PendingPaymentID as SourceID,
			cs.CaseID,
			cs.TransactionID,
			cs.ExtPolicyNumber as Policy,
			cs.ProductCode,
			cs.BusinessCode,
			cs.AgentCode as SellerCode,				--AG 13/06/2018
			0.0 as PointsTotal,
			0.0 as BSC,
			case 
				when mbf.MortgageFeeID is not null and cs.INIssued <> 0 then (((mbf.AdviceFeeAmount)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * MRbkr.FACTOR) - ((mbf.AdviceFeeAmount)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * Mfca.FACTOR)) --Note that mbf.AdviceFeeAmount is signed correctly - so no coding for signing is needed here
				else 0.0
			end as MBF,
			case 
				--When the adviser has changed, the AgentSplit can become zero in which case the ELITE points should be zero.
				when cs.AgentSplit = 0 then 0
				
				--WEALTH CALCULATION START
				--Indemnity payments or SINGLEs or IC Clawbacks or IC adjustments Start
				when (ph.ProductCategoryCode = 1 or pcc.KeyValue2 = '1') and (cs.FrequencyCode = 6 or cs.PayBasisCode in ('T') or cs.CommissionType in (2,17)) and cs.commissiontype in (1,2,17) and cs.INIssued <> 0 then (((e.AMOUNT_REC)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * Crate.FACTOR) - ((e.AMOUNT_REC)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * Cfca.FACTOR)) * case when cs.INIssued < 0 then -1 else 1 end
				--Indemnity payments or SINGLEs or IC Clawbacks or IC adjustments End
				--Accruals & Level Start
				when (ph.ProductCategoryCode = 1 or pcc.KeyValue2 = '1') and cs.INIssued <> 0 then (((pt.CommInitialAmount)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * Crate.FACTOR) - ((pt.CommInitialAmount)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * Cfca.FACTOR)) * case when cs.INIssued < 0 then -1 else 1 end
				--Accruals & Level End
				--WEALTH CALCULATION END
				
				--MORTGAGE CALCULATION START
				--Note: The MBF component has its own table column
				--Only 1 payment for mortgages
				when ph.ProductGroupCode = 3 and cs.INIssued <> 0 then (((e.AMOUNT_REC)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * MRproc.FACTOR) - ((e.AMOUNT_REC)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * Mfca.FACTOR)) * case when cs.INIssued < 0 then -1 else 1 end	--AG 18/05/2018
				--MORTGAGE CALCULATION END
				
				--PROTECTION CALCULATION START
				--Indemnity payments or SINGLEs or IC Clawbacks or IC adjustments Start
				when ph.ProductGroupCode = 6 and (cs.FrequencyCode = 6 or cs.PayBasisCode in ('T') or cs.CommissionType in (2,17)) and cs.commissiontype in (1,2,17) and cs.INIssued <> 0 then ((abs(e.AMOUNT_REC)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * Prate.FACTOR) - (abs(e.AMOUNT_REC)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * Pfca.FACTOR)) * case when cs.INIssued < 0 then -1 else 1 end	--AG 11/06/2018 (1)
				--Indemnity payments or SINGLEs or IC Clawbacks or IC adjustments End
				--Accruals & Level Start
				when ph.ProductGroupCode = 6 and cs.INIssued <> 0 then (((pt.CommInitialAmount)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * Prate.FACTOR) - ((pt.CommInitialAmount)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * Pfca.FACTOR)) * case when cs.INIssued < 0 then -1 else 1 end
				--Accruals & Level End
				--PROTECTION CALCULATION END

				else 0.0

			end as Initial,
			0.0 as OngoingTotal,
			0.0 as OngoingYr01,
			0.0 as OngoingYr02,
			0.0 as OngoingYr03,
			0.0 as OngoingYr04,
			0.0 as OngoingYr05,
			0.0 as OngoingYr06,
			0.0 as OngoingYr07,
			0.0 as OngoingYr08,
			0.0 as OngoingYr09,
			0.0 as OngoingYr10,
			case 
				when (ph.ProductCategoryCode = 1 or pcc.KeyValue2 = '1') then Cfca.FACTOR*100.0		--COB
				when ph.ProductGroupCode = 3 then Mfca.FACTOR*100.0		--MORT
				when ph.ProductGroupCode = 6 then Pfca.FACTOR*100.0		--PROT
				else 0.0
			end as FCARate,
			case 
				when (ph.ProductCategoryCode = 1 or pcc.KeyValue2 = '1') then Crate.FACTOR*100.0	--COB
				when ph.ProductGroupCode = 3 then MRproc.FACTOR*100.0	--MORT
				when ph.ProductGroupCode = 6 then Prate.FACTOR*100.0	--PROT
				else 0.0
			end as RetentionRate,
			case 
				when mbf.MortgageFeeID is not null then  MRbkr.FACTOR*100.0	
				else 0.0
			end as RetentionRateBroker,
			null as OngoingServicingRate,
			null as OngoingServicingSource,
			pt.CommInitialAmount as DA,
			e.AMOUNT_REC as AmountReceived,
			cs.Premium,
			cs.AgentSplit,
			cs.CommissionType,
			left(cs.StandingOrderDesc,50) as CommissionTypeDesc,
			cs.PayBasisCode,							--AG 13/06/2018
			cs.PayBasisDesc,							--AG 13/06/2018
			cs.CreateDate as PaymentMatchedDate,		--AG 13/06/2018
			cs.Month,
			cs.FrequencyCode,
			cs.FrequencyDesc,
			pg.ProductGroupCode as ReassignedProductGroupCode,	--Force the re-assigned products...		AG 05/06/2018
			pg.ProductGroupName as ReassignedProductGroupName,	--...to be processed as investments		AG 05/06/2018
			'VNB-INI-PHASE-1' as RecognitionType,
			case 
				when (ph.ProductCategoryCode = 1 or pcc.KeyValue2 = '1') then 'WEALTH-INITIAL'
				when ph.ProductGroupCode = 3 then 'MORTGAGE'
				when ph.ProductGroupCode = 6 then 'PROTECTION'
				else null
			end as CalculationType,
			'Openwork 2006' as Source,
			@DateLastUpdated as DateInserted,
			@DateLastUpdated as DateLastUpdated,
			csp.year as CommissionYear
	--select count(*)
	from	msit_CommissionStatement cs
/*			inner join (select	distinct PKID
						from	owt_TransformationMovements tm 
						where	tm.DriverTableName = 'sa_swift_S_AGMFIL'
						and		tm.CommissionStatement = 'Y') tm on tm.PKID = cs.PendingPaymentID
*/			inner join mstt_Agents ag on ag.Code = cs.BusinessCode
			inner join mstt_PolicyTransactions pt on pt.ID = cs.TransactionID
			inner join mstt_Policies p on p.POL_NUM = pt.PolicyID
			inner join msit_CommissionStatementPeriods VNBStart on convert(date,pt.CreateDateTime) between VNBStart.PeriodStartDate and VNBStart.PeriodEndDate
			inner join msit_Commissionstatementperiods csp on csp.month = cs.month
			inner join mstt_ProductHierarchy ph on ph.productcode = cs.productcode
			inner join mstt_Expectation e on e.ID = cs.ExpectationID
			left join dbo.owt_MortgageBrokerFees mbf on mbf.PendingPaymentID = cs.PendingPaymentID and mbf.AdviceFeeCharged = 'Yes'
			left join owt_SelectionControl SC
						on SC.Process = 'ElitePoints' 
						and SC.KeyType = 'NSCPotCode' 
						and cs.CreateDate between SC.EffectiveStartDate and SC.EffectiveEndDate
			left join mstt_Commissions BSCpot
						on BSCpot.TransactionID = cs.TransactionID 
						and BSCpot.Agent_Code = sc.KeyValue
						and BSCpot.CommissionType = 10
			left join owt_SelectionControl SFMPC						
						on SFMPC.Process = 'ElitePoints' 
						and SFMPC.KeyType = 'ServicingFeeMarginPotCode' 
						and cs.CreateDate between SFMPC.EffectiveStartDate and SFMPC.EffectiveEndDate
			left join mstt_Commissions SFMpot							
						on SFMpot.TransactionID = cs.TransactionID 
						and SFMpot.Agent_Code = SFMPC.KeyValue
						and SFMpot.CommissionType = 10	
			left join owt_SelectionControl pcc 
						on pcc.Process = 'ElitePoints'
						and pcc.KeyType = 'ProductCategoryCode'
						and pcc.KeyValue = cs.ProductCode	
						and cs.CreateDate between pcc.EffectiveStartDate and pcc.EffectiveEndDate
			left join owt_SelectionControl ogsdflt 
						on ogsdflt.Process = 'ElitePoints'
						and ogsdflt.KeyType = 'DefaultOngoingServicingRate'
						and ogsdflt.SelectionType = 'VNB'
						and ogsdflt.KeyValue = case when ph.RDRType = 'ONPLAT' then 'ONPLAT' else 'OFPLAT' end
						and cs.CreateDate between ogsdflt.EffectiveStartDate and ogsdflt.EffectiveEndDate
			left join mstt_CodeProductGroup pg on pg.ProductGroupCode = case when pcc.KeyValue2 = '1' then 2 else ph.ProductGroupCode end
			left join owt_EliteFactors Cfca on Cfca.FeeType = 'VNB' and Cfca.category = 'COB-FCA-RATE' and csp.year between Cfca.StartYear and Cfca.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors Crate on Crate.FeeType = 'VNB' and Crate.category = 'COB-RETENTION-RATE' and csp.year between Crate.StartYear and Crate.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors Mfca on Mfca.FeeType = 'VNB' and Mfca.category = 'MORT-FCA-RATE' and csp.year between Mfca.StartYear and Mfca.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors MRproc on MRproc.FeeType = 'VNB' and MRproc.category = 'MORT-RETENTION-RATE-PROC' and csp.year between MRproc.StartYear and MRproc.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors MRbkr on MRbkr.FeeType = 'VNB' and MRbkr.category = 'MORT-RETENTION-RATE-BROKER' and csp.year between MRbkr.StartYear and MRbkr.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors Pfca on Pfca.FeeType = 'VNB' and Pfca.category = 'PROT-FCA-RATE' and csp.year between Pfca.StartYear and Pfca.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors Prate on Prate.FeeType = 'VNB' and Prate.category = 'PROT-RETENTION-RATE' and csp.year between Prate.StartYear and Prate.EndYear 
			left join msit_CommissionStatement csadj 
						on csadj.TransactionID = cs.TransactionID 
						and csadj.AgentCode = cs.AgentCode 
						and csadj.CommissionType in (2,17)
						and	csadj.PayBasisCode in ('F')				--Accrual
						and	csadj.FrequencyCode <> 6				--Regular 
	where	cs.ReportingClassCode = 1
	and		ag.Manager2Code <> @OwlManager2Code		--Exclude Owl
	and		cs.INIssued <> 0
	and		csp.Year >= 2017						--Ensure in-scope payments are consistent with VNB start
	and		VNBStart.Year >= 2017
	and		cs.CommissionType in (1,2,17)
	and		abs(e.AMOUNT_REC) >= 0.01	
	--and		((VNBStart.Year >= 2017 and cs.CommissionType = 1 and e.AMOUNT_REC >= 0.01)		--VNB to start from new slices in 2017 for +ve payments but...			AG 11/06/2018 (2)
	--		or (cs.CommissionType in (2,17) or e.AMOUNT_REC <= -0.01))						--...for -ve payments, the slice can start from any date in the past	AG 11/06/2018 (2)
	and		csadj.ID is null						--Deal with accrual regular clawbacks/adjustments later

	select @RowCount = @@rowcount
	set @ProcessMessage = '#TEMP_owt_Recognition (ini ph1 - no accr adj) = ' + convert(nvarchar(10), @RowCount)
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseLog, @ProcessMessage, null, @Module, @Client

	/****************************************************************************

		Now deal with accrual clawbacks and adjustments
																		
	****************************************************************************/

	--drop table #msit_CommissionStatementSUMMARY

	create table #msit_CommissionStatementSUMMARY
	(
		TransactionID						int,
		AgentCode							varchar(7),
		MinInitialPendingPaymentID			varchar(10),
		MaxInitialPendingPaymentID			varchar(10),	
		MaxAdjPendingPaymentID				varchar(10),
		MinInitialAfterAdjPendingPaymentID	varchar(10)
	)

	--Find transactions with clawbacks/adj on them
	insert into #msit_CommissionStatementSUMMARY
	(
		TransactionID,
		AgentCode,
		MinInitialPendingPaymentID,
		MaxInitialPendingPaymentID,	
		MaxAdjPendingPaymentID,
		MinInitialAfterAdjPendingPaymentID
	)
	select	cs.TransactionID,
			cs.AgentCode,
			Min(case when cs.CommissionType = 1 then cs.PendingPaymentID else null end) as MinInitialPendingPaymentID,
			MAX(case when cs.CommissionType = 1 then cs.PendingPaymentID else null end) as MaxInitialPendingPaymentID,
			MAX(case when cs.CommissionType in (2,17) then cs.PendingPaymentID else null end) as MaxAdjPendingPaymentID,
			null as MinInitialAfterAdjPendingPaymentID
	from	msit_CommissionStatement cs
			inner join mstt_Agents ag on ag.Code = cs.BusinessCode
			inner join mstt_PolicyTransactions pt on pt.ID = cs.TransactionID
			inner join mstt_Policies p on p.POL_NUM = pt.PolicyID
			inner join msit_CommissionStatementPeriods VNBStart on convert(date,pt.CreateDateTime) between VNBStart.PeriodStartDate and VNBStart.PeriodEndDate
			inner join msit_Commissionstatementperiods csp on csp.month = cs.month
			inner join mstt_Expectation e on e.ID = cs.ExpectationID
			left join msit_CommissionStatement csadj 
						on csadj.TransactionID = cs.TransactionID 
						and csadj.AgentCode = cs.AgentCode 
						and csadj.CommissionType in (2,17)
						and	csadj.PayBasisCode in ('F')				--Accrual
						and	csadj.FrequencyCode <> 6				--Regular 
	where	cs.ReportingClassCode = 1
	and		cs.CommissionType in (1,2,17)			--We want all the initial payment types (i.e. not trail (ongoing))
	and		ag.Manager2Code <> @OwlManager2Code		--Exclude Owl
	and		csp.Year >= 2017						--Ensure in-scope payments are consistent with VNB start
	and		VNBStart.Year >= 2017 
	and		abs(e.AMOUNT_REC) >= 0.01	
	and		csadj.ID is not null					--select regular accrual transactions with clawbacks/adjustments
	--and cs.TransactionID in (5613333,6296827)
	group by	cs.TransactionID,
				cs.AgentCode

	select @RowCount = @@rowcount
	set @ProcessMessage = '#msit_CommissionStatementSUMMARY (accr adj txns) = ' + convert(nvarchar(10), @RowCount)
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseLog, @ProcessMessage, null, @Module, @Client

	--Get first initial payment after last clawback/adj
	update css
		set MinInitialAfterAdjPendingPaymentID = summ.MinPendingPaymentID 
	from  #msit_CommissionStatementSUMMARY css
			inner join  (
						select cssinner.TransactionID, cssinner.AgentCode, min(cs.PendingPaymentID) as MinPendingPaymentID
						from #msit_CommissionStatementSUMMARY cssinner
								inner join msit_CommissionStatement cs
											on cs.TransactionID = cssinner.TransactionID
											and cs.AgentCode = cssinner.AgentCode
						where cs.PendingPaymentID > cssinner.MaxAdjPendingPaymentID
						group by cssinner.TransactionID, cssinner.AgentCode
						) summ on  summ.TransactionID = css.TransactionID
							   and summ.AgentCode = css.AgentCode

	select @RowCount = @@rowcount
	set @ProcessMessage = '#msit_CommissionStatementSUMMARY (1st IC after adj) = ' + convert(nvarchar(10), @RowCount)
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseLog, @ProcessMessage, null, @Module, @Client

	/****************************************************************************

		Phase 2 - This phase deals with regular accrual cases where there is at 
		least one clawback/adjustment. In this scenario the VNB is changed from 
		front loaded to a per payment basis.
																		
	****************************************************************************/

	insert into #TEMP_owt_Recognition
	(
		SourceID,
		CaseID,
		TransactionID,
		Policy,
		ProductCode,
		BusinessCode,
		SellerCode,						
		PointsTotal,
		BSC,
		MBF,
		Initial,
		OngoingTotal,
		OngoingYr01,
		OngoingYr02,
		OngoingYr03,
		OngoingYr04,
		OngoingYr05,
		OngoingYr06,
		OngoingYr07,
		OngoingYr08,
		OngoingYr09,
		OngoingYr10,
		FCARate,
		RetentionRate,
		RetentionRateBroker,
		OngoingServicingRate,
		OngoingServicingSource,
		DA,
		AmountReceived,
		Premium,
		AgentSplit,
		CommissionType,
		CommissionTypeDesc,
		PayBasisCode,					
		PayBasisDesc,					
		PaymentMatchedDate,				
		Month,
		FrequencyCode,
		FrequencyDesc,
		ReassignedProductGroupCode,		
		ReassignedProductGroupName,		
		RecognitionType,
		CalculationType,
		Source,
		DateInserted,
		DateLastUpdated,
		CommissionYear
	)
	select	cs.PendingPaymentID as SourceID,
			cs.CaseID,
			cs.TransactionID,
			cs.ExtPolicyNumber as Policy,
			cs.ProductCode,
			cs.BusinessCode,
			cs.AgentCode as SellerCode,				
			0.0 as PointsTotal,
			0.0 as BSC,
			case 
				when mbf.MortgageFeeID is not null and cs.INIssued <> 0 then (((mbf.AdviceFeeAmount)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * MRbkr.FACTOR) - ((mbf.AdviceFeeAmount)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * Mfca.FACTOR)) --Note that mbf.AdviceFeeAmount is signed correctly - so no coding for signing is needed here
				else 0.0
			end as MBF,
			case 
				--When the adviser has changed, the AgentSplit can become zero in which case the ELITE points should be zero.
				when cs.AgentSplit = 0 then 0
				
				--WEALTH CALCULATION START
				--Indemnity payments or SINGLEs or IC Clawbacks or IC adjustments Start
				--THIS SCENARIO DOESN'T OCCUR IN PHASE 2
				--Indemnity payments or SINGLEs or IC Clawbacks or IC adjustments End
				--Accruals & Level Start
				when (ph.ProductCategoryCode = 1 or pcc.KeyValue2 = '1') then (((e.AMOUNT_REC)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * Crate.FACTOR) - ((e.AMOUNT_REC)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * Cfca.FACTOR)) * case when cs.CommissionType in (2,17) then -1 else 1 end
				--Accruals & Level End
				--WEALTH CALCULATION END
				
				--MORTGAGE CALCULATION START
				--Note: The MBF component has its own table column
				--Only 1 payment for mortgages
				when ph.ProductGroupCode = 3 then (((e.AMOUNT_REC)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * MRproc.FACTOR) - ((e.AMOUNT_REC)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * Mfca.FACTOR)) * case when cs.CommissionType in (2,17) then -1 else 1 end	
				--MORTGAGE CALCULATION END
				
				--PROTECTION CALCULATION START
				--Indemnity payments or SINGLEs or IC Clawbacks or IC adjustments Start
				--THIS SCENARIO DOESN'T OCCUR IN PHASE 2
				--Indemnity payments or SINGLEs or IC Clawbacks or IC adjustments End
				--Accruals & Level Start
				when ph.ProductGroupCode = 6 then (((e.AMOUNT_REC)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * Prate.FACTOR) - ((e.AMOUNT_REC)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * Pfca.FACTOR)) * case when cs.CommissionType in (2,17) then -1 else 1 end
				--Accruals & Level End
				--PROTECTION CALCULATION END

				else 0.0

			end as Initial,
			0.0 as OngoingTotal,
			0.0 as OngoingYr01,
			0.0 as OngoingYr02,
			0.0 as OngoingYr03,
			0.0 as OngoingYr04,
			0.0 as OngoingYr05,
			0.0 as OngoingYr06,
			0.0 as OngoingYr07,
			0.0 as OngoingYr08,
			0.0 as OngoingYr09,
			0.0 as OngoingYr10,
			case 
				when (ph.ProductCategoryCode = 1 or pcc.KeyValue2 = '1') then Cfca.FACTOR*100.0		--COB
				when ph.ProductGroupCode = 3 then Mfca.FACTOR*100.0		--MORT
				when ph.ProductGroupCode = 6 then Pfca.FACTOR*100.0		--PROT
				else 0.0
			end as FCARate,
			case 
				when (ph.ProductCategoryCode = 1 or pcc.KeyValue2 = '1') then Crate.FACTOR*100.0	--COB
				when ph.ProductGroupCode = 3 then MRproc.FACTOR*100.0	--MORT
				when ph.ProductGroupCode = 6 then Prate.FACTOR*100.0	--PROT
				else 0.0
			end as RetentionRate,
			case 
				when mbf.MortgageFeeID is not null then  MRbkr.FACTOR*100.0	
				else 0.0
			end as RetentionRateBroker,
			null as OngoingServicingRate,
			null as OngoingServicingSource,
			pt.CommInitialAmount as DA,
			e.AMOUNT_REC as AmountReceived,
			cs.Premium,
			cs.AgentSplit,
			cs.CommissionType,
			left(cs.StandingOrderDesc,50) as CommissionTypeDesc,
			cs.PayBasisCode,							
			cs.PayBasisDesc,							
			cs.CreateDate as PaymentMatchedDate,		
			cs.Month,
			cs.FrequencyCode,
			cs.FrequencyDesc,
			pg.ProductGroupCode as ReassignedProductGroupCode,	--Force the re-assigned products...		
			pg.ProductGroupName as ReassignedProductGroupName,	--...to be processed as investments		
			'VNB-INI-PHASE-2' as RecognitionType,
			case 
				when (ph.ProductCategoryCode = 1 or pcc.KeyValue2 = '1') then 'WEALTH-INITIAL'
				when ph.ProductGroupCode = 3 then 'MORTGAGE'
				when ph.ProductGroupCode = 6 then 'PROTECTION'
				else null
			end as CalculationType,
			'Openwork 2006' as Source,
			@DateLastUpdated as DateInserted,
			@DateLastUpdated as DateLastUpdated,
			csp.year as CommissionYear
	from	#msit_CommissionStatementSUMMARY css
			inner join msit_CommissionStatement cs
						on cs.TransactionID = css.TransactionID
						and cs.AgentCode = css.AgentCode
			inner join mstt_Agents ag on ag.Code = cs.BusinessCode
			inner join mstt_PolicyTransactions pt on pt.ID = cs.TransactionID
			inner join mstt_Policies p on p.POL_NUM = pt.PolicyID
			inner join msit_CommissionStatementPeriods VNBStart on convert(date,pt.CreateDateTime) between VNBStart.PeriodStartDate and VNBStart.PeriodEndDate
			inner join msit_Commissionstatementperiods csp on csp.month = cs.month
			inner join mstt_ProductHierarchy ph on ph.productcode = cs.productcode
			inner join mstt_Expectation e on e.ID = cs.ExpectationID
			left join dbo.owt_MortgageBrokerFees mbf on mbf.PendingPaymentID = cs.PendingPaymentID and mbf.AdviceFeeCharged = 'Yes'
			left join owt_SelectionControl SC
						on SC.Process = 'ElitePoints' 
						and SC.KeyType = 'NSCPotCode' 
						and cs.CreateDate between SC.EffectiveStartDate and SC.EffectiveEndDate
			left join mstt_Commissions BSCpot
						on BSCpot.TransactionID = cs.TransactionID 
						and BSCpot.Agent_Code = sc.KeyValue
						and BSCpot.CommissionType = 10
			left join owt_SelectionControl SFMPC						
						on SFMPC.Process = 'ElitePoints' 
						and SFMPC.KeyType = 'ServicingFeeMarginPotCode' 
						and cs.CreateDate between SFMPC.EffectiveStartDate and SFMPC.EffectiveEndDate
			left join mstt_Commissions SFMpot							
						on SFMpot.TransactionID = cs.TransactionID 
						and SFMpot.Agent_Code = SFMPC.KeyValue
						and SFMpot.CommissionType = 10	
			left join owt_SelectionControl pcc 
						on pcc.Process = 'ElitePoints'
						and pcc.KeyType = 'ProductCategoryCode'
						and pcc.KeyValue = cs.ProductCode	
						and cs.CreateDate between pcc.EffectiveStartDate and pcc.EffectiveEndDate
			left join owt_SelectionControl ogsdflt 
						on ogsdflt.Process = 'ElitePoints'
						and ogsdflt.KeyType = 'DefaultOngoingServicingRate'
						and ogsdflt.SelectionType = 'VNB'
						and ogsdflt.KeyValue = case when ph.RDRType = 'ONPLAT' then 'ONPLAT' else 'OFPLAT' end
						and cs.CreateDate between ogsdflt.EffectiveStartDate and ogsdflt.EffectiveEndDate
			left join mstt_CodeProductGroup pg on pg.ProductGroupCode = case when pcc.KeyValue2 = '1' then 2 else ph.ProductGroupCode end
			left join owt_EliteFactors Cfca on Cfca.FeeType = 'VNB' and Cfca.category = 'COB-FCA-RATE' and csp.year between Cfca.StartYear and Cfca.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors Crate on Crate.FeeType = 'VNB' and Crate.category = 'COB-RETENTION-RATE' and csp.year between Crate.StartYear and Crate.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors Mfca on Mfca.FeeType = 'VNB' and Mfca.category = 'MORT-FCA-RATE' and csp.year between Mfca.StartYear and Mfca.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors MRproc on MRproc.FeeType = 'VNB' and MRproc.category = 'MORT-RETENTION-RATE-PROC' and csp.year between MRproc.StartYear and MRproc.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors MRbkr on MRbkr.FeeType = 'VNB' and MRbkr.category = 'MORT-RETENTION-RATE-BROKER' and csp.year between MRbkr.StartYear and MRbkr.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors Pfca on Pfca.FeeType = 'VNB' and Pfca.category = 'PROT-FCA-RATE' and csp.year between Pfca.StartYear and Pfca.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors Prate on Prate.FeeType = 'VNB' and Prate.category = 'PROT-RETENTION-RATE' and csp.year between Prate.StartYear and Prate.EndYear 
	where	cs.ReportingClassCode = 1
	and		cs.CommissionType in (1,2,17)			--We want all the initial payment types (i.e. not trail (ongoing))
	and		ag.Manager2Code <> @OwlManager2Code		--Exclude Owl

	select @RowCount = @@rowcount
	set @ProcessMessage = '#TEMP_owt_Recognition (ini ph2 - accr adj) = ' + convert(nvarchar(10), @RowCount)
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseLog, @ProcessMessage, null, @Module, @Client

	/****************************************************************************

		Initial Phase 3
		1) Add up the +ves and -ves prior to the NEW front loaded amount and
			net them off on the first +ve following the last -ve
		2) Now set all the +ves following the one updated in (1) to zero.
																
	****************************************************************************/

	update r
		set RecognitionType	= case when r.SourceID >= css.MinInitialAfterAdjPendingPaymentID 
								then 'VNB-INI-PHASE-3'
								else r.RecognitionType
							  end,
			Initial = case  when r.SourceID = css.MinInitialAfterAdjPendingPaymentID 
								then (((r.DA)*(r.AgentSplit/100) * (r.RetentionRate/100.0)) - ((r.DA)*(r.AgentSplit/100) * (r.FCARate/100))) - derived.SumInitial
							when r.SourceID > css.MinInitialAfterAdjPendingPaymentID 
								then 0.0
							else r.Initial
					  end,
			DateLastUpdated = @DateLastUpdated
	from	#msit_CommissionStatementSUMMARY css
			inner join #TEMP_owt_Recognition r
						on r.TransactionID = css.TransactionID
						and r.SellerCode = css.AgentCode
			inner join (select	r.TransactionID, r.SellerCode, SUM(Initial) as SumInitial
						from	#msit_CommissionStatementSUMMARY s
								inner join #TEMP_owt_Recognition r 
											on r.TransactionID = s.TransactionID
											and r.SellerCode = s.AgentCode
						where	r.SourceID <= s.MaxAdjPendingPaymentID
						group	by r.TransactionID, r.SellerCode
						) derived 
							on  derived.TransactionID = r.TransactionID
							and	derived.SellerCode = r.SellerCode 
	where	isnull(css.MaxInitialPendingPaymentID,0) > isnull(css.MaxAdjPendingPaymentID,0)-- An initial payment follows the clawback, so time to revert back to front loading

	select @RowCount = @@rowcount
	set @ProcessMessage = '#TEMP_owt_Recognition (ini ph3 - accr adj) = ' + convert(nvarchar(10), @RowCount)
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseLog, @ProcessMessage, null, @Module, @Client

	/****************************************************************************

		Now do the ongoing.
		
		Build an ongoing summary row for each transaction (slice).
		
		Note we do not care about ongoing clawbacks and adjustments for VNB.
		We want VNB to be on the oldest positive payment on each slice for the
		policy (split by adviser if needed).
						
	****************************************************************************/

	create table #msit_CommissionStatementOGSSUMMARY
	(
		CaseID								varchar(10),
		TransactionID						varchar(10),
		AgentCode							varchar(7),
		AgentSplit							float,
		MinOngoingPendingPaymentID			varchar(10),
		MaxOngoingPendingPaymentID			varchar(10),
		MaxOngoingAdjPendingPaymentID		varchar(10),
		MaxPremium							float,
		MinOngoingAfterAdjPendingPaymentID	varchar(10),
		Premium								float,						
		FrequencyCode						tinyint,
		FrequencyDesc						varchar(20)
	)

	insert into #msit_CommissionStatementOGSSUMMARY
	(
		CaseID,
		TransactionID,
		AgentCode,
		AgentSplit,
		MinOngoingPendingPaymentID,
		MaxOngoingPendingPaymentID,
		MaxOngoingAdjPendingPaymentID,
		MaxPremium,
		MinOngoingAfterAdjPendingPaymentID,
		Premium,						
		FrequencyCode,
		FrequencyDesc
	)
	select	cs.CaseID,
			cs.TransactionID,
			cs.AgentCode,
			c.AGENT_PERC as AgentSplit,
			min(case when cs.CommissionType = 10 then cs.PendingPaymentID else null end) as MinOngoingPendingPaymentID,
			max(case when cs.CommissionType = 10 then cs.PendingPaymentID else null end) as MaxOngoingPendingPaymentID,
			max(case when cs.CommissionType in (16,19) then cs.PendingPaymentID else null end) as MaxOngoingAdjPendingPaymentID,
			max(case when cs.CommissionType = 10 then case when cs.FrequencyCode <> 6 then (cs.Premium * 12.0 * (c.Agent_Perc/100)) else (cs.Premium * (c.Agent_Perc/100)) end else 0.0 end) as MaxPremium,	--AG 19/07/2018
			null as MinOngoingAfterAdjPendingPaymentID,
			cs.Premium,			--AG 17/07/2018
			cs.FrequencyCode,	--AG 17/07/2018
			cs.FrequencyDesc	--AG 17/07/2018
	from 	msit_CommissionStatement cs
			inner join mstt_Commissions c
						on c.TransactionID = cs.TransactionID
						and c.Agent_Code = cs.AgentCode
						and c.CommissionType = 1
			inner join mstt_Agents ag on ag.Code = cs.BusinessCode
			inner join mstt_PolicyTransactions pt on pt.ID = cs.TransactionID
			inner join mstt_Policies p on p.POL_NUM = pt.PolicyID
			inner join msit_CommissionStatementPeriods VNBStart on convert(date,pt.CreateDateTime) between VNBStart.PeriodStartDate and VNBStart.PeriodEndDate
			inner join msit_Commissionstatementperiods csp on csp.month = cs.month
			inner join mstt_ProductHierarchy ph on ph.productcode = cs.productcode
			inner join mstt_Expectation e on e.ID = cs.ExpectationID
			left join owt_SelectionControl pcc 
						on pcc.Process = 'ElitePoints'
						and pcc.KeyType = 'ProductCategoryCode'
						and pcc.KeyValue = cs.ProductCode	
						and cs.CreateDate between pcc.EffectiveStartDate and pcc.EffectiveEndDate
	where	cs.ReportingClassCode = 1
	and		cs.CommissionType in (10,16,19)					--Choose only where the ongoing payment is positive
	and		cs.CommFeeType = 'Ongoing'
	and		(ph.ProductCategoryCode = 1 or pcc.KeyValue2 = '1')
	and		ag.Manager2Code <> @OwlManager2Code		--Exclude Owl
	and		csp.Year >= 2017						--Ensure in-scope payments are consistent with VNB start
	and		VNBStart.Year >= 2017 
	and		abs(e.AMOUNT_REC) >= 0.01
	and		((cs.FrequencyCode = 6 and cs.Premium > 1.00)		--Frequency=6->Single
			or (cs.FrequencyCode <> 6 and cs.Premium > 0.01))	--Frequency<>6->Regular	
	group by	cs.CaseID,
				cs.TransactionID,
				cs.AgentCode,
				c.Agent_Perc,
				cs.Premium,			--AG 17/07/2018
				cs.FrequencyCode,	--AG 17/07/2018
				cs.FrequencyDesc	--AG 17/07/2018

	select @RowCount = @@rowcount
	set @ProcessMessage = '#msit_CommissionStatementOGSSUMMARY (ogs txn) = ' + convert(nvarchar(10), @RowCount)
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseLog, @ProcessMessage, null, @Module, @Client

	--Get first ongoing payment after last clawback/adj
	update cso
		set MinOngoingAfterAdjPendingPaymentID = summ.MinPendingPaymentID 
	from  #msit_CommissionStatementOGSSUMMARY cso
			inner join  (
						select	csoinner.TransactionID, csoinner.AgentCode, min(cs.PendingPaymentID) as MinPendingPaymentID
						from	#msit_CommissionStatementOGSSUMMARY csoinner
								inner join msit_CommissionStatement cs
											on cs.TransactionID = csoinner.TransactionID
											and cs.AgentCode = csoinner.AgentCode
						where	cs.PendingPaymentID > csoinner.MaxOngoingAdjPendingPaymentID
						and		cs.CommissionType = 10
						group by csoinner.TransactionID, csoinner.AgentCode
						) summ on  summ.TransactionID = cso.TransactionID
							   and summ.AgentCode = cso.AgentCode

	select @RowCount = @@rowcount
	set @ProcessMessage = '#msit_CommissionStatementOGSSUMMARY (ogs latest +ve) = ' + convert(nvarchar(10), @RowCount)
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseLog, @ProcessMessage, null, @Module, @Client

	/****************************************************************************
		
		Using the OGS SUMMARY table, get all the individual payment records that
		will be carriers of VNB points as follows:
		
		SelectionSource 1 - The oldest +ve payment where no clawbacks or 
								adjustments occur for front loading

		SelectionSource 2 - All the +ve payments that will get a spread of the 
								per payment +ve points 		

		SelectionSource 3 - All the -ve payments that will get a spread of the 
								per payment -ve points
								 															
	****************************************************************************/
	
	--AG 19/07/2018
	--Combine the premium on all the transactions (slices) for each case and seller
	--In case of mixed frequencies, force the sum to be a single
	create table #PremiumTotal
	(
		CaseID						int,
		SellerCode					varchar(7),
		InitialSumOfPremium			float,
		OngoingSumOfPremium			float,	
		MinOngoingPendingPaymentID	varchar(10)
	)

	insert into #PremiumTotal
	(
		CaseID,
		SellerCode,
		InitialSumOfPremium,
		OngoingSumOfPremium,	
		MinOngoingPendingPaymentID
	)
	select	CaseID,
			SellerCode,
			sum(case when CommissionType = 1 then SumOfPremium else 0 end) as InitialSumOfPremium,
			sum(case when CommissionType = 10 then SumOfPremium else 0 end) as OngoingSumOfPremium,
			min(case when CommissionType = 10 then MinOngoingPendingPaymentID end) as MinOngoingPendingPaymentID
	from
		(
		select	CaseID,
				SellerCode,
				1 as CommissionType,						--IC
				min(SourceID) as MinOngoingPendingPaymentID,
				sum(case when FrequencyCode <> 6 then Premium * 12.0 * (AgentSplit/100) else Premium * (AgentSplit/100) end) as SumOfPremium
		from	#TEMP_owt_Recognition
		where	CalculationType = 'WEALTH-INITIAL'
		and		CommissionType = 1
		group	by CaseID, SellerCode
		
		union
		
		select	CaseID,
				AgentCode as SellerCode,
				10 as CommissionType,						--Trail (OGS)
				min(MinOngoingPendingPaymentID) as MinOngoingPendingPaymentID,
				sum(MaxPremium) as SumOfPremium
		from	#msit_CommissionStatementOGSSUMMARY
		group	by CaseID, AgentCode
		) a
	group by CaseID, SellerCode

	select @RowCount = @@rowcount
	set @ProcessMessage = '#PremiumTotal = ' + convert(nvarchar(10), @RowCount)
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseLog, @ProcessMessage, null, @Module, @Client
	
	create table #msit_CommissionStatementONGOING
	(
		SelectionSource		int,
		TransactionID		varchar(10),
		AgentCode			varchar(7),
		PendingPaymentID	varchar(10),
		AgentSplit			decimal(8,4),
		Premium				decimal(16,2),
		FrequencyCode		tinyint,
		SpreadNumber		int,
		MaxSpread			int
	)
	
	--Front loaded -> Just the oldest +ve payment
	--Note: These transactions have NO clawbacks or adjustments
	insert into #msit_CommissionStatementONGOING
	(
		SelectionSource,
		TransactionID,
		AgentCode,
		PendingPaymentID,
		AgentSplit,
		Premium,
		FrequencyCode,
		SpreadNumber,
		MaxSpread
	)
	select	1 as SelectionSource,
			cso.TransactionID,
			cso.AgentCode,
			cso.MinOngoingPendingPaymentID as PendingPaymentID,
			cso.AgentSplit,
			case when ptot.CaseID is null
				then cso.Premium
				else	case when	ptot.MinOngoingPendingPaymentID = cso.MinOngoingPendingPaymentID 
									and ptot.InitialSumOfPremium - ptot.OngoingSumOfPremium > 0.0 
							then	cso.Premium + ptot.InitialSumOfPremium - ptot.OngoingSumOfPremium 
							else	cso.Premium 
						end	--AG 19/07/2018
			end as Premium,
			case when ptot.CaseID is null
				then cso.FrequencyCode
				else 6					--Single - had to be hardcoded because proc kept failing when column was used. Weird but true.
			end as FrequencyCode,
			1 as SpreadNumber,
			1 as MaxSpread 
	from	#msit_CommissionStatementOGSSUMMARY cso	
			left join mstt_PolicyTransactions pt on pt.ID = cso.TransactionID
			left join mstt_Policies p on p.POL_NUM = pt.PolicyID
			left join #PremiumTotal ptot				--When NO clawbacks or adjustments, the seller gets credit for the combined premium
						on ptot.CaseID = p.PolicyRef
						and ptot.SellerCode = cso.AgentCode
	where	cso.MaxOngoingAdjPendingPaymentID is null	--No clawbacks or adjustments - so front load
	and		cso.MinOngoingPendingPaymentID is not null	--At least one +ve payment on the transaction

	union	--Add in with dedupe
	
	--Per payment -> all +ve payments with max spread also used for divisor
	--Note: ALL these transactions have clawbacks or adjustments
	select	2 as SelectionSource,
			cso.TransactionID,
			cso.AgentCode,
			cs.PendingPaymentID,
			cso.AgentSplit,
			cso.Premium,
			cso.FrequencyCode,
			ROW_NUMBER() over (partition by cs.TransactionID, cs.AgentCode order by cs.TransactionID, cs.AgentCode, cs.PendingPaymentID) as SpreadNumber,
			12 as MaxSpread
	from	#msit_CommissionStatementOGSSUMMARY cso	
			inner join msit_CommissionStatement cs 
						on cs.TransactionID = cso.TransactionID
						and cs.AgentCode = cso.AgentCode
	where	cso.MaxOngoingAdjPendingPaymentID is not null	--Clawbacks or adjustments so per payment
	and		cs.CommissionType in (10)	

	union	--Add in with dedupe
	
	--Per payment -> all -ve payments - with max spread also used for divisor
	--Note: ALL these transactions have clawbacks or adjustments
	select	3 as SelectionSource,
			cso.TransactionID,
			cso.AgentCode,
			cs.PendingPaymentID,
			cso.AgentSplit,
			cso.Premium,
			cso.FrequencyCode,
			ROW_NUMBER() over (partition by cs.TransactionID, cs.AgentCode order by cs.TransactionID, cs.AgentCode, cs.PendingPaymentID) as SpreadNumber,
			12 as MaxSpread
	from	#msit_CommissionStatementOGSSUMMARY cso	
			inner join msit_CommissionStatement cs 
						on cs.TransactionID = cso.TransactionID
						and cs.AgentCode = cso.AgentCode
	where	cso.MaxOngoingAdjPendingPaymentID is not null	--Clawbacks or adjustments so per payment
	and		cs.CommissionType in (16,19)	

	select @RowCount = @@rowcount
	set @ProcessMessage = '#msit_CommissionStatementONGOING (ogs payments) = ' + convert(nvarchar(10), @RowCount)
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseLog, @ProcessMessage, null, @Module, @Client

	/****************************************************************************
		
		Insert the ongoing VNB results for those transactions 
																		
	****************************************************************************/

	insert into #TEMP_owt_Recognition
	(
		SourceID,
		CaseID,
		TransactionID,
		Policy,
		ProductCode,
		BusinessCode,
		SellerCode,
		PointsTotal,
		BSC,
		MBF,
		Initial,
		OngoingTotal,
		OngoingYr01,
		OngoingYr02,
		OngoingYr03,
		OngoingYr04,
		OngoingYr05,
		OngoingYr06,
		OngoingYr07,
		OngoingYr08,
		OngoingYr09,
		OngoingYr10,
		FCARate,
		RetentionRate,
		RetentionRateBroker,
		OngoingServicingRate,
		OngoingServicingSource,
		DA,
		AmountReceived,
		Premium,
		AgentSplit,
		CommissionType,
		CommissionTypeDesc,
		PayBasisCode,
		PayBasisDesc,
		PaymentMatchedDate,
		Month,
		FrequencyCode,
		FrequencyDesc,
		ReassignedProductGroupCode,
		ReassignedProductGroupName,
		RecognitionType,
		CalculationType,
		Source,
		DateInserted,
		DateLastUpdated,
		CommissionYear
	)
	select	cs.PendingPaymentID as SourceID,
			cs.CaseID,
			cs.TransactionID,
			cs.ExtPolicyNumber as Policy,
			cs.ProductCode,
			cs.BusinessCode,
			cs.AgentCode as SellerCode,
			0.0 as PointsTotal,
			case
				when BSCpot.ID is not null then 
					--BSC takes the first 0.12 of the ongoing fee %. If the ongoing fee % is 0.12% or less, then 100% of the ongoing fee is allocated to BSC
					case when coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2)) - convert(decimal(8,4),sc.KeyValue2) >= 0.01
						then 
							case when cso.FrequencyCode = 2	--Monthly 
								then (cso.AgentSplit/100) * 12.0 * (isnull(cso.Premium/cso.MaxSpread,0)/2.0) * convert(decimal(8,4),sc.KeyValue3) * case when cs.CommissionType in (16,19) then -1 else 1 end
								else (cso.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(cso.Premium/cso.MaxSpread,0) * convert(decimal(8,4),sc.KeyValue3) * case when cs.CommissionType in (16,19) then -1 else 1 end
							end			
						else
							case when cso.FrequencyCode = 2	--Monthly 
								then (cso.AgentSplit/100) * 12.0 * (isnull(cso.Premium/cso.MaxSpread,0)/2.0) * coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2)) * case when cs.CommissionType in (16,19) then -1 else 1 end
								else (cso.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(cso.Premium/cso.MaxSpread,0) * (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))/100.0) * case when cs.CommissionType in (16,19) then -1 else 1 end
							end
					end
				else 0.0
			end as BSC,
			0.0 as MBF,
			0.0 as Initial,
			0.0 as OngoingTotal,
			case
				--WEALTH ONGOING CALCULATION START
				--When the adviser has changed, the AgentSplit can become zero in which case the ELITE points should be zero.
				when cso.AgentSplit = 0 then 0

				--SINGLE start
				--Calculate when BSC and ongoing applies (where ongoing rate is greater than BSC rate) 
				when cso.FrequencyCode = 6 and SFMpot.ID is not null and BSCpot.ID is not null and (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2)) - convert(decimal(8,4),sc.KeyValue2)) >= 0.01 then 
							--(AUM X BSC Rate)...
							((cso.AgentSplit/100) * (isnull(cso.Premium/cso.MaxSpread,0) * convert(decimal(8,4),sc.KeyValue3)) 
							--(AUM X OGS Rate X COB FCA Rate)...
							- ((cso.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(cso.Premium/cso.MaxSpread,0) * (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))/100.0) * Cfca.FACTOR)
							--(AUM X (OGS Rate - BSC Rate) X COB Retention Rate)...
							+ ((cso.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(cso.Premium/cso.MaxSpread,0) * ((coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))-convert(decimal(8,4),sc.KeyValue2))/100.0)) * Crate.FACTOR) 
							--Sign correctly for +ve or clawback payment
							* (case when cs.CommissionType in (16,19) then -1 else 1 end)
				--Calculate when BSC and ongoing applies (where ongoing rate less than BSC rate, then BSC gets all the ongoing available) 
				when cso.FrequencyCode = 6 and SFMpot.ID is not null and BSCpot.ID is not null then
							--(AUM X BSC Rate)...(in this scenario it's all of the OGS rate)
							((cso.AgentSplit/100) * (isnull(cso.Premium/cso.MaxSpread,0) * (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))/100.0)) 
							--(AUM X OGS Rate X COB FCA Rate)...
							- ((cso.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(cso.Premium/cso.MaxSpread,0) * (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))/100.0) * Cfca.FACTOR)
							--(AUM X (OGS Rate - BSC Rate) X COB Retention Rate)...
							+ (0.0)) --BSC got it all, so this part of the calculation is zero
							--Sign correctly for +ve or clawback payment
							* (case when cs.CommissionType in (16,19) then -1 else 1 end)
				--Calculate when no BSC applies and ongoing applies
				when cso.FrequencyCode = 6 and SFMpot.ID is not null and BSCpot.ID is null then 
							--(AUM X OGS Rate X COB Retention Rate)...
							(((cso.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(cso.Premium/cso.MaxSpread,0) * (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))/100.0) * Crate.FACTOR) 
							--(AUM X OGS Rate X COB FCA Rate)...
							- ((cso.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(cso.Premium/cso.MaxSpread,0) * (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))/100.0) * Cfca.FACTOR))
							--Sign correctly for +ve or clawback payment
							* (case when cs.CommissionType in (16,19) then -1 else 1 end)
				--SINGLE end
				
				--REGULAR start
				--Calculate when BSC and ongoing applies (where ongoing rate is greater than BSC rate) 
				when cso.FrequencyCode <> 6 and SFMpot.ID is not null and BSCpot.ID is not null and (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2)) - convert(decimal(8,4),sc.KeyValue2)) >= 0.01 then		--AG 04/06/2018 (1)
							--The non-BSC portion (Ave AUM X (OGS Rate - BSC Rate) X COB Retention Rate)...
							((((((cso.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(cso.Premium/cso.MaxSpread,0) * (case when cso.FrequencyCode = 2 then 12 else 1 end))/2.0) * (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2)) - convert(decimal(8,4),sc.KeyValue2))/100.0)) * Crate.FACTOR
							--The BSC portion (Ave AUM X BSC Rate)...
							+ case when cso.FrequencyCode = 2	--Monthly 
									then (cso.AgentSplit/100) * 12.0 * (isnull(cso.Premium/cso.MaxSpread,0)/2.0) * convert(decimal(8,4),sc.KeyValue3) 
									else (cso.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(cso.Premium/cso.MaxSpread,0) * convert(decimal(8,4),sc.KeyValue3) 
							  end
							--FCA Charge (Ave AUM X OGS Rate X FCA Rate)...
							- (case when cso.FrequencyCode = 2	--Monthly 
									then (cso.AgentSplit/100) * 12.0 * (isnull(cso.Premium/cso.MaxSpread,0)/2.0) 
									else (cso.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(cso.Premium/cso.MaxSpread,0) 
							   end * (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))/100.0) * Cfca.FACTOR))
							--Sign correctly for +ve or clawback payment
							* (case when cs.CommissionType in (16,19) then -1 else 1 end)   
				--Calculate when BSC and ongoing applies (where ongoing rate less than BSC rate, then BSC gets all the ongoing available) 
				when cso.FrequencyCode <> 6 and SFMpot.ID is not null and BSCpot.ID is not null then		--AG 04/06/2018 (1)
							--The non-BSC portion (Ave AUM X (OGS Rate - BSC Rate) X COB Retention Rate)...
							((0.0)	--BSC got it all, so this part of the calculation is zero
							--The BSC portion (Ave AUM X BSC Rate)...(in this scenario it's all of the OGS rate)
							+ case when cso.FrequencyCode = 2	--Monthly 
									then (cso.AgentSplit/100) * 12.0 * (isnull(cso.Premium/cso.MaxSpread,0)/2.0) * (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))/100.0) 
									else (cso.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(cso.Premium/cso.MaxSpread,0) * (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))/100.0) 
							  end
							--FCA Charge (Ave AUM X OGS Rate X FCA Rate)...
							- (case when cso.FrequencyCode = 2	--Monthly 
									then (cso.AgentSplit/100) * 12.0 * (isnull(cso.Premium/cso.MaxSpread,0)/2.0) 
									else (cso.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(cso.Premium/cso.MaxSpread,0) 
							   end * (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))/100.0) * Cfca.FACTOR))
							--Sign correctly for +ve or clawback payment
							* (case when cs.CommissionType in (16,19) then -1 else 1 end)   
				--Calculate when no BSC applies, but ongoing servicing applies
				when cso.FrequencyCode <> 6 and SFMpot.ID is not null and BSCpot.ID is null then		--AG 04/06/2018	(1)
							--(Ave AUM X OGS Rate X COB Retention Rate)...
							(((((cso.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(cso.Premium/cso.MaxSpread,0) * (case when cso.FrequencyCode = 2 then 12 else 1 end))/2.0) * (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))/100.0) * Crate.FACTOR) 
							--(Ave AUM X OGS Rate X COB FCA Rate)...
							- ((((cso.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(cso.Premium/cso.MaxSpread,0) * (case when cso.FrequencyCode = 2 then 12 else 1 end))/2.0) * (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))/100.0) * Cfca.FACTOR))
							--Sign correctly for +ve or clawback payment
							* (case when cs.CommissionType in (16,19) then -1 else 1 end)   
				--REGULAR end
				
				else 0.0

				--WEALTH ONGOING CALCULATION END
			end as OngoingYr01,
			0.0 as OngoingYr02,
			0.0 as OngoingYr03,
			0.0 as OngoingYr04,
			0.0 as OngoingYr05,
			0.0 as OngoingYr06,
			0.0 as OngoingYr07,
			0.0 as OngoingYr08,
			0.0 as OngoingYr09,
			0.0 as OngoingYr10,
			Cfca.FACTOR*100.0 as FCARate,
			Crate.FACTOR*100.0 as RetentionRate,
			0.0 as RetentionRateBroker,
			case when SFMpot.ID is not null
				then coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))
				else null
			end as OngoingServicingRate,
			case when SFMpot.ID is not null
				then case 
						when ogs.OngoingServiceFee is null and ogscli.OngoingServiceFee is null 
							then case
								when ogsdflt.KeyValue = 'ONPLAT' then 'Default - On Plat'
								else 'Default - Off Plat'
							end
						when ogs.OngoingServiceFee is not null then 'Client Product'
						when ogscli.OngoingServiceFee is not null then 'Client Only'
						else 'Unknown'
					 end
				else case when (ph.ProductCategoryCode = 1 or pcc.KeyValue2 = '1')
						then 'No OGS'					--WEALTH, but no OGS
						else null						--Not WEALTH, so OGS is n/a and is therefore null
					 end
			end as OngoingServicingSource,
			pt.CommInitialAmount as DA,
			e.AMOUNT_REC as AmountReceived,
			cso.Premium,								--AG 17/07/2018
			cso.AgentSplit,								--Use the split from the IC record
			cs.CommissionType,
			left(cs.StandingOrderDesc,50) as CommissionTypeDesc,
			cs.PayBasisCode,
			cs.PayBasisDesc,
			cs.CreateDate as PaymentMatchedDate,
			cs.Month,
			cso.FrequencyCode,							--AG 17/07/2018
			case when cso.FrequencyCode = 6
				then 'Single'
				else 'Monthly'
			end as FrequencyDesc,						--AG 17/07/2018
			pg.ProductGroupCode as ReassignedProductGroupCode,	--Force the re-assigned products...		
			pg.ProductGroupName as ReassignedProductGroupName,	--...to be processed as investments		
			case cso.SelectionSource
				when 1 then 'VNB-OGS-PHASE-1' 
				when 2 then 'VNB-OGS-PHASE-2' 
				when 3 then 'VNB-OGS-PHASE-3' 
			end as RecognitionType,
			'WEALTH-ONGOING' as CalculationType,
			'Openwork 2006' as Source,
			@DateLastUpdated as DateInserted,
			@DateLastUpdated as DateLastUpdated,
			csp.year as CommissionYear
	from	#msit_CommissionStatementONGOING cso
			inner join msit_CommissionStatement cs on cs.PendingPaymentID = cso.PendingPaymentID
			inner join mstt_Agents ag on ag.Code = cs.BusinessCode
			inner join mstt_PolicyTransactions pt on pt.ID = cs.TransactionID
			inner join mstt_Policies p on p.POL_NUM = pt.PolicyID
			inner join msit_CommissionStatementPeriods VNBStart on convert(date,pt.CreateDateTime) between VNBStart.PeriodStartDate and VNBStart.PeriodEndDate
			inner join msit_Commissionstatementperiods csp on csp.month = cs.month
			inner join mstt_ProductHierarchy ph on ph.productcode = cs.productcode
			inner join mstt_Expectation e on e.ID = cs.ExpectationID
			left join dbo.owt_MortgageBrokerFees mbf on mbf.PendingPaymentID = cs.PendingPaymentID and mbf.AdviceFeeCharged = 'Yes'
			left join owt_SelectionControl SC
						on SC.Process = 'ElitePoints' 
						and SC.KeyType = 'NSCPotCode' 
						and cs.CreateDate between SC.EffectiveStartDate and SC.EffectiveEndDate
			left join mstt_Commissions BSCpot
						on BSCpot.TransactionID = cs.TransactionID 
						and BSCpot.Agent_Code = sc.KeyValue
						and BSCpot.CommissionType = 10
			left join owt_SelectionControl SFMPC						
						on SFMPC.Process = 'ElitePoints' 
						and SFMPC.KeyType = 'ServicingFeeMarginPotCode' 
						and cs.CreateDate between SFMPC.EffectiveStartDate and SFMPC.EffectiveEndDate
			left join mstt_Commissions SFMpot							
						on SFMpot.TransactionID = cs.TransactionID 
						and SFMpot.Agent_Code = SFMPC.KeyValue
						and SFMpot.CommissionType = 10	
			left join owt_SelectionControl pcc 
						on pcc.Process = 'ElitePoints'
						and pcc.KeyType = 'ProductCategoryCode'
						and pcc.KeyValue = cs.ProductCode	
						and cs.CreateDate between pcc.EffectiveStartDate and pcc.EffectiveEndDate
			left join owt_SelectionControl ogsdflt 
						on ogsdflt.Process = 'ElitePoints'
						and ogsdflt.KeyType = 'DefaultOngoingServicingRate'
						and ogsdflt.SelectionType = 'VNB'
						and ogsdflt.KeyValue = case when ph.RDRType = 'ONPLAT' then 'ONPLAT' else 'OFPLAT' end
						and cs.CreateDate between ogsdflt.EffectiveStartDate and ogsdflt.EffectiveEndDate
			left join mstt_CodeProductGroup pg on pg.ProductGroupCode = case when pcc.KeyValue2 = '1' then 2 else ph.ProductGroupCode end
			left join owt_EliteFactors Cfca on Cfca.FeeType = 'VNB' and Cfca.category = 'COB-FCA-RATE' and csp.year between Cfca.StartYear and Cfca.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors Crate on Crate.FeeType = 'VNB' and Crate.category = 'COB-RETENTION-RATE' and csp.year between Crate.StartYear and Crate.EndYear 
			left join dbo.owt_OngoingRate ogs 
						on  ogs.CLIENT_NUM = cs.ClientID 
						and ogs.ProductCode = cs.ProductCode
						and convert(date,pt.CreateDateTime) between ogs.EffectiveStartDate and ogs.EffectiveEndDate
			left join dbo.owt_OngoingRate ogscli 
						on  ogscli.CLIENT_NUM = cs.ClientID 
						and ogscli.ProductCode = '(CLIENT)'
						and convert(date,pt.CreateDateTime) between ogscli.EffectiveStartDate and ogscli.EffectiveEndDate
	where	cso.SpreadNumber <= cso.MaxSpread	-- if per payment spreading, then limit the spread
	
	select @RowCount = @@rowcount
	set @ProcessMessage = '#TEMP_owt_Recognition (ogs ph1-3 yr1) = ' + convert(nvarchar(10), @RowCount)
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseLog, @ProcessMessage, null, @Module, @Client

	/****************************************************************************

		Ongoing Phase 3
		1) Add up the +ves and -ves prior to the NEW front loaded amount and
			net them off on the first +ve following the last -ve
		2) Now set all the +ves following the one updated in (1) to zero.
																
	****************************************************************************/

	update r
		set RecognitionType	= case when r.SourceID >= csos.MinOngoingAfterAdjPendingPaymentID 
								then 'VNB-OGS-PHASE-4'
								else r.RecognitionType
							  end,
			OngoingYr01 = case  when r.SourceID = csos.MinOngoingAfterAdjPendingPaymentID 
									then (abs(r.OngoingYr01) * cso.MaxSpread) - derived.SumOngoingYr01
								when r.SourceID > csos.MinOngoingAfterAdjPendingPaymentID 
									then 0.0
								else r.OngoingYr01
						  end,
			DateLastUpdated = @DateLastUpdated
	from	#msit_CommissionStatementONGOING cso 
			inner join #TEMP_owt_Recognition r on r.SourceID = cso.PendingPaymentID
			inner join #msit_CommissionStatementOGSSUMMARY csos
						on  csos.TransactionID = cso.TransactionID
						and csos.AgentCode = cso.AgentCode
			inner join (select	r.TransactionID, r.SellerCode, SUM(OngoingYr01) as SumOngoingYr01
						from	#msit_CommissionStatementOGSSUMMARY s
								inner join #TEMP_owt_Recognition r 
											on r.TransactionID = s.TransactionID
											and r.SellerCode = s.AgentCode
						where	r.SourceID <= s.MaxOngoingAdjPendingPaymentID
						group	by r.TransactionID, r.SellerCode
						) derived 
							on  derived.TransactionID = r.TransactionID
							and	derived.SellerCode = r.SellerCode 
	where	isnull(csos.MaxOngoingPendingPaymentID,0) > isnull(csos.MaxOngoingAdjPendingPaymentID,0)	--An ongoing +ve payment follows the clawback, so time to revert back to front loading
	and		cso.SpreadNumber <= cso.MaxSpread	--Only payments within the spread period get a portion of the ongoing VNB
	and		cso.SelectionSource <> 1			--Just process the per-payment rows (not the front loaded rows)

	select @RowCount = @@rowcount
	set @ProcessMessage = '#TEMP_owt_Recognition (ogs ph4 - accr adj) = ' + convert(nvarchar(10), @RowCount)
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseLog, @ProcessMessage, null, @Module, @Client

	/****************************************************************************

		Now calculate the ongoing spread as follows:
		1) Investments: Years 1 to 6
		2) Pensions:	Years 1 to 10
		Note that regular payments get an additional multiplier to uplift the 
		average AUM for each year.
																		
	****************************************************************************/

	update r
		set OngoingYr02 = case when r.FrequencyCode = 2									--Monthly
							then r.OngoingYr01 * YR02.Multiplier * YR02.Factor			--Regular
							else r.OngoingYr01 * YR02.Factor							--Single
						  end,
			OngoingYr03 = case when r.FrequencyCode = 2									--Monthly
							then r.OngoingYr01 * YR03.Multiplier * YR03.Factor			--Regular
							else r.OngoingYr01 * YR03.Factor							--Single
						  end,
			OngoingYr04 = case when r.FrequencyCode = 2									--Monthly
							then r.OngoingYr01 * YR04.Multiplier * YR04.Factor			--Regular
							else r.OngoingYr01 * YR04.Factor							--Single
						  end,
			OngoingYr05 = case when r.FrequencyCode = 2									--Monthly 
							then r.OngoingYr01 * YR05.Multiplier * YR05.Factor			--Regular
							else r.OngoingYr01 * YR05.Factor							--Single
						  end,
			OngoingYr06 = case when r.FrequencyCode = 2									--Monthly 
							then r.OngoingYr01 * YR06.Multiplier * YR06.Factor			--Regular
							else r.OngoingYr01 * YR06.Factor							--Single
						  end,
			OngoingYr07 = case when r.ReassignedProductGroupCode = 5					--Pensions	AG 05/06/2018
							then
								case when r.FrequencyCode = 2							--Monthly 
									then r.OngoingYr01 * YR07.Multiplier * YR07.Factor	--Regular
									else r.OngoingYr01 * YR07.Factor					--Single
								end
							else 
								0.0
						  end,
			OngoingYr08 = case when r.ReassignedProductGroupCode = 5					--Pensions	AG 05/06/2018 
							then
								case when r.FrequencyCode = 2							--Monthly 
									then r.OngoingYr01 * YR08.Multiplier * YR08.Factor	--Regular
									else r.OngoingYr01 * YR08.Factor					--Single
								end
							else 
								0.0
						  end,
			OngoingYr09 = case when r.ReassignedProductGroupCode = 5					--Pensions	AG 05/06/2018 
							then
								case when r.FrequencyCode = 2							--Monthly 
									then r.OngoingYr01 * YR09.Multiplier * YR09.Factor	--Regular
									else r.OngoingYr01 * YR09.Factor					--Single
								end
							else 
								0.0
						  end,
			OngoingYr10 = case when r.ReassignedProductGroupCode = 5					--Pensions	AG 05/06/2018
							then
								case when r.FrequencyCode = 2							--Monthly 
									then r.OngoingYr01 * YR10.Multiplier * YR10.Factor	--Regular
									else r.OngoingYr01 * YR10.Factor					--Single
								end
							else 
								0.0
						  end
	from	#TEMP_owt_Recognition r
			left join owt_EliteFactors YR01 on YR01.FeeType = 'VNB' and YR01.Category = 'COB-ONGOING-DISCOUNT-YR01' and r.CommissionYear between YR01.StartYear and YR01.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors YR02 on YR02.FeeType = 'VNB' and YR02.Category = 'COB-ONGOING-DISCOUNT-YR02' and r.CommissionYear between YR02.StartYear and YR02.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors YR03 on YR03.FeeType = 'VNB' and YR03.Category = 'COB-ONGOING-DISCOUNT-YR03' and r.CommissionYear between YR03.StartYear and YR03.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors YR04 on YR04.FeeType = 'VNB' and YR04.Category = 'COB-ONGOING-DISCOUNT-YR04' and r.CommissionYear between YR04.StartYear and YR04.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors YR05 on YR05.FeeType = 'VNB' and YR05.Category = 'COB-ONGOING-DISCOUNT-YR05' and r.CommissionYear between YR05.StartYear and YR05.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors YR06 on YR06.FeeType = 'VNB' and YR06.Category = 'COB-ONGOING-DISCOUNT-YR06' and r.CommissionYear between YR06.StartYear and YR06.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors YR07 on YR07.FeeType = 'VNB' and YR07.Category = 'COB-ONGOING-DISCOUNT-YR07' and r.CommissionYear between YR07.StartYear and YR07.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors YR08 on YR08.FeeType = 'VNB' and YR08.Category = 'COB-ONGOING-DISCOUNT-YR08' and r.CommissionYear between YR08.StartYear and YR08.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors YR09 on YR09.FeeType = 'VNB' and YR09.Category = 'COB-ONGOING-DISCOUNT-YR09' and r.CommissionYear between YR09.StartYear and YR09.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors YR10 on YR10.FeeType = 'VNB' and YR10.Category = 'COB-ONGOING-DISCOUNT-YR10' and r.CommissionYear between YR10.StartYear and YR10.EndYear 
	where	r.CalculationType = 'WEALTH-ONGOING'

	select @RowCount = @@rowcount
	set @ProcessMessage = '#TEMP_owt_Recognition (ongoing yr2-10) = ' + convert(nvarchar(10), @RowCount)
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseLog, @ProcessMessage, null, @Module, @Client
	
	/****************************************************************************

		Now add up all the numbers
																		
	****************************************************************************/
	
	update r
		set OngoingTotal	=	OngoingYr01 + OngoingYr02 + OngoingYr03 + OngoingYr04 + OngoingYr05 +
								OngoingYr06 + OngoingYr07 + OngoingYr08 + OngoingYr09 + OngoingYr10,
			PointsTotal		=	OngoingYr01 + OngoingYr02 + OngoingYr03 + OngoingYr04 + OngoingYr05 +
								OngoingYr06 + OngoingYr07 + OngoingYr08 + OngoingYr09 + OngoingYr10 +
								Initial + MBF	-- Note BSC is already included in the Ongoing, so don't include it in the Points Total.
	from	#TEMP_owt_Recognition r

	select @RowCount = @@rowcount
	set @ProcessMessage = '#TEMP_owt_Recognition (points total) = ' + convert(nvarchar(10), @RowCount)
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseLog, @ProcessMessage, null, @Module, @Client

	/****************************************************************************

		Merge the temporary table into the permanent table (IC data)
																		
	****************************************************************************/

	BEGIN TRANSACTION

	declare @SummaryOfChanges table (Change varchar(20))
	merge	dbo.owt_Recognition as trg
	using	#TEMP_owt_Recognition as src
	on		trg.SourceID = src.SourceID
	and		trg.Source = src.Source
	when	matched 
	and		isnull(trg.PointsTotal,0) <> isnull(src.PointsTotal,0)
	then	update 
				set trg.CaseID = src.CaseID,
					trg.TransactionID = src.TransactionID,
					trg.Policy = src.Policy,
					trg.ProductCode = src.ProductCode,
					trg.BusinessCode = src.BusinessCode,
					trg.SellerCode = src.SellerCode,					--AG 13/06/2018
					trg.PointsTotal = src.PointsTotal,
					trg.BSC = src.BSC,
					trg.MBF = src.MBF,
					trg.Initial = src.Initial,
					trg.OngoingTotal = src.OngoingTotal,
					trg.OngoingYr01 = src.OngoingYr01,
					trg.OngoingYr02 = src.OngoingYr02,
					trg.OngoingYr03 = src.OngoingYr03,
					trg.OngoingYr04 = src.OngoingYr04,
					trg.OngoingYr05 = src.OngoingYr05,
					trg.OngoingYr06 = src.OngoingYr06,
					trg.OngoingYr07 = src.OngoingYr07,
					trg.OngoingYr08 = src.OngoingYr08,
					trg.OngoingYr09 = src.OngoingYr09,
					trg.OngoingYr10 = src.OngoingYr10,
					trg.FCARate = src.FCARate,
					trg.RetentionRate = src.RetentionRate,
					trg.RetentionRateBroker = src.RetentionRateBroker,
					trg.OngoingServicingRate = src.OngoingServicingRate,
					trg.OngoingServicingSource = src.OngoingServicingSource,
					trg.DA = src.DA,
					trg.AmountReceived = src.AmountReceived,
					trg.Premium = src.Premium,
					trg.AgentSplit = src.AgentSplit,
					trg.CommissionType = src.CommissionType,
					trg.CommissionTypeDesc = src.CommissionTypeDesc,
					trg.PayBasisCode = src.PayBasisCode,				--AG 13/06/2018
					trg.PayBasisDesc = src.PayBasisDesc,				--AG 13/06/2018
					trg.PaymentMatchedDate = src.PaymentMatchedDate,	--AG 13/06/2018	
					trg.Month = src.Month,
					trg.FrequencyCode = src.FrequencyCode,
					trg.FrequencyDesc = src.FrequencyDesc,
					trg.ReassignedProductGroupCode = src.ReassignedProductGroupCode,	--AG 05/06/2018
					trg.ReassignedProductGroupName = src.ReassignedProductGroupName,	--AG 05/06/2018
					trg.RecognitionType = src.RecognitionType,
					trg.CalculationType = src.CalculationType,
					trg.DateLastUpdated = @DateLastUpdated
	when	not matched by source					--AG 24/07/2018
	and		trg.Source = 'Openwork 2006'			--AG 24/07/2018
	then	delete									--AG 24/07/2018
	when	not matched by target 
	then	insert
			(
				SourceID,
				CaseID,
				TransactionID,
				Policy,
				ProductCode,
				BusinessCode,
				SellerCode,							--AG 13/06/2018
				PointsTotal,
				BSC,
				MBF,
				Initial,
				OngoingTotal,
				OngoingYr01,
				OngoingYr02,
				OngoingYr03,
				OngoingYr04,
				OngoingYr05,
				OngoingYr06,
				OngoingYr07,
				OngoingYr08,
				OngoingYr09,
				OngoingYr10,
				FCARate,
				RetentionRate,
				RetentionRateBroker,
				OngoingServicingRate,
				OngoingServicingSource,
				DA,
				AmountReceived,
				Premium,
				AgentSplit,
				CommissionType,
				CommissionTypeDesc,
				PayBasisCode,						--AG 13/06/2018
				PayBasisDesc,						--AG 13/06/2018
				PaymentMatchedDate,					--AG 13/06/2018
				Month,
				FrequencyCode,
				FrequencyDesc,
				ReassignedProductGroupCode,			--AG 05/06/2018
				ReassignedProductGroupName,			--AG 05/06/2018
				RecognitionType,
				CalculationType,
				Source,
				DateInserted,
				DateLastUpdated
			)		
			values
			(
				src.SourceID,
				src.CaseID,
				src.TransactionID,
				src.Policy,
				src.ProductCode,
				src.BusinessCode,
				src.SellerCode,						--AG 13/06/2018
				src.PointsTotal,
				src.BSC,
				src.MBF,
				src.Initial,
				src.OngoingTotal,
				src.OngoingYr01,
				src.OngoingYr02,
				src.OngoingYr03,
				src.OngoingYr04,
				src.OngoingYr05,
				src.OngoingYr06,
				src.OngoingYr07,
				src.OngoingYr08,
				src.OngoingYr09,
				src.OngoingYr10,
				src.FCARate,
				src.RetentionRate,
				src.RetentionRateBroker,
				src.OngoingServicingRate,
				src.OngoingServicingSource,
				src.DA,
				src.AmountReceived,
				src.Premium,
				src.AgentSplit,
				src.CommissionType,
				src.CommissionTypeDesc,
				src.PayBasisCode,					--AG 13/06/2018
				src.PayBasisDesc,					--AG 13/06/2018
				src.PaymentMatchedDate,				--AG 13/06/2018
				src.Month,
				src.FrequencyCode,
				src.FrequencyDesc,
				src.ReassignedProductGroupCode,		--AG 05/06/2018
				src.ReassignedProductGroupName,		--AG 05/06/2018
				src.RecognitionType,
				src.CalculationType,
				src.Source,
				src.DateInserted,
				src.DateLastUpdated)				--Merge statements must have a ;
	output $action into @SummaryOfChanges;
						
	/****************************************************************************

		Update OpenAccess
																		
	****************************************************************************/

	--Do not include MBF in the OpenAccess Commission Listing as it is on the MBF download
	--and we don't want MBF double counting.
	--00:01:37	423189
	update	oal
		set VNB_Points = r.PointsTotal - r.MBF		--AG 04/06/2018 (2)
	from	msit_CommissionStatement cs
			inner join msit_OpenworkAdviserListing oal on oal.SourceID = cs.ID and oal.Source = 'Openwork 2006'
			inner join owt_Recognition r 
						on r.SourceID = cs.PendingPaymentID
						and r.Source = oal.Source
	where	isnull(oal.VNB_Points,0) <> isnull(r.PointsTotal - r.MBF,0)	--AG 27/07/2018
	and		cs.ReportingClassCode = 1
	
	select @OALRowCount = @@rowcount

	COMMIT TRANSACTION      
	
	select	@RowCount = COUNT(*)
	from	@SummaryOfChanges
	where	Change = 'INSERT'

	set @ProcessMessage = 'owt_Recognition (insert) = ' + convert(nvarchar(10), @RowCount)
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseLog, @ProcessMessage, null, @Module, @Client

	select	@RowCount = COUNT(*)
	from	@SummaryOfChanges
	where	Change = 'UPDATE'

	set @ProcessMessage = 'owt_Recognition (update) = ' + convert(nvarchar(10), @RowCount)
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseLog, @ProcessMessage, null, @Module, @Client

	select	@RowCount = COUNT(*)
	from	@SummaryOfChanges
	where	Change = 'DELETE'

	set @ProcessMessage = 'owt_Recognition (delete) = ' + convert(nvarchar(10), @RowCount)
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseLog, @ProcessMessage, null, @Module, @Client

	set @ProcessMessage = 'msit_OpenworkAdviserListing (update) = ' + convert(nvarchar(10), @OALRowCount)
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseLog, @ProcessMessage, null, @Module, @Client

	/****************************************************************************

		T H E   E N D
																		
	****************************************************************************/
	
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseEnd, @ProcName, null, @Module, @Client

END TRY

BEGIN CATCH 

	select @ErrNum = ERROR_NUMBER(), @ErrMsg = ERROR_MESSAGE(), @ErrSev = ERROR_SEVERITY(), @ErrLine = ERROR_LINE(), @ErrState = XACT_STATE()
	set @ErrMsg = REPLACE(@ErrMsg, '.', '') + ' (error no: ' + CAST(@ErrNum AS VARCHAR(10)) + ') on line ' + CAST(@ErrLine AS VARCHAR(10))
	
	-- Test XACT_STATE for 0, 1, or -1.
    -- If 1, the transaction is committable.
    -- If -1, the transaction is uncommittable and should be rolled back.
    -- If 0, there is no transaction and a commit or rollback operation would generate an error.

	if @ErrState = -1			-- Transaction is uncommitable
		rollback transaction

	if @ErrState = 1			
		commit transaction

	-- Error message line 1
	set @ErrMsgBrief = left(@ErrMsg,100)
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseError, @ErrMsgBrief, null, @Module, @Client
	
	-- Error message line 2 - if any text exists
	set @ErrMsgBrief = substring(@ErrMsg,101,100)
	if len(@ErrMsgBrief) > 0
		exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseError, @ErrMsgBrief, null, @Module, @Client

	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseEnd, @ProcName, null, @Module, @Client

	RAISERROR(@ErrMsg, @ErrSev , 1)

END CATCH

/****************************************************************************

			E N D															

****************************************************************************/

return @ErrNum


GO
/****** Object:  StoredProcedure [dbo].[owp_RecognitionSwift_Backup20180518AG]    Script Date: 7/3/2026 3:44:25 PM ******/
SET ANSI_NULLS ON
GO
SET QUOTED_IDENTIFIER ON
GO
/*********************************************************************************************************

Program:		owp_RecognitionSwift					
Author:			Alan Groves
Date created:	11/04/2018
											
Description:
===========

This proc populates the new recognition table called "owt_Recognition" with "Value of New Business"
(VNB) points.

This proc handles all of the swift data which includes:
WEALTH - COB business i.e. pensions and investments
MORTGAGES
PROTECTION

Note: There is a separate proc that calculates the GI VNB points from the Paymentshield data.

The approach of this proc is to use the incremental PendingPaymentIDs from the overnight batch
to calculate the VNB points in a temporary table.

The temporary table is then merged with the permanent table to make the calculated (or
re-calculated values) permanent.

Terms
-----
BSC			- Business Service Charge.
MBF			- Mortgage Broker Fee.
OGS			- Ongoing Servicing.
BSC Rate	- 0.12% at the time of writing (24/04/2018). This could be changed by the business, but
				would also require some DEV work in OWS.
DF			- Discount Factor.
DA			- Distribution Allowance (the total amount paid out by the provider to Openwork)
AUM			- Assets Under Management. Basically the amount invested or the premium on investment
				cases.
Average AUM - Average amount invested annually which is equivalent to 6 months' premium.

THE CALCULATIONS
================

There are two potential parts: initial + ongoing (if ongoing applies). If BSC (applies to ongoing 
only) and MBF (applies to mortgages only) apply, then these are also included:

MORTGAGE
--------
Part 1: MBF column = (Advice Fee Amount X Broker Retention Rate) - (Advice Fee Amount X Mort FCA Rate)
Part 2: Initial column = (Proc Fee Amount X Mortgage Retention Rate) - (Proc Fee X Mort FCA Rate) 
Mortgage Points Total = Initial + MBF

PROTECTION
----------
= (DA X Protection Retention Rate) - (DA X Protection FCA Rate) 
Protection Points Total = Initial

WEALTH (COB i.e. pensions and investments)
------
Part 1: Initial column = (DA X Wealth Retention Rate) - (DA X Wealth FCA Rate)

Part 2:

REGULAR - BSC applies:
Year 1 column = BSC Points + Non-BSC Points - FCA Points
Non-BSC Points = Ave AUM X (OGS Rate - BSC Rate) X COB Retention Rate
BSC Points = Ave AUM X OGS Rate X FCA Rate
FCA Points = Ave AUM X OGS Rate X Wealth FCA Rate

REGULAR - Non-BSC: 
Year 1 column = (Ave AUM X OGS Rate X COB Retention Rate) - (Ave AUM X OGS Rate X COB FCA Rate)

SINGLE - BSC applies:
Year 1 column = (AUM X BSC Rate) + (AUM X (OGS Rate - BSC Rate) X COB Retention Rate) - (AUM X OGS Rate X COB FCA Rate) 

SINGLE - Non-BSC:
Year 1 column = (AUM X OGS Rate X COB Retention Rate) - (AUM X OGS Rate X COB FCA Rate) 

Then years 2 to 10 are calculated by applying a discount factor
Year  2 = Year 1 X  3 X DF
Year  3 = Year 1 X  5 X DF
Year  4 = Year 1 X  7 X DF
Year  5 = Year 1 X  9 X DF
Year  6 = Year 1 X 11 X DF
Year  7 = Year 1 X 13 X DF
Year  8 = Year 1 X 15 X DF
Year  9 = Year 1 X 17 X DF
Year 10 = Year 1 X 19 X DF

Wealth Points Total =	OngoingYr01 + OngoingYr02 + OngoingYr03 + OngoingYr04 + OngoingYr05 +
						OngoingYr06 + OngoingYr07 + OngoingYr08 + OngoingYr09 + OngoingYr10 +
						Initial

GI
--
See stored proc "owp_RecognitionGIPaymentshield".
 
Notes:
-----

There is a BSC column on table owt_Recognition. However, BSC is already included in the ongoing
years 1 - 10, so the BSC column does not need to be added in. In fact you will double count if 
you attempt to do anything with it other than display it.


This proc is called as follows:
	declare @rc int
	exec @rc = dbo.owp_RecognitionSwift 'Openwork', 'Recognition'
	select @rc

					
AMENDMENT HISTORY				
=================								

Date		Author		Description
----		------		-----------
26/04/2018	A Groves	Only include rows in the OGS lookups where the OngoingServiceFee > 0.0.
						Negative OGS rates are bad data and at the time of writing, there are
						39 of these.
27/04/2018	A Groves	Additional calculation and condition to handle the scenario where BSC applies
						but the OGS Rate is less than the BSC rate. Previously, this caused the
						total ongoing to be zero. However, there are two components to ongoing VNB 
						points, the BSC share and the non-BSC share. So the BSC share (which takes 
						100% when the OGS rate is less than 0.12%) should still yield ongoing points.
27/04/2018	A Groves	Single ongoing Yr01 corrected by applying outer brackets before signing the result.
*************************************************************************************************************/

CREATE PROCEDURE [dbo].[owp_RecognitionSwift_Backup20180518AG]
	@Client		varchar(50),
	@Module		Varchar(50)
AS

set nocount on

declare		@PhaseStart				varchar(50),
			@PhaseEnd				varchar(50),
			@PhaseError				varchar(50),
			@PhaseLog				varchar(50),
			@ProcName				varchar(100),
			@ProcessMessage			varchar(100),
			@RowCount				int,
			@ErrMsg					nvarchar(4000),
			@ErrMsgBrief			nvarchar(100),
			@ErrNum					int,
			@ErrSev					int,
			@ErrLine				int,
			@ErrState				int,
			@DateLastUpdated		datetime,
			@OwlManager2Code		nvarchar(10)
			
/****************************************************************************

	Set initial parameters																
																		
****************************************************************************/

set @ProcName			= object_name(@@procid)
set @PhaseStart			= 'START'
set @PhaseEnd			= 'END'
set @PhaseError			= 'ERROR'
set @PhaseLog			= 'LOG'
set @ErrNum				= 0	
set @DateLastUpdated	= getdate()

set @OwlManager2Code = (select cde.Code from msit_MIWarehouseCodesAndDescriptions cde
			where cde.ColumnName = 'Manager2Code' and cde.Description = 'Owl Financial')

-- We want this logging irrespective of whether or not there is a rollback
exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseStart, @ProcName, null, @Module, @Client

/****************************************************************************

	Populate the table																
																		
****************************************************************************/

SET XACT_ABORT ON	-- Needed if XACT_STATE() function is used.

BEGIN TRY

	/****************************************************************************

		Link OWS data to Swift data to enable the ongoing servicng (OGS) rate
		to be looked up.
																		
	****************************************************************************/
	
	select	distinct s.PersonID, swp.Client_Num, p.InternalProductID, swp.ProductCode 
	into	#SwiftOWSClientLink
	from	sa_ows_Sale s
			inner join sa_ows_Policies p on p.SaleID = s.SaleID
			inner join mstt_Policies swp on swp.PolicyRef = p.PolicyID
	where	s.DateSubmitted is not null
	--and		s.PersonID = 146030

	select @RowCount = @@rowcount
	set @ProcessMessage = '#SwiftOWSClientLink = ' + convert(nvarchar(10), @RowCount)
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseLog, @ProcessMessage, null, @Module, @Client

	-- The OGS rate is stored for the client/product combination
	select	link.Client_Num, link.ProductCode, max(ogs.OngoingServiceFee) as OngoingServiceFee
	into	#OGSLookUp
	from	#SwiftOWSClientLink link 
			inner join mstt_ProductHierarchy ph on ph.ProductCode = link.ProductCode
			inner join Submission.sa_ows_SubmittedProductCurrentOngoingServiceFee ogs
							on ogs.PersonID = link.PersonID
							and ogs.InternalProductID = (case when ph.RDRType = 'ONPLAT' 
															then -2 
															else link.InternalProductID 
														 end)
	where	ogs.OngoingServiceFee > 0.0							--AG 26/04/2018
	group	by 	link.Client_Num, link.ProductCode

	select @RowCount = @@rowcount
	set @ProcessMessage = '#OGSLookUp = ' + convert(nvarchar(10), @RowCount)
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseLog, @ProcessMessage, null, @Module, @Client

	create index idx_OGSLookUp on #OGSLookUp (Client_num, ProductCode)

	--This is an additional catch for OGS by storing the client's highest OGS
	--rate against their client number. This lookup will apply if the first
	--look up fails. The first lookup can fail, for example, if the case was 
	--not submitted on OWS i.e. the CaseID has a "17" prefix. 
	select	Client_Num, MAX(OngoingServiceFee) as OngoingServiceFee
	into	#OGSLookUpClient
	from	#OGSLookUp
	group	by Client_Num

	select @RowCount = @@rowcount
	set @ProcessMessage = '#OGSLookUpClient = ' + convert(nvarchar(10), @RowCount)
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseLog, @ProcessMessage, null, @Module, @Client
	
	create index idx_OGSLookUpClient on #OGSLookUpClient (Client_num)

	/****************************************************************************

		Calculate VNB and populate the temporary table with the results
		
		Note that there are oddities like LV protection payments which always
		come in pairs with one large and one much smaller amount (e.g. TransactionID 
		= 6684787.) The system treats both payments in the pair as first payments 
		and the (projected) DA associated with both is the same (because it's on 
		the policy transaction). 
		
		There is also a requirement to front-load VNB points on accrual and level
		payments. This means calculate the VNB for the full amount of the DA and 
		put it on the first payment record and then on all subsequent accrual and 
		level payments, set the VNB to zero.
		
		Thus two different sources of DA are used depending on whether we need the
		full DA amount for accruals and level or the actual amount received for all
		other scenarios including the LV split payment scenario. The two sources are:
		
		mstt_PolicyTransactions.CommInitialAmount - Full (projected) DA amount
		
		mstt_Expectation.AMOUNT_REC - The DA actually received. This handles the
										LV scenario whereby the AMOUNT_REC is 
										proportioned across the two payments received.   
																		
	****************************************************************************/

	select top 0 *, convert(int,NULL) as CommissionYear
	into #owt_Recognition
	from owt_Recognition

	insert into #owt_Recognition
	(
		SourceID,
		CaseID,
		TransactionID,
		Policy,
		ProductCode,
		BusinessCode,
		PointsTotal,
		BSC,
		MBF,
		Initial,
		OngoingTotal,
		OngoingYr01,
		OngoingYr02,
		OngoingYr03,
		OngoingYr04,
		OngoingYr05,
		OngoingYr06,
		OngoingYr07,
		OngoingYr08,
		OngoingYr09,
		OngoingYr10,
		FCARate,
		RetentionRate,
		RetentionRateBroker,
		OngoingServicingRate,
		OngoingServicingSource,
		DA,
		AmountReceived,
		Premium,
		AgentSplit,
		CommissionType,
		CommissionTypeDesc,
		Month,
		FrequencyCode,
		FrequencyDesc,
		RecognitionType,
		CalculationType,
		Source,
		DateInserted,
		DateLastUpdated,
		CommissionYear
	)
	select	cs.PendingPaymentID as SourceID,
			cs.CaseID,
			cs.TransactionID,
			cs.ExtPolicyNumber as Policy,
			cs.ProductCode,
			cs.BusinessCode,
			0.0 as PointsTotal,
			case
				when BSCpot.ID is not null then 
					--BSC takes the first 0.12 of the ongoing fee %. If the ongoing fee % is 0.12% or less, then 100% of the ongoing fee is allocated to BSC
					case when coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2)) - convert(decimal(8,4),sc.KeyValue2) >= 0.01
						then 
							case when cs.FrequencyCode = 2	--Monthly 
								then (cs.AgentSplit/100) * 12.0 * (isnull(cs.Premium,0)/2.0) * convert(decimal(8,4),sc.KeyValue3) * case when cs.INIssued < 0 then -1 else 1 end
								else (cs.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(cs.Premium,0) * convert(decimal(8,4),sc.KeyValue3) * case when cs.INIssued < 0 then -1 else 1 end
							end			
						else
							case when cs.FrequencyCode = 2	--Monthly 
								then (cs.AgentSplit/100) * 12.0 * (isnull(cs.Premium,0)/2.0) * coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2)) * case when cs.INIssued < 0 then -1 else 1 end
								else (cs.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(cs.Premium,0) * (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))/100.0) * case when cs.INIssued < 0 then -1 else 1 end
							end
					end
				else 0.0
			end as BSC,
			case 
				when mbf.MortgageFeeID is not null and cs.INIssued <> 0 then (((mbf.AdviceFeeAmount)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * MRbkr.FACTOR) - ((mbf.AdviceFeeAmount)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * Mfca.FACTOR)) --Note that mbf.AdviceFeeAmount is signed correctly - so no coding for signing is needed here
				else 0.0
			end as MBF,
			case 
				--When the adviser has changed, the AgentSplit can become zero in which case the ELITE points should be zero.
				when cs.AgentSplit = 0 then 0
				
				--WEALTH CALCULATION START
				--Indemnity payments or SINGLEs or IC Clawbacks or IC adjustments Start
				when (ph.ProductCategoryCode = 1 or pcc.KeyValue2 = '1') and (cs.FrequencyCode = 6 or cs.PayBasisCode in ('T') or cs.CommissionType in (2,17)) and cs.commissiontype in (1,2,17) and cs.INIssued <> 0 then (((e.AMOUNT_REC)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * Crate.FACTOR) - ((e.AMOUNT_REC)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * Cfca.FACTOR)) * case when cs.INIssued < 0 then -1 else 1 end
				--Indemnity payments or SINGLEs or IC Clawbacks or IC adjustments End
				--Accruals & Level Start
				when (ph.ProductCategoryCode = 1 or pcc.KeyValue2 = '1') and cs.INIssued <> 0 then (((pt.CommInitialAmount)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * Crate.FACTOR) - ((pt.CommInitialAmount)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * Cfca.FACTOR)) * case when cs.INIssued < 0 then -1 else 1 end
				--Accruals & Level End
				--WEALTH CALCULATION END
				
				--MORTGAGE CALCULATION START
				--Note: The MBF component has its own table column
				--Only 1 payment for mortgages
				when ph.ProductGroupCode = 3 and cs.INIssued <> 0 then (((pt.CommInitialAmount)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * MRproc.FACTOR) - ((pt.CommInitialAmount)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * Mfca.FACTOR)) * case when cs.INIssued < 0 then -1 else 1 end
				--MORTGAGE CALCULATION END
				
				--PROTECTION CALCULATION START
				--Indemnity payments or SINGLEs or IC Clawbacks or IC adjustments Start
				when ph.ProductGroupCode = 6 and (cs.FrequencyCode = 6 or cs.PayBasisCode in ('T') or cs.CommissionType in (2,17)) and cs.commissiontype in (1,2,17) and cs.INIssued <> 0 then (((e.AMOUNT_REC)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * Prate.FACTOR) - ((e.AMOUNT_REC)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * Pfca.FACTOR)) * case when cs.INIssued < 0 then -1 else 1 end
				--Indemnity payments or SINGLEs or IC Clawbacks or IC adjustments End
				--Accruals & Level Start
				when ph.ProductGroupCode = 6 and cs.INIssued <> 0 then (((pt.CommInitialAmount)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * Prate.FACTOR) - ((pt.CommInitialAmount)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * Pfca.FACTOR)) * case when cs.INIssued < 0 then -1 else 1 end
				--Accruals & Level End
				--PROTECTION CALCULATION END

				else 0.0

			end as Initial,
			0.0 as OngoingTotal,
			case
				--WEALTH ONGOING CALCULATION START
				--When the adviser has changed, the AgentSplit can become zero in which case the ELITE points should be zero.
				when cs.AgentSplit = 0 then 0

				--SINGLE start
				--Calculate when BSC and ongoing applies (where ongoing rate is greater than BSC rate) 
				when (ph.ProductCategoryCode = 1 or pcc.KeyValue2 = '1') and cs.FrequencyCode = 6 and SFMpot.ID is not null and BSCpot.ID is not null and (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2)) - convert(decimal(8,4),sc.KeyValue2)) >= 0.01 then 
							--(AUM X BSC Rate)...
							((cs.AgentSplit/100) * (isnull(cs.Premium,0) * convert(decimal(8,4),sc.KeyValue3)) 
							--(AUM X OGS Rate X COB FCA Rate)...
							- ((cs.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(cs.Premium,0) * (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))/100.0) * Cfca.FACTOR)
							--(AUM X (OGS Rate - BSC Rate) X COB Retention Rate)...
							+ ((cs.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(cs.Premium,0) * ((coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))-convert(decimal(8,4),sc.KeyValue2))/100.0)) * Crate.FACTOR) 
							--Sign correctly for +ve or clawback payment
							* (case when cs.INIssued < 0 then -1 else 1 end)
				--Calculate when BSC and ongoing applies (where ongoing rate less than BSC rate, then BSC gets all the ongoing available) 
				when (ph.ProductCategoryCode = 1 or pcc.KeyValue2 = '1') and cs.FrequencyCode = 6 and SFMpot.ID is not null and BSCpot.ID is not null then
							--(AUM X BSC Rate)...(in this scenario it's all of the OGS rate)
							((cs.AgentSplit/100) * (isnull(cs.Premium,0) * (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))/100.0)) 
							--(AUM X OGS Rate X COB FCA Rate)...
							- ((cs.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(cs.Premium,0) * (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))/100.0) * Cfca.FACTOR)
							--(AUM X (OGS Rate - BSC Rate) X COB Retention Rate)...
							+ (0.0)) --BSC got it all, so this part of the calculation is zero
							--Sign correctly for +ve or clawback payment
							* (case when cs.INIssued < 0 then -1 else 1 end)
				--Calculate when no BSC applies and ongoing applies
				when (ph.ProductCategoryCode = 1 or pcc.KeyValue2 = '1') and cs.FrequencyCode = 6 and SFMpot.ID is not null and BSCpot.ID is null then 
							--(AUM X OGS Rate X COB Retention Rate)...
							(((cs.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(cs.Premium,0) * (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))/100.0) * Crate.FACTOR) 
							--(AUM X OGS Rate X COB FCA Rate)...
							- ((cs.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(cs.Premium,0) * (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))/100.0) * Cfca.FACTOR))
							--Sign correctly for +ve or clawback payment
							* (case when cs.INIssued < 0 then -1 else 1 end)
				--SINGLE end
				
				--REGULAR start
				--Calculate when BSC and ongoing applies (where ongoing rate is greater than BSC rate) 
				when (ph.ProductCategoryCode = 1 or pcc.KeyValue2 = '1') and SFMpot.ID is not null and BSCpot.ID is not null and (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2)) - convert(decimal(8,4),sc.KeyValue2)) >= 0.01 then 
							--The non-BSC portion (Ave AUM X (OGS Rate - BSC Rate) X COB Retention Rate)...
							((((((cs.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(cs.Premium,0) * (case when cs.FrequencyCode = 2 then 12 else 1 end))/2.0) * (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2)) - convert(decimal(8,4),sc.KeyValue2))/100.0)) * Crate.FACTOR
							--The BSC portion (Ave AUM X BSC Rate)...
							+ case when cs.FrequencyCode = 2	--Monthly 
									then (cs.AgentSplit/100) * 12.0 * (isnull(cs.Premium,0)/2.0) * convert(decimal(8,4),sc.KeyValue3) 
									else (cs.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(cs.Premium,0) * convert(decimal(8,4),sc.KeyValue3) 
							  end
							--FCA Charge (Ave AUM X OGS Rate X FCA Rate)...
							- (case when cs.FrequencyCode = 2	--Monthly 
									then (cs.AgentSplit/100) * 12.0 * (isnull(cs.Premium,0)/2.0) 
									else (cs.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(cs.Premium,0) 
							   end * (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))/100.0) * Cfca.FACTOR))
							--Sign correctly for +ve or clawback payment
							* (case when cs.INIssued < 0 then -1 else 1 end)   
				--Calculate when BSC and ongoing applies (where ongoing rate less than BSC rate, then BSC gets all the ongoing available) 
				when (ph.ProductCategoryCode = 1 or pcc.KeyValue2 = '1') and SFMpot.ID is not null and BSCpot.ID is not null then 
							--The non-BSC portion (Ave AUM X (OGS Rate - BSC Rate) X COB Retention Rate)...
							((0/0)	--BSC got it all, so this part of the calculation is zero
							--The BSC portion (Ave AUM X BSC Rate)...(in this scenario it's all of the OGS rate)
							+ case when cs.FrequencyCode = 2	--Monthly 
									then (cs.AgentSplit/100) * 12.0 * (isnull(cs.Premium,0)/2.0) * (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))/100.0) 
									else (cs.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(cs.Premium,0) * (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))/100.0) 
							  end
							--FCA Charge (Ave AUM X OGS Rate X FCA Rate)...
							- (case when cs.FrequencyCode = 2	--Monthly 
									then (cs.AgentSplit/100) * 12.0 * (isnull(cs.Premium,0)/2.0) 
									else (cs.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(cs.Premium,0) 
							   end * (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))/100.0) * Cfca.FACTOR))
							--Sign correctly for +ve or clawback payment
							* (case when cs.INIssued < 0 then -1 else 1 end)   
				--Calculate when no BSC applies, but ongoing servicing applies
				when (ph.ProductCategoryCode = 1 or pcc.KeyValue2 = '1') and SFMpot.ID is not null and BSCpot.ID is null then 
							--(Ave AUM X OGS Rate X COB Retention Rate)...
							(((((cs.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(cs.Premium,0) * (case when cs.FrequencyCode = 2 then 12 else 1 end))/2.0) * (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))/100.0) * Crate.FACTOR) 
							--(Ave AUM X OGS Rate X COB FCA Rate)...
							- ((((cs.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(cs.Premium,0) * (case when cs.FrequencyCode = 2 then 12 else 1 end))/2.0) * (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))/100.0) * Cfca.FACTOR))
							--Sign correctly for +ve or clawback payment
							* (case when cs.INIssued < 0 then -1 else 1 end)   
				--REGULAR end
				
				else 0.0

				--WEALTH ONGOING CALCULATION END
			end as OngoingYr01,
			0.0 as OngoingYr02,
			0.0 as OngoingYr03,
			0.0 as OngoingYr04,
			0.0 as OngoingYr05,
			0.0 as OngoingYr06,
			0.0 as OngoingYr07,
			0.0 as OngoingYr08,
			0.0 as OngoingYr09,
			0.0 as OngoingYr10,
			case 
				when (ph.ProductCategoryCode = 1 or pcc.KeyValue2 = '1') then Cfca.FACTOR*100.0		--COB
				when ph.ProductGroupCode = 3 then Mfca.FACTOR*100.0		--MORT
				when ph.ProductGroupCode = 6 then Pfca.FACTOR*100.0		--PROT
				else 0.0
			end as FCARate,
			case 
				when (ph.ProductCategoryCode = 1 or pcc.KeyValue2 = '1') then Crate.FACTOR*100.0	--COB
				when ph.ProductGroupCode = 3 then MRproc.FACTOR*100.0	--MORT
				when ph.ProductGroupCode = 6 then Prate.FACTOR*100.0	--PROT
				else 0.0
			end as RetentionRate,
			case 
				when mbf.MortgageFeeID is not null then  MRbkr.FACTOR*100.0	
				else 0.0
			end as RetentionRateBroker,
			case when SFMpot.ID is not null
				then coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))
				else null
			end as OngoingServicingRate,
			case when SFMpot.ID is not null
				then case 
						when ogs.OngoingServiceFee is null and ogscli.OngoingServiceFee is null 
							then case
								when ogsdflt.KeyValue = 'ONPLAT' then 'Default - On Plat'
								else 'Default - Off Plat'
							end
						when ogs.OngoingServiceFee is not null then 'Client Product'
						when ogscli.OngoingServiceFee is not null then 'Client Only'
						else 'Unknown'
					 end
				else case when (ph.ProductCategoryCode = 1 or pcc.KeyValue2 = '1')
						then 'No OGS'					--WEALTH, but no OGS
						else null						--Not WEALTH, so OGS is n/a and is therefore null
					 end
			end as OngoingServicingSource,
			pt.CommInitialAmount as DA,
			e.AMOUNT_REC as AmountReceived,
			cs.Premium,
			cs.AgentSplit,
			cs.CommissionType,
			left(cs.StandingOrderDesc,50) as CommissionTypeDesc,
			cs.Month,
			cs.FrequencyCode,
			cs.FrequencyDesc,
			'VNB' as RecognitionType,
			case 
				when (ph.ProductCategoryCode = 1 or pcc.KeyValue2 = '1') then 'WEALTH'
				when ph.ProductGroupCode = 3 then 'MORTGAGE'
				when ph.ProductGroupCode = 6 then 'PROTECTION'
				else null
			end as CalculationType,
			'Openwork 2006' as Source,
			@DateLastUpdated as DateInserted,
			@DateLastUpdated as DateLastUpdated,
			csp.year as CommissionYear
	--select count(*)
	from	msit_CommissionStatement cs
			inner join (select	distinct PKID
						from	owt_TransformationMovements tm 
						where	tm.DriverTableName = 'sa_swift_S_AGMFIL'
						and		tm.CommissionStatement = 'Y') tm on tm.PKID = cs.PendingPaymentID
			inner join mstt_Agents ag on ag.Code = cs.BusinessCode
			inner join mstt_PolicyTransactions pt on pt.ID = cs.TransactionID
			inner join mstt_Policies p on p.POL_NUM = pt.PolicyID
			inner join msit_CommissionStatementPeriods VNBStart on convert(date,pt.CreateDateTime) between VNBStart.PeriodStartDate and VNBStart.PeriodEndDate
			inner join msit_Commissionstatementperiods csp on csp.month = cs.month
			inner join mstt_ProductHierarchy ph on ph.productcode = cs.productcode
			inner join mstt_Expectation e on e.ID = cs.ExpectationID
			left join dbo.owt_MortgageBrokerFees mbf on mbf.PendingPaymentID = cs.PendingPaymentID and mbf.AdviceFeeCharged = 'Yes'
			left join owt_SelectionControl SC
						on SC.Process = 'ElitePoints' 
						and SC.KeyType = 'NSCPotCode' 
						and cs.CreateDate between SC.EffectiveStartDate and SC.EffectiveEndDate
			left join mstt_Commissions BSCpot
						on BSCpot.TransactionID = cs.TransactionID 
						and BSCpot.Agent_Code = sc.KeyValue
						and BSCpot.CommissionType = 10
			left join owt_SelectionControl SFMPC						
						on SFMPC.Process = 'ElitePoints' 
						and SFMPC.KeyType = 'ServicingFeeMarginPotCode' 
						and cs.CreateDate between SFMPC.EffectiveStartDate and SFMPC.EffectiveEndDate
			left join mstt_Commissions SFMpot							
						on SFMpot.TransactionID = cs.TransactionID 
						and SFMpot.Agent_Code = SFMPC.KeyValue
						and SFMpot.CommissionType = 10	
			left join owt_SelectionControl pcc 
						on pcc.Process = 'ElitePoints'
						and pcc.KeyType = 'ProductCategoryCode'
						and pcc.KeyValue = cs.ProductCode	
						and cs.CreateDate between pcc.EffectiveStartDate and pcc.EffectiveEndDate
			left join owt_SelectionControl ogsdflt 
						on ogsdflt.Process = 'ElitePoints'
						and ogsdflt.KeyType = 'DefaultOngoingServicingRate'
						and ogsdflt.SelectionType = 'VNB'
						and ogsdflt.KeyValue = case when ph.RDRType = 'ONPLAT' then 'ONPLAT' else 'OFPLAT' end
						and cs.CreateDate between ogsdflt.EffectiveStartDate and ogsdflt.EffectiveEndDate
			left join owt_EliteFactors Cfca on Cfca.FeeType = 'VNB' and Cfca.category = 'COB-FCA-RATE' and csp.year between Cfca.StartYear and Cfca.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors Crate on Crate.FeeType = 'VNB' and Crate.category = 'COB-RETENTION-RATE' and csp.year between Crate.StartYear and Crate.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors Mfca on Mfca.FeeType = 'VNB' and Mfca.category = 'MORT-FCA-RATE' and csp.year between Mfca.StartYear and Mfca.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors MRproc on MRproc.FeeType = 'VNB' and MRproc.category = 'MORT-RETENTION-RATE-PROC' and csp.year between MRproc.StartYear and MRproc.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors MRbkr on MRbkr.FeeType = 'VNB' and MRbkr.category = 'MORT-RETENTION-RATE-BROKER' and csp.year between MRbkr.StartYear and MRbkr.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors Pfca on Pfca.FeeType = 'VNB' and Pfca.category = 'PROT-FCA-RATE' and csp.year between Pfca.StartYear and Pfca.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors Prate on Prate.FeeType = 'VNB' and Prate.category = 'PROT-RETENTION-RATE' and csp.year between Prate.StartYear and Prate.EndYear 
			left join #OGSLookUp ogs on ogs.CLIENT_NUM = cs.ClientID and ogs.ProductCode = cs.ProductCode
			left join #OGSLookUpClient ogscli on ogscli.CLIENT_NUM = cs.ClientID 
	where	cs.ReportingClassCode = 1
	and		ag.Manager2Code <> @OwlManager2Code		--Exclude Owl
	--and		p.PolicyRef in (1460996,1714642,550842754,551078732,550951391,550771221)
	and		cs.INIssued <> 0
	--and		cs.PendingPaymentID = 39709463
	and		VNBStart.Year >= 2017			--VNB to start from 2017
	and		csp.Year >= 2017				--Ensure in-scope payments are consistent with VNB start

	select @RowCount = @@rowcount
	set @ProcessMessage = '#owt_Recognition = ' + convert(nvarchar(10), @RowCount)
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseLog, @ProcessMessage, null, @Module, @Client
	
	/****************************************************************************

		Now calculate the ongoing spread for each of 10 years.
		Note that regular payments get an additional multiplier to uplift the 
		average AUM for each year.
																		
	****************************************************************************/

	update r
		set OngoingYr02 = case when r.FrequencyCode = 2							--Monthly
							then r.OngoingYr01 * YR02.Multiplier * YR02.Factor	--Regular
							else r.OngoingYr01 * YR02.Factor					--Single
						  end,
			OngoingYr03 = case when r.FrequencyCode = 2							--Monthly
							then r.OngoingYr01 * YR03.Multiplier * YR03.Factor	--Regular
							else r.OngoingYr01 * YR03.Factor					--Single
						  end,
			OngoingYr04 = case when r.FrequencyCode = 2							--Monthly
							then r.OngoingYr01 * YR04.Multiplier * YR04.Factor	--Regular
							else r.OngoingYr01 * YR04.Factor					--Single
						  end,
			OngoingYr05 = case when r.FrequencyCode = 2							--Monthly 
							then r.OngoingYr01 * YR05.Multiplier * YR05.Factor	--Regular
							else r.OngoingYr01 * YR05.Factor					--Single
						  end,
			OngoingYr06 = case when r.FrequencyCode = 2							--Monthly 
							then r.OngoingYr01 * YR06.Multiplier * YR06.Factor	--Regular
							else r.OngoingYr01 * YR06.Factor					--Single
						  end,
			OngoingYr07 = case when r.FrequencyCode = 2							--Monthly 
							then r.OngoingYr01 * YR07.Multiplier * YR07.Factor	--Regular
							else r.OngoingYr01 * YR07.Factor					--Single
						  end,
			OngoingYr08 = case when r.FrequencyCode = 2							--Monthly 
							then r.OngoingYr01 * YR08.Multiplier * YR08.Factor	--Regular
							else r.OngoingYr01 * YR08.Factor					--Single
						  end,
			OngoingYr09 = case when r.FrequencyCode = 2							--Monthly 
							then r.OngoingYr01 * YR09.Multiplier * YR09.Factor	--Regular
							else r.OngoingYr01 * YR09.Factor					--Single
						  end,
			OngoingYr10 = case when r.FrequencyCode = 2							--Monthly 
							then r.OngoingYr01 * YR10.Multiplier * YR10.Factor	--Regular
							else r.OngoingYr01 * YR10.Factor					--Single
						   end
	from	#owt_Recognition r
			left join owt_EliteFactors YR01 on YR01.FeeType = 'VNB' and YR01.Category = 'COB-ONGOING-DISCOUNT-YR01' and r.CommissionYear between YR01.StartYear and YR01.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors YR02 on YR02.FeeType = 'VNB' and YR02.Category = 'COB-ONGOING-DISCOUNT-YR02' and r.CommissionYear between YR02.StartYear and YR02.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors YR03 on YR03.FeeType = 'VNB' and YR03.Category = 'COB-ONGOING-DISCOUNT-YR03' and r.CommissionYear between YR03.StartYear and YR03.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors YR04 on YR04.FeeType = 'VNB' and YR04.Category = 'COB-ONGOING-DISCOUNT-YR04' and r.CommissionYear between YR04.StartYear and YR04.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors YR05 on YR05.FeeType = 'VNB' and YR05.Category = 'COB-ONGOING-DISCOUNT-YR05' and r.CommissionYear between YR05.StartYear and YR05.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors YR06 on YR06.FeeType = 'VNB' and YR06.Category = 'COB-ONGOING-DISCOUNT-YR06' and r.CommissionYear between YR06.StartYear and YR06.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors YR07 on YR07.FeeType = 'VNB' and YR07.Category = 'COB-ONGOING-DISCOUNT-YR07' and r.CommissionYear between YR07.StartYear and YR07.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors YR08 on YR08.FeeType = 'VNB' and YR08.Category = 'COB-ONGOING-DISCOUNT-YR08' and r.CommissionYear between YR08.StartYear and YR08.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors YR09 on YR09.FeeType = 'VNB' and YR09.Category = 'COB-ONGOING-DISCOUNT-YR09' and r.CommissionYear between YR09.StartYear and YR09.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors YR10 on YR10.FeeType = 'VNB' and YR10.Category = 'COB-ONGOING-DISCOUNT-YR10' and r.CommissionYear between YR10.StartYear and YR10.EndYear 

	select @RowCount = @@rowcount
	set @ProcessMessage = '#owt_Recognition (ongoing) = ' + convert(nvarchar(10), @RowCount)
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseLog, @ProcessMessage, null, @Module, @Client

	/****************************************************************************

		Now add up all the numbers
																		
	****************************************************************************/
	
	update r
		set OngoingTotal	=	OngoingYr01 + OngoingYr02 + OngoingYr03 + OngoingYr04 + OngoingYr05 +
								OngoingYr06 + OngoingYr07 + OngoingYr08 + OngoingYr09 + OngoingYr10,
			PointsTotal		=	OngoingYr01 + OngoingYr02 + OngoingYr03 + OngoingYr04 + OngoingYr05 +
								OngoingYr06 + OngoingYr07 + OngoingYr08 + OngoingYr09 + OngoingYr10 +
								Initial + MBF	-- Note BSC is already included in the Ongoing, so don't include it in the Points Total.
	from	#owt_Recognition r

	select @RowCount = @@rowcount
	set @ProcessMessage = '#owt_Recognition (totals) = ' + convert(nvarchar(10), @RowCount)
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseLog, @ProcessMessage, null, @Module, @Client

	/****************************************************************************

		Merge the temporary table into the permanent table
																		
	****************************************************************************/

	BEGIN TRANSACTION

	declare @SummaryOfChanges table (Change varchar(20))
	merge	dbo.owt_Recognition as trg
	using	#owt_Recognition as src
	on		trg.SourceID = src.SourceID
	and		trg.Source = src.Source
	when	matched 
	and		isnull(trg.PointsTotal,0) <> isnull(src.PointsTotal,0)
	then	update 
				set trg.CaseID = src.CaseID,
					trg.TransactionID = src.TransactionID,
					trg.Policy = src.Policy,
					trg.ProductCode = src.ProductCode,
					trg.BusinessCode = src.BusinessCode,
					trg.PointsTotal = src.PointsTotal,
					trg.BSC = src.BSC,
					trg.MBF = src.MBF,
					trg.Initial = src.Initial,
					trg.OngoingTotal = src.OngoingTotal,
					trg.OngoingYr01 = src.OngoingYr01,
					trg.OngoingYr02 = src.OngoingYr02,
					trg.OngoingYr03 = src.OngoingYr03,
					trg.OngoingYr04 = src.OngoingYr04,
					trg.OngoingYr05 = src.OngoingYr05,
					trg.OngoingYr06 = src.OngoingYr06,
					trg.OngoingYr07 = src.OngoingYr07,
					trg.OngoingYr08 = src.OngoingYr08,
					trg.OngoingYr09 = src.OngoingYr09,
					trg.OngoingYr10 = src.OngoingYr10,
					trg.FCARate = src.FCARate,
					trg.RetentionRate = src.RetentionRate,
					trg.RetentionRateBroker = src.RetentionRateBroker,
					trg.OngoingServicingRate = src.OngoingServicingRate,
					trg.OngoingServicingSource = src.OngoingServicingSource,
					trg.DA = src.DA,
					trg.AmountReceived = src.AmountReceived,
					trg.Premium = src.Premium,
					trg.AgentSplit = src.AgentSplit,
					trg.CommissionType = src.CommissionType,
					trg.CommissionTypeDesc = src.CommissionTypeDesc,
					trg.Month = src.Month,
					trg.FrequencyCode = src.FrequencyCode,
					trg.FrequencyDesc = src.FrequencyDesc,
					trg.RecognitionType = src.RecognitionType,
					trg.CalculationType = src.CalculationType,
					trg.DateLastUpdated = @DateLastUpdated
	when	not matched by target 
	then	insert
			(
				SourceID,
				CaseID,
				TransactionID,
				Policy,
				ProductCode,
				BusinessCode,
				PointsTotal,
				BSC,
				MBF,
				Initial,
				OngoingTotal,
				OngoingYr01,
				OngoingYr02,
				OngoingYr03,
				OngoingYr04,
				OngoingYr05,
				OngoingYr06,
				OngoingYr07,
				OngoingYr08,
				OngoingYr09,
				OngoingYr10,
				FCARate,
				RetentionRate,
				RetentionRateBroker,
				OngoingServicingRate,
				OngoingServicingSource,
				DA,
				AmountReceived,
				Premium,
				AgentSplit,
				CommissionType,
				CommissionTypeDesc,
				Month,
				FrequencyCode,
				FrequencyDesc,
				RecognitionType,
				CalculationType,
				Source,
				DateInserted,
				DateLastUpdated
			)		
			values
			(
				src.SourceID,
				src.CaseID,
				src.TransactionID,
				src.Policy,
				src.ProductCode,
				src.BusinessCode,
				src.PointsTotal,
				src.BSC,
				src.MBF,
				src.Initial,
				src.OngoingTotal,
				src.OngoingYr01,
				src.OngoingYr02,
				src.OngoingYr03,
				src.OngoingYr04,
				src.OngoingYr05,
				src.OngoingYr06,
				src.OngoingYr07,
				src.OngoingYr08,
				src.OngoingYr09,
				src.OngoingYr10,
				src.FCARate,
				src.RetentionRate,
				src.RetentionRateBroker,
				src.OngoingServicingRate,
				src.OngoingServicingSource,
				src.DA,
				src.AmountReceived,
				src.Premium,
				src.AgentSplit,
				src.CommissionType,
				src.CommissionTypeDesc,
				src.Month,
				src.FrequencyCode,
				src.FrequencyDesc,
				src.RecognitionType,
				src.CalculationType,
				src.Source,
				src.DateInserted,
				src.DateLastUpdated)				--Merge statements must have a ;
	output $action into @SummaryOfChanges;
	
	COMMIT TRANSACTION      

	select	@RowCount = COUNT(*)
	from	@SummaryOfChanges
	where	Change = 'INSERT'

	set @ProcessMessage = 'owt_Recognition (insert) = ' + convert(nvarchar(10), @RowCount)
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseLog, @ProcessMessage, null, @Module, @Client

	select	@RowCount = COUNT(*)
	from	@SummaryOfChanges
	where	Change = 'UPDATE'

	set @ProcessMessage = 'owt_Recognition (update) = ' + convert(nvarchar(10), @RowCount)
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseLog, @ProcessMessage, null, @Module, @Client

	/****************************************************************************

		T H E   E N D
																		
	****************************************************************************/
	
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseEnd, @ProcName, null, @Module, @Client

END TRY

BEGIN CATCH 

	select @ErrNum = ERROR_NUMBER(), @ErrMsg = ERROR_MESSAGE(), @ErrSev = ERROR_SEVERITY(), @ErrLine = ERROR_LINE(), @ErrState = XACT_STATE()
	set @ErrMsg = REPLACE(@ErrMsg, '.', '') + ' (error no: ' + CAST(@ErrNum AS VARCHAR(10)) + ') on line ' + CAST(@ErrLine AS VARCHAR(10))
	
	-- Test XACT_STATE for 0, 1, or -1.
    -- If 1, the transaction is committable.
    -- If -1, the transaction is uncommittable and should be rolled back.
    -- If 0, there is no transaction and a commit or rollback operation would generate an error.

	if @ErrState = -1			-- Transaction is uncommitable
		rollback transaction

	if @ErrState = 1			
		commit transaction

	-- Error message line 1
	set @ErrMsgBrief = left(@ErrMsg,100)
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseError, @ErrMsgBrief, null, @Module, @Client
	
	-- Error message line 2 - if any text exists
	set @ErrMsgBrief = substring(@ErrMsg,101,100)
	if len(@ErrMsgBrief) > 0
		exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseError, @ErrMsgBrief, null, @Module, @Client

	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseEnd, @ProcName, null, @Module, @Client

	RAISERROR(@ErrMsg, @ErrSev , 1)

END CATCH

/****************************************************************************

			E N D															

****************************************************************************/

return @ErrNum



GO
/****** Object:  StoredProcedure [dbo].[owp_RecognitionSwift_Backup20180604AG]    Script Date: 7/3/2026 3:44:25 PM ******/
SET ANSI_NULLS ON
GO
SET QUOTED_IDENTIFIER ON
GO
/*********************************************************************************************************

Program:		owp_RecognitionSwift					
Author:			Alan Groves
Date created:	11/04/2018
											
Description:
===========

This proc populates the new recognition table called "owt_Recognition" with "Value of New Business"
(VNB) points.

This proc handles all of the swift data which includes:
WEALTH - COB business i.e. pensions and investments
MORTGAGES
PROTECTION

Note: There is a separate proc that calculates the GI VNB points from the Paymentshield data.

The approach of this proc is to use the incremental PendingPaymentIDs from the overnight batch
to calculate the VNB points in a temporary table.

The temporary table is then merged with the permanent table to make the calculated (or
re-calculated values) permanent.

Terms
-----
BSC			- Business Service Charge.
MBF			- Mortgage Broker Fee.
OGS			- Ongoing Servicing.
BSC Rate	- 0.12% at the time of writing (24/04/2018). This could be changed by the business, but
				would also require some DEV work in OWS.
DF			- Discount Factor.
DA			- Distribution Allowance (the total amount paid out by the provider to Openwork)
AUM			- Assets Under Management. Basically the amount invested or the premium on investment
				cases.
Average AUM - Average amount invested annually which is equivalent to 6 months' premium.

THE CALCULATIONS
================

There are two potential parts: initial + ongoing (if ongoing applies). If BSC (applies to ongoing 
only) and MBF (applies to mortgages only) apply, then these are also included:

MORTGAGE
--------
Part 1: MBF column = (Advice Fee Amount X Broker Retention Rate) - (Advice Fee Amount X Mort FCA Rate)
Part 2: Initial column = (Proc Fee Amount X Mortgage Retention Rate) - (Proc Fee X Mort FCA Rate) 
Mortgage Points Total = Initial + MBF

PROTECTION
----------
= (DA X Protection Retention Rate) - (DA X Protection FCA Rate) 
Protection Points Total = Initial

WEALTH (COB i.e. pensions and investments)
------
Part 1: Initial column = (DA X Wealth Retention Rate) - (DA X Wealth FCA Rate)

Part 2:

REGULAR - BSC applies:
Year 1 column = BSC Points + Non-BSC Points - FCA Points
Non-BSC Points = Ave AUM X (OGS Rate - BSC Rate) X COB Retention Rate
BSC Points = Ave AUM X OGS Rate X FCA Rate
FCA Points = Ave AUM X OGS Rate X Wealth FCA Rate

REGULAR - Non-BSC: 
Year 1 column = (Ave AUM X OGS Rate X COB Retention Rate) - (Ave AUM X OGS Rate X COB FCA Rate)

SINGLE - BSC applies:
Year 1 column = (AUM X BSC Rate) + (AUM X (OGS Rate - BSC Rate) X COB Retention Rate) - (AUM X OGS Rate X COB FCA Rate) 

SINGLE - Non-BSC:
Year 1 column = (AUM X OGS Rate X COB Retention Rate) - (AUM X OGS Rate X COB FCA Rate) 

Then years 2 to 10 are calculated by applying a discount factor
Year  2 = Year 1 X  3 X DF
Year  3 = Year 1 X  5 X DF
Year  4 = Year 1 X  7 X DF
Year  5 = Year 1 X  9 X DF
Year  6 = Year 1 X 11 X DF
Year  7 = Year 1 X 13 X DF
Year  8 = Year 1 X 15 X DF
Year  9 = Year 1 X 17 X DF
Year 10 = Year 1 X 19 X DF

Wealth Points Total =	OngoingYr01 + OngoingYr02 + OngoingYr03 + OngoingYr04 + OngoingYr05 +
						OngoingYr06 + OngoingYr07 + OngoingYr08 + OngoingYr09 + OngoingYr10 +
						Initial

GI
--
See stored proc "owp_RecognitionGIPaymentshield".
 
Notes:
-----

There is a BSC column on table owt_Recognition. However, BSC is already included in the ongoing
years 1 - 10, so the BSC column does not need to be added in. In fact you will double count if 
you attempt to do anything with it other than display it.


This proc is called as follows:
	declare @rc int
	exec @rc = dbo.owp_RecognitionSwift 'Openwork', 'Recognition'
	select @rc

					
AMENDMENT HISTORY				
=================								

Date		Author		Description
----		------		-----------
26/04/2018	A Groves	Only include rows in the OGS lookups where the OngoingServiceFee > 0.0.
						Negative OGS rates are bad data and at the time of writing, there are
						39 of these.
27/04/2018	A Groves	Additional calculation and condition to handle the scenario where BSC applies
						but the OGS Rate is less than the BSC rate. Previously, this caused the
						total ongoing to be zero. However, there are two components to ongoing VNB 
						points, the BSC share and the non-BSC share. So the BSC share (which takes 
						100% when the OGS rate is less than 0.12%) should still yield ongoing points.
27/04/2018	A Groves	Single ongoing Yr01 corrected by applying outer brackets before signing the result.
03/05/2018	A Groves	Added update of column "msit_OpenworkAdviserListing.VNB_Points".
18/05/2018	A Groves	Changed mortgage calculation to use e.AMOUNT_REC instead of pt.CommInitialAmount
						as Marcus Cossey wanted the actual amount received to be used for the DA.
*************************************************************************************************************/

CREATE PROCEDURE [dbo].[owp_RecognitionSwift_Backup20180604AG]
	@Client		varchar(50),
	@Module		Varchar(50)
AS

set nocount on

declare		@PhaseStart				varchar(50),
			@PhaseEnd				varchar(50),
			@PhaseError				varchar(50),
			@PhaseLog				varchar(50),
			@ProcName				varchar(100),
			@ProcessMessage			varchar(100),
			@RowCount				int,
			@OALRowCount			int,
			@ErrMsg					nvarchar(4000),
			@ErrMsgBrief			nvarchar(100),
			@ErrNum					int,
			@ErrSev					int,
			@ErrLine				int,
			@ErrState				int,
			@DateLastUpdated		datetime,
			@OwlManager2Code		nvarchar(10)
			
/****************************************************************************

	Set initial parameters																
																		
****************************************************************************/

set @ProcName			= object_name(@@procid)
set @PhaseStart			= 'START'
set @PhaseEnd			= 'END'
set @PhaseError			= 'ERROR'
set @PhaseLog			= 'LOG'
set @ErrNum				= 0	
set @DateLastUpdated	= getdate()

set @OwlManager2Code = (select cde.Code from msit_MIWarehouseCodesAndDescriptions cde
			where cde.ColumnName = 'Manager2Code' and cde.Description = 'Owl Financial')

-- We want this logging irrespective of whether or not there is a rollback
exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseStart, @ProcName, null, @Module, @Client

/****************************************************************************

	Populate the table																
																		
****************************************************************************/

SET XACT_ABORT ON	-- Needed if XACT_STATE() function is used.

BEGIN TRY

	/****************************************************************************

		Link OWS data to Swift data to enable the ongoing servicng (OGS) rate
		to be looked up.
																		
	****************************************************************************/
	
	select	distinct s.PersonID, swp.Client_Num, p.InternalProductID, swp.ProductCode 
	into	#SwiftOWSClientLink
	from	sa_ows_Sale s
			inner join sa_ows_Policies p on p.SaleID = s.SaleID
			inner join mstt_Policies swp on swp.PolicyRef = p.PolicyID
	where	s.DateSubmitted is not null
	--and		s.PersonID = 146030

	select @RowCount = @@rowcount
	set @ProcessMessage = '#SwiftOWSClientLink = ' + convert(nvarchar(10), @RowCount)
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseLog, @ProcessMessage, null, @Module, @Client

	-- The OGS rate is stored for the client/product combination
	select	link.Client_Num, link.ProductCode, max(ogs.OngoingServiceFee) as OngoingServiceFee
	into	#OGSLookUp
	from	#SwiftOWSClientLink link 
			inner join mstt_ProductHierarchy ph on ph.ProductCode = link.ProductCode
			inner join Submission.sa_ows_SubmittedProductCurrentOngoingServiceFee ogs
							on ogs.PersonID = link.PersonID
							and ogs.InternalProductID = (case when ph.RDRType = 'ONPLAT' 
															then -2 
															else link.InternalProductID 
														 end)
	where	ogs.OngoingServiceFee > 0.0							--AG 26/04/2018
	group	by 	link.Client_Num, link.ProductCode

	select @RowCount = @@rowcount
	set @ProcessMessage = '#OGSLookUp = ' + convert(nvarchar(10), @RowCount)
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseLog, @ProcessMessage, null, @Module, @Client

	create index idx_OGSLookUp on #OGSLookUp (Client_num, ProductCode)

	--This is an additional catch for OGS by storing the client's highest OGS
	--rate against their client number. This lookup will apply if the first
	--look up fails. The first lookup can fail, for example, if the case was 
	--not submitted on OWS i.e. the CaseID has a "17" prefix. 
	select	Client_Num, MAX(OngoingServiceFee) as OngoingServiceFee
	into	#OGSLookUpClient
	from	#OGSLookUp
	group	by Client_Num

	select @RowCount = @@rowcount
	set @ProcessMessage = '#OGSLookUpClient = ' + convert(nvarchar(10), @RowCount)
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseLog, @ProcessMessage, null, @Module, @Client
	
	create index idx_OGSLookUpClient on #OGSLookUpClient (Client_num)

	/****************************************************************************

		Calculate VNB and populate the temporary table with the results
		
		Note that there are oddities like LV protection payments which always
		come in pairs with one large and one much smaller amount (e.g. TransactionID 
		= 6684787.) The system treats both payments in the pair as first payments 
		and the (projected) DA associated with both is the same (because it's on 
		the policy transaction). 
		
		There is also a requirement to front-load VNB points on accrual and level
		payments. This means calculate the VNB for the full amount of the DA and 
		put it on the first payment record and then on all subsequent accrual and 
		level payments, set the VNB to zero.
		
		Thus two different sources of DA are used depending on whether we need the
		full DA amount for accruals and level or the actual amount received for all
		other scenarios including the LV split payment scenario. The two sources are:
		
		mstt_PolicyTransactions.CommInitialAmount - Full (projected) DA amount
		
		mstt_Expectation.AMOUNT_REC - The DA actually received. This handles the
										LV scenario whereby the AMOUNT_REC is 
										proportioned across the two payments received.   
																		
	****************************************************************************/

	select top 0 *, convert(int,NULL) as CommissionYear
	into #owt_Recognition
	from owt_Recognition

	insert into #owt_Recognition
	(
		SourceID,
		CaseID,
		TransactionID,
		Policy,
		ProductCode,
		BusinessCode,
		PointsTotal,
		BSC,
		MBF,
		Initial,
		OngoingTotal,
		OngoingYr01,
		OngoingYr02,
		OngoingYr03,
		OngoingYr04,
		OngoingYr05,
		OngoingYr06,
		OngoingYr07,
		OngoingYr08,
		OngoingYr09,
		OngoingYr10,
		FCARate,
		RetentionRate,
		RetentionRateBroker,
		OngoingServicingRate,
		OngoingServicingSource,
		DA,
		AmountReceived,
		Premium,
		AgentSplit,
		CommissionType,
		CommissionTypeDesc,
		Month,
		FrequencyCode,
		FrequencyDesc,
		RecognitionType,
		CalculationType,
		Source,
		DateInserted,
		DateLastUpdated,
		CommissionYear
	)
	select	cs.PendingPaymentID as SourceID,
			cs.CaseID,
			cs.TransactionID,
			cs.ExtPolicyNumber as Policy,
			cs.ProductCode,
			cs.BusinessCode,
			0.0 as PointsTotal,
			case
				when BSCpot.ID is not null then 
					--BSC takes the first 0.12 of the ongoing fee %. If the ongoing fee % is 0.12% or less, then 100% of the ongoing fee is allocated to BSC
					case when coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2)) - convert(decimal(8,4),sc.KeyValue2) >= 0.01
						then 
							case when cs.FrequencyCode = 2	--Monthly 
								then (cs.AgentSplit/100) * 12.0 * (isnull(cs.Premium,0)/2.0) * convert(decimal(8,4),sc.KeyValue3) * case when cs.INIssued < 0 then -1 else 1 end
								else (cs.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(cs.Premium,0) * convert(decimal(8,4),sc.KeyValue3) * case when cs.INIssued < 0 then -1 else 1 end
							end			
						else
							case when cs.FrequencyCode = 2	--Monthly 
								then (cs.AgentSplit/100) * 12.0 * (isnull(cs.Premium,0)/2.0) * coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2)) * case when cs.INIssued < 0 then -1 else 1 end
								else (cs.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(cs.Premium,0) * (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))/100.0) * case when cs.INIssued < 0 then -1 else 1 end
							end
					end
				else 0.0
			end as BSC,
			case 
				when mbf.MortgageFeeID is not null and cs.INIssued <> 0 then (((mbf.AdviceFeeAmount)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * MRbkr.FACTOR) - ((mbf.AdviceFeeAmount)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * Mfca.FACTOR)) --Note that mbf.AdviceFeeAmount is signed correctly - so no coding for signing is needed here
				else 0.0
			end as MBF,
			case 
				--When the adviser has changed, the AgentSplit can become zero in which case the ELITE points should be zero.
				when cs.AgentSplit = 0 then 0
				
				--WEALTH CALCULATION START
				--Indemnity payments or SINGLEs or IC Clawbacks or IC adjustments Start
				when (ph.ProductCategoryCode = 1 or pcc.KeyValue2 = '1') and (cs.FrequencyCode = 6 or cs.PayBasisCode in ('T') or cs.CommissionType in (2,17)) and cs.commissiontype in (1,2,17) and cs.INIssued <> 0 then (((e.AMOUNT_REC)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * Crate.FACTOR) - ((e.AMOUNT_REC)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * Cfca.FACTOR)) * case when cs.INIssued < 0 then -1 else 1 end
				--Indemnity payments or SINGLEs or IC Clawbacks or IC adjustments End
				--Accruals & Level Start
				when (ph.ProductCategoryCode = 1 or pcc.KeyValue2 = '1') and cs.INIssued <> 0 then (((pt.CommInitialAmount)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * Crate.FACTOR) - ((pt.CommInitialAmount)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * Cfca.FACTOR)) * case when cs.INIssued < 0 then -1 else 1 end
				--Accruals & Level End
				--WEALTH CALCULATION END
				
				--MORTGAGE CALCULATION START
				--Note: The MBF component has its own table column
				--Only 1 payment for mortgages
				when ph.ProductGroupCode = 3 and cs.INIssued <> 0 then (((e.AMOUNT_REC)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * MRproc.FACTOR) - ((e.AMOUNT_REC)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * Mfca.FACTOR)) * case when cs.INIssued < 0 then -1 else 1 end	--AG 18/05/2018
				--MORTGAGE CALCULATION END
				
				--PROTECTION CALCULATION START
				--Indemnity payments or SINGLEs or IC Clawbacks or IC adjustments Start
				when ph.ProductGroupCode = 6 and (cs.FrequencyCode = 6 or cs.PayBasisCode in ('T') or cs.CommissionType in (2,17)) and cs.commissiontype in (1,2,17) and cs.INIssued <> 0 then (((e.AMOUNT_REC)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * Prate.FACTOR) - ((e.AMOUNT_REC)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * Pfca.FACTOR)) * case when cs.INIssued < 0 then -1 else 1 end
				--Indemnity payments or SINGLEs or IC Clawbacks or IC adjustments End
				--Accruals & Level Start
				when ph.ProductGroupCode = 6 and cs.INIssued <> 0 then (((pt.CommInitialAmount)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * Prate.FACTOR) - ((pt.CommInitialAmount)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * Pfca.FACTOR)) * case when cs.INIssued < 0 then -1 else 1 end
				--Accruals & Level End
				--PROTECTION CALCULATION END

				else 0.0

			end as Initial,
			0.0 as OngoingTotal,
			case
				--WEALTH ONGOING CALCULATION START
				--When the adviser has changed, the AgentSplit can become zero in which case the ELITE points should be zero.
				when cs.AgentSplit = 0 then 0

				--SINGLE start
				--Calculate when BSC and ongoing applies (where ongoing rate is greater than BSC rate) 
				when (ph.ProductCategoryCode = 1 or pcc.KeyValue2 = '1') and cs.FrequencyCode = 6 and SFMpot.ID is not null and BSCpot.ID is not null and (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2)) - convert(decimal(8,4),sc.KeyValue2)) >= 0.01 then 
							--(AUM X BSC Rate)...
							((cs.AgentSplit/100) * (isnull(cs.Premium,0) * convert(decimal(8,4),sc.KeyValue3)) 
							--(AUM X OGS Rate X COB FCA Rate)...
							- ((cs.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(cs.Premium,0) * (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))/100.0) * Cfca.FACTOR)
							--(AUM X (OGS Rate - BSC Rate) X COB Retention Rate)...
							+ ((cs.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(cs.Premium,0) * ((coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))-convert(decimal(8,4),sc.KeyValue2))/100.0)) * Crate.FACTOR) 
							--Sign correctly for +ve or clawback payment
							* (case when cs.INIssued < 0 then -1 else 1 end)
				--Calculate when BSC and ongoing applies (where ongoing rate less than BSC rate, then BSC gets all the ongoing available) 
				when (ph.ProductCategoryCode = 1 or pcc.KeyValue2 = '1') and cs.FrequencyCode = 6 and SFMpot.ID is not null and BSCpot.ID is not null then
							--(AUM X BSC Rate)...(in this scenario it's all of the OGS rate)
							((cs.AgentSplit/100) * (isnull(cs.Premium,0) * (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))/100.0)) 
							--(AUM X OGS Rate X COB FCA Rate)...
							- ((cs.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(cs.Premium,0) * (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))/100.0) * Cfca.FACTOR)
							--(AUM X (OGS Rate - BSC Rate) X COB Retention Rate)...
							+ (0.0)) --BSC got it all, so this part of the calculation is zero
							--Sign correctly for +ve or clawback payment
							* (case when cs.INIssued < 0 then -1 else 1 end)
				--Calculate when no BSC applies and ongoing applies
				when (ph.ProductCategoryCode = 1 or pcc.KeyValue2 = '1') and cs.FrequencyCode = 6 and SFMpot.ID is not null and BSCpot.ID is null then 
							--(AUM X OGS Rate X COB Retention Rate)...
							(((cs.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(cs.Premium,0) * (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))/100.0) * Crate.FACTOR) 
							--(AUM X OGS Rate X COB FCA Rate)...
							- ((cs.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(cs.Premium,0) * (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))/100.0) * Cfca.FACTOR))
							--Sign correctly for +ve or clawback payment
							* (case when cs.INIssued < 0 then -1 else 1 end)
				--SINGLE end
				
				--REGULAR start
				--Calculate when BSC and ongoing applies (where ongoing rate is greater than BSC rate) 
				when (ph.ProductCategoryCode = 1 or pcc.KeyValue2 = '1') and SFMpot.ID is not null and BSCpot.ID is not null and (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2)) - convert(decimal(8,4),sc.KeyValue2)) >= 0.01 then 
							--The non-BSC portion (Ave AUM X (OGS Rate - BSC Rate) X COB Retention Rate)...
							((((((cs.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(cs.Premium,0) * (case when cs.FrequencyCode = 2 then 12 else 1 end))/2.0) * (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2)) - convert(decimal(8,4),sc.KeyValue2))/100.0)) * Crate.FACTOR
							--The BSC portion (Ave AUM X BSC Rate)...
							+ case when cs.FrequencyCode = 2	--Monthly 
									then (cs.AgentSplit/100) * 12.0 * (isnull(cs.Premium,0)/2.0) * convert(decimal(8,4),sc.KeyValue3) 
									else (cs.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(cs.Premium,0) * convert(decimal(8,4),sc.KeyValue3) 
							  end
							--FCA Charge (Ave AUM X OGS Rate X FCA Rate)...
							- (case when cs.FrequencyCode = 2	--Monthly 
									then (cs.AgentSplit/100) * 12.0 * (isnull(cs.Premium,0)/2.0) 
									else (cs.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(cs.Premium,0) 
							   end * (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))/100.0) * Cfca.FACTOR))
							--Sign correctly for +ve or clawback payment
							* (case when cs.INIssued < 0 then -1 else 1 end)   
				--Calculate when BSC and ongoing applies (where ongoing rate less than BSC rate, then BSC gets all the ongoing available) 
				when (ph.ProductCategoryCode = 1 or pcc.KeyValue2 = '1') and SFMpot.ID is not null and BSCpot.ID is not null then 
							--The non-BSC portion (Ave AUM X (OGS Rate - BSC Rate) X COB Retention Rate)...
							((0/0)	--BSC got it all, so this part of the calculation is zero
							--The BSC portion (Ave AUM X BSC Rate)...(in this scenario it's all of the OGS rate)
							+ case when cs.FrequencyCode = 2	--Monthly 
									then (cs.AgentSplit/100) * 12.0 * (isnull(cs.Premium,0)/2.0) * (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))/100.0) 
									else (cs.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(cs.Premium,0) * (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))/100.0) 
							  end
							--FCA Charge (Ave AUM X OGS Rate X FCA Rate)...
							- (case when cs.FrequencyCode = 2	--Monthly 
									then (cs.AgentSplit/100) * 12.0 * (isnull(cs.Premium,0)/2.0) 
									else (cs.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(cs.Premium,0) 
							   end * (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))/100.0) * Cfca.FACTOR))
							--Sign correctly for +ve or clawback payment
							* (case when cs.INIssued < 0 then -1 else 1 end)   
				--Calculate when no BSC applies, but ongoing servicing applies
				when (ph.ProductCategoryCode = 1 or pcc.KeyValue2 = '1') and SFMpot.ID is not null and BSCpot.ID is null then 
							--(Ave AUM X OGS Rate X COB Retention Rate)...
							(((((cs.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(cs.Premium,0) * (case when cs.FrequencyCode = 2 then 12 else 1 end))/2.0) * (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))/100.0) * Crate.FACTOR) 
							--(Ave AUM X OGS Rate X COB FCA Rate)...
							- ((((cs.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(cs.Premium,0) * (case when cs.FrequencyCode = 2 then 12 else 1 end))/2.0) * (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))/100.0) * Cfca.FACTOR))
							--Sign correctly for +ve or clawback payment
							* (case when cs.INIssued < 0 then -1 else 1 end)   
				--REGULAR end
				
				else 0.0

				--WEALTH ONGOING CALCULATION END
			end as OngoingYr01,
			0.0 as OngoingYr02,
			0.0 as OngoingYr03,
			0.0 as OngoingYr04,
			0.0 as OngoingYr05,
			0.0 as OngoingYr06,
			0.0 as OngoingYr07,
			0.0 as OngoingYr08,
			0.0 as OngoingYr09,
			0.0 as OngoingYr10,
			case 
				when (ph.ProductCategoryCode = 1 or pcc.KeyValue2 = '1') then Cfca.FACTOR*100.0		--COB
				when ph.ProductGroupCode = 3 then Mfca.FACTOR*100.0		--MORT
				when ph.ProductGroupCode = 6 then Pfca.FACTOR*100.0		--PROT
				else 0.0
			end as FCARate,
			case 
				when (ph.ProductCategoryCode = 1 or pcc.KeyValue2 = '1') then Crate.FACTOR*100.0	--COB
				when ph.ProductGroupCode = 3 then MRproc.FACTOR*100.0	--MORT
				when ph.ProductGroupCode = 6 then Prate.FACTOR*100.0	--PROT
				else 0.0
			end as RetentionRate,
			case 
				when mbf.MortgageFeeID is not null then  MRbkr.FACTOR*100.0	
				else 0.0
			end as RetentionRateBroker,
			case when SFMpot.ID is not null
				then coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))
				else null
			end as OngoingServicingRate,
			case when SFMpot.ID is not null
				then case 
						when ogs.OngoingServiceFee is null and ogscli.OngoingServiceFee is null 
							then case
								when ogsdflt.KeyValue = 'ONPLAT' then 'Default - On Plat'
								else 'Default - Off Plat'
							end
						when ogs.OngoingServiceFee is not null then 'Client Product'
						when ogscli.OngoingServiceFee is not null then 'Client Only'
						else 'Unknown'
					 end
				else case when (ph.ProductCategoryCode = 1 or pcc.KeyValue2 = '1')
						then 'No OGS'					--WEALTH, but no OGS
						else null						--Not WEALTH, so OGS is n/a and is therefore null
					 end
			end as OngoingServicingSource,
			pt.CommInitialAmount as DA,
			e.AMOUNT_REC as AmountReceived,
			cs.Premium,
			cs.AgentSplit,
			cs.CommissionType,
			left(cs.StandingOrderDesc,50) as CommissionTypeDesc,
			cs.Month,
			cs.FrequencyCode,
			cs.FrequencyDesc,
			'VNB' as RecognitionType,
			case 
				when (ph.ProductCategoryCode = 1 or pcc.KeyValue2 = '1') then 'WEALTH'
				when ph.ProductGroupCode = 3 then 'MORTGAGE'
				when ph.ProductGroupCode = 6 then 'PROTECTION'
				else null
			end as CalculationType,
			'Openwork 2006' as Source,
			@DateLastUpdated as DateInserted,
			@DateLastUpdated as DateLastUpdated,
			csp.year as CommissionYear
	--select count(*)
	from	msit_CommissionStatement cs
/*			inner join (select	distinct PKID
						from	owt_TransformationMovements tm 
						where	tm.DriverTableName = 'sa_swift_S_AGMFIL'
						and		tm.CommissionStatement = 'Y') tm on tm.PKID = cs.PendingPaymentID
*/			inner join mstt_Agents ag on ag.Code = cs.BusinessCode
			inner join mstt_PolicyTransactions pt on pt.ID = cs.TransactionID
			inner join mstt_Policies p on p.POL_NUM = pt.PolicyID
			inner join msit_CommissionStatementPeriods VNBStart on convert(date,pt.CreateDateTime) between VNBStart.PeriodStartDate and VNBStart.PeriodEndDate
			inner join msit_Commissionstatementperiods csp on csp.month = cs.month
			inner join mstt_ProductHierarchy ph on ph.productcode = cs.productcode
			inner join mstt_Expectation e on e.ID = cs.ExpectationID
			left join dbo.owt_MortgageBrokerFees mbf on mbf.PendingPaymentID = cs.PendingPaymentID and mbf.AdviceFeeCharged = 'Yes'
			left join owt_SelectionControl SC
						on SC.Process = 'ElitePoints' 
						and SC.KeyType = 'NSCPotCode' 
						and cs.CreateDate between SC.EffectiveStartDate and SC.EffectiveEndDate
			left join mstt_Commissions BSCpot
						on BSCpot.TransactionID = cs.TransactionID 
						and BSCpot.Agent_Code = sc.KeyValue
						and BSCpot.CommissionType = 10
			left join owt_SelectionControl SFMPC						
						on SFMPC.Process = 'ElitePoints' 
						and SFMPC.KeyType = 'ServicingFeeMarginPotCode' 
						and cs.CreateDate between SFMPC.EffectiveStartDate and SFMPC.EffectiveEndDate
			left join mstt_Commissions SFMpot							
						on SFMpot.TransactionID = cs.TransactionID 
						and SFMpot.Agent_Code = SFMPC.KeyValue
						and SFMpot.CommissionType = 10	
			left join owt_SelectionControl pcc 
						on pcc.Process = 'ElitePoints'
						and pcc.KeyType = 'ProductCategoryCode'
						and pcc.KeyValue = cs.ProductCode	
						and cs.CreateDate between pcc.EffectiveStartDate and pcc.EffectiveEndDate
			left join owt_SelectionControl ogsdflt 
						on ogsdflt.Process = 'ElitePoints'
						and ogsdflt.KeyType = 'DefaultOngoingServicingRate'
						and ogsdflt.SelectionType = 'VNB'
						and ogsdflt.KeyValue = case when ph.RDRType = 'ONPLAT' then 'ONPLAT' else 'OFPLAT' end
						and cs.CreateDate between ogsdflt.EffectiveStartDate and ogsdflt.EffectiveEndDate
			left join owt_EliteFactors Cfca on Cfca.FeeType = 'VNB' and Cfca.category = 'COB-FCA-RATE' and csp.year between Cfca.StartYear and Cfca.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors Crate on Crate.FeeType = 'VNB' and Crate.category = 'COB-RETENTION-RATE' and csp.year between Crate.StartYear and Crate.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors Mfca on Mfca.FeeType = 'VNB' and Mfca.category = 'MORT-FCA-RATE' and csp.year between Mfca.StartYear and Mfca.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors MRproc on MRproc.FeeType = 'VNB' and MRproc.category = 'MORT-RETENTION-RATE-PROC' and csp.year between MRproc.StartYear and MRproc.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors MRbkr on MRbkr.FeeType = 'VNB' and MRbkr.category = 'MORT-RETENTION-RATE-BROKER' and csp.year between MRbkr.StartYear and MRbkr.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors Pfca on Pfca.FeeType = 'VNB' and Pfca.category = 'PROT-FCA-RATE' and csp.year between Pfca.StartYear and Pfca.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors Prate on Prate.FeeType = 'VNB' and Prate.category = 'PROT-RETENTION-RATE' and csp.year between Prate.StartYear and Prate.EndYear 
			left join #OGSLookUp ogs on ogs.CLIENT_NUM = cs.ClientID and ogs.ProductCode = cs.ProductCode
			left join #OGSLookUpClient ogscli on ogscli.CLIENT_NUM = cs.ClientID 
	where	cs.ReportingClassCode = 1
	and		ag.Manager2Code <> @OwlManager2Code		--Exclude Owl
	and		cs.INIssued <> 0
	and		VNBStart.Year >= 2017			--VNB to start from 2017
	and		csp.Year >= 2017				--Ensure in-scope payments are consistent with VNB start

	select @RowCount = @@rowcount
	set @ProcessMessage = '#owt_Recognition = ' + convert(nvarchar(10), @RowCount)
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseLog, @ProcessMessage, null, @Module, @Client
	
	/****************************************************************************

		Now calculate the ongoing spread for each of 10 years.
		Note that regular payments get an additional multiplier to uplift the 
		average AUM for each year.
																		
	****************************************************************************/

	update r
		set OngoingYr02 = case when r.FrequencyCode = 2							--Monthly
							then r.OngoingYr01 * YR02.Multiplier * YR02.Factor	--Regular
							else r.OngoingYr01 * YR02.Factor					--Single
						  end,
			OngoingYr03 = case when r.FrequencyCode = 2							--Monthly
							then r.OngoingYr01 * YR03.Multiplier * YR03.Factor	--Regular
							else r.OngoingYr01 * YR03.Factor					--Single
						  end,
			OngoingYr04 = case when r.FrequencyCode = 2							--Monthly
							then r.OngoingYr01 * YR04.Multiplier * YR04.Factor	--Regular
							else r.OngoingYr01 * YR04.Factor					--Single
						  end,
			OngoingYr05 = case when r.FrequencyCode = 2							--Monthly 
							then r.OngoingYr01 * YR05.Multiplier * YR05.Factor	--Regular
							else r.OngoingYr01 * YR05.Factor					--Single
						  end,
			OngoingYr06 = case when r.FrequencyCode = 2							--Monthly 
							then r.OngoingYr01 * YR06.Multiplier * YR06.Factor	--Regular
							else r.OngoingYr01 * YR06.Factor					--Single
						  end,
			OngoingYr07 = case when r.FrequencyCode = 2							--Monthly 
							then r.OngoingYr01 * YR07.Multiplier * YR07.Factor	--Regular
							else r.OngoingYr01 * YR07.Factor					--Single
						  end,
			OngoingYr08 = case when r.FrequencyCode = 2							--Monthly 
							then r.OngoingYr01 * YR08.Multiplier * YR08.Factor	--Regular
							else r.OngoingYr01 * YR08.Factor					--Single
						  end,
			OngoingYr09 = case when r.FrequencyCode = 2							--Monthly 
							then r.OngoingYr01 * YR09.Multiplier * YR09.Factor	--Regular
							else r.OngoingYr01 * YR09.Factor					--Single
						  end,
			OngoingYr10 = case when r.FrequencyCode = 2							--Monthly 
							then r.OngoingYr01 * YR10.Multiplier * YR10.Factor	--Regular
							else r.OngoingYr01 * YR10.Factor					--Single
						   end
	from	#owt_Recognition r
			left join owt_EliteFactors YR01 on YR01.FeeType = 'VNB' and YR01.Category = 'COB-ONGOING-DISCOUNT-YR01' and r.CommissionYear between YR01.StartYear and YR01.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors YR02 on YR02.FeeType = 'VNB' and YR02.Category = 'COB-ONGOING-DISCOUNT-YR02' and r.CommissionYear between YR02.StartYear and YR02.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors YR03 on YR03.FeeType = 'VNB' and YR03.Category = 'COB-ONGOING-DISCOUNT-YR03' and r.CommissionYear between YR03.StartYear and YR03.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors YR04 on YR04.FeeType = 'VNB' and YR04.Category = 'COB-ONGOING-DISCOUNT-YR04' and r.CommissionYear between YR04.StartYear and YR04.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors YR05 on YR05.FeeType = 'VNB' and YR05.Category = 'COB-ONGOING-DISCOUNT-YR05' and r.CommissionYear between YR05.StartYear and YR05.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors YR06 on YR06.FeeType = 'VNB' and YR06.Category = 'COB-ONGOING-DISCOUNT-YR06' and r.CommissionYear between YR06.StartYear and YR06.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors YR07 on YR07.FeeType = 'VNB' and YR07.Category = 'COB-ONGOING-DISCOUNT-YR07' and r.CommissionYear between YR07.StartYear and YR07.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors YR08 on YR08.FeeType = 'VNB' and YR08.Category = 'COB-ONGOING-DISCOUNT-YR08' and r.CommissionYear between YR08.StartYear and YR08.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors YR09 on YR09.FeeType = 'VNB' and YR09.Category = 'COB-ONGOING-DISCOUNT-YR09' and r.CommissionYear between YR09.StartYear and YR09.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors YR10 on YR10.FeeType = 'VNB' and YR10.Category = 'COB-ONGOING-DISCOUNT-YR10' and r.CommissionYear between YR10.StartYear and YR10.EndYear 

	select @RowCount = @@rowcount
	set @ProcessMessage = '#owt_Recognition (ongoing) = ' + convert(nvarchar(10), @RowCount)
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseLog, @ProcessMessage, null, @Module, @Client

	/****************************************************************************

		Now add up all the numbers
																		
	****************************************************************************/
	
	update r
		set OngoingTotal	=	OngoingYr01 + OngoingYr02 + OngoingYr03 + OngoingYr04 + OngoingYr05 +
								OngoingYr06 + OngoingYr07 + OngoingYr08 + OngoingYr09 + OngoingYr10,
			PointsTotal		=	OngoingYr01 + OngoingYr02 + OngoingYr03 + OngoingYr04 + OngoingYr05 +
								OngoingYr06 + OngoingYr07 + OngoingYr08 + OngoingYr09 + OngoingYr10 +
								Initial + MBF	-- Note BSC is already included in the Ongoing, so don't include it in the Points Total.
	from	#owt_Recognition r

	select @RowCount = @@rowcount
	set @ProcessMessage = '#owt_Recognition (totals) = ' + convert(nvarchar(10), @RowCount)
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseLog, @ProcessMessage, null, @Module, @Client

	/****************************************************************************

		Merge the temporary table into the permanent table
																		
	****************************************************************************/

	BEGIN TRANSACTION

	declare @SummaryOfChanges table (Change varchar(20))
	merge	dbo.owt_Recognition as trg
	using	#owt_Recognition as src
	on		trg.SourceID = src.SourceID
	and		trg.Source = src.Source
	when	matched 
	and		isnull(trg.PointsTotal,0) <> isnull(src.PointsTotal,0)
	then	update 
				set trg.CaseID = src.CaseID,
					trg.TransactionID = src.TransactionID,
					trg.Policy = src.Policy,
					trg.ProductCode = src.ProductCode,
					trg.BusinessCode = src.BusinessCode,
					trg.PointsTotal = src.PointsTotal,
					trg.BSC = src.BSC,
					trg.MBF = src.MBF,
					trg.Initial = src.Initial,
					trg.OngoingTotal = src.OngoingTotal,
					trg.OngoingYr01 = src.OngoingYr01,
					trg.OngoingYr02 = src.OngoingYr02,
					trg.OngoingYr03 = src.OngoingYr03,
					trg.OngoingYr04 = src.OngoingYr04,
					trg.OngoingYr05 = src.OngoingYr05,
					trg.OngoingYr06 = src.OngoingYr06,
					trg.OngoingYr07 = src.OngoingYr07,
					trg.OngoingYr08 = src.OngoingYr08,
					trg.OngoingYr09 = src.OngoingYr09,
					trg.OngoingYr10 = src.OngoingYr10,
					trg.FCARate = src.FCARate,
					trg.RetentionRate = src.RetentionRate,
					trg.RetentionRateBroker = src.RetentionRateBroker,
					trg.OngoingServicingRate = src.OngoingServicingRate,
					trg.OngoingServicingSource = src.OngoingServicingSource,
					trg.DA = src.DA,
					trg.AmountReceived = src.AmountReceived,
					trg.Premium = src.Premium,
					trg.AgentSplit = src.AgentSplit,
					trg.CommissionType = src.CommissionType,
					trg.CommissionTypeDesc = src.CommissionTypeDesc,
					trg.Month = src.Month,
					trg.FrequencyCode = src.FrequencyCode,
					trg.FrequencyDesc = src.FrequencyDesc,
					trg.RecognitionType = src.RecognitionType,
					trg.CalculationType = src.CalculationType,
					trg.DateLastUpdated = @DateLastUpdated
	when	not matched by target 
	then	insert
			(
				SourceID,
				CaseID,
				TransactionID,
				Policy,
				ProductCode,
				BusinessCode,
				PointsTotal,
				BSC,
				MBF,
				Initial,
				OngoingTotal,
				OngoingYr01,
				OngoingYr02,
				OngoingYr03,
				OngoingYr04,
				OngoingYr05,
				OngoingYr06,
				OngoingYr07,
				OngoingYr08,
				OngoingYr09,
				OngoingYr10,
				FCARate,
				RetentionRate,
				RetentionRateBroker,
				OngoingServicingRate,
				OngoingServicingSource,
				DA,
				AmountReceived,
				Premium,
				AgentSplit,
				CommissionType,
				CommissionTypeDesc,
				Month,
				FrequencyCode,
				FrequencyDesc,
				RecognitionType,
				CalculationType,
				Source,
				DateInserted,
				DateLastUpdated
			)		
			values
			(
				src.SourceID,
				src.CaseID,
				src.TransactionID,
				src.Policy,
				src.ProductCode,
				src.BusinessCode,
				src.PointsTotal,
				src.BSC,
				src.MBF,
				src.Initial,
				src.OngoingTotal,
				src.OngoingYr01,
				src.OngoingYr02,
				src.OngoingYr03,
				src.OngoingYr04,
				src.OngoingYr05,
				src.OngoingYr06,
				src.OngoingYr07,
				src.OngoingYr08,
				src.OngoingYr09,
				src.OngoingYr10,
				src.FCARate,
				src.RetentionRate,
				src.RetentionRateBroker,
				src.OngoingServicingRate,
				src.OngoingServicingSource,
				src.DA,
				src.AmountReceived,
				src.Premium,
				src.AgentSplit,
				src.CommissionType,
				src.CommissionTypeDesc,
				src.Month,
				src.FrequencyCode,
				src.FrequencyDesc,
				src.RecognitionType,
				src.CalculationType,
				src.Source,
				src.DateInserted,
				src.DateLastUpdated)				--Merge statements must have a ;
	output $action into @SummaryOfChanges;
/*	
	update	oal
		set VNB_Points = r.PointsTotal
	from	msit_CommissionStatement cs
			inner join (select	distinct PKID
						from	owt_TransformationMovements tm 
						where	tm.DriverTableName = 'sa_swift_S_AGMFIL'
						and		tm.CommissionStatement = 'Y') tm on tm.PKID = cs.PendingPaymentID
			inner join msit_OpenworkAdviserListing oal on oal.SourceID = cs.ID and oal.Source = 'Openwork 2006'
			inner join owt_Recognition r 
						on r.RecognitionType = 'VNB'
						and r.SourceID = cs.PendingPaymentID
						and r.Source = oal.Source
	where	isnull(oal.VNB_Points,0) <> isnull(r.PointsTotal,0)
	
	select @OALRowCount = @@rowcount
*/
	COMMIT TRANSACTION      

	select	@RowCount = COUNT(*)
	from	@SummaryOfChanges
	where	Change = 'INSERT'

	set @ProcessMessage = 'owt_Recognition (insert) = ' + convert(nvarchar(10), @RowCount)
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseLog, @ProcessMessage, null, @Module, @Client

	select	@RowCount = COUNT(*)
	from	@SummaryOfChanges
	where	Change = 'UPDATE'

	set @ProcessMessage = 'owt_Recognition (update) = ' + convert(nvarchar(10), @RowCount)
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseLog, @ProcessMessage, null, @Module, @Client
/*
	set @ProcessMessage = 'msit_OpenworkAdviserListing (update) = ' + convert(nvarchar(10), @OALRowCount)
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseLog, @ProcessMessage, null, @Module, @Client
*/
	/****************************************************************************

		T H E   E N D
																		
	****************************************************************************/
	
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseEnd, @ProcName, null, @Module, @Client

END TRY

BEGIN CATCH 

	select @ErrNum = ERROR_NUMBER(), @ErrMsg = ERROR_MESSAGE(), @ErrSev = ERROR_SEVERITY(), @ErrLine = ERROR_LINE(), @ErrState = XACT_STATE()
	set @ErrMsg = REPLACE(@ErrMsg, '.', '') + ' (error no: ' + CAST(@ErrNum AS VARCHAR(10)) + ') on line ' + CAST(@ErrLine AS VARCHAR(10))
	
	-- Test XACT_STATE for 0, 1, or -1.
    -- If 1, the transaction is committable.
    -- If -1, the transaction is uncommittable and should be rolled back.
    -- If 0, there is no transaction and a commit or rollback operation would generate an error.

	if @ErrState = -1			-- Transaction is uncommitable
		rollback transaction

	if @ErrState = 1			
		commit transaction

	-- Error message line 1
	set @ErrMsgBrief = left(@ErrMsg,100)
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseError, @ErrMsgBrief, null, @Module, @Client
	
	-- Error message line 2 - if any text exists
	set @ErrMsgBrief = substring(@ErrMsg,101,100)
	if len(@ErrMsgBrief) > 0
		exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseError, @ErrMsgBrief, null, @Module, @Client

	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseEnd, @ProcName, null, @Module, @Client

	RAISERROR(@ErrMsg, @ErrSev , 1)

END CATCH

/****************************************************************************

			E N D															

****************************************************************************/

return @ErrNum



GO
/****** Object:  StoredProcedure [dbo].[owp_RecognitionSwift_Backup20180606AG]    Script Date: 7/3/2026 3:44:25 PM ******/
SET ANSI_NULLS ON
GO
SET QUOTED_IDENTIFIER ON
GO
/*********************************************************************************************************

Program:		owp_RecognitionSwift					
Author:			Alan Groves
Date created:	11/04/2018
											
Description:
===========

This proc populates the new recognition table called "owt_Recognition" with "Value of New Business"
(VNB) points.

This proc handles all of the swift data which includes:
WEALTH - COB business i.e. pensions and investments
MORTGAGES
PROTECTION

Note: There is a separate proc that calculates the GI VNB points from the Paymentshield data.

The approach of this proc is to use the incremental PendingPaymentIDs from the overnight batch
to calculate the VNB points in a temporary table.

The temporary table is then merged with the permanent table to make the calculated (or
re-calculated values) permanent.

Terms
-----
BSC			- Business Service Charge.
MBF			- Mortgage Broker Fee.
OGS			- Ongoing Servicing.
BSC Rate	- 0.12% at the time of writing (24/04/2018). This could be changed by the business, but
				would also require some DEV work in OWS.
DF			- Discount Factor.
DA			- Distribution Allowance (the total amount paid out by the provider to Openwork)
AUM			- Assets Under Management. Basically the amount invested or the premium on investment
				cases.
Average AUM - Average amount invested annually which is equivalent to 6 months' premium.

THE CALCULATIONS
================

There are two potential parts: initial + ongoing (if ongoing applies). If BSC (applies to ongoing 
only) and MBF (applies to mortgages only) apply, then these are also included:

MORTGAGE
--------
Part 1: MBF column = (Advice Fee Amount X Broker Retention Rate) - (Advice Fee Amount X Mort FCA Rate)
Part 2: Initial column = (Proc Fee Amount X Mortgage Retention Rate) - (Proc Fee X Mort FCA Rate) 
Mortgage Points Total = Initial + MBF

PROTECTION
----------
= (DA X Protection Retention Rate) - (DA X Protection FCA Rate) 
Protection Points Total = Initial

WEALTH (COB i.e. pensions and investments)
------
Part 1: Initial column = (DA X Wealth Retention Rate) - (DA X Wealth FCA Rate)

Part 2:

****XXXX****

NOTE: Where the BSC rate is greater than the ongoing rate, then BSC gets ALL of the AVAILABLE 
ongoing.

****XXXX****

REGULAR - BSC applies:
Year 1 column = BSC Points + Non-BSC Points - FCA Points
Non-BSC Points = Ave AUM X (OGS Rate - BSC Rate) X COB Retention Rate
BSC Points = Ave AUM X BSC Rate
FCA Points = Ave AUM X OGS Rate X COB FCA Rate

REGULAR - Non-BSC: 
Year 1 column = (Ave AUM X OGS Rate X COB Retention Rate) - (Ave AUM X OGS Rate X COB FCA Rate)

SINGLE - BSC applies:
Year 1 column = (AUM X BSC Rate) + (AUM X (OGS Rate - BSC Rate) X COB Retention Rate) - (AUM X OGS Rate X COB FCA Rate) 

SINGLE - Non-BSC:
Year 1 column = (AUM X OGS Rate X COB Retention Rate) - (AUM X OGS Rate X COB FCA Rate) 

Then years 2 to 10 are calculated by applying a discount factor
Year  2 = Year 1 X  3 X DF
Year  3 = Year 1 X  5 X DF
Year  4 = Year 1 X  7 X DF
Year  5 = Year 1 X  9 X DF
Year  6 = Year 1 X 11 X DF
Year  7 = Year 1 X 13 X DF
Year  8 = Year 1 X 15 X DF
Year  9 = Year 1 X 17 X DF
Year 10 = Year 1 X 19 X DF

Wealth Points Total =	OngoingYr01 + OngoingYr02 + OngoingYr03 + OngoingYr04 + OngoingYr05 +
						OngoingYr06 + OngoingYr07 + OngoingYr08 + OngoingYr09 + OngoingYr10 +
						Initial

GI
--
See stored proc "owp_RecognitionGIPaymentshield".
 
Notes:
-----

There is a BSC column on table owt_Recognition. However, BSC is already included in the ongoing
years 1 - 10, so the BSC column does not need to be added in. In fact you will double count if 
you attempt to do anything with it other than display it.


This proc is called as follows:
	declare @rc int
	exec @rc = dbo.owp_RecognitionSwift 'Openwork', 'Recognition'
	select @rc

					
AMENDMENT HISTORY				
=================								

Date		Author		Description
----		------		-----------
26/04/2018	A Groves	Only include rows in the OGS lookups where the OngoingServiceFee > 0.0.
						Negative OGS rates are bad data and at the time of writing, there are
						39 of these.
27/04/2018	A Groves	Additional calculation and condition to handle the scenario where BSC applies
						but the OGS Rate is less than the BSC rate. Previously, this caused the
						total ongoing to be zero. However, there are two components to ongoing VNB 
						points, the BSC share and the non-BSC share. So the BSC share (which takes 
						100% when the OGS rate is less than 0.12%) should still yield ongoing points.
27/04/2018	A Groves	Single ongoing Yr01 corrected by applying outer brackets before signing the result.
03/05/2018	A Groves	Added update of column "msit_OpenworkAdviserListing.VNB_Points".
18/05/2018	A Groves	Changed mortgage calculation to use e.AMOUNT_REC instead of pt.CommInitialAmount
						as Marcus Cossey wanted the actual amount received to be used for the DA.
04/06/2018	A Groves	1) In the REGULAR section of column "OngoingYr01", the condition for cs.FrequencyCode <> 6
							was added to ensure the code differentiates to the SINGLE section.
						2) Exclude MBF from the OpenAccess table (msit_OpenworkAdviserListing) as this
							is shown on the MBF download and would otherwise incur MBF double counting. 
*************************************************************************************************************/

CREATE PROCEDURE [dbo].[owp_RecognitionSwift_Backup20180606AG]
	@Client		varchar(50),
	@Module		Varchar(50)
AS

set nocount on

declare		@PhaseStart				varchar(50),
			@PhaseEnd				varchar(50),
			@PhaseError				varchar(50),
			@PhaseLog				varchar(50),
			@ProcName				varchar(100),
			@ProcessMessage			varchar(100),
			@RowCount				int,
			@OALRowCount			int,
			@ErrMsg					nvarchar(4000),
			@ErrMsgBrief			nvarchar(100),
			@ErrNum					int,
			@ErrSev					int,
			@ErrLine				int,
			@ErrState				int,
			@DateLastUpdated		datetime,
			@OwlManager2Code		nvarchar(10)
			
/****************************************************************************

	Set initial parameters																
																		
****************************************************************************/

set @ProcName			= object_name(@@procid)
set @PhaseStart			= 'START'
set @PhaseEnd			= 'END'
set @PhaseError			= 'ERROR'
set @PhaseLog			= 'LOG'
set @ErrNum				= 0	
set @DateLastUpdated	= getdate()

set @OwlManager2Code = (select cde.Code from msit_MIWarehouseCodesAndDescriptions cde
			where cde.ColumnName = 'Manager2Code' and cde.Description = 'Owl Financial')

-- We want this logging irrespective of whether or not there is a rollback
exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseStart, @ProcName, null, @Module, @Client

/****************************************************************************

	Populate the table																
																		
****************************************************************************/

SET XACT_ABORT ON	-- Needed if XACT_STATE() function is used.

BEGIN TRY

	/****************************************************************************

		Link OWS data to Swift data to enable the ongoing servicng (OGS) rate
		to be looked up.
																		
	****************************************************************************/
	
	select	distinct s.PersonID, swp.Client_Num, p.InternalProductID, swp.ProductCode 
	into	#SwiftOWSClientLink
	from	sa_ows_Sale s
			inner join sa_ows_Policies p on p.SaleID = s.SaleID
			inner join mstt_Policies swp on swp.PolicyRef = p.PolicyID
	where	s.DateSubmitted is not null
	--and		s.PersonID = 146030

	select @RowCount = @@rowcount
	set @ProcessMessage = '#SwiftOWSClientLink = ' + convert(nvarchar(10), @RowCount)
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseLog, @ProcessMessage, null, @Module, @Client

	-- The OGS rate is stored for the client/product combination
	select	link.Client_Num, link.ProductCode, max(ogs.OngoingServiceFee) as OngoingServiceFee
	into	#OGSLookUp
	from	#SwiftOWSClientLink link 
			inner join mstt_ProductHierarchy ph on ph.ProductCode = link.ProductCode
			inner join Submission.sa_ows_SubmittedProductCurrentOngoingServiceFee ogs
							on ogs.PersonID = link.PersonID
							and ogs.InternalProductID = (case when ph.RDRType = 'ONPLAT' 
															then -2 
															else link.InternalProductID 
														 end)
	where	ogs.OngoingServiceFee > 0.0							--AG 26/04/2018
	group	by 	link.Client_Num, link.ProductCode

	select @RowCount = @@rowcount
	set @ProcessMessage = '#OGSLookUp = ' + convert(nvarchar(10), @RowCount)
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseLog, @ProcessMessage, null, @Module, @Client

	create index idx_OGSLookUp on #OGSLookUp (Client_num, ProductCode)

	--This is an additional catch for OGS by storing the client's highest OGS
	--rate against their client number. This lookup will apply if the first
	--look up fails. The first lookup can fail, for example, if the case was 
	--not submitted on OWS i.e. the CaseID has a "17" prefix. 
	select	Client_Num, MAX(OngoingServiceFee) as OngoingServiceFee
	into	#OGSLookUpClient
	from	#OGSLookUp
	group	by Client_Num

	select @RowCount = @@rowcount
	set @ProcessMessage = '#OGSLookUpClient = ' + convert(nvarchar(10), @RowCount)
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseLog, @ProcessMessage, null, @Module, @Client
	
	create index idx_OGSLookUpClient on #OGSLookUpClient (Client_num)

	/****************************************************************************

		Calculate VNB and populate the temporary table with the results
		
		Note that there are oddities like LV protection payments which always
		come in pairs with one large and one much smaller amount (e.g. TransactionID 
		= 6684787.) The system treats both payments in the pair as first payments 
		and the (projected) DA associated with both is the same (because it's on 
		the policy transaction). 
		
		There is also a requirement to front-load VNB points on accrual and level
		payments. This means calculate the VNB for the full amount of the DA and 
		put it on the first payment record and then on all subsequent accrual and 
		level payments, set the VNB to zero.
		
		Thus two different sources of DA are used depending on whether we need the
		full DA amount for accruals and level or the actual amount received for all
		other scenarios including the LV split payment scenario. The two sources are:
		
		mstt_PolicyTransactions.CommInitialAmount - Full (projected) DA amount
		
		mstt_Expectation.AMOUNT_REC - The DA actually received. This handles the
										LV scenario whereby the AMOUNT_REC is 
										proportioned across the two payments received.   
																		
	****************************************************************************/

	select top 0 *, convert(int,NULL) as CommissionYear
	into #owt_Recognition
	from owt_Recognition

	insert into #owt_Recognition
	(
		SourceID,
		CaseID,
		TransactionID,
		Policy,
		ProductCode,
		BusinessCode,
		PointsTotal,
		BSC,
		MBF,
		Initial,
		OngoingTotal,
		OngoingYr01,
		OngoingYr02,
		OngoingYr03,
		OngoingYr04,
		OngoingYr05,
		OngoingYr06,
		OngoingYr07,
		OngoingYr08,
		OngoingYr09,
		OngoingYr10,
		FCARate,
		RetentionRate,
		RetentionRateBroker,
		OngoingServicingRate,
		OngoingServicingSource,
		DA,
		AmountReceived,
		Premium,
		AgentSplit,
		CommissionType,
		CommissionTypeDesc,
		Month,
		FrequencyCode,
		FrequencyDesc,
		RecognitionType,
		CalculationType,
		Source,
		DateInserted,
		DateLastUpdated,
		CommissionYear
	)
	select	cs.PendingPaymentID as SourceID,
			cs.CaseID,
			cs.TransactionID,
			cs.ExtPolicyNumber as Policy,
			cs.ProductCode,
			cs.BusinessCode,
			0.0 as PointsTotal,
			case
				when BSCpot.ID is not null then 
					--BSC takes the first 0.12 of the ongoing fee %. If the ongoing fee % is 0.12% or less, then 100% of the ongoing fee is allocated to BSC
					case when coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2)) - convert(decimal(8,4),sc.KeyValue2) >= 0.01
						then 
							case when cs.FrequencyCode = 2	--Monthly 
								then (cs.AgentSplit/100) * 12.0 * (isnull(cs.Premium,0)/2.0) * convert(decimal(8,4),sc.KeyValue3) * case when cs.INIssued < 0 then -1 else 1 end
								else (cs.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(cs.Premium,0) * convert(decimal(8,4),sc.KeyValue3) * case when cs.INIssued < 0 then -1 else 1 end
							end			
						else
							case when cs.FrequencyCode = 2	--Monthly 
								then (cs.AgentSplit/100) * 12.0 * (isnull(cs.Premium,0)/2.0) * coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2)) * case when cs.INIssued < 0 then -1 else 1 end
								else (cs.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(cs.Premium,0) * (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))/100.0) * case when cs.INIssued < 0 then -1 else 1 end
							end
					end
				else 0.0
			end as BSC,
			case 
				when mbf.MortgageFeeID is not null and cs.INIssued <> 0 then (((mbf.AdviceFeeAmount)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * MRbkr.FACTOR) - ((mbf.AdviceFeeAmount)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * Mfca.FACTOR)) --Note that mbf.AdviceFeeAmount is signed correctly - so no coding for signing is needed here
				else 0.0
			end as MBF,
			case 
				--When the adviser has changed, the AgentSplit can become zero in which case the ELITE points should be zero.
				when cs.AgentSplit = 0 then 0
				
				--WEALTH CALCULATION START
				--Indemnity payments or SINGLEs or IC Clawbacks or IC adjustments Start
				when (ph.ProductCategoryCode = 1 or pcc.KeyValue2 = '1') and (cs.FrequencyCode = 6 or cs.PayBasisCode in ('T') or cs.CommissionType in (2,17)) and cs.commissiontype in (1,2,17) and cs.INIssued <> 0 then (((e.AMOUNT_REC)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * Crate.FACTOR) - ((e.AMOUNT_REC)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * Cfca.FACTOR)) * case when cs.INIssued < 0 then -1 else 1 end
				--Indemnity payments or SINGLEs or IC Clawbacks or IC adjustments End
				--Accruals & Level Start
				when (ph.ProductCategoryCode = 1 or pcc.KeyValue2 = '1') and cs.INIssued <> 0 then (((pt.CommInitialAmount)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * Crate.FACTOR) - ((pt.CommInitialAmount)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * Cfca.FACTOR)) * case when cs.INIssued < 0 then -1 else 1 end
				--Accruals & Level End
				--WEALTH CALCULATION END
				
				--MORTGAGE CALCULATION START
				--Note: The MBF component has its own table column
				--Only 1 payment for mortgages
				when ph.ProductGroupCode = 3 and cs.INIssued <> 0 then (((e.AMOUNT_REC)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * MRproc.FACTOR) - ((e.AMOUNT_REC)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * Mfca.FACTOR)) * case when cs.INIssued < 0 then -1 else 1 end	--AG 18/05/2018
				--MORTGAGE CALCULATION END
				
				--PROTECTION CALCULATION START
				--Indemnity payments or SINGLEs or IC Clawbacks or IC adjustments Start
				when ph.ProductGroupCode = 6 and (cs.FrequencyCode = 6 or cs.PayBasisCode in ('T') or cs.CommissionType in (2,17)) and cs.commissiontype in (1,2,17) and cs.INIssued <> 0 then (((e.AMOUNT_REC)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * Prate.FACTOR) - ((e.AMOUNT_REC)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * Pfca.FACTOR)) * case when cs.INIssued < 0 then -1 else 1 end
				--Indemnity payments or SINGLEs or IC Clawbacks or IC adjustments End
				--Accruals & Level Start
				when ph.ProductGroupCode = 6 and cs.INIssued <> 0 then (((pt.CommInitialAmount)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * Prate.FACTOR) - ((pt.CommInitialAmount)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * Pfca.FACTOR)) * case when cs.INIssued < 0 then -1 else 1 end
				--Accruals & Level End
				--PROTECTION CALCULATION END

				else 0.0

			end as Initial,
			0.0 as OngoingTotal,
			case
				--WEALTH ONGOING CALCULATION START
				--When the adviser has changed, the AgentSplit can become zero in which case the ELITE points should be zero.
				when cs.AgentSplit = 0 then 0

				--SINGLE start
				--Calculate when BSC and ongoing applies (where ongoing rate is greater than BSC rate) 
				when (ph.ProductCategoryCode = 1 or pcc.KeyValue2 = '1') and cs.FrequencyCode = 6 and SFMpot.ID is not null and BSCpot.ID is not null and (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2)) - convert(decimal(8,4),sc.KeyValue2)) >= 0.01 then 
							--(AUM X BSC Rate)...
							((cs.AgentSplit/100) * (isnull(cs.Premium,0) * convert(decimal(8,4),sc.KeyValue3)) 
							--(AUM X OGS Rate X COB FCA Rate)...
							- ((cs.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(cs.Premium,0) * (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))/100.0) * Cfca.FACTOR)
							--(AUM X (OGS Rate - BSC Rate) X COB Retention Rate)...
							+ ((cs.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(cs.Premium,0) * ((coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))-convert(decimal(8,4),sc.KeyValue2))/100.0)) * Crate.FACTOR) 
							--Sign correctly for +ve or clawback payment
							* (case when cs.INIssued < 0 then -1 else 1 end)
				--Calculate when BSC and ongoing applies (where ongoing rate less than BSC rate, then BSC gets all the ongoing available) 
				when (ph.ProductCategoryCode = 1 or pcc.KeyValue2 = '1') and cs.FrequencyCode = 6 and SFMpot.ID is not null and BSCpot.ID is not null then
							--(AUM X BSC Rate)...(in this scenario it's all of the OGS rate)
							((cs.AgentSplit/100) * (isnull(cs.Premium,0) * (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))/100.0)) 
							--(AUM X OGS Rate X COB FCA Rate)...
							- ((cs.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(cs.Premium,0) * (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))/100.0) * Cfca.FACTOR)
							--(AUM X (OGS Rate - BSC Rate) X COB Retention Rate)...
							+ (0.0)) --BSC got it all, so this part of the calculation is zero
							--Sign correctly for +ve or clawback payment
							* (case when cs.INIssued < 0 then -1 else 1 end)
				--Calculate when no BSC applies and ongoing applies
				when (ph.ProductCategoryCode = 1 or pcc.KeyValue2 = '1') and cs.FrequencyCode = 6 and SFMpot.ID is not null and BSCpot.ID is null then 
							--(AUM X OGS Rate X COB Retention Rate)...
							(((cs.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(cs.Premium,0) * (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))/100.0) * Crate.FACTOR) 
							--(AUM X OGS Rate X COB FCA Rate)...
							- ((cs.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(cs.Premium,0) * (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))/100.0) * Cfca.FACTOR))
							--Sign correctly for +ve or clawback payment
							* (case when cs.INIssued < 0 then -1 else 1 end)
				--SINGLE end
				
				--REGULAR start
				--Calculate when BSC and ongoing applies (where ongoing rate is greater than BSC rate) 
				when (ph.ProductCategoryCode = 1 or pcc.KeyValue2 = '1') and cs.FrequencyCode <> 6 and SFMpot.ID is not null and BSCpot.ID is not null and (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2)) - convert(decimal(8,4),sc.KeyValue2)) >= 0.01 then		--AG 04/06/2018 (1)
							--The non-BSC portion (Ave AUM X (OGS Rate - BSC Rate) X COB Retention Rate)...
							((((((cs.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(cs.Premium,0) * (case when cs.FrequencyCode = 2 then 12 else 1 end))/2.0) * (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2)) - convert(decimal(8,4),sc.KeyValue2))/100.0)) * Crate.FACTOR
							--The BSC portion (Ave AUM X BSC Rate)...
							+ case when cs.FrequencyCode = 2	--Monthly 
									then (cs.AgentSplit/100) * 12.0 * (isnull(cs.Premium,0)/2.0) * convert(decimal(8,4),sc.KeyValue3) 
									else (cs.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(cs.Premium,0) * convert(decimal(8,4),sc.KeyValue3) 
							  end
							--FCA Charge (Ave AUM X OGS Rate X FCA Rate)...
							- (case when cs.FrequencyCode = 2	--Monthly 
									then (cs.AgentSplit/100) * 12.0 * (isnull(cs.Premium,0)/2.0) 
									else (cs.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(cs.Premium,0) 
							   end * (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))/100.0) * Cfca.FACTOR))
							--Sign correctly for +ve or clawback payment
							* (case when cs.INIssued < 0 then -1 else 1 end)   
				--Calculate when BSC and ongoing applies (where ongoing rate less than BSC rate, then BSC gets all the ongoing available) 
				when (ph.ProductCategoryCode = 1 or pcc.KeyValue2 = '1') and cs.FrequencyCode <> 6 and SFMpot.ID is not null and BSCpot.ID is not null then		--AG 04/06/2018 (1)
							--The non-BSC portion (Ave AUM X (OGS Rate - BSC Rate) X COB Retention Rate)...
							((0/0)	--BSC got it all, so this part of the calculation is zero
							--The BSC portion (Ave AUM X BSC Rate)...(in this scenario it's all of the OGS rate)
							+ case when cs.FrequencyCode = 2	--Monthly 
									then (cs.AgentSplit/100) * 12.0 * (isnull(cs.Premium,0)/2.0) * (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))/100.0) 
									else (cs.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(cs.Premium,0) * (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))/100.0) 
							  end
							--FCA Charge (Ave AUM X OGS Rate X FCA Rate)...
							- (case when cs.FrequencyCode = 2	--Monthly 
									then (cs.AgentSplit/100) * 12.0 * (isnull(cs.Premium,0)/2.0) 
									else (cs.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(cs.Premium,0) 
							   end * (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))/100.0) * Cfca.FACTOR))
							--Sign correctly for +ve or clawback payment
							* (case when cs.INIssued < 0 then -1 else 1 end)   
				--Calculate when no BSC applies, but ongoing servicing applies
				when (ph.ProductCategoryCode = 1 or pcc.KeyValue2 = '1') and cs.FrequencyCode <> 6 and SFMpot.ID is not null and BSCpot.ID is null then		--AG 04/06/2018	(1)
							--(Ave AUM X OGS Rate X COB Retention Rate)...
							(((((cs.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(cs.Premium,0) * (case when cs.FrequencyCode = 2 then 12 else 1 end))/2.0) * (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))/100.0) * Crate.FACTOR) 
							--(Ave AUM X OGS Rate X COB FCA Rate)...
							- ((((cs.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(cs.Premium,0) * (case when cs.FrequencyCode = 2 then 12 else 1 end))/2.0) * (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))/100.0) * Cfca.FACTOR))
							--Sign correctly for +ve or clawback payment
							* (case when cs.INIssued < 0 then -1 else 1 end)   
				--REGULAR end
				
				else 0.0

				--WEALTH ONGOING CALCULATION END
			end as OngoingYr01,
			0.0 as OngoingYr02,
			0.0 as OngoingYr03,
			0.0 as OngoingYr04,
			0.0 as OngoingYr05,
			0.0 as OngoingYr06,
			0.0 as OngoingYr07,
			0.0 as OngoingYr08,
			0.0 as OngoingYr09,
			0.0 as OngoingYr10,
			case 
				when (ph.ProductCategoryCode = 1 or pcc.KeyValue2 = '1') then Cfca.FACTOR*100.0		--COB
				when ph.ProductGroupCode = 3 then Mfca.FACTOR*100.0		--MORT
				when ph.ProductGroupCode = 6 then Pfca.FACTOR*100.0		--PROT
				else 0.0
			end as FCARate,
			case 
				when (ph.ProductCategoryCode = 1 or pcc.KeyValue2 = '1') then Crate.FACTOR*100.0	--COB
				when ph.ProductGroupCode = 3 then MRproc.FACTOR*100.0	--MORT
				when ph.ProductGroupCode = 6 then Prate.FACTOR*100.0	--PROT
				else 0.0
			end as RetentionRate,
			case 
				when mbf.MortgageFeeID is not null then  MRbkr.FACTOR*100.0	
				else 0.0
			end as RetentionRateBroker,
			case when SFMpot.ID is not null
				then coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))
				else null
			end as OngoingServicingRate,
			case when SFMpot.ID is not null
				then case 
						when ogs.OngoingServiceFee is null and ogscli.OngoingServiceFee is null 
							then case
								when ogsdflt.KeyValue = 'ONPLAT' then 'Default - On Plat'
								else 'Default - Off Plat'
							end
						when ogs.OngoingServiceFee is not null then 'Client Product'
						when ogscli.OngoingServiceFee is not null then 'Client Only'
						else 'Unknown'
					 end
				else case when (ph.ProductCategoryCode = 1 or pcc.KeyValue2 = '1')
						then 'No OGS'					--WEALTH, but no OGS
						else null						--Not WEALTH, so OGS is n/a and is therefore null
					 end
			end as OngoingServicingSource,
			pt.CommInitialAmount as DA,
			e.AMOUNT_REC as AmountReceived,
			cs.Premium,
			cs.AgentSplit,
			cs.CommissionType,
			left(cs.StandingOrderDesc,50) as CommissionTypeDesc,
			cs.Month,
			cs.FrequencyCode,
			cs.FrequencyDesc,
			'VNB' as RecognitionType,
			case 
				when (ph.ProductCategoryCode = 1 or pcc.KeyValue2 = '1') then 'WEALTH'
				when ph.ProductGroupCode = 3 then 'MORTGAGE'
				when ph.ProductGroupCode = 6 then 'PROTECTION'
				else null
			end as CalculationType,
			'Openwork 2006' as Source,
			@DateLastUpdated as DateInserted,
			@DateLastUpdated as DateLastUpdated,
			csp.year as CommissionYear
	--select count(*)
	from	msit_CommissionStatement cs
/*			inner join (select	distinct PKID
						from	owt_TransformationMovements tm 
						where	tm.DriverTableName = 'sa_swift_S_AGMFIL'
						and		tm.CommissionStatement = 'Y') tm on tm.PKID = cs.PendingPaymentID
*/			inner join mstt_Agents ag on ag.Code = cs.BusinessCode
			inner join mstt_PolicyTransactions pt on pt.ID = cs.TransactionID
			inner join mstt_Policies p on p.POL_NUM = pt.PolicyID
			inner join msit_CommissionStatementPeriods VNBStart on convert(date,pt.CreateDateTime) between VNBStart.PeriodStartDate and VNBStart.PeriodEndDate
			inner join msit_Commissionstatementperiods csp on csp.month = cs.month
			inner join mstt_ProductHierarchy ph on ph.productcode = cs.productcode
			inner join mstt_Expectation e on e.ID = cs.ExpectationID
			left join dbo.owt_MortgageBrokerFees mbf on mbf.PendingPaymentID = cs.PendingPaymentID and mbf.AdviceFeeCharged = 'Yes'
			left join owt_SelectionControl SC
						on SC.Process = 'ElitePoints' 
						and SC.KeyType = 'NSCPotCode' 
						and cs.CreateDate between SC.EffectiveStartDate and SC.EffectiveEndDate
			left join mstt_Commissions BSCpot
						on BSCpot.TransactionID = cs.TransactionID 
						and BSCpot.Agent_Code = sc.KeyValue
						and BSCpot.CommissionType = 10
			left join owt_SelectionControl SFMPC						
						on SFMPC.Process = 'ElitePoints' 
						and SFMPC.KeyType = 'ServicingFeeMarginPotCode' 
						and cs.CreateDate between SFMPC.EffectiveStartDate and SFMPC.EffectiveEndDate
			left join mstt_Commissions SFMpot							
						on SFMpot.TransactionID = cs.TransactionID 
						and SFMpot.Agent_Code = SFMPC.KeyValue
						and SFMpot.CommissionType = 10	
			left join owt_SelectionControl pcc 
						on pcc.Process = 'ElitePoints'
						and pcc.KeyType = 'ProductCategoryCode'
						and pcc.KeyValue = cs.ProductCode	
						and cs.CreateDate between pcc.EffectiveStartDate and pcc.EffectiveEndDate
			left join owt_SelectionControl ogsdflt 
						on ogsdflt.Process = 'ElitePoints'
						and ogsdflt.KeyType = 'DefaultOngoingServicingRate'
						and ogsdflt.SelectionType = 'VNB'
						and ogsdflt.KeyValue = case when ph.RDRType = 'ONPLAT' then 'ONPLAT' else 'OFPLAT' end
						and cs.CreateDate between ogsdflt.EffectiveStartDate and ogsdflt.EffectiveEndDate
			left join owt_EliteFactors Cfca on Cfca.FeeType = 'VNB' and Cfca.category = 'COB-FCA-RATE' and csp.year between Cfca.StartYear and Cfca.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors Crate on Crate.FeeType = 'VNB' and Crate.category = 'COB-RETENTION-RATE' and csp.year between Crate.StartYear and Crate.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors Mfca on Mfca.FeeType = 'VNB' and Mfca.category = 'MORT-FCA-RATE' and csp.year between Mfca.StartYear and Mfca.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors MRproc on MRproc.FeeType = 'VNB' and MRproc.category = 'MORT-RETENTION-RATE-PROC' and csp.year between MRproc.StartYear and MRproc.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors MRbkr on MRbkr.FeeType = 'VNB' and MRbkr.category = 'MORT-RETENTION-RATE-BROKER' and csp.year between MRbkr.StartYear and MRbkr.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors Pfca on Pfca.FeeType = 'VNB' and Pfca.category = 'PROT-FCA-RATE' and csp.year between Pfca.StartYear and Pfca.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors Prate on Prate.FeeType = 'VNB' and Prate.category = 'PROT-RETENTION-RATE' and csp.year between Prate.StartYear and Prate.EndYear 
			left join #OGSLookUp ogs on ogs.CLIENT_NUM = cs.ClientID and ogs.ProductCode = cs.ProductCode
			left join #OGSLookUpClient ogscli on ogscli.CLIENT_NUM = cs.ClientID 
	where	cs.ReportingClassCode = 1
	and		ag.Manager2Code <> @OwlManager2Code		--Exclude Owl
	and		cs.INIssued <> 0
	and		VNBStart.Year >= 2017			--VNB to start from 2017
	and		csp.Year >= 2017				--Ensure in-scope payments are consistent with VNB start

	select @RowCount = @@rowcount
	set @ProcessMessage = '#owt_Recognition = ' + convert(nvarchar(10), @RowCount)
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseLog, @ProcessMessage, null, @Module, @Client
	
	/****************************************************************************

		Now calculate the ongoing spread for each of 10 years.
		Note that regular payments get an additional multiplier to uplift the 
		average AUM for each year.
																		
	****************************************************************************/

	update r
		set OngoingYr02 = case when r.FrequencyCode = 2							--Monthly
							then r.OngoingYr01 * YR02.Multiplier * YR02.Factor	--Regular
							else r.OngoingYr01 * YR02.Factor					--Single
						  end,
			OngoingYr03 = case when r.FrequencyCode = 2							--Monthly
							then r.OngoingYr01 * YR03.Multiplier * YR03.Factor	--Regular
							else r.OngoingYr01 * YR03.Factor					--Single
						  end,
			OngoingYr04 = case when r.FrequencyCode = 2							--Monthly
							then r.OngoingYr01 * YR04.Multiplier * YR04.Factor	--Regular
							else r.OngoingYr01 * YR04.Factor					--Single
						  end,
			OngoingYr05 = case when r.FrequencyCode = 2							--Monthly 
							then r.OngoingYr01 * YR05.Multiplier * YR05.Factor	--Regular
							else r.OngoingYr01 * YR05.Factor					--Single
						  end,
			OngoingYr06 = case when r.FrequencyCode = 2							--Monthly 
							then r.OngoingYr01 * YR06.Multiplier * YR06.Factor	--Regular
							else r.OngoingYr01 * YR06.Factor					--Single
						  end,
			OngoingYr07 = case when r.FrequencyCode = 2							--Monthly 
							then r.OngoingYr01 * YR07.Multiplier * YR07.Factor	--Regular
							else r.OngoingYr01 * YR07.Factor					--Single
						  end,
			OngoingYr08 = case when r.FrequencyCode = 2							--Monthly 
							then r.OngoingYr01 * YR08.Multiplier * YR08.Factor	--Regular
							else r.OngoingYr01 * YR08.Factor					--Single
						  end,
			OngoingYr09 = case when r.FrequencyCode = 2							--Monthly 
							then r.OngoingYr01 * YR09.Multiplier * YR09.Factor	--Regular
							else r.OngoingYr01 * YR09.Factor					--Single
						  end,
			OngoingYr10 = case when r.FrequencyCode = 2							--Monthly 
							then r.OngoingYr01 * YR10.Multiplier * YR10.Factor	--Regular
							else r.OngoingYr01 * YR10.Factor					--Single
						   end
	from	#owt_Recognition r
			left join owt_EliteFactors YR01 on YR01.FeeType = 'VNB' and YR01.Category = 'COB-ONGOING-DISCOUNT-YR01' and r.CommissionYear between YR01.StartYear and YR01.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors YR02 on YR02.FeeType = 'VNB' and YR02.Category = 'COB-ONGOING-DISCOUNT-YR02' and r.CommissionYear between YR02.StartYear and YR02.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors YR03 on YR03.FeeType = 'VNB' and YR03.Category = 'COB-ONGOING-DISCOUNT-YR03' and r.CommissionYear between YR03.StartYear and YR03.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors YR04 on YR04.FeeType = 'VNB' and YR04.Category = 'COB-ONGOING-DISCOUNT-YR04' and r.CommissionYear between YR04.StartYear and YR04.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors YR05 on YR05.FeeType = 'VNB' and YR05.Category = 'COB-ONGOING-DISCOUNT-YR05' and r.CommissionYear between YR05.StartYear and YR05.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors YR06 on YR06.FeeType = 'VNB' and YR06.Category = 'COB-ONGOING-DISCOUNT-YR06' and r.CommissionYear between YR06.StartYear and YR06.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors YR07 on YR07.FeeType = 'VNB' and YR07.Category = 'COB-ONGOING-DISCOUNT-YR07' and r.CommissionYear between YR07.StartYear and YR07.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors YR08 on YR08.FeeType = 'VNB' and YR08.Category = 'COB-ONGOING-DISCOUNT-YR08' and r.CommissionYear between YR08.StartYear and YR08.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors YR09 on YR09.FeeType = 'VNB' and YR09.Category = 'COB-ONGOING-DISCOUNT-YR09' and r.CommissionYear between YR09.StartYear and YR09.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors YR10 on YR10.FeeType = 'VNB' and YR10.Category = 'COB-ONGOING-DISCOUNT-YR10' and r.CommissionYear between YR10.StartYear and YR10.EndYear 

	select @RowCount = @@rowcount
	set @ProcessMessage = '#owt_Recognition (ongoing) = ' + convert(nvarchar(10), @RowCount)
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseLog, @ProcessMessage, null, @Module, @Client

	/****************************************************************************

		Now add up all the numbers
																		
	****************************************************************************/
	
	update r
		set OngoingTotal	=	OngoingYr01 + OngoingYr02 + OngoingYr03 + OngoingYr04 + OngoingYr05 +
								OngoingYr06 + OngoingYr07 + OngoingYr08 + OngoingYr09 + OngoingYr10,
			PointsTotal		=	OngoingYr01 + OngoingYr02 + OngoingYr03 + OngoingYr04 + OngoingYr05 +
								OngoingYr06 + OngoingYr07 + OngoingYr08 + OngoingYr09 + OngoingYr10 +
								Initial + MBF	-- Note BSC is already included in the Ongoing, so don't include it in the Points Total.
	from	#owt_Recognition r

	select @RowCount = @@rowcount
	set @ProcessMessage = '#owt_Recognition (totals) = ' + convert(nvarchar(10), @RowCount)
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseLog, @ProcessMessage, null, @Module, @Client

	/****************************************************************************

		Merge the temporary table into the permanent table
																		
	****************************************************************************/

	BEGIN TRANSACTION

	declare @SummaryOfChanges table (Change varchar(20))
	merge	dbo.owt_Recognition as trg
	using	#owt_Recognition as src
	on		trg.SourceID = src.SourceID
	and		trg.Source = src.Source
	when	matched 
	and		isnull(trg.PointsTotal,0) <> isnull(src.PointsTotal,0)
	then	update 
				set trg.CaseID = src.CaseID,
					trg.TransactionID = src.TransactionID,
					trg.Policy = src.Policy,
					trg.ProductCode = src.ProductCode,
					trg.BusinessCode = src.BusinessCode,
					trg.PointsTotal = src.PointsTotal,
					trg.BSC = src.BSC,
					trg.MBF = src.MBF,
					trg.Initial = src.Initial,
					trg.OngoingTotal = src.OngoingTotal,
					trg.OngoingYr01 = src.OngoingYr01,
					trg.OngoingYr02 = src.OngoingYr02,
					trg.OngoingYr03 = src.OngoingYr03,
					trg.OngoingYr04 = src.OngoingYr04,
					trg.OngoingYr05 = src.OngoingYr05,
					trg.OngoingYr06 = src.OngoingYr06,
					trg.OngoingYr07 = src.OngoingYr07,
					trg.OngoingYr08 = src.OngoingYr08,
					trg.OngoingYr09 = src.OngoingYr09,
					trg.OngoingYr10 = src.OngoingYr10,
					trg.FCARate = src.FCARate,
					trg.RetentionRate = src.RetentionRate,
					trg.RetentionRateBroker = src.RetentionRateBroker,
					trg.OngoingServicingRate = src.OngoingServicingRate,
					trg.OngoingServicingSource = src.OngoingServicingSource,
					trg.DA = src.DA,
					trg.AmountReceived = src.AmountReceived,
					trg.Premium = src.Premium,
					trg.AgentSplit = src.AgentSplit,
					trg.CommissionType = src.CommissionType,
					trg.CommissionTypeDesc = src.CommissionTypeDesc,
					trg.Month = src.Month,
					trg.FrequencyCode = src.FrequencyCode,
					trg.FrequencyDesc = src.FrequencyDesc,
					trg.RecognitionType = src.RecognitionType,
					trg.CalculationType = src.CalculationType,
					trg.DateLastUpdated = @DateLastUpdated
	when	not matched by target 
	then	insert
			(
				SourceID,
				CaseID,
				TransactionID,
				Policy,
				ProductCode,
				BusinessCode,
				PointsTotal,
				BSC,
				MBF,
				Initial,
				OngoingTotal,
				OngoingYr01,
				OngoingYr02,
				OngoingYr03,
				OngoingYr04,
				OngoingYr05,
				OngoingYr06,
				OngoingYr07,
				OngoingYr08,
				OngoingYr09,
				OngoingYr10,
				FCARate,
				RetentionRate,
				RetentionRateBroker,
				OngoingServicingRate,
				OngoingServicingSource,
				DA,
				AmountReceived,
				Premium,
				AgentSplit,
				CommissionType,
				CommissionTypeDesc,
				Month,
				FrequencyCode,
				FrequencyDesc,
				RecognitionType,
				CalculationType,
				Source,
				DateInserted,
				DateLastUpdated
			)		
			values
			(
				src.SourceID,
				src.CaseID,
				src.TransactionID,
				src.Policy,
				src.ProductCode,
				src.BusinessCode,
				src.PointsTotal,
				src.BSC,
				src.MBF,
				src.Initial,
				src.OngoingTotal,
				src.OngoingYr01,
				src.OngoingYr02,
				src.OngoingYr03,
				src.OngoingYr04,
				src.OngoingYr05,
				src.OngoingYr06,
				src.OngoingYr07,
				src.OngoingYr08,
				src.OngoingYr09,
				src.OngoingYr10,
				src.FCARate,
				src.RetentionRate,
				src.RetentionRateBroker,
				src.OngoingServicingRate,
				src.OngoingServicingSource,
				src.DA,
				src.AmountReceived,
				src.Premium,
				src.AgentSplit,
				src.CommissionType,
				src.CommissionTypeDesc,
				src.Month,
				src.FrequencyCode,
				src.FrequencyDesc,
				src.RecognitionType,
				src.CalculationType,
				src.Source,
				src.DateInserted,
				src.DateLastUpdated)				--Merge statements must have a ;
	output $action into @SummaryOfChanges;
/*	
	--Do not include MBF in the OpenAccess Commission Listing as it is on the MBF download
	--and we don't want MBF double counting.
	update	oal
		set VNB_Points = r.PointsTotal - r.MBF		--AG 04/06/2018 (2)
	from	msit_CommissionStatement cs
			inner join (select	distinct PKID
						from	owt_TransformationMovements tm 
						where	tm.DriverTableName = 'sa_swift_S_AGMFIL'
						and		tm.CommissionStatement = 'Y') tm on tm.PKID = cs.PendingPaymentID
			inner join msit_OpenworkAdviserListing oal on oal.SourceID = cs.ID and oal.Source = 'Openwork 2006'
			inner join owt_Recognition r 
						on r.RecognitionType = 'VNB'
						and r.SourceID = cs.PendingPaymentID
						and r.Source = oal.Source
	--where	isnull(oal.VNB_Points,0) <> isnull(r.PointsTotal,0)
	
	select @OALRowCount = @@rowcount
*/
	COMMIT TRANSACTION      

	select	@RowCount = COUNT(*)
	from	@SummaryOfChanges
	where	Change = 'INSERT'

	set @ProcessMessage = 'owt_Recognition (insert) = ' + convert(nvarchar(10), @RowCount)
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseLog, @ProcessMessage, null, @Module, @Client

	select	@RowCount = COUNT(*)
	from	@SummaryOfChanges
	where	Change = 'UPDATE'

	set @ProcessMessage = 'owt_Recognition (update) = ' + convert(nvarchar(10), @RowCount)
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseLog, @ProcessMessage, null, @Module, @Client
/*
	set @ProcessMessage = 'msit_OpenworkAdviserListing (update) = ' + convert(nvarchar(10), @OALRowCount)
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseLog, @ProcessMessage, null, @Module, @Client
*/
	/****************************************************************************

		T H E   E N D
																		
	****************************************************************************/
	
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseEnd, @ProcName, null, @Module, @Client

END TRY

BEGIN CATCH 

	select @ErrNum = ERROR_NUMBER(), @ErrMsg = ERROR_MESSAGE(), @ErrSev = ERROR_SEVERITY(), @ErrLine = ERROR_LINE(), @ErrState = XACT_STATE()
	set @ErrMsg = REPLACE(@ErrMsg, '.', '') + ' (error no: ' + CAST(@ErrNum AS VARCHAR(10)) + ') on line ' + CAST(@ErrLine AS VARCHAR(10))
	
	-- Test XACT_STATE for 0, 1, or -1.
    -- If 1, the transaction is committable.
    -- If -1, the transaction is uncommittable and should be rolled back.
    -- If 0, there is no transaction and a commit or rollback operation would generate an error.

	if @ErrState = -1			-- Transaction is uncommitable
		rollback transaction

	if @ErrState = 1			
		commit transaction

	-- Error message line 1
	set @ErrMsgBrief = left(@ErrMsg,100)
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseError, @ErrMsgBrief, null, @Module, @Client
	
	-- Error message line 2 - if any text exists
	set @ErrMsgBrief = substring(@ErrMsg,101,100)
	if len(@ErrMsgBrief) > 0
		exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseError, @ErrMsgBrief, null, @Module, @Client

	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseEnd, @ProcName, null, @Module, @Client

	RAISERROR(@ErrMsg, @ErrSev , 1)

END CATCH

/****************************************************************************

			E N D															

****************************************************************************/

return @ErrNum



GO
/****** Object:  StoredProcedure [dbo].[owp_RecognitionSwift_Backup20180611AG]    Script Date: 7/3/2026 3:44:25 PM ******/
SET ANSI_NULLS ON
GO
SET QUOTED_IDENTIFIER ON
GO
/*********************************************************************************************************

Program:		owp_RecognitionSwift					
Author:			Alan Groves
Date created:	11/04/2018
											
Description:
===========

This proc populates the new recognition table called "owt_Recognition" with "Value of New Business"
(VNB) points.

This proc handles all of the swift data which includes:
WEALTH - COB business i.e. pensions and investments
MORTGAGES
PROTECTION

Note: There is a separate proc that calculates the GI VNB points from the Paymentshield data.

The approach of this proc is to use the incremental PendingPaymentIDs from the overnight batch
to calculate the VNB points in a temporary table.

The temporary table is then merged with the permanent table to make the calculated (or
re-calculated values) permanent.

Terms
-----
BSC			- Business Service Charge.
MBF			- Mortgage Broker Fee.
OGS			- Ongoing Servicing.
BSC Rate	- 0.12% at the time of writing (24/04/2018). This could be changed by the business, but
				would also require some DEV work in OWS.
DF			- Discount Factor.
DA			- Distribution Allowance (the total amount paid out by the provider to Openwork)
AUM			- Assets Under Management. Basically the amount invested or the premium on investment
				cases.
Average AUM - Average amount invested annually which is equivalent to 6 months' premium.

THE CALCULATIONS
================

There are two potential parts: initial + ongoing (if ongoing applies). If BSC (applies to ongoing 
only) and MBF (applies to mortgages only) apply, then these are also included:

MORTGAGE
--------
Part 1: MBF column = (Advice Fee Amount X Broker Retention Rate) - (Advice Fee Amount X Mort FCA Rate)
Part 2: Initial column = (Proc Fee Amount X Mortgage Retention Rate) - (Proc Fee X Mort FCA Rate) 
Mortgage Points Total = Initial + MBF

PROTECTION
----------
= (DA X Protection Retention Rate) - (DA X Protection FCA Rate) 
Protection Points Total = Initial

WEALTH (COB i.e. pensions and investments)
------
Part 1: Initial column = (DA X Wealth Retention Rate) - (DA X Wealth FCA Rate)

Part 2:

****XXXX****

NOTE: Where the BSC rate is greater than the ongoing rate, then BSC gets ALL of the AVAILABLE 
ongoing.

****XXXX****

REGULAR - BSC applies:
Year 1 column = BSC Points + Non-BSC Points - FCA Points
Non-BSC Points = Ave AUM X (OGS Rate - BSC Rate) X COB Retention Rate
BSC Points = Ave AUM X BSC Rate
FCA Points = Ave AUM X OGS Rate X COB FCA Rate

REGULAR - Non-BSC: 
Year 1 column = (Ave AUM X OGS Rate X COB Retention Rate) - (Ave AUM X OGS Rate X COB FCA Rate)

SINGLE - BSC applies:
Year 1 column = (AUM X BSC Rate) + (AUM X (OGS Rate - BSC Rate) X COB Retention Rate) - (AUM X OGS Rate X COB FCA Rate) 

SINGLE - Non-BSC:
Year 1 column = (AUM X OGS Rate X COB Retention Rate) - (AUM X OGS Rate X COB FCA Rate) 

Then years 2 to 10 are calculated by applying a discount factor
Year  2 = Year 1 X  3 X DF
Year  3 = Year 1 X  5 X DF
Year  4 = Year 1 X  7 X DF
Year  5 = Year 1 X  9 X DF
Year  6 = Year 1 X 11 X DF
Year  7 = Year 1 X 13 X DF
Year  8 = Year 1 X 15 X DF
Year  9 = Year 1 X 17 X DF
Year 10 = Year 1 X 19 X DF

Wealth Points Total =	OngoingYr01 + OngoingYr02 + OngoingYr03 + OngoingYr04 + OngoingYr05 +
						OngoingYr06 + OngoingYr07 + OngoingYr08 + OngoingYr09 + OngoingYr10 +
						Initial

GI
--
See stored proc "owp_RecognitionGIPaymentshield".
 
Notes:
-----

There is a BSC column on table owt_Recognition. However, BSC is already included in the ongoing
years 1 - 10, so the BSC column does not need to be added in. In fact you will double count if 
you attempt to do anything with it other than display it.


This proc is called as follows:
	declare @rc int
	exec @rc = dbo.owp_RecognitionSwift 'Openwork', 'Recognition'
	select @rc

					
AMENDMENT HISTORY				
=================								

Date		Author		Description
----		------		-----------
26/04/2018	A Groves	Only include rows in the OGS lookups where the OngoingServiceFee > 0.0.
						Negative OGS rates are bad data and at the time of writing, there are
						39 of these.
27/04/2018	A Groves	Additional calculation and condition to handle the scenario where BSC applies
						but the OGS Rate is less than the BSC rate. Previously, this caused the
						total ongoing to be zero. However, there are two components to ongoing VNB 
						points, the BSC share and the non-BSC share. So the BSC share (which takes 
						100% when the OGS rate is less than 0.12%) should still yield ongoing points.
27/04/2018	A Groves	Single ongoing Yr01 corrected by applying outer brackets before signing the result.
03/05/2018	A Groves	Added update of column "msit_OpenworkAdviserListing.VNB_Points".
18/05/2018	A Groves	Changed mortgage calculation to use e.AMOUNT_REC instead of pt.CommInitialAmount
						as Marcus Cossey wanted the actual amount received to be used for the DA.
04/06/2018	A Groves	1) In the REGULAR section of column "OngoingYr01", the condition for cs.FrequencyCode <> 6
							was added to ensure the code differentiates to the SINGLE section.
						2) Exclude MBF from the OpenAccess table (msit_OpenworkAdviserListing) as this
							is shown on the MBF download and would otherwise incur MBF double counting.
05/06/2018	A Groves	1) Marcus Cossey advised that investments should get ongoing for years 1 to 6 and
							pensions for years 1 to 10. Previously, both lines of business got years 1 to 10.
						2) Marcus Cossey asked for split payments (i.e. where multiple cheques are processed
							for a SINGLE investment) to only claculate ongoing VNB on the oldest payment. 
*************************************************************************************************************/

CREATE PROCEDURE [dbo].[owp_RecognitionSwift_Backup20180611AG]
	@Client		varchar(50),
	@Module		Varchar(50)
AS

set nocount on

declare		@PhaseStart				varchar(50),
			@PhaseEnd				varchar(50),
			@PhaseError				varchar(50),
			@PhaseLog				varchar(50),
			@ProcName				varchar(100),
			@ProcessMessage			varchar(100),
			@RowCount				int,
			@OALRowCount			int,
			@ErrMsg					nvarchar(4000),
			@ErrMsgBrief			nvarchar(100),
			@ErrNum					int,
			@ErrSev					int,
			@ErrLine				int,
			@ErrState				int,
			@DateLastUpdated		datetime,
			@OwlManager2Code		nvarchar(10)
			
/****************************************************************************

	Set initial parameters																
																		
****************************************************************************/

set @ProcName			= object_name(@@procid)
set @PhaseStart			= 'START'
set @PhaseEnd			= 'END'
set @PhaseError			= 'ERROR'
set @PhaseLog			= 'LOG'
set @ErrNum				= 0	
set @DateLastUpdated	= getdate()

set @OwlManager2Code = (select cde.Code from msit_MIWarehouseCodesAndDescriptions cde
			where cde.ColumnName = 'Manager2Code' and cde.Description = 'Owl Financial')

-- We want this logging irrespective of whether or not there is a rollback
exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseStart, @ProcName, null, @Module, @Client

/****************************************************************************

	Populate the table																
																		
****************************************************************************/

SET XACT_ABORT ON	-- Needed if XACT_STATE() function is used.

BEGIN TRY

	/****************************************************************************

		Link OWS data to Swift data to enable the ongoing servicng (OGS) rate
		to be looked up.
																		
	****************************************************************************/
	
	select	distinct s.PersonID, swp.Client_Num, p.InternalProductID, swp.ProductCode 
	into	#SwiftOWSClientLink
	from	sa_ows_Sale s
			inner join sa_ows_Policies p on p.SaleID = s.SaleID
			inner join mstt_Policies swp on swp.PolicyRef = p.PolicyID
	where	s.DateSubmitted is not null
	--and		s.PersonID = 146030

	select @RowCount = @@rowcount
	set @ProcessMessage = '#SwiftOWSClientLink = ' + convert(nvarchar(10), @RowCount)
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseLog, @ProcessMessage, null, @Module, @Client

	-- The OGS rate is stored for the client/product combination
	select	link.Client_Num, link.ProductCode, max(ogs.OngoingServiceFee) as OngoingServiceFee
	into	#OGSLookUp
	from	#SwiftOWSClientLink link 
			inner join mstt_ProductHierarchy ph on ph.ProductCode = link.ProductCode
			inner join Submission.sa_ows_SubmittedProductCurrentOngoingServiceFee ogs
							on ogs.PersonID = link.PersonID
							and ogs.InternalProductID = (case when ph.RDRType = 'ONPLAT' 
															then -2 
															else link.InternalProductID 
														 end)
	where	ogs.OngoingServiceFee > 0.0							--AG 26/04/2018
	group	by 	link.Client_Num, link.ProductCode

	select @RowCount = @@rowcount
	set @ProcessMessage = '#OGSLookUp = ' + convert(nvarchar(10), @RowCount)
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseLog, @ProcessMessage, null, @Module, @Client

	create index idx_OGSLookUp on #OGSLookUp (Client_num, ProductCode)

	--This is an additional catch for OGS by storing the client's highest OGS
	--rate against their client number. This lookup will apply if the first
	--look up fails. The first lookup can fail, for example, if the case was 
	--not submitted on OWS i.e. the CaseID has a "17" prefix. 
	select	Client_Num, MAX(OngoingServiceFee) as OngoingServiceFee
	into	#OGSLookUpClient
	from	#OGSLookUp
	group	by Client_Num

	select @RowCount = @@rowcount
	set @ProcessMessage = '#OGSLookUpClient = ' + convert(nvarchar(10), @RowCount)
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseLog, @ProcessMessage, null, @Module, @Client
	
	create index idx_OGSLookUpClient on #OGSLookUpClient (Client_num)

	/****************************************************************************

		Calculate VNB and populate the temporary table with the results
		
		Note that there are oddities like LV protection payments which always
		come in pairs with one large and one much smaller amount (e.g. TransactionID 
		= 6684787.) The system treats both payments in the pair as first payments 
		and the (projected) DA associated with both is the same (because it's on 
		the policy transaction). 
		
		There is also a requirement to front-load VNB points on accrual and level
		payments. This means calculate the VNB for the full amount of the DA and 
		put it on the first payment record and then on all subsequent accrual and 
		level payments, set the VNB to zero.
		
		Thus two different sources of DA are used depending on whether we need the
		full DA amount for accruals and level or the actual amount received for all
		other scenarios including the LV split payment scenario. The two sources are:
		
		mstt_PolicyTransactions.CommInitialAmount - Full (projected) DA amount
		
		mstt_Expectation.AMOUNT_REC - The DA actually received. This handles the
										LV scenario whereby the AMOUNT_REC is 
										proportioned across the two payments received.   
																		
	****************************************************************************/

	select	top 0 
			*, 
			convert(int,NULL) as CommissionYear
	into	#owt_Recognition
	from	owt_Recognition

	insert into #owt_Recognition
	(
		SourceID,
		CaseID,
		TransactionID,
		Policy,
		ProductCode,
		BusinessCode,
		PointsTotal,
		BSC,
		MBF,
		Initial,
		OngoingTotal,
		OngoingYr01,
		OngoingYr02,
		OngoingYr03,
		OngoingYr04,
		OngoingYr05,
		OngoingYr06,
		OngoingYr07,
		OngoingYr08,
		OngoingYr09,
		OngoingYr10,
		FCARate,
		RetentionRate,
		RetentionRateBroker,
		OngoingServicingRate,
		OngoingServicingSource,
		DA,
		AmountReceived,
		Premium,
		AgentSplit,
		CommissionType,
		CommissionTypeDesc,
		Month,
		FrequencyCode,
		FrequencyDesc,
		ReassignedProductGroupCode,		--AG 05/06/2018
		ReassignedProductGroupName,		--AG 05/06/2018
		RecognitionType,
		CalculationType,
		Source,
		DateInserted,
		DateLastUpdated,
		CommissionYear
	)
	select	cs.PendingPaymentID as SourceID,
			cs.CaseID,
			cs.TransactionID,
			cs.ExtPolicyNumber as Policy,
			cs.ProductCode,
			cs.BusinessCode,
			0.0 as PointsTotal,
			case
				when BSCpot.ID is not null then 
					--BSC takes the first 0.12 of the ongoing fee %. If the ongoing fee % is 0.12% or less, then 100% of the ongoing fee is allocated to BSC
					case when coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2)) - convert(decimal(8,4),sc.KeyValue2) >= 0.01
						then 
							case when cs.FrequencyCode = 2	--Monthly 
								then (cs.AgentSplit/100) * 12.0 * (isnull(cs.Premium,0)/2.0) * convert(decimal(8,4),sc.KeyValue3) * case when cs.INIssued < 0 then -1 else 1 end
								else (cs.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(cs.Premium,0) * convert(decimal(8,4),sc.KeyValue3) * case when cs.INIssued < 0 then -1 else 1 end
							end			
						else
							case when cs.FrequencyCode = 2	--Monthly 
								then (cs.AgentSplit/100) * 12.0 * (isnull(cs.Premium,0)/2.0) * coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2)) * case when cs.INIssued < 0 then -1 else 1 end
								else (cs.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(cs.Premium,0) * (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))/100.0) * case when cs.INIssued < 0 then -1 else 1 end
							end
					end
				else 0.0
			end as BSC,
			case 
				when mbf.MortgageFeeID is not null and cs.INIssued <> 0 then (((mbf.AdviceFeeAmount)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * MRbkr.FACTOR) - ((mbf.AdviceFeeAmount)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * Mfca.FACTOR)) --Note that mbf.AdviceFeeAmount is signed correctly - so no coding for signing is needed here
				else 0.0
			end as MBF,
			case 
				--When the adviser has changed, the AgentSplit can become zero in which case the ELITE points should be zero.
				when cs.AgentSplit = 0 then 0
				
				--WEALTH CALCULATION START
				--Indemnity payments or SINGLEs or IC Clawbacks or IC adjustments Start
				when (ph.ProductCategoryCode = 1 or pcc.KeyValue2 = '1') and (cs.FrequencyCode = 6 or cs.PayBasisCode in ('T') or cs.CommissionType in (2,17)) and cs.commissiontype in (1,2,17) and cs.INIssued <> 0 then (((e.AMOUNT_REC)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * Crate.FACTOR) - ((e.AMOUNT_REC)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * Cfca.FACTOR)) * case when cs.INIssued < 0 then -1 else 1 end
				--Indemnity payments or SINGLEs or IC Clawbacks or IC adjustments End
				--Accruals & Level Start
				when (ph.ProductCategoryCode = 1 or pcc.KeyValue2 = '1') and cs.INIssued <> 0 then (((pt.CommInitialAmount)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * Crate.FACTOR) - ((pt.CommInitialAmount)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * Cfca.FACTOR)) * case when cs.INIssued < 0 then -1 else 1 end
				--Accruals & Level End
				--WEALTH CALCULATION END
				
				--MORTGAGE CALCULATION START
				--Note: The MBF component has its own table column
				--Only 1 payment for mortgages
				when ph.ProductGroupCode = 3 and cs.INIssued <> 0 then (((e.AMOUNT_REC)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * MRproc.FACTOR) - ((e.AMOUNT_REC)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * Mfca.FACTOR)) * case when cs.INIssued < 0 then -1 else 1 end	--AG 18/05/2018
				--MORTGAGE CALCULATION END
				
				--PROTECTION CALCULATION START
				--Indemnity payments or SINGLEs or IC Clawbacks or IC adjustments Start
				when ph.ProductGroupCode = 6 and (cs.FrequencyCode = 6 or cs.PayBasisCode in ('T') or cs.CommissionType in (2,17)) and cs.commissiontype in (1,2,17) and cs.INIssued <> 0 then (((e.AMOUNT_REC)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * Prate.FACTOR) - ((e.AMOUNT_REC)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * Pfca.FACTOR)) * case when cs.INIssued < 0 then -1 else 1 end
				--Indemnity payments or SINGLEs or IC Clawbacks or IC adjustments End
				--Accruals & Level Start
				when ph.ProductGroupCode = 6 and cs.INIssued <> 0 then (((pt.CommInitialAmount)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * Prate.FACTOR) - ((pt.CommInitialAmount)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * Pfca.FACTOR)) * case when cs.INIssued < 0 then -1 else 1 end
				--Accruals & Level End
				--PROTECTION CALCULATION END

				else 0.0

			end as Initial,
			0.0 as OngoingTotal,
			case
				--WEALTH ONGOING CALCULATION START
				--When the adviser has changed, the AgentSplit can become zero in which case the ELITE points should be zero.
				when cs.AgentSplit = 0 then 0

				--SINGLE start
				--Calculate when BSC and ongoing applies (where ongoing rate is greater than BSC rate) 
				when (ph.ProductCategoryCode = 1 or pcc.KeyValue2 = '1') and cs.FrequencyCode = 6 and SFMpot.ID is not null and BSCpot.ID is not null and (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2)) - convert(decimal(8,4),sc.KeyValue2)) >= 0.01 then 
							--(AUM X BSC Rate)...
							((cs.AgentSplit/100) * (isnull(cs.Premium,0) * convert(decimal(8,4),sc.KeyValue3)) 
							--(AUM X OGS Rate X COB FCA Rate)...
							- ((cs.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(cs.Premium,0) * (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))/100.0) * Cfca.FACTOR)
							--(AUM X (OGS Rate - BSC Rate) X COB Retention Rate)...
							+ ((cs.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(cs.Premium,0) * ((coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))-convert(decimal(8,4),sc.KeyValue2))/100.0)) * Crate.FACTOR) 
							--Sign correctly for +ve or clawback payment
							* (case when cs.INIssued < 0 then -1 else 1 end)
				--Calculate when BSC and ongoing applies (where ongoing rate less than BSC rate, then BSC gets all the ongoing available) 
				when (ph.ProductCategoryCode = 1 or pcc.KeyValue2 = '1') and cs.FrequencyCode = 6 and SFMpot.ID is not null and BSCpot.ID is not null then
							--(AUM X BSC Rate)...(in this scenario it's all of the OGS rate)
							((cs.AgentSplit/100) * (isnull(cs.Premium,0) * (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))/100.0)) 
							--(AUM X OGS Rate X COB FCA Rate)...
							- ((cs.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(cs.Premium,0) * (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))/100.0) * Cfca.FACTOR)
							--(AUM X (OGS Rate - BSC Rate) X COB Retention Rate)...
							+ (0.0)) --BSC got it all, so this part of the calculation is zero
							--Sign correctly for +ve or clawback payment
							* (case when cs.INIssued < 0 then -1 else 1 end)
				--Calculate when no BSC applies and ongoing applies
				when (ph.ProductCategoryCode = 1 or pcc.KeyValue2 = '1') and cs.FrequencyCode = 6 and SFMpot.ID is not null and BSCpot.ID is null then 
							--(AUM X OGS Rate X COB Retention Rate)...
							(((cs.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(cs.Premium,0) * (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))/100.0) * Crate.FACTOR) 
							--(AUM X OGS Rate X COB FCA Rate)...
							- ((cs.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(cs.Premium,0) * (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))/100.0) * Cfca.FACTOR))
							--Sign correctly for +ve or clawback payment
							* (case when cs.INIssued < 0 then -1 else 1 end)
				--SINGLE end
				
				--REGULAR start
				--Calculate when BSC and ongoing applies (where ongoing rate is greater than BSC rate) 
				when (ph.ProductCategoryCode = 1 or pcc.KeyValue2 = '1') and cs.FrequencyCode <> 6 and SFMpot.ID is not null and BSCpot.ID is not null and (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2)) - convert(decimal(8,4),sc.KeyValue2)) >= 0.01 then		--AG 04/06/2018 (1)
							--The non-BSC portion (Ave AUM X (OGS Rate - BSC Rate) X COB Retention Rate)...
							((((((cs.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(cs.Premium,0) * (case when cs.FrequencyCode = 2 then 12 else 1 end))/2.0) * (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2)) - convert(decimal(8,4),sc.KeyValue2))/100.0)) * Crate.FACTOR
							--The BSC portion (Ave AUM X BSC Rate)...
							+ case when cs.FrequencyCode = 2	--Monthly 
									then (cs.AgentSplit/100) * 12.0 * (isnull(cs.Premium,0)/2.0) * convert(decimal(8,4),sc.KeyValue3) 
									else (cs.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(cs.Premium,0) * convert(decimal(8,4),sc.KeyValue3) 
							  end
							--FCA Charge (Ave AUM X OGS Rate X FCA Rate)...
							- (case when cs.FrequencyCode = 2	--Monthly 
									then (cs.AgentSplit/100) * 12.0 * (isnull(cs.Premium,0)/2.0) 
									else (cs.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(cs.Premium,0) 
							   end * (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))/100.0) * Cfca.FACTOR))
							--Sign correctly for +ve or clawback payment
							* (case when cs.INIssued < 0 then -1 else 1 end)   
				--Calculate when BSC and ongoing applies (where ongoing rate less than BSC rate, then BSC gets all the ongoing available) 
				when (ph.ProductCategoryCode = 1 or pcc.KeyValue2 = '1') and cs.FrequencyCode <> 6 and SFMpot.ID is not null and BSCpot.ID is not null then		--AG 04/06/2018 (1)
							--The non-BSC portion (Ave AUM X (OGS Rate - BSC Rate) X COB Retention Rate)...
							((0/0)	--BSC got it all, so this part of the calculation is zero
							--The BSC portion (Ave AUM X BSC Rate)...(in this scenario it's all of the OGS rate)
							+ case when cs.FrequencyCode = 2	--Monthly 
									then (cs.AgentSplit/100) * 12.0 * (isnull(cs.Premium,0)/2.0) * (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))/100.0) 
									else (cs.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(cs.Premium,0) * (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))/100.0) 
							  end
							--FCA Charge (Ave AUM X OGS Rate X FCA Rate)...
							- (case when cs.FrequencyCode = 2	--Monthly 
									then (cs.AgentSplit/100) * 12.0 * (isnull(cs.Premium,0)/2.0) 
									else (cs.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(cs.Premium,0) 
							   end * (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))/100.0) * Cfca.FACTOR))
							--Sign correctly for +ve or clawback payment
							* (case when cs.INIssued < 0 then -1 else 1 end)   
				--Calculate when no BSC applies, but ongoing servicing applies
				when (ph.ProductCategoryCode = 1 or pcc.KeyValue2 = '1') and cs.FrequencyCode <> 6 and SFMpot.ID is not null and BSCpot.ID is null then		--AG 04/06/2018	(1)
							--(Ave AUM X OGS Rate X COB Retention Rate)...
							(((((cs.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(cs.Premium,0) * (case when cs.FrequencyCode = 2 then 12 else 1 end))/2.0) * (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))/100.0) * Crate.FACTOR) 
							--(Ave AUM X OGS Rate X COB FCA Rate)...
							- ((((cs.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(cs.Premium,0) * (case when cs.FrequencyCode = 2 then 12 else 1 end))/2.0) * (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))/100.0) * Cfca.FACTOR))
							--Sign correctly for +ve or clawback payment
							* (case when cs.INIssued < 0 then -1 else 1 end)   
				--REGULAR end
				
				else 0.0

				--WEALTH ONGOING CALCULATION END
			end as OngoingYr01,
			0.0 as OngoingYr02,
			0.0 as OngoingYr03,
			0.0 as OngoingYr04,
			0.0 as OngoingYr05,
			0.0 as OngoingYr06,
			0.0 as OngoingYr07,
			0.0 as OngoingYr08,
			0.0 as OngoingYr09,
			0.0 as OngoingYr10,
			case 
				when (ph.ProductCategoryCode = 1 or pcc.KeyValue2 = '1') then Cfca.FACTOR*100.0		--COB
				when ph.ProductGroupCode = 3 then Mfca.FACTOR*100.0		--MORT
				when ph.ProductGroupCode = 6 then Pfca.FACTOR*100.0		--PROT
				else 0.0
			end as FCARate,
			case 
				when (ph.ProductCategoryCode = 1 or pcc.KeyValue2 = '1') then Crate.FACTOR*100.0	--COB
				when ph.ProductGroupCode = 3 then MRproc.FACTOR*100.0	--MORT
				when ph.ProductGroupCode = 6 then Prate.FACTOR*100.0	--PROT
				else 0.0
			end as RetentionRate,
			case 
				when mbf.MortgageFeeID is not null then  MRbkr.FACTOR*100.0	
				else 0.0
			end as RetentionRateBroker,
			case when SFMpot.ID is not null
				then coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))
				else null
			end as OngoingServicingRate,
			case when SFMpot.ID is not null
				then case 
						when ogs.OngoingServiceFee is null and ogscli.OngoingServiceFee is null 
							then case
								when ogsdflt.KeyValue = 'ONPLAT' then 'Default - On Plat'
								else 'Default - Off Plat'
							end
						when ogs.OngoingServiceFee is not null then 'Client Product'
						when ogscli.OngoingServiceFee is not null then 'Client Only'
						else 'Unknown'
					 end
				else case when (ph.ProductCategoryCode = 1 or pcc.KeyValue2 = '1')
						then 'No OGS'					--WEALTH, but no OGS
						else null						--Not WEALTH, so OGS is n/a and is therefore null
					 end
			end as OngoingServicingSource,
			pt.CommInitialAmount as DA,
			e.AMOUNT_REC as AmountReceived,
			cs.Premium,
			cs.AgentSplit,
			cs.CommissionType,
			left(cs.StandingOrderDesc,50) as CommissionTypeDesc,
			cs.Month,
			cs.FrequencyCode,
			cs.FrequencyDesc,
			pg.ProductGroupCode as ReassignedProductGroupCode,	--Force the re-assigned products...		AG 05/06/2018
			pg.ProductGroupName as ReassignedProductGroupName,	--...to be processed as investments		AG 05/06/2018
			'VNB' as RecognitionType,
			case 
				when (ph.ProductCategoryCode = 1 or pcc.KeyValue2 = '1') then 'WEALTH'
				when ph.ProductGroupCode = 3 then 'MORTGAGE'
				when ph.ProductGroupCode = 6 then 'PROTECTION'
				else null
			end as CalculationType,
			'Openwork 2006' as Source,
			@DateLastUpdated as DateInserted,
			@DateLastUpdated as DateLastUpdated,
			csp.year as CommissionYear
	--select count(*)
	from	msit_CommissionStatement cs
/*			inner join (select	distinct PKID
						from	owt_TransformationMovements tm 
						where	tm.DriverTableName = 'sa_swift_S_AGMFIL'
						and		tm.CommissionStatement = 'Y') tm on tm.PKID = cs.PendingPaymentID
*/			inner join mstt_Agents ag on ag.Code = cs.BusinessCode
			inner join mstt_PolicyTransactions pt on pt.ID = cs.TransactionID
			inner join mstt_Policies p on p.POL_NUM = pt.PolicyID
			inner join msit_CommissionStatementPeriods VNBStart on convert(date,pt.CreateDateTime) between VNBStart.PeriodStartDate and VNBStart.PeriodEndDate
			inner join msit_Commissionstatementperiods csp on csp.month = cs.month
			inner join mstt_ProductHierarchy ph on ph.productcode = cs.productcode
			inner join mstt_Expectation e on e.ID = cs.ExpectationID
			left join dbo.owt_MortgageBrokerFees mbf on mbf.PendingPaymentID = cs.PendingPaymentID and mbf.AdviceFeeCharged = 'Yes'
			left join owt_SelectionControl SC
						on SC.Process = 'ElitePoints' 
						and SC.KeyType = 'NSCPotCode' 
						and cs.CreateDate between SC.EffectiveStartDate and SC.EffectiveEndDate
			left join mstt_Commissions BSCpot
						on BSCpot.TransactionID = cs.TransactionID 
						and BSCpot.Agent_Code = sc.KeyValue
						and BSCpot.CommissionType = 10
			left join owt_SelectionControl SFMPC						
						on SFMPC.Process = 'ElitePoints' 
						and SFMPC.KeyType = 'ServicingFeeMarginPotCode' 
						and cs.CreateDate between SFMPC.EffectiveStartDate and SFMPC.EffectiveEndDate
			left join mstt_Commissions SFMpot							
						on SFMpot.TransactionID = cs.TransactionID 
						and SFMpot.Agent_Code = SFMPC.KeyValue
						and SFMpot.CommissionType = 10	
			left join owt_SelectionControl pcc 
						on pcc.Process = 'ElitePoints'
						and pcc.KeyType = 'ProductCategoryCode'
						and pcc.KeyValue = cs.ProductCode	
						and cs.CreateDate between pcc.EffectiveStartDate and pcc.EffectiveEndDate
			left join owt_SelectionControl ogsdflt 
						on ogsdflt.Process = 'ElitePoints'
						and ogsdflt.KeyType = 'DefaultOngoingServicingRate'
						and ogsdflt.SelectionType = 'VNB'
						and ogsdflt.KeyValue = case when ph.RDRType = 'ONPLAT' then 'ONPLAT' else 'OFPLAT' end
						and cs.CreateDate between ogsdflt.EffectiveStartDate and ogsdflt.EffectiveEndDate
			left join mstt_CodeProductGroup pg on pg.ProductGroupCode = case when pcc.KeyValue2 = '1' then 2 else ph.ProductGroupCode end
			left join owt_EliteFactors Cfca on Cfca.FeeType = 'VNB' and Cfca.category = 'COB-FCA-RATE' and csp.year between Cfca.StartYear and Cfca.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors Crate on Crate.FeeType = 'VNB' and Crate.category = 'COB-RETENTION-RATE' and csp.year between Crate.StartYear and Crate.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors Mfca on Mfca.FeeType = 'VNB' and Mfca.category = 'MORT-FCA-RATE' and csp.year between Mfca.StartYear and Mfca.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors MRproc on MRproc.FeeType = 'VNB' and MRproc.category = 'MORT-RETENTION-RATE-PROC' and csp.year between MRproc.StartYear and MRproc.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors MRbkr on MRbkr.FeeType = 'VNB' and MRbkr.category = 'MORT-RETENTION-RATE-BROKER' and csp.year between MRbkr.StartYear and MRbkr.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors Pfca on Pfca.FeeType = 'VNB' and Pfca.category = 'PROT-FCA-RATE' and csp.year between Pfca.StartYear and Pfca.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors Prate on Prate.FeeType = 'VNB' and Prate.category = 'PROT-RETENTION-RATE' and csp.year between Prate.StartYear and Prate.EndYear 
			left join #OGSLookUp ogs on ogs.CLIENT_NUM = cs.ClientID and ogs.ProductCode = cs.ProductCode
			left join #OGSLookUpClient ogscli on ogscli.CLIENT_NUM = cs.ClientID 
	where	cs.ReportingClassCode = 1
	and		ag.Manager2Code <> @OwlManager2Code		--Exclude Owl
	and		cs.INIssued <> 0
	and		VNBStart.Year >= 2017			--VNB to start from 2017
	and		csp.Year >= 2017				--Ensure in-scope payments are consistent with VNB start

	select @RowCount = @@rowcount
	set @ProcessMessage = '#owt_Recognition = ' + convert(nvarchar(10), @RowCount)
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseLog, @ProcessMessage, null, @Module, @Client

	/****************************************************************************

		Occasionally an investment case may receive two or more cheques which
		then go through Swift as two or more SINGLE investments on the SAME
		slice. Although the INITIAL VNB calculation will pro-rata correctly
		because it is based on the amount received, this scenario will cause
		ongoing VNB to be calculated on each of the payment records and so will 
		double count (or worse if there are more than two cheques received).
		
		The code below ensures that any "extra" (unwanted) ongoing that has been
		calculated due to the above scenario is zeroed out as required.
																		
	****************************************************************************/
	
	select	derived.TransactionID, MIN(derived.SourceID) as MinSourceID
	into	#FirstPaymentOnTransaction
	from
	(	
		select	TransactionID, SourceID
		from	owt_Recognition				--Permanent table
		where	CommissionType = 1			--Initial
		and		Source = 'Openwork 2006'	--Just the data that relates to this proc
		union	--dedupe
		select	TransactionID, SourceID
		from	#owt_Recognition			--Temporary table
		where	CommissionType = 1			--Initial
	) derived 
	group by derived.TransactionID

	update	r
		set OngoingYr01 = 0.0
	from	#owt_Recognition r
			inner join #FirstPaymentOnTransaction fpot on fpot.TransactionID = r.TransactionID
	where	r.CommissionType = 1			--Initial
	and		r.SourceID <> fpot.MinSourceID	--Not the first payment
	and		r.OngoingYr01 <> 0.0			--Ongoing calc'd but requiring reset

	select @RowCount = @@rowcount
	set @ProcessMessage = '#owt_Recognition (ongoing reset) = ' + convert(nvarchar(10), @RowCount)
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseLog, @ProcessMessage, null, @Module, @Client

	/****************************************************************************

		Now calculate the ongoing spread as follows:
		1) Investments: Years 1 to 6
		2) Pensions:	Years 1 to 10
		Note that regular payments get an additional multiplier to uplift the 
		average AUM for each year.
																		
	****************************************************************************/

	update r
		set OngoingYr02 = case when r.FrequencyCode = 2									--Monthly
							then r.OngoingYr01 * YR02.Multiplier * YR02.Factor			--Regular
							else r.OngoingYr01 * YR02.Factor							--Single
						  end,
			OngoingYr03 = case when r.FrequencyCode = 2									--Monthly
							then r.OngoingYr01 * YR03.Multiplier * YR03.Factor			--Regular
							else r.OngoingYr01 * YR03.Factor							--Single
						  end,
			OngoingYr04 = case when r.FrequencyCode = 2									--Monthly
							then r.OngoingYr01 * YR04.Multiplier * YR04.Factor			--Regular
							else r.OngoingYr01 * YR04.Factor							--Single
						  end,
			OngoingYr05 = case when r.FrequencyCode = 2									--Monthly 
							then r.OngoingYr01 * YR05.Multiplier * YR05.Factor			--Regular
							else r.OngoingYr01 * YR05.Factor							--Single
						  end,
			OngoingYr06 = case when r.FrequencyCode = 2									--Monthly 
							then r.OngoingYr01 * YR06.Multiplier * YR06.Factor			--Regular
							else r.OngoingYr01 * YR06.Factor							--Single
						  end,
			OngoingYr07 = case when r.ReassignedProductGroupCode = 5					--Pensions	AG 05/06/2018
							then
								case when r.FrequencyCode = 2							--Monthly 
									then r.OngoingYr01 * YR07.Multiplier * YR07.Factor	--Regular
									else r.OngoingYr01 * YR07.Factor					--Single
								end
							else 
								0.0
						  end,
			OngoingYr08 = case when r.ReassignedProductGroupCode = 5					--Pensions	AG 05/06/2018 
							then
								case when r.FrequencyCode = 2							--Monthly 
									then r.OngoingYr01 * YR08.Multiplier * YR08.Factor	--Regular
									else r.OngoingYr01 * YR08.Factor					--Single
								end
							else 
								0.0
						  end,
			OngoingYr09 = case when r.ReassignedProductGroupCode = 5					--Pensions	AG 05/06/2018 
							then
								case when r.FrequencyCode = 2							--Monthly 
									then r.OngoingYr01 * YR09.Multiplier * YR09.Factor	--Regular
									else r.OngoingYr01 * YR09.Factor					--Single
								end
							else 
								0.0
						  end,
			OngoingYr10 = case when r.ReassignedProductGroupCode = 5					--Pensions	AG 05/06/2018
							then
								case when r.FrequencyCode = 2							--Monthly 
									then r.OngoingYr01 * YR10.Multiplier * YR10.Factor	--Regular
									else r.OngoingYr01 * YR10.Factor					--Single
								end
							else 
								0.0
						  end
	from	#owt_Recognition r
			left join owt_EliteFactors YR01 on YR01.FeeType = 'VNB' and YR01.Category = 'COB-ONGOING-DISCOUNT-YR01' and r.CommissionYear between YR01.StartYear and YR01.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors YR02 on YR02.FeeType = 'VNB' and YR02.Category = 'COB-ONGOING-DISCOUNT-YR02' and r.CommissionYear between YR02.StartYear and YR02.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors YR03 on YR03.FeeType = 'VNB' and YR03.Category = 'COB-ONGOING-DISCOUNT-YR03' and r.CommissionYear between YR03.StartYear and YR03.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors YR04 on YR04.FeeType = 'VNB' and YR04.Category = 'COB-ONGOING-DISCOUNT-YR04' and r.CommissionYear between YR04.StartYear and YR04.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors YR05 on YR05.FeeType = 'VNB' and YR05.Category = 'COB-ONGOING-DISCOUNT-YR05' and r.CommissionYear between YR05.StartYear and YR05.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors YR06 on YR06.FeeType = 'VNB' and YR06.Category = 'COB-ONGOING-DISCOUNT-YR06' and r.CommissionYear between YR06.StartYear and YR06.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors YR07 on YR07.FeeType = 'VNB' and YR07.Category = 'COB-ONGOING-DISCOUNT-YR07' and r.CommissionYear between YR07.StartYear and YR07.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors YR08 on YR08.FeeType = 'VNB' and YR08.Category = 'COB-ONGOING-DISCOUNT-YR08' and r.CommissionYear between YR08.StartYear and YR08.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors YR09 on YR09.FeeType = 'VNB' and YR09.Category = 'COB-ONGOING-DISCOUNT-YR09' and r.CommissionYear between YR09.StartYear and YR09.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors YR10 on YR10.FeeType = 'VNB' and YR10.Category = 'COB-ONGOING-DISCOUNT-YR10' and r.CommissionYear between YR10.StartYear and YR10.EndYear 
	where	r.CalculationType = 'WEALTH'
	
	select @RowCount = @@rowcount
	set @ProcessMessage = '#owt_Recognition (ongoing) = ' + convert(nvarchar(10), @RowCount)
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseLog, @ProcessMessage, null, @Module, @Client

	/****************************************************************************

		Now add up all the numbers
																		
	****************************************************************************/
	
	update r
		set OngoingTotal	=	OngoingYr01 + OngoingYr02 + OngoingYr03 + OngoingYr04 + OngoingYr05 +
								OngoingYr06 + OngoingYr07 + OngoingYr08 + OngoingYr09 + OngoingYr10,
			PointsTotal		=	OngoingYr01 + OngoingYr02 + OngoingYr03 + OngoingYr04 + OngoingYr05 +
								OngoingYr06 + OngoingYr07 + OngoingYr08 + OngoingYr09 + OngoingYr10 +
								Initial + MBF	-- Note BSC is already included in the Ongoing, so don't include it in the Points Total.
	from	#owt_Recognition r

	select @RowCount = @@rowcount
	set @ProcessMessage = '#owt_Recognition (totals) = ' + convert(nvarchar(10), @RowCount)
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseLog, @ProcessMessage, null, @Module, @Client

	/****************************************************************************

		Merge the temporary table into the permanent table
																		
	****************************************************************************/

	BEGIN TRANSACTION

	declare @SummaryOfChanges table (Change varchar(20))
	merge	dbo.owt_Recognition as trg
	using	#owt_Recognition as src
	on		trg.SourceID = src.SourceID
	and		trg.Source = src.Source
	when	matched 
	and		isnull(trg.PointsTotal,0) <> isnull(src.PointsTotal,0)
	then	update 
				set trg.CaseID = src.CaseID,
					trg.TransactionID = src.TransactionID,
					trg.Policy = src.Policy,
					trg.ProductCode = src.ProductCode,
					trg.BusinessCode = src.BusinessCode,
					trg.PointsTotal = src.PointsTotal,
					trg.BSC = src.BSC,
					trg.MBF = src.MBF,
					trg.Initial = src.Initial,
					trg.OngoingTotal = src.OngoingTotal,
					trg.OngoingYr01 = src.OngoingYr01,
					trg.OngoingYr02 = src.OngoingYr02,
					trg.OngoingYr03 = src.OngoingYr03,
					trg.OngoingYr04 = src.OngoingYr04,
					trg.OngoingYr05 = src.OngoingYr05,
					trg.OngoingYr06 = src.OngoingYr06,
					trg.OngoingYr07 = src.OngoingYr07,
					trg.OngoingYr08 = src.OngoingYr08,
					trg.OngoingYr09 = src.OngoingYr09,
					trg.OngoingYr10 = src.OngoingYr10,
					trg.FCARate = src.FCARate,
					trg.RetentionRate = src.RetentionRate,
					trg.RetentionRateBroker = src.RetentionRateBroker,
					trg.OngoingServicingRate = src.OngoingServicingRate,
					trg.OngoingServicingSource = src.OngoingServicingSource,
					trg.DA = src.DA,
					trg.AmountReceived = src.AmountReceived,
					trg.Premium = src.Premium,
					trg.AgentSplit = src.AgentSplit,
					trg.CommissionType = src.CommissionType,
					trg.CommissionTypeDesc = src.CommissionTypeDesc,
					trg.Month = src.Month,
					trg.FrequencyCode = src.FrequencyCode,
					trg.FrequencyDesc = src.FrequencyDesc,
					trg.ReassignedProductGroupCode = src.ReassignedProductGroupCode,	--AG 05/06/2018
					trg.ReassignedProductGroupName = src.ReassignedProductGroupName,	--AG 05/06/2018
					trg.RecognitionType = src.RecognitionType,
					trg.CalculationType = src.CalculationType,
					trg.DateLastUpdated = @DateLastUpdated
	when	not matched by target 
	then	insert
			(
				SourceID,
				CaseID,
				TransactionID,
				Policy,
				ProductCode,
				BusinessCode,
				PointsTotal,
				BSC,
				MBF,
				Initial,
				OngoingTotal,
				OngoingYr01,
				OngoingYr02,
				OngoingYr03,
				OngoingYr04,
				OngoingYr05,
				OngoingYr06,
				OngoingYr07,
				OngoingYr08,
				OngoingYr09,
				OngoingYr10,
				FCARate,
				RetentionRate,
				RetentionRateBroker,
				OngoingServicingRate,
				OngoingServicingSource,
				DA,
				AmountReceived,
				Premium,
				AgentSplit,
				CommissionType,
				CommissionTypeDesc,
				Month,
				FrequencyCode,
				FrequencyDesc,
				ReassignedProductGroupCode,		--AG 05/06/2018
				ReassignedProductGroupName,		--AG 05/06/2018
				RecognitionType,
				CalculationType,
				Source,
				DateInserted,
				DateLastUpdated
			)		
			values
			(
				src.SourceID,
				src.CaseID,
				src.TransactionID,
				src.Policy,
				src.ProductCode,
				src.BusinessCode,
				src.PointsTotal,
				src.BSC,
				src.MBF,
				src.Initial,
				src.OngoingTotal,
				src.OngoingYr01,
				src.OngoingYr02,
				src.OngoingYr03,
				src.OngoingYr04,
				src.OngoingYr05,
				src.OngoingYr06,
				src.OngoingYr07,
				src.OngoingYr08,
				src.OngoingYr09,
				src.OngoingYr10,
				src.FCARate,
				src.RetentionRate,
				src.RetentionRateBroker,
				src.OngoingServicingRate,
				src.OngoingServicingSource,
				src.DA,
				src.AmountReceived,
				src.Premium,
				src.AgentSplit,
				src.CommissionType,
				src.CommissionTypeDesc,
				src.Month,
				src.FrequencyCode,
				src.FrequencyDesc,
				src.ReassignedProductGroupCode,		--AG 05/06/2018
				src.ReassignedProductGroupName,		--AG 05/06/2018
				src.RecognitionType,
				src.CalculationType,
				src.Source,
				src.DateInserted,
				src.DateLastUpdated)				--Merge statements must have a ;
	output $action into @SummaryOfChanges;
/*	
	--Do not include MBF in the OpenAccess Commission Listing as it is on the MBF download
	--and we don't want MBF double counting.
	update	oal
		set VNB_Points = r.PointsTotal - r.MBF		--AG 04/06/2018 (2)
	from	msit_CommissionStatement cs
/*			inner join (select	distinct PKID
						from	owt_TransformationMovements tm 
						where	tm.DriverTableName = 'sa_swift_S_AGMFIL'
						and		tm.CommissionStatement = 'Y') tm on tm.PKID = cs.PendingPaymentID
*/			inner join msit_OpenworkAdviserListing oal on oal.SourceID = cs.ID and oal.Source = 'Openwork 2006'
			inner join owt_Recognition r 
						on r.RecognitionType = 'VNB'
						and r.SourceID = cs.PendingPaymentID
						and r.Source = oal.Source
	where	isnull(oal.VNB_Points,0) <> isnull(r.PointsTotal,0)
	
	select @OALRowCount = @@rowcount
*/
	COMMIT TRANSACTION      

	select	@RowCount = COUNT(*)
	from	@SummaryOfChanges
	where	Change = 'INSERT'

	set @ProcessMessage = 'owt_Recognition (insert) = ' + convert(nvarchar(10), @RowCount)
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseLog, @ProcessMessage, null, @Module, @Client

	select	@RowCount = COUNT(*)
	from	@SummaryOfChanges
	where	Change = 'UPDATE'

	set @ProcessMessage = 'owt_Recognition (update) = ' + convert(nvarchar(10), @RowCount)
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseLog, @ProcessMessage, null, @Module, @Client
/*
	set @ProcessMessage = 'msit_OpenworkAdviserListing (update) = ' + convert(nvarchar(10), @OALRowCount)
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseLog, @ProcessMessage, null, @Module, @Client
*/
	/****************************************************************************

		T H E   E N D
																		
	****************************************************************************/
	
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseEnd, @ProcName, null, @Module, @Client

END TRY

BEGIN CATCH 

	select @ErrNum = ERROR_NUMBER(), @ErrMsg = ERROR_MESSAGE(), @ErrSev = ERROR_SEVERITY(), @ErrLine = ERROR_LINE(), @ErrState = XACT_STATE()
	set @ErrMsg = REPLACE(@ErrMsg, '.', '') + ' (error no: ' + CAST(@ErrNum AS VARCHAR(10)) + ') on line ' + CAST(@ErrLine AS VARCHAR(10))
	
	-- Test XACT_STATE for 0, 1, or -1.
    -- If 1, the transaction is committable.
    -- If -1, the transaction is uncommittable and should be rolled back.
    -- If 0, there is no transaction and a commit or rollback operation would generate an error.

	if @ErrState = -1			-- Transaction is uncommitable
		rollback transaction

	if @ErrState = 1			
		commit transaction

	-- Error message line 1
	set @ErrMsgBrief = left(@ErrMsg,100)
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseError, @ErrMsgBrief, null, @Module, @Client
	
	-- Error message line 2 - if any text exists
	set @ErrMsgBrief = substring(@ErrMsg,101,100)
	if len(@ErrMsgBrief) > 0
		exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseError, @ErrMsgBrief, null, @Module, @Client

	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseEnd, @ProcName, null, @Module, @Client

	RAISERROR(@ErrMsg, @ErrSev , 1)

END CATCH

/****************************************************************************

			E N D															

****************************************************************************/

return @ErrNum



GO
/****** Object:  StoredProcedure [dbo].[owp_RecognitionSwift_Backup20180613AG]    Script Date: 7/3/2026 3:44:25 PM ******/
SET ANSI_NULLS ON
GO
SET QUOTED_IDENTIFIER ON
GO
/*********************************************************************************************************

Program:		owp_RecognitionSwift					
Author:			Alan Groves
Date created:	11/04/2018
											
Description:
===========

This proc populates the new recognition table called "owt_Recognition" with "Value of New Business"
(VNB) points.

This proc handles all of the swift data which includes:
WEALTH - COB business i.e. pensions and investments
MORTGAGES
PROTECTION

Note: There is a separate proc that calculates the GI VNB points from the Paymentshield data.

The approach of this proc is to use the incremental PendingPaymentIDs from the overnight batch
to calculate the VNB points in a temporary table.

The temporary table is then merged with the permanent table to make the calculated (or
re-calculated values) permanent.

Terms
-----
BSC			- Business Service Charge.
MBF			- Mortgage Broker Fee.
OGS			- Ongoing Servicing.
BSC Rate	- 0.12% at the time of writing (24/04/2018). This could be changed by the business, but
				would also require some DEV work in OWS.
DF			- Discount Factor.
DA			- Distribution Allowance (the total amount paid out by the provider to Openwork)
AUM			- Assets Under Management. Basically the amount invested or the premium on investment
				cases.
Average AUM - Average amount invested annually which is equivalent to 6 months' premium.

THE CALCULATIONS
================

There are two potential parts: initial + ongoing (if ongoing applies). If BSC (applies to ongoing 
only) and MBF (applies to mortgages only) apply, then these are also included:

MORTGAGE
--------
Part 1: MBF column = (Advice Fee Amount X Broker Retention Rate) - (Advice Fee Amount X Mort FCA Rate)
Part 2: Initial column = (Proc Fee Amount X Mortgage Retention Rate) - (Proc Fee X Mort FCA Rate) 
Mortgage Points Total = Initial + MBF

PROTECTION
----------
= (DA X Protection Retention Rate) - (DA X Protection FCA Rate) 
Protection Points Total = Initial

WEALTH (COB i.e. pensions and investments)
------
Part 1: Initial column = (DA X Wealth Retention Rate) - (DA X Wealth FCA Rate)

Part 2:

****XXXX****

NOTE: Where the BSC rate is greater than the ongoing rate, then BSC gets ALL of the AVAILABLE 
ongoing.

****XXXX****

REGULAR - BSC applies:
Year 1 column = BSC Points + Non-BSC Points - FCA Points
Non-BSC Points = Ave AUM X (OGS Rate - BSC Rate) X COB Retention Rate
BSC Points = Ave AUM X BSC Rate
FCA Points = Ave AUM X OGS Rate X COB FCA Rate

REGULAR - Non-BSC: 
Year 1 column = (Ave AUM X OGS Rate X COB Retention Rate) - (Ave AUM X OGS Rate X COB FCA Rate)

SINGLE - BSC applies:
Year 1 column = (AUM X BSC Rate) + (AUM X (OGS Rate - BSC Rate) X COB Retention Rate) - (AUM X OGS Rate X COB FCA Rate) 

SINGLE - Non-BSC:
Year 1 column = (AUM X OGS Rate X COB Retention Rate) - (AUM X OGS Rate X COB FCA Rate) 

Then years 2 to 10 are calculated by applying a discount factor
Year  2 = Year 1 X  3 X DF
Year  3 = Year 1 X  5 X DF
Year  4 = Year 1 X  7 X DF
Year  5 = Year 1 X  9 X DF
Year  6 = Year 1 X 11 X DF
Year  7 = Year 1 X 13 X DF
Year  8 = Year 1 X 15 X DF
Year  9 = Year 1 X 17 X DF
Year 10 = Year 1 X 19 X DF

Wealth Points Total =	OngoingYr01 + OngoingYr02 + OngoingYr03 + OngoingYr04 + OngoingYr05 +
						OngoingYr06 + OngoingYr07 + OngoingYr08 + OngoingYr09 + OngoingYr10 +
						Initial

GI
--
See stored proc "owp_RecognitionGIPaymentshield".
 
Notes:
-----

There is a BSC column on table owt_Recognition. However, BSC is already included in the ongoing
years 1 - 10, so the BSC column does not need to be added in. In fact you will double count if 
you attempt to do anything with it other than display it.


This proc is called as follows:
	declare @rc int
	exec @rc = dbo.owp_RecognitionSwift 'Openwork', 'Recognition'
	select @rc

					
AMENDMENT HISTORY				
=================								

Date		Author		Description
----		------		-----------
26/04/2018	A Groves	Only include rows in the OGS lookups where the OngoingServiceFee > 0.0.
						Negative OGS rates are bad data and at the time of writing, there are
						39 of these.
27/04/2018	A Groves	Additional calculation and condition to handle the scenario where BSC applies
						but the OGS Rate is less than the BSC rate. Previously, this caused the
						total ongoing to be zero. However, there are two components to ongoing VNB 
						points, the BSC share and the non-BSC share. So the BSC share (which takes 
						100% when the OGS rate is less than 0.12%) should still yield ongoing points.
27/04/2018	A Groves	Single ongoing Yr01 corrected by applying outer brackets before signing the result.
03/05/2018	A Groves	Added update of column "msit_OpenworkAdviserListing.VNB_Points".
18/05/2018	A Groves	Changed mortgage calculation to use e.AMOUNT_REC instead of pt.CommInitialAmount
						as Marcus Cossey wanted the actual amount received to be used for the DA.
04/06/2018	A Groves	1) In the REGULAR section of column "OngoingYr01", the condition for cs.FrequencyCode <> 6
							was added to ensure the code differentiates to the SINGLE section.
						2) Exclude MBF from the OpenAccess table (msit_OpenworkAdviserListing) as this
							is shown on the MBF download and would otherwise incur MBF double counting.
05/06/2018	A Groves	1) Marcus Cossey advised that investments should get ongoing for years 1 to 6 and
							pensions for years 1 to 10. Previously, both lines of business got years 1 to 10.
						2) Marcus Cossey asked for split payments (i.e. where multiple cheques are processed
							for a SINGLE investment) to only claculate ongoing VNB on the oldest payment. 
11/06/2018	A Groves	1) PSD processed a protection clawback statement as fee type initial. These clawbacks
							all generated +ve instead of -ve VNB points. A tweak was added to ensure that the 
							absolute value of AMOUNT_REC is used to ensure the VNB is correctly signed. 
						2) Another unknown business rule has surfaced: Previously, only initial, clawbacks and
							adjustments on slices created new from 2017 were included. This rule only applies
							to initial. Clawbacks and adjustments can belong to a slice created at any point
							in the past. However, note that the payment (irrespective of whether it is +ve or 
							-ve), must not pre-date 2017.
*************************************************************************************************************/

CREATE PROCEDURE [dbo].[owp_RecognitionSwift_Backup20180613AG]
	@Client		varchar(50),
	@Module		Varchar(50)
AS

set nocount on

declare		@PhaseStart				varchar(50),
			@PhaseEnd				varchar(50),
			@PhaseError				varchar(50),
			@PhaseLog				varchar(50),
			@ProcName				varchar(100),
			@ProcessMessage			varchar(100),
			@RowCount				int,
			@OALRowCount			int,
			@ErrMsg					nvarchar(4000),
			@ErrMsgBrief			nvarchar(100),
			@ErrNum					int,
			@ErrSev					int,
			@ErrLine				int,
			@ErrState				int,
			@DateLastUpdated		datetime,
			@OwlManager2Code		nvarchar(10)
			
/****************************************************************************

	Set initial parameters																
																		
****************************************************************************/

set @ProcName			= object_name(@@procid)
set @PhaseStart			= 'START'
set @PhaseEnd			= 'END'
set @PhaseError			= 'ERROR'
set @PhaseLog			= 'LOG'
set @ErrNum				= 0	
set @DateLastUpdated	= getdate()

set @OwlManager2Code = (select cde.Code from msit_MIWarehouseCodesAndDescriptions cde
			where cde.ColumnName = 'Manager2Code' and cde.Description = 'Owl Financial')

-- We want this logging irrespective of whether or not there is a rollback
exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseStart, @ProcName, null, @Module, @Client

/****************************************************************************

	Populate the table																
																		
****************************************************************************/

SET XACT_ABORT ON	-- Needed if XACT_STATE() function is used.

BEGIN TRY

	/****************************************************************************

		Link OWS data to Swift data to enable the ongoing servicng (OGS) rate
		to be looked up.
																		
	****************************************************************************/
	
	select	distinct s.PersonID, swp.Client_Num, p.InternalProductID, swp.ProductCode 
	into	#SwiftOWSClientLink
	from	sa_ows_Sale s
			inner join sa_ows_Policies p on p.SaleID = s.SaleID
			inner join mstt_Policies swp on swp.PolicyRef = p.PolicyID
	where	s.DateSubmitted is not null
	--and		s.PersonID = 146030

	select @RowCount = @@rowcount
	set @ProcessMessage = '#SwiftOWSClientLink = ' + convert(nvarchar(10), @RowCount)
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseLog, @ProcessMessage, null, @Module, @Client

	-- The OGS rate is stored for the client/product combination
	select	link.Client_Num, link.ProductCode, max(ogs.OngoingServiceFee) as OngoingServiceFee
	into	#OGSLookUp
	from	#SwiftOWSClientLink link 
			inner join mstt_ProductHierarchy ph on ph.ProductCode = link.ProductCode
			inner join Submission.sa_ows_SubmittedProductCurrentOngoingServiceFee ogs
							on ogs.PersonID = link.PersonID
							and ogs.InternalProductID = (case when ph.RDRType = 'ONPLAT' 
															then -2 
															else link.InternalProductID 
														 end)
	where	ogs.OngoingServiceFee > 0.0							--AG 26/04/2018
	group	by 	link.Client_Num, link.ProductCode

	select @RowCount = @@rowcount
	set @ProcessMessage = '#OGSLookUp = ' + convert(nvarchar(10), @RowCount)
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseLog, @ProcessMessage, null, @Module, @Client

	create index idx_OGSLookUp on #OGSLookUp (Client_num, ProductCode)

	--This is an additional catch for OGS by storing the client's highest OGS
	--rate against their client number. This lookup will apply if the first
	--look up fails. The first lookup can fail, for example, if the case was 
	--not submitted on OWS i.e. the CaseID has a "17" prefix. 
	select	Client_Num, MAX(OngoingServiceFee) as OngoingServiceFee
	into	#OGSLookUpClient
	from	#OGSLookUp
	group	by Client_Num

	select @RowCount = @@rowcount
	set @ProcessMessage = '#OGSLookUpClient = ' + convert(nvarchar(10), @RowCount)
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseLog, @ProcessMessage, null, @Module, @Client
	
	create index idx_OGSLookUpClient on #OGSLookUpClient (Client_num)

	/****************************************************************************

		Calculate VNB and populate the temporary table with the results
		
		Note that there are oddities like LV protection payments which always
		come in pairs with one large and one much smaller amount (e.g. TransactionID 
		= 6684787.) The system treats both payments in the pair as first payments 
		and the (projected) DA associated with both is the same (because it's on 
		the policy transaction). 
		
		There is also a requirement to front-load VNB points on accrual and level
		payments. This means calculate the VNB for the full amount of the DA and 
		put it on the first payment record and then on all subsequent accrual and 
		level payments, set the VNB to zero.
		
		Thus two different sources of DA are used depending on whether we need the
		full DA amount for accruals and level or the actual amount received for all
		other scenarios including the LV split payment scenario. The two sources are:
		
		mstt_PolicyTransactions.CommInitialAmount - Full (projected) DA amount
		
		mstt_Expectation.AMOUNT_REC - The DA actually received. This handles the
										LV scenario whereby the AMOUNT_REC is 
										proportioned across the two payments received.   
																		
	****************************************************************************/

	select	top 0 
			*, 
			convert(int,NULL) as CommissionYear
	into	#owt_Recognition
	from	owt_Recognition

	insert into #owt_Recognition
	(
		SourceID,
		CaseID,
		TransactionID,
		Policy,
		ProductCode,
		BusinessCode,
		PointsTotal,
		BSC,
		MBF,
		Initial,
		OngoingTotal,
		OngoingYr01,
		OngoingYr02,
		OngoingYr03,
		OngoingYr04,
		OngoingYr05,
		OngoingYr06,
		OngoingYr07,
		OngoingYr08,
		OngoingYr09,
		OngoingYr10,
		FCARate,
		RetentionRate,
		RetentionRateBroker,
		OngoingServicingRate,
		OngoingServicingSource,
		DA,
		AmountReceived,
		Premium,
		AgentSplit,
		CommissionType,
		CommissionTypeDesc,
		Month,
		FrequencyCode,
		FrequencyDesc,
		ReassignedProductGroupCode,		--AG 05/06/2018
		ReassignedProductGroupName,		--AG 05/06/2018
		RecognitionType,
		CalculationType,
		Source,
		DateInserted,
		DateLastUpdated,
		CommissionYear
	)
	select	cs.PendingPaymentID as SourceID,
			cs.CaseID,
			cs.TransactionID,
			cs.ExtPolicyNumber as Policy,
			cs.ProductCode,
			cs.BusinessCode,
			0.0 as PointsTotal,
			case
				when BSCpot.ID is not null then 
					--BSC takes the first 0.12 of the ongoing fee %. If the ongoing fee % is 0.12% or less, then 100% of the ongoing fee is allocated to BSC
					case when coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2)) - convert(decimal(8,4),sc.KeyValue2) >= 0.01
						then 
							case when cs.FrequencyCode = 2	--Monthly 
								then (cs.AgentSplit/100) * 12.0 * (isnull(cs.Premium,0)/2.0) * convert(decimal(8,4),sc.KeyValue3) * case when cs.INIssued < 0 then -1 else 1 end
								else (cs.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(cs.Premium,0) * convert(decimal(8,4),sc.KeyValue3) * case when cs.INIssued < 0 then -1 else 1 end
							end			
						else
							case when cs.FrequencyCode = 2	--Monthly 
								then (cs.AgentSplit/100) * 12.0 * (isnull(cs.Premium,0)/2.0) * coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2)) * case when cs.INIssued < 0 then -1 else 1 end
								else (cs.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(cs.Premium,0) * (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))/100.0) * case when cs.INIssued < 0 then -1 else 1 end
							end
					end
				else 0.0
			end as BSC,
			case 
				when mbf.MortgageFeeID is not null and cs.INIssued <> 0 then (((mbf.AdviceFeeAmount)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * MRbkr.FACTOR) - ((mbf.AdviceFeeAmount)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * Mfca.FACTOR)) --Note that mbf.AdviceFeeAmount is signed correctly - so no coding for signing is needed here
				else 0.0
			end as MBF,
			case 
				--When the adviser has changed, the AgentSplit can become zero in which case the ELITE points should be zero.
				when cs.AgentSplit = 0 then 0
				
				--WEALTH CALCULATION START
				--Indemnity payments or SINGLEs or IC Clawbacks or IC adjustments Start
				when (ph.ProductCategoryCode = 1 or pcc.KeyValue2 = '1') and (cs.FrequencyCode = 6 or cs.PayBasisCode in ('T') or cs.CommissionType in (2,17)) and cs.commissiontype in (1,2,17) and cs.INIssued <> 0 then (((e.AMOUNT_REC)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * Crate.FACTOR) - ((e.AMOUNT_REC)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * Cfca.FACTOR)) * case when cs.INIssued < 0 then -1 else 1 end
				--Indemnity payments or SINGLEs or IC Clawbacks or IC adjustments End
				--Accruals & Level Start
				when (ph.ProductCategoryCode = 1 or pcc.KeyValue2 = '1') and cs.INIssued <> 0 then (((pt.CommInitialAmount)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * Crate.FACTOR) - ((pt.CommInitialAmount)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * Cfca.FACTOR)) * case when cs.INIssued < 0 then -1 else 1 end
				--Accruals & Level End
				--WEALTH CALCULATION END
				
				--MORTGAGE CALCULATION START
				--Note: The MBF component has its own table column
				--Only 1 payment for mortgages
				when ph.ProductGroupCode = 3 and cs.INIssued <> 0 then (((e.AMOUNT_REC)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * MRproc.FACTOR) - ((e.AMOUNT_REC)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * Mfca.FACTOR)) * case when cs.INIssued < 0 then -1 else 1 end	--AG 18/05/2018
				--MORTGAGE CALCULATION END
				
				--PROTECTION CALCULATION START
				--Indemnity payments or SINGLEs or IC Clawbacks or IC adjustments Start
				when ph.ProductGroupCode = 6 and (cs.FrequencyCode = 6 or cs.PayBasisCode in ('T') or cs.CommissionType in (2,17)) and cs.commissiontype in (1,2,17) and cs.INIssued <> 0 then ((abs(e.AMOUNT_REC)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * Prate.FACTOR) - (abs(e.AMOUNT_REC)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * Pfca.FACTOR)) * case when cs.INIssued < 0 then -1 else 1 end	--AG 11/06/2018 (1)
				--Indemnity payments or SINGLEs or IC Clawbacks or IC adjustments End
				--Accruals & Level Start
				when ph.ProductGroupCode = 6 and cs.INIssued <> 0 then (((pt.CommInitialAmount)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * Prate.FACTOR) - ((pt.CommInitialAmount)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * Pfca.FACTOR)) * case when cs.INIssued < 0 then -1 else 1 end
				--Accruals & Level End
				--PROTECTION CALCULATION END

				else 0.0

			end as Initial,
			0.0 as OngoingTotal,
			case
				--WEALTH ONGOING CALCULATION START
				--When the adviser has changed, the AgentSplit can become zero in which case the ELITE points should be zero.
				when cs.AgentSplit = 0 then 0

				--SINGLE start
				--Calculate when BSC and ongoing applies (where ongoing rate is greater than BSC rate) 
				when (ph.ProductCategoryCode = 1 or pcc.KeyValue2 = '1') and cs.FrequencyCode = 6 and SFMpot.ID is not null and BSCpot.ID is not null and (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2)) - convert(decimal(8,4),sc.KeyValue2)) >= 0.01 then 
							--(AUM X BSC Rate)...
							((cs.AgentSplit/100) * (isnull(cs.Premium,0) * convert(decimal(8,4),sc.KeyValue3)) 
							--(AUM X OGS Rate X COB FCA Rate)...
							- ((cs.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(cs.Premium,0) * (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))/100.0) * Cfca.FACTOR)
							--(AUM X (OGS Rate - BSC Rate) X COB Retention Rate)...
							+ ((cs.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(cs.Premium,0) * ((coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))-convert(decimal(8,4),sc.KeyValue2))/100.0)) * Crate.FACTOR) 
							--Sign correctly for +ve or clawback payment
							* (case when cs.INIssued < 0 then -1 else 1 end)
				--Calculate when BSC and ongoing applies (where ongoing rate less than BSC rate, then BSC gets all the ongoing available) 
				when (ph.ProductCategoryCode = 1 or pcc.KeyValue2 = '1') and cs.FrequencyCode = 6 and SFMpot.ID is not null and BSCpot.ID is not null then
							--(AUM X BSC Rate)...(in this scenario it's all of the OGS rate)
							((cs.AgentSplit/100) * (isnull(cs.Premium,0) * (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))/100.0)) 
							--(AUM X OGS Rate X COB FCA Rate)...
							- ((cs.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(cs.Premium,0) * (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))/100.0) * Cfca.FACTOR)
							--(AUM X (OGS Rate - BSC Rate) X COB Retention Rate)...
							+ (0.0)) --BSC got it all, so this part of the calculation is zero
							--Sign correctly for +ve or clawback payment
							* (case when cs.INIssued < 0 then -1 else 1 end)
				--Calculate when no BSC applies and ongoing applies
				when (ph.ProductCategoryCode = 1 or pcc.KeyValue2 = '1') and cs.FrequencyCode = 6 and SFMpot.ID is not null and BSCpot.ID is null then 
							--(AUM X OGS Rate X COB Retention Rate)...
							(((cs.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(cs.Premium,0) * (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))/100.0) * Crate.FACTOR) 
							--(AUM X OGS Rate X COB FCA Rate)...
							- ((cs.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(cs.Premium,0) * (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))/100.0) * Cfca.FACTOR))
							--Sign correctly for +ve or clawback payment
							* (case when cs.INIssued < 0 then -1 else 1 end)
				--SINGLE end
				
				--REGULAR start
				--Calculate when BSC and ongoing applies (where ongoing rate is greater than BSC rate) 
				when (ph.ProductCategoryCode = 1 or pcc.KeyValue2 = '1') and cs.FrequencyCode <> 6 and SFMpot.ID is not null and BSCpot.ID is not null and (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2)) - convert(decimal(8,4),sc.KeyValue2)) >= 0.01 then		--AG 04/06/2018 (1)
							--The non-BSC portion (Ave AUM X (OGS Rate - BSC Rate) X COB Retention Rate)...
							((((((cs.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(cs.Premium,0) * (case when cs.FrequencyCode = 2 then 12 else 1 end))/2.0) * (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2)) - convert(decimal(8,4),sc.KeyValue2))/100.0)) * Crate.FACTOR
							--The BSC portion (Ave AUM X BSC Rate)...
							+ case when cs.FrequencyCode = 2	--Monthly 
									then (cs.AgentSplit/100) * 12.0 * (isnull(cs.Premium,0)/2.0) * convert(decimal(8,4),sc.KeyValue3) 
									else (cs.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(cs.Premium,0) * convert(decimal(8,4),sc.KeyValue3) 
							  end
							--FCA Charge (Ave AUM X OGS Rate X FCA Rate)...
							- (case when cs.FrequencyCode = 2	--Monthly 
									then (cs.AgentSplit/100) * 12.0 * (isnull(cs.Premium,0)/2.0) 
									else (cs.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(cs.Premium,0) 
							   end * (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))/100.0) * Cfca.FACTOR))
							--Sign correctly for +ve or clawback payment
							* (case when cs.INIssued < 0 then -1 else 1 end)   
				--Calculate when BSC and ongoing applies (where ongoing rate less than BSC rate, then BSC gets all the ongoing available) 
				when (ph.ProductCategoryCode = 1 or pcc.KeyValue2 = '1') and cs.FrequencyCode <> 6 and SFMpot.ID is not null and BSCpot.ID is not null then		--AG 04/06/2018 (1)
							--The non-BSC portion (Ave AUM X (OGS Rate - BSC Rate) X COB Retention Rate)...
							((0/0)	--BSC got it all, so this part of the calculation is zero
							--The BSC portion (Ave AUM X BSC Rate)...(in this scenario it's all of the OGS rate)
							+ case when cs.FrequencyCode = 2	--Monthly 
									then (cs.AgentSplit/100) * 12.0 * (isnull(cs.Premium,0)/2.0) * (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))/100.0) 
									else (cs.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(cs.Premium,0) * (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))/100.0) 
							  end
							--FCA Charge (Ave AUM X OGS Rate X FCA Rate)...
							- (case when cs.FrequencyCode = 2	--Monthly 
									then (cs.AgentSplit/100) * 12.0 * (isnull(cs.Premium,0)/2.0) 
									else (cs.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(cs.Premium,0) 
							   end * (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))/100.0) * Cfca.FACTOR))
							--Sign correctly for +ve or clawback payment
							* (case when cs.INIssued < 0 then -1 else 1 end)   
				--Calculate when no BSC applies, but ongoing servicing applies
				when (ph.ProductCategoryCode = 1 or pcc.KeyValue2 = '1') and cs.FrequencyCode <> 6 and SFMpot.ID is not null and BSCpot.ID is null then		--AG 04/06/2018	(1)
							--(Ave AUM X OGS Rate X COB Retention Rate)...
							(((((cs.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(cs.Premium,0) * (case when cs.FrequencyCode = 2 then 12 else 1 end))/2.0) * (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))/100.0) * Crate.FACTOR) 
							--(Ave AUM X OGS Rate X COB FCA Rate)...
							- ((((cs.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(cs.Premium,0) * (case when cs.FrequencyCode = 2 then 12 else 1 end))/2.0) * (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))/100.0) * Cfca.FACTOR))
							--Sign correctly for +ve or clawback payment
							* (case when cs.INIssued < 0 then -1 else 1 end)   
				--REGULAR end
				
				else 0.0

				--WEALTH ONGOING CALCULATION END
			end as OngoingYr01,
			0.0 as OngoingYr02,
			0.0 as OngoingYr03,
			0.0 as OngoingYr04,
			0.0 as OngoingYr05,
			0.0 as OngoingYr06,
			0.0 as OngoingYr07,
			0.0 as OngoingYr08,
			0.0 as OngoingYr09,
			0.0 as OngoingYr10,
			case 
				when (ph.ProductCategoryCode = 1 or pcc.KeyValue2 = '1') then Cfca.FACTOR*100.0		--COB
				when ph.ProductGroupCode = 3 then Mfca.FACTOR*100.0		--MORT
				when ph.ProductGroupCode = 6 then Pfca.FACTOR*100.0		--PROT
				else 0.0
			end as FCARate,
			case 
				when (ph.ProductCategoryCode = 1 or pcc.KeyValue2 = '1') then Crate.FACTOR*100.0	--COB
				when ph.ProductGroupCode = 3 then MRproc.FACTOR*100.0	--MORT
				when ph.ProductGroupCode = 6 then Prate.FACTOR*100.0	--PROT
				else 0.0
			end as RetentionRate,
			case 
				when mbf.MortgageFeeID is not null then  MRbkr.FACTOR*100.0	
				else 0.0
			end as RetentionRateBroker,
			case when SFMpot.ID is not null
				then coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))
				else null
			end as OngoingServicingRate,
			case when SFMpot.ID is not null
				then case 
						when ogs.OngoingServiceFee is null and ogscli.OngoingServiceFee is null 
							then case
								when ogsdflt.KeyValue = 'ONPLAT' then 'Default - On Plat'
								else 'Default - Off Plat'
							end
						when ogs.OngoingServiceFee is not null then 'Client Product'
						when ogscli.OngoingServiceFee is not null then 'Client Only'
						else 'Unknown'
					 end
				else case when (ph.ProductCategoryCode = 1 or pcc.KeyValue2 = '1')
						then 'No OGS'					--WEALTH, but no OGS
						else null						--Not WEALTH, so OGS is n/a and is therefore null
					 end
			end as OngoingServicingSource,
			pt.CommInitialAmount as DA,
			e.AMOUNT_REC as AmountReceived,
			cs.Premium,
			cs.AgentSplit,
			cs.CommissionType,
			left(cs.StandingOrderDesc,50) as CommissionTypeDesc,
			cs.Month,
			cs.FrequencyCode,
			cs.FrequencyDesc,
			pg.ProductGroupCode as ReassignedProductGroupCode,	--Force the re-assigned products...		AG 05/06/2018
			pg.ProductGroupName as ReassignedProductGroupName,	--...to be processed as investments		AG 05/06/2018
			'VNB' as RecognitionType,
			case 
				when (ph.ProductCategoryCode = 1 or pcc.KeyValue2 = '1') then 'WEALTH'
				when ph.ProductGroupCode = 3 then 'MORTGAGE'
				when ph.ProductGroupCode = 6 then 'PROTECTION'
				else null
			end as CalculationType,
			'Openwork 2006' as Source,
			@DateLastUpdated as DateInserted,
			@DateLastUpdated as DateLastUpdated,
			csp.year as CommissionYear
	--select count(*)
	from	msit_CommissionStatement cs
/*			inner join (select	distinct PKID
						from	owt_TransformationMovements tm 
						where	tm.DriverTableName = 'sa_swift_S_AGMFIL'
						and		tm.CommissionStatement = 'Y') tm on tm.PKID = cs.PendingPaymentID
*/			inner join mstt_Agents ag on ag.Code = cs.BusinessCode
			inner join mstt_PolicyTransactions pt on pt.ID = cs.TransactionID
			inner join mstt_Policies p on p.POL_NUM = pt.PolicyID
			inner join msit_CommissionStatementPeriods VNBStart on convert(date,pt.CreateDateTime) between VNBStart.PeriodStartDate and VNBStart.PeriodEndDate
			inner join msit_Commissionstatementperiods csp on csp.month = cs.month
			inner join mstt_ProductHierarchy ph on ph.productcode = cs.productcode
			inner join mstt_Expectation e on e.ID = cs.ExpectationID
			left join dbo.owt_MortgageBrokerFees mbf on mbf.PendingPaymentID = cs.PendingPaymentID and mbf.AdviceFeeCharged = 'Yes'
			left join owt_SelectionControl SC
						on SC.Process = 'ElitePoints' 
						and SC.KeyType = 'NSCPotCode' 
						and cs.CreateDate between SC.EffectiveStartDate and SC.EffectiveEndDate
			left join mstt_Commissions BSCpot
						on BSCpot.TransactionID = cs.TransactionID 
						and BSCpot.Agent_Code = sc.KeyValue
						and BSCpot.CommissionType = 10
			left join owt_SelectionControl SFMPC						
						on SFMPC.Process = 'ElitePoints' 
						and SFMPC.KeyType = 'ServicingFeeMarginPotCode' 
						and cs.CreateDate between SFMPC.EffectiveStartDate and SFMPC.EffectiveEndDate
			left join mstt_Commissions SFMpot							
						on SFMpot.TransactionID = cs.TransactionID 
						and SFMpot.Agent_Code = SFMPC.KeyValue
						and SFMpot.CommissionType = 10	
			left join owt_SelectionControl pcc 
						on pcc.Process = 'ElitePoints'
						and pcc.KeyType = 'ProductCategoryCode'
						and pcc.KeyValue = cs.ProductCode	
						and cs.CreateDate between pcc.EffectiveStartDate and pcc.EffectiveEndDate
			left join owt_SelectionControl ogsdflt 
						on ogsdflt.Process = 'ElitePoints'
						and ogsdflt.KeyType = 'DefaultOngoingServicingRate'
						and ogsdflt.SelectionType = 'VNB'
						and ogsdflt.KeyValue = case when ph.RDRType = 'ONPLAT' then 'ONPLAT' else 'OFPLAT' end
						and cs.CreateDate between ogsdflt.EffectiveStartDate and ogsdflt.EffectiveEndDate
			left join mstt_CodeProductGroup pg on pg.ProductGroupCode = case when pcc.KeyValue2 = '1' then 2 else ph.ProductGroupCode end
			left join owt_EliteFactors Cfca on Cfca.FeeType = 'VNB' and Cfca.category = 'COB-FCA-RATE' and csp.year between Cfca.StartYear and Cfca.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors Crate on Crate.FeeType = 'VNB' and Crate.category = 'COB-RETENTION-RATE' and csp.year between Crate.StartYear and Crate.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors Mfca on Mfca.FeeType = 'VNB' and Mfca.category = 'MORT-FCA-RATE' and csp.year between Mfca.StartYear and Mfca.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors MRproc on MRproc.FeeType = 'VNB' and MRproc.category = 'MORT-RETENTION-RATE-PROC' and csp.year between MRproc.StartYear and MRproc.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors MRbkr on MRbkr.FeeType = 'VNB' and MRbkr.category = 'MORT-RETENTION-RATE-BROKER' and csp.year between MRbkr.StartYear and MRbkr.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors Pfca on Pfca.FeeType = 'VNB' and Pfca.category = 'PROT-FCA-RATE' and csp.year between Pfca.StartYear and Pfca.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors Prate on Prate.FeeType = 'VNB' and Prate.category = 'PROT-RETENTION-RATE' and csp.year between Prate.StartYear and Prate.EndYear 
			left join #OGSLookUp ogs on ogs.CLIENT_NUM = cs.ClientID and ogs.ProductCode = cs.ProductCode
			left join #OGSLookUpClient ogscli on ogscli.CLIENT_NUM = cs.ClientID 
	where	cs.ReportingClassCode = 1
	and		ag.Manager2Code <> @OwlManager2Code		--Exclude Owl
	and		cs.INIssued <> 0
	and		csp.Year >= 2017				--Ensure in-scope payments are consistent with VNB start
--	and		VNBStart.Year >= 2017			--VNB to start from 2017						AG 11/06/2018 (2)
	and		((VNBStart.Year >= 2017 and cs.CommissionType = 1 and e.AMOUNT_REC >= 0.01)		--VNB to start from new slices in 2017 for +ve payments but...			AG 11/06/2018 (2)
			or (cs.CommissionType in (2,17) or e.AMOUNT_REC <= -0.01))						--...for -ve payments, the slice can start from any date in the past	AG 11/06/2018 (2)

	select @RowCount = @@rowcount
	set @ProcessMessage = '#owt_Recognition = ' + convert(nvarchar(10), @RowCount)
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseLog, @ProcessMessage, null, @Module, @Client

	/****************************************************************************

		Occasionally an investment case may receive two or more cheques which
		then go through Swift as two or more SINGLE investments on the SAME
		slice. Although the INITIAL VNB calculation will pro-rata correctly
		because it is based on the amount received, this scenario will cause
		ongoing VNB to be calculated on each of the payment records and so will 
		double count (or worse if there are more than two cheques received).
		
		The code below ensures that any "extra" (unwanted) ongoing that has been
		calculated due to the above scenario is zeroed out as required.
																		
	****************************************************************************/
	
	select	derived.TransactionID, MIN(derived.SourceID) as MinSourceID
	into	#FirstPaymentOnTransaction
	from
	(	
		select	TransactionID, SourceID
		from	owt_Recognition				--Permanent table
		where	CommissionType = 1			--Initial
		and		Source = 'Openwork 2006'	--Just the data that relates to this proc
		union	--dedupe
		select	TransactionID, SourceID
		from	#owt_Recognition			--Temporary table
		where	CommissionType = 1			--Initial
	) derived 
	group by derived.TransactionID

	update	r
		set OngoingYr01 = 0.0
	from	#owt_Recognition r
			inner join #FirstPaymentOnTransaction fpot on fpot.TransactionID = r.TransactionID
	where	r.CommissionType = 1			--Initial
	and		r.SourceID <> fpot.MinSourceID	--Not the first payment
	and		r.OngoingYr01 <> 0.0			--Ongoing calc'd but requiring reset

	select @RowCount = @@rowcount
	set @ProcessMessage = '#owt_Recognition (ongoing reset) = ' + convert(nvarchar(10), @RowCount)
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseLog, @ProcessMessage, null, @Module, @Client

	/****************************************************************************

		Now calculate the ongoing spread as follows:
		1) Investments: Years 1 to 6
		2) Pensions:	Years 1 to 10
		Note that regular payments get an additional multiplier to uplift the 
		average AUM for each year.
																		
	****************************************************************************/

	update r
		set OngoingYr02 = case when r.FrequencyCode = 2									--Monthly
							then r.OngoingYr01 * YR02.Multiplier * YR02.Factor			--Regular
							else r.OngoingYr01 * YR02.Factor							--Single
						  end,
			OngoingYr03 = case when r.FrequencyCode = 2									--Monthly
							then r.OngoingYr01 * YR03.Multiplier * YR03.Factor			--Regular
							else r.OngoingYr01 * YR03.Factor							--Single
						  end,
			OngoingYr04 = case when r.FrequencyCode = 2									--Monthly
							then r.OngoingYr01 * YR04.Multiplier * YR04.Factor			--Regular
							else r.OngoingYr01 * YR04.Factor							--Single
						  end,
			OngoingYr05 = case when r.FrequencyCode = 2									--Monthly 
							then r.OngoingYr01 * YR05.Multiplier * YR05.Factor			--Regular
							else r.OngoingYr01 * YR05.Factor							--Single
						  end,
			OngoingYr06 = case when r.FrequencyCode = 2									--Monthly 
							then r.OngoingYr01 * YR06.Multiplier * YR06.Factor			--Regular
							else r.OngoingYr01 * YR06.Factor							--Single
						  end,
			OngoingYr07 = case when r.ReassignedProductGroupCode = 5					--Pensions	AG 05/06/2018
							then
								case when r.FrequencyCode = 2							--Monthly 
									then r.OngoingYr01 * YR07.Multiplier * YR07.Factor	--Regular
									else r.OngoingYr01 * YR07.Factor					--Single
								end
							else 
								0.0
						  end,
			OngoingYr08 = case when r.ReassignedProductGroupCode = 5					--Pensions	AG 05/06/2018 
							then
								case when r.FrequencyCode = 2							--Monthly 
									then r.OngoingYr01 * YR08.Multiplier * YR08.Factor	--Regular
									else r.OngoingYr01 * YR08.Factor					--Single
								end
							else 
								0.0
						  end,
			OngoingYr09 = case when r.ReassignedProductGroupCode = 5					--Pensions	AG 05/06/2018 
							then
								case when r.FrequencyCode = 2							--Monthly 
									then r.OngoingYr01 * YR09.Multiplier * YR09.Factor	--Regular
									else r.OngoingYr01 * YR09.Factor					--Single
								end
							else 
								0.0
						  end,
			OngoingYr10 = case when r.ReassignedProductGroupCode = 5					--Pensions	AG 05/06/2018
							then
								case when r.FrequencyCode = 2							--Monthly 
									then r.OngoingYr01 * YR10.Multiplier * YR10.Factor	--Regular
									else r.OngoingYr01 * YR10.Factor					--Single
								end
							else 
								0.0
						  end
	from	#owt_Recognition r
			left join owt_EliteFactors YR01 on YR01.FeeType = 'VNB' and YR01.Category = 'COB-ONGOING-DISCOUNT-YR01' and r.CommissionYear between YR01.StartYear and YR01.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors YR02 on YR02.FeeType = 'VNB' and YR02.Category = 'COB-ONGOING-DISCOUNT-YR02' and r.CommissionYear between YR02.StartYear and YR02.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors YR03 on YR03.FeeType = 'VNB' and YR03.Category = 'COB-ONGOING-DISCOUNT-YR03' and r.CommissionYear between YR03.StartYear and YR03.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors YR04 on YR04.FeeType = 'VNB' and YR04.Category = 'COB-ONGOING-DISCOUNT-YR04' and r.CommissionYear between YR04.StartYear and YR04.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors YR05 on YR05.FeeType = 'VNB' and YR05.Category = 'COB-ONGOING-DISCOUNT-YR05' and r.CommissionYear between YR05.StartYear and YR05.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors YR06 on YR06.FeeType = 'VNB' and YR06.Category = 'COB-ONGOING-DISCOUNT-YR06' and r.CommissionYear between YR06.StartYear and YR06.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors YR07 on YR07.FeeType = 'VNB' and YR07.Category = 'COB-ONGOING-DISCOUNT-YR07' and r.CommissionYear between YR07.StartYear and YR07.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors YR08 on YR08.FeeType = 'VNB' and YR08.Category = 'COB-ONGOING-DISCOUNT-YR08' and r.CommissionYear between YR08.StartYear and YR08.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors YR09 on YR09.FeeType = 'VNB' and YR09.Category = 'COB-ONGOING-DISCOUNT-YR09' and r.CommissionYear between YR09.StartYear and YR09.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors YR10 on YR10.FeeType = 'VNB' and YR10.Category = 'COB-ONGOING-DISCOUNT-YR10' and r.CommissionYear between YR10.StartYear and YR10.EndYear 
	where	r.CalculationType = 'WEALTH'
	
	select @RowCount = @@rowcount
	set @ProcessMessage = '#owt_Recognition (ongoing) = ' + convert(nvarchar(10), @RowCount)
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseLog, @ProcessMessage, null, @Module, @Client

	/****************************************************************************

		Now add up all the numbers
																		
	****************************************************************************/
	
	update r
		set OngoingTotal	=	OngoingYr01 + OngoingYr02 + OngoingYr03 + OngoingYr04 + OngoingYr05 +
								OngoingYr06 + OngoingYr07 + OngoingYr08 + OngoingYr09 + OngoingYr10,
			PointsTotal		=	OngoingYr01 + OngoingYr02 + OngoingYr03 + OngoingYr04 + OngoingYr05 +
								OngoingYr06 + OngoingYr07 + OngoingYr08 + OngoingYr09 + OngoingYr10 +
								Initial + MBF	-- Note BSC is already included in the Ongoing, so don't include it in the Points Total.
	from	#owt_Recognition r

	select @RowCount = @@rowcount
	set @ProcessMessage = '#owt_Recognition (totals) = ' + convert(nvarchar(10), @RowCount)
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseLog, @ProcessMessage, null, @Module, @Client

	/****************************************************************************

		Merge the temporary table into the permanent table
																		
	****************************************************************************/

	BEGIN TRANSACTION

	declare @SummaryOfChanges table (Change varchar(20))
	merge	dbo.owt_Recognition as trg
	using	#owt_Recognition as src
	on		trg.SourceID = src.SourceID
	and		trg.Source = src.Source
	when	matched 
	and		isnull(trg.PointsTotal,0) <> isnull(src.PointsTotal,0)
	then	update 
				set trg.CaseID = src.CaseID,
					trg.TransactionID = src.TransactionID,
					trg.Policy = src.Policy,
					trg.ProductCode = src.ProductCode,
					trg.BusinessCode = src.BusinessCode,
					trg.PointsTotal = src.PointsTotal,
					trg.BSC = src.BSC,
					trg.MBF = src.MBF,
					trg.Initial = src.Initial,
					trg.OngoingTotal = src.OngoingTotal,
					trg.OngoingYr01 = src.OngoingYr01,
					trg.OngoingYr02 = src.OngoingYr02,
					trg.OngoingYr03 = src.OngoingYr03,
					trg.OngoingYr04 = src.OngoingYr04,
					trg.OngoingYr05 = src.OngoingYr05,
					trg.OngoingYr06 = src.OngoingYr06,
					trg.OngoingYr07 = src.OngoingYr07,
					trg.OngoingYr08 = src.OngoingYr08,
					trg.OngoingYr09 = src.OngoingYr09,
					trg.OngoingYr10 = src.OngoingYr10,
					trg.FCARate = src.FCARate,
					trg.RetentionRate = src.RetentionRate,
					trg.RetentionRateBroker = src.RetentionRateBroker,
					trg.OngoingServicingRate = src.OngoingServicingRate,
					trg.OngoingServicingSource = src.OngoingServicingSource,
					trg.DA = src.DA,
					trg.AmountReceived = src.AmountReceived,
					trg.Premium = src.Premium,
					trg.AgentSplit = src.AgentSplit,
					trg.CommissionType = src.CommissionType,
					trg.CommissionTypeDesc = src.CommissionTypeDesc,
					trg.Month = src.Month,
					trg.FrequencyCode = src.FrequencyCode,
					trg.FrequencyDesc = src.FrequencyDesc,
					trg.ReassignedProductGroupCode = src.ReassignedProductGroupCode,	--AG 05/06/2018
					trg.ReassignedProductGroupName = src.ReassignedProductGroupName,	--AG 05/06/2018
					trg.RecognitionType = src.RecognitionType,
					trg.CalculationType = src.CalculationType,
					trg.DateLastUpdated = @DateLastUpdated
	when	not matched by target 
	then	insert
			(
				SourceID,
				CaseID,
				TransactionID,
				Policy,
				ProductCode,
				BusinessCode,
				PointsTotal,
				BSC,
				MBF,
				Initial,
				OngoingTotal,
				OngoingYr01,
				OngoingYr02,
				OngoingYr03,
				OngoingYr04,
				OngoingYr05,
				OngoingYr06,
				OngoingYr07,
				OngoingYr08,
				OngoingYr09,
				OngoingYr10,
				FCARate,
				RetentionRate,
				RetentionRateBroker,
				OngoingServicingRate,
				OngoingServicingSource,
				DA,
				AmountReceived,
				Premium,
				AgentSplit,
				CommissionType,
				CommissionTypeDesc,
				Month,
				FrequencyCode,
				FrequencyDesc,
				ReassignedProductGroupCode,		--AG 05/06/2018
				ReassignedProductGroupName,		--AG 05/06/2018
				RecognitionType,
				CalculationType,
				Source,
				DateInserted,
				DateLastUpdated
			)		
			values
			(
				src.SourceID,
				src.CaseID,
				src.TransactionID,
				src.Policy,
				src.ProductCode,
				src.BusinessCode,
				src.PointsTotal,
				src.BSC,
				src.MBF,
				src.Initial,
				src.OngoingTotal,
				src.OngoingYr01,
				src.OngoingYr02,
				src.OngoingYr03,
				src.OngoingYr04,
				src.OngoingYr05,
				src.OngoingYr06,
				src.OngoingYr07,
				src.OngoingYr08,
				src.OngoingYr09,
				src.OngoingYr10,
				src.FCARate,
				src.RetentionRate,
				src.RetentionRateBroker,
				src.OngoingServicingRate,
				src.OngoingServicingSource,
				src.DA,
				src.AmountReceived,
				src.Premium,
				src.AgentSplit,
				src.CommissionType,
				src.CommissionTypeDesc,
				src.Month,
				src.FrequencyCode,
				src.FrequencyDesc,
				src.ReassignedProductGroupCode,		--AG 05/06/2018
				src.ReassignedProductGroupName,		--AG 05/06/2018
				src.RecognitionType,
				src.CalculationType,
				src.Source,
				src.DateInserted,
				src.DateLastUpdated)				--Merge statements must have a ;
	output $action into @SummaryOfChanges;
/*	
	--Do not include MBF in the OpenAccess Commission Listing as it is on the MBF download
	--and we don't want MBF double counting.
	update	oal
		set VNB_Points = r.PointsTotal - r.MBF		--AG 04/06/2018 (2)
	from	msit_CommissionStatement cs
/*			inner join (select	distinct PKID
						from	owt_TransformationMovements tm 
						where	tm.DriverTableName = 'sa_swift_S_AGMFIL'
						and		tm.CommissionStatement = 'Y') tm on tm.PKID = cs.PendingPaymentID
*/			inner join msit_OpenworkAdviserListing oal on oal.SourceID = cs.ID and oal.Source = 'Openwork 2006'
			inner join owt_Recognition r 
						on r.RecognitionType = 'VNB'
						and r.SourceID = cs.PendingPaymentID
						and r.Source = oal.Source
	--where	isnull(oal.VNB_Points,0) <> isnull(r.PointsTotal,0)
	
	select @OALRowCount = @@rowcount
*/
	COMMIT TRANSACTION      

	select	@RowCount = COUNT(*)
	from	@SummaryOfChanges
	where	Change = 'INSERT'

	set @ProcessMessage = 'owt_Recognition (insert) = ' + convert(nvarchar(10), @RowCount)
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseLog, @ProcessMessage, null, @Module, @Client

	select	@RowCount = COUNT(*)
	from	@SummaryOfChanges
	where	Change = 'UPDATE'

	set @ProcessMessage = 'owt_Recognition (update) = ' + convert(nvarchar(10), @RowCount)
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseLog, @ProcessMessage, null, @Module, @Client
/*
	set @ProcessMessage = 'msit_OpenworkAdviserListing (update) = ' + convert(nvarchar(10), @OALRowCount)
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseLog, @ProcessMessage, null, @Module, @Client
*/
	/****************************************************************************

		T H E   E N D
																		
	****************************************************************************/
	
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseEnd, @ProcName, null, @Module, @Client

END TRY

BEGIN CATCH 

	select @ErrNum = ERROR_NUMBER(), @ErrMsg = ERROR_MESSAGE(), @ErrSev = ERROR_SEVERITY(), @ErrLine = ERROR_LINE(), @ErrState = XACT_STATE()
	set @ErrMsg = REPLACE(@ErrMsg, '.', '') + ' (error no: ' + CAST(@ErrNum AS VARCHAR(10)) + ') on line ' + CAST(@ErrLine AS VARCHAR(10))
	
	-- Test XACT_STATE for 0, 1, or -1.
    -- If 1, the transaction is committable.
    -- If -1, the transaction is uncommittable and should be rolled back.
    -- If 0, there is no transaction and a commit or rollback operation would generate an error.

	if @ErrState = -1			-- Transaction is uncommitable
		rollback transaction

	if @ErrState = 1			
		commit transaction

	-- Error message line 1
	set @ErrMsgBrief = left(@ErrMsg,100)
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseError, @ErrMsgBrief, null, @Module, @Client
	
	-- Error message line 2 - if any text exists
	set @ErrMsgBrief = substring(@ErrMsg,101,100)
	if len(@ErrMsgBrief) > 0
		exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseError, @ErrMsgBrief, null, @Module, @Client

	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseEnd, @ProcName, null, @Module, @Client

	RAISERROR(@ErrMsg, @ErrSev , 1)

END CATCH

/****************************************************************************

			E N D															

****************************************************************************/

return @ErrNum



GO
/****** Object:  StoredProcedure [dbo].[owp_RecognitionSwift_Backup20180724AG]    Script Date: 7/3/2026 3:44:25 PM ******/
SET ANSI_NULLS ON
GO
SET QUOTED_IDENTIFIER ON
GO
/*********************************************************************************************************

Program:		owp_RecognitionSwift					
Author:			Alan Groves
Date created:	11/04/2018
											
Description:
===========

This proc populates the new recognition table called "owt_Recognition" with "Value of New Business"
(VNB) points.

This proc handles all of the swift data which includes:
WEALTH - COB business i.e. pensions and investments
MORTGAGES
PROTECTION

Note: There is a separate proc that calculates the GI VNB points from the Paymentshield data.

The approach of this proc is to use the incremental PendingPaymentIDs from the overnight batch
to calculate the VNB points in a temporary table.

The temporary table is then merged with the permanent table to make the calculated (or
re-calculated values) permanent.

Terms
-----
BSC			- Business Service Charge.
MBF			- Mortgage Broker Fee.
OGS			- Ongoing Servicing.
BSC Rate	- 0.12% at the time of writing (24/04/2018). This could be changed by the business, but
				would also require some DEV work in OWS.
DF			- Discount Factor.
DA			- Distribution Allowance (the total amount paid out by the provider to Openwork)
AUM			- Assets Under Management. Basically the amount invested or the premium on investment
				cases.
Average AUM - Average amount invested annually which is equivalent to 6 months' premium.

THE CALCULATIONS
================

There are two potential parts: initial + ongoing (if ongoing applies). If BSC (applies to ongoing 
only) and MBF (applies to mortgages only) apply, then these are also included:

MORTGAGE
--------
Part 1: MBF column = (Advice Fee Amount X Broker Retention Rate) - (Advice Fee Amount X Mort FCA Rate)
Part 2: Initial column = (Proc Fee Amount X Mortgage Retention Rate) - (Proc Fee X Mort FCA Rate) 
Mortgage Points Total = Initial + MBF

PROTECTION
----------
= (DA X Protection Retention Rate) - (DA X Protection FCA Rate) 
Protection Points Total = Initial

WEALTH (COB i.e. pensions and investments)
------
Part 1: Initial column = (DA X Wealth Retention Rate) - (DA X Wealth FCA Rate)

Part 2:

****XXXX****

NOTE: Where the BSC rate is greater than the ongoing rate, then BSC gets ALL of the AVAILABLE 
ongoing.

****XXXX****

REGULAR - BSC applies:
Year 1 column = BSC Points + Non-BSC Points - FCA Points
Non-BSC Points = Ave AUM X (OGS Rate - BSC Rate) X COB Retention Rate
BSC Points = Ave AUM X BSC Rate
FCA Points = Ave AUM X OGS Rate X COB FCA Rate

REGULAR - Non-BSC: 
Year 1 column = (Ave AUM X OGS Rate X COB Retention Rate) - (Ave AUM X OGS Rate X COB FCA Rate)

SINGLE - BSC applies:
Year 1 column = (AUM X BSC Rate) + (AUM X (OGS Rate - BSC Rate) X COB Retention Rate) - (AUM X OGS Rate X COB FCA Rate) 

SINGLE - Non-BSC:
Year 1 column = (AUM X OGS Rate X COB Retention Rate) - (AUM X OGS Rate X COB FCA Rate) 

Then years 2 to 10 are calculated by applying a discount factor
Year  2 = Year 1 X  3 X DF
Year  3 = Year 1 X  5 X DF
Year  4 = Year 1 X  7 X DF
Year  5 = Year 1 X  9 X DF
Year  6 = Year 1 X 11 X DF
Year  7 = Year 1 X 13 X DF
Year  8 = Year 1 X 15 X DF
Year  9 = Year 1 X 17 X DF
Year 10 = Year 1 X 19 X DF

Wealth Points Total =	OngoingYr01 + OngoingYr02 + OngoingYr03 + OngoingYr04 + OngoingYr05 +
						OngoingYr06 + OngoingYr07 + OngoingYr08 + OngoingYr09 + OngoingYr10 +
						Initial

GI
--
See stored proc "owp_RecognitionGIPaymentshield".
 
Notes:
-----

There is a BSC column on table owt_Recognition. However, BSC is already included in the ongoing
years 1 - 10, so the BSC column does not need to be added in. In fact you will double count if 
you attempt to do anything with it other than display it.


This proc is called as follows:
	declare @rc int
	exec @rc = dbo.owp_RecognitionSwift 'Openwork', 'Recognition'
	select @rc

					
AMENDMENT HISTORY				
=================								

Date		Author		Description
----		------		-----------
26/04/2018	A Groves	Only include rows in the OGS lookups where the OngoingServiceFee > 0.0.
						Negative OGS rates are bad data and at the time of writing, there are
						39 of these.
27/04/2018	A Groves	Additional calculation and condition to handle the scenario where BSC applies
						but the OGS Rate is less than the BSC rate. Previously, this caused the
						total ongoing to be zero. However, there are two components to ongoing VNB 
						points, the BSC share and the non-BSC share. So the BSC share (which takes 
						100% when the OGS rate is less than 0.12%) should still yield ongoing points.
27/04/2018	A Groves	Single ongoing Yr01 corrected by applying outer brackets before signing the result.
03/05/2018	A Groves	Added update of column "msit_OpenworkAdviserListing.VNB_Points".
18/05/2018	A Groves	Changed mortgage calculation to use e.AMOUNT_REC instead of pt.CommInitialAmount
						as Marcus Cossey wanted the actual amount received to be used for the DA.
04/06/2018	A Groves	1) In the REGULAR section of column "OngoingYr01", the condition for cs.FrequencyCode <> 6
							was added to ensure the code differentiates to the SINGLE section.
						2) Exclude MBF from the OpenAccess table (msit_OpenworkAdviserListing) as this
							is shown on the MBF download and would otherwise incur MBF double counting.
05/06/2018	A Groves	1) Marcus Cossey advised that investments should get ongoing for years 1 to 6 and
							pensions for years 1 to 10. Previously, both lines of business got years 1 to 10.
						2) Marcus Cossey asked for split payments (i.e. where multiple cheques are processed
							for a SINGLE investment) to only claculate ongoing VNB on the oldest payment. 
11/06/2018	A Groves	1) PSD processed a protection clawback statement as fee type initial. These clawbacks
							all generated +ve instead of -ve VNB points. A tweak was added to ensure that the 
							absolute value of AMOUNT_REC is used to ensure the VNB is correctly signed. 
						2) Another unknown business rule has surfaced: Previously, only initial, clawbacks and
							adjustments on slices created new from 2017 were included. This rule only applies
							to initial. Clawbacks and adjustments can belong to a slice created at any point
							in the past. However, note that the payment (irrespective of whether it is +ve or 
							-ve), must not pre-date 2017.
13/06/2018	A Groves	Marcus asked for SellerCode and PaymentMatchedDate to be added so he need only use 
							the one table for both the adviser and enterprise leagues. PayBasisCode and 
							PayBasisDesc were also added at the same time as these are used in the calculations.
*************************************************************************************************************/

CREATE PROCEDURE [dbo].[owp_RecognitionSwift_Backup20180724AG]
	@Client		varchar(50),
	@Module		Varchar(50)

AS

set nocount on

declare		@PhaseStart				varchar(50),
			@PhaseEnd				varchar(50),
			@PhaseError				varchar(50),
			@PhaseLog				varchar(50),
			@ProcName				varchar(100),
			@ProcessMessage			varchar(100),
			@RowCount				int,
			@OALRowCount			int,
			@ErrMsg					nvarchar(4000),
			@ErrMsgBrief			nvarchar(100),
			@ErrNum					int,
			@ErrSev					int,
			@ErrLine				int,
			@ErrState				int,
			@DateLastUpdated		datetime,
			@OwlManager2Code		nvarchar(10)
			
/****************************************************************************

	Set initial parameters																
																		
****************************************************************************/

set @ProcName			= object_name(@@procid)
set @PhaseStart			= 'START'
set @PhaseEnd			= 'END'
set @PhaseError			= 'ERROR'
set @PhaseLog			= 'LOG'
set @ErrNum				= 0	
set @DateLastUpdated	= getdate()

set @OwlManager2Code = (select cde.Code from msit_MIWarehouseCodesAndDescriptions cde
			where cde.ColumnName = 'Manager2Code' and cde.Description = 'Owl Financial')

-- We want this logging irrespective of whether or not there is a rollback
exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseStart, @ProcName, null, @Module, @Client

/****************************************************************************

	Populate the table																
																		
****************************************************************************/

SET XACT_ABORT ON	-- Needed if XACT_STATE() function is used.

BEGIN TRY

	/****************************************************************************

		Link OWS data to Swift data to enable the ongoing servicng (OGS) rate
		to be looked up.
																		
	****************************************************************************/
	
	select	distinct s.PersonID, swp.Client_Num, p.InternalProductID, swp.ProductCode 
	into	#SwiftOWSClientLink
	from	sa_ows_Sale s
			inner join sa_ows_Policies p on p.SaleID = s.SaleID
			inner join mstt_Policies swp on swp.PolicyRef = p.PolicyID
	where	s.DateSubmitted is not null
	--and		s.PersonID = 146030

	select @RowCount = @@rowcount
	set @ProcessMessage = '#SwiftOWSClientLink = ' + convert(nvarchar(10), @RowCount)
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseLog, @ProcessMessage, null, @Module, @Client

	-- The OGS rate is stored for the client/product combination
	select	link.Client_Num, link.ProductCode, max(ogs.OngoingServiceFee) as OngoingServiceFee
	into	#OGSLookUp
	from	#SwiftOWSClientLink link 
			inner join mstt_ProductHierarchy ph on ph.ProductCode = link.ProductCode
			inner join Submission.sa_ows_SubmittedProductCurrentOngoingServiceFee ogs
							on ogs.PersonID = link.PersonID
							and ogs.InternalProductID = (case when ph.RDRType = 'ONPLAT' 
															then -2 
															else link.InternalProductID 
														 end)
	where	ogs.OngoingServiceFee > 0.0							--AG 26/04/2018
	group	by 	link.Client_Num, link.ProductCode

	select @RowCount = @@rowcount
	set @ProcessMessage = '#OGSLookUp = ' + convert(nvarchar(10), @RowCount)
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseLog, @ProcessMessage, null, @Module, @Client

	create index idx_OGSLookUp on #OGSLookUp (Client_num, ProductCode)

	--This is an additional catch for OGS by storing the client's highest OGS
	--rate against their client number. This lookup will apply if the first
	--look up fails. The first lookup can fail, for example, if the case was 
	--not submitted on OWS i.e. the CaseID has a "17" prefix. 
	select	Client_Num, MAX(OngoingServiceFee) as OngoingServiceFee
	into	#OGSLookUpClient
	from	#OGSLookUp
	group	by Client_Num

	select @RowCount = @@rowcount
	set @ProcessMessage = '#OGSLookUpClient = ' + convert(nvarchar(10), @RowCount)
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseLog, @ProcessMessage, null, @Module, @Client
	
	create index idx_OGSLookUpClient on #OGSLookUpClient (Client_num)

	/****************************************************************************

		Calculate VNB and populate the temporary table with the results
		
		Note that there are oddities like LV protection payments which always
		come in pairs with one large and one much smaller amount (e.g. TransactionID 
		= 6684787.) The system treats both payments in the pair as first payments 
		and the (projected) DA associated with both is the same (because it's on 
		the policy transaction). 
		
		There is also a requirement to front-load VNB points on accrual and level
		payments. This means calculate the VNB for the full amount of the DA and 
		put it on the first payment record and then on all subsequent accrual and 
		level payments, set the VNB to zero.
		
		Thus two different sources of DA are used depending on whether we need the
		full DA amount for accruals and level or the actual amount received for all
		other scenarios including the LV split payment scenario. The two sources are:
		
		mstt_PolicyTransactions.CommInitialAmount - Full (projected) DA amount
		
		mstt_Expectation.AMOUNT_REC - The DA actually received. This handles the
										LV scenario whereby the AMOUNT_REC is 
										proportioned across the two payments received.   
																		
	****************************************************************************/

	select	top 0 
			*, 
			convert(int,NULL) as CommissionYear
	into	#owt_Recognition
	from	owt_Recognition

	insert into #owt_Recognition
	(
		SourceID,
		CaseID,
		TransactionID,
		Policy,
		ProductCode,
		BusinessCode,
		SellerCode,						--AG 13/06/2018
		PointsTotal,
		BSC,
		MBF,
		Initial,
		OngoingTotal,
		OngoingYr01,
		OngoingYr02,
		OngoingYr03,
		OngoingYr04,
		OngoingYr05,
		OngoingYr06,
		OngoingYr07,
		OngoingYr08,
		OngoingYr09,
		OngoingYr10,
		FCARate,
		RetentionRate,
		RetentionRateBroker,
		OngoingServicingRate,
		OngoingServicingSource,
		DA,
		AmountReceived,
		Premium,
		AgentSplit,
		CommissionType,
		CommissionTypeDesc,
		PayBasisCode,					--AG 13/06/2018
		PayBasisDesc,					--AG 13/06/2018
		PaymentMatchedDate,				--AG 13/06/2018
		Month,
		FrequencyCode,
		FrequencyDesc,
		ReassignedProductGroupCode,		--AG 05/06/2018
		ReassignedProductGroupName,		--AG 05/06/2018
		RecognitionType,
		CalculationType,
		Source,
		DateInserted,
		DateLastUpdated,
		CommissionYear
	)
	select	cs.PendingPaymentID as SourceID,
			cs.CaseID,
			cs.TransactionID,
			cs.ExtPolicyNumber as Policy,
			cs.ProductCode,
			cs.BusinessCode,
			cs.AgentCode as SellerCode,				--AG 13/06/2018
			0.0 as PointsTotal,
			case
				when BSCpot.ID is not null then 
					--BSC takes the first 0.12 of the ongoing fee %. If the ongoing fee % is 0.12% or less, then 100% of the ongoing fee is allocated to BSC
					case when coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2)) - convert(decimal(8,4),sc.KeyValue2) >= 0.01
						then 
							case when cs.FrequencyCode = 2	--Monthly 
								then (cs.AgentSplit/100) * 12.0 * (isnull(cs.Premium,0)/2.0) * convert(decimal(8,4),sc.KeyValue3) * case when cs.INIssued < 0 then -1 else 1 end
								else (cs.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(cs.Premium,0) * convert(decimal(8,4),sc.KeyValue3) * case when cs.INIssued < 0 then -1 else 1 end
							end			
						else
							case when cs.FrequencyCode = 2	--Monthly 
								then (cs.AgentSplit/100) * 12.0 * (isnull(cs.Premium,0)/2.0) * coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2)) * case when cs.INIssued < 0 then -1 else 1 end
								else (cs.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(cs.Premium,0) * (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))/100.0) * case when cs.INIssued < 0 then -1 else 1 end
							end
					end
				else 0.0
			end as BSC,
			case 
				when mbf.MortgageFeeID is not null and cs.INIssued <> 0 then (((mbf.AdviceFeeAmount)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * MRbkr.FACTOR) - ((mbf.AdviceFeeAmount)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * Mfca.FACTOR)) --Note that mbf.AdviceFeeAmount is signed correctly - so no coding for signing is needed here
				else 0.0
			end as MBF,
			case 
				--When the adviser has changed, the AgentSplit can become zero in which case the ELITE points should be zero.
				when cs.AgentSplit = 0 then 0
				
				--WEALTH CALCULATION START
				--Indemnity payments or SINGLEs or IC Clawbacks or IC adjustments Start
				when (ph.ProductCategoryCode = 1 or pcc.KeyValue2 = '1') and (cs.FrequencyCode = 6 or cs.PayBasisCode in ('T') or cs.CommissionType in (2,17)) and cs.commissiontype in (1,2,17) and cs.INIssued <> 0 then (((e.AMOUNT_REC)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * Crate.FACTOR) - ((e.AMOUNT_REC)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * Cfca.FACTOR)) * case when cs.INIssued < 0 then -1 else 1 end
				--Indemnity payments or SINGLEs or IC Clawbacks or IC adjustments End
				--Accruals & Level Start
				when (ph.ProductCategoryCode = 1 or pcc.KeyValue2 = '1') and cs.INIssued <> 0 then (((pt.CommInitialAmount)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * Crate.FACTOR) - ((pt.CommInitialAmount)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * Cfca.FACTOR)) * case when cs.INIssued < 0 then -1 else 1 end
				--Accruals & Level End
				--WEALTH CALCULATION END
				
				--MORTGAGE CALCULATION START
				--Note: The MBF component has its own table column
				--Only 1 payment for mortgages
				when ph.ProductGroupCode = 3 and cs.INIssued <> 0 then (((e.AMOUNT_REC)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * MRproc.FACTOR) - ((e.AMOUNT_REC)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * Mfca.FACTOR)) * case when cs.INIssued < 0 then -1 else 1 end	--AG 18/05/2018
				--MORTGAGE CALCULATION END
				
				--PROTECTION CALCULATION START
				--Indemnity payments or SINGLEs or IC Clawbacks or IC adjustments Start
				when ph.ProductGroupCode = 6 and (cs.FrequencyCode = 6 or cs.PayBasisCode in ('T') or cs.CommissionType in (2,17)) and cs.commissiontype in (1,2,17) and cs.INIssued <> 0 then ((abs(e.AMOUNT_REC)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * Prate.FACTOR) - (abs(e.AMOUNT_REC)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * Pfca.FACTOR)) * case when cs.INIssued < 0 then -1 else 1 end	--AG 11/06/2018 (1)
				--Indemnity payments or SINGLEs or IC Clawbacks or IC adjustments End
				--Accruals & Level Start
				when ph.ProductGroupCode = 6 and cs.INIssued <> 0 then (((pt.CommInitialAmount)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * Prate.FACTOR) - ((pt.CommInitialAmount)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * Pfca.FACTOR)) * case when cs.INIssued < 0 then -1 else 1 end
				--Accruals & Level End
				--PROTECTION CALCULATION END

				else 0.0

			end as Initial,
			0.0 as OngoingTotal,
			case
				--WEALTH ONGOING CALCULATION START
				--When the adviser has changed, the AgentSplit can become zero in which case the ELITE points should be zero.
				when cs.AgentSplit = 0 then 0

				--SINGLE start
				--Calculate when BSC and ongoing applies (where ongoing rate is greater than BSC rate) 
				when (ph.ProductCategoryCode = 1 or pcc.KeyValue2 = '1') and cs.FrequencyCode = 6 and SFMpot.ID is not null and BSCpot.ID is not null and (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2)) - convert(decimal(8,4),sc.KeyValue2)) >= 0.01 then 
							--(AUM X BSC Rate)...
							((cs.AgentSplit/100) * (isnull(cs.Premium,0) * convert(decimal(8,4),sc.KeyValue3)) 
							--(AUM X OGS Rate X COB FCA Rate)...
							- ((cs.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(cs.Premium,0) * (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))/100.0) * Cfca.FACTOR)
							--(AUM X (OGS Rate - BSC Rate) X COB Retention Rate)...
							+ ((cs.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(cs.Premium,0) * ((coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))-convert(decimal(8,4),sc.KeyValue2))/100.0)) * Crate.FACTOR) 
							--Sign correctly for +ve or clawback payment
							* (case when cs.INIssued < 0 then -1 else 1 end)
				--Calculate when BSC and ongoing applies (where ongoing rate less than BSC rate, then BSC gets all the ongoing available) 
				when (ph.ProductCategoryCode = 1 or pcc.KeyValue2 = '1') and cs.FrequencyCode = 6 and SFMpot.ID is not null and BSCpot.ID is not null then
							--(AUM X BSC Rate)...(in this scenario it's all of the OGS rate)
							((cs.AgentSplit/100) * (isnull(cs.Premium,0) * (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))/100.0)) 
							--(AUM X OGS Rate X COB FCA Rate)...
							- ((cs.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(cs.Premium,0) * (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))/100.0) * Cfca.FACTOR)
							--(AUM X (OGS Rate - BSC Rate) X COB Retention Rate)...
							+ (0.0)) --BSC got it all, so this part of the calculation is zero
							--Sign correctly for +ve or clawback payment
							* (case when cs.INIssued < 0 then -1 else 1 end)
				--Calculate when no BSC applies and ongoing applies
				when (ph.ProductCategoryCode = 1 or pcc.KeyValue2 = '1') and cs.FrequencyCode = 6 and SFMpot.ID is not null and BSCpot.ID is null then 
							--(AUM X OGS Rate X COB Retention Rate)...
							(((cs.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(cs.Premium,0) * (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))/100.0) * Crate.FACTOR) 
							--(AUM X OGS Rate X COB FCA Rate)...
							- ((cs.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(cs.Premium,0) * (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))/100.0) * Cfca.FACTOR))
							--Sign correctly for +ve or clawback payment
							* (case when cs.INIssued < 0 then -1 else 1 end)
				--SINGLE end
				
				--REGULAR start
				--Calculate when BSC and ongoing applies (where ongoing rate is greater than BSC rate) 
				when (ph.ProductCategoryCode = 1 or pcc.KeyValue2 = '1') and cs.FrequencyCode <> 6 and SFMpot.ID is not null and BSCpot.ID is not null and (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2)) - convert(decimal(8,4),sc.KeyValue2)) >= 0.01 then		--AG 04/06/2018 (1)
							--The non-BSC portion (Ave AUM X (OGS Rate - BSC Rate) X COB Retention Rate)...
							((((((cs.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(cs.Premium,0) * (case when cs.FrequencyCode = 2 then 12 else 1 end))/2.0) * (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2)) - convert(decimal(8,4),sc.KeyValue2))/100.0)) * Crate.FACTOR
							--The BSC portion (Ave AUM X BSC Rate)...
							+ case when cs.FrequencyCode = 2	--Monthly 
									then (cs.AgentSplit/100) * 12.0 * (isnull(cs.Premium,0)/2.0) * convert(decimal(8,4),sc.KeyValue3) 
									else (cs.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(cs.Premium,0) * convert(decimal(8,4),sc.KeyValue3) 
							  end
							--FCA Charge (Ave AUM X OGS Rate X FCA Rate)...
							- (case when cs.FrequencyCode = 2	--Monthly 
									then (cs.AgentSplit/100) * 12.0 * (isnull(cs.Premium,0)/2.0) 
									else (cs.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(cs.Premium,0) 
							   end * (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))/100.0) * Cfca.FACTOR))
							--Sign correctly for +ve or clawback payment
							* (case when cs.INIssued < 0 then -1 else 1 end)   
				--Calculate when BSC and ongoing applies (where ongoing rate less than BSC rate, then BSC gets all the ongoing available) 
				when (ph.ProductCategoryCode = 1 or pcc.KeyValue2 = '1') and cs.FrequencyCode <> 6 and SFMpot.ID is not null and BSCpot.ID is not null then		--AG 04/06/2018 (1)
							--The non-BSC portion (Ave AUM X (OGS Rate - BSC Rate) X COB Retention Rate)...
							((0.0)	--BSC got it all, so this part of the calculation is zero
							--The BSC portion (Ave AUM X BSC Rate)...(in this scenario it's all of the OGS rate)
							+ case when cs.FrequencyCode = 2	--Monthly 
									then (cs.AgentSplit/100) * 12.0 * (isnull(cs.Premium,0)/2.0) * (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))/100.0) 
									else (cs.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(cs.Premium,0) * (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))/100.0) 
							  end
							--FCA Charge (Ave AUM X OGS Rate X FCA Rate)...
							- (case when cs.FrequencyCode = 2	--Monthly 
									then (cs.AgentSplit/100) * 12.0 * (isnull(cs.Premium,0)/2.0) 
									else (cs.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(cs.Premium,0) 
							   end * (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))/100.0) * Cfca.FACTOR))
							--Sign correctly for +ve or clawback payment
							* (case when cs.INIssued < 0 then -1 else 1 end)   
				--Calculate when no BSC applies, but ongoing servicing applies
				when (ph.ProductCategoryCode = 1 or pcc.KeyValue2 = '1') and cs.FrequencyCode <> 6 and SFMpot.ID is not null and BSCpot.ID is null then		--AG 04/06/2018	(1)
							--(Ave AUM X OGS Rate X COB Retention Rate)...
							(((((cs.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(cs.Premium,0) * (case when cs.FrequencyCode = 2 then 12 else 1 end))/2.0) * (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))/100.0) * Crate.FACTOR) 
							--(Ave AUM X OGS Rate X COB FCA Rate)...
							- ((((cs.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(cs.Premium,0) * (case when cs.FrequencyCode = 2 then 12 else 1 end))/2.0) * (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))/100.0) * Cfca.FACTOR))
							--Sign correctly for +ve or clawback payment
							* (case when cs.INIssued < 0 then -1 else 1 end)   
				--REGULAR end
				
				else 0.0

				--WEALTH ONGOING CALCULATION END
			end as OngoingYr01,
			0.0 as OngoingYr02,
			0.0 as OngoingYr03,
			0.0 as OngoingYr04,
			0.0 as OngoingYr05,
			0.0 as OngoingYr06,
			0.0 as OngoingYr07,
			0.0 as OngoingYr08,
			0.0 as OngoingYr09,
			0.0 as OngoingYr10,
			case 
				when (ph.ProductCategoryCode = 1 or pcc.KeyValue2 = '1') then Cfca.FACTOR*100.0		--COB
				when ph.ProductGroupCode = 3 then Mfca.FACTOR*100.0		--MORT
				when ph.ProductGroupCode = 6 then Pfca.FACTOR*100.0		--PROT
				else 0.0
			end as FCARate,
			case 
				when (ph.ProductCategoryCode = 1 or pcc.KeyValue2 = '1') then Crate.FACTOR*100.0	--COB
				when ph.ProductGroupCode = 3 then MRproc.FACTOR*100.0	--MORT
				when ph.ProductGroupCode = 6 then Prate.FACTOR*100.0	--PROT
				else 0.0
			end as RetentionRate,
			case 
				when mbf.MortgageFeeID is not null then  MRbkr.FACTOR*100.0	
				else 0.0
			end as RetentionRateBroker,
			case when SFMpot.ID is not null
				then coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))
				else null
			end as OngoingServicingRate,
			case when SFMpot.ID is not null
				then case 
						when ogs.OngoingServiceFee is null and ogscli.OngoingServiceFee is null 
							then case
								when ogsdflt.KeyValue = 'ONPLAT' then 'Default - On Plat'
								else 'Default - Off Plat'
							end
						when ogs.OngoingServiceFee is not null then 'Client Product'
						when ogscli.OngoingServiceFee is not null then 'Client Only'
						else 'Unknown'
					 end
				else case when (ph.ProductCategoryCode = 1 or pcc.KeyValue2 = '1')
						then 'No OGS'					--WEALTH, but no OGS
						else null						--Not WEALTH, so OGS is n/a and is therefore null
					 end
			end as OngoingServicingSource,
			pt.CommInitialAmount as DA,
			e.AMOUNT_REC as AmountReceived,
			cs.Premium,
			cs.AgentSplit,
			cs.CommissionType,
			left(cs.StandingOrderDesc,50) as CommissionTypeDesc,
			cs.PayBasisCode,							--AG 13/06/2018
			cs.PayBasisDesc,							--AG 13/06/2018
			cs.CreateDate as PaymentMatchedDate,		--AG 13/06/2018
			cs.Month,
			cs.FrequencyCode,
			cs.FrequencyDesc,
			pg.ProductGroupCode as ReassignedProductGroupCode,	--Force the re-assigned products...		AG 05/06/2018
			pg.ProductGroupName as ReassignedProductGroupName,	--...to be processed as investments		AG 05/06/2018
			'VNB' as RecognitionType,
			case 
				when (ph.ProductCategoryCode = 1 or pcc.KeyValue2 = '1') then 'WEALTH'
				when ph.ProductGroupCode = 3 then 'MORTGAGE'
				when ph.ProductGroupCode = 6 then 'PROTECTION'
				else null
			end as CalculationType,
			'Openwork 2006' as Source,
			@DateLastUpdated as DateInserted,
			@DateLastUpdated as DateLastUpdated,
			csp.year as CommissionYear
	--select count(*)
	from	msit_CommissionStatement cs
/*			inner join (select	distinct PKID
						from	owt_TransformationMovements tm 
						where	tm.DriverTableName = 'sa_swift_S_AGMFIL'
						and		tm.CommissionStatement = 'Y') tm on tm.PKID = cs.PendingPaymentID
*/			inner join mstt_Agents ag on ag.Code = cs.BusinessCode
			inner join mstt_PolicyTransactions pt on pt.ID = cs.TransactionID
			inner join mstt_Policies p on p.POL_NUM = pt.PolicyID
			inner join msit_CommissionStatementPeriods VNBStart on convert(date,pt.CreateDateTime) between VNBStart.PeriodStartDate and VNBStart.PeriodEndDate
			inner join msit_Commissionstatementperiods csp on csp.month = cs.month
			inner join mstt_ProductHierarchy ph on ph.productcode = cs.productcode
			inner join mstt_Expectation e on e.ID = cs.ExpectationID
			left join dbo.owt_MortgageBrokerFees mbf on mbf.PendingPaymentID = cs.PendingPaymentID and mbf.AdviceFeeCharged = 'Yes'
			left join owt_SelectionControl SC
						on SC.Process = 'ElitePoints' 
						and SC.KeyType = 'NSCPotCode' 
						and cs.CreateDate between SC.EffectiveStartDate and SC.EffectiveEndDate
			left join mstt_Commissions BSCpot
						on BSCpot.TransactionID = cs.TransactionID 
						and BSCpot.Agent_Code = sc.KeyValue
						and BSCpot.CommissionType = 10
			left join owt_SelectionControl SFMPC						
						on SFMPC.Process = 'ElitePoints' 
						and SFMPC.KeyType = 'ServicingFeeMarginPotCode' 
						and cs.CreateDate between SFMPC.EffectiveStartDate and SFMPC.EffectiveEndDate
			left join mstt_Commissions SFMpot							
						on SFMpot.TransactionID = cs.TransactionID 
						and SFMpot.Agent_Code = SFMPC.KeyValue
						and SFMpot.CommissionType = 10	
			left join owt_SelectionControl pcc 
						on pcc.Process = 'ElitePoints'
						and pcc.KeyType = 'ProductCategoryCode'
						and pcc.KeyValue = cs.ProductCode	
						and cs.CreateDate between pcc.EffectiveStartDate and pcc.EffectiveEndDate
			left join owt_SelectionControl ogsdflt 
						on ogsdflt.Process = 'ElitePoints'
						and ogsdflt.KeyType = 'DefaultOngoingServicingRate'
						and ogsdflt.SelectionType = 'VNB'
						and ogsdflt.KeyValue = case when ph.RDRType = 'ONPLAT' then 'ONPLAT' else 'OFPLAT' end
						and cs.CreateDate between ogsdflt.EffectiveStartDate and ogsdflt.EffectiveEndDate
			left join mstt_CodeProductGroup pg on pg.ProductGroupCode = case when pcc.KeyValue2 = '1' then 2 else ph.ProductGroupCode end
			left join owt_EliteFactors Cfca on Cfca.FeeType = 'VNB' and Cfca.category = 'COB-FCA-RATE' and csp.year between Cfca.StartYear and Cfca.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors Crate on Crate.FeeType = 'VNB' and Crate.category = 'COB-RETENTION-RATE' and csp.year between Crate.StartYear and Crate.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors Mfca on Mfca.FeeType = 'VNB' and Mfca.category = 'MORT-FCA-RATE' and csp.year between Mfca.StartYear and Mfca.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors MRproc on MRproc.FeeType = 'VNB' and MRproc.category = 'MORT-RETENTION-RATE-PROC' and csp.year between MRproc.StartYear and MRproc.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors MRbkr on MRbkr.FeeType = 'VNB' and MRbkr.category = 'MORT-RETENTION-RATE-BROKER' and csp.year between MRbkr.StartYear and MRbkr.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors Pfca on Pfca.FeeType = 'VNB' and Pfca.category = 'PROT-FCA-RATE' and csp.year between Pfca.StartYear and Pfca.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors Prate on Prate.FeeType = 'VNB' and Prate.category = 'PROT-RETENTION-RATE' and csp.year between Prate.StartYear and Prate.EndYear 
			left join #OGSLookUp ogs on ogs.CLIENT_NUM = cs.ClientID and ogs.ProductCode = cs.ProductCode
			left join #OGSLookUpClient ogscli on ogscli.CLIENT_NUM = cs.ClientID 
	where	cs.ReportingClassCode = 1
	and		ag.Manager2Code <> @OwlManager2Code		--Exclude Owl
	and		cs.INIssued <> 0
	and		csp.Year >= 2017				--Ensure in-scope payments are consistent with VNB start
--	and		VNBStart.Year >= 2010			--VNB to start from 2017						AG 11/06/2018 (2)
	and		((VNBStart.Year >= 2017 and cs.CommissionType = 1 and e.AMOUNT_REC >= 0.01)		--VNB to start from new slices in 2017 for +ve payments but...			AG 11/06/2018 (2)
			or (cs.CommissionType in (2,17) or e.AMOUNT_REC <= -0.01))						--...for -ve payments, the slice can start from any date in the past	AG 11/06/2018 (2)

	select @RowCount = @@rowcount
	set @ProcessMessage = '#owt_Recognition = ' + convert(nvarchar(10), @RowCount)
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseLog, @ProcessMessage, null, @Module, @Client

	/****************************************************************************

		Occasionally an investment case may receive two or more cheques which
		then go through Swift as two or more SINGLE investments on the SAME
		slice. Although the INITIAL VNB calculation will pro-rata correctly
		because it is based on the amount received, this scenario will cause
		ongoing VNB to be calculated on each of the payment records and so will 
		double count (or worse if there are more than two cheques received).
		
		The code below ensures that any "extra" (unwanted) ongoing that has been
		calculated due to the above scenario is zeroed out as required.
																		
	****************************************************************************/
/*	
	select	derived.TransactionID, MIN(derived.SourceID) as MinSourceID
	into	#FirstPaymentOnTransaction
	from
	(	
		select	TransactionID, SourceID
		from	owt_Recognition				--Permanent table
		where	CommissionType = 1			--Initial
		and		Source = 'Openwork 2006'	--Just the data that relates to this proc
		union	--dedupe
		select	TransactionID, SourceID
		from	#owt_Recognition			--Temporary table
		where	CommissionType = 1			--Initial
	) derived 
	group by derived.TransactionID

	update	r
		set OngoingYr01 = 0.0
	from	#owt_Recognition r
			inner join #FirstPaymentOnTransaction fpot on fpot.TransactionID = r.TransactionID
	where	r.CommissionType = 1			--Initial
	and		r.SourceID <> fpot.MinSourceID	--Not the first payment
	and		r.OngoingYr01 <> 0.0			--Ongoing calc'd but requiring reset

	select @RowCount = @@rowcount
	set @ProcessMessage = '#owt_Recognition (ongoing reset) = ' + convert(nvarchar(10), @RowCount)
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseLog, @ProcessMessage, null, @Module, @Client
*/
	/****************************************************************************

		Now calculate the ongoing spread as follows:
		1) Investments: Years 1 to 6
		2) Pensions:	Years 1 to 10
		Note that regular payments get an additional multiplier to uplift the 
		average AUM for each year.
																		
	****************************************************************************/

	update r
		set OngoingYr02 = case when r.FrequencyCode = 2									--Monthly
							then r.OngoingYr01 * YR02.Multiplier * YR02.Factor			--Regular
							else r.OngoingYr01 * YR02.Factor							--Single
						  end,
			OngoingYr03 = case when r.FrequencyCode = 2									--Monthly
							then r.OngoingYr01 * YR03.Multiplier * YR03.Factor			--Regular
							else r.OngoingYr01 * YR03.Factor							--Single
						  end,
			OngoingYr04 = case when r.FrequencyCode = 2									--Monthly
							then r.OngoingYr01 * YR04.Multiplier * YR04.Factor			--Regular
							else r.OngoingYr01 * YR04.Factor							--Single
						  end,
			OngoingYr05 = case when r.FrequencyCode = 2									--Monthly 
							then r.OngoingYr01 * YR05.Multiplier * YR05.Factor			--Regular
							else r.OngoingYr01 * YR05.Factor							--Single
						  end,
			OngoingYr06 = case when r.FrequencyCode = 2									--Monthly 
							then r.OngoingYr01 * YR06.Multiplier * YR06.Factor			--Regular
							else r.OngoingYr01 * YR06.Factor							--Single
						  end,
			OngoingYr07 = case when r.ReassignedProductGroupCode = 5					--Pensions	AG 05/06/2018
							then
								case when r.FrequencyCode = 2							--Monthly 
									then r.OngoingYr01 * YR07.Multiplier * YR07.Factor	--Regular
									else r.OngoingYr01 * YR07.Factor					--Single
								end
							else 
								0.0
						  end,
			OngoingYr08 = case when r.ReassignedProductGroupCode = 5					--Pensions	AG 05/06/2018 
							then
								case when r.FrequencyCode = 2							--Monthly 
									then r.OngoingYr01 * YR08.Multiplier * YR08.Factor	--Regular
									else r.OngoingYr01 * YR08.Factor					--Single
								end
							else 
								0.0
						  end,
			OngoingYr09 = case when r.ReassignedProductGroupCode = 5					--Pensions	AG 05/06/2018 
							then
								case when r.FrequencyCode = 2							--Monthly 
									then r.OngoingYr01 * YR09.Multiplier * YR09.Factor	--Regular
									else r.OngoingYr01 * YR09.Factor					--Single
								end
							else 
								0.0
						  end,
			OngoingYr10 = case when r.ReassignedProductGroupCode = 5					--Pensions	AG 05/06/2018
							then
								case when r.FrequencyCode = 2							--Monthly 
									then r.OngoingYr01 * YR10.Multiplier * YR10.Factor	--Regular
									else r.OngoingYr01 * YR10.Factor					--Single
								end
							else 
								0.0
						  end
	from	#owt_Recognition r
			left join owt_EliteFactors YR01 on YR01.FeeType = 'VNB' and YR01.Category = 'COB-ONGOING-DISCOUNT-YR01' and r.CommissionYear between YR01.StartYear and YR01.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors YR02 on YR02.FeeType = 'VNB' and YR02.Category = 'COB-ONGOING-DISCOUNT-YR02' and r.CommissionYear between YR02.StartYear and YR02.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors YR03 on YR03.FeeType = 'VNB' and YR03.Category = 'COB-ONGOING-DISCOUNT-YR03' and r.CommissionYear between YR03.StartYear and YR03.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors YR04 on YR04.FeeType = 'VNB' and YR04.Category = 'COB-ONGOING-DISCOUNT-YR04' and r.CommissionYear between YR04.StartYear and YR04.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors YR05 on YR05.FeeType = 'VNB' and YR05.Category = 'COB-ONGOING-DISCOUNT-YR05' and r.CommissionYear between YR05.StartYear and YR05.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors YR06 on YR06.FeeType = 'VNB' and YR06.Category = 'COB-ONGOING-DISCOUNT-YR06' and r.CommissionYear between YR06.StartYear and YR06.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors YR07 on YR07.FeeType = 'VNB' and YR07.Category = 'COB-ONGOING-DISCOUNT-YR07' and r.CommissionYear between YR07.StartYear and YR07.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors YR08 on YR08.FeeType = 'VNB' and YR08.Category = 'COB-ONGOING-DISCOUNT-YR08' and r.CommissionYear between YR08.StartYear and YR08.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors YR09 on YR09.FeeType = 'VNB' and YR09.Category = 'COB-ONGOING-DISCOUNT-YR09' and r.CommissionYear between YR09.StartYear and YR09.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors YR10 on YR10.FeeType = 'VNB' and YR10.Category = 'COB-ONGOING-DISCOUNT-YR10' and r.CommissionYear between YR10.StartYear and YR10.EndYear 
	where	r.CalculationType = 'WEALTH'
	
	select @RowCount = @@rowcount
	set @ProcessMessage = '#owt_Recognition (ongoing) = ' + convert(nvarchar(10), @RowCount)
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseLog, @ProcessMessage, null, @Module, @Client

	/****************************************************************************

		Now add up all the numbers
																		
	****************************************************************************/
	
	update r
		set OngoingTotal	=	OngoingYr01 + OngoingYr02 + OngoingYr03 + OngoingYr04 + OngoingYr05 +
								OngoingYr06 + OngoingYr07 + OngoingYr08 + OngoingYr09 + OngoingYr10,
			PointsTotal		=	OngoingYr01 + OngoingYr02 + OngoingYr03 + OngoingYr04 + OngoingYr05 +
								OngoingYr06 + OngoingYr07 + OngoingYr08 + OngoingYr09 + OngoingYr10 +
								Initial + MBF	-- Note BSC is already included in the Ongoing, so don't include it in the Points Total.
	from	#owt_Recognition r

	select @RowCount = @@rowcount
	set @ProcessMessage = '#owt_Recognition (totals) = ' + convert(nvarchar(10), @RowCount)
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseLog, @ProcessMessage, null, @Module, @Client

	/****************************************************************************

		Merge the temporary table into the permanent table
																		
	****************************************************************************/

	BEGIN TRANSACTION

	declare @SummaryOfChanges table (Change varchar(20))
	merge	dbo.owt_Recognition as trg
	using	#owt_Recognition as src
	on		trg.SourceID = src.SourceID
	and		trg.Source = src.Source
	when	matched 
	and		isnull(trg.PointsTotal,0) <> isnull(src.PointsTotal,0)
	then	update 
				set trg.CaseID = src.CaseID,
					trg.TransactionID = src.TransactionID,
					trg.Policy = src.Policy,
					trg.ProductCode = src.ProductCode,
					trg.BusinessCode = src.BusinessCode,
					trg.SellerCode = src.SellerCode,					--AG 13/06/2018
					trg.PointsTotal = src.PointsTotal,
					trg.BSC = src.BSC,
					trg.MBF = src.MBF,
					trg.Initial = src.Initial,
					trg.OngoingTotal = src.OngoingTotal,
					trg.OngoingYr01 = src.OngoingYr01,
					trg.OngoingYr02 = src.OngoingYr02,
					trg.OngoingYr03 = src.OngoingYr03,
					trg.OngoingYr04 = src.OngoingYr04,
					trg.OngoingYr05 = src.OngoingYr05,
					trg.OngoingYr06 = src.OngoingYr06,
					trg.OngoingYr07 = src.OngoingYr07,
					trg.OngoingYr08 = src.OngoingYr08,
					trg.OngoingYr09 = src.OngoingYr09,
					trg.OngoingYr10 = src.OngoingYr10,
					trg.FCARate = src.FCARate,
					trg.RetentionRate = src.RetentionRate,
					trg.RetentionRateBroker = src.RetentionRateBroker,
					trg.OngoingServicingRate = src.OngoingServicingRate,
					trg.OngoingServicingSource = src.OngoingServicingSource,
					trg.DA = src.DA,
					trg.AmountReceived = src.AmountReceived,
					trg.Premium = src.Premium,
					trg.AgentSplit = src.AgentSplit,
					trg.CommissionType = src.CommissionType,
					trg.CommissionTypeDesc = src.CommissionTypeDesc,
					trg.PayBasisCode = src.PayBasisCode,				--AG 13/06/2018
					trg.PayBasisDesc = src.PayBasisDesc,				--AG 13/06/2018
					trg.PaymentMatchedDate = src.PaymentMatchedDate,	--AG 13/06/2018	
					trg.Month = src.Month,
					trg.FrequencyCode = src.FrequencyCode,
					trg.FrequencyDesc = src.FrequencyDesc,
					trg.ReassignedProductGroupCode = src.ReassignedProductGroupCode,	--AG 05/06/2018
					trg.ReassignedProductGroupName = src.ReassignedProductGroupName,	--AG 05/06/2018
					trg.RecognitionType = src.RecognitionType,
					trg.CalculationType = src.CalculationType,
					trg.DateLastUpdated = @DateLastUpdated
	when	not matched by target 
	then	insert
			(
				SourceID,
				CaseID,
				TransactionID,
				Policy,
				ProductCode,
				BusinessCode,
				SellerCode,							--AG 13/06/2018
				PointsTotal,
				BSC,
				MBF,
				Initial,
				OngoingTotal,
				OngoingYr01,
				OngoingYr02,
				OngoingYr03,
				OngoingYr04,
				OngoingYr05,
				OngoingYr06,
				OngoingYr07,
				OngoingYr08,
				OngoingYr09,
				OngoingYr10,
				FCARate,
				RetentionRate,
				RetentionRateBroker,
				OngoingServicingRate,
				OngoingServicingSource,
				DA,
				AmountReceived,
				Premium,
				AgentSplit,
				CommissionType,
				CommissionTypeDesc,
				PayBasisCode,						--AG 13/06/2018
				PayBasisDesc,						--AG 13/06/2018
				PaymentMatchedDate,					--AG 13/06/2018
				Month,
				FrequencyCode,
				FrequencyDesc,
				ReassignedProductGroupCode,			--AG 05/06/2018
				ReassignedProductGroupName,			--AG 05/06/2018
				RecognitionType,
				CalculationType,
				Source,
				DateInserted,
				DateLastUpdated
			)		
			values
			(
				src.SourceID,
				src.CaseID,
				src.TransactionID,
				src.Policy,
				src.ProductCode,
				src.BusinessCode,
				src.SellerCode,						--AG 13/06/2018
				src.PointsTotal,
				src.BSC,
				src.MBF,
				src.Initial,
				src.OngoingTotal,
				src.OngoingYr01,
				src.OngoingYr02,
				src.OngoingYr03,
				src.OngoingYr04,
				src.OngoingYr05,
				src.OngoingYr06,
				src.OngoingYr07,
				src.OngoingYr08,
				src.OngoingYr09,
				src.OngoingYr10,
				src.FCARate,
				src.RetentionRate,
				src.RetentionRateBroker,
				src.OngoingServicingRate,
				src.OngoingServicingSource,
				src.DA,
				src.AmountReceived,
				src.Premium,
				src.AgentSplit,
				src.CommissionType,
				src.CommissionTypeDesc,
				src.PayBasisCode,					--AG 13/06/2018
				src.PayBasisDesc,					--AG 13/06/2018
				src.PaymentMatchedDate,				--AG 13/06/2018
				src.Month,
				src.FrequencyCode,
				src.FrequencyDesc,
				src.ReassignedProductGroupCode,		--AG 05/06/2018
				src.ReassignedProductGroupName,		--AG 05/06/2018
				src.RecognitionType,
				src.CalculationType,
				src.Source,
				src.DateInserted,
				src.DateLastUpdated)				--Merge statements must have a ;
	output $action into @SummaryOfChanges;
/*	
	--Do not include MBF in the OpenAccess Commission Listing as it is on the MBF download
	--and we don't want MBF double counting.
	update	oal
		set VNB_Points = r.PointsTotal - r.MBF		--AG 04/06/2018 (2)
	from	msit_CommissionStatement cs
/*			inner join (select	distinct PKID
						from	owt_TransformationMovements tm 
						where	tm.DriverTableName = 'sa_swift_S_AGMFIL'
						and		tm.CommissionStatement = 'Y') tm on tm.PKID = cs.PendingPaymentID
*/			inner join msit_OpenworkAdviserListing oal on oal.SourceID = cs.ID and oal.Source = 'Openwork 2006'
			inner join owt_Recognition r 
						on r.RecognitionType = 'VNB'
						and r.SourceID = cs.PendingPaymentID
						and r.Source = oal.Source
	--where	isnull(oal.VNB_Points,0) <> isnull(r.PointsTotal,0)
	
	select @OALRowCount = @@rowcount
*/
	COMMIT TRANSACTION      

	select	@RowCount = COUNT(*)
	from	@SummaryOfChanges
	where	Change = 'INSERT'

	set @ProcessMessage = 'owt_Recognition (insert) = ' + convert(nvarchar(10), @RowCount)
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseLog, @ProcessMessage, null, @Module, @Client

	select	@RowCount = COUNT(*)
	from	@SummaryOfChanges
	where	Change = 'UPDATE'

	set @ProcessMessage = 'owt_Recognition (update) = ' + convert(nvarchar(10), @RowCount)
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseLog, @ProcessMessage, null, @Module, @Client
/*
	set @ProcessMessage = 'msit_OpenworkAdviserListing (update) = ' + convert(nvarchar(10), @OALRowCount)
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseLog, @ProcessMessage, null, @Module, @Client
*/
	/****************************************************************************

		T H E   E N D
																		
	****************************************************************************/
	
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseEnd, @ProcName, null, @Module, @Client

END TRY

BEGIN CATCH 

	select @ErrNum = ERROR_NUMBER(), @ErrMsg = ERROR_MESSAGE(), @ErrSev = ERROR_SEVERITY(), @ErrLine = ERROR_LINE(), @ErrState = XACT_STATE()
	set @ErrMsg = REPLACE(@ErrMsg, '.', '') + ' (error no: ' + CAST(@ErrNum AS VARCHAR(10)) + ') on line ' + CAST(@ErrLine AS VARCHAR(10))
	
	-- Test XACT_STATE for 0, 1, or -1.
    -- If 1, the transaction is committable.
    -- If -1, the transaction is uncommittable and should be rolled back.
    -- If 0, there is no transaction and a commit or rollback operation would generate an error.

	if @ErrState = -1			-- Transaction is uncommitable
		rollback transaction

	if @ErrState = 1			
		commit transaction

	-- Error message line 1
	set @ErrMsgBrief = left(@ErrMsg,100)
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseError, @ErrMsgBrief, null, @Module, @Client
	
	-- Error message line 2 - if any text exists
	set @ErrMsgBrief = substring(@ErrMsg,101,100)
	if len(@ErrMsgBrief) > 0
		exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseError, @ErrMsgBrief, null, @Module, @Client

	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseEnd, @ProcName, null, @Module, @Client

	RAISERROR(@ErrMsg, @ErrSev , 1)

END CATCH

/****************************************************************************

			E N D															

****************************************************************************/

return @ErrNum



GO
/****** Object:  StoredProcedure [dbo].[owp_RecognitionSwift_PreLowOGSRate]    Script Date: 7/3/2026 3:44:25 PM ******/
SET ANSI_NULLS ON
GO
SET QUOTED_IDENTIFIER ON
GO
/*********************************************************************************************************

Program:		owp_RecognitionSwift					
Author:			Alan Groves
Date created:	11/04/2018
											
Description:
===========

This proc populates the new recognition table called "owt_Recognition" with "Value of New Business"
(VNB) points.

This proc handles all of the swift data which includes:
WEALTH - COB business i.e. pensions and investments
MORTGAGES
PROTECTION

Note: There is a separate proc that calculates the GI VNB points from the Paymentshield data.

The approach of this proc is to use the incremental PendingPaymentIDs from the overnight batch
to calculate the VNB points in a temporary table.

The temporary table is then merged with the permanent table to make the calculated (or
re-calculated values) permanent.

Terms
-----
BSC			- Business Service Charge.
MBF			- Mortgage Broker Fee.
OGS			- Ongoing Servicing.
BSC Rate	- 0.12% at the time of writing (24/04/2018). This could be changed by the business, but
				would also require some DEV work in OWS.
DF			- Discount Factor.
DA			- Distribution Allowance (the total amount paid out by the provider to Openwork)
AUM			- Assets Under Management. Basically the amount invested or the premium on investment
				cases.
Average AUM - Average amount invested annually which is equivalent to 6 months' premium.

THE CALCULATIONS
================

There are two potential parts: initial + ongoing (if ongoing applies). If BSC (applies to ongoing 
only) and MBF (applies to mortgages only) apply, then these are also included:

MORTGAGE
--------
Part 1: MBF column = (Advice Fee Amount X Broker Retention Rate) - (Advice Fee Amount X Mort FCA Rate)
Part 2: Initial column = (Proc Fee Amount X Mortgage Retention Rate) - (Proc Fee X Mort FCA Rate) 
Mortgage Points Total = Initial + MBF

PROTECTION
----------
= (DA X Protection Retention Rate) - (DA X Protection FCA Rate) 
Protection Points Total = Initial

WEALTH (COB i.e. pensions and investments)
------
Part 1: Initial column = (DA X Wealth Retention Rate) - (DA X Wealth FCA Rate)

Part 2:

REGULAR - BSC applies:
Year 1 column = BSC Points + Non-BSC Points - FCA Points
Non-BSC Points = Ave AUM X (OGS Rate - BSC Rate) X COB Retention Rate
BSC Points = Ave AUM X OGS Rate X FCA Rate
FCA Points = Ave AUM X OGS Rate X Wealth FCA Rate

REGULAR - Non-BSC: 
Year 1 column = (Ave AUM X OGS Rate X COB Retention Rate) - (Ave AUM X OGS Rate X COB FCA Rate)

SINGLE - BSC applies:
Year 1 column = (AUM X BSC Rate) + (AUM X (OGS Rate - BSC Rate) X COB Retention Rate) - (AUM X OGS Rate X COB FCA Rate) 

SINGLE - Non-BSC:
Year 1 column = (AUM X OGS Rate X COB Retention Rate) - (AUM X OGS Rate X COB FCA Rate) 

Then years 2 to 10 are calculated by applying a discount factor
Year  2 = Year 1 X  3 X DF
Year  3 = Year 1 X  5 X DF
Year  4 = Year 1 X  7 X DF
Year  5 = Year 1 X  9 X DF
Year  6 = Year 1 X 11 X DF
Year  7 = Year 1 X 13 X DF
Year  8 = Year 1 X 15 X DF
Year  9 = Year 1 X 17 X DF
Year 10 = Year 1 X 19 X DF

Wealth Points Total =	OngoingYr01 + OngoingYr02 + OngoingYr03 + OngoingYr04 + OngoingYr05 +
						OngoingYr06 + OngoingYr07 + OngoingYr08 + OngoingYr09 + OngoingYr10 +
						Initial

GI
--
See stored proc "owp_RecognitionGIPaymentshield".
 
Notes:
-----

There is a BSC column on table owt_Recognition. However, BSC is already included in the ongoing
years 1 - 10, so the BSC column does not need to be added in. In fact you will double count if 
you attempt to do anything with it other than display it.


This proc is called as follows:
	declare @rc int
	exec @rc = dbo.owp_RecognitionSwift 'Openwork', 'Recognition'
	select @rc

					
AMENDMENT HISTORY				
=================								

Date		Author		Description
----		------		-----------
26/04/2017	A Groves	Only include rows in the OGS lookups where the OngoingServiceFee > 0.0.
						Negative OGS rates are bad data and at the time of writing, there are
						39 of these.
*************************************************************************************************************/

CREATE PROCEDURE [dbo].[owp_RecognitionSwift_PreLowOGSRate]
	@Client		varchar(50),
	@Module		Varchar(50)
AS

set nocount on

declare		@PhaseStart				varchar(50),
			@PhaseEnd				varchar(50),
			@PhaseError				varchar(50),
			@PhaseLog				varchar(50),
			@ProcName				varchar(100),
			@ProcessMessage			varchar(100),
			@RowCount				int,
			@ErrMsg					nvarchar(4000),
			@ErrMsgBrief			nvarchar(100),
			@ErrNum					int,
			@ErrSev					int,
			@ErrLine				int,
			@ErrState				int,
			@DateLastUpdated		datetime,
			@OwlManager2Code		nvarchar(10)
			
/****************************************************************************

	Set initial parameters																
																		
****************************************************************************/

set @ProcName			= object_name(@@procid)
set @PhaseStart			= 'START'
set @PhaseEnd			= 'END'
set @PhaseError			= 'ERROR'
set @PhaseLog			= 'LOG'
set @ErrNum				= 0	
set @DateLastUpdated	= getdate()

set @OwlManager2Code = (select cde.Code from msit_MIWarehouseCodesAndDescriptions cde
			where cde.ColumnName = 'Manager2Code' and cde.Description = 'Owl Financial')

-- We want this logging irrespective of whether or not there is a rollback
exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseStart, @ProcName, null, @Module, @Client

/****************************************************************************

	Populate the table																
																		
****************************************************************************/

SET XACT_ABORT ON	-- Needed if XACT_STATE() function is used.

BEGIN TRY

	/****************************************************************************

		Link OWS data to Swift data to enable the ongoing servicng (OGS) rate
		to be looked up.
																		
	****************************************************************************/
	
	select	distinct s.PersonID, swp.Client_Num, p.InternalProductID, swp.ProductCode 
	into	#SwiftOWSClientLink
	from	sa_ows_Sale s
			inner join sa_ows_Policies p on p.SaleID = s.SaleID
			inner join mstt_Policies swp on swp.PolicyRef = p.PolicyID
	where	s.DateSubmitted is not null
	--and		s.PersonID = 146030

	select @RowCount = @@rowcount
	set @ProcessMessage = '#SwiftOWSClientLink = ' + convert(nvarchar(10), @RowCount)
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseLog, @ProcessMessage, null, @Module, @Client

	-- The OGS rate is stored for the client/product combination
	select	link.Client_Num, link.ProductCode, max(ogs.OngoingServiceFee) as OngoingServiceFee
	into	#OGSLookUp
	from	#SwiftOWSClientLink link 
			inner join mstt_ProductHierarchy ph on ph.ProductCode = link.ProductCode
			inner join Submission.sa_ows_SubmittedProductCurrentOngoingServiceFee ogs
							on ogs.PersonID = link.PersonID
							and ogs.InternalProductID = (case when ph.RDRType = 'ONPLAT' 
															then -2 
															else link.InternalProductID 
														 end)
	where	ogs.OngoingServiceFee > 0.0							--AG 26/04/2018
	group	by 	link.Client_Num, link.ProductCode

	select @RowCount = @@rowcount
	set @ProcessMessage = '#OGSLookUp = ' + convert(nvarchar(10), @RowCount)
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseLog, @ProcessMessage, null, @Module, @Client

	create index idx_OGSLookUp on #OGSLookUp (Client_num, ProductCode)

	--This is an additional catch for OGS by storing the client's highest OGS
	--rate against their client number. This lookup will apply if the first
	--look up fails. The first lookup can fail, for example, if the case was 
	--not submitted on OWS i.e. the CaseID has a "17" prefix. 
	select	Client_Num, MAX(OngoingServiceFee) as OngoingServiceFee
	into	#OGSLookUpClient
	from	#OGSLookUp
	group	by Client_Num

	select @RowCount = @@rowcount
	set @ProcessMessage = '#OGSLookUpClient = ' + convert(nvarchar(10), @RowCount)
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseLog, @ProcessMessage, null, @Module, @Client
	
	create index idx_OGSLookUpClient on #OGSLookUpClient (Client_num)

	/****************************************************************************

		Calculate VNB and populate the temporary table with the results
		
		Note that there are oddities like LV protection payments which always
		come in pairs with one large and one much smaller amount (e.g. TransactionID 
		= 6684787.) The system treats both payments in the pair as first payments 
		and the (projected) DA associated with both is the same (because it's on 
		the policy transaction). 
		
		There is also a requirement to front-load VNB points on accrual and level
		payments. This means calculate the VNB for the full amount of the DA and 
		put it on the first payment record and then on all subsequent accrual and 
		level payments, set the VNB to zero.
		
		Thus two different sources of DA are used depending on whether we need the
		full DA amount for accruals and level or the actual amount received for all
		other scenarios including the LV split payment scenario. The two sources are:
		
		mstt_PolicyTransactions.CommInitialAmount - Full (projected) DA amount
		
		mstt_Expectation.AMOUNT_REC - The DA actually received. This handles the
										LV scenario whereby the AMOUNT_REC is 
										proportioned across the two payments received.   
																		
	****************************************************************************/

	select top 0 *, convert(int,NULL) as CommissionYear
	into #owt_Recognition
	from owt_Recognition

	insert into #owt_Recognition
	(
		SourceID,
		CaseID,
		TransactionID,
		Policy,
		ProductCode,
		BusinessCode,
		PointsTotal,
		BSC,
		MBF,
		Initial,
		OngoingTotal,
		OngoingYr01,
		OngoingYr02,
		OngoingYr03,
		OngoingYr04,
		OngoingYr05,
		OngoingYr06,
		OngoingYr07,
		OngoingYr08,
		OngoingYr09,
		OngoingYr10,
		FCARate,
		RetentionRate,
		RetentionRateBroker,
		OngoingServicingRate,
		OngoingServicingSource,
		DA,
		AmountReceived,
		Premium,
		AgentSplit,
		CommissionType,
		CommissionTypeDesc,
		Month,
		FrequencyCode,
		FrequencyDesc,
		RecognitionType,
		CalculationType,
		Source,
		DateInserted,
		DateLastUpdated,
		CommissionYear
	)
	select	cs.PendingPaymentID as SourceID,
			cs.CaseID,
			cs.TransactionID,
			cs.ExtPolicyNumber as Policy,
			cs.ProductCode,
			cs.BusinessCode,
			0.0 as PointsTotal,
			case
				when BSCpot.ID is not null then 
					case when cs.FrequencyCode = 2	--Monthly 
						then (cs.AgentSplit/100) * 12.0 * (isnull(cs.Premium,0)/2.0) * convert(decimal(8,4),sc.KeyValue3) * case when cs.INIssued < 0 then -1 else 1 end
						else (cs.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(cs.Premium,0) * convert(decimal(8,4),sc.KeyValue3) * case when cs.INIssued < 0 then -1 else 1 end
					end
				else 0.0
			end as BSC,
			case 
				when mbf.MortgageFeeID is not null and cs.INIssued <> 0 then (((mbf.AdviceFeeAmount)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * MRbkr.FACTOR) - ((mbf.AdviceFeeAmount)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * Mfca.FACTOR)) --Note that mbf.AdviceFeeAmount is signed correctly - so no coding for signing is needed here
				else 0.0
			end as MBF,
			case 
				--When the adviser has changed, the AgentSplit can become zero in which case the ELITE points should be zero.
				when cs.AgentSplit = 0 then 0
				
				--WEALTH CALCULATION START
				--Indemnity payments or SINGLEs or IC Clawbacks or IC adjustments Start
				when (ph.ProductCategoryCode = 1 or pcc.KeyValue2 = '1') and (cs.FrequencyCode = 6 or cs.PayBasisCode in ('T') or cs.CommissionType in (2,17)) and cs.commissiontype in (1,2,17) and cs.INIssued <> 0 then (((e.AMOUNT_REC)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * Crate.FACTOR) - ((e.AMOUNT_REC)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * Cfca.FACTOR)) * case when cs.INIssued < 0 then -1 else 1 end
				--Indemnity payments or SINGLEs or IC Clawbacks or IC adjustments End
				--Accruals & Level Start
				when (ph.ProductCategoryCode = 1 or pcc.KeyValue2 = '1') and cs.INIssued <> 0 then (((pt.CommInitialAmount)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * Crate.FACTOR) - ((pt.CommInitialAmount)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * Cfca.FACTOR)) * case when cs.INIssued < 0 then -1 else 1 end
				--Accruals & Level End
				--WEALTH CALCULATION END
				
				--MORTGAGE CALCULATION START
				--Note: The MBF component has its own table column
				--Only 1 payment for mortgages
				when ph.ProductGroupCode = 3 and cs.INIssued <> 0 then (((pt.CommInitialAmount)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * MRproc.FACTOR) - ((pt.CommInitialAmount)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * Mfca.FACTOR)) * case when cs.INIssued < 0 then -1 else 1 end
				--MORTGAGE CALCULATION END
				
				--PROTECTION CALCULATION START
				--Indemnity payments or SINGLEs or IC Clawbacks or IC adjustments Start
				when ph.ProductGroupCode = 6 and (cs.FrequencyCode = 6 or cs.PayBasisCode in ('T') or cs.CommissionType in (2,17)) and cs.commissiontype in (1,2,17) and cs.INIssued <> 0 then (((e.AMOUNT_REC)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * Prate.FACTOR) - ((e.AMOUNT_REC)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * Pfca.FACTOR)) * case when cs.INIssued < 0 then -1 else 1 end
				--Indemnity payments or SINGLEs or IC Clawbacks or IC adjustments End
				--Accruals & Level Start
				when ph.ProductGroupCode = 6 and cs.INIssued <> 0 then (((pt.CommInitialAmount)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * Prate.FACTOR) - ((pt.CommInitialAmount)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * Pfca.FACTOR)) * case when cs.INIssued < 0 then -1 else 1 end
				--Accruals & Level End
				--PROTECTION CALCULATION END

				else 0.0

			end as Initial,
			0.0 as OngoingTotal,
			case
				--WEALTH ONGOING CALCULATION START
				--When the adviser has changed, the AgentSplit can become zero in which case the ELITE points should be zero.
				when cs.AgentSplit = 0 then 0

				--SINGLE start
				--Calculate when BSC and ongoing applies (ongoing rate must be greater than BSC rate) 
				when (ph.ProductCategoryCode = 1 or pcc.KeyValue2 = '1') and cs.FrequencyCode = 6 and SFMpot.ID is not null and BSCpot.ID is not null and (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2)) - convert(decimal(8,4),sc.KeyValue2)) >= 0.01 then 
							--(AUM X BSC Rate)...
							((cs.AgentSplit/100) * (isnull(cs.Premium,0) * convert(decimal(8,4),sc.KeyValue3)) 
							--(AUM X OGS Rate X COB FCA Rate)...
							- ((cs.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(cs.Premium,0) * (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))/100.0) * Cfca.FACTOR)
							--(AUM X (OGS Rate - BSC Rate) X COB Retention Rate)...
							+ ((cs.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(cs.Premium,0) * ((coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))-convert(decimal(8,4),sc.KeyValue2))/100.0)) * Crate.FACTOR) 
							--Sign correctly for +ve or clawback payment
							* (case when cs.INIssued < 0 then -1 else 1 end)
				--Calculate when no BSC applies and ongoing applies
				when (ph.ProductCategoryCode = 1 or pcc.KeyValue2 = '1') and cs.FrequencyCode = 6 and SFMpot.ID is not null and BSCpot.ID is null then 
							--(AUM X OGS Rate X COB Retention Rate)...
							((cs.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(cs.Premium,0) * (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))/100.0) * Crate.FACTOR) 
							--(AUM X OGS Rate X COB FCA Rate)...
							- ((cs.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(cs.Premium,0) * (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))/100.0) * Cfca.FACTOR)
							--Sign correctly for +ve or clawback payment
							* (case when cs.INIssued < 0 then -1 else 1 end)
				--SINGLE end
				
				--REGULAR start
				--Calculate when BSC and ongoing servicing applies (ongoing rate must be greater than BSC rate) 
				when (ph.ProductCategoryCode = 1 or pcc.KeyValue2 = '1') and SFMpot.ID is not null and BSCpot.ID is not null and (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2)) - convert(decimal(8,4),sc.KeyValue2)) >= 0.01 then 
							--The non-BSC portion (Ave AUM X (OGS Rate - BSC Rate) X COB Retention Rate)...
							((((((cs.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(cs.Premium,0) * (case when cs.FrequencyCode = 2 then 12 else 1 end))/2.0) * (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2)) - convert(decimal(8,4),sc.KeyValue2))/100.0)) * Crate.FACTOR
							--The BSC portion (Ave AUM X BSC Rate)...
							+ case when cs.FrequencyCode = 2	--Monthly 
									then (cs.AgentSplit/100) * 12.0 * (isnull(cs.Premium,0)/2.0) * convert(decimal(8,4),sc.KeyValue3) 
									else (cs.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(cs.Premium,0) * convert(decimal(8,4),sc.KeyValue3) 
							  end
							--FCA Charge (Ave AUM X OGS Rate X FCA Rate)...
							- (case when cs.FrequencyCode = 2	--Monthly 
									then (cs.AgentSplit/100) * 12.0 * (isnull(cs.Premium,0)/2.0) 
									else (cs.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(cs.Premium,0) 
							   end * (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))/100.0) * Cfca.FACTOR))
							--Sign correctly for +ve or clawback payment
							* (case when cs.INIssued < 0 then -1 else 1 end)   
				--Calculate when no BSC applies, but ongoing servicing applies
				when (ph.ProductCategoryCode = 1 or pcc.KeyValue2 = '1') and SFMpot.ID is not null and BSCpot.ID is null then 
							--(Ave AUM X OGS Rate X COB Retention Rate)...
							(((((cs.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(cs.Premium,0) * (case when cs.FrequencyCode = 2 then 12 else 1 end))/2.0) * (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))/100.0) * Crate.FACTOR) 
							--(Ave AUM X OGS Rate X COB FCA Rate)...
							- ((((cs.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(cs.Premium,0) * (case when cs.FrequencyCode = 2 then 12 else 1 end))/2.0) * (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))/100.0) * Cfca.FACTOR))
							--Sign correctly for +ve or clawback payment
							* (case when cs.INIssued < 0 then -1 else 1 end)   
				--REGULAR end
				
				else 0.0

				--WEALTH ONGOING CALCULATION END
			end as OngoingYr01,
			0.0 as OngoingYr02,
			0.0 as OngoingYr03,
			0.0 as OngoingYr04,
			0.0 as OngoingYr05,
			0.0 as OngoingYr06,
			0.0 as OngoingYr07,
			0.0 as OngoingYr08,
			0.0 as OngoingYr09,
			0.0 as OngoingYr10,
			case 
				when (ph.ProductCategoryCode = 1 or pcc.KeyValue2 = '1') then Cfca.FACTOR*100.0		--COB
				when ph.ProductGroupCode = 3 then Mfca.FACTOR*100.0		--MORT
				when ph.ProductGroupCode = 6 then Pfca.FACTOR*100.0		--PROT
				else 0.0
			end as FCARate,
			case 
				when (ph.ProductCategoryCode = 1 or pcc.KeyValue2 = '1') then Crate.FACTOR*100.0	--COB
				when ph.ProductGroupCode = 3 then MRproc.FACTOR*100.0	--MORT
				when ph.ProductGroupCode = 6 then Prate.FACTOR*100.0	--PROT
				else 0.0
			end as RetentionRate,
			case 
				when mbf.MortgageFeeID is not null then  MRbkr.FACTOR*100.0	
				else 0.0
			end as RetentionRateBroker,
			case when SFMpot.ID is not null
				then coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))
				else null
			end as OngoingServicingRate,
			case when SFMpot.ID is not null
				then case 
						when ogs.OngoingServiceFee is null and ogscli.OngoingServiceFee is null 
							then case
								when ogsdflt.KeyValue = 'ONPLAT' then 'Default - On Plat'
								else 'Default - Off Plat'
							end
						when ogs.OngoingServiceFee is not null then 'Client Product'
						when ogscli.OngoingServiceFee is not null then 'Client Only'
						else 'Unknown'
					 end
				else case when (ph.ProductCategoryCode = 1 or pcc.KeyValue2 = '1')
						then 'No OGS'					--WEALTH, but no OGS
						else null						--Not WEALTH, so OGS is n/a and is therefore null
					 end
			end as OngoingServicingSource,
			pt.CommInitialAmount as DA,
			e.AMOUNT_REC as AmountReceived,
			cs.Premium,
			cs.AgentSplit,
			cs.CommissionType,
			left(cs.StandingOrderDesc,50) as CommissionTypeDesc,
			cs.Month,
			cs.FrequencyCode,
			cs.FrequencyDesc,
			'VNB' as RecognitionType,
			case 
				when (ph.ProductCategoryCode = 1 or pcc.KeyValue2 = '1') then 'WEALTH'
				when ph.ProductGroupCode = 3 then 'MORTGAGE'
				when ph.ProductGroupCode = 6 then 'PROTECTION'
				else null
			end as CalculationType,
			'Openwork 2006' as Source,
			@DateLastUpdated as DateInserted,
			@DateLastUpdated as DateLastUpdated,
			csp.year as CommissionYear
	--select count(*)
	from	msit_CommissionStatement cs
/*			inner join (select	distinct PKID
						from	owt_TransformationMovements tm 
						where	tm.DriverTableName = 'sa_swift_S_AGMFIL'
						and		tm.CommissionStatement = 'Y') tm on tm.PKID = cs.PendingPaymentID
*/			inner join mstt_Agents ag on ag.Code = cs.BusinessCode
			inner join mstt_PolicyTransactions pt on pt.ID = cs.TransactionID
			inner join mstt_Policies p on p.POL_NUM = pt.PolicyID
			inner join msit_CommissionStatementPeriods VNBStart on convert(date,pt.CreateDateTime) between VNBStart.PeriodStartDate and VNBStart.PeriodEndDate
			inner join msit_Commissionstatementperiods csp on csp.month = cs.month
			inner join mstt_ProductHierarchy ph on ph.productcode = cs.productcode
			inner join mstt_Expectation e on e.ID = cs.ExpectationID
			left join dbo.owt_MortgageBrokerFees mbf on mbf.PendingPaymentID = cs.PendingPaymentID and mbf.AdviceFeeCharged = 'Yes'
			left join owt_SelectionControl SC
						on SC.Process = 'ElitePoints' 
						and SC.KeyType = 'NSCPotCode' 
						and cs.CreateDate between SC.EffectiveStartDate and SC.EffectiveEndDate
			left join mstt_Commissions BSCpot
						on BSCpot.TransactionID = cs.TransactionID 
						and BSCpot.Agent_Code = sc.KeyValue
						and BSCpot.CommissionType = 10
			left join owt_SelectionControl SFMPC						
						on SFMPC.Process = 'ElitePoints' 
						and SFMPC.KeyType = 'ServicingFeeMarginPotCode' 
						and cs.CreateDate between SFMPC.EffectiveStartDate and SFMPC.EffectiveEndDate
			left join mstt_Commissions SFMpot							
						on SFMpot.TransactionID = cs.TransactionID 
						and SFMpot.Agent_Code = SFMPC.KeyValue
						and SFMpot.CommissionType = 10	
			left join owt_SelectionControl pcc 
						on pcc.Process = 'ElitePoints'
						and pcc.KeyType = 'ProductCategoryCode'
						and pcc.KeyValue = cs.ProductCode	
						and cs.CreateDate between pcc.EffectiveStartDate and pcc.EffectiveEndDate
			left join owt_SelectionControl ogsdflt 
						on ogsdflt.Process = 'ElitePoints'
						and ogsdflt.KeyType = 'DefaultOngoingServicingRate'
						and ogsdflt.SelectionType = 'VNB'
						and ogsdflt.KeyValue = case when ph.RDRType = 'ONPLAT' then 'ONPLAT' else 'OFPLAT' end
						and cs.CreateDate between ogsdflt.EffectiveStartDate and ogsdflt.EffectiveEndDate
			left join owt_EliteFactors Cfca on Cfca.FeeType = 'VNB' and Cfca.category = 'COB-FCA-RATE' and csp.year between Cfca.StartYear and Cfca.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors Crate on Crate.FeeType = 'VNB' and Crate.category = 'COB-RETENTION-RATE' and csp.year between Crate.StartYear and Crate.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors Mfca on Mfca.FeeType = 'VNB' and Mfca.category = 'MORT-FCA-RATE' and csp.year between Mfca.StartYear and Mfca.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors MRproc on MRproc.FeeType = 'VNB' and MRproc.category = 'MORT-RETENTION-RATE-PROC' and csp.year between MRproc.StartYear and MRproc.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors MRbkr on MRbkr.FeeType = 'VNB' and MRbkr.category = 'MORT-RETENTION-RATE-BROKER' and csp.year between MRbkr.StartYear and MRbkr.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors Pfca on Pfca.FeeType = 'VNB' and Pfca.category = 'PROT-FCA-RATE' and csp.year between Pfca.StartYear and Pfca.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors Prate on Prate.FeeType = 'VNB' and Prate.category = 'PROT-RETENTION-RATE' and csp.year between Prate.StartYear and Prate.EndYear 
			left join #OGSLookUp ogs on ogs.CLIENT_NUM = cs.ClientID and ogs.ProductCode = cs.ProductCode
			left join #OGSLookUpClient ogscli on ogscli.CLIENT_NUM = cs.ClientID 
	where	cs.ReportingClassCode = 1
	and		ag.Manager2Code <> @OwlManager2Code		--Exclude Owl
	--and		p.PolicyRef in (1460996,1714642,550842754,551078732,550951391,550771221)
	and		cs.INIssued <> 0
	--and		cs.PendingPaymentID = 39709463
	and		VNBStart.Year >= 2017			--VNB to start from 2017
	and		csp.Year >= 2017				--Ensure in-scope payments are consistent with VNB start

	select @RowCount = @@rowcount
	set @ProcessMessage = '#owt_Recognition = ' + convert(nvarchar(10), @RowCount)
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseLog, @ProcessMessage, null, @Module, @Client
	
	/****************************************************************************

		Now calculate the ongoing spread for each of 10 years.
		Note that regular payments get an additional multiplier to uplift the 
		average AUM for each year.
																		
	****************************************************************************/

	update r
		set OngoingYr02 = case when r.FrequencyCode = 2							--Monthly
							then r.OngoingYr01 * YR02.Multiplier * YR02.Factor	--Regular
							else r.OngoingYr01 * YR02.Factor					--Single
						  end,
			OngoingYr03 = case when r.FrequencyCode = 2							--Monthly
							then r.OngoingYr01 * YR03.Multiplier * YR03.Factor	--Regular
							else r.OngoingYr01 * YR03.Factor					--Single
						  end,
			OngoingYr04 = case when r.FrequencyCode = 2							--Monthly
							then r.OngoingYr01 * YR04.Multiplier * YR04.Factor	--Regular
							else r.OngoingYr01 * YR04.Factor					--Single
						  end,
			OngoingYr05 = case when r.FrequencyCode = 2							--Monthly 
							then r.OngoingYr01 * YR05.Multiplier * YR05.Factor	--Regular
							else r.OngoingYr01 * YR05.Factor					--Single
						  end,
			OngoingYr06 = case when r.FrequencyCode = 2							--Monthly 
							then r.OngoingYr01 * YR06.Multiplier * YR06.Factor	--Regular
							else r.OngoingYr01 * YR06.Factor					--Single
						  end,
			OngoingYr07 = case when r.FrequencyCode = 2							--Monthly 
							then r.OngoingYr01 * YR07.Multiplier * YR07.Factor	--Regular
							else r.OngoingYr01 * YR07.Factor					--Single
						  end,
			OngoingYr08 = case when r.FrequencyCode = 2							--Monthly 
							then r.OngoingYr01 * YR08.Multiplier * YR08.Factor	--Regular
							else r.OngoingYr01 * YR08.Factor					--Single
						  end,
			OngoingYr09 = case when r.FrequencyCode = 2							--Monthly 
							then r.OngoingYr01 * YR09.Multiplier * YR09.Factor	--Regular
							else r.OngoingYr01 * YR09.Factor					--Single
						  end,
			OngoingYr10 = case when r.FrequencyCode = 2							--Monthly 
							then r.OngoingYr01 * YR10.Multiplier * YR10.Factor	--Regular
							else r.OngoingYr01 * YR10.Factor					--Single
						   end
	from	#owt_Recognition r
			left join owt_EliteFactors YR01 on YR01.FeeType = 'VNB' and YR01.Category = 'COB-ONGOING-DISCOUNT-YR01' and r.CommissionYear between YR01.StartYear and YR01.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors YR02 on YR02.FeeType = 'VNB' and YR02.Category = 'COB-ONGOING-DISCOUNT-YR02' and r.CommissionYear between YR02.StartYear and YR02.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors YR03 on YR03.FeeType = 'VNB' and YR03.Category = 'COB-ONGOING-DISCOUNT-YR03' and r.CommissionYear between YR03.StartYear and YR03.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors YR04 on YR04.FeeType = 'VNB' and YR04.Category = 'COB-ONGOING-DISCOUNT-YR04' and r.CommissionYear between YR04.StartYear and YR04.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors YR05 on YR05.FeeType = 'VNB' and YR05.Category = 'COB-ONGOING-DISCOUNT-YR05' and r.CommissionYear between YR05.StartYear and YR05.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors YR06 on YR06.FeeType = 'VNB' and YR06.Category = 'COB-ONGOING-DISCOUNT-YR06' and r.CommissionYear between YR06.StartYear and YR06.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors YR07 on YR07.FeeType = 'VNB' and YR07.Category = 'COB-ONGOING-DISCOUNT-YR07' and r.CommissionYear between YR07.StartYear and YR07.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors YR08 on YR08.FeeType = 'VNB' and YR08.Category = 'COB-ONGOING-DISCOUNT-YR08' and r.CommissionYear between YR08.StartYear and YR08.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors YR09 on YR09.FeeType = 'VNB' and YR09.Category = 'COB-ONGOING-DISCOUNT-YR09' and r.CommissionYear between YR09.StartYear and YR09.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors YR10 on YR10.FeeType = 'VNB' and YR10.Category = 'COB-ONGOING-DISCOUNT-YR10' and r.CommissionYear between YR10.StartYear and YR10.EndYear 

	select @RowCount = @@rowcount
	set @ProcessMessage = '#owt_Recognition (ongoing) = ' + convert(nvarchar(10), @RowCount)
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseLog, @ProcessMessage, null, @Module, @Client

	/****************************************************************************

		Now add up all the numbers
																		
	****************************************************************************/
	
	update r
		set OngoingTotal	=	OngoingYr01 + OngoingYr02 + OngoingYr03 + OngoingYr04 + OngoingYr05 +
								OngoingYr06 + OngoingYr07 + OngoingYr08 + OngoingYr09 + OngoingYr10,
			PointsTotal		=	OngoingYr01 + OngoingYr02 + OngoingYr03 + OngoingYr04 + OngoingYr05 +
								OngoingYr06 + OngoingYr07 + OngoingYr08 + OngoingYr09 + OngoingYr10 +
								Initial + MBF	-- Note BSC is already included in the Ongoing, so don't include it in the Points Total.
	from	#owt_Recognition r

	select @RowCount = @@rowcount
	set @ProcessMessage = '#owt_Recognition (totals) = ' + convert(nvarchar(10), @RowCount)
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseLog, @ProcessMessage, null, @Module, @Client

	/****************************************************************************

		Merge the temporary table into the permanent table
																		
	****************************************************************************/

	BEGIN TRANSACTION

	declare @SummaryOfChanges table (Change varchar(20))
	merge	dbo.owt_Recognition as trg
	using	#owt_Recognition as src
	on		trg.SourceID = src.SourceID
	and		trg.Source = src.Source
	when	matched 
	and		isnull(trg.PointsTotal,0) <> isnull(src.PointsTotal,0)
	then	update 
				set trg.CaseID = src.CaseID,
					trg.TransactionID = src.TransactionID,
					trg.Policy = src.Policy,
					trg.ProductCode = src.ProductCode,
					trg.BusinessCode = src.BusinessCode,
					trg.PointsTotal = src.PointsTotal,
					trg.BSC = src.BSC,
					trg.MBF = src.MBF,
					trg.Initial = src.Initial,
					trg.OngoingTotal = src.OngoingTotal,
					trg.OngoingYr01 = src.OngoingYr01,
					trg.OngoingYr02 = src.OngoingYr02,
					trg.OngoingYr03 = src.OngoingYr03,
					trg.OngoingYr04 = src.OngoingYr04,
					trg.OngoingYr05 = src.OngoingYr05,
					trg.OngoingYr06 = src.OngoingYr06,
					trg.OngoingYr07 = src.OngoingYr07,
					trg.OngoingYr08 = src.OngoingYr08,
					trg.OngoingYr09 = src.OngoingYr09,
					trg.OngoingYr10 = src.OngoingYr10,
					trg.FCARate = src.FCARate,
					trg.RetentionRate = src.RetentionRate,
					trg.RetentionRateBroker = src.RetentionRateBroker,
					trg.OngoingServicingRate = src.OngoingServicingRate,
					trg.OngoingServicingSource = src.OngoingServicingSource,
					trg.DA = src.DA,
					trg.AmountReceived = src.AmountReceived,
					trg.Premium = src.Premium,
					trg.AgentSplit = src.AgentSplit,
					trg.CommissionType = src.CommissionType,
					trg.CommissionTypeDesc = src.CommissionTypeDesc,
					trg.Month = src.Month,
					trg.FrequencyCode = src.FrequencyCode,
					trg.FrequencyDesc = src.FrequencyDesc,
					trg.RecognitionType = src.RecognitionType,
					trg.CalculationType = src.CalculationType,
					trg.DateLastUpdated = @DateLastUpdated
	when	not matched by target 
	then	insert
			(
				SourceID,
				CaseID,
				TransactionID,
				Policy,
				ProductCode,
				BusinessCode,
				PointsTotal,
				BSC,
				MBF,
				Initial,
				OngoingTotal,
				OngoingYr01,
				OngoingYr02,
				OngoingYr03,
				OngoingYr04,
				OngoingYr05,
				OngoingYr06,
				OngoingYr07,
				OngoingYr08,
				OngoingYr09,
				OngoingYr10,
				FCARate,
				RetentionRate,
				RetentionRateBroker,
				OngoingServicingRate,
				OngoingServicingSource,
				DA,
				AmountReceived,
				Premium,
				AgentSplit,
				CommissionType,
				CommissionTypeDesc,
				Month,
				FrequencyCode,
				FrequencyDesc,
				RecognitionType,
				CalculationType,
				Source,
				DateInserted,
				DateLastUpdated
			)		
			values
			(
				src.SourceID,
				src.CaseID,
				src.TransactionID,
				src.Policy,
				src.ProductCode,
				src.BusinessCode,
				src.PointsTotal,
				src.BSC,
				src.MBF,
				src.Initial,
				src.OngoingTotal,
				src.OngoingYr01,
				src.OngoingYr02,
				src.OngoingYr03,
				src.OngoingYr04,
				src.OngoingYr05,
				src.OngoingYr06,
				src.OngoingYr07,
				src.OngoingYr08,
				src.OngoingYr09,
				src.OngoingYr10,
				src.FCARate,
				src.RetentionRate,
				src.RetentionRateBroker,
				src.OngoingServicingRate,
				src.OngoingServicingSource,
				src.DA,
				src.AmountReceived,
				src.Premium,
				src.AgentSplit,
				src.CommissionType,
				src.CommissionTypeDesc,
				src.Month,
				src.FrequencyCode,
				src.FrequencyDesc,
				src.RecognitionType,
				src.CalculationType,
				src.Source,
				src.DateInserted,
				src.DateLastUpdated)				--Merge statements must have a ;
	output $action into @SummaryOfChanges;
	
	COMMIT TRANSACTION      

	select	@RowCount = COUNT(*)
	from	@SummaryOfChanges
	where	Change = 'INSERT'

	set @ProcessMessage = 'owt_Recognition (insert) = ' + convert(nvarchar(10), @RowCount)
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseLog, @ProcessMessage, null, @Module, @Client

	select	@RowCount = COUNT(*)
	from	@SummaryOfChanges
	where	Change = 'UPDATE'

	set @ProcessMessage = 'owt_Recognition (update) = ' + convert(nvarchar(10), @RowCount)
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseLog, @ProcessMessage, null, @Module, @Client

	/****************************************************************************

		T H E   E N D
																		
	****************************************************************************/
	
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseEnd, @ProcName, null, @Module, @Client

END TRY

BEGIN CATCH 

	select @ErrNum = ERROR_NUMBER(), @ErrMsg = ERROR_MESSAGE(), @ErrSev = ERROR_SEVERITY(), @ErrLine = ERROR_LINE(), @ErrState = XACT_STATE()
	set @ErrMsg = REPLACE(@ErrMsg, '.', '') + ' (error no: ' + CAST(@ErrNum AS VARCHAR(10)) + ') on line ' + CAST(@ErrLine AS VARCHAR(10))
	
	-- Test XACT_STATE for 0, 1, or -1.
    -- If 1, the transaction is committable.
    -- If -1, the transaction is uncommittable and should be rolled back.
    -- If 0, there is no transaction and a commit or rollback operation would generate an error.

	if @ErrState = -1			-- Transaction is uncommitable
		rollback transaction

	if @ErrState = 1			
		commit transaction

	-- Error message line 1
	set @ErrMsgBrief = left(@ErrMsg,100)
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseError, @ErrMsgBrief, null, @Module, @Client
	
	-- Error message line 2 - if any text exists
	set @ErrMsgBrief = substring(@ErrMsg,101,100)
	if len(@ErrMsgBrief) > 0
		exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseError, @ErrMsgBrief, null, @Module, @Client

	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseEnd, @ProcName, null, @Module, @Client

	RAISERROR(@ErrMsg, @ErrSev , 1)

END CATCH

/****************************************************************************

			E N D															

****************************************************************************/

return @ErrNum



GO
/****** Object:  StoredProcedure [dbo].[owp_RecognitionSwiftONGOING_Backup20180627AG]    Script Date: 7/3/2026 3:44:25 PM ******/
SET ANSI_NULLS ON
GO
SET QUOTED_IDENTIFIER ON
GO
/*********************************************************************************************************

Program:		owp_RecognitionSwift					
Author:			Alan Groves
Date created:	11/04/2018
											
Description:
===========

This proc populates the new recognition table called "owt_Recognition" with "Value of New Business"
(VNB) points.

This proc handles all of the swift data which includes:
WEALTH - COB business i.e. pensions and investments
MORTGAGES
PROTECTION

Note: There is a separate proc that calculates the GI VNB points from the Paymentshield data.

The approach of this proc is to use the incremental PendingPaymentIDs from the overnight batch
to calculate the VNB points in a temporary table.

The temporary table is then merged with the permanent table to make the calculated (or
re-calculated values) permanent.

Terms
-----
BSC			- Business Service Charge.
MBF			- Mortgage Broker Fee.
OGS			- Ongoing Servicing.
BSC Rate	- 0.12% at the time of writing (24/04/2018). This could be changed by the business, but
				would also require some DEV work in OWS.
DF			- Discount Factor.
DA			- Distribution Allowance (the total amount paid out by the provider to Openwork)
AUM			- Assets Under Management. Basically the amount invested or the premium on investment
				cases.
Average AUM - Average amount invested annually which is equivalent to 6 months' premium.

THE CALCULATIONS
================

There are two potential parts: initial + ongoing (if ongoing applies). If BSC (applies to ongoing 
only) and MBF (applies to mortgages only) apply, then these are also included:

MORTGAGE
--------
Part 1: MBF column = (Advice Fee Amount X Broker Retention Rate) - (Advice Fee Amount X Mort FCA Rate)
Part 2: Initial column = (Proc Fee Amount X Mortgage Retention Rate) - (Proc Fee X Mort FCA Rate) 
Mortgage Points Total = Initial + MBF

PROTECTION
----------
= (DA X Protection Retention Rate) - (DA X Protection FCA Rate) 
Protection Points Total = Initial

WEALTH (COB i.e. pensions and investments)
------
Part 1: Initial column = (DA X Wealth Retention Rate) - (DA X Wealth FCA Rate)

Part 2:

****XXXX****

NOTE: Where the BSC rate is greater than the ongoing rate, then BSC gets ALL of the AVAILABLE 
ongoing.

****XXXX****

REGULAR - BSC applies:
Year 1 column = BSC Points + Non-BSC Points - FCA Points
Non-BSC Points = Ave AUM X (OGS Rate - BSC Rate) X COB Retention Rate
BSC Points = Ave AUM X BSC Rate
FCA Points = Ave AUM X OGS Rate X COB FCA Rate

REGULAR - Non-BSC: 
Year 1 column = (Ave AUM X OGS Rate X COB Retention Rate) - (Ave AUM X OGS Rate X COB FCA Rate)

SINGLE - BSC applies:
Year 1 column = (AUM X BSC Rate) + (AUM X (OGS Rate - BSC Rate) X COB Retention Rate) - (AUM X OGS Rate X COB FCA Rate) 

SINGLE - Non-BSC:
Year 1 column = (AUM X OGS Rate X COB Retention Rate) - (AUM X OGS Rate X COB FCA Rate) 

Then years 2 to 10 are calculated by applying a discount factor
Year  2 = Year 1 X  3 X DF
Year  3 = Year 1 X  5 X DF
Year  4 = Year 1 X  7 X DF
Year  5 = Year 1 X  9 X DF
Year  6 = Year 1 X 11 X DF
Year  7 = Year 1 X 13 X DF
Year  8 = Year 1 X 15 X DF
Year  9 = Year 1 X 17 X DF
Year 10 = Year 1 X 19 X DF

Wealth Points Total =	OngoingYr01 + OngoingYr02 + OngoingYr03 + OngoingYr04 + OngoingYr05 +
						OngoingYr06 + OngoingYr07 + OngoingYr08 + OngoingYr09 + OngoingYr10 +
						Initial

GI
--
See stored proc "owp_RecognitionGIPaymentshield".
 
Notes:
-----

There is a BSC column on table owt_Recognition. However, BSC is already included in the ongoing
years 1 - 10, so the BSC column does not need to be added in. In fact you will double count if 
you attempt to do anything with it other than display it.


This proc is called as follows:
	declare @rc int
	exec @rc = dbo.owp_RecognitionSwift 'Openwork', 'Recognition'
	select @rc

					
AMENDMENT HISTORY				
=================								

Date		Author		Description
----		------		-----------
26/04/2018	A Groves	Only include rows in the OGS lookups where the OngoingServiceFee > 0.0.
						Negative OGS rates are bad data and at the time of writing, there are
						39 of these.
27/04/2018	A Groves	Additional calculation and condition to handle the scenario where BSC applies
						but the OGS Rate is less than the BSC rate. Previously, this caused the
						total ongoing to be zero. However, there are two components to ongoing VNB 
						points, the BSC share and the non-BSC share. So the BSC share (which takes 
						100% when the OGS rate is less than 0.12%) should still yield ongoing points.
27/04/2018	A Groves	Single ongoing Yr01 corrected by applying outer brackets before signing the result.
03/05/2018	A Groves	Added update of column "msit_OpenworkAdviserListing.VNB_Points".
18/05/2018	A Groves	Changed mortgage calculation to use e.AMOUNT_REC instead of pt.CommInitialAmount
						as Marcus Cossey wanted the actual amount received to be used for the DA.
04/06/2018	A Groves	1) In the REGULAR section of column "OngoingYr01", the condition for cs.FrequencyCode <> 6
							was added to ensure the code differentiates to the SINGLE section.
						2) Exclude MBF from the OpenAccess table (msit_OpenworkAdviserListing) as this
							is shown on the MBF download and would otherwise incur MBF double counting.
05/06/2018	A Groves	1) Marcus Cossey advised that investments should get ongoing for years 1 to 6 and
							pensions for years 1 to 10. Previously, both lines of business got years 1 to 10.
						2) Marcus Cossey asked for split payments (i.e. where multiple cheques are processed
							for a SINGLE investment) to only claculate ongoing VNB on the oldest payment. 
11/06/2018	A Groves	1) PSD processed a protection clawback statement as fee type initial. These clawbacks
							all generated +ve instead of -ve VNB points. A tweak was added to ensure that the 
							absolute value of AMOUNT_REC is used to ensure the VNB is correctly signed. 
						2) Another unknown business rule has surfaced: Previously, only initial, clawbacks and
							adjustments on slices created new from 2017 were included. This rule only applies
							to initial. Clawbacks and adjustments can belong to a slice created at any point
							in the past. However, note that the payment (irrespective of whether it is +ve or 
							-ve), must not pre-date 2017.
13/06/2018	A Groves	Marcus asked for SellerCode and PaymentMatchedDate to be added so he need only use 
							the one table for both the adviser and enterprise leagues. PayBasisCode and 
							PayBasisDesc were also added at the same time as these are used in the calculations.
*************************************************************************************************************/

CREATE PROCEDURE [dbo].[owp_RecognitionSwiftONGOING_Backup20180627AG]
	@Client		varchar(50),
	@Module		Varchar(50)

AS

set nocount on

declare		@PhaseStart				varchar(50),
			@PhaseEnd				varchar(50),
			@PhaseError				varchar(50),
			@PhaseLog				varchar(50),
			@ProcName				varchar(100),
			@ProcessMessage			varchar(100),
			@RowCount				int,
			@OALRowCount			int,
			@ErrMsg					nvarchar(4000),
			@ErrMsgBrief			nvarchar(100),
			@ErrNum					int,
			@ErrSev					int,
			@ErrLine				int,
			@ErrState				int,
			@DateLastUpdated		datetime,
			@OwlManager2Code		nvarchar(10)
			
/****************************************************************************

	Set initial parameters																
																		
****************************************************************************/

set @ProcName			= object_name(@@procid)
set @PhaseStart			= 'START'
set @PhaseEnd			= 'END'
set @PhaseError			= 'ERROR'
set @PhaseLog			= 'LOG'
set @ErrNum				= 0	
set @DateLastUpdated	= getdate()

set @OwlManager2Code = (select cde.Code from msit_MIWarehouseCodesAndDescriptions cde
			where cde.ColumnName = 'Manager2Code' and cde.Description = 'Owl Financial')

-- We want this logging irrespective of whether or not there is a rollback
exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseStart, @ProcName, null, @Module, @Client

/****************************************************************************

	Populate the table																
																		
****************************************************************************/

SET XACT_ABORT ON	-- Needed if XACT_STATE() function is used.

BEGIN TRY

	/****************************************************************************

		Link OWS data to Swift data to enable the ongoing servicng (OGS) rate
		to be looked up.
																		
	****************************************************************************/
	
	select	distinct s.PersonID, swp.Client_Num, p.InternalProductID, swp.ProductCode 
	into	#SwiftOWSClientLink
	from	sa_ows_Sale s
			inner join sa_ows_Policies p on p.SaleID = s.SaleID
			inner join mstt_Policies swp on swp.PolicyRef = p.PolicyID
	where	s.DateSubmitted is not null
	--and		s.PersonID = 146030

	select @RowCount = @@rowcount
	set @ProcessMessage = '#SwiftOWSClientLink = ' + convert(nvarchar(10), @RowCount)
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseLog, @ProcessMessage, null, @Module, @Client

	-- The OGS rate is stored for the client/product combination
	select	link.Client_Num, link.ProductCode, max(ogs.OngoingServiceFee) as OngoingServiceFee
	into	#OGSLookUp
	from	#SwiftOWSClientLink link 
			inner join mstt_ProductHierarchy ph on ph.ProductCode = link.ProductCode
			inner join Submission.sa_ows_SubmittedProductCurrentOngoingServiceFee ogs
							on ogs.PersonID = link.PersonID
							and ogs.InternalProductID = (case when ph.RDRType = 'ONPLAT' 
															then -2 
															else link.InternalProductID 
														 end)
	where	ogs.OngoingServiceFee > 0.0							--AG 26/04/2018
	group	by 	link.Client_Num, link.ProductCode

	select @RowCount = @@rowcount
	set @ProcessMessage = '#OGSLookUp = ' + convert(nvarchar(10), @RowCount)
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseLog, @ProcessMessage, null, @Module, @Client

	create index idx_OGSLookUp on #OGSLookUp (Client_num, ProductCode)

	--This is an additional catch for OGS by storing the client's highest OGS
	--rate against their client number. This lookup will apply if the first
	--look up fails. The first lookup can fail, for example, if the case was 
	--not submitted on OWS i.e. the CaseID has a "17" prefix. 
	select	Client_Num, MAX(OngoingServiceFee) as OngoingServiceFee
	into	#OGSLookUpClient
	from	#OGSLookUp
	group	by Client_Num

	select @RowCount = @@rowcount
	set @ProcessMessage = '#OGSLookUpClient = ' + convert(nvarchar(10), @RowCount)
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseLog, @ProcessMessage, null, @Module, @Client
	
	create index idx_OGSLookUpClient on #OGSLookUpClient (Client_num)

	/****************************************************************************

		Calculate VNB and populate the temporary table with the results
		
		Note that there are oddities like LV protection payments which always
		come in pairs with one large and one much smaller amount (e.g. TransactionID 
		= 6684787.) The system treats both payments in the pair as first payments 
		and the (projected) DA associated with both is the same (because it's on 
		the policy transaction). 
		
		There is also a requirement to front-load VNB points on accrual and level
		payments. This means calculate the VNB for the full amount of the DA and 
		put it on the first payment record and then on all subsequent accrual and 
		level payments, set the VNB to zero.
		
		Thus two different sources of DA are used depending on whether we need the
		full DA amount for accruals and level or the actual amount received for all
		other scenarios including the LV split payment scenario. The two sources are:
		
		mstt_PolicyTransactions.CommInitialAmount - Full (projected) DA amount
		
		mstt_Expectation.AMOUNT_REC - The DA actually received. This handles the
										LV scenario whereby the AMOUNT_REC is 
										proportioned across the two payments received.   
																		
	****************************************************************************/

	select	top 0 
			*, 
			convert(int,NULL) as CommissionYear
	into	#AG_owt_Recognition_SEPARATE_ONGOING
	from	AG_owt_Recognition_SEPARATE_ONGOING

	/****************************************************************************

		Phase 1 - Process all but regular accrual cases with clawbacks/adjustments
		Accruals are front loaded unless their latest payment is a clawback/adjudtment
		in which case they accrue VNB points on a per payment basis and so these
		are dealt with in Phases 2 and 3.
																		
	****************************************************************************/

	insert into #AG_owt_Recognition_SEPARATE_ONGOING
	(
		SourceID,
		CaseID,
		TransactionID,
		Policy,
		ProductCode,
		BusinessCode,
		SellerCode,						--AG 13/06/2018
		PointsTotal,
		BSC,
		MBF,
		Initial,
		OngoingTotal,
		OngoingYr01,
		OngoingYr02,
		OngoingYr03,
		OngoingYr04,
		OngoingYr05,
		OngoingYr06,
		OngoingYr07,
		OngoingYr08,
		OngoingYr09,
		OngoingYr10,
		FCARate,
		RetentionRate,
		RetentionRateBroker,
		OngoingServicingRate,
		OngoingServicingSource,
		DA,
		AmountReceived,
		Premium,
		AgentSplit,
		CommissionType,
		CommissionTypeDesc,
		PayBasisCode,					--AG 13/06/2018
		PayBasisDesc,					--AG 13/06/2018
		PaymentMatchedDate,				--AG 13/06/2018
		Month,
		FrequencyCode,
		FrequencyDesc,
		ReassignedProductGroupCode,		--AG 05/06/2018
		ReassignedProductGroupName,		--AG 05/06/2018
		RecognitionType,
		CalculationType,
		Source,
		DateInserted,
		DateLastUpdated,
		CommissionYear
	)
	select	cs.PendingPaymentID as SourceID,
			cs.CaseID,
			cs.TransactionID,
			cs.ExtPolicyNumber as Policy,
			cs.ProductCode,
			cs.BusinessCode,
			cs.AgentCode as SellerCode,				--AG 13/06/2018
			0.0 as PointsTotal,
			0.0 as BSC,
			case 
				when mbf.MortgageFeeID is not null and cs.INIssued <> 0 then (((mbf.AdviceFeeAmount)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * MRbkr.FACTOR) - ((mbf.AdviceFeeAmount)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * Mfca.FACTOR)) --Note that mbf.AdviceFeeAmount is signed correctly - so no coding for signing is needed here
				else 0.0
			end as MBF,
			case 
				--When the adviser has changed, the AgentSplit can become zero in which case the ELITE points should be zero.
				when cs.AgentSplit = 0 then 0
				
				--WEALTH CALCULATION START
				--Indemnity payments or SINGLEs or IC Clawbacks or IC adjustments Start
				when (ph.ProductCategoryCode = 1 or pcc.KeyValue2 = '1') and (cs.FrequencyCode = 6 or cs.PayBasisCode in ('T') or cs.CommissionType in (2,17)) and cs.commissiontype in (1,2,17) and cs.INIssued <> 0 then (((e.AMOUNT_REC)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * Crate.FACTOR) - ((e.AMOUNT_REC)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * Cfca.FACTOR)) * case when cs.INIssued < 0 then -1 else 1 end
				--Indemnity payments or SINGLEs or IC Clawbacks or IC adjustments End
				--Accruals & Level Start
				when (ph.ProductCategoryCode = 1 or pcc.KeyValue2 = '1') and cs.INIssued <> 0 then (((pt.CommInitialAmount)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * Crate.FACTOR) - ((pt.CommInitialAmount)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * Cfca.FACTOR)) * case when cs.INIssued < 0 then -1 else 1 end
				--Accruals & Level End
				--WEALTH CALCULATION END
				
				--MORTGAGE CALCULATION START
				--Note: The MBF component has its own table column
				--Only 1 payment for mortgages
				when ph.ProductGroupCode = 3 and cs.INIssued <> 0 then (((e.AMOUNT_REC)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * MRproc.FACTOR) - ((e.AMOUNT_REC)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * Mfca.FACTOR)) * case when cs.INIssued < 0 then -1 else 1 end	--AG 18/05/2018
				--MORTGAGE CALCULATION END
				
				--PROTECTION CALCULATION START
				--Indemnity payments or SINGLEs or IC Clawbacks or IC adjustments Start
				when ph.ProductGroupCode = 6 and (cs.FrequencyCode = 6 or cs.PayBasisCode in ('T') or cs.CommissionType in (2,17)) and cs.commissiontype in (1,2,17) and cs.INIssued <> 0 then ((abs(e.AMOUNT_REC)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * Prate.FACTOR) - (abs(e.AMOUNT_REC)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * Pfca.FACTOR)) * case when cs.INIssued < 0 then -1 else 1 end	--AG 11/06/2018 (1)
				--Indemnity payments or SINGLEs or IC Clawbacks or IC adjustments End
				--Accruals & Level Start
				when ph.ProductGroupCode = 6 and cs.INIssued <> 0 then (((pt.CommInitialAmount)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * Prate.FACTOR) - ((pt.CommInitialAmount)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * Pfca.FACTOR)) * case when cs.INIssued < 0 then -1 else 1 end
				--Accruals & Level End
				--PROTECTION CALCULATION END

				else 0.0

			end as Initial,
			0.0 as OngoingTotal,
			0.0 as OngoingYr01,
			0.0 as OngoingYr02,
			0.0 as OngoingYr03,
			0.0 as OngoingYr04,
			0.0 as OngoingYr05,
			0.0 as OngoingYr06,
			0.0 as OngoingYr07,
			0.0 as OngoingYr08,
			0.0 as OngoingYr09,
			0.0 as OngoingYr10,
			case 
				when (ph.ProductCategoryCode = 1 or pcc.KeyValue2 = '1') then Cfca.FACTOR*100.0		--COB
				when ph.ProductGroupCode = 3 then Mfca.FACTOR*100.0		--MORT
				when ph.ProductGroupCode = 6 then Pfca.FACTOR*100.0		--PROT
				else 0.0
			end as FCARate,
			case 
				when (ph.ProductCategoryCode = 1 or pcc.KeyValue2 = '1') then Crate.FACTOR*100.0	--COB
				when ph.ProductGroupCode = 3 then MRproc.FACTOR*100.0	--MORT
				when ph.ProductGroupCode = 6 then Prate.FACTOR*100.0	--PROT
				else 0.0
			end as RetentionRate,
			case 
				when mbf.MortgageFeeID is not null then  MRbkr.FACTOR*100.0	
				else 0.0
			end as RetentionRateBroker,
			null as OngoingServicingRate,
			null as OngoingServicingSource,
			pt.CommInitialAmount as DA,
			e.AMOUNT_REC as AmountReceived,
			cs.Premium,
			cs.AgentSplit,
			cs.CommissionType,
			left(cs.StandingOrderDesc,50) as CommissionTypeDesc,
			cs.PayBasisCode,							--AG 13/06/2018
			cs.PayBasisDesc,							--AG 13/06/2018
			cs.CreateDate as PaymentMatchedDate,		--AG 13/06/2018
			cs.Month,
			cs.FrequencyCode,
			cs.FrequencyDesc,
			pg.ProductGroupCode as ReassignedProductGroupCode,	--Force the re-assigned products...		AG 05/06/2018
			pg.ProductGroupName as ReassignedProductGroupName,	--...to be processed as investments		AG 05/06/2018
			'VNB-PHASE-1' as RecognitionType,
			case 
				when (ph.ProductCategoryCode = 1 or pcc.KeyValue2 = '1') then 'WEALTH-INITIAL'
				when ph.ProductGroupCode = 3 then 'MORTGAGE'
				when ph.ProductGroupCode = 6 then 'PROTECTION'
				else null
			end as CalculationType,
			'Openwork 2006' as Source,
			@DateLastUpdated as DateInserted,
			@DateLastUpdated as DateLastUpdated,
			csp.year as CommissionYear
	--select count(*)
	from	msit_CommissionStatement cs
/*			inner join (select	distinct PKID
						from	owt_TransformationMovements tm 
						where	tm.DriverTableName = 'sa_swift_S_AGMFIL'
						and		tm.CommissionStatement = 'Y') tm on tm.PKID = cs.PendingPaymentID
*/			inner join mstt_Agents ag on ag.Code = cs.BusinessCode
			inner join mstt_PolicyTransactions pt on pt.ID = cs.TransactionID
			inner join mstt_Policies p on p.POL_NUM = pt.PolicyID
			inner join msit_CommissionStatementPeriods VNBStart on convert(date,pt.CreateDateTime) between VNBStart.PeriodStartDate and VNBStart.PeriodEndDate
			inner join msit_Commissionstatementperiods csp on csp.month = cs.month
			inner join mstt_ProductHierarchy ph on ph.productcode = cs.productcode
			inner join mstt_Expectation e on e.ID = cs.ExpectationID
			left join dbo.owt_MortgageBrokerFees mbf on mbf.PendingPaymentID = cs.PendingPaymentID and mbf.AdviceFeeCharged = 'Yes'
			left join owt_SelectionControl SC
						on SC.Process = 'ElitePoints' 
						and SC.KeyType = 'NSCPotCode' 
						and cs.CreateDate between SC.EffectiveStartDate and SC.EffectiveEndDate
			left join mstt_Commissions BSCpot
						on BSCpot.TransactionID = cs.TransactionID 
						and BSCpot.Agent_Code = sc.KeyValue
						and BSCpot.CommissionType = 10
			left join owt_SelectionControl SFMPC						
						on SFMPC.Process = 'ElitePoints' 
						and SFMPC.KeyType = 'ServicingFeeMarginPotCode' 
						and cs.CreateDate between SFMPC.EffectiveStartDate and SFMPC.EffectiveEndDate
			left join mstt_Commissions SFMpot							
						on SFMpot.TransactionID = cs.TransactionID 
						and SFMpot.Agent_Code = SFMPC.KeyValue
						and SFMpot.CommissionType = 10	
			left join owt_SelectionControl pcc 
						on pcc.Process = 'ElitePoints'
						and pcc.KeyType = 'ProductCategoryCode'
						and pcc.KeyValue = cs.ProductCode	
						and cs.CreateDate between pcc.EffectiveStartDate and pcc.EffectiveEndDate
			left join owt_SelectionControl ogsdflt 
						on ogsdflt.Process = 'ElitePoints'
						and ogsdflt.KeyType = 'DefaultOngoingServicingRate'
						and ogsdflt.SelectionType = 'VNB'
						and ogsdflt.KeyValue = case when ph.RDRType = 'ONPLAT' then 'ONPLAT' else 'OFPLAT' end
						and cs.CreateDate between ogsdflt.EffectiveStartDate and ogsdflt.EffectiveEndDate
			left join mstt_CodeProductGroup pg on pg.ProductGroupCode = case when pcc.KeyValue2 = '1' then 2 else ph.ProductGroupCode end
			left join owt_EliteFactors Cfca on Cfca.FeeType = 'VNB' and Cfca.category = 'COB-FCA-RATE' and csp.year between Cfca.StartYear and Cfca.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors Crate on Crate.FeeType = 'VNB' and Crate.category = 'COB-RETENTION-RATE' and csp.year between Crate.StartYear and Crate.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors Mfca on Mfca.FeeType = 'VNB' and Mfca.category = 'MORT-FCA-RATE' and csp.year between Mfca.StartYear and Mfca.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors MRproc on MRproc.FeeType = 'VNB' and MRproc.category = 'MORT-RETENTION-RATE-PROC' and csp.year between MRproc.StartYear and MRproc.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors MRbkr on MRbkr.FeeType = 'VNB' and MRbkr.category = 'MORT-RETENTION-RATE-BROKER' and csp.year between MRbkr.StartYear and MRbkr.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors Pfca on Pfca.FeeType = 'VNB' and Pfca.category = 'PROT-FCA-RATE' and csp.year between Pfca.StartYear and Pfca.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors Prate on Prate.FeeType = 'VNB' and Prate.category = 'PROT-RETENTION-RATE' and csp.year between Prate.StartYear and Prate.EndYear 
			left join msit_CommissionStatement csadj 
						on csadj.TransactionID = cs.TransactionID 
						and csadj.AgentCode = cs.AgentCode 
						and csadj.CommissionType in (2,17)
						and	csadj.PayBasisCode in ('F')				--Accrual
						and	csadj.FrequencyCode <> 6				--Regular 
	where	cs.ReportingClassCode = 1
	and		ag.Manager2Code <> @OwlManager2Code		--Exclude Owl
	and		cs.INIssued <> 0
	and		csp.Year >= 2017				--Ensure in-scope payments are consistent with VNB start
	and		((VNBStart.Year >= 2017 and cs.CommissionType = 1 and e.AMOUNT_REC >= 0.01)		--VNB to start from new slices in 2017 for +ve payments but...			AG 11/06/2018 (2)
			or (cs.CommissionType in (2,17) or e.AMOUNT_REC <= -0.01))						--...for -ve payments, the slice can start from any date in the past	AG 11/06/2018 (2)
	and		csadj.ID is null				--Deal with accrual regular clawbacks/adjustments later

	select @RowCount = @@rowcount
	set @ProcessMessage = '#owt_Recognition = ' + convert(nvarchar(10), @RowCount)
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseLog, @ProcessMessage, null, @Module, @Client

	/****************************************************************************

		Occasionally an investment case may receive two or more cheques which
		then go through Swift as two or more SINGLE investments on the SAME
		slice. Although the INITIAL VNB calculation will pro-rata correctly
		because it is based on the amount received, this scenario will cause
		ongoing VNB to be calculated on each of the payment records and so will 
		double count (or worse if there are more than two cheques received).
		
		The code below ensures that any "extra" (unwanted) ongoing that has been
		calculated due to the above scenario is zeroed out as required.
																		
	****************************************************************************/
	

	/****************************************************************************

		Now deal with accrual clawbacks and adjustments
																		
	****************************************************************************/

	--drop table #msit_CommissionStatementSUMMARY

	--Find transactions with clawbacks/adj on them
	select	cs.TransactionID,
			cs.AgentCode,
			Min(case when cs.CommissionType = 1 then cs.PendingPaymentID else null end) as MinInitialPendingPaymentID,
			MAX(case when cs.CommissionType = 1 then cs.PendingPaymentID else null end) as MaxInitialPendingPaymentID,
			MAX(case when cs.CommissionType in (2,17) then cs.PendingPaymentID else null end) as MaxAdjPendingPaymentID,
			null as MinInitialAfterAdjPendingPaymentID
	into	#msit_CommissionStatementSUMMARY
	from	msit_CommissionStatement cs
			inner join mstt_Agents ag on ag.Code = cs.BusinessCode
			inner join mstt_PolicyTransactions pt on pt.ID = cs.TransactionID
			inner join mstt_Policies p on p.POL_NUM = pt.PolicyID
			inner join msit_CommissionStatementPeriods VNBStart on convert(date,pt.CreateDateTime) between VNBStart.PeriodStartDate and VNBStart.PeriodEndDate
			inner join msit_Commissionstatementperiods csp on csp.month = cs.month
			inner join mstt_Expectation e on e.ID = cs.ExpectationID
			left join msit_CommissionStatement csadj 
						on csadj.TransactionID = cs.TransactionID 
						and csadj.AgentCode = cs.AgentCode 
						and csadj.CommissionType in (2,17)
						and	csadj.PayBasisCode in ('F')				--Accrual
						and	csadj.FrequencyCode <> 6				--Regular 
	where	cs.ReportingClassCode = 1
	and		ag.Manager2Code <> '1011671'--@OwlManager2Code		--Exclude Owl
	and		csp.Year >= 2017				--Ensure in-scope payments are consistent with VNB start
	and		VNBStart.Year >= 2017 
	and		abs(e.AMOUNT_REC) >= 0.01	
	and		csadj.ID is not null			--select regular accrual transactions with clawbacks/adjustments
and cs.TransactionID in (5613333,6296827)
	group by	cs.TransactionID,
				cs.AgentCode

	--Get first initial payment after last clawback/adj
	update css
		set MinInitialAfterAdjPendingPaymentID = summ.MinPendingPaymentID 
	from  #msit_CommissionStatementSUMMARY css
			inner join  (
						select cssinner.TransactionID, cssinner.AgentCode, min(cs.PendingPaymentID) as MinPendingPaymentID
						from #msit_CommissionStatementSUMMARY cssinner
								inner join msit_CommissionStatement cs
											on cs.TransactionID = cssinner.TransactionID
											and cs.AgentCode = cssinner.AgentCode
						where cs.PendingPaymentID > cssinner.MaxAdjPendingPaymentID
						group by cssinner.TransactionID, cssinner.AgentCode
						) summ on  summ.TransactionID = css.TransactionID
							   and summ.AgentCode = css.AgentCode

	/****************************************************************************

		Phase 2 - This phase deals with regular accrual cases where the latest payment
		is a clawback/adjustment. In this scenario the VNB is changed from front loaded 
		to a per payment basis.
																		
	****************************************************************************/

	insert into #AG_owt_Recognition_SEPARATE_ONGOING
	(
		SourceID,
		CaseID,
		TransactionID,
		Policy,
		ProductCode,
		BusinessCode,
		SellerCode,						
		PointsTotal,
		BSC,
		MBF,
		Initial,
		OngoingTotal,
		OngoingYr01,
		OngoingYr02,
		OngoingYr03,
		OngoingYr04,
		OngoingYr05,
		OngoingYr06,
		OngoingYr07,
		OngoingYr08,
		OngoingYr09,
		OngoingYr10,
		FCARate,
		RetentionRate,
		RetentionRateBroker,
		OngoingServicingRate,
		OngoingServicingSource,
		DA,
		AmountReceived,
		Premium,
		AgentSplit,
		CommissionType,
		CommissionTypeDesc,
		PayBasisCode,					
		PayBasisDesc,					
		PaymentMatchedDate,				
		Month,
		FrequencyCode,
		FrequencyDesc,
		ReassignedProductGroupCode,		
		ReassignedProductGroupName,		
		RecognitionType,
		CalculationType,
		Source,
		DateInserted,
		DateLastUpdated,
		CommissionYear
	)
	select	cs.PendingPaymentID as SourceID,
			cs.CaseID,
			cs.TransactionID,
			cs.ExtPolicyNumber as Policy,
			cs.ProductCode,
			cs.BusinessCode,
			cs.AgentCode as SellerCode,				
			0.0 as PointsTotal,
			0.0 as BSC,
			case 
				when mbf.MortgageFeeID is not null and cs.INIssued <> 0 then (((mbf.AdviceFeeAmount)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * MRbkr.FACTOR) - ((mbf.AdviceFeeAmount)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * Mfca.FACTOR)) --Note that mbf.AdviceFeeAmount is signed correctly - so no coding for signing is needed here
				else 0.0
			end as MBF,
			case 
				--When the adviser has changed, the AgentSplit can become zero in which case the ELITE points should be zero.
				when cs.AgentSplit = 0 then 0
				
				--WEALTH CALCULATION START
				--Indemnity payments or SINGLEs or IC Clawbacks or IC adjustments Start
				--THIS SCENARIO DOESN'T OCCUR IN PHASE 2
				--Indemnity payments or SINGLEs or IC Clawbacks or IC adjustments End
				--Accruals & Level Start
				when (ph.ProductCategoryCode = 1 or pcc.KeyValue2 = '1') then (((e.AMOUNT_REC)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * Crate.FACTOR) - ((e.AMOUNT_REC)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * Cfca.FACTOR)) * case when cs.CommissionType in (2,17) then -1 else 1 end
				--Accruals & Level End
				--WEALTH CALCULATION END
				
				--MORTGAGE CALCULATION START
				--Note: The MBF component has its own table column
				--Only 1 payment for mortgages
				when ph.ProductGroupCode = 3 then (((e.AMOUNT_REC)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * MRproc.FACTOR) - ((e.AMOUNT_REC)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * Mfca.FACTOR)) * case when cs.CommissionType in (2,17) then -1 else 1 end	
				--MORTGAGE CALCULATION END
				
				--PROTECTION CALCULATION START
				--Indemnity payments or SINGLEs or IC Clawbacks or IC adjustments Start
				--THIS SCENARIO DOESN'T OCCUR IN PHASE 2
				--Indemnity payments or SINGLEs or IC Clawbacks or IC adjustments End
				--Accruals & Level Start
				when ph.ProductGroupCode = 6 then (((e.AMOUNT_REC)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * Prate.FACTOR) - ((e.AMOUNT_REC)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * Pfca.FACTOR)) * case when cs.CommissionType in (2,17) then -1 else 1 end
				--Accruals & Level End
				--PROTECTION CALCULATION END

				else 0.0

			end as Initial,
			0.0 as OngoingTotal,
			0.0 as OngoingYr01,
			0.0 as OngoingYr02,
			0.0 as OngoingYr03,
			0.0 as OngoingYr04,
			0.0 as OngoingYr05,
			0.0 as OngoingYr06,
			0.0 as OngoingYr07,
			0.0 as OngoingYr08,
			0.0 as OngoingYr09,
			0.0 as OngoingYr10,
			case 
				when (ph.ProductCategoryCode = 1 or pcc.KeyValue2 = '1') then Cfca.FACTOR*100.0		--COB
				when ph.ProductGroupCode = 3 then Mfca.FACTOR*100.0		--MORT
				when ph.ProductGroupCode = 6 then Pfca.FACTOR*100.0		--PROT
				else 0.0
			end as FCARate,
			case 
				when (ph.ProductCategoryCode = 1 or pcc.KeyValue2 = '1') then Crate.FACTOR*100.0	--COB
				when ph.ProductGroupCode = 3 then MRproc.FACTOR*100.0	--MORT
				when ph.ProductGroupCode = 6 then Prate.FACTOR*100.0	--PROT
				else 0.0
			end as RetentionRate,
			case 
				when mbf.MortgageFeeID is not null then  MRbkr.FACTOR*100.0	
				else 0.0
			end as RetentionRateBroker,
			null as OngoingServicingRate,
			null as OngoingServicingSource,
			pt.CommInitialAmount as DA,
			e.AMOUNT_REC as AmountReceived,
			cs.Premium,
			cs.AgentSplit,
			cs.CommissionType,
			left(cs.StandingOrderDesc,50) as CommissionTypeDesc,
			cs.PayBasisCode,							
			cs.PayBasisDesc,							
			cs.CreateDate as PaymentMatchedDate,		
			cs.Month,
			cs.FrequencyCode,
			cs.FrequencyDesc,
			pg.ProductGroupCode as ReassignedProductGroupCode,	--Force the re-assigned products...		
			pg.ProductGroupName as ReassignedProductGroupName,	--...to be processed as investments		
			'VNB-PHASE-2' as RecognitionType,
			case 
				when (ph.ProductCategoryCode = 1 or pcc.KeyValue2 = '1') then 'WEALTH-INITIAL'
				when ph.ProductGroupCode = 3 then 'MORTGAGE'
				when ph.ProductGroupCode = 6 then 'PROTECTION'
				else null
			end as CalculationType,
			'Openwork 2006' as Source,
			@DateLastUpdated as DateInserted,
			@DateLastUpdated as DateLastUpdated,
			csp.year as CommissionYear
	from	#msit_CommissionStatementSUMMARY css
			inner join msit_CommissionStatement cs
						on cs.TransactionID = css.TransactionID
						and cs.AgentCode = css.AgentCode
			inner join mstt_Agents ag on ag.Code = cs.BusinessCode
			inner join mstt_PolicyTransactions pt on pt.ID = cs.TransactionID
			inner join mstt_Policies p on p.POL_NUM = pt.PolicyID
			inner join msit_CommissionStatementPeriods VNBStart on convert(date,pt.CreateDateTime) between VNBStart.PeriodStartDate and VNBStart.PeriodEndDate
			inner join msit_Commissionstatementperiods csp on csp.month = cs.month
			inner join mstt_ProductHierarchy ph on ph.productcode = cs.productcode
			inner join mstt_Expectation e on e.ID = cs.ExpectationID
			left join dbo.owt_MortgageBrokerFees mbf on mbf.PendingPaymentID = cs.PendingPaymentID and mbf.AdviceFeeCharged = 'Yes'
			left join owt_SelectionControl SC
						on SC.Process = 'ElitePoints' 
						and SC.KeyType = 'NSCPotCode' 
						and cs.CreateDate between SC.EffectiveStartDate and SC.EffectiveEndDate
			left join mstt_Commissions BSCpot
						on BSCpot.TransactionID = cs.TransactionID 
						and BSCpot.Agent_Code = sc.KeyValue
						and BSCpot.CommissionType = 10
			left join owt_SelectionControl SFMPC						
						on SFMPC.Process = 'ElitePoints' 
						and SFMPC.KeyType = 'ServicingFeeMarginPotCode' 
						and cs.CreateDate between SFMPC.EffectiveStartDate and SFMPC.EffectiveEndDate
			left join mstt_Commissions SFMpot							
						on SFMpot.TransactionID = cs.TransactionID 
						and SFMpot.Agent_Code = SFMPC.KeyValue
						and SFMpot.CommissionType = 10	
			left join owt_SelectionControl pcc 
						on pcc.Process = 'ElitePoints'
						and pcc.KeyType = 'ProductCategoryCode'
						and pcc.KeyValue = cs.ProductCode	
						and cs.CreateDate between pcc.EffectiveStartDate and pcc.EffectiveEndDate
			left join owt_SelectionControl ogsdflt 
						on ogsdflt.Process = 'ElitePoints'
						and ogsdflt.KeyType = 'DefaultOngoingServicingRate'
						and ogsdflt.SelectionType = 'VNB'
						and ogsdflt.KeyValue = case when ph.RDRType = 'ONPLAT' then 'ONPLAT' else 'OFPLAT' end
						and cs.CreateDate between ogsdflt.EffectiveStartDate and ogsdflt.EffectiveEndDate
			left join mstt_CodeProductGroup pg on pg.ProductGroupCode = case when pcc.KeyValue2 = '1' then 2 else ph.ProductGroupCode end
			left join owt_EliteFactors Cfca on Cfca.FeeType = 'VNB' and Cfca.category = 'COB-FCA-RATE' and csp.year between Cfca.StartYear and Cfca.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors Crate on Crate.FeeType = 'VNB' and Crate.category = 'COB-RETENTION-RATE' and csp.year between Crate.StartYear and Crate.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors Mfca on Mfca.FeeType = 'VNB' and Mfca.category = 'MORT-FCA-RATE' and csp.year between Mfca.StartYear and Mfca.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors MRproc on MRproc.FeeType = 'VNB' and MRproc.category = 'MORT-RETENTION-RATE-PROC' and csp.year between MRproc.StartYear and MRproc.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors MRbkr on MRbkr.FeeType = 'VNB' and MRbkr.category = 'MORT-RETENTION-RATE-BROKER' and csp.year between MRbkr.StartYear and MRbkr.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors Pfca on Pfca.FeeType = 'VNB' and Pfca.category = 'PROT-FCA-RATE' and csp.year between Pfca.StartYear and Pfca.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors Prate on Prate.FeeType = 'VNB' and Prate.category = 'PROT-RETENTION-RATE' and csp.year between Prate.StartYear and Prate.EndYear 
	where	cs.ReportingClassCode = 1
	and		ag.Manager2Code <> '1011671'--@OwlManager2Code		--Exclude Owl
	and		isnull(css.MaxInitialPendingPaymentID,0) < isnull(css.MaxAdjPendingPaymentID,0)	-- Clawback/adj is the latest payment
	and		cs.TransactionID = 5613333
	--order by cs.PendingPaymentID

	/****************************************************************************

		Phase 3a - initial payments restart after clawback/adj
		1) Set original (front loaded) points on first payment as per Phase 1
		2) Set (front loaded) points DIFFERENCE on first payment following clawback/adj
																
	****************************************************************************/

	insert into #AG_owt_Recognition_SEPARATE_ONGOING
	(
		SourceID,
		CaseID,
		TransactionID,
		Policy,
		ProductCode,
		BusinessCode,
		SellerCode,						
		PointsTotal,
		BSC,
		MBF,
		Initial,
		OngoingTotal,
		OngoingYr01,
		OngoingYr02,
		OngoingYr03,
		OngoingYr04,
		OngoingYr05,
		OngoingYr06,
		OngoingYr07,
		OngoingYr08,
		OngoingYr09,
		OngoingYr10,
		FCARate,
		RetentionRate,
		RetentionRateBroker,
		OngoingServicingRate,
		OngoingServicingSource,
		DA,
		AmountReceived,
		Premium,
		AgentSplit,
		CommissionType,
		CommissionTypeDesc,
		PayBasisCode,					
		PayBasisDesc,					
		PaymentMatchedDate,				
		Month,
		FrequencyCode,
		FrequencyDesc,
		ReassignedProductGroupCode,		
		ReassignedProductGroupName,		
		RecognitionType,
		CalculationType,
		Source,
		DateInserted,
		DateLastUpdated,
		CommissionYear
	)
	select	cs.PendingPaymentID as SourceID,
			cs.CaseID,
			cs.TransactionID,
			cs.ExtPolicyNumber as Policy,
			cs.ProductCode,
			cs.BusinessCode,
			cs.AgentCode as SellerCode,				
			0.0 as PointsTotal,
			0.0 as BSC,
			case 
				when mbf.MortgageFeeID is not null and cs.INIssued <> 0 then (((mbf.AdviceFeeAmount)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * MRbkr.FACTOR) - ((mbf.AdviceFeeAmount)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * Mfca.FACTOR)) --Note that mbf.AdviceFeeAmount is signed correctly - so no coding for signing is needed here
				else 0.0
			end as MBF,
			case 
				--When the adviser has changed, the AgentSplit can become zero in which case the ELITE points should be zero.
				when cs.AgentSplit = 0 then 0
				
				--WEALTH CALCULATION START
				--Indemnity payments or SINGLEs or IC Clawbacks or IC adjustments Start
				--THIS SCENARIO DOESN'T OCCUR IN PHASE 2
				--Indemnity payments or SINGLEs or IC Clawbacks or IC adjustments End
				--Accruals & Level Start
				--First payment front load as before
				when (cs.PendingPaymentID = css.MinInitialPendingPaymentID and (ph.ProductCategoryCode = 1 or pcc.KeyValue2 = '1')) then (((pt.CommInitialAmount)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * Crate.FACTOR) - ((pt.CommInitialAmount)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * Cfca.FACTOR)) * case when cs.CommissionType in (2,17) then -1 else 1 end
				--Accruals & Level End
				--WEALTH CALCULATION END
				
				--MORTGAGE CALCULATION START
				--Note: The MBF component has its own table column
				--Only 1 payment for mortgages
				when cs.PendingPaymentID = css.MinInitialPendingPaymentID and ph.ProductGroupCode = 3 then (((pt.CommInitialAmount)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * MRproc.FACTOR) - ((pt.CommInitialAmount)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * Mfca.FACTOR)) * case when cs.CommissionType in (2,17) then -1 else 1 end	
				--MORTGAGE CALCULATION END
				
				--PROTECTION CALCULATION START
				--Indemnity payments or SINGLEs or IC Clawbacks or IC adjustments Start
				--THIS SCENARIO DOESN'T OCCUR IN PHASE 2
				--Indemnity payments or SINGLEs or IC Clawbacks or IC adjustments End
				--Accruals & Level Start
				when cs.PendingPaymentID = css.MinInitialPendingPaymentID and ph.ProductGroupCode = 6 then (((pt.CommInitialAmount)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * Prate.FACTOR) - ((pt.CommInitialAmount)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * Pfca.FACTOR)) * case when cs.CommissionType in (2,17) then -1 else 1 end
				--Accruals & Level End
				--PROTECTION CALCULATION END

				else 0.0

			end as Initial,
			0.0 as OngoingTotal,
			0.0 as OngoingYr01,
			0.0 as OngoingYr02,
			0.0 as OngoingYr03,
			0.0 as OngoingYr04,
			0.0 as OngoingYr05,
			0.0 as OngoingYr06,
			0.0 as OngoingYr07,
			0.0 as OngoingYr08,
			0.0 as OngoingYr09,
			0.0 as OngoingYr10,
			case 
				when (ph.ProductCategoryCode = 1 or pcc.KeyValue2 = '1') then Cfca.FACTOR*100.0		--COB
				when ph.ProductGroupCode = 3 then Mfca.FACTOR*100.0		--MORT
				when ph.ProductGroupCode = 6 then Pfca.FACTOR*100.0		--PROT
				else 0.0
			end as FCARate,
			case 
				when (ph.ProductCategoryCode = 1 or pcc.KeyValue2 = '1') then Crate.FACTOR*100.0	--COB
				when ph.ProductGroupCode = 3 then MRproc.FACTOR*100.0	--MORT
				when ph.ProductGroupCode = 6 then Prate.FACTOR*100.0	--PROT
				else 0.0
			end as RetentionRate,
			case 
				when mbf.MortgageFeeID is not null then  MRbkr.FACTOR*100.0	
				else 0.0
			end as RetentionRateBroker,
			null as OngoingServicingRate,
			null as OngoingServicingSource,
			pt.CommInitialAmount as DA,
			e.AMOUNT_REC as AmountReceived,
			cs.Premium,
			cs.AgentSplit,
			cs.CommissionType,
			left(cs.StandingOrderDesc,50) as CommissionTypeDesc,
			cs.PayBasisCode,							
			cs.PayBasisDesc,							
			cs.CreateDate as PaymentMatchedDate,		
			cs.Month,
			cs.FrequencyCode,
			cs.FrequencyDesc,
			pg.ProductGroupCode as ReassignedProductGroupCode,	--Force the re-assigned products...		
			pg.ProductGroupName as ReassignedProductGroupName,	--...to be processed as investments		
			'VNB-PHASE-3a' as RecognitionType,
			case 
				when (ph.ProductCategoryCode = 1 or pcc.KeyValue2 = '1') then 'WEALTH-INITIAL'
				when ph.ProductGroupCode = 3 then 'MORTGAGE'
				when ph.ProductGroupCode = 6 then 'PROTECTION'
				else null
			end as CalculationType,
			'Openwork 2006' as Source,
			@DateLastUpdated as DateInserted,
			@DateLastUpdated as DateLastUpdated,
			csp.year as CommissionYear
	from	#msit_CommissionStatementSUMMARY css
			inner join msit_CommissionStatement cs
						on cs.TransactionID = css.TransactionID
						and cs.AgentCode = css.AgentCode
			inner join mstt_Agents ag on ag.Code = cs.BusinessCode
			inner join mstt_PolicyTransactions pt on pt.ID = cs.TransactionID
			inner join mstt_Policies p on p.POL_NUM = pt.PolicyID
			inner join msit_CommissionStatementPeriods VNBStart on convert(date,pt.CreateDateTime) between VNBStart.PeriodStartDate and VNBStart.PeriodEndDate
			inner join msit_Commissionstatementperiods csp on csp.month = cs.month
			inner join mstt_ProductHierarchy ph on ph.productcode = cs.productcode
			inner join mstt_Expectation e on e.ID = cs.ExpectationID
			left join dbo.owt_MortgageBrokerFees mbf on mbf.PendingPaymentID = cs.PendingPaymentID and mbf.AdviceFeeCharged = 'Yes'
			left join owt_SelectionControl SC
						on SC.Process = 'ElitePoints' 
						and SC.KeyType = 'NSCPotCode' 
						and cs.CreateDate between SC.EffectiveStartDate and SC.EffectiveEndDate
			left join mstt_Commissions BSCpot
						on BSCpot.TransactionID = cs.TransactionID 
						and BSCpot.Agent_Code = sc.KeyValue
						and BSCpot.CommissionType = 10
			left join owt_SelectionControl SFMPC						
						on SFMPC.Process = 'ElitePoints' 
						and SFMPC.KeyType = 'ServicingFeeMarginPotCode' 
						and cs.CreateDate between SFMPC.EffectiveStartDate and SFMPC.EffectiveEndDate
			left join mstt_Commissions SFMpot							
						on SFMpot.TransactionID = cs.TransactionID 
						and SFMpot.Agent_Code = SFMPC.KeyValue
						and SFMpot.CommissionType = 10	
			left join owt_SelectionControl pcc 
						on pcc.Process = 'ElitePoints'
						and pcc.KeyType = 'ProductCategoryCode'
						and pcc.KeyValue = cs.ProductCode	
						and cs.CreateDate between pcc.EffectiveStartDate and pcc.EffectiveEndDate
			left join owt_SelectionControl ogsdflt 
						on ogsdflt.Process = 'ElitePoints'
						and ogsdflt.KeyType = 'DefaultOngoingServicingRate'
						and ogsdflt.SelectionType = 'VNB'
						and ogsdflt.KeyValue = case when ph.RDRType = 'ONPLAT' then 'ONPLAT' else 'OFPLAT' end
						and cs.CreateDate between ogsdflt.EffectiveStartDate and ogsdflt.EffectiveEndDate
			left join mstt_CodeProductGroup pg on pg.ProductGroupCode = case when pcc.KeyValue2 = '1' then 2 else ph.ProductGroupCode end
			left join owt_EliteFactors Cfca on Cfca.FeeType = 'VNB' and Cfca.category = 'COB-FCA-RATE' and csp.year between Cfca.StartYear and Cfca.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors Crate on Crate.FeeType = 'VNB' and Crate.category = 'COB-RETENTION-RATE' and csp.year between Crate.StartYear and Crate.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors Mfca on Mfca.FeeType = 'VNB' and Mfca.category = 'MORT-FCA-RATE' and csp.year between Mfca.StartYear and Mfca.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors MRproc on MRproc.FeeType = 'VNB' and MRproc.category = 'MORT-RETENTION-RATE-PROC' and csp.year between MRproc.StartYear and MRproc.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors MRbkr on MRbkr.FeeType = 'VNB' and MRbkr.category = 'MORT-RETENTION-RATE-BROKER' and csp.year between MRbkr.StartYear and MRbkr.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors Pfca on Pfca.FeeType = 'VNB' and Pfca.category = 'PROT-FCA-RATE' and csp.year between Pfca.StartYear and Pfca.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors Prate on Prate.FeeType = 'VNB' and Prate.category = 'PROT-RETENTION-RATE' and csp.year between Prate.StartYear and Prate.EndYear 
	where	cs.ReportingClassCode = 1
	and		ag.Manager2Code <> '1011671'--@OwlManager2Code		--Exclude Owl
	and		isnull(css.MaxInitialPendingPaymentID,0) > isnull(css.MaxAdjPendingPaymentID,0)-- An initial payment follows the clawback, so time to revert back to front loading
	and		cs.TransactionID = 5613333
	--order by cs.PendingPaymentID

	/****************************************************************************

		Phase 3a - initial payments restart after clawback/adj
		1) Set original (front loaded) points on first payment as per Phase 1
		2) Set (front loaded) points DIFFERENCE on first payment following clawback/adj
																
	****************************************************************************/

	update	PaymentAfterAdj
		set RecognitionType	= 'VNB-PHASE-3b',
			Initial =	case when FirstPayment.AmountReceived <> 0.0
							then ((FirstPayment.Initial / FirstPayment.AmountReceived) * PaymentAfterAdj.AmountReceived) - FirstPayment.Initial
							else 0.0
						end,
			DateLastUpdated = @DateLastUpdated
	from	#msit_CommissionStatementSUMMARY css
			inner join #AG_owt_Recognition_SEPARATE_ONGOING FirstPayment on FirstPayment.SourceID = css.MinInitialPendingPaymentID
			inner join #AG_owt_Recognition_SEPARATE_ONGOING PaymentAfterAdj on PaymentAfterAdj.SourceID = css.MinInitialAfterAdjPendingPaymentID
	where	isnull(css.MaxInitialPendingPaymentID,0) > isnull(css.MaxAdjPendingPaymentID,0)-- An initial payment follows the clawback, so front load it with the difference

---------------------

select *
from #msit_CommissionStatementSUMMARY
where TransactionID in (5613333)


----------------------

	/****************************************************************************

		Now add up the numbers
																		
	****************************************************************************/
	
	update r
		set PointsTotal	= Initial + MBF	-- Note BSC is already included in the Ongoing, so don't include it in the Points Total.
	from	#AG_owt_Recognition_SEPARATE_ONGOING r

	select @RowCount = @@rowcount
	set @ProcessMessage = '#owt_Recognition (initial totals) = ' + convert(nvarchar(10), @RowCount)
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseLog, @ProcessMessage, null, @Module, @Client
	
	/****************************************************************************

		Merge the temporary table into the permanent table (IC data)
																		
	****************************************************************************/

	BEGIN TRANSACTION

	declare @SummaryOfChangesINITIAL table (Change varchar(20))
	merge	dbo.AG_owt_Recognition_SEPARATE_ONGOING as trg
	using	#AG_owt_Recognition_SEPARATE_ONGOING as src
	on		trg.SourceID = src.SourceID
	and		trg.Source = src.Source
	when	matched 
	and		isnull(trg.PointsTotal,0) <> isnull(src.PointsTotal,0)
	then	update 
				set trg.CaseID = src.CaseID,
					trg.TransactionID = src.TransactionID,
					trg.Policy = src.Policy,
					trg.ProductCode = src.ProductCode,
					trg.BusinessCode = src.BusinessCode,
					trg.SellerCode = src.SellerCode,					--AG 13/06/2018
					trg.PointsTotal = src.PointsTotal,
					trg.BSC = src.BSC,
					trg.MBF = src.MBF,
					trg.Initial = src.Initial,
					trg.OngoingTotal = src.OngoingTotal,
					trg.OngoingYr01 = src.OngoingYr01,
					trg.OngoingYr02 = src.OngoingYr02,
					trg.OngoingYr03 = src.OngoingYr03,
					trg.OngoingYr04 = src.OngoingYr04,
					trg.OngoingYr05 = src.OngoingYr05,
					trg.OngoingYr06 = src.OngoingYr06,
					trg.OngoingYr07 = src.OngoingYr07,
					trg.OngoingYr08 = src.OngoingYr08,
					trg.OngoingYr09 = src.OngoingYr09,
					trg.OngoingYr10 = src.OngoingYr10,
					trg.FCARate = src.FCARate,
					trg.RetentionRate = src.RetentionRate,
					trg.RetentionRateBroker = src.RetentionRateBroker,
					trg.OngoingServicingRate = src.OngoingServicingRate,
					trg.OngoingServicingSource = src.OngoingServicingSource,
					trg.DA = src.DA,
					trg.AmountReceived = src.AmountReceived,
					trg.Premium = src.Premium,
					trg.AgentSplit = src.AgentSplit,
					trg.CommissionType = src.CommissionType,
					trg.CommissionTypeDesc = src.CommissionTypeDesc,
					trg.PayBasisCode = src.PayBasisCode,				--AG 13/06/2018
					trg.PayBasisDesc = src.PayBasisDesc,				--AG 13/06/2018
					trg.PaymentMatchedDate = src.PaymentMatchedDate,	--AG 13/06/2018	
					trg.Month = src.Month,
					trg.FrequencyCode = src.FrequencyCode,
					trg.FrequencyDesc = src.FrequencyDesc,
					trg.ReassignedProductGroupCode = src.ReassignedProductGroupCode,	--AG 05/06/2018
					trg.ReassignedProductGroupName = src.ReassignedProductGroupName,	--AG 05/06/2018
					trg.RecognitionType = src.RecognitionType,
					trg.CalculationType = src.CalculationType,
					trg.DateLastUpdated = @DateLastUpdated
	when	not matched by target 
	then	insert
			(
				SourceID,
				CaseID,
				TransactionID,
				Policy,
				ProductCode,
				BusinessCode,
				SellerCode,							--AG 13/06/2018
				PointsTotal,
				BSC,
				MBF,
				Initial,
				OngoingTotal,
				OngoingYr01,
				OngoingYr02,
				OngoingYr03,
				OngoingYr04,
				OngoingYr05,
				OngoingYr06,
				OngoingYr07,
				OngoingYr08,
				OngoingYr09,
				OngoingYr10,
				FCARate,
				RetentionRate,
				RetentionRateBroker,
				OngoingServicingRate,
				OngoingServicingSource,
				DA,
				AmountReceived,
				Premium,
				AgentSplit,
				CommissionType,
				CommissionTypeDesc,
				PayBasisCode,						--AG 13/06/2018
				PayBasisDesc,						--AG 13/06/2018
				PaymentMatchedDate,					--AG 13/06/2018
				Month,
				FrequencyCode,
				FrequencyDesc,
				ReassignedProductGroupCode,			--AG 05/06/2018
				ReassignedProductGroupName,			--AG 05/06/2018
				RecognitionType,
				CalculationType,
				Source,
				DateInserted,
				DateLastUpdated
			)		
			values
			(
				src.SourceID,
				src.CaseID,
				src.TransactionID,
				src.Policy,
				src.ProductCode,
				src.BusinessCode,
				src.SellerCode,						--AG 13/06/2018
				src.PointsTotal,
				src.BSC,
				src.MBF,
				src.Initial,
				src.OngoingTotal,
				src.OngoingYr01,
				src.OngoingYr02,
				src.OngoingYr03,
				src.OngoingYr04,
				src.OngoingYr05,
				src.OngoingYr06,
				src.OngoingYr07,
				src.OngoingYr08,
				src.OngoingYr09,
				src.OngoingYr10,
				src.FCARate,
				src.RetentionRate,
				src.RetentionRateBroker,
				src.OngoingServicingRate,
				src.OngoingServicingSource,
				src.DA,
				src.AmountReceived,
				src.Premium,
				src.AgentSplit,
				src.CommissionType,
				src.CommissionTypeDesc,
				src.PayBasisCode,					--AG 13/06/2018
				src.PayBasisDesc,					--AG 13/06/2018
				src.PaymentMatchedDate,				--AG 13/06/2018
				src.Month,
				src.FrequencyCode,
				src.FrequencyDesc,
				src.ReassignedProductGroupCode,		--AG 05/06/2018
				src.ReassignedProductGroupName,		--AG 05/06/2018
				src.RecognitionType,
				src.CalculationType,
				src.Source,
				src.DateInserted,
				src.DateLastUpdated)				--Merge statements must have a ;
	output $action into @SummaryOfChangesINITIAL;
	
	/****************************************************************************

		Now do the ongoing.
		
		Start with some work temp tables.
																		
	****************************************************************************/

	--Find the oldest initial payment as we'll be using data from this row in the ongoing calc.
	select	TransactionID, SellerCode, MIN(SourceID) as MinSourceID
	into	#owt_RecognitionINITIAL
	from	dbo.AG_owt_Recognition_SEPARATE_ONGOING	
	where	CommissionType = 1			--Initial
	and		Source = 'Openwork 2006'	--Just the data that relates to this proc
	group	by TransactionID, SellerCode

	--00:05:25
	--60,044
	--Find the oldest ongoing payment for each transaction (slice).
	select	cs.TransactionID, cs.AgentCode, cs.CommissionType, min(cs.PendingPaymentID) as MinPendingPaymentID
	into	#msit_CommissionStatementONGOING
	from	msit_CommissionStatement cs
			inner join mstt_Agents ag on ag.Code = cs.BusinessCode
			inner join mstt_PolicyTransactions pt on pt.ID = cs.TransactionID
			inner join mstt_Policies p on p.POL_NUM = pt.PolicyID
			inner join msit_CommissionStatementPeriods VNBStart on convert(date,pt.CreateDateTime) between VNBStart.PeriodStartDate and VNBStart.PeriodEndDate
			inner join msit_Commissionstatementperiods csp on csp.month = cs.month
			inner join mstt_ProductHierarchy ph on ph.productcode = cs.productcode
			inner join mstt_Expectation e on e.ID = cs.ExpectationID
			left join owt_SelectionControl pcc 
						on pcc.Process = 'ElitePoints'
						and pcc.KeyType = 'ProductCategoryCode'
						and pcc.KeyValue = cs.ProductCode	
						and cs.CreateDate between pcc.EffectiveStartDate and pcc.EffectiveEndDate
	where	cs.ReportingClassCode = 1
	and		cs.CommFeeType = 'Ongoing'
	and		(ph.ProductCategoryCode = 1 or pcc.KeyValue2 = '1')
	and		ag.Manager2Code <> @OwlManager2Code		--Exclude Owl
	and		csp.Year >= 2017						--Ensure in-scope payments are consistent with VNB start
	and		VNBStart.Year >= 2017					--VNB to start from new slices in 2017 for +ve payments
	and		cs.CommissionType = 10 
	and		e.AMOUNT_REC >= 0.01		
	group	by cs.TransactionID, cs.AgentCode, cs.CommissionType

	union
	
	--We need all ongoing adjustment and clawback payments i.e. NOT just the oldest 
	select	cs.TransactionID, cs.AgentCode, cs.CommissionType, cs.PendingPaymentID as MinPendingPaymentID
	from	msit_CommissionStatement cs
			inner join mstt_Agents ag on ag.Code = cs.BusinessCode
			inner join mstt_PolicyTransactions pt on pt.ID = cs.TransactionID
			inner join mstt_Policies p on p.POL_NUM = pt.PolicyID
			inner join msit_CommissionStatementPeriods VNBStart on convert(date,pt.CreateDateTime) between VNBStart.PeriodStartDate and VNBStart.PeriodEndDate
			inner join msit_Commissionstatementperiods csp on csp.month = cs.month
			inner join mstt_ProductHierarchy ph on ph.productcode = cs.productcode
			inner join mstt_Expectation e on e.ID = cs.ExpectationID
			left join owt_SelectionControl pcc 
						on pcc.Process = 'ElitePoints'
						and pcc.KeyType = 'ProductCategoryCode'
						and pcc.KeyValue = cs.ProductCode	
						and cs.CreateDate between pcc.EffectiveStartDate and pcc.EffectiveEndDate
	where	cs.ReportingClassCode = 1
	and		cs.CommFeeType = 'Ongoing'
	and		(ph.ProductCategoryCode = 1 or pcc.KeyValue2 = '1')
	and		ag.Manager2Code <> @OwlManager2Code		--Exclude Owl
	and		csp.Year >= 2017						--We don't care when the transaction started but the payment must be from 2017
	and		cs.CommissionType in (16,19) 
	and		abs(e.AMOUNT_REC) >= 0.01					

	/****************************************************************************
		
		Insert the ongoing VNB results into the main work table
																		
	****************************************************************************/

	--Empty the table so we can build it up again with ongoing.
	truncate table #AG_owt_Recognition_SEPARATE_ONGOING

	--Now Add the ongoing
	insert into #AG_owt_Recognition_SEPARATE_ONGOING
	(
		SourceID,
		CaseID,
		TransactionID,
		Policy,
		ProductCode,
		BusinessCode,
		SellerCode,
		PointsTotal,
		BSC,
		MBF,
		Initial,
		OngoingTotal,
		OngoingYr01,
		OngoingYr02,
		OngoingYr03,
		OngoingYr04,
		OngoingYr05,
		OngoingYr06,
		OngoingYr07,
		OngoingYr08,
		OngoingYr09,
		OngoingYr10,
		FCARate,
		RetentionRate,
		RetentionRateBroker,
		OngoingServicingRate,
		OngoingServicingSource,
		DA,
		AmountReceived,
		Premium,
		AgentSplit,
		CommissionType,
		CommissionTypeDesc,
		PayBasisCode,
		PayBasisDesc,
		PaymentMatchedDate,
		Month,
		FrequencyCode,
		FrequencyDesc,
		ReassignedProductGroupCode,
		ReassignedProductGroupName,
		RecognitionType,
		CalculationType,
		Source,
		DateInserted,
		DateLastUpdated,
		CommissionYear
	)
	select	cs.PendingPaymentID as SourceID,
			cs.CaseID,
			cs.TransactionID,
			cs.ExtPolicyNumber as Policy,
			cs.ProductCode,
			cs.BusinessCode,
			cs.AgentCode as SellerCode,
			0.0 as PointsTotal,
			case
				when BSCpot.ID is not null then 
					--BSC takes the first 0.12 of the ongoing fee %. If the ongoing fee % is 0.12% or less, then 100% of the ongoing fee is allocated to BSC
					case when coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2)) - convert(decimal(8,4),sc.KeyValue2) >= 0.01
						then 
							case when r.FrequencyCode = 2	--Monthly 
								then (r.AgentSplit/100) * 12.0 * (isnull(r.Premium,0)/2.0) * convert(decimal(8,4),sc.KeyValue3) * case when cs.CommissionType in (16,19) then -1 else 1 end
								else (r.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(r.Premium,0) * convert(decimal(8,4),sc.KeyValue3) * case when cs.CommissionType in (16,19) then -1 else 1 end
							end			
						else
							case when r.FrequencyCode = 2	--Monthly 
								then (r.AgentSplit/100) * 12.0 * (isnull(r.Premium,0)/2.0) * coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2)) * case when cs.CommissionType in (16,19) then -1 else 1 end
								else (r.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(r.Premium,0) * (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))/100.0) * case when cs.CommissionType in (16,19) then -1 else 1 end
							end
					end
				else 0.0
			end as BSC,
			0.0 as MBF,
			0.0 as Initial,
			0.0 as OngoingTotal,
			case
				--WEALTH ONGOING CALCULATION START
				--When the adviser has changed, the AgentSplit can become zero in which case the ELITE points should be zero.
				when cs.AgentSplit = 0 then 0

				--SINGLE start
				--Calculate when BSC and ongoing applies (where ongoing rate is greater than BSC rate) 
				when r.FrequencyCode = 6 and SFMpot.ID is not null and BSCpot.ID is not null and (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2)) - convert(decimal(8,4),sc.KeyValue2)) >= 0.01 then 
							--(AUM X BSC Rate)...
							((r.AgentSplit/100) * (isnull(r.Premium,0) * convert(decimal(8,4),sc.KeyValue3)) 
							--(AUM X OGS Rate X COB FCA Rate)...
							- ((r.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(r.Premium,0) * (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))/100.0) * Cfca.FACTOR)
							--(AUM X (OGS Rate - BSC Rate) X COB Retention Rate)...
							+ ((r.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(r.Premium,0) * ((coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))-convert(decimal(8,4),sc.KeyValue2))/100.0)) * Crate.FACTOR) 
							--Sign correctly for +ve or clawback payment
							* (case when cs.CommissionType in (16,19) then -1 else 1 end)
				--Calculate when BSC and ongoing applies (where ongoing rate less than BSC rate, then BSC gets all the ongoing available) 
				when r.FrequencyCode = 6 and SFMpot.ID is not null and BSCpot.ID is not null then
							--(AUM X BSC Rate)...(in this scenario it's all of the OGS rate)
							((r.AgentSplit/100) * (isnull(r.Premium,0) * (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))/100.0)) 
							--(AUM X OGS Rate X COB FCA Rate)...
							- ((r.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(r.Premium,0) * (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))/100.0) * Cfca.FACTOR)
							--(AUM X (OGS Rate - BSC Rate) X COB Retention Rate)...
							+ (0.0)) --BSC got it all, so this part of the calculation is zero
							--Sign correctly for +ve or clawback payment
							* (case when cs.CommissionType in (16,19) then -1 else 1 end)
				--Calculate when no BSC applies and ongoing applies
				when r.FrequencyCode = 6 and SFMpot.ID is not null and BSCpot.ID is null then 
							--(AUM X OGS Rate X COB Retention Rate)...
							(((r.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(r.Premium,0) * (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))/100.0) * Crate.FACTOR) 
							--(AUM X OGS Rate X COB FCA Rate)...
							- ((r.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(cs.Premium,0) * (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))/100.0) * Cfca.FACTOR))
							--Sign correctly for +ve or clawback payment
							* (case when cs.CommissionType in (16,19) then -1 else 1 end)
				--SINGLE end
				
				--REGULAR start
				--Calculate when BSC and ongoing applies (where ongoing rate is greater than BSC rate) 
				when r.FrequencyCode <> 6 and SFMpot.ID is not null and BSCpot.ID is not null and (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2)) - convert(decimal(8,4),sc.KeyValue2)) >= 0.01 then		--AG 04/06/2018 (1)
							--The non-BSC portion (Ave AUM X (OGS Rate - BSC Rate) X COB Retention Rate)...
							((((((r.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(r.Premium,0) * (case when r.FrequencyCode = 2 then 12 else 1 end))/2.0) * (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2)) - convert(decimal(8,4),sc.KeyValue2))/100.0)) * Crate.FACTOR
							--The BSC portion (Ave AUM X BSC Rate)...
							+ case when r.FrequencyCode = 2	--Monthly 
									then (r.AgentSplit/100) * 12.0 * (isnull(r.Premium,0)/2.0) * convert(decimal(8,4),sc.KeyValue3) 
									else (r.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(r.Premium,0) * convert(decimal(8,4),sc.KeyValue3) 
							  end
							--FCA Charge (Ave AUM X OGS Rate X FCA Rate)...
							- (case when r.FrequencyCode = 2	--Monthly 
									then (r.AgentSplit/100) * 12.0 * (isnull(r.Premium,0)/2.0) 
									else (r.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(r.Premium,0) 
							   end * (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))/100.0) * Cfca.FACTOR))
							--Sign correctly for +ve or clawback payment
							* (case when cs.CommissionType in (16,19) then -1 else 1 end)   
				--Calculate when BSC and ongoing applies (where ongoing rate less than BSC rate, then BSC gets all the ongoing available) 
				when r.FrequencyCode <> 6 and SFMpot.ID is not null and BSCpot.ID is not null then		--AG 04/06/2018 (1)
							--The non-BSC portion (Ave AUM X (OGS Rate - BSC Rate) X COB Retention Rate)...
							((0.0)	--BSC got it all, so this part of the calculation is zero
							--The BSC portion (Ave AUM X BSC Rate)...(in this scenario it's all of the OGS rate)
							+ case when r.FrequencyCode = 2	--Monthly 
									then (r.AgentSplit/100) * 12.0 * (isnull(r.Premium,0)/2.0) * (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))/100.0) 
									else (r.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(r.Premium,0) * (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))/100.0) 
							  end
							--FCA Charge (Ave AUM X OGS Rate X FCA Rate)...
							- (case when r.FrequencyCode = 2	--Monthly 
									then (r.AgentSplit/100) * 12.0 * (isnull(r.Premium,0)/2.0) 
									else (r.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(r.Premium,0) 
							   end * (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))/100.0) * Cfca.FACTOR))
							--Sign correctly for +ve or clawback payment
							* (case when cs.CommissionType in (16,19) then -1 else 1 end)   
				--Calculate when no BSC applies, but ongoing servicing applies
				when r.FrequencyCode <> 6 and SFMpot.ID is not null and BSCpot.ID is null then		--AG 04/06/2018	(1)
							--(Ave AUM X OGS Rate X COB Retention Rate)...
							(((((r.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(r.Premium,0) * (case when r.FrequencyCode = 2 then 12 else 1 end))/2.0) * (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))/100.0) * Crate.FACTOR) 
							--(Ave AUM X OGS Rate X COB FCA Rate)...
							- ((((r.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(r.Premium,0) * (case when r.FrequencyCode = 2 then 12 else 1 end))/2.0) * (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))/100.0) * Cfca.FACTOR))
							--Sign correctly for +ve or clawback payment
							* (case when cs.CommissionType in (16,19) then -1 else 1 end)   
				--REGULAR end
				
				else 0.0

				--WEALTH ONGOING CALCULATION END
			end as OngoingYr01,
			0.0 as OngoingYr02,
			0.0 as OngoingYr03,
			0.0 as OngoingYr04,
			0.0 as OngoingYr05,
			0.0 as OngoingYr06,
			0.0 as OngoingYr07,
			0.0 as OngoingYr08,
			0.0 as OngoingYr09,
			0.0 as OngoingYr10,
			Cfca.FACTOR*100.0 as FCARate,
			Crate.FACTOR*100.0 as RetentionRate,
			0.0 as RetentionRateBroker,
			case when SFMpot.ID is not null
				then coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))
				else null
			end as OngoingServicingRate,
			case when SFMpot.ID is not null
				then case 
						when ogs.OngoingServiceFee is null and ogscli.OngoingServiceFee is null 
							then case
								when ogsdflt.KeyValue = 'ONPLAT' then 'Default - On Plat'
								else 'Default - Off Plat'
							end
						when ogs.OngoingServiceFee is not null then 'Client Product'
						when ogscli.OngoingServiceFee is not null then 'Client Only'
						else 'Unknown'
					 end
				else case when (ph.ProductCategoryCode = 1 or pcc.KeyValue2 = '1')
						then 'No OGS'					--WEALTH, but no OGS
						else null						--Not WEALTH, so OGS is n/a and is therefore null
					 end
			end as OngoingServicingSource,
			pt.CommInitialAmount as DA,
			e.AMOUNT_REC as AmountReceived,
			cs.Premium,
			r.AgentSplit,								--Use the split from the initial record
			cs.CommissionType,
			left(cs.StandingOrderDesc,50) as CommissionTypeDesc,
			cs.PayBasisCode,
			cs.PayBasisDesc,
			cs.CreateDate as PaymentMatchedDate,
			cs.Month,
			cs.FrequencyCode,
			cs.FrequencyDesc,
			r.ReassignedProductGroupCode,
			r.ReassignedProductGroupName,
			'VNB-OGS-INITIAL' as RecognitionType,
			'WEALTH-ONGOING' as CalculationType,
			'Openwork 2006' as Source,
			@DateLastUpdated as DateInserted,
			@DateLastUpdated as DateLastUpdated,
			csp.year as CommissionYear
	from	#msit_CommissionStatementONGOING cso
			inner join msit_CommissionStatement cs on cs.PendingPaymentID = cso.MinPendingPaymentID
			inner join #owt_RecognitionINITIAL ri 
						on ri.TransactionID = cs.TransactionID
						and ri.SellerCode = cs.AgentCode
			inner join AG_owt_Recognition_SEPARATE_ONGOING r on r.SourceID = ri.MinSourceID	
			inner join mstt_Agents ag on ag.Code = cs.BusinessCode
			inner join mstt_PolicyTransactions pt on pt.ID = cs.TransactionID
			inner join mstt_Policies p on p.POL_NUM = pt.PolicyID
			inner join msit_CommissionStatementPeriods VNBStart on convert(date,pt.CreateDateTime) between VNBStart.PeriodStartDate and VNBStart.PeriodEndDate
			inner join msit_Commissionstatementperiods csp on csp.month = cs.month
			inner join mstt_ProductHierarchy ph on ph.productcode = cs.productcode
			inner join mstt_Expectation e on e.ID = cs.ExpectationID
			left join dbo.owt_MortgageBrokerFees mbf on mbf.PendingPaymentID = cs.PendingPaymentID and mbf.AdviceFeeCharged = 'Yes'
			left join owt_SelectionControl SC
						on SC.Process = 'ElitePoints' 
						and SC.KeyType = 'NSCPotCode' 
						and cs.CreateDate between SC.EffectiveStartDate and SC.EffectiveEndDate
			left join mstt_Commissions BSCpot
						on BSCpot.TransactionID = cs.TransactionID 
						and BSCpot.Agent_Code = sc.KeyValue
						and BSCpot.CommissionType = 10
			left join owt_SelectionControl SFMPC						
						on SFMPC.Process = 'ElitePoints' 
						and SFMPC.KeyType = 'ServicingFeeMarginPotCode' 
						and cs.CreateDate between SFMPC.EffectiveStartDate and SFMPC.EffectiveEndDate
			left join mstt_Commissions SFMpot							
						on SFMpot.TransactionID = cs.TransactionID 
						and SFMpot.Agent_Code = SFMPC.KeyValue
						and SFMpot.CommissionType = 10	
			left join owt_SelectionControl pcc 
						on pcc.Process = 'ElitePoints'
						and pcc.KeyType = 'ProductCategoryCode'
						and pcc.KeyValue = cs.ProductCode	
						and cs.CreateDate between pcc.EffectiveStartDate and pcc.EffectiveEndDate
			left join owt_SelectionControl ogsdflt 
						on ogsdflt.Process = 'ElitePoints'
						and ogsdflt.KeyType = 'DefaultOngoingServicingRate'
						and ogsdflt.SelectionType = 'VNB'
						and ogsdflt.KeyValue = case when ph.RDRType = 'ONPLAT' then 'ONPLAT' else 'OFPLAT' end
						and cs.CreateDate between ogsdflt.EffectiveStartDate and ogsdflt.EffectiveEndDate
			left join mstt_CodeProductGroup pg on pg.ProductGroupCode = case when pcc.KeyValue2 = '1' then 2 else ph.ProductGroupCode end
			left join owt_EliteFactors Cfca on Cfca.FeeType = 'VNB' and Cfca.category = 'COB-FCA-RATE' and csp.year between Cfca.StartYear and Cfca.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors Crate on Crate.FeeType = 'VNB' and Crate.category = 'COB-RETENTION-RATE' and csp.year between Crate.StartYear and Crate.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors Mfca on Mfca.FeeType = 'VNB' and Mfca.category = 'MORT-FCA-RATE' and csp.year between Mfca.StartYear and Mfca.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors MRproc on MRproc.FeeType = 'VNB' and MRproc.category = 'MORT-RETENTION-RATE-PROC' and csp.year between MRproc.StartYear and MRproc.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors MRbkr on MRbkr.FeeType = 'VNB' and MRbkr.category = 'MORT-RETENTION-RATE-BROKER' and csp.year between MRbkr.StartYear and MRbkr.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors Pfca on Pfca.FeeType = 'VNB' and Pfca.category = 'PROT-FCA-RATE' and csp.year between Pfca.StartYear and Pfca.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors Prate on Prate.FeeType = 'VNB' and Prate.category = 'PROT-RETENTION-RATE' and csp.year between Prate.StartYear and Prate.EndYear 
			left join #OGSLookUp ogs on ogs.CLIENT_NUM = cs.ClientID and ogs.ProductCode = cs.ProductCode
			left join #OGSLookUpClient ogscli on ogscli.CLIENT_NUM = cs.ClientID 	

	/****************************************************************************

		Now select zero fee cases. Zero fee cases have no initial
		payment rows on msit_CommissionStatement.
																		
	****************************************************************************/

	select	co.TransactionID, 
			co.Agent_Code as SellerCode, 
			co.Agent_Perc as AgentSplit, 
			co.Firm as BusinessCode
	into	#ZeroFeeTransactions
	from	mstt_Commissions co 
			inner join mstt_PolicyTransactions pt on pt.ID = co.TransactionID 
			inner join mstt_Policies po on po.pol_num = pt.PolicyID 
			inner join msit_CommissionStatementPeriods VNBStart on convert(date,pt.CreateDateTime) between VNBStart.PeriodStartDate and VNBStart.PeriodEndDate
			inner join mstt_ProductHierarchy ph ON ph.ProductCode = co.ProductCode 
			inner join mstt_Agents ag on ag.Code = co.Firm	
			left join dbo.AG_owt_Recognition_SEPARATE_ONGOING r
						on r.TransactionID = co.TransactionID
						and r.SellerCode = co.Agent_Code	
	where	co.Agent_Code <> '10002'
	and		VNBStart.Year >= 2017 
	and		co.CommissionType = 1
	and		ph.RDRType is not null							--Pensions and investments (wealth)
	and		pt.CommInitialAmount <= 0 
	and		((pt.Frequency = 6 and pt.Amount > 1.00)		--Frequency=6->Single	These filters remove fixes put in by PSD because you can't...
			or (pt.Frequency <> 6 and pt.Amount > 0.01))	--Frequency<>6->Regular	... amend trail splits, you need to add a new slice.
	and		co.PolTranTransType = 17
	and		ag.Manager2Code <> '1011671'	-- Not Owl
	and		r.ID is null
	group	by	co.TransactionID, co.Agent_Code, co.Agent_Perc, co.Firm
	--order by 1

	/****************************************************************************

		Now calculate the ongoing for zero fee cases. Zero fee cases have no initial
		payment rows on msit_CommissionStatement.
																		
	****************************************************************************/

	--Now Add the ongoing
	insert into #AG_owt_Recognition_SEPARATE_ONGOING
	(
		SourceID,
		CaseID,
		TransactionID,
		Policy,
		ProductCode,
		BusinessCode,
		SellerCode,
		PointsTotal,
		BSC,
		MBF,
		Initial,
		OngoingTotal,
		OngoingYr01,
		OngoingYr02,
		OngoingYr03,
		OngoingYr04,
		OngoingYr05,
		OngoingYr06,
		OngoingYr07,
		OngoingYr08,
		OngoingYr09,
		OngoingYr10,
		FCARate,
		RetentionRate,
		RetentionRateBroker,
		OngoingServicingRate,
		OngoingServicingSource,
		DA,
		AmountReceived,
		Premium,
		AgentSplit,
		CommissionType,
		CommissionTypeDesc,
		PayBasisCode,
		PayBasisDesc,
		PaymentMatchedDate,
		Month,
		FrequencyCode,
		FrequencyDesc,
		ReassignedProductGroupCode,
		ReassignedProductGroupName,
		RecognitionType,
		CalculationType,
		Source,
		DateInserted,
		DateLastUpdated,
		CommissionYear
	)
	select	cs.PendingPaymentID as SourceID,
			cs.CaseID,
			cs.TransactionID,
			cs.ExtPolicyNumber as Policy,
			cs.ProductCode,
			cs.BusinessCode,
			cs.AgentCode as SellerCode,
			0.0 as PointsTotal,
			case
				when BSCpot.ID is not null then 
					--BSC takes the first 0.12 of the ongoing fee %. If the ongoing fee % is 0.12% or less, then 100% of the ongoing fee is allocated to BSC
					case when coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2)) - convert(decimal(8,4),sc.KeyValue2) >= 0.01
						then 
							case when r.FrequencyCode = 2	--Monthly 
								then (r.AgentSplit/100) * 12.0 * (isnull(r.Premium,0)/2.0) * convert(decimal(8,4),sc.KeyValue3) * case when cs.CommissionType in (16,19) then -1 else 1 end
								else (r.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(r.Premium,0) * convert(decimal(8,4),sc.KeyValue3) * case when cs.CommissionType in (16,19) then -1 else 1 end
							end			
						else
							case when r.FrequencyCode = 2	--Monthly 
								then (r.AgentSplit/100) * 12.0 * (isnull(r.Premium,0)/2.0) * coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2)) * case when cs.CommissionType in (16,19) then -1 else 1 end
								else (r.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(r.Premium,0) * (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))/100.0) * case when cs.CommissionType in (16,19) then -1 else 1 end
							end
					end
				else 0.0
			end as BSC,
			0.0 as MBF,
			0.0 as Initial,
			0.0 as OngoingTotal,
			case
				--WEALTH ONGOING CALCULATION START
				--When the adviser has changed, the AgentSplit can become zero in which case the ELITE points should be zero.
				when cs.AgentSplit = 0 then 0

				--SINGLE start
				--Calculate when BSC and ongoing applies (where ongoing rate is greater than BSC rate) 
				when r.FrequencyCode = 6 and SFMpot.ID is not null and BSCpot.ID is not null and (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2)) - convert(decimal(8,4),sc.KeyValue2)) >= 0.01 then 
							--(AUM X BSC Rate)...
							((r.AgentSplit/100) * (isnull(r.Premium,0) * convert(decimal(8,4),sc.KeyValue3)) 
							--(AUM X OGS Rate X COB FCA Rate)...
							- ((r.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(r.Premium,0) * (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))/100.0) * Cfca.FACTOR)
							--(AUM X (OGS Rate - BSC Rate) X COB Retention Rate)...
							+ ((r.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(r.Premium,0) * ((coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))-convert(decimal(8,4),sc.KeyValue2))/100.0)) * Crate.FACTOR) 
							--Sign correctly for +ve or clawback payment
							* (case when cs.CommissionType in (16,19) then -1 else 1 end)
				--Calculate when BSC and ongoing applies (where ongoing rate less than BSC rate, then BSC gets all the ongoing available) 
				when r.FrequencyCode = 6 and SFMpot.ID is not null and BSCpot.ID is not null then
							--(AUM X BSC Rate)...(in this scenario it's all of the OGS rate)
							((r.AgentSplit/100) * (isnull(r.Premium,0) * (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))/100.0)) 
							--(AUM X OGS Rate X COB FCA Rate)...
							- ((r.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(r.Premium,0) * (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))/100.0) * Cfca.FACTOR)
							--(AUM X (OGS Rate - BSC Rate) X COB Retention Rate)...
							+ (0.0)) --BSC got it all, so this part of the calculation is zero
							--Sign correctly for +ve or clawback payment
							* (case when cs.CommissionType in (16,19) then -1 else 1 end)
				--Calculate when no BSC applies and ongoing applies
				when r.FrequencyCode = 6 and SFMpot.ID is not null and BSCpot.ID is null then 
							--(AUM X OGS Rate X COB Retention Rate)...
							(((r.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(r.Premium,0) * (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))/100.0) * Crate.FACTOR) 
							--(AUM X OGS Rate X COB FCA Rate)...
							- ((r.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(cs.Premium,0) * (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))/100.0) * Cfca.FACTOR))
							--Sign correctly for +ve or clawback payment
							* (case when cs.CommissionType in (16,19) then -1 else 1 end)
				--SINGLE end
				
				--REGULAR start
				--Calculate when BSC and ongoing applies (where ongoing rate is greater than BSC rate) 
				when r.FrequencyCode <> 6 and SFMpot.ID is not null and BSCpot.ID is not null and (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2)) - convert(decimal(8,4),sc.KeyValue2)) >= 0.01 then		--AG 04/06/2018 (1)
							--The non-BSC portion (Ave AUM X (OGS Rate - BSC Rate) X COB Retention Rate)...
							((((((r.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(r.Premium,0) * (case when r.FrequencyCode = 2 then 12 else 1 end))/2.0) * (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2)) - convert(decimal(8,4),sc.KeyValue2))/100.0)) * Crate.FACTOR
							--The BSC portion (Ave AUM X BSC Rate)...
							+ case when r.FrequencyCode = 2	--Monthly 
									then (r.AgentSplit/100) * 12.0 * (isnull(r.Premium,0)/2.0) * convert(decimal(8,4),sc.KeyValue3) 
									else (r.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(r.Premium,0) * convert(decimal(8,4),sc.KeyValue3) 
							  end
							--FCA Charge (Ave AUM X OGS Rate X FCA Rate)...
							- (case when r.FrequencyCode = 2	--Monthly 
									then (r.AgentSplit/100) * 12.0 * (isnull(r.Premium,0)/2.0) 
									else (r.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(r.Premium,0) 
							   end * (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))/100.0) * Cfca.FACTOR))
							--Sign correctly for +ve or clawback payment
							* (case when cs.CommissionType in (16,19) then -1 else 1 end)   
				--Calculate when BSC and ongoing applies (where ongoing rate less than BSC rate, then BSC gets all the ongoing available) 
				when r.FrequencyCode <> 6 and SFMpot.ID is not null and BSCpot.ID is not null then		--AG 04/06/2018 (1)
							--The non-BSC portion (Ave AUM X (OGS Rate - BSC Rate) X COB Retention Rate)...
							((0.0)	--BSC got it all, so this part of the calculation is zero
							--The BSC portion (Ave AUM X BSC Rate)...(in this scenario it's all of the OGS rate)
							+ case when r.FrequencyCode = 2	--Monthly 
									then (r.AgentSplit/100) * 12.0 * (isnull(r.Premium,0)/2.0) * (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))/100.0) 
									else (r.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(r.Premium,0) * (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))/100.0) 
							  end
							--FCA Charge (Ave AUM X OGS Rate X FCA Rate)...
							- (case when r.FrequencyCode = 2	--Monthly 
									then (r.AgentSplit/100) * 12.0 * (isnull(r.Premium,0)/2.0) 
									else (r.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(r.Premium,0) 
							   end * (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))/100.0) * Cfca.FACTOR))
							--Sign correctly for +ve or clawback payment
							* (case when cs.CommissionType in (16,19) then -1 else 1 end)   
				--Calculate when no BSC applies, but ongoing servicing applies
				when r.FrequencyCode <> 6 and SFMpot.ID is not null and BSCpot.ID is null then		--AG 04/06/2018	(1)
							--(Ave AUM X OGS Rate X COB Retention Rate)...
							(((((r.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(r.Premium,0) * (case when r.FrequencyCode = 2 then 12 else 1 end))/2.0) * (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))/100.0) * Crate.FACTOR) 
							--(Ave AUM X OGS Rate X COB FCA Rate)...
							- ((((r.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(r.Premium,0) * (case when r.FrequencyCode = 2 then 12 else 1 end))/2.0) * (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))/100.0) * Cfca.FACTOR))
							--Sign correctly for +ve or clawback payment
							* (case when cs.CommissionType in (16,19) then -1 else 1 end)   
				--REGULAR end
				
				else 0.0

				--WEALTH ONGOING CALCULATION END
			end as OngoingYr01,
			0.0 as OngoingYr02,
			0.0 as OngoingYr03,
			0.0 as OngoingYr04,
			0.0 as OngoingYr05,
			0.0 as OngoingYr06,
			0.0 as OngoingYr07,
			0.0 as OngoingYr08,
			0.0 as OngoingYr09,
			0.0 as OngoingYr10,
			Cfca.FACTOR*100.0 as FCARate,
			Crate.FACTOR*100.0 as RetentionRate,
			0.0 as RetentionRateBroker,
			case when SFMpot.ID is not null
				then coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))
				else null
			end as OngoingServicingRate,
			case when SFMpot.ID is not null
				then case 
						when ogs.OngoingServiceFee is null and ogscli.OngoingServiceFee is null 
							then case
								when ogsdflt.KeyValue = 'ONPLAT' then 'Default - On Plat'
								else 'Default - Off Plat'
							end
						when ogs.OngoingServiceFee is not null then 'Client Product'
						when ogscli.OngoingServiceFee is not null then 'Client Only'
						else 'Unknown'
					 end
				else case when (ph.ProductCategoryCode = 1 or pcc.KeyValue2 = '1')
						then 'No OGS'					--WEALTH, but no OGS
						else null						--Not WEALTH, so OGS is n/a and is therefore null
					 end
			end as OngoingServicingSource,
			pt.CommInitialAmount as DA,
			e.AMOUNT_REC as AmountReceived,
			cs.Premium,
			r.AgentSplit,								--Use the split from the initial record
			cs.CommissionType,
			left(cs.StandingOrderDesc,50) as CommissionTypeDesc,
			cs.PayBasisCode,
			cs.PayBasisDesc,
			cs.CreateDate as PaymentMatchedDate,
			cs.Month,
			cs.FrequencyCode,
			cs.FrequencyDesc,
			r.ReassignedProductGroupCode,
			r.ReassignedProductGroupName,
			'VNB-OGS-ZEROFEE' as RecognitionType,
			'WEALTH-ONGOING' as CalculationType,
			'Openwork 2006' as Source,
			@DateLastUpdated as DateInserted,
			@DateLastUpdated as DateLastUpdated,
			csp.year as CommissionYear
	from	#msit_CommissionStatementONGOING cso
			inner join msit_CommissionStatement cs on cs.PendingPaymentID = cso.MinPendingPaymentID
			inner join #owt_RecognitionINITIAL ri 
						on ri.TransactionID = cs.TransactionID
						and ri.SellerCode = cs.AgentCode
			inner join AG_owt_Recognition_SEPARATE_ONGOING r on r.SourceID = ri.MinSourceID	
			inner join mstt_Agents ag on ag.Code = cs.BusinessCode
			inner join mstt_PolicyTransactions pt on pt.ID = cs.TransactionID
			inner join mstt_Policies p on p.POL_NUM = pt.PolicyID
			inner join msit_CommissionStatementPeriods VNBStart on convert(date,pt.CreateDateTime) between VNBStart.PeriodStartDate and VNBStart.PeriodEndDate
			inner join msit_Commissionstatementperiods csp on csp.month = cs.month
			inner join mstt_ProductHierarchy ph on ph.productcode = cs.productcode
			inner join mstt_Expectation e on e.ID = cs.ExpectationID
			left join dbo.owt_MortgageBrokerFees mbf on mbf.PendingPaymentID = cs.PendingPaymentID and mbf.AdviceFeeCharged = 'Yes'
			left join owt_SelectionControl SC
						on SC.Process = 'ElitePoints' 
						and SC.KeyType = 'NSCPotCode' 
						and cs.CreateDate between SC.EffectiveStartDate and SC.EffectiveEndDate
			left join mstt_Commissions BSCpot
						on BSCpot.TransactionID = cs.TransactionID 
						and BSCpot.Agent_Code = sc.KeyValue
						and BSCpot.CommissionType = 10
			left join owt_SelectionControl SFMPC						
						on SFMPC.Process = 'ElitePoints' 
						and SFMPC.KeyType = 'ServicingFeeMarginPotCode' 
						and cs.CreateDate between SFMPC.EffectiveStartDate and SFMPC.EffectiveEndDate
			left join mstt_Commissions SFMpot							
						on SFMpot.TransactionID = cs.TransactionID 
						and SFMpot.Agent_Code = SFMPC.KeyValue
						and SFMpot.CommissionType = 10	
			left join owt_SelectionControl pcc 
						on pcc.Process = 'ElitePoints'
						and pcc.KeyType = 'ProductCategoryCode'
						and pcc.KeyValue = cs.ProductCode	
						and cs.CreateDate between pcc.EffectiveStartDate and pcc.EffectiveEndDate
			left join owt_SelectionControl ogsdflt 
						on ogsdflt.Process = 'ElitePoints'
						and ogsdflt.KeyType = 'DefaultOngoingServicingRate'
						and ogsdflt.SelectionType = 'VNB'
						and ogsdflt.KeyValue = case when ph.RDRType = 'ONPLAT' then 'ONPLAT' else 'OFPLAT' end
						and cs.CreateDate between ogsdflt.EffectiveStartDate and ogsdflt.EffectiveEndDate
			left join mstt_CodeProductGroup pg on pg.ProductGroupCode = case when pcc.KeyValue2 = '1' then 2 else ph.ProductGroupCode end
			left join owt_EliteFactors Cfca on Cfca.FeeType = 'VNB' and Cfca.category = 'COB-FCA-RATE' and csp.year between Cfca.StartYear and Cfca.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors Crate on Crate.FeeType = 'VNB' and Crate.category = 'COB-RETENTION-RATE' and csp.year between Crate.StartYear and Crate.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors Mfca on Mfca.FeeType = 'VNB' and Mfca.category = 'MORT-FCA-RATE' and csp.year between Mfca.StartYear and Mfca.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors MRproc on MRproc.FeeType = 'VNB' and MRproc.category = 'MORT-RETENTION-RATE-PROC' and csp.year between MRproc.StartYear and MRproc.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors MRbkr on MRbkr.FeeType = 'VNB' and MRbkr.category = 'MORT-RETENTION-RATE-BROKER' and csp.year between MRbkr.StartYear and MRbkr.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors Pfca on Pfca.FeeType = 'VNB' and Pfca.category = 'PROT-FCA-RATE' and csp.year between Pfca.StartYear and Pfca.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors Prate on Prate.FeeType = 'VNB' and Prate.category = 'PROT-RETENTION-RATE' and csp.year between Prate.StartYear and Prate.EndYear 
			left join #OGSLookUp ogs on ogs.CLIENT_NUM = cs.ClientID and ogs.ProductCode = cs.ProductCode
			left join #OGSLookUpClient ogscli on ogscli.CLIENT_NUM = cs.ClientID 	




	/****************************************************************************

		Now calculate the ongoing spread as follows:
		1) Investments: Years 1 to 6
		2) Pensions:	Years 1 to 10
		Note that regular payments get an additional multiplier to uplift the 
		average AUM for each year.
																		
	****************************************************************************/

	update r
		set OngoingYr02 = case when r.FrequencyCode = 2									--Monthly
							then r.OngoingYr01 * YR02.Multiplier * YR02.Factor			--Regular
							else r.OngoingYr01 * YR02.Factor							--Single
						  end,
			OngoingYr03 = case when r.FrequencyCode = 2									--Monthly
							then r.OngoingYr01 * YR03.Multiplier * YR03.Factor			--Regular
							else r.OngoingYr01 * YR03.Factor							--Single
						  end,
			OngoingYr04 = case when r.FrequencyCode = 2									--Monthly
							then r.OngoingYr01 * YR04.Multiplier * YR04.Factor			--Regular
							else r.OngoingYr01 * YR04.Factor							--Single
						  end,
			OngoingYr05 = case when r.FrequencyCode = 2									--Monthly 
							then r.OngoingYr01 * YR05.Multiplier * YR05.Factor			--Regular
							else r.OngoingYr01 * YR05.Factor							--Single
						  end,
			OngoingYr06 = case when r.FrequencyCode = 2									--Monthly 
							then r.OngoingYr01 * YR06.Multiplier * YR06.Factor			--Regular
							else r.OngoingYr01 * YR06.Factor							--Single
						  end,
			OngoingYr07 = case when r.ReassignedProductGroupCode = 5					--Pensions	AG 05/06/2018
							then
								case when r.FrequencyCode = 2							--Monthly 
									then r.OngoingYr01 * YR07.Multiplier * YR07.Factor	--Regular
									else r.OngoingYr01 * YR07.Factor					--Single
								end
							else 
								0.0
						  end,
			OngoingYr08 = case when r.ReassignedProductGroupCode = 5					--Pensions	AG 05/06/2018 
							then
								case when r.FrequencyCode = 2							--Monthly 
									then r.OngoingYr01 * YR08.Multiplier * YR08.Factor	--Regular
									else r.OngoingYr01 * YR08.Factor					--Single
								end
							else 
								0.0
						  end,
			OngoingYr09 = case when r.ReassignedProductGroupCode = 5					--Pensions	AG 05/06/2018 
							then
								case when r.FrequencyCode = 2							--Monthly 
									then r.OngoingYr01 * YR09.Multiplier * YR09.Factor	--Regular
									else r.OngoingYr01 * YR09.Factor					--Single
								end
							else 
								0.0
						  end,
			OngoingYr10 = case when r.ReassignedProductGroupCode = 5					--Pensions	AG 05/06/2018
							then
								case when r.FrequencyCode = 2							--Monthly 
									then r.OngoingYr01 * YR10.Multiplier * YR10.Factor	--Regular
									else r.OngoingYr01 * YR10.Factor					--Single
								end
							else 
								0.0
						  end
	from	#AG_owt_Recognition_SEPARATE_ONGOING r
			left join owt_EliteFactors YR01 on YR01.FeeType = 'VNB' and YR01.Category = 'COB-ONGOING-DISCOUNT-YR01' and r.CommissionYear between YR01.StartYear and YR01.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors YR02 on YR02.FeeType = 'VNB' and YR02.Category = 'COB-ONGOING-DISCOUNT-YR02' and r.CommissionYear between YR02.StartYear and YR02.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors YR03 on YR03.FeeType = 'VNB' and YR03.Category = 'COB-ONGOING-DISCOUNT-YR03' and r.CommissionYear between YR03.StartYear and YR03.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors YR04 on YR04.FeeType = 'VNB' and YR04.Category = 'COB-ONGOING-DISCOUNT-YR04' and r.CommissionYear between YR04.StartYear and YR04.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors YR05 on YR05.FeeType = 'VNB' and YR05.Category = 'COB-ONGOING-DISCOUNT-YR05' and r.CommissionYear between YR05.StartYear and YR05.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors YR06 on YR06.FeeType = 'VNB' and YR06.Category = 'COB-ONGOING-DISCOUNT-YR06' and r.CommissionYear between YR06.StartYear and YR06.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors YR07 on YR07.FeeType = 'VNB' and YR07.Category = 'COB-ONGOING-DISCOUNT-YR07' and r.CommissionYear between YR07.StartYear and YR07.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors YR08 on YR08.FeeType = 'VNB' and YR08.Category = 'COB-ONGOING-DISCOUNT-YR08' and r.CommissionYear between YR08.StartYear and YR08.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors YR09 on YR09.FeeType = 'VNB' and YR09.Category = 'COB-ONGOING-DISCOUNT-YR09' and r.CommissionYear between YR09.StartYear and YR09.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors YR10 on YR10.FeeType = 'VNB' and YR10.Category = 'COB-ONGOING-DISCOUNT-YR10' and r.CommissionYear between YR10.StartYear and YR10.EndYear 
	where	r.CalculationType = 'WEALTH-ONGOING'
	
	/****************************************************************************

		Now add up all the numbers
																		
	****************************************************************************/
	
	update r
		set OngoingTotal	=	OngoingYr01 + OngoingYr02 + OngoingYr03 + OngoingYr04 + OngoingYr05 +
								OngoingYr06 + OngoingYr07 + OngoingYr08 + OngoingYr09 + OngoingYr10,
			PointsTotal		=	OngoingYr01 + OngoingYr02 + OngoingYr03 + OngoingYr04 + OngoingYr05 +
								OngoingYr06 + OngoingYr07 + OngoingYr08 + OngoingYr09 + OngoingYr10
	from	#AG_owt_Recognition_SEPARATE_ONGOING r

	/****************************************************************************

		Merge the temporary table into the permanent table (IC data)
																		
	****************************************************************************/

	declare @SummaryOfChangesONGOING table (Change varchar(20))
	merge	dbo.AG_owt_Recognition_SEPARATE_ONGOING as trg
	using	#AG_owt_Recognition_SEPARATE_ONGOING as src
	on		trg.SourceID = src.SourceID
	and		trg.Source = src.Source
	when	matched 
	and		isnull(trg.PointsTotal,0) <> isnull(src.PointsTotal,0)
	then	update 
				set trg.CaseID = src.CaseID,
					trg.TransactionID = src.TransactionID,
					trg.Policy = src.Policy,
					trg.ProductCode = src.ProductCode,
					trg.BusinessCode = src.BusinessCode,
					trg.SellerCode = src.SellerCode,					--AG 13/06/2018
					trg.PointsTotal = src.PointsTotal,
					trg.BSC = src.BSC,
					trg.MBF = src.MBF,
					trg.Initial = src.Initial,
					trg.OngoingTotal = src.OngoingTotal,
					trg.OngoingYr01 = src.OngoingYr01,
					trg.OngoingYr02 = src.OngoingYr02,
					trg.OngoingYr03 = src.OngoingYr03,
					trg.OngoingYr04 = src.OngoingYr04,
					trg.OngoingYr05 = src.OngoingYr05,
					trg.OngoingYr06 = src.OngoingYr06,
					trg.OngoingYr07 = src.OngoingYr07,
					trg.OngoingYr08 = src.OngoingYr08,
					trg.OngoingYr09 = src.OngoingYr09,
					trg.OngoingYr10 = src.OngoingYr10,
					trg.FCARate = src.FCARate,
					trg.RetentionRate = src.RetentionRate,
					trg.RetentionRateBroker = src.RetentionRateBroker,
					trg.OngoingServicingRate = src.OngoingServicingRate,
					trg.OngoingServicingSource = src.OngoingServicingSource,
					trg.DA = src.DA,
					trg.AmountReceived = src.AmountReceived,
					trg.Premium = src.Premium,
					trg.AgentSplit = src.AgentSplit,
					trg.CommissionType = src.CommissionType,
					trg.CommissionTypeDesc = src.CommissionTypeDesc,
					trg.PayBasisCode = src.PayBasisCode,				--AG 13/06/2018
					trg.PayBasisDesc = src.PayBasisDesc,				--AG 13/06/2018
					trg.PaymentMatchedDate = src.PaymentMatchedDate,	--AG 13/06/2018	
					trg.Month = src.Month,
					trg.FrequencyCode = src.FrequencyCode,
					trg.FrequencyDesc = src.FrequencyDesc,
					trg.ReassignedProductGroupCode = src.ReassignedProductGroupCode,	--AG 05/06/2018
					trg.ReassignedProductGroupName = src.ReassignedProductGroupName,	--AG 05/06/2018
					trg.RecognitionType = src.RecognitionType,
					trg.CalculationType = src.CalculationType,
					trg.DateLastUpdated = @DateLastUpdated
	when	not matched by target 
	then	insert
			(
				SourceID,
				CaseID,
				TransactionID,
				Policy,
				ProductCode,
				BusinessCode,
				SellerCode,							--AG 13/06/2018
				PointsTotal,
				BSC,
				MBF,
				Initial,
				OngoingTotal,
				OngoingYr01,
				OngoingYr02,
				OngoingYr03,
				OngoingYr04,
				OngoingYr05,
				OngoingYr06,
				OngoingYr07,
				OngoingYr08,
				OngoingYr09,
				OngoingYr10,
				FCARate,
				RetentionRate,
				RetentionRateBroker,
				OngoingServicingRate,
				OngoingServicingSource,
				DA,
				AmountReceived,
				Premium,
				AgentSplit,
				CommissionType,
				CommissionTypeDesc,
				PayBasisCode,						--AG 13/06/2018
				PayBasisDesc,						--AG 13/06/2018
				PaymentMatchedDate,					--AG 13/06/2018
				Month,
				FrequencyCode,
				FrequencyDesc,
				ReassignedProductGroupCode,			--AG 05/06/2018
				ReassignedProductGroupName,			--AG 05/06/2018
				RecognitionType,
				CalculationType,
				Source,
				DateInserted,
				DateLastUpdated
			)		
			values
			(
				src.SourceID,
				src.CaseID,
				src.TransactionID,
				src.Policy,
				src.ProductCode,
				src.BusinessCode,
				src.SellerCode,						--AG 13/06/2018
				src.PointsTotal,
				src.BSC,
				src.MBF,
				src.Initial,
				src.OngoingTotal,
				src.OngoingYr01,
				src.OngoingYr02,
				src.OngoingYr03,
				src.OngoingYr04,
				src.OngoingYr05,
				src.OngoingYr06,
				src.OngoingYr07,
				src.OngoingYr08,
				src.OngoingYr09,
				src.OngoingYr10,
				src.FCARate,
				src.RetentionRate,
				src.RetentionRateBroker,
				src.OngoingServicingRate,
				src.OngoingServicingSource,
				src.DA,
				src.AmountReceived,
				src.Premium,
				src.AgentSplit,
				src.CommissionType,
				src.CommissionTypeDesc,
				src.PayBasisCode,					--AG 13/06/2018
				src.PayBasisDesc,					--AG 13/06/2018
				src.PaymentMatchedDate,				--AG 13/06/2018
				src.Month,
				src.FrequencyCode,
				src.FrequencyDesc,
				src.ReassignedProductGroupCode,		--AG 05/06/2018
				src.ReassignedProductGroupName,		--AG 05/06/2018
				src.RecognitionType,
				src.CalculationType,
				src.Source,
				src.DateInserted,
				src.DateLastUpdated)				--Merge statements must have a ;
	output $action into @SummaryOfChangesONGOING;
						
	/****************************************************************************

		Update OpenAccess
																		
	****************************************************************************/

	
/*	
	--Do not include MBF in the OpenAccess Commission Listing as it is on the MBF download
	--and we don't want MBF double counting.
	update	oal
		set VNB_Points = r.PointsTotal - r.MBF		--AG 04/06/2018 (2)
	from	msit_CommissionStatement cs
/*			inner join (select	distinct PKID
						from	owt_TransformationMovements tm 
						where	tm.DriverTableName = 'sa_swift_S_AGMFIL'
						and		tm.CommissionStatement = 'Y') tm on tm.PKID = cs.PendingPaymentID
*/			inner join msit_OpenworkAdviserListing oal on oal.SourceID = cs.ID and oal.Source = 'Openwork 2006'
			inner join owt_Recognition r 
						on r.RecognitionType = 'VNB'
						and r.SourceID = cs.PendingPaymentID
						and r.Source = oal.Source
	--where	isnull(oal.VNB_Points,0) <> isnull(r.PointsTotal,0)
	
	select @OALRowCount = @@rowcount
*/
	COMMIT TRANSACTION      

	select	@RowCount = COUNT(*)
	from	@SummaryOfChangesINITIAL
	where	Change = 'INSERT'

	set @ProcessMessage = 'owt_Recognition (initial insert) = ' + convert(nvarchar(10), @RowCount)
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseLog, @ProcessMessage, null, @Module, @Client

	select	@RowCount = COUNT(*)
	from	@SummaryOfChangesINITIAL
	where	Change = 'UPDATE'

	set @ProcessMessage = 'owt_Recognition (initial update) = ' + convert(nvarchar(10), @RowCount)
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseLog, @ProcessMessage, null, @Module, @Client
	
	select	@RowCount = COUNT(*)
	from	@SummaryOfChangesONGOING
	where	Change = 'INSERT'

	set @ProcessMessage = 'owt_Recognition (ongoing insert) = ' + convert(nvarchar(10), @RowCount)
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseLog, @ProcessMessage, null, @Module, @Client

	select	@RowCount = COUNT(*)
	from	@SummaryOfChangesONGOING
	where	Change = 'UPDATE'

	set @ProcessMessage = 'owt_Recognition (ongoing update) = ' + convert(nvarchar(10), @RowCount)
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseLog, @ProcessMessage, null, @Module, @Client
	
/*
	set @ProcessMessage = 'msit_OpenworkAdviserListing (update) = ' + convert(nvarchar(10), @OALRowCount)
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseLog, @ProcessMessage, null, @Module, @Client
*/
	/****************************************************************************

		T H E   E N D
																		
	****************************************************************************/
	
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseEnd, @ProcName, null, @Module, @Client

END TRY

BEGIN CATCH 

	select @ErrNum = ERROR_NUMBER(), @ErrMsg = ERROR_MESSAGE(), @ErrSev = ERROR_SEVERITY(), @ErrLine = ERROR_LINE(), @ErrState = XACT_STATE()
	set @ErrMsg = REPLACE(@ErrMsg, '.', '') + ' (error no: ' + CAST(@ErrNum AS VARCHAR(10)) + ') on line ' + CAST(@ErrLine AS VARCHAR(10))
	
	-- Test XACT_STATE for 0, 1, or -1.
    -- If 1, the transaction is committable.
    -- If -1, the transaction is uncommittable and should be rolled back.
    -- If 0, there is no transaction and a commit or rollback operation would generate an error.

	if @ErrState = -1			-- Transaction is uncommitable
		rollback transaction

	if @ErrState = 1			
		commit transaction

	-- Error message line 1
	set @ErrMsgBrief = left(@ErrMsg,100)
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseError, @ErrMsgBrief, null, @Module, @Client
	
	-- Error message line 2 - if any text exists
	set @ErrMsgBrief = substring(@ErrMsg,101,100)
	if len(@ErrMsgBrief) > 0
		exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseError, @ErrMsgBrief, null, @Module, @Client

	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseEnd, @ProcName, null, @Module, @Client

	RAISERROR(@ErrMsg, @ErrSev , 1)

END CATCH

/****************************************************************************

			E N D															

****************************************************************************/

return @ErrNum


GO
/****** Object:  StoredProcedure [dbo].[owp_RecognitionSwiftONGOING_Backup20180628AG]    Script Date: 7/3/2026 3:44:25 PM ******/
SET ANSI_NULLS ON
GO
SET QUOTED_IDENTIFIER ON
GO
/*********************************************************************************************************

Program:		owp_RecognitionSwift					
Author:			Alan Groves
Date created:	11/04/2018
											
Description:
===========

This proc populates the new recognition table called "owt_Recognition" with "Value of New Business"
(VNB) points.

This proc handles all of the swift data which includes:
WEALTH - COB business i.e. pensions and investments
MORTGAGES
PROTECTION

Note: There is a separate proc that calculates the GI VNB points from the Paymentshield data.

The approach of this proc is to use the incremental PendingPaymentIDs from the overnight batch
to calculate the VNB points in a temporary table.

The temporary table is then merged with the permanent table to make the calculated (or
re-calculated values) permanent.

Terms
-----
BSC			- Business Service Charge.
MBF			- Mortgage Broker Fee.
OGS			- Ongoing Servicing.
BSC Rate	- 0.12% at the time of writing (24/04/2018). This could be changed by the business, but
				would also require some DEV work in OWS.
DF			- Discount Factor.
DA			- Distribution Allowance (the total amount paid out by the provider to Openwork)
AUM			- Assets Under Management. Basically the amount invested or the premium on investment
				cases.
Average AUM - Average amount invested annually which is equivalent to 6 months' premium.

THE CALCULATIONS
================

There are two potential parts: initial + ongoing (if ongoing applies). If BSC (applies to ongoing 
only) and MBF (applies to mortgages only) apply, then these are also included:

MORTGAGE
--------
Part 1: MBF column = (Advice Fee Amount X Broker Retention Rate) - (Advice Fee Amount X Mort FCA Rate)
Part 2: Initial column = (Proc Fee Amount X Mortgage Retention Rate) - (Proc Fee X Mort FCA Rate) 
Mortgage Points Total = Initial + MBF

PROTECTION
----------
= (DA X Protection Retention Rate) - (DA X Protection FCA Rate) 
Protection Points Total = Initial

WEALTH (COB i.e. pensions and investments)
------
Part 1: Initial column = (DA X Wealth Retention Rate) - (DA X Wealth FCA Rate)

Part 2:

****XXXX****

NOTE: Where the BSC rate is greater than the ongoing rate, then BSC gets ALL of the AVAILABLE 
ongoing.

****XXXX****

REGULAR - BSC applies:
Year 1 column = BSC Points + Non-BSC Points - FCA Points
Non-BSC Points = Ave AUM X (OGS Rate - BSC Rate) X COB Retention Rate
BSC Points = Ave AUM X BSC Rate
FCA Points = Ave AUM X OGS Rate X COB FCA Rate

REGULAR - Non-BSC: 
Year 1 column = (Ave AUM X OGS Rate X COB Retention Rate) - (Ave AUM X OGS Rate X COB FCA Rate)

SINGLE - BSC applies:
Year 1 column = (AUM X BSC Rate) + (AUM X (OGS Rate - BSC Rate) X COB Retention Rate) - (AUM X OGS Rate X COB FCA Rate) 

SINGLE - Non-BSC:
Year 1 column = (AUM X OGS Rate X COB Retention Rate) - (AUM X OGS Rate X COB FCA Rate) 

Then years 2 to 10 are calculated by applying a discount factor
Year  2 = Year 1 X  3 X DF
Year  3 = Year 1 X  5 X DF
Year  4 = Year 1 X  7 X DF
Year  5 = Year 1 X  9 X DF
Year  6 = Year 1 X 11 X DF
Year  7 = Year 1 X 13 X DF
Year  8 = Year 1 X 15 X DF
Year  9 = Year 1 X 17 X DF
Year 10 = Year 1 X 19 X DF

Wealth Points Total =	OngoingYr01 + OngoingYr02 + OngoingYr03 + OngoingYr04 + OngoingYr05 +
						OngoingYr06 + OngoingYr07 + OngoingYr08 + OngoingYr09 + OngoingYr10 +
						Initial

GI
--
See stored proc "owp_RecognitionGIPaymentshield".
 
Notes:
-----

1)	There is a BSC column on table owt_Recognition. However, BSC is already included in the ongoing
	years 1 - 10, so the BSC column does not need to be added in. In fact you will double count if 
	you attempt to do anything with it other than display it.

2)	Occasionally an investment case may receive two or more cheques which
	then go through Swift as two or more SINGLE investments on the SAME
	slice. Although the INITIAL VNB calculation will pro-rata correctly
	because it is based on the amount received, this scenario will cause
	ongoing VNB to be calculated on each of the payment records and so will 
	double count (or worse if there are more than two cheques received).
	Since de-coupling IC from ongoing i.e. they now have separate rows on
	table owt_Recognition, the issue of multiple cheques should no longer
	cause ongoing double counting.


This proc is called as follows:
	declare @rc int
	exec @rc = dbo.owp_RecognitionSwift 'Openwork', 'Recognition'
	select @rc

					
AMENDMENT HISTORY				
=================								

Date		Author		Description
----		------		-----------
26/04/2018	A Groves	Only include rows in the OGS lookups where the OngoingServiceFee > 0.0.
						Negative OGS rates are bad data and at the time of writing, there are
						39 of these.
27/04/2018	A Groves	Additional calculation and condition to handle the scenario where BSC applies
						but the OGS Rate is less than the BSC rate. Previously, this caused the
						total ongoing to be zero. However, there are two components to ongoing VNB 
						points, the BSC share and the non-BSC share. So the BSC share (which takes 
						100% when the OGS rate is less than 0.12%) should still yield ongoing points.
27/04/2018	A Groves	Single ongoing Yr01 corrected by applying outer brackets before signing the result.
03/05/2018	A Groves	Added update of column "msit_OpenworkAdviserListing.VNB_Points".
18/05/2018	A Groves	Changed mortgage calculation to use e.AMOUNT_REC instead of pt.CommInitialAmount
						as Marcus Cossey wanted the actual amount received to be used for the DA.
04/06/2018	A Groves	1) In the REGULAR section of column "OngoingYr01", the condition for cs.FrequencyCode <> 6
							was added to ensure the code differentiates to the SINGLE section.
						2) Exclude MBF from the OpenAccess table (msit_OpenworkAdviserListing) as this
							is shown on the MBF download and would otherwise incur MBF double counting.
05/06/2018	A Groves	1) Marcus Cossey advised that investments should get ongoing for years 1 to 6 and
							pensions for years 1 to 10. Previously, both lines of business got years 1 to 10.
						2) Marcus Cossey asked for split payments (i.e. where multiple cheques are processed
							for a SINGLE investment) to only claculate ongoing VNB on the oldest payment. 
11/06/2018	A Groves	1) PSD processed a protection clawback statement as fee type initial. These clawbacks
							all generated +ve instead of -ve VNB points. A tweak was added to ensure that the 
							absolute value of AMOUNT_REC is used to ensure the VNB is correctly signed. 
						2) Another unknown business rule has surfaced: Previously, only initial, clawbacks and
							adjustments on slices created new from 2017 were included. This rule only applies
							to initial. Clawbacks and adjustments can belong to a slice created at any point
							in the past. However, note that the payment (irrespective of whether it is +ve or 
							-ve), must not pre-date 2017.
13/06/2018	A Groves	Marcus asked for SellerCode and PaymentMatchedDate to be added so he need only use 
							the one table for both the adviser and enterprise leagues. PayBasisCode and 
							PayBasisDesc were also added at the same time as these are used in the calculations.
*************************************************************************************************************/

CREATE PROCEDURE [dbo].[owp_RecognitionSwiftONGOING_Backup20180628AG]
	@Client		varchar(50),
	@Module		Varchar(50)

AS

set nocount on

declare		@PhaseStart				varchar(50),
			@PhaseEnd				varchar(50),
			@PhaseError				varchar(50),
			@PhaseLog				varchar(50),
			@ProcName				varchar(100),
			@ProcessMessage			varchar(100),
			@RowCount				int,
			@OALRowCount			int,
			@ErrMsg					nvarchar(4000),
			@ErrMsgBrief			nvarchar(100),
			@ErrNum					int,
			@ErrSev					int,
			@ErrLine				int,
			@ErrState				int,
			@DateLastUpdated		datetime,
			@OwlManager2Code		nvarchar(10)
			
/****************************************************************************

	Set initial parameters																
																		
****************************************************************************/

set @ProcName			= object_name(@@procid)
set @PhaseStart			= 'START'
set @PhaseEnd			= 'END'
set @PhaseError			= 'ERROR'
set @PhaseLog			= 'LOG'
set @ErrNum				= 0	
set @DateLastUpdated	= getdate()

set @OwlManager2Code = (select cde.Code from msit_MIWarehouseCodesAndDescriptions cde
			where cde.ColumnName = 'Manager2Code' and cde.Description = 'Owl Financial')

-- We want this logging irrespective of whether or not there is a rollback
exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseStart, @ProcName, null, @Module, @Client

/****************************************************************************

	Populate the table																
																		
****************************************************************************/

SET XACT_ABORT ON	-- Needed if XACT_STATE() function is used.

BEGIN TRY

	/****************************************************************************

		Link OWS data to Swift data to enable the ongoing servicng (OGS) rate
		to be looked up.
																		
	****************************************************************************/
	
	select	distinct s.PersonID, swp.Client_Num, p.InternalProductID, swp.ProductCode 
	into	#SwiftOWSClientLink
	from	sa_ows_Sale s
			inner join sa_ows_Policies p on p.SaleID = s.SaleID
			inner join mstt_Policies swp on swp.PolicyRef = p.PolicyID
	where	s.DateSubmitted is not null
	--and		s.PersonID = 146030

	select @RowCount = @@rowcount
	set @ProcessMessage = '#SwiftOWSClientLink = ' + convert(nvarchar(10), @RowCount)
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseLog, @ProcessMessage, null, @Module, @Client

	-- The OGS rate is stored for the client/product combination
	select	link.Client_Num, link.ProductCode, max(ogs.OngoingServiceFee) as OngoingServiceFee
	into	#OGSLookUp
	from	#SwiftOWSClientLink link 
			inner join mstt_ProductHierarchy ph on ph.ProductCode = link.ProductCode
			inner join Submission.sa_ows_SubmittedProductCurrentOngoingServiceFee ogs
							on ogs.PersonID = link.PersonID
							and ogs.InternalProductID = (case when ph.RDRType = 'ONPLAT' 
															then -2 
															else link.InternalProductID 
														 end)
	where	ogs.OngoingServiceFee > 0.0							--AG 26/04/2018
	group	by 	link.Client_Num, link.ProductCode

	select @RowCount = @@rowcount
	set @ProcessMessage = '#OGSLookUp = ' + convert(nvarchar(10), @RowCount)
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseLog, @ProcessMessage, null, @Module, @Client

	create index idx_OGSLookUp on #OGSLookUp (Client_num, ProductCode)

	--This is an additional catch for OGS by storing the client's highest OGS
	--rate against their client number. This lookup will apply if the first
	--look up fails. The first lookup can fail, for example, if the case was 
	--not submitted on OWS i.e. the CaseID has a "17" prefix. 
	select	Client_Num, MAX(OngoingServiceFee) as OngoingServiceFee
	into	#OGSLookUpClient
	from	#OGSLookUp
	group	by Client_Num

	select @RowCount = @@rowcount
	set @ProcessMessage = '#OGSLookUpClient = ' + convert(nvarchar(10), @RowCount)
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseLog, @ProcessMessage, null, @Module, @Client
	
	create index idx_OGSLookUpClient on #OGSLookUpClient (Client_num)

	/****************************************************************************

		Calculate VNB and populate the temporary table with the results
		
		Note that there are oddities like LV protection payments which always
		come in pairs with one large and one much smaller amount (e.g. TransactionID 
		= 6684787.) The system treats both payments in the pair as first payments 
		and the (projected) DA associated with both is the same (because it's on 
		the policy transaction). 
		
		There is also a requirement to front-load VNB points on accrual and level
		payments. This means calculate the VNB for the full amount of the DA and 
		put it on the first payment record and then on all subsequent accrual and 
		level payments, set the VNB to zero.
		
		Thus two different sources of DA are used depending on whether we need the
		full DA amount for accruals and level or the actual amount received for all
		other scenarios including the LV split payment scenario. The two sources are:
		
		mstt_PolicyTransactions.CommInitialAmount - Full (projected) DA amount
		
		mstt_Expectation.AMOUNT_REC - The DA actually received. This handles the
										LV scenario whereby the AMOUNT_REC is 
										proportioned across the two payments received.   
																		
	****************************************************************************/

	select	top 0 
			*, 
			convert(int,NULL) as CommissionYear
	into	#AG_owt_Recognition_SEPARATE_ONGOING
	from	AG_owt_Recognition_SEPARATE_ONGOING

	/****************************************************************************

		Phase 1 - Process all but regular accrual cases with clawbacks/adjustments
		Accruals are front loaded unless their latest payment is a clawback/adjudtment
		in which case they accrue VNB points on a per payment basis and so these
		are dealt with in Phases 2 and 3.
																		
	****************************************************************************/

	insert into #AG_owt_Recognition_SEPARATE_ONGOING
	(
		SourceID,
		CaseID,
		TransactionID,
		Policy,
		ProductCode,
		BusinessCode,
		SellerCode,						--AG 13/06/2018
		PointsTotal,
		BSC,
		MBF,
		Initial,
		OngoingTotal,
		OngoingYr01,
		OngoingYr02,
		OngoingYr03,
		OngoingYr04,
		OngoingYr05,
		OngoingYr06,
		OngoingYr07,
		OngoingYr08,
		OngoingYr09,
		OngoingYr10,
		FCARate,
		RetentionRate,
		RetentionRateBroker,
		OngoingServicingRate,
		OngoingServicingSource,
		DA,
		AmountReceived,
		Premium,
		AgentSplit,
		CommissionType,
		CommissionTypeDesc,
		PayBasisCode,					--AG 13/06/2018
		PayBasisDesc,					--AG 13/06/2018
		PaymentMatchedDate,				--AG 13/06/2018
		Month,
		FrequencyCode,
		FrequencyDesc,
		ReassignedProductGroupCode,		--AG 05/06/2018
		ReassignedProductGroupName,		--AG 05/06/2018
		RecognitionType,
		CalculationType,
		Source,
		DateInserted,
		DateLastUpdated,
		CommissionYear
	)
	select	cs.PendingPaymentID as SourceID,
			cs.CaseID,
			cs.TransactionID,
			cs.ExtPolicyNumber as Policy,
			cs.ProductCode,
			cs.BusinessCode,
			cs.AgentCode as SellerCode,				--AG 13/06/2018
			0.0 as PointsTotal,
			0.0 as BSC,
			case 
				when mbf.MortgageFeeID is not null and cs.INIssued <> 0 then (((mbf.AdviceFeeAmount)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * MRbkr.FACTOR) - ((mbf.AdviceFeeAmount)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * Mfca.FACTOR)) --Note that mbf.AdviceFeeAmount is signed correctly - so no coding for signing is needed here
				else 0.0
			end as MBF,
			case 
				--When the adviser has changed, the AgentSplit can become zero in which case the ELITE points should be zero.
				when cs.AgentSplit = 0 then 0
				
				--WEALTH CALCULATION START
				--Indemnity payments or SINGLEs or IC Clawbacks or IC adjustments Start
				when (ph.ProductCategoryCode = 1 or pcc.KeyValue2 = '1') and (cs.FrequencyCode = 6 or cs.PayBasisCode in ('T') or cs.CommissionType in (2,17)) and cs.commissiontype in (1,2,17) and cs.INIssued <> 0 then (((e.AMOUNT_REC)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * Crate.FACTOR) - ((e.AMOUNT_REC)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * Cfca.FACTOR)) * case when cs.INIssued < 0 then -1 else 1 end
				--Indemnity payments or SINGLEs or IC Clawbacks or IC adjustments End
				--Accruals & Level Start
				when (ph.ProductCategoryCode = 1 or pcc.KeyValue2 = '1') and cs.INIssued <> 0 then (((pt.CommInitialAmount)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * Crate.FACTOR) - ((pt.CommInitialAmount)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * Cfca.FACTOR)) * case when cs.INIssued < 0 then -1 else 1 end
				--Accruals & Level End
				--WEALTH CALCULATION END
				
				--MORTGAGE CALCULATION START
				--Note: The MBF component has its own table column
				--Only 1 payment for mortgages
				when ph.ProductGroupCode = 3 and cs.INIssued <> 0 then (((e.AMOUNT_REC)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * MRproc.FACTOR) - ((e.AMOUNT_REC)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * Mfca.FACTOR)) * case when cs.INIssued < 0 then -1 else 1 end	--AG 18/05/2018
				--MORTGAGE CALCULATION END
				
				--PROTECTION CALCULATION START
				--Indemnity payments or SINGLEs or IC Clawbacks or IC adjustments Start
				when ph.ProductGroupCode = 6 and (cs.FrequencyCode = 6 or cs.PayBasisCode in ('T') or cs.CommissionType in (2,17)) and cs.commissiontype in (1,2,17) and cs.INIssued <> 0 then ((abs(e.AMOUNT_REC)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * Prate.FACTOR) - (abs(e.AMOUNT_REC)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * Pfca.FACTOR)) * case when cs.INIssued < 0 then -1 else 1 end	--AG 11/06/2018 (1)
				--Indemnity payments or SINGLEs or IC Clawbacks or IC adjustments End
				--Accruals & Level Start
				when ph.ProductGroupCode = 6 and cs.INIssued <> 0 then (((pt.CommInitialAmount)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * Prate.FACTOR) - ((pt.CommInitialAmount)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * Pfca.FACTOR)) * case when cs.INIssued < 0 then -1 else 1 end
				--Accruals & Level End
				--PROTECTION CALCULATION END

				else 0.0

			end as Initial,
			0.0 as OngoingTotal,
			0.0 as OngoingYr01,
			0.0 as OngoingYr02,
			0.0 as OngoingYr03,
			0.0 as OngoingYr04,
			0.0 as OngoingYr05,
			0.0 as OngoingYr06,
			0.0 as OngoingYr07,
			0.0 as OngoingYr08,
			0.0 as OngoingYr09,
			0.0 as OngoingYr10,
			case 
				when (ph.ProductCategoryCode = 1 or pcc.KeyValue2 = '1') then Cfca.FACTOR*100.0		--COB
				when ph.ProductGroupCode = 3 then Mfca.FACTOR*100.0		--MORT
				when ph.ProductGroupCode = 6 then Pfca.FACTOR*100.0		--PROT
				else 0.0
			end as FCARate,
			case 
				when (ph.ProductCategoryCode = 1 or pcc.KeyValue2 = '1') then Crate.FACTOR*100.0	--COB
				when ph.ProductGroupCode = 3 then MRproc.FACTOR*100.0	--MORT
				when ph.ProductGroupCode = 6 then Prate.FACTOR*100.0	--PROT
				else 0.0
			end as RetentionRate,
			case 
				when mbf.MortgageFeeID is not null then  MRbkr.FACTOR*100.0	
				else 0.0
			end as RetentionRateBroker,
			null as OngoingServicingRate,
			null as OngoingServicingSource,
			pt.CommInitialAmount as DA,
			e.AMOUNT_REC as AmountReceived,
			cs.Premium,
			cs.AgentSplit,
			cs.CommissionType,
			left(cs.StandingOrderDesc,50) as CommissionTypeDesc,
			cs.PayBasisCode,							--AG 13/06/2018
			cs.PayBasisDesc,							--AG 13/06/2018
			cs.CreateDate as PaymentMatchedDate,		--AG 13/06/2018
			cs.Month,
			cs.FrequencyCode,
			cs.FrequencyDesc,
			pg.ProductGroupCode as ReassignedProductGroupCode,	--Force the re-assigned products...		AG 05/06/2018
			pg.ProductGroupName as ReassignedProductGroupName,	--...to be processed as investments		AG 05/06/2018
			'VNB-PHASE-1' as RecognitionType,
			case 
				when (ph.ProductCategoryCode = 1 or pcc.KeyValue2 = '1') then 'WEALTH-INITIAL'
				when ph.ProductGroupCode = 3 then 'MORTGAGE'
				when ph.ProductGroupCode = 6 then 'PROTECTION'
				else null
			end as CalculationType,
			'Openwork 2006' as Source,
			@DateLastUpdated as DateInserted,
			@DateLastUpdated as DateLastUpdated,
			csp.year as CommissionYear
	--select count(*)
	from	msit_CommissionStatement cs
/*			inner join (select	distinct PKID
						from	owt_TransformationMovements tm 
						where	tm.DriverTableName = 'sa_swift_S_AGMFIL'
						and		tm.CommissionStatement = 'Y') tm on tm.PKID = cs.PendingPaymentID
*/			inner join mstt_Agents ag on ag.Code = cs.BusinessCode
			inner join mstt_PolicyTransactions pt on pt.ID = cs.TransactionID
			inner join mstt_Policies p on p.POL_NUM = pt.PolicyID
			inner join msit_CommissionStatementPeriods VNBStart on convert(date,pt.CreateDateTime) between VNBStart.PeriodStartDate and VNBStart.PeriodEndDate
			inner join msit_Commissionstatementperiods csp on csp.month = cs.month
			inner join mstt_ProductHierarchy ph on ph.productcode = cs.productcode
			inner join mstt_Expectation e on e.ID = cs.ExpectationID
			left join dbo.owt_MortgageBrokerFees mbf on mbf.PendingPaymentID = cs.PendingPaymentID and mbf.AdviceFeeCharged = 'Yes'
			left join owt_SelectionControl SC
						on SC.Process = 'ElitePoints' 
						and SC.KeyType = 'NSCPotCode' 
						and cs.CreateDate between SC.EffectiveStartDate and SC.EffectiveEndDate
			left join mstt_Commissions BSCpot
						on BSCpot.TransactionID = cs.TransactionID 
						and BSCpot.Agent_Code = sc.KeyValue
						and BSCpot.CommissionType = 10
			left join owt_SelectionControl SFMPC						
						on SFMPC.Process = 'ElitePoints' 
						and SFMPC.KeyType = 'ServicingFeeMarginPotCode' 
						and cs.CreateDate between SFMPC.EffectiveStartDate and SFMPC.EffectiveEndDate
			left join mstt_Commissions SFMpot							
						on SFMpot.TransactionID = cs.TransactionID 
						and SFMpot.Agent_Code = SFMPC.KeyValue
						and SFMpot.CommissionType = 10	
			left join owt_SelectionControl pcc 
						on pcc.Process = 'ElitePoints'
						and pcc.KeyType = 'ProductCategoryCode'
						and pcc.KeyValue = cs.ProductCode	
						and cs.CreateDate between pcc.EffectiveStartDate and pcc.EffectiveEndDate
			left join owt_SelectionControl ogsdflt 
						on ogsdflt.Process = 'ElitePoints'
						and ogsdflt.KeyType = 'DefaultOngoingServicingRate'
						and ogsdflt.SelectionType = 'VNB'
						and ogsdflt.KeyValue = case when ph.RDRType = 'ONPLAT' then 'ONPLAT' else 'OFPLAT' end
						and cs.CreateDate between ogsdflt.EffectiveStartDate and ogsdflt.EffectiveEndDate
			left join mstt_CodeProductGroup pg on pg.ProductGroupCode = case when pcc.KeyValue2 = '1' then 2 else ph.ProductGroupCode end
			left join owt_EliteFactors Cfca on Cfca.FeeType = 'VNB' and Cfca.category = 'COB-FCA-RATE' and csp.year between Cfca.StartYear and Cfca.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors Crate on Crate.FeeType = 'VNB' and Crate.category = 'COB-RETENTION-RATE' and csp.year between Crate.StartYear and Crate.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors Mfca on Mfca.FeeType = 'VNB' and Mfca.category = 'MORT-FCA-RATE' and csp.year between Mfca.StartYear and Mfca.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors MRproc on MRproc.FeeType = 'VNB' and MRproc.category = 'MORT-RETENTION-RATE-PROC' and csp.year between MRproc.StartYear and MRproc.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors MRbkr on MRbkr.FeeType = 'VNB' and MRbkr.category = 'MORT-RETENTION-RATE-BROKER' and csp.year between MRbkr.StartYear and MRbkr.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors Pfca on Pfca.FeeType = 'VNB' and Pfca.category = 'PROT-FCA-RATE' and csp.year between Pfca.StartYear and Pfca.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors Prate on Prate.FeeType = 'VNB' and Prate.category = 'PROT-RETENTION-RATE' and csp.year between Prate.StartYear and Prate.EndYear 
			left join msit_CommissionStatement csadj 
						on csadj.TransactionID = cs.TransactionID 
						and csadj.AgentCode = cs.AgentCode 
						and csadj.CommissionType in (2,17)
						and	csadj.PayBasisCode in ('F')				--Accrual
						and	csadj.FrequencyCode <> 6				--Regular 
	where	cs.ReportingClassCode = 1
	and		ag.Manager2Code <> @OwlManager2Code		--Exclude Owl
	and		cs.INIssued <> 0
	and		csp.Year >= 2017						--Ensure in-scope payments are consistent with VNB start
	and		((VNBStart.Year >= 2017 and cs.CommissionType = 1 and e.AMOUNT_REC >= 0.01)		--VNB to start from new slices in 2017 for +ve payments but...			AG 11/06/2018 (2)
			or (cs.CommissionType in (2,17) or e.AMOUNT_REC <= -0.01))						--...for -ve payments, the slice can start from any date in the past	AG 11/06/2018 (2)
	and		csadj.ID is null						--Deal with accrual regular clawbacks/adjustments later

	select @RowCount = @@rowcount
	set @ProcessMessage = '#owt_Recognition = ' + convert(nvarchar(10), @RowCount)
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseLog, @ProcessMessage, null, @Module, @Client

	/****************************************************************************

		Now deal with accrual clawbacks and adjustments
																		
	****************************************************************************/

	--drop table #msit_CommissionStatementSUMMARY

	--Find transactions with clawbacks/adj on them
	select	cs.TransactionID,
			cs.AgentCode,
			Min(case when cs.CommissionType = 1 then cs.PendingPaymentID else null end) as MinInitialPendingPaymentID,
			MAX(case when cs.CommissionType = 1 then cs.PendingPaymentID else null end) as MaxInitialPendingPaymentID,
			MAX(case when cs.CommissionType in (2,17) then cs.PendingPaymentID else null end) as MaxAdjPendingPaymentID,
			null as MinInitialAfterAdjPendingPaymentID
	into	#msit_CommissionStatementSUMMARY
	from	msit_CommissionStatement cs
			inner join mstt_Agents ag on ag.Code = cs.BusinessCode
			inner join mstt_PolicyTransactions pt on pt.ID = cs.TransactionID
			inner join mstt_Policies p on p.POL_NUM = pt.PolicyID
			inner join msit_CommissionStatementPeriods VNBStart on convert(date,pt.CreateDateTime) between VNBStart.PeriodStartDate and VNBStart.PeriodEndDate
			inner join msit_Commissionstatementperiods csp on csp.month = cs.month
			inner join mstt_Expectation e on e.ID = cs.ExpectationID
			left join msit_CommissionStatement csadj 
						on csadj.TransactionID = cs.TransactionID 
						and csadj.AgentCode = cs.AgentCode 
						and csadj.CommissionType in (2,17)
						and	csadj.PayBasisCode in ('F')				--Accrual
						and	csadj.FrequencyCode <> 6				--Regular 
	where	cs.ReportingClassCode = 1
	and		ag.Manager2Code <> @OwlManager2Code		--Exclude Owl
	and		csp.Year >= 2017						--Ensure in-scope payments are consistent with VNB start
	and		VNBStart.Year >= 2017 
	and		abs(e.AMOUNT_REC) >= 0.01	
	and		csadj.ID is not null					--select regular accrual transactions with clawbacks/adjustments
	--and cs.TransactionID in (5613333,6296827)
	group by	cs.TransactionID,
				cs.AgentCode

	--Get first initial payment after last clawback/adj
	update css
		set MinInitialAfterAdjPendingPaymentID = summ.MinPendingPaymentID 
	from  #msit_CommissionStatementSUMMARY css
			inner join  (
						select cssinner.TransactionID, cssinner.AgentCode, min(cs.PendingPaymentID) as MinPendingPaymentID
						from #msit_CommissionStatementSUMMARY cssinner
								inner join msit_CommissionStatement cs
											on cs.TransactionID = cssinner.TransactionID
											and cs.AgentCode = cssinner.AgentCode
						where cs.PendingPaymentID > cssinner.MaxAdjPendingPaymentID
						group by cssinner.TransactionID, cssinner.AgentCode
						) summ on  summ.TransactionID = css.TransactionID
							   and summ.AgentCode = css.AgentCode

	/****************************************************************************

		Phase 2 - This phase deals with regular accrual cases where the latest payment
		is a clawback/adjustment. In this scenario the VNB is changed from front loaded 
		to a per payment basis.
																		
	****************************************************************************/

	insert into #AG_owt_Recognition_SEPARATE_ONGOING
	(
		SourceID,
		CaseID,
		TransactionID,
		Policy,
		ProductCode,
		BusinessCode,
		SellerCode,						
		PointsTotal,
		BSC,
		MBF,
		Initial,
		OngoingTotal,
		OngoingYr01,
		OngoingYr02,
		OngoingYr03,
		OngoingYr04,
		OngoingYr05,
		OngoingYr06,
		OngoingYr07,
		OngoingYr08,
		OngoingYr09,
		OngoingYr10,
		FCARate,
		RetentionRate,
		RetentionRateBroker,
		OngoingServicingRate,
		OngoingServicingSource,
		DA,
		AmountReceived,
		Premium,
		AgentSplit,
		CommissionType,
		CommissionTypeDesc,
		PayBasisCode,					
		PayBasisDesc,					
		PaymentMatchedDate,				
		Month,
		FrequencyCode,
		FrequencyDesc,
		ReassignedProductGroupCode,		
		ReassignedProductGroupName,		
		RecognitionType,
		CalculationType,
		Source,
		DateInserted,
		DateLastUpdated,
		CommissionYear
	)
	select	cs.PendingPaymentID as SourceID,
			cs.CaseID,
			cs.TransactionID,
			cs.ExtPolicyNumber as Policy,
			cs.ProductCode,
			cs.BusinessCode,
			cs.AgentCode as SellerCode,				
			0.0 as PointsTotal,
			0.0 as BSC,
			case 
				when mbf.MortgageFeeID is not null and cs.INIssued <> 0 then (((mbf.AdviceFeeAmount)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * MRbkr.FACTOR) - ((mbf.AdviceFeeAmount)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * Mfca.FACTOR)) --Note that mbf.AdviceFeeAmount is signed correctly - so no coding for signing is needed here
				else 0.0
			end as MBF,
			case 
				--When the adviser has changed, the AgentSplit can become zero in which case the ELITE points should be zero.
				when cs.AgentSplit = 0 then 0
				
				--WEALTH CALCULATION START
				--Indemnity payments or SINGLEs or IC Clawbacks or IC adjustments Start
				--THIS SCENARIO DOESN'T OCCUR IN PHASE 2
				--Indemnity payments or SINGLEs or IC Clawbacks or IC adjustments End
				--Accruals & Level Start
				when (ph.ProductCategoryCode = 1 or pcc.KeyValue2 = '1') then (((e.AMOUNT_REC)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * Crate.FACTOR) - ((e.AMOUNT_REC)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * Cfca.FACTOR)) * case when cs.CommissionType in (2,17) then -1 else 1 end
				--Accruals & Level End
				--WEALTH CALCULATION END
				
				--MORTGAGE CALCULATION START
				--Note: The MBF component has its own table column
				--Only 1 payment for mortgages
				when ph.ProductGroupCode = 3 then (((e.AMOUNT_REC)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * MRproc.FACTOR) - ((e.AMOUNT_REC)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * Mfca.FACTOR)) * case when cs.CommissionType in (2,17) then -1 else 1 end	
				--MORTGAGE CALCULATION END
				
				--PROTECTION CALCULATION START
				--Indemnity payments or SINGLEs or IC Clawbacks or IC adjustments Start
				--THIS SCENARIO DOESN'T OCCUR IN PHASE 2
				--Indemnity payments or SINGLEs or IC Clawbacks or IC adjustments End
				--Accruals & Level Start
				when ph.ProductGroupCode = 6 then (((e.AMOUNT_REC)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * Prate.FACTOR) - ((e.AMOUNT_REC)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * Pfca.FACTOR)) * case when cs.CommissionType in (2,17) then -1 else 1 end
				--Accruals & Level End
				--PROTECTION CALCULATION END

				else 0.0

			end as Initial,
			0.0 as OngoingTotal,
			0.0 as OngoingYr01,
			0.0 as OngoingYr02,
			0.0 as OngoingYr03,
			0.0 as OngoingYr04,
			0.0 as OngoingYr05,
			0.0 as OngoingYr06,
			0.0 as OngoingYr07,
			0.0 as OngoingYr08,
			0.0 as OngoingYr09,
			0.0 as OngoingYr10,
			case 
				when (ph.ProductCategoryCode = 1 or pcc.KeyValue2 = '1') then Cfca.FACTOR*100.0		--COB
				when ph.ProductGroupCode = 3 then Mfca.FACTOR*100.0		--MORT
				when ph.ProductGroupCode = 6 then Pfca.FACTOR*100.0		--PROT
				else 0.0
			end as FCARate,
			case 
				when (ph.ProductCategoryCode = 1 or pcc.KeyValue2 = '1') then Crate.FACTOR*100.0	--COB
				when ph.ProductGroupCode = 3 then MRproc.FACTOR*100.0	--MORT
				when ph.ProductGroupCode = 6 then Prate.FACTOR*100.0	--PROT
				else 0.0
			end as RetentionRate,
			case 
				when mbf.MortgageFeeID is not null then  MRbkr.FACTOR*100.0	
				else 0.0
			end as RetentionRateBroker,
			null as OngoingServicingRate,
			null as OngoingServicingSource,
			pt.CommInitialAmount as DA,
			e.AMOUNT_REC as AmountReceived,
			cs.Premium,
			cs.AgentSplit,
			cs.CommissionType,
			left(cs.StandingOrderDesc,50) as CommissionTypeDesc,
			cs.PayBasisCode,							
			cs.PayBasisDesc,							
			cs.CreateDate as PaymentMatchedDate,		
			cs.Month,
			cs.FrequencyCode,
			cs.FrequencyDesc,
			pg.ProductGroupCode as ReassignedProductGroupCode,	--Force the re-assigned products...		
			pg.ProductGroupName as ReassignedProductGroupName,	--...to be processed as investments		
			'VNB-PHASE-2' as RecognitionType,
			case 
				when (ph.ProductCategoryCode = 1 or pcc.KeyValue2 = '1') then 'WEALTH-INITIAL'
				when ph.ProductGroupCode = 3 then 'MORTGAGE'
				when ph.ProductGroupCode = 6 then 'PROTECTION'
				else null
			end as CalculationType,
			'Openwork 2006' as Source,
			@DateLastUpdated as DateInserted,
			@DateLastUpdated as DateLastUpdated,
			csp.year as CommissionYear
	from	#msit_CommissionStatementSUMMARY css
			inner join msit_CommissionStatement cs
						on cs.TransactionID = css.TransactionID
						and cs.AgentCode = css.AgentCode
			inner join mstt_Agents ag on ag.Code = cs.BusinessCode
			inner join mstt_PolicyTransactions pt on pt.ID = cs.TransactionID
			inner join mstt_Policies p on p.POL_NUM = pt.PolicyID
			inner join msit_CommissionStatementPeriods VNBStart on convert(date,pt.CreateDateTime) between VNBStart.PeriodStartDate and VNBStart.PeriodEndDate
			inner join msit_Commissionstatementperiods csp on csp.month = cs.month
			inner join mstt_ProductHierarchy ph on ph.productcode = cs.productcode
			inner join mstt_Expectation e on e.ID = cs.ExpectationID
			left join dbo.owt_MortgageBrokerFees mbf on mbf.PendingPaymentID = cs.PendingPaymentID and mbf.AdviceFeeCharged = 'Yes'
			left join owt_SelectionControl SC
						on SC.Process = 'ElitePoints' 
						and SC.KeyType = 'NSCPotCode' 
						and cs.CreateDate between SC.EffectiveStartDate and SC.EffectiveEndDate
			left join mstt_Commissions BSCpot
						on BSCpot.TransactionID = cs.TransactionID 
						and BSCpot.Agent_Code = sc.KeyValue
						and BSCpot.CommissionType = 10
			left join owt_SelectionControl SFMPC						
						on SFMPC.Process = 'ElitePoints' 
						and SFMPC.KeyType = 'ServicingFeeMarginPotCode' 
						and cs.CreateDate between SFMPC.EffectiveStartDate and SFMPC.EffectiveEndDate
			left join mstt_Commissions SFMpot							
						on SFMpot.TransactionID = cs.TransactionID 
						and SFMpot.Agent_Code = SFMPC.KeyValue
						and SFMpot.CommissionType = 10	
			left join owt_SelectionControl pcc 
						on pcc.Process = 'ElitePoints'
						and pcc.KeyType = 'ProductCategoryCode'
						and pcc.KeyValue = cs.ProductCode	
						and cs.CreateDate between pcc.EffectiveStartDate and pcc.EffectiveEndDate
			left join owt_SelectionControl ogsdflt 
						on ogsdflt.Process = 'ElitePoints'
						and ogsdflt.KeyType = 'DefaultOngoingServicingRate'
						and ogsdflt.SelectionType = 'VNB'
						and ogsdflt.KeyValue = case when ph.RDRType = 'ONPLAT' then 'ONPLAT' else 'OFPLAT' end
						and cs.CreateDate between ogsdflt.EffectiveStartDate and ogsdflt.EffectiveEndDate
			left join mstt_CodeProductGroup pg on pg.ProductGroupCode = case when pcc.KeyValue2 = '1' then 2 else ph.ProductGroupCode end
			left join owt_EliteFactors Cfca on Cfca.FeeType = 'VNB' and Cfca.category = 'COB-FCA-RATE' and csp.year between Cfca.StartYear and Cfca.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors Crate on Crate.FeeType = 'VNB' and Crate.category = 'COB-RETENTION-RATE' and csp.year between Crate.StartYear and Crate.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors Mfca on Mfca.FeeType = 'VNB' and Mfca.category = 'MORT-FCA-RATE' and csp.year between Mfca.StartYear and Mfca.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors MRproc on MRproc.FeeType = 'VNB' and MRproc.category = 'MORT-RETENTION-RATE-PROC' and csp.year between MRproc.StartYear and MRproc.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors MRbkr on MRbkr.FeeType = 'VNB' and MRbkr.category = 'MORT-RETENTION-RATE-BROKER' and csp.year between MRbkr.StartYear and MRbkr.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors Pfca on Pfca.FeeType = 'VNB' and Pfca.category = 'PROT-FCA-RATE' and csp.year between Pfca.StartYear and Pfca.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors Prate on Prate.FeeType = 'VNB' and Prate.category = 'PROT-RETENTION-RATE' and csp.year between Prate.StartYear and Prate.EndYear 
	where	cs.ReportingClassCode = 1
	and		ag.Manager2Code <> @OwlManager2Code		--Exclude Owl
	and		isnull(css.MaxInitialPendingPaymentID,0) < isnull(css.MaxAdjPendingPaymentID,0)	-- Clawback/adj is the latest payment
	--and		cs.TransactionID = 5613333
	--order by cs.PendingPaymentID

	/****************************************************************************

		Phase 3a - initial payments restart after clawback/adj
		1) Set original (front loaded) points on first payment as per Phase 1
		2) Set (front loaded) points DIFFERENCE on first payment following clawback/adj
																
	****************************************************************************/

	insert into #AG_owt_Recognition_SEPARATE_ONGOING
	(
		SourceID,
		CaseID,
		TransactionID,
		Policy,
		ProductCode,
		BusinessCode,
		SellerCode,						
		PointsTotal,
		BSC,
		MBF,
		Initial,
		OngoingTotal,
		OngoingYr01,
		OngoingYr02,
		OngoingYr03,
		OngoingYr04,
		OngoingYr05,
		OngoingYr06,
		OngoingYr07,
		OngoingYr08,
		OngoingYr09,
		OngoingYr10,
		FCARate,
		RetentionRate,
		RetentionRateBroker,
		OngoingServicingRate,
		OngoingServicingSource,
		DA,
		AmountReceived,
		Premium,
		AgentSplit,
		CommissionType,
		CommissionTypeDesc,
		PayBasisCode,					
		PayBasisDesc,					
		PaymentMatchedDate,				
		Month,
		FrequencyCode,
		FrequencyDesc,
		ReassignedProductGroupCode,		
		ReassignedProductGroupName,		
		RecognitionType,
		CalculationType,
		Source,
		DateInserted,
		DateLastUpdated,
		CommissionYear
	)
	select	cs.PendingPaymentID as SourceID,
			cs.CaseID,
			cs.TransactionID,
			cs.ExtPolicyNumber as Policy,
			cs.ProductCode,
			cs.BusinessCode,
			cs.AgentCode as SellerCode,				
			0.0 as PointsTotal,
			0.0 as BSC,
			case 
				when mbf.MortgageFeeID is not null and cs.INIssued <> 0 then (((mbf.AdviceFeeAmount)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * MRbkr.FACTOR) - ((mbf.AdviceFeeAmount)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * Mfca.FACTOR)) --Note that mbf.AdviceFeeAmount is signed correctly - so no coding for signing is needed here
				else 0.0
			end as MBF,
			case 
				--When the adviser has changed, the AgentSplit can become zero in which case the ELITE points should be zero.
				when cs.AgentSplit = 0 then 0
				
				--WEALTH CALCULATION START
				--Indemnity payments or SINGLEs or IC Clawbacks or IC adjustments Start
				--THIS SCENARIO DOESN'T OCCUR IN PHASE 2
				--Indemnity payments or SINGLEs or IC Clawbacks or IC adjustments End
				--Accruals & Level Start
				--First payment front load as before
				when (cs.PendingPaymentID = css.MinInitialPendingPaymentID and (ph.ProductCategoryCode = 1 or pcc.KeyValue2 = '1')) then (((pt.CommInitialAmount)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * Crate.FACTOR) - ((pt.CommInitialAmount)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * Cfca.FACTOR)) * case when cs.CommissionType in (2,17) then -1 else 1 end
				--Accruals & Level End
				--WEALTH CALCULATION END
				
				--MORTGAGE CALCULATION START
				--Note: The MBF component has its own table column
				--Only 1 payment for mortgages
				when cs.PendingPaymentID = css.MinInitialPendingPaymentID and ph.ProductGroupCode = 3 then (((pt.CommInitialAmount)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * MRproc.FACTOR) - ((pt.CommInitialAmount)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * Mfca.FACTOR)) * case when cs.CommissionType in (2,17) then -1 else 1 end	
				--MORTGAGE CALCULATION END
				
				--PROTECTION CALCULATION START
				--Indemnity payments or SINGLEs or IC Clawbacks or IC adjustments Start
				--THIS SCENARIO DOESN'T OCCUR IN PHASE 2
				--Indemnity payments or SINGLEs or IC Clawbacks or IC adjustments End
				--Accruals & Level Start
				when cs.PendingPaymentID = css.MinInitialPendingPaymentID and ph.ProductGroupCode = 6 then (((pt.CommInitialAmount)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * Prate.FACTOR) - ((pt.CommInitialAmount)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * Pfca.FACTOR)) * case when cs.CommissionType in (2,17) then -1 else 1 end
				--Accruals & Level End
				--PROTECTION CALCULATION END

				else 0.0

			end as Initial,
			0.0 as OngoingTotal,
			0.0 as OngoingYr01,
			0.0 as OngoingYr02,
			0.0 as OngoingYr03,
			0.0 as OngoingYr04,
			0.0 as OngoingYr05,
			0.0 as OngoingYr06,
			0.0 as OngoingYr07,
			0.0 as OngoingYr08,
			0.0 as OngoingYr09,
			0.0 as OngoingYr10,
			case 
				when (ph.ProductCategoryCode = 1 or pcc.KeyValue2 = '1') then Cfca.FACTOR*100.0		--COB
				when ph.ProductGroupCode = 3 then Mfca.FACTOR*100.0		--MORT
				when ph.ProductGroupCode = 6 then Pfca.FACTOR*100.0		--PROT
				else 0.0
			end as FCARate,
			case 
				when (ph.ProductCategoryCode = 1 or pcc.KeyValue2 = '1') then Crate.FACTOR*100.0	--COB
				when ph.ProductGroupCode = 3 then MRproc.FACTOR*100.0	--MORT
				when ph.ProductGroupCode = 6 then Prate.FACTOR*100.0	--PROT
				else 0.0
			end as RetentionRate,
			case 
				when mbf.MortgageFeeID is not null then  MRbkr.FACTOR*100.0	
				else 0.0
			end as RetentionRateBroker,
			null as OngoingServicingRate,
			null as OngoingServicingSource,
			pt.CommInitialAmount as DA,
			e.AMOUNT_REC as AmountReceived,
			cs.Premium,
			cs.AgentSplit,
			cs.CommissionType,
			left(cs.StandingOrderDesc,50) as CommissionTypeDesc,
			cs.PayBasisCode,							
			cs.PayBasisDesc,							
			cs.CreateDate as PaymentMatchedDate,		
			cs.Month,
			cs.FrequencyCode,
			cs.FrequencyDesc,
			pg.ProductGroupCode as ReassignedProductGroupCode,	--Force the re-assigned products...		
			pg.ProductGroupName as ReassignedProductGroupName,	--...to be processed as investments		
			'VNB-PHASE-3a' as RecognitionType,
			case 
				when (ph.ProductCategoryCode = 1 or pcc.KeyValue2 = '1') then 'WEALTH-INITIAL'
				when ph.ProductGroupCode = 3 then 'MORTGAGE'
				when ph.ProductGroupCode = 6 then 'PROTECTION'
				else null
			end as CalculationType,
			'Openwork 2006' as Source,
			@DateLastUpdated as DateInserted,
			@DateLastUpdated as DateLastUpdated,
			csp.year as CommissionYear
	from	#msit_CommissionStatementSUMMARY css
			inner join msit_CommissionStatement cs
						on cs.TransactionID = css.TransactionID
						and cs.AgentCode = css.AgentCode
			inner join mstt_Agents ag on ag.Code = cs.BusinessCode
			inner join mstt_PolicyTransactions pt on pt.ID = cs.TransactionID
			inner join mstt_Policies p on p.POL_NUM = pt.PolicyID
			inner join msit_CommissionStatementPeriods VNBStart on convert(date,pt.CreateDateTime) between VNBStart.PeriodStartDate and VNBStart.PeriodEndDate
			inner join msit_Commissionstatementperiods csp on csp.month = cs.month
			inner join mstt_ProductHierarchy ph on ph.productcode = cs.productcode
			inner join mstt_Expectation e on e.ID = cs.ExpectationID
			left join dbo.owt_MortgageBrokerFees mbf on mbf.PendingPaymentID = cs.PendingPaymentID and mbf.AdviceFeeCharged = 'Yes'
			left join owt_SelectionControl SC
						on SC.Process = 'ElitePoints' 
						and SC.KeyType = 'NSCPotCode' 
						and cs.CreateDate between SC.EffectiveStartDate and SC.EffectiveEndDate
			left join mstt_Commissions BSCpot
						on BSCpot.TransactionID = cs.TransactionID 
						and BSCpot.Agent_Code = sc.KeyValue
						and BSCpot.CommissionType = 10
			left join owt_SelectionControl SFMPC						
						on SFMPC.Process = 'ElitePoints' 
						and SFMPC.KeyType = 'ServicingFeeMarginPotCode' 
						and cs.CreateDate between SFMPC.EffectiveStartDate and SFMPC.EffectiveEndDate
			left join mstt_Commissions SFMpot							
						on SFMpot.TransactionID = cs.TransactionID 
						and SFMpot.Agent_Code = SFMPC.KeyValue
						and SFMpot.CommissionType = 10	
			left join owt_SelectionControl pcc 
						on pcc.Process = 'ElitePoints'
						and pcc.KeyType = 'ProductCategoryCode'
						and pcc.KeyValue = cs.ProductCode	
						and cs.CreateDate between pcc.EffectiveStartDate and pcc.EffectiveEndDate
			left join owt_SelectionControl ogsdflt 
						on ogsdflt.Process = 'ElitePoints'
						and ogsdflt.KeyType = 'DefaultOngoingServicingRate'
						and ogsdflt.SelectionType = 'VNB'
						and ogsdflt.KeyValue = case when ph.RDRType = 'ONPLAT' then 'ONPLAT' else 'OFPLAT' end
						and cs.CreateDate between ogsdflt.EffectiveStartDate and ogsdflt.EffectiveEndDate
			left join mstt_CodeProductGroup pg on pg.ProductGroupCode = case when pcc.KeyValue2 = '1' then 2 else ph.ProductGroupCode end
			left join owt_EliteFactors Cfca on Cfca.FeeType = 'VNB' and Cfca.category = 'COB-FCA-RATE' and csp.year between Cfca.StartYear and Cfca.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors Crate on Crate.FeeType = 'VNB' and Crate.category = 'COB-RETENTION-RATE' and csp.year between Crate.StartYear and Crate.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors Mfca on Mfca.FeeType = 'VNB' and Mfca.category = 'MORT-FCA-RATE' and csp.year between Mfca.StartYear and Mfca.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors MRproc on MRproc.FeeType = 'VNB' and MRproc.category = 'MORT-RETENTION-RATE-PROC' and csp.year between MRproc.StartYear and MRproc.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors MRbkr on MRbkr.FeeType = 'VNB' and MRbkr.category = 'MORT-RETENTION-RATE-BROKER' and csp.year between MRbkr.StartYear and MRbkr.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors Pfca on Pfca.FeeType = 'VNB' and Pfca.category = 'PROT-FCA-RATE' and csp.year between Pfca.StartYear and Pfca.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors Prate on Prate.FeeType = 'VNB' and Prate.category = 'PROT-RETENTION-RATE' and csp.year between Prate.StartYear and Prate.EndYear 
	where	cs.ReportingClassCode = 1
	and		ag.Manager2Code <> @OwlManager2Code		--Exclude Owl
	and		isnull(css.MaxInitialPendingPaymentID,0) > isnull(css.MaxAdjPendingPaymentID,0)-- An initial payment follows the clawback, so time to revert back to front loading
	--and		cs.TransactionID = 5613333
	--order by cs.PendingPaymentID

	/****************************************************************************

		Phase 3a - initial payments restart after clawback/adj
		1) Set original (front loaded) points on first payment as per Phase 1
		2) Set (front loaded) points DIFFERENCE on first payment following clawback/adj
																
	****************************************************************************/

	update	PaymentAfterAdj
		set RecognitionType	= 'VNB-PHASE-3b',
			Initial =	case when FirstPayment.AmountReceived <> 0.0
							then ((FirstPayment.Initial / FirstPayment.AmountReceived) * PaymentAfterAdj.AmountReceived) - FirstPayment.Initial
							else 0.0
						end,
			DateLastUpdated = @DateLastUpdated
	from	#msit_CommissionStatementSUMMARY css
			inner join #AG_owt_Recognition_SEPARATE_ONGOING PaymentAfterAdj on PaymentAfterAdj.SourceID = css.MinInitialAfterAdjPendingPaymentID
			inner join #AG_owt_Recognition_SEPARATE_ONGOING FirstPayment on FirstPayment.SourceID = css.MinInitialPendingPaymentID
	where	isnull(css.MaxInitialPendingPaymentID,0) > isnull(css.MaxAdjPendingPaymentID,0)-- An initial payment follows the clawback, so front load it with the difference
	
	/****************************************************************************

		Now do the ongoing.
		
		Start with some work temp tables.
		
		Note: The Agent Split from the IC record is used because the ongoing (trail)
		splits are skewed by BSC and OGS margin.
																		
	****************************************************************************/

	--Find the oldest ongoing payment for each transaction (slice).
	select	cs.TransactionID, cs.AgentCode, cs.CommissionType, c.Agent_Perc as AgentSplit, min(cs.PendingPaymentID) as MinPendingPaymentID
	into	#msit_CommissionStatementONGOING
	from	msit_CommissionStatement cs
			inner join mstt_Commissions c
						on c.TransactionID = cs.TransactionID
						and c.Agent_Code = cs.AgentCode
						and c.CommissionType = 1
			inner join mstt_Agents ag on ag.Code = cs.BusinessCode
			inner join mstt_PolicyTransactions pt on pt.ID = cs.TransactionID
			inner join mstt_Policies p on p.POL_NUM = pt.PolicyID
			inner join msit_CommissionStatementPeriods VNBStart on convert(date,pt.CreateDateTime) between VNBStart.PeriodStartDate and VNBStart.PeriodEndDate
			inner join msit_Commissionstatementperiods csp on csp.month = cs.month
			inner join mstt_ProductHierarchy ph on ph.productcode = cs.productcode
			inner join mstt_Expectation e on e.ID = cs.ExpectationID
			left join owt_SelectionControl pcc 
						on pcc.Process = 'ElitePoints'
						and pcc.KeyType = 'ProductCategoryCode'
						and pcc.KeyValue = cs.ProductCode	
						and cs.CreateDate between pcc.EffectiveStartDate and pcc.EffectiveEndDate
	where	cs.ReportingClassCode = 1
	and		cs.CommFeeType = 'Ongoing'
	and		(ph.ProductCategoryCode = 1 or pcc.KeyValue2 = '1')
	and		ag.Manager2Code <> @OwlManager2Code					--Exclude Owl
	and		csp.Year >= 2017									--Ensure in-scope payments are consistent with VNB start
	and		VNBStart.Year >= 2017								--VNB to start from new slices in 2017 for +ve payments
	and		cs.CommissionType = 10								--10=Trail Fee
	and		abs(e.AMOUNT_REC) >= 0.01		
	and		((cs.FrequencyCode = 6 and cs.Premium > 1.00)		--Frequency=6->Single
			or (cs.FrequencyCode <> 6 and cs.Premium > 0.01))	--Frequency<>6->Regular
	group	by cs.TransactionID, cs.AgentCode, cs.CommissionType, c.Agent_Perc

	union
	
	--We need all ongoing adjustment and clawback payments i.e. NOT just the oldest 
	select	cs.TransactionID, cs.AgentCode, cs.CommissionType, c.Agent_Perc as AgentSplit, cs.PendingPaymentID as MinPendingPaymentID
	from	msit_CommissionStatement cs
			inner join mstt_Commissions c
						on c.TransactionID = cs.TransactionID
						and c.Agent_Code = cs.AgentCode
						and c.CommissionType = 1
			inner join mstt_Agents ag on ag.Code = cs.BusinessCode
			inner join mstt_PolicyTransactions pt on pt.ID = cs.TransactionID
			inner join mstt_Policies p on p.POL_NUM = pt.PolicyID
			inner join msit_CommissionStatementPeriods VNBStart on convert(date,pt.CreateDateTime) between VNBStart.PeriodStartDate and VNBStart.PeriodEndDate
			inner join msit_Commissionstatementperiods csp on csp.month = cs.month
			inner join mstt_ProductHierarchy ph on ph.productcode = cs.productcode
			inner join mstt_Expectation e on e.ID = cs.ExpectationID
			left join owt_SelectionControl pcc 
						on pcc.Process = 'ElitePoints'
						and pcc.KeyType = 'ProductCategoryCode'
						and pcc.KeyValue = cs.ProductCode	
						and cs.CreateDate between pcc.EffectiveStartDate and pcc.EffectiveEndDate
	where	cs.ReportingClassCode = 1
	and		cs.CommFeeType = 'Ongoing'
	and		(ph.ProductCategoryCode = 1 or pcc.KeyValue2 = '1')
	and		ag.Manager2Code <> @OwlManager2Code					--Exclude Owl
	and		csp.Year >= 2017									--We don't care when the transaction started but the payment must be from 2017
	and		cs.CommissionType in (16,19)						--16=Clawback Trail;19=Adjustment Trail
	and		abs(e.AMOUNT_REC) >= 0.01					
	and		((cs.FrequencyCode = 6 and cs.Premium > 1.00)		--Frequency=6->Single
			or (cs.FrequencyCode <> 6 and cs.Premium > 0.01))	--Frequency<>6->Regular

	/****************************************************************************
		
		Insert the ongoing VNB results into the main work table
																		
	****************************************************************************/

	insert into #AG_owt_Recognition_SEPARATE_ONGOING
	(
		SourceID,
		CaseID,
		TransactionID,
		Policy,
		ProductCode,
		BusinessCode,
		SellerCode,
		PointsTotal,
		BSC,
		MBF,
		Initial,
		OngoingTotal,
		OngoingYr01,
		OngoingYr02,
		OngoingYr03,
		OngoingYr04,
		OngoingYr05,
		OngoingYr06,
		OngoingYr07,
		OngoingYr08,
		OngoingYr09,
		OngoingYr10,
		FCARate,
		RetentionRate,
		RetentionRateBroker,
		OngoingServicingRate,
		OngoingServicingSource,
		DA,
		AmountReceived,
		Premium,
		AgentSplit,
		CommissionType,
		CommissionTypeDesc,
		PayBasisCode,
		PayBasisDesc,
		PaymentMatchedDate,
		Month,
		FrequencyCode,
		FrequencyDesc,
		ReassignedProductGroupCode,
		ReassignedProductGroupName,
		RecognitionType,
		CalculationType,
		Source,
		DateInserted,
		DateLastUpdated,
		CommissionYear
	)
	select	cs.PendingPaymentID as SourceID,
			cs.CaseID,
			cs.TransactionID,
			cs.ExtPolicyNumber as Policy,
			cs.ProductCode,
			cs.BusinessCode,
			cs.AgentCode as SellerCode,
			0.0 as PointsTotal,
			case
				when BSCpot.ID is not null then 
					--BSC takes the first 0.12 of the ongoing fee %. If the ongoing fee % is 0.12% or less, then 100% of the ongoing fee is allocated to BSC
					case when coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2)) - convert(decimal(8,4),sc.KeyValue2) >= 0.01
						then 
							case when cs.FrequencyCode = 2	--Monthly 
								then (cso.AgentSplit/100) * 12.0 * (isnull(cs.Premium,0)/2.0) * convert(decimal(8,4),sc.KeyValue3) * case when cs.CommissionType in (16,19) then -1 else 1 end
								else (cso.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(cs.Premium,0) * convert(decimal(8,4),sc.KeyValue3) * case when cs.CommissionType in (16,19) then -1 else 1 end
							end			
						else
							case when cs.FrequencyCode = 2	--Monthly 
								then (cso.AgentSplit/100) * 12.0 * (isnull(cs.Premium,0)/2.0) * coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2)) * case when cs.CommissionType in (16,19) then -1 else 1 end
								else (cso.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(cs.Premium,0) * (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))/100.0) * case when cs.CommissionType in (16,19) then -1 else 1 end
							end
					end
				else 0.0
			end as BSC,
			0.0 as MBF,
			0.0 as Initial,
			0.0 as OngoingTotal,
			case
				--WEALTH ONGOING CALCULATION START
				--When the adviser has changed, the AgentSplit can become zero in which case the ELITE points should be zero.
				when cso.AgentSplit = 0 then 0

				--SINGLE start
				--Calculate when BSC and ongoing applies (where ongoing rate is greater than BSC rate) 
				when cs.FrequencyCode = 6 and SFMpot.ID is not null and BSCpot.ID is not null and (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2)) - convert(decimal(8,4),sc.KeyValue2)) >= 0.01 then 
							--(AUM X BSC Rate)...
							((cso.AgentSplit/100) * (isnull(cs.Premium,0) * convert(decimal(8,4),sc.KeyValue3)) 
							--(AUM X OGS Rate X COB FCA Rate)...
							- ((cso.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(cs.Premium,0) * (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))/100.0) * Cfca.FACTOR)
							--(AUM X (OGS Rate - BSC Rate) X COB Retention Rate)...
							+ ((cso.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(cs.Premium,0) * ((coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))-convert(decimal(8,4),sc.KeyValue2))/100.0)) * Crate.FACTOR) 
							--Sign correctly for +ve or clawback payment
							* (case when cs.CommissionType in (16,19) then -1 else 1 end)
				--Calculate when BSC and ongoing applies (where ongoing rate less than BSC rate, then BSC gets all the ongoing available) 
				when cs.FrequencyCode = 6 and SFMpot.ID is not null and BSCpot.ID is not null then
							--(AUM X BSC Rate)...(in this scenario it's all of the OGS rate)
							((cso.AgentSplit/100) * (isnull(cs.Premium,0) * (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))/100.0)) 
							--(AUM X OGS Rate X COB FCA Rate)...
							- ((cso.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(cs.Premium,0) * (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))/100.0) * Cfca.FACTOR)
							--(AUM X (OGS Rate - BSC Rate) X COB Retention Rate)...
							+ (0.0)) --BSC got it all, so this part of the calculation is zero
							--Sign correctly for +ve or clawback payment
							* (case when cs.CommissionType in (16,19) then -1 else 1 end)
				--Calculate when no BSC applies and ongoing applies
				when cs.FrequencyCode = 6 and SFMpot.ID is not null and BSCpot.ID is null then 
							--(AUM X OGS Rate X COB Retention Rate)...
							(((cso.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(cs.Premium,0) * (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))/100.0) * Crate.FACTOR) 
							--(AUM X OGS Rate X COB FCA Rate)...
							- ((cso.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(cs.Premium,0) * (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))/100.0) * Cfca.FACTOR))
							--Sign correctly for +ve or clawback payment
							* (case when cs.CommissionType in (16,19) then -1 else 1 end)
				--SINGLE end
				
				--REGULAR start
				--Calculate when BSC and ongoing applies (where ongoing rate is greater than BSC rate) 
				when cs.FrequencyCode <> 6 and SFMpot.ID is not null and BSCpot.ID is not null and (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2)) - convert(decimal(8,4),sc.KeyValue2)) >= 0.01 then		--AG 04/06/2018 (1)
							--The non-BSC portion (Ave AUM X (OGS Rate - BSC Rate) X COB Retention Rate)...
							((((((cso.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(cs.Premium,0) * (case when cs.FrequencyCode = 2 then 12 else 1 end))/2.0) * (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2)) - convert(decimal(8,4),sc.KeyValue2))/100.0)) * Crate.FACTOR
							--The BSC portion (Ave AUM X BSC Rate)...
							+ case when cs.FrequencyCode = 2	--Monthly 
									then (cso.AgentSplit/100) * 12.0 * (isnull(cs.Premium,0)/2.0) * convert(decimal(8,4),sc.KeyValue3) 
									else (cso.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(cs.Premium,0) * convert(decimal(8,4),sc.KeyValue3) 
							  end
							--FCA Charge (Ave AUM X OGS Rate X FCA Rate)...
							- (case when cs.FrequencyCode = 2	--Monthly 
									then (cso.AgentSplit/100) * 12.0 * (isnull(cs.Premium,0)/2.0) 
									else (cso.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(cs.Premium,0) 
							   end * (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))/100.0) * Cfca.FACTOR))
							--Sign correctly for +ve or clawback payment
							* (case when cs.CommissionType in (16,19) then -1 else 1 end)   
				--Calculate when BSC and ongoing applies (where ongoing rate less than BSC rate, then BSC gets all the ongoing available) 
				when cs.FrequencyCode <> 6 and SFMpot.ID is not null and BSCpot.ID is not null then		--AG 04/06/2018 (1)
							--The non-BSC portion (Ave AUM X (OGS Rate - BSC Rate) X COB Retention Rate)...
							((0.0)	--BSC got it all, so this part of the calculation is zero
							--The BSC portion (Ave AUM X BSC Rate)...(in this scenario it's all of the OGS rate)
							+ case when cs.FrequencyCode = 2	--Monthly 
									then (cso.AgentSplit/100) * 12.0 * (isnull(cs.Premium,0)/2.0) * (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))/100.0) 
									else (cso.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(cs.Premium,0) * (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))/100.0) 
							  end
							--FCA Charge (Ave AUM X OGS Rate X FCA Rate)...
							- (case when cs.FrequencyCode = 2	--Monthly 
									then (cso.AgentSplit/100) * 12.0 * (isnull(cs.Premium,0)/2.0) 
									else (cso.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(cs.Premium,0) 
							   end * (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))/100.0) * Cfca.FACTOR))
							--Sign correctly for +ve or clawback payment
							* (case when cs.CommissionType in (16,19) then -1 else 1 end)   
				--Calculate when no BSC applies, but ongoing servicing applies
				when cs.FrequencyCode <> 6 and SFMpot.ID is not null and BSCpot.ID is null then		--AG 04/06/2018	(1)
							--(Ave AUM X OGS Rate X COB Retention Rate)...
							(((((cso.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(cs.Premium,0) * (case when cs.FrequencyCode = 2 then 12 else 1 end))/2.0) * (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))/100.0) * Crate.FACTOR) 
							--(Ave AUM X OGS Rate X COB FCA Rate)...
							- ((((cso.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(cs.Premium,0) * (case when cs.FrequencyCode = 2 then 12 else 1 end))/2.0) * (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))/100.0) * Cfca.FACTOR))
							--Sign correctly for +ve or clawback payment
							* (case when cs.CommissionType in (16,19) then -1 else 1 end)   
				--REGULAR end
				
				else 0.0

				--WEALTH ONGOING CALCULATION END
			end as OngoingYr01,
			0.0 as OngoingYr02,
			0.0 as OngoingYr03,
			0.0 as OngoingYr04,
			0.0 as OngoingYr05,
			0.0 as OngoingYr06,
			0.0 as OngoingYr07,
			0.0 as OngoingYr08,
			0.0 as OngoingYr09,
			0.0 as OngoingYr10,
			Cfca.FACTOR*100.0 as FCARate,
			Crate.FACTOR*100.0 as RetentionRate,
			0.0 as RetentionRateBroker,
			case when SFMpot.ID is not null
				then coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))
				else null
			end as OngoingServicingRate,
			case when SFMpot.ID is not null
				then case 
						when ogs.OngoingServiceFee is null and ogscli.OngoingServiceFee is null 
							then case
								when ogsdflt.KeyValue = 'ONPLAT' then 'Default - On Plat'
								else 'Default - Off Plat'
							end
						when ogs.OngoingServiceFee is not null then 'Client Product'
						when ogscli.OngoingServiceFee is not null then 'Client Only'
						else 'Unknown'
					 end
				else case when (ph.ProductCategoryCode = 1 or pcc.KeyValue2 = '1')
						then 'No OGS'					--WEALTH, but no OGS
						else null						--Not WEALTH, so OGS is n/a and is therefore null
					 end
			end as OngoingServicingSource,
			pt.CommInitialAmount as DA,
			e.AMOUNT_REC as AmountReceived,
			cs.Premium,
			cso.AgentSplit,								--Use the split from the IC record
			cs.CommissionType,
			left(cs.StandingOrderDesc,50) as CommissionTypeDesc,
			cs.PayBasisCode,
			cs.PayBasisDesc,
			cs.CreateDate as PaymentMatchedDate,
			cs.Month,
			cs.FrequencyCode,
			cs.FrequencyDesc,
			pg.ProductGroupCode as ReassignedProductGroupCode,	--Force the re-assigned products...		
			pg.ProductGroupName as ReassignedProductGroupName,	--...to be processed as investments		
			'VNB-OGS' as RecognitionType,
			'WEALTH-ONGOING' as CalculationType,
			'Openwork 2006' as Source,
			@DateLastUpdated as DateInserted,
			@DateLastUpdated as DateLastUpdated,
			csp.year as CommissionYear
	from	#msit_CommissionStatementONGOING cso
			inner join msit_CommissionStatement cs on cs.PendingPaymentID = cso.MinPendingPaymentID
			inner join mstt_Agents ag on ag.Code = cs.BusinessCode
			inner join mstt_PolicyTransactions pt on pt.ID = cs.TransactionID
			inner join mstt_Policies p on p.POL_NUM = pt.PolicyID
			inner join msit_CommissionStatementPeriods VNBStart on convert(date,pt.CreateDateTime) between VNBStart.PeriodStartDate and VNBStart.PeriodEndDate
			inner join msit_Commissionstatementperiods csp on csp.month = cs.month
			inner join mstt_ProductHierarchy ph on ph.productcode = cs.productcode
			inner join mstt_Expectation e on e.ID = cs.ExpectationID
			left join dbo.owt_MortgageBrokerFees mbf on mbf.PendingPaymentID = cs.PendingPaymentID and mbf.AdviceFeeCharged = 'Yes'
			left join owt_SelectionControl SC
						on SC.Process = 'ElitePoints' 
						and SC.KeyType = 'NSCPotCode' 
						and cs.CreateDate between SC.EffectiveStartDate and SC.EffectiveEndDate
			left join mstt_Commissions BSCpot
						on BSCpot.TransactionID = cs.TransactionID 
						and BSCpot.Agent_Code = sc.KeyValue
						and BSCpot.CommissionType = 10
			left join owt_SelectionControl SFMPC						
						on SFMPC.Process = 'ElitePoints' 
						and SFMPC.KeyType = 'ServicingFeeMarginPotCode' 
						and cs.CreateDate between SFMPC.EffectiveStartDate and SFMPC.EffectiveEndDate
			left join mstt_Commissions SFMpot							
						on SFMpot.TransactionID = cs.TransactionID 
						and SFMpot.Agent_Code = SFMPC.KeyValue
						and SFMpot.CommissionType = 10	
			left join owt_SelectionControl pcc 
						on pcc.Process = 'ElitePoints'
						and pcc.KeyType = 'ProductCategoryCode'
						and pcc.KeyValue = cs.ProductCode	
						and cs.CreateDate between pcc.EffectiveStartDate and pcc.EffectiveEndDate
			left join owt_SelectionControl ogsdflt 
						on ogsdflt.Process = 'ElitePoints'
						and ogsdflt.KeyType = 'DefaultOngoingServicingRate'
						and ogsdflt.SelectionType = 'VNB'
						and ogsdflt.KeyValue = case when ph.RDRType = 'ONPLAT' then 'ONPLAT' else 'OFPLAT' end
						and cs.CreateDate between ogsdflt.EffectiveStartDate and ogsdflt.EffectiveEndDate
			left join mstt_CodeProductGroup pg on pg.ProductGroupCode = case when pcc.KeyValue2 = '1' then 2 else ph.ProductGroupCode end
			left join owt_EliteFactors Cfca on Cfca.FeeType = 'VNB' and Cfca.category = 'COB-FCA-RATE' and csp.year between Cfca.StartYear and Cfca.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors Crate on Crate.FeeType = 'VNB' and Crate.category = 'COB-RETENTION-RATE' and csp.year between Crate.StartYear and Crate.EndYear 
--			left join owt_EliteFactors Mfca on Mfca.FeeType = 'VNB' and Mfca.category = 'MORT-FCA-RATE' and csp.year between Mfca.StartYear and Mfca.EndYear 
--			left join owt_EliteFactors MRproc on MRproc.FeeType = 'VNB' and MRproc.category = 'MORT-RETENTION-RATE-PROC' and csp.year between MRproc.StartYear and MRproc.EndYear 
--			left join owt_EliteFactors MRbkr on MRbkr.FeeType = 'VNB' and MRbkr.category = 'MORT-RETENTION-RATE-BROKER' and csp.year between MRbkr.StartYear and MRbkr.EndYear 
--			left join owt_EliteFactors Pfca on Pfca.FeeType = 'VNB' and Pfca.category = 'PROT-FCA-RATE' and csp.year between Pfca.StartYear and Pfca.EndYear 
--			left join owt_EliteFactors Prate on Prate.FeeType = 'VNB' and Prate.category = 'PROT-RETENTION-RATE' and csp.year between Prate.StartYear and Prate.EndYear 
			left join #OGSLookUp ogs on ogs.CLIENT_NUM = cs.ClientID and ogs.ProductCode = cs.ProductCode
			left join #OGSLookUpClient ogscli on ogscli.CLIENT_NUM = cs.ClientID 	

	/****************************************************************************

		Now calculate the ongoing spread as follows:
		1) Investments: Years 1 to 6
		2) Pensions:	Years 1 to 10
		Note that regular payments get an additional multiplier to uplift the 
		average AUM for each year.
																		
	****************************************************************************/

	update r
		set OngoingYr02 = case when r.FrequencyCode = 2									--Monthly
							then r.OngoingYr01 * YR02.Multiplier * YR02.Factor			--Regular
							else r.OngoingYr01 * YR02.Factor							--Single
						  end,
			OngoingYr03 = case when r.FrequencyCode = 2									--Monthly
							then r.OngoingYr01 * YR03.Multiplier * YR03.Factor			--Regular
							else r.OngoingYr01 * YR03.Factor							--Single
						  end,
			OngoingYr04 = case when r.FrequencyCode = 2									--Monthly
							then r.OngoingYr01 * YR04.Multiplier * YR04.Factor			--Regular
							else r.OngoingYr01 * YR04.Factor							--Single
						  end,
			OngoingYr05 = case when r.FrequencyCode = 2									--Monthly 
							then r.OngoingYr01 * YR05.Multiplier * YR05.Factor			--Regular
							else r.OngoingYr01 * YR05.Factor							--Single
						  end,
			OngoingYr06 = case when r.FrequencyCode = 2									--Monthly 
							then r.OngoingYr01 * YR06.Multiplier * YR06.Factor			--Regular
							else r.OngoingYr01 * YR06.Factor							--Single
						  end,
			OngoingYr07 = case when r.ReassignedProductGroupCode = 5					--Pensions	AG 05/06/2018
							then
								case when r.FrequencyCode = 2							--Monthly 
									then r.OngoingYr01 * YR07.Multiplier * YR07.Factor	--Regular
									else r.OngoingYr01 * YR07.Factor					--Single
								end
							else 
								0.0
						  end,
			OngoingYr08 = case when r.ReassignedProductGroupCode = 5					--Pensions	AG 05/06/2018 
							then
								case when r.FrequencyCode = 2							--Monthly 
									then r.OngoingYr01 * YR08.Multiplier * YR08.Factor	--Regular
									else r.OngoingYr01 * YR08.Factor					--Single
								end
							else 
								0.0
						  end,
			OngoingYr09 = case when r.ReassignedProductGroupCode = 5					--Pensions	AG 05/06/2018 
							then
								case when r.FrequencyCode = 2							--Monthly 
									then r.OngoingYr01 * YR09.Multiplier * YR09.Factor	--Regular
									else r.OngoingYr01 * YR09.Factor					--Single
								end
							else 
								0.0
						  end,
			OngoingYr10 = case when r.ReassignedProductGroupCode = 5					--Pensions	AG 05/06/2018
							then
								case when r.FrequencyCode = 2							--Monthly 
									then r.OngoingYr01 * YR10.Multiplier * YR10.Factor	--Regular
									else r.OngoingYr01 * YR10.Factor					--Single
								end
							else 
								0.0
						  end
	from	#AG_owt_Recognition_SEPARATE_ONGOING r
			left join owt_EliteFactors YR01 on YR01.FeeType = 'VNB' and YR01.Category = 'COB-ONGOING-DISCOUNT-YR01' and r.CommissionYear between YR01.StartYear and YR01.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors YR02 on YR02.FeeType = 'VNB' and YR02.Category = 'COB-ONGOING-DISCOUNT-YR02' and r.CommissionYear between YR02.StartYear and YR02.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors YR03 on YR03.FeeType = 'VNB' and YR03.Category = 'COB-ONGOING-DISCOUNT-YR03' and r.CommissionYear between YR03.StartYear and YR03.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors YR04 on YR04.FeeType = 'VNB' and YR04.Category = 'COB-ONGOING-DISCOUNT-YR04' and r.CommissionYear between YR04.StartYear and YR04.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors YR05 on YR05.FeeType = 'VNB' and YR05.Category = 'COB-ONGOING-DISCOUNT-YR05' and r.CommissionYear between YR05.StartYear and YR05.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors YR06 on YR06.FeeType = 'VNB' and YR06.Category = 'COB-ONGOING-DISCOUNT-YR06' and r.CommissionYear between YR06.StartYear and YR06.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors YR07 on YR07.FeeType = 'VNB' and YR07.Category = 'COB-ONGOING-DISCOUNT-YR07' and r.CommissionYear between YR07.StartYear and YR07.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors YR08 on YR08.FeeType = 'VNB' and YR08.Category = 'COB-ONGOING-DISCOUNT-YR08' and r.CommissionYear between YR08.StartYear and YR08.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors YR09 on YR09.FeeType = 'VNB' and YR09.Category = 'COB-ONGOING-DISCOUNT-YR09' and r.CommissionYear between YR09.StartYear and YR09.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors YR10 on YR10.FeeType = 'VNB' and YR10.Category = 'COB-ONGOING-DISCOUNT-YR10' and r.CommissionYear between YR10.StartYear and YR10.EndYear 
	where	r.CalculationType = 'WEALTH-ONGOING'
	
	/****************************************************************************

		Now add up all the numbers
																		
	****************************************************************************/
	
	update r
		set OngoingTotal	=	OngoingYr01 + OngoingYr02 + OngoingYr03 + OngoingYr04 + OngoingYr05 +
								OngoingYr06 + OngoingYr07 + OngoingYr08 + OngoingYr09 + OngoingYr10,
			PointsTotal		=	OngoingYr01 + OngoingYr02 + OngoingYr03 + OngoingYr04 + OngoingYr05 +
								OngoingYr06 + OngoingYr07 + OngoingYr08 + OngoingYr09 + OngoingYr10 +
								Initial + MBF	-- Note BSC is already included in the Ongoing, so don't include it in the Points Total.
	from	#AG_owt_Recognition_SEPARATE_ONGOING r

	/****************************************************************************

		Merge the temporary table into the permanent table (IC data)
																		
	****************************************************************************/

	BEGIN TRANSACTION

	declare @SummaryOfChanges table (Change varchar(20))
	merge	dbo.AG_owt_Recognition_SEPARATE_ONGOING as trg
	using	#AG_owt_Recognition_SEPARATE_ONGOING as src
	on		trg.SourceID = src.SourceID
	and		trg.Source = src.Source
	when	matched 
	and		isnull(trg.PointsTotal,0) <> isnull(src.PointsTotal,0)
	then	update 
				set trg.CaseID = src.CaseID,
					trg.TransactionID = src.TransactionID,
					trg.Policy = src.Policy,
					trg.ProductCode = src.ProductCode,
					trg.BusinessCode = src.BusinessCode,
					trg.SellerCode = src.SellerCode,					--AG 13/06/2018
					trg.PointsTotal = src.PointsTotal,
					trg.BSC = src.BSC,
					trg.MBF = src.MBF,
					trg.Initial = src.Initial,
					trg.OngoingTotal = src.OngoingTotal,
					trg.OngoingYr01 = src.OngoingYr01,
					trg.OngoingYr02 = src.OngoingYr02,
					trg.OngoingYr03 = src.OngoingYr03,
					trg.OngoingYr04 = src.OngoingYr04,
					trg.OngoingYr05 = src.OngoingYr05,
					trg.OngoingYr06 = src.OngoingYr06,
					trg.OngoingYr07 = src.OngoingYr07,
					trg.OngoingYr08 = src.OngoingYr08,
					trg.OngoingYr09 = src.OngoingYr09,
					trg.OngoingYr10 = src.OngoingYr10,
					trg.FCARate = src.FCARate,
					trg.RetentionRate = src.RetentionRate,
					trg.RetentionRateBroker = src.RetentionRateBroker,
					trg.OngoingServicingRate = src.OngoingServicingRate,
					trg.OngoingServicingSource = src.OngoingServicingSource,
					trg.DA = src.DA,
					trg.AmountReceived = src.AmountReceived,
					trg.Premium = src.Premium,
					trg.AgentSplit = src.AgentSplit,
					trg.CommissionType = src.CommissionType,
					trg.CommissionTypeDesc = src.CommissionTypeDesc,
					trg.PayBasisCode = src.PayBasisCode,				--AG 13/06/2018
					trg.PayBasisDesc = src.PayBasisDesc,				--AG 13/06/2018
					trg.PaymentMatchedDate = src.PaymentMatchedDate,	--AG 13/06/2018	
					trg.Month = src.Month,
					trg.FrequencyCode = src.FrequencyCode,
					trg.FrequencyDesc = src.FrequencyDesc,
					trg.ReassignedProductGroupCode = src.ReassignedProductGroupCode,	--AG 05/06/2018
					trg.ReassignedProductGroupName = src.ReassignedProductGroupName,	--AG 05/06/2018
					trg.RecognitionType = src.RecognitionType,
					trg.CalculationType = src.CalculationType,
					trg.DateLastUpdated = @DateLastUpdated
	when	not matched by target 
	then	insert
			(
				SourceID,
				CaseID,
				TransactionID,
				Policy,
				ProductCode,
				BusinessCode,
				SellerCode,							--AG 13/06/2018
				PointsTotal,
				BSC,
				MBF,
				Initial,
				OngoingTotal,
				OngoingYr01,
				OngoingYr02,
				OngoingYr03,
				OngoingYr04,
				OngoingYr05,
				OngoingYr06,
				OngoingYr07,
				OngoingYr08,
				OngoingYr09,
				OngoingYr10,
				FCARate,
				RetentionRate,
				RetentionRateBroker,
				OngoingServicingRate,
				OngoingServicingSource,
				DA,
				AmountReceived,
				Premium,
				AgentSplit,
				CommissionType,
				CommissionTypeDesc,
				PayBasisCode,						--AG 13/06/2018
				PayBasisDesc,						--AG 13/06/2018
				PaymentMatchedDate,					--AG 13/06/2018
				Month,
				FrequencyCode,
				FrequencyDesc,
				ReassignedProductGroupCode,			--AG 05/06/2018
				ReassignedProductGroupName,			--AG 05/06/2018
				RecognitionType,
				CalculationType,
				Source,
				DateInserted,
				DateLastUpdated
			)		
			values
			(
				src.SourceID,
				src.CaseID,
				src.TransactionID,
				src.Policy,
				src.ProductCode,
				src.BusinessCode,
				src.SellerCode,						--AG 13/06/2018
				src.PointsTotal,
				src.BSC,
				src.MBF,
				src.Initial,
				src.OngoingTotal,
				src.OngoingYr01,
				src.OngoingYr02,
				src.OngoingYr03,
				src.OngoingYr04,
				src.OngoingYr05,
				src.OngoingYr06,
				src.OngoingYr07,
				src.OngoingYr08,
				src.OngoingYr09,
				src.OngoingYr10,
				src.FCARate,
				src.RetentionRate,
				src.RetentionRateBroker,
				src.OngoingServicingRate,
				src.OngoingServicingSource,
				src.DA,
				src.AmountReceived,
				src.Premium,
				src.AgentSplit,
				src.CommissionType,
				src.CommissionTypeDesc,
				src.PayBasisCode,					--AG 13/06/2018
				src.PayBasisDesc,					--AG 13/06/2018
				src.PaymentMatchedDate,				--AG 13/06/2018
				src.Month,
				src.FrequencyCode,
				src.FrequencyDesc,
				src.ReassignedProductGroupCode,		--AG 05/06/2018
				src.ReassignedProductGroupName,		--AG 05/06/2018
				src.RecognitionType,
				src.CalculationType,
				src.Source,
				src.DateInserted,
				src.DateLastUpdated)				--Merge statements must have a ;
	output $action into @SummaryOfChanges;
						
	/****************************************************************************

		Update OpenAccess
																		
	****************************************************************************/

/*	
	--Do not include MBF in the OpenAccess Commission Listing as it is on the MBF download
	--and we don't want MBF double counting.
	update	oal
		set VNB_Points = r.PointsTotal - r.MBF		--AG 04/06/2018 (2)
	from	msit_CommissionStatement cs
/*			inner join (select	distinct PKID
						from	owt_TransformationMovements tm 
						where	tm.DriverTableName = 'sa_swift_S_AGMFIL'
						and		tm.CommissionStatement = 'Y') tm on tm.PKID = cs.PendingPaymentID
*/			inner join msit_OpenworkAdviserListing oal on oal.SourceID = cs.ID and oal.Source = 'Openwork 2006'
			inner join owt_Recognition r 
						on r.SourceID = cs.PendingPaymentID
						and r.Source = oal.Source
	--where	isnull(oal.VNB_Points,0) <> isnull(r.PointsTotal,0)
	
	select @OALRowCount = @@rowcount
*/
	COMMIT TRANSACTION      
	
	select	@RowCount = COUNT(*)
	from	@SummaryOfChanges
	where	Change = 'INSERT'

	set @ProcessMessage = 'owt_Recognition (insert) = ' + convert(nvarchar(10), @RowCount)
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseLog, @ProcessMessage, null, @Module, @Client

	select	@RowCount = COUNT(*)
	from	@SummaryOfChanges
	where	Change = 'UPDATE'

	set @ProcessMessage = 'owt_Recognition (update) = ' + convert(nvarchar(10), @RowCount)
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseLog, @ProcessMessage, null, @Module, @Client
/*
	set @ProcessMessage = 'msit_OpenworkAdviserListing (update) = ' + convert(nvarchar(10), @OALRowCount)
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseLog, @ProcessMessage, null, @Module, @Client
*/
	/****************************************************************************

		T H E   E N D
																		
	****************************************************************************/
	
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseEnd, @ProcName, null, @Module, @Client

END TRY

BEGIN CATCH 

	select @ErrNum = ERROR_NUMBER(), @ErrMsg = ERROR_MESSAGE(), @ErrSev = ERROR_SEVERITY(), @ErrLine = ERROR_LINE(), @ErrState = XACT_STATE()
	set @ErrMsg = REPLACE(@ErrMsg, '.', '') + ' (error no: ' + CAST(@ErrNum AS VARCHAR(10)) + ') on line ' + CAST(@ErrLine AS VARCHAR(10))
	
	-- Test XACT_STATE for 0, 1, or -1.
    -- If 1, the transaction is committable.
    -- If -1, the transaction is uncommittable and should be rolled back.
    -- If 0, there is no transaction and a commit or rollback operation would generate an error.

	if @ErrState = -1			-- Transaction is uncommitable
		rollback transaction

	if @ErrState = 1			
		commit transaction

	-- Error message line 1
	set @ErrMsgBrief = left(@ErrMsg,100)
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseError, @ErrMsgBrief, null, @Module, @Client
	
	-- Error message line 2 - if any text exists
	set @ErrMsgBrief = substring(@ErrMsg,101,100)
	if len(@ErrMsgBrief) > 0
		exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseError, @ErrMsgBrief, null, @Module, @Client

	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseEnd, @ProcName, null, @Module, @Client

	RAISERROR(@ErrMsg, @ErrSev , 1)

END CATCH

/****************************************************************************

			E N D															

****************************************************************************/

return @ErrNum


GO


/****** Object:  StoredProcedure [dbo].[owp_RecognitionSwiftONGOING_Backup20180630AG]    Script Date: 7/3/2026 3:44:25 PM ******/
SET ANSI_NULLS ON
GO
SET QUOTED_IDENTIFIER ON
GO
/*********************************************************************************************************

Program:		owp_RecognitionSwift					
Author:			Alan Groves
Date created:	11/04/2018
											
Description:
===========

This proc populates the new recognition table called "owt_Recognition" with "Value of New Business"
(VNB) points.

This proc handles all of the swift data which includes:
WEALTH - COB business i.e. pensions and investments
MORTGAGES
PROTECTION

Note: There is a separate proc that calculates the GI VNB points from the Paymentshield data.

The approach of this proc is to use the incremental PendingPaymentIDs from the overnight batch
to calculate the VNB points in a temporary table.

The temporary table is then merged with the permanent table to make the calculated (or
re-calculated values) permanent.

Terms
-----
BSC			- Business Service Charge.
MBF			- Mortgage Broker Fee.
OGS			- Ongoing Servicing.
BSC Rate	- 0.12% at the time of writing (24/04/2018). This could be changed by the business, but
				would also require some DEV work in OWS.
DF			- Discount Factor.
DA			- Distribution Allowance (the total amount paid out by the provider to Openwork)
AUM			- Assets Under Management. Basically the amount invested or the premium on investment
				cases.
Average AUM - Average amount invested annually which is equivalent to 6 months' premium.

THE CALCULATIONS
================

There are two potential parts: initial + ongoing (if ongoing applies). If BSC (applies to ongoing 
only) and MBF (applies to mortgages only) apply, then these are also included:

MORTGAGE
--------
Part 1: MBF column = (Advice Fee Amount X Broker Retention Rate) - (Advice Fee Amount X Mort FCA Rate)
Part 2: Initial column = (Proc Fee Amount X Mortgage Retention Rate) - (Proc Fee X Mort FCA Rate) 
Mortgage Points Total = Initial + MBF

PROTECTION
----------
= (DA X Protection Retention Rate) - (DA X Protection FCA Rate) 
Protection Points Total = Initial

WEALTH (COB i.e. pensions and investments)
------
Part 1: Initial column = (DA X Wealth Retention Rate) - (DA X Wealth FCA Rate)

Part 2:

****XXXX****

NOTE: Where the BSC rate is greater than the ongoing rate, then BSC gets ALL of the AVAILABLE 
ongoing.

****XXXX****

REGULAR - BSC applies:
Year 1 column = BSC Points + Non-BSC Points - FCA Points
Non-BSC Points = Ave AUM X (OGS Rate - BSC Rate) X COB Retention Rate
BSC Points = Ave AUM X BSC Rate
FCA Points = Ave AUM X OGS Rate X COB FCA Rate

REGULAR - Non-BSC: 
Year 1 column = (Ave AUM X OGS Rate X COB Retention Rate) - (Ave AUM X OGS Rate X COB FCA Rate)

SINGLE - BSC applies:
Year 1 column = (AUM X BSC Rate) + (AUM X (OGS Rate - BSC Rate) X COB Retention Rate) - (AUM X OGS Rate X COB FCA Rate) 

SINGLE - Non-BSC:
Year 1 column = (AUM X OGS Rate X COB Retention Rate) - (AUM X OGS Rate X COB FCA Rate) 

Then years 2 to 10 are calculated by applying a discount factor
Year  2 = Year 1 X  3 X DF
Year  3 = Year 1 X  5 X DF
Year  4 = Year 1 X  7 X DF
Year  5 = Year 1 X  9 X DF
Year  6 = Year 1 X 11 X DF
Year  7 = Year 1 X 13 X DF
Year  8 = Year 1 X 15 X DF
Year  9 = Year 1 X 17 X DF
Year 10 = Year 1 X 19 X DF

Wealth Points Total =	OngoingYr01 + OngoingYr02 + OngoingYr03 + OngoingYr04 + OngoingYr05 +
						OngoingYr06 + OngoingYr07 + OngoingYr08 + OngoingYr09 + OngoingYr10 +
						Initial

GI
--
See stored proc "owp_RecognitionGIPaymentshield".
 
Notes:
-----

1)	There is a BSC column on table owt_Recognition. However, BSC is already included in the ongoing
	years 1 - 10, so the BSC column does not need to be added in. In fact you will double count if 
	you attempt to do anything with it other than display it.

2)	Occasionally an investment case may receive two or more cheques which
	then go through Swift as two or more SINGLE investments on the SAME
	slice. Although the INITIAL VNB calculation will pro-rata correctly
	because it is based on the amount received, this scenario will cause
	ongoing VNB to be calculated on each of the payment records and so will 
	double count (or worse if there are more than two cheques received).
	Since de-coupling IC from ongoing i.e. they now have separate rows on
	table owt_Recognition, the issue of multiple cheques should no longer
	cause ongoing double counting.


This proc is called as follows:
	declare @rc int
	exec @rc = dbo.owp_RecognitionSwift 'Openwork', 'Recognition'
	select @rc

					
AMENDMENT HISTORY				
=================								

Date		Author		Description
----		------		-----------
26/04/2018	A Groves	Only include rows in the OGS lookups where the OngoingServiceFee > 0.0.
						Negative OGS rates are bad data and at the time of writing, there are
						39 of these.
27/04/2018	A Groves	Additional calculation and condition to handle the scenario where BSC applies
						but the OGS Rate is less than the BSC rate. Previously, this caused the
						total ongoing to be zero. However, there are two components to ongoing VNB 
						points, the BSC share and the non-BSC share. So the BSC share (which takes 
						100% when the OGS rate is less than 0.12%) should still yield ongoing points.
27/04/2018	A Groves	Single ongoing Yr01 corrected by applying outer brackets before signing the result.
03/05/2018	A Groves	Added update of column "msit_OpenworkAdviserListing.VNB_Points".
18/05/2018	A Groves	Changed mortgage calculation to use e.AMOUNT_REC instead of pt.CommInitialAmount
						as Marcus Cossey wanted the actual amount received to be used for the DA.
04/06/2018	A Groves	1) In the REGULAR section of column "OngoingYr01", the condition for cs.FrequencyCode <> 6
							was added to ensure the code differentiates to the SINGLE section.
						2) Exclude MBF from the OpenAccess table (msit_OpenworkAdviserListing) as this
							is shown on the MBF download and would otherwise incur MBF double counting.
05/06/2018	A Groves	1) Marcus Cossey advised that investments should get ongoing for years 1 to 6 and
							pensions for years 1 to 10. Previously, both lines of business got years 1 to 10.
						2) Marcus Cossey asked for split payments (i.e. where multiple cheques are processed
							for a SINGLE investment) to only claculate ongoing VNB on the oldest payment. 
11/06/2018	A Groves	1) PSD processed a protection clawback statement as fee type initial. These clawbacks
							all generated +ve instead of -ve VNB points. A tweak was added to ensure that the 
							absolute value of AMOUNT_REC is used to ensure the VNB is correctly signed. 
						2) Another unknown business rule has surfaced: Previously, only initial, clawbacks and
							adjustments on slices created new from 2017 were included. This rule only applies
							to initial. Clawbacks and adjustments can belong to a slice created at any point
							in the past. However, note that the payment (irrespective of whether it is +ve or 
							-ve), must not pre-date 2017.
13/06/2018	A Groves	Marcus asked for SellerCode and PaymentMatchedDate to be added so he need only use 
							the one table for both the adviser and enterprise leagues. PayBasisCode and 
							PayBasisDesc were also added at the same time as these are used in the calculations.
*************************************************************************************************************/

CREATE PROCEDURE [dbo].[owp_RecognitionSwiftONGOING_Backup20180630AG]
	@Client		varchar(50),
	@Module		Varchar(50)

AS

set nocount on

declare		@PhaseStart				varchar(50),
			@PhaseEnd				varchar(50),
			@PhaseError				varchar(50),
			@PhaseLog				varchar(50),
			@ProcName				varchar(100),
			@ProcessMessage			varchar(100),
			@RowCount				int,
			@OALRowCount			int,
			@ErrMsg					nvarchar(4000),
			@ErrMsgBrief			nvarchar(100),
			@ErrNum					int,
			@ErrSev					int,
			@ErrLine				int,
			@ErrState				int,
			@DateLastUpdated		datetime,
			@OwlManager2Code		nvarchar(10)
			
/****************************************************************************

	Set initial parameters																
																		
****************************************************************************/

set @ProcName			= object_name(@@procid)
set @PhaseStart			= 'START'
set @PhaseEnd			= 'END'
set @PhaseError			= 'ERROR'
set @PhaseLog			= 'LOG'
set @ErrNum				= 0	
set @DateLastUpdated	= getdate()

set @OwlManager2Code = (select cde.Code from msit_MIWarehouseCodesAndDescriptions cde
			where cde.ColumnName = 'Manager2Code' and cde.Description = 'Owl Financial')

-- We want this logging irrespective of whether or not there is a rollback
exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseStart, @ProcName, null, @Module, @Client

/****************************************************************************

	Populate the table																
																		
****************************************************************************/

SET XACT_ABORT ON	-- Needed if XACT_STATE() function is used.

BEGIN TRY

	/****************************************************************************

		Link OWS data to Swift data to enable the ongoing servicng (OGS) rate
		to be looked up.
																		
	****************************************************************************/
	
	select	distinct s.PersonID, swp.Client_Num, p.InternalProductID, swp.ProductCode 
	into	#SwiftOWSClientLink
	from	sa_ows_Sale s
			inner join sa_ows_Policies p on p.SaleID = s.SaleID
			inner join mstt_Policies swp on swp.PolicyRef = p.PolicyID
	where	s.DateSubmitted is not null
	--and		s.PersonID = 146030

	select @RowCount = @@rowcount
	set @ProcessMessage = '#SwiftOWSClientLink = ' + convert(nvarchar(10), @RowCount)
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseLog, @ProcessMessage, null, @Module, @Client

	-- The OGS rate is stored for the client/product combination
	select	link.Client_Num, link.ProductCode, max(ogs.OngoingServiceFee) as OngoingServiceFee
	into	#OGSLookUp
	from	#SwiftOWSClientLink link 
			inner join mstt_ProductHierarchy ph on ph.ProductCode = link.ProductCode
			inner join Submission.sa_ows_SubmittedProductCurrentOngoingServiceFee ogs
							on ogs.PersonID = link.PersonID
							and ogs.InternalProductID = (case when ph.RDRType = 'ONPLAT' 
															then -2 
															else link.InternalProductID 
														 end)
	where	ogs.OngoingServiceFee > 0.0							--AG 26/04/2018
	group	by 	link.Client_Num, link.ProductCode

	select @RowCount = @@rowcount
	set @ProcessMessage = '#OGSLookUp = ' + convert(nvarchar(10), @RowCount)
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseLog, @ProcessMessage, null, @Module, @Client

	create index idx_OGSLookUp on #OGSLookUp (Client_num, ProductCode)

	--This is an additional catch for OGS by storing the client's highest OGS
	--rate against their client number. This lookup will apply if the first
	--look up fails. The first lookup can fail, for example, if the case was 
	--not submitted on OWS i.e. the CaseID has a "17" prefix. 
	select	Client_Num, MAX(OngoingServiceFee) as OngoingServiceFee
	into	#OGSLookUpClient
	from	#OGSLookUp
	group	by Client_Num

	select @RowCount = @@rowcount
	set @ProcessMessage = '#OGSLookUpClient = ' + convert(nvarchar(10), @RowCount)
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseLog, @ProcessMessage, null, @Module, @Client
	
	create index idx_OGSLookUpClient on #OGSLookUpClient (Client_num)

	/****************************************************************************

		Calculate VNB and populate the temporary table with the results
		
		Note that there are oddities like LV protection payments which always
		come in pairs with one large and one much smaller amount (e.g. TransactionID 
		= 6684787.) The system treats both payments in the pair as first payments 
		and the (projected) DA associated with both is the same (because it's on 
		the policy transaction). 
		
		There is also a requirement to front-load VNB points on accrual and level
		payments. This means calculate the VNB for the full amount of the DA and 
		put it on the first payment record and then on all subsequent accrual and 
		level payments, set the VNB to zero.
		
		Thus two different sources of DA are used depending on whether we need the
		full DA amount for accruals and level or the actual amount received for all
		other scenarios including the LV split payment scenario. The two sources are:
		
		mstt_PolicyTransactions.CommInitialAmount - Full (projected) DA amount
		
		mstt_Expectation.AMOUNT_REC - The DA actually received. This handles the
										LV scenario whereby the AMOUNT_REC is 
										proportioned across the two payments received.   
																		
	****************************************************************************/

	select	top 0 
			*, 
			convert(int,NULL) as CommissionYear
	into	#AG_owt_Recognition_SEPARATE_ONGOING
	from	AG_owt_Recognition_SEPARATE_ONGOING

	/****************************************************************************

		Phase 1 - Process all but regular accrual cases with clawbacks/adjustments
		Accruals are front loaded unless their latest payment is a clawback/adjudtment
		in which case they accrue VNB points on a per payment basis and so these
		are dealt with in Phases 2 and 3.
																		
	****************************************************************************/

	insert into #AG_owt_Recognition_SEPARATE_ONGOING
	(
		SourceID,
		CaseID,
		TransactionID,
		Policy,
		ProductCode,
		BusinessCode,
		SellerCode,						--AG 13/06/2018
		PointsTotal,
		BSC,
		MBF,
		Initial,
		OngoingTotal,
		OngoingYr01,
		OngoingYr02,
		OngoingYr03,
		OngoingYr04,
		OngoingYr05,
		OngoingYr06,
		OngoingYr07,
		OngoingYr08,
		OngoingYr09,
		OngoingYr10,
		FCARate,
		RetentionRate,
		RetentionRateBroker,
		OngoingServicingRate,
		OngoingServicingSource,
		DA,
		AmountReceived,
		Premium,
		AgentSplit,
		CommissionType,
		CommissionTypeDesc,
		PayBasisCode,					--AG 13/06/2018
		PayBasisDesc,					--AG 13/06/2018
		PaymentMatchedDate,				--AG 13/06/2018
		Month,
		FrequencyCode,
		FrequencyDesc,
		ReassignedProductGroupCode,		--AG 05/06/2018
		ReassignedProductGroupName,		--AG 05/06/2018
		RecognitionType,
		CalculationType,
		Source,
		DateInserted,
		DateLastUpdated,
		CommissionYear
	)
	select	cs.PendingPaymentID as SourceID,
			cs.CaseID,
			cs.TransactionID,
			cs.ExtPolicyNumber as Policy,
			cs.ProductCode,
			cs.BusinessCode,
			cs.AgentCode as SellerCode,				--AG 13/06/2018
			0.0 as PointsTotal,
			0.0 as BSC,
			case 
				when mbf.MortgageFeeID is not null and cs.INIssued <> 0 then (((mbf.AdviceFeeAmount)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * MRbkr.FACTOR) - ((mbf.AdviceFeeAmount)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * Mfca.FACTOR)) --Note that mbf.AdviceFeeAmount is signed correctly - so no coding for signing is needed here
				else 0.0
			end as MBF,
			case 
				--When the adviser has changed, the AgentSplit can become zero in which case the ELITE points should be zero.
				when cs.AgentSplit = 0 then 0
				
				--WEALTH CALCULATION START
				--Indemnity payments or SINGLEs or IC Clawbacks or IC adjustments Start
				when (ph.ProductCategoryCode = 1 or pcc.KeyValue2 = '1') and (cs.FrequencyCode = 6 or cs.PayBasisCode in ('T') or cs.CommissionType in (2,17)) and cs.commissiontype in (1,2,17) and cs.INIssued <> 0 then (((e.AMOUNT_REC)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * Crate.FACTOR) - ((e.AMOUNT_REC)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * Cfca.FACTOR)) * case when cs.INIssued < 0 then -1 else 1 end
				--Indemnity payments or SINGLEs or IC Clawbacks or IC adjustments End
				--Accruals & Level Start
				when (ph.ProductCategoryCode = 1 or pcc.KeyValue2 = '1') and cs.INIssued <> 0 then (((pt.CommInitialAmount)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * Crate.FACTOR) - ((pt.CommInitialAmount)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * Cfca.FACTOR)) * case when cs.INIssued < 0 then -1 else 1 end
				--Accruals & Level End
				--WEALTH CALCULATION END
				
				--MORTGAGE CALCULATION START
				--Note: The MBF component has its own table column
				--Only 1 payment for mortgages
				when ph.ProductGroupCode = 3 and cs.INIssued <> 0 then (((e.AMOUNT_REC)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * MRproc.FACTOR) - ((e.AMOUNT_REC)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * Mfca.FACTOR)) * case when cs.INIssued < 0 then -1 else 1 end	--AG 18/05/2018
				--MORTGAGE CALCULATION END
				
				--PROTECTION CALCULATION START
				--Indemnity payments or SINGLEs or IC Clawbacks or IC adjustments Start
				when ph.ProductGroupCode = 6 and (cs.FrequencyCode = 6 or cs.PayBasisCode in ('T') or cs.CommissionType in (2,17)) and cs.commissiontype in (1,2,17) and cs.INIssued <> 0 then ((abs(e.AMOUNT_REC)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * Prate.FACTOR) - (abs(e.AMOUNT_REC)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * Pfca.FACTOR)) * case when cs.INIssued < 0 then -1 else 1 end	--AG 11/06/2018 (1)
				--Indemnity payments or SINGLEs or IC Clawbacks or IC adjustments End
				--Accruals & Level Start
				when ph.ProductGroupCode = 6 and cs.INIssued <> 0 then (((pt.CommInitialAmount)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * Prate.FACTOR) - ((pt.CommInitialAmount)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * Pfca.FACTOR)) * case when cs.INIssued < 0 then -1 else 1 end
				--Accruals & Level End
				--PROTECTION CALCULATION END

				else 0.0

			end as Initial,
			0.0 as OngoingTotal,
			0.0 as OngoingYr01,
			0.0 as OngoingYr02,
			0.0 as OngoingYr03,
			0.0 as OngoingYr04,
			0.0 as OngoingYr05,
			0.0 as OngoingYr06,
			0.0 as OngoingYr07,
			0.0 as OngoingYr08,
			0.0 as OngoingYr09,
			0.0 as OngoingYr10,
			case 
				when (ph.ProductCategoryCode = 1 or pcc.KeyValue2 = '1') then Cfca.FACTOR*100.0		--COB
				when ph.ProductGroupCode = 3 then Mfca.FACTOR*100.0		--MORT
				when ph.ProductGroupCode = 6 then Pfca.FACTOR*100.0		--PROT
				else 0.0
			end as FCARate,
			case 
				when (ph.ProductCategoryCode = 1 or pcc.KeyValue2 = '1') then Crate.FACTOR*100.0	--COB
				when ph.ProductGroupCode = 3 then MRproc.FACTOR*100.0	--MORT
				when ph.ProductGroupCode = 6 then Prate.FACTOR*100.0	--PROT
				else 0.0
			end as RetentionRate,
			case 
				when mbf.MortgageFeeID is not null then  MRbkr.FACTOR*100.0	
				else 0.0
			end as RetentionRateBroker,
			null as OngoingServicingRate,
			null as OngoingServicingSource,
			pt.CommInitialAmount as DA,
			e.AMOUNT_REC as AmountReceived,
			cs.Premium,
			cs.AgentSplit,
			cs.CommissionType,
			left(cs.StandingOrderDesc,50) as CommissionTypeDesc,
			cs.PayBasisCode,							--AG 13/06/2018
			cs.PayBasisDesc,							--AG 13/06/2018
			cs.CreateDate as PaymentMatchedDate,		--AG 13/06/2018
			cs.Month,
			cs.FrequencyCode,
			cs.FrequencyDesc,
			pg.ProductGroupCode as ReassignedProductGroupCode,	--Force the re-assigned products...		AG 05/06/2018
			pg.ProductGroupName as ReassignedProductGroupName,	--...to be processed as investments		AG 05/06/2018
			'VNB-PHASE-1' as RecognitionType,
			case 
				when (ph.ProductCategoryCode = 1 or pcc.KeyValue2 = '1') then 'WEALTH-INITIAL'
				when ph.ProductGroupCode = 3 then 'MORTGAGE'
				when ph.ProductGroupCode = 6 then 'PROTECTION'
				else null
			end as CalculationType,
			'Openwork 2006' as Source,
			@DateLastUpdated as DateInserted,
			@DateLastUpdated as DateLastUpdated,
			csp.year as CommissionYear
	--select count(*)
	from	msit_CommissionStatement cs
/*			inner join (select	distinct PKID
						from	owt_TransformationMovements tm 
						where	tm.DriverTableName = 'sa_swift_S_AGMFIL'
						and		tm.CommissionStatement = 'Y') tm on tm.PKID = cs.PendingPaymentID
*/			inner join mstt_Agents ag on ag.Code = cs.BusinessCode
			inner join mstt_PolicyTransactions pt on pt.ID = cs.TransactionID
			inner join mstt_Policies p on p.POL_NUM = pt.PolicyID
			inner join msit_CommissionStatementPeriods VNBStart on convert(date,pt.CreateDateTime) between VNBStart.PeriodStartDate and VNBStart.PeriodEndDate
			inner join msit_Commissionstatementperiods csp on csp.month = cs.month
			inner join mstt_ProductHierarchy ph on ph.productcode = cs.productcode
			inner join mstt_Expectation e on e.ID = cs.ExpectationID
			left join dbo.owt_MortgageBrokerFees mbf on mbf.PendingPaymentID = cs.PendingPaymentID and mbf.AdviceFeeCharged = 'Yes'
			left join owt_SelectionControl SC
						on SC.Process = 'ElitePoints' 
						and SC.KeyType = 'NSCPotCode' 
						and cs.CreateDate between SC.EffectiveStartDate and SC.EffectiveEndDate
			left join mstt_Commissions BSCpot
						on BSCpot.TransactionID = cs.TransactionID 
						and BSCpot.Agent_Code = sc.KeyValue
						and BSCpot.CommissionType = 10
			left join owt_SelectionControl SFMPC						
						on SFMPC.Process = 'ElitePoints' 
						and SFMPC.KeyType = 'ServicingFeeMarginPotCode' 
						and cs.CreateDate between SFMPC.EffectiveStartDate and SFMPC.EffectiveEndDate
			left join mstt_Commissions SFMpot							
						on SFMpot.TransactionID = cs.TransactionID 
						and SFMpot.Agent_Code = SFMPC.KeyValue
						and SFMpot.CommissionType = 10	
			left join owt_SelectionControl pcc 
						on pcc.Process = 'ElitePoints'
						and pcc.KeyType = 'ProductCategoryCode'
						and pcc.KeyValue = cs.ProductCode	
						and cs.CreateDate between pcc.EffectiveStartDate and pcc.EffectiveEndDate
			left join owt_SelectionControl ogsdflt 
						on ogsdflt.Process = 'ElitePoints'
						and ogsdflt.KeyType = 'DefaultOngoingServicingRate'
						and ogsdflt.SelectionType = 'VNB'
						and ogsdflt.KeyValue = case when ph.RDRType = 'ONPLAT' then 'ONPLAT' else 'OFPLAT' end
						and cs.CreateDate between ogsdflt.EffectiveStartDate and ogsdflt.EffectiveEndDate
			left join mstt_CodeProductGroup pg on pg.ProductGroupCode = case when pcc.KeyValue2 = '1' then 2 else ph.ProductGroupCode end
			left join owt_EliteFactors Cfca on Cfca.FeeType = 'VNB' and Cfca.category = 'COB-FCA-RATE' and csp.year between Cfca.StartYear and Cfca.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors Crate on Crate.FeeType = 'VNB' and Crate.category = 'COB-RETENTION-RATE' and csp.year between Crate.StartYear and Crate.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors Mfca on Mfca.FeeType = 'VNB' and Mfca.category = 'MORT-FCA-RATE' and csp.year between Mfca.StartYear and Mfca.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors MRproc on MRproc.FeeType = 'VNB' and MRproc.category = 'MORT-RETENTION-RATE-PROC' and csp.year between MRproc.StartYear and MRproc.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors MRbkr on MRbkr.FeeType = 'VNB' and MRbkr.category = 'MORT-RETENTION-RATE-BROKER' and csp.year between MRbkr.StartYear and MRbkr.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors Pfca on Pfca.FeeType = 'VNB' and Pfca.category = 'PROT-FCA-RATE' and csp.year between Pfca.StartYear and Pfca.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors Prate on Prate.FeeType = 'VNB' and Prate.category = 'PROT-RETENTION-RATE' and csp.year between Prate.StartYear and Prate.EndYear 
			left join msit_CommissionStatement csadj 
						on csadj.TransactionID = cs.TransactionID 
						and csadj.AgentCode = cs.AgentCode 
						and csadj.CommissionType in (2,17)
						and	csadj.PayBasisCode in ('F')				--Accrual
						and	csadj.FrequencyCode <> 6				--Regular 
	where	cs.ReportingClassCode = 1
	and		ag.Manager2Code <> @OwlManager2Code		--Exclude Owl
	and		cs.INIssued <> 0
	and		csp.Year >= 2017						--Ensure in-scope payments are consistent with VNB start
	and		((VNBStart.Year >= 2017 and cs.CommissionType = 1 and e.AMOUNT_REC >= 0.01)		--VNB to start from new slices in 2017 for +ve payments but...			AG 11/06/2018 (2)
			or (cs.CommissionType in (2,17) or e.AMOUNT_REC <= -0.01))						--...for -ve payments, the slice can start from any date in the past	AG 11/06/2018 (2)
	and		csadj.ID is null						--Deal with accrual regular clawbacks/adjustments later

	select @RowCount = @@rowcount
	set @ProcessMessage = '#owt_Recognition (ph1 - no accr adj) = ' + convert(nvarchar(10), @RowCount)
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseLog, @ProcessMessage, null, @Module, @Client

	/****************************************************************************

		Now deal with accrual clawbacks and adjustments
																		
	****************************************************************************/

	--drop table #msit_CommissionStatementSUMMARY

	--Find transactions with clawbacks/adj on them
	select	cs.TransactionID,
			cs.AgentCode,
			Min(case when cs.CommissionType = 1 then cs.PendingPaymentID else null end) as MinInitialPendingPaymentID,
			MAX(case when cs.CommissionType = 1 then cs.PendingPaymentID else null end) as MaxInitialPendingPaymentID,
			MAX(case when cs.CommissionType in (2,17) then cs.PendingPaymentID else null end) as MaxAdjPendingPaymentID,
			null as MinInitialAfterAdjPendingPaymentID
	into	#msit_CommissionStatementSUMMARY
	from	msit_CommissionStatement cs
			inner join mstt_Agents ag on ag.Code = cs.BusinessCode
			inner join mstt_PolicyTransactions pt on pt.ID = cs.TransactionID
			inner join mstt_Policies p on p.POL_NUM = pt.PolicyID
			inner join msit_CommissionStatementPeriods VNBStart on convert(date,pt.CreateDateTime) between VNBStart.PeriodStartDate and VNBStart.PeriodEndDate
			inner join msit_Commissionstatementperiods csp on csp.month = cs.month
			inner join mstt_Expectation e on e.ID = cs.ExpectationID
			left join msit_CommissionStatement csadj 
						on csadj.TransactionID = cs.TransactionID 
						and csadj.AgentCode = cs.AgentCode 
						and csadj.CommissionType in (2,17)
						and	csadj.PayBasisCode in ('F')				--Accrual
						and	csadj.FrequencyCode <> 6				--Regular 
	where	cs.ReportingClassCode = 1
	and		cs.CommissionType in (1,2,17)			--We want all the initial payment types (i.e. not trail (ongoing))
	and		ag.Manager2Code <> @OwlManager2Code		--Exclude Owl
	and		csp.Year >= 2017						--Ensure in-scope payments are consistent with VNB start
	and		VNBStart.Year >= 2017 
	and		abs(e.AMOUNT_REC) >= 0.01	
	and		csadj.ID is not null					--select regular accrual transactions with clawbacks/adjustments
	--and cs.TransactionID in (5613333,6296827)
	group by	cs.TransactionID,
				cs.AgentCode

	select @RowCount = @@rowcount
	set @ProcessMessage = '#msit_CommissionStatementSUMMARY (accr adj txns) = ' + convert(nvarchar(10), @RowCount)
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseLog, @ProcessMessage, null, @Module, @Client

	--Get first initial payment after last clawback/adj
	update css
		set MinInitialAfterAdjPendingPaymentID = summ.MinPendingPaymentID 
	from  #msit_CommissionStatementSUMMARY css
			inner join  (
						select cssinner.TransactionID, cssinner.AgentCode, min(cs.PendingPaymentID) as MinPendingPaymentID
						from #msit_CommissionStatementSUMMARY cssinner
								inner join msit_CommissionStatement cs
											on cs.TransactionID = cssinner.TransactionID
											and cs.AgentCode = cssinner.AgentCode
						where cs.PendingPaymentID > cssinner.MaxAdjPendingPaymentID
						group by cssinner.TransactionID, cssinner.AgentCode
						) summ on  summ.TransactionID = css.TransactionID
							   and summ.AgentCode = css.AgentCode

	select @RowCount = @@rowcount
	set @ProcessMessage = '#msit_CommissionStatementSUMMARY (1st IC after adj) = ' + convert(nvarchar(10), @RowCount)
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseLog, @ProcessMessage, null, @Module, @Client

	/****************************************************************************

		Phase 2 - This phase deals with regular accrual cases where there is at 
		least one clawback/adjustment. In this scenario the VNB is changed from 
		front loaded to a per payment basis.
																		
	****************************************************************************/

	insert into #AG_owt_Recognition_SEPARATE_ONGOING
	(
		SourceID,
		CaseID,
		TransactionID,
		Policy,
		ProductCode,
		BusinessCode,
		SellerCode,						
		PointsTotal,
		BSC,
		MBF,
		Initial,
		OngoingTotal,
		OngoingYr01,
		OngoingYr02,
		OngoingYr03,
		OngoingYr04,
		OngoingYr05,
		OngoingYr06,
		OngoingYr07,
		OngoingYr08,
		OngoingYr09,
		OngoingYr10,
		FCARate,
		RetentionRate,
		RetentionRateBroker,
		OngoingServicingRate,
		OngoingServicingSource,
		DA,
		AmountReceived,
		Premium,
		AgentSplit,
		CommissionType,
		CommissionTypeDesc,
		PayBasisCode,					
		PayBasisDesc,					
		PaymentMatchedDate,				
		Month,
		FrequencyCode,
		FrequencyDesc,
		ReassignedProductGroupCode,		
		ReassignedProductGroupName,		
		RecognitionType,
		CalculationType,
		Source,
		DateInserted,
		DateLastUpdated,
		CommissionYear
	)
	select	cs.PendingPaymentID as SourceID,
			cs.CaseID,
			cs.TransactionID,
			cs.ExtPolicyNumber as Policy,
			cs.ProductCode,
			cs.BusinessCode,
			cs.AgentCode as SellerCode,				
			0.0 as PointsTotal,
			0.0 as BSC,
			case 
				when mbf.MortgageFeeID is not null and cs.INIssued <> 0 then (((mbf.AdviceFeeAmount)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * MRbkr.FACTOR) - ((mbf.AdviceFeeAmount)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * Mfca.FACTOR)) --Note that mbf.AdviceFeeAmount is signed correctly - so no coding for signing is needed here
				else 0.0
			end as MBF,
			case 
				--When the adviser has changed, the AgentSplit can become zero in which case the ELITE points should be zero.
				when cs.AgentSplit = 0 then 0
				
				--WEALTH CALCULATION START
				--Indemnity payments or SINGLEs or IC Clawbacks or IC adjustments Start
				--THIS SCENARIO DOESN'T OCCUR IN PHASE 2
				--Indemnity payments or SINGLEs or IC Clawbacks or IC adjustments End
				--Accruals & Level Start
				when (ph.ProductCategoryCode = 1 or pcc.KeyValue2 = '1') then (((e.AMOUNT_REC)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * Crate.FACTOR) - ((e.AMOUNT_REC)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * Cfca.FACTOR)) * case when cs.CommissionType in (2,17) then -1 else 1 end
				--Accruals & Level End
				--WEALTH CALCULATION END
				
				--MORTGAGE CALCULATION START
				--Note: The MBF component has its own table column
				--Only 1 payment for mortgages
				when ph.ProductGroupCode = 3 then (((e.AMOUNT_REC)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * MRproc.FACTOR) - ((e.AMOUNT_REC)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * Mfca.FACTOR)) * case when cs.CommissionType in (2,17) then -1 else 1 end	
				--MORTGAGE CALCULATION END
				
				--PROTECTION CALCULATION START
				--Indemnity payments or SINGLEs or IC Clawbacks or IC adjustments Start
				--THIS SCENARIO DOESN'T OCCUR IN PHASE 2
				--Indemnity payments or SINGLEs or IC Clawbacks or IC adjustments End
				--Accruals & Level Start
				when ph.ProductGroupCode = 6 then (((e.AMOUNT_REC)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * Prate.FACTOR) - ((e.AMOUNT_REC)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * Pfca.FACTOR)) * case when cs.CommissionType in (2,17) then -1 else 1 end
				--Accruals & Level End
				--PROTECTION CALCULATION END

				else 0.0

			end as Initial,
			0.0 as OngoingTotal,
			0.0 as OngoingYr01,
			0.0 as OngoingYr02,
			0.0 as OngoingYr03,
			0.0 as OngoingYr04,
			0.0 as OngoingYr05,
			0.0 as OngoingYr06,
			0.0 as OngoingYr07,
			0.0 as OngoingYr08,
			0.0 as OngoingYr09,
			0.0 as OngoingYr10,
			case 
				when (ph.ProductCategoryCode = 1 or pcc.KeyValue2 = '1') then Cfca.FACTOR*100.0		--COB
				when ph.ProductGroupCode = 3 then Mfca.FACTOR*100.0		--MORT
				when ph.ProductGroupCode = 6 then Pfca.FACTOR*100.0		--PROT
				else 0.0
			end as FCARate,
			case 
				when (ph.ProductCategoryCode = 1 or pcc.KeyValue2 = '1') then Crate.FACTOR*100.0	--COB
				when ph.ProductGroupCode = 3 then MRproc.FACTOR*100.0	--MORT
				when ph.ProductGroupCode = 6 then Prate.FACTOR*100.0	--PROT
				else 0.0
			end as RetentionRate,
			case 
				when mbf.MortgageFeeID is not null then  MRbkr.FACTOR*100.0	
				else 0.0
			end as RetentionRateBroker,
			null as OngoingServicingRate,
			null as OngoingServicingSource,
			pt.CommInitialAmount as DA,
			e.AMOUNT_REC as AmountReceived,
			cs.Premium,
			cs.AgentSplit,
			cs.CommissionType,
			left(cs.StandingOrderDesc,50) as CommissionTypeDesc,
			cs.PayBasisCode,							
			cs.PayBasisDesc,							
			cs.CreateDate as PaymentMatchedDate,		
			cs.Month,
			cs.FrequencyCode,
			cs.FrequencyDesc,
			pg.ProductGroupCode as ReassignedProductGroupCode,	--Force the re-assigned products...		
			pg.ProductGroupName as ReassignedProductGroupName,	--...to be processed as investments		
			'VNB-PHASE-2' as RecognitionType,
			case 
				when (ph.ProductCategoryCode = 1 or pcc.KeyValue2 = '1') then 'WEALTH-INITIAL'
				when ph.ProductGroupCode = 3 then 'MORTGAGE'
				when ph.ProductGroupCode = 6 then 'PROTECTION'
				else null
			end as CalculationType,
			'Openwork 2006' as Source,
			@DateLastUpdated as DateInserted,
			@DateLastUpdated as DateLastUpdated,
			csp.year as CommissionYear
	from	#msit_CommissionStatementSUMMARY css
			inner join msit_CommissionStatement cs
						on cs.TransactionID = css.TransactionID
						and cs.AgentCode = css.AgentCode
			inner join mstt_Agents ag on ag.Code = cs.BusinessCode
			inner join mstt_PolicyTransactions pt on pt.ID = cs.TransactionID
			inner join mstt_Policies p on p.POL_NUM = pt.PolicyID
			inner join msit_CommissionStatementPeriods VNBStart on convert(date,pt.CreateDateTime) between VNBStart.PeriodStartDate and VNBStart.PeriodEndDate
			inner join msit_Commissionstatementperiods csp on csp.month = cs.month
			inner join mstt_ProductHierarchy ph on ph.productcode = cs.productcode
			inner join mstt_Expectation e on e.ID = cs.ExpectationID
			left join dbo.owt_MortgageBrokerFees mbf on mbf.PendingPaymentID = cs.PendingPaymentID and mbf.AdviceFeeCharged = 'Yes'
			left join owt_SelectionControl SC
						on SC.Process = 'ElitePoints' 
						and SC.KeyType = 'NSCPotCode' 
						and cs.CreateDate between SC.EffectiveStartDate and SC.EffectiveEndDate
			left join mstt_Commissions BSCpot
						on BSCpot.TransactionID = cs.TransactionID 
						and BSCpot.Agent_Code = sc.KeyValue
						and BSCpot.CommissionType = 10
			left join owt_SelectionControl SFMPC						
						on SFMPC.Process = 'ElitePoints' 
						and SFMPC.KeyType = 'ServicingFeeMarginPotCode' 
						and cs.CreateDate between SFMPC.EffectiveStartDate and SFMPC.EffectiveEndDate
			left join mstt_Commissions SFMpot							
						on SFMpot.TransactionID = cs.TransactionID 
						and SFMpot.Agent_Code = SFMPC.KeyValue
						and SFMpot.CommissionType = 10	
			left join owt_SelectionControl pcc 
						on pcc.Process = 'ElitePoints'
						and pcc.KeyType = 'ProductCategoryCode'
						and pcc.KeyValue = cs.ProductCode	
						and cs.CreateDate between pcc.EffectiveStartDate and pcc.EffectiveEndDate
			left join owt_SelectionControl ogsdflt 
						on ogsdflt.Process = 'ElitePoints'
						and ogsdflt.KeyType = 'DefaultOngoingServicingRate'
						and ogsdflt.SelectionType = 'VNB'
						and ogsdflt.KeyValue = case when ph.RDRType = 'ONPLAT' then 'ONPLAT' else 'OFPLAT' end
						and cs.CreateDate between ogsdflt.EffectiveStartDate and ogsdflt.EffectiveEndDate
			left join mstt_CodeProductGroup pg on pg.ProductGroupCode = case when pcc.KeyValue2 = '1' then 2 else ph.ProductGroupCode end
			left join owt_EliteFactors Cfca on Cfca.FeeType = 'VNB' and Cfca.category = 'COB-FCA-RATE' and csp.year between Cfca.StartYear and Cfca.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors Crate on Crate.FeeType = 'VNB' and Crate.category = 'COB-RETENTION-RATE' and csp.year between Crate.StartYear and Crate.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors Mfca on Mfca.FeeType = 'VNB' and Mfca.category = 'MORT-FCA-RATE' and csp.year between Mfca.StartYear and Mfca.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors MRproc on MRproc.FeeType = 'VNB' and MRproc.category = 'MORT-RETENTION-RATE-PROC' and csp.year between MRproc.StartYear and MRproc.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors MRbkr on MRbkr.FeeType = 'VNB' and MRbkr.category = 'MORT-RETENTION-RATE-BROKER' and csp.year between MRbkr.StartYear and MRbkr.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors Pfca on Pfca.FeeType = 'VNB' and Pfca.category = 'PROT-FCA-RATE' and csp.year between Pfca.StartYear and Pfca.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors Prate on Prate.FeeType = 'VNB' and Prate.category = 'PROT-RETENTION-RATE' and csp.year between Prate.StartYear and Prate.EndYear 
	where	cs.ReportingClassCode = 1
	and		cs.CommissionType in (1,2,17)			--We want all the initial payment types (i.e. not trail (ongoing))
	and		ag.Manager2Code <> @OwlManager2Code		--Exclude Owl

	select @RowCount = @@rowcount
	set @ProcessMessage = '#owt_Recognition (ph2 - accr adj) = ' + convert(nvarchar(10), @RowCount)
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseLog, @ProcessMessage, null, @Module, @Client

	/****************************************************************************

		Phase 3
		1) Add up the +ves and -ves prior to the NEW front loaded amount and
			net them off on the first +ve following the last -ve
		2) Now set all the +ves following the one updated in (1) to zero.
																
	****************************************************************************/

	update r
		set RecognitionType	= case when r.SourceID >= css.MinInitialAfterAdjPendingPaymentID 
								then 'VNB-PHASE-3'
								else r.RecognitionType
							  end,
			Initial = case  when r.SourceID = css.MinInitialAfterAdjPendingPaymentID 
								then (((r.DA)*(r.AgentSplit/100) * (r.RetentionRate/100.0)) - ((r.DA)*(r.AgentSplit/100) * (r.FCARate/100))) - derived.SumInitial
							when r.SourceID > css.MinInitialAfterAdjPendingPaymentID 
								then 0.0
							else r.Initial
					  end,
			DateLastUpdated = @DateLastUpdated
	from	#msit_CommissionStatementSUMMARY css
			inner join #AG_owt_Recognition_SEPARATE_ONGOING r
						on r.TransactionID = css.TransactionID
						and r.SellerCode = css.AgentCode
			inner join (select	r.TransactionID, r.SellerCode, SUM(Initial) as SumInitial
						from	#msit_CommissionStatementSUMMARY s
								inner join #AG_owt_Recognition_SEPARATE_ONGOING r 
											on r.TransactionID = s.TransactionID
											and r.SellerCode = s.AgentCode
						where	r.SourceID <= s.MaxAdjPendingPaymentID
						group	by r.TransactionID, r.SellerCode
						) derived 
							on  derived.TransactionID = r.TransactionID
							and	derived.SellerCode = r.SellerCode 
	where	isnull(css.MaxInitialPendingPaymentID,0) > isnull(css.MaxAdjPendingPaymentID,0)-- An initial payment follows the clawback, so time to revert back to front loading
	--and		r.SourceID = css.MinInitialAfterAdjPendingPaymentID
	--and		css.TransactionID = 5696809

	select @RowCount = @@rowcount
	set @ProcessMessage = '#owt_Recognition (ph3 - accr adj) = ' + convert(nvarchar(10), @RowCount)
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseLog, @ProcessMessage, null, @Module, @Client

	/****************************************************************************

		Now do the ongoing.
		
		Grab the oldest ogoing payment for the transaction and adviser pair and
		all the clawbacks and adjustments.
		
		Note: The Agent Split from the IC record is used because the ongoing (trail)
		splits are skewed by BSC and OGS margin.
																		
	****************************************************************************/

	--Find the oldest ongoing payment for each transaction (slice).
	select	cs.TransactionID, cs.AgentCode, cs.CommissionType, c.Agent_Perc as AgentSplit, min(cs.PendingPaymentID) as MinPendingPaymentID
	into	#msit_CommissionStatementONGOING
	from	msit_CommissionStatement cs
			inner join mstt_Commissions c
						on c.TransactionID = cs.TransactionID
						and c.Agent_Code = cs.AgentCode
						and c.CommissionType = 1
			inner join mstt_Agents ag on ag.Code = cs.BusinessCode
			inner join mstt_PolicyTransactions pt on pt.ID = cs.TransactionID
			inner join mstt_Policies p on p.POL_NUM = pt.PolicyID
			inner join msit_CommissionStatementPeriods VNBStart on convert(date,pt.CreateDateTime) between VNBStart.PeriodStartDate and VNBStart.PeriodEndDate
			inner join msit_Commissionstatementperiods csp on csp.month = cs.month
			inner join mstt_ProductHierarchy ph on ph.productcode = cs.productcode
			inner join mstt_Expectation e on e.ID = cs.ExpectationID
			left join owt_SelectionControl pcc 
						on pcc.Process = 'ElitePoints'
						and pcc.KeyType = 'ProductCategoryCode'
						and pcc.KeyValue = cs.ProductCode	
						and cs.CreateDate between pcc.EffectiveStartDate and pcc.EffectiveEndDate
	where	cs.ReportingClassCode = 1
	and		cs.CommissionType = 10								--10=Trail Fee
	and		cs.CommFeeType = 'Ongoing'
	and		(ph.ProductCategoryCode = 1 or pcc.KeyValue2 = '1')
	and		ag.Manager2Code <> @OwlManager2Code					--Exclude Owl
	and		csp.Year >= 2017									--Ensure in-scope payments are consistent with VNB start
	and		VNBStart.Year >= 2017								--VNB to start from new slices in 2017 for +ve payments
	and		abs(e.AMOUNT_REC) >= 0.01		
	and		((cs.FrequencyCode = 6 and cs.Premium > 1.00)		--Frequency=6->Single
			or (cs.FrequencyCode <> 6 and cs.Premium > 0.01))	--Frequency<>6->Regular
	group	by cs.TransactionID, cs.AgentCode, cs.CommissionType, c.Agent_Perc

	union
	
	--We need all ongoing adjustment and clawback payments i.e. NOT just the oldest 
	select	cs.TransactionID, cs.AgentCode, cs.CommissionType, c.Agent_Perc as AgentSplit, cs.PendingPaymentID as MinPendingPaymentID
	from	msit_CommissionStatement cs
			inner join mstt_Commissions c
						on c.TransactionID = cs.TransactionID
						and c.Agent_Code = cs.AgentCode
						and c.CommissionType = 1
			inner join mstt_Agents ag on ag.Code = cs.BusinessCode
			inner join mstt_PolicyTransactions pt on pt.ID = cs.TransactionID
			inner join mstt_Policies p on p.POL_NUM = pt.PolicyID
			inner join msit_CommissionStatementPeriods VNBStart on convert(date,pt.CreateDateTime) between VNBStart.PeriodStartDate and VNBStart.PeriodEndDate
			inner join msit_Commissionstatementperiods csp on csp.month = cs.month
			inner join mstt_ProductHierarchy ph on ph.productcode = cs.productcode
			inner join mstt_Expectation e on e.ID = cs.ExpectationID
			left join owt_SelectionControl pcc 
						on pcc.Process = 'ElitePoints'
						and pcc.KeyType = 'ProductCategoryCode'
						and pcc.KeyValue = cs.ProductCode	
						and cs.CreateDate between pcc.EffectiveStartDate and pcc.EffectiveEndDate
	where	cs.ReportingClassCode = 1
	and		cs.CommissionType in (16,19)						--16=Clawback Trail;19=Adjustment Trail
	and		cs.CommFeeType = 'Ongoing'
	and		(ph.ProductCategoryCode = 1 or pcc.KeyValue2 = '1')
	and		ag.Manager2Code <> @OwlManager2Code					--Exclude Owl
	and		csp.Year >= 2017									--We don't care when the transaction started but the payment must be from 2017
	and		VNBStart.Year >= 2017								--VNB to start from new slices in 2017 for +ve payments. Without this condition, the front loaded ongoing could be a clawback.
	and		abs(e.AMOUNT_REC) >= 0.01					
	and		((cs.FrequencyCode = 6 and cs.Premium > 1.00)		--Frequency=6->Single
			or (cs.FrequencyCode <> 6 and cs.Premium > 0.01))	--Frequency<>6->Regular

	select @RowCount = @@rowcount
	set @ProcessMessage = '#msit_CommissionStatementONGOING (1st IC + all adj) = ' + convert(nvarchar(10), @RowCount)
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseLog, @ProcessMessage, null, @Module, @Client

	/****************************************************************************
		
		Insert the ongoing VNB results into the main work table
																		
	****************************************************************************/

	insert into #AG_owt_Recognition_SEPARATE_ONGOING
	(
		SourceID,
		CaseID,
		TransactionID,
		Policy,
		ProductCode,
		BusinessCode,
		SellerCode,
		PointsTotal,
		BSC,
		MBF,
		Initial,
		OngoingTotal,
		OngoingYr01,
		OngoingYr02,
		OngoingYr03,
		OngoingYr04,
		OngoingYr05,
		OngoingYr06,
		OngoingYr07,
		OngoingYr08,
		OngoingYr09,
		OngoingYr10,
		FCARate,
		RetentionRate,
		RetentionRateBroker,
		OngoingServicingRate,
		OngoingServicingSource,
		DA,
		AmountReceived,
		Premium,
		AgentSplit,
		CommissionType,
		CommissionTypeDesc,
		PayBasisCode,
		PayBasisDesc,
		PaymentMatchedDate,
		Month,
		FrequencyCode,
		FrequencyDesc,
		ReassignedProductGroupCode,
		ReassignedProductGroupName,
		RecognitionType,
		CalculationType,
		Source,
		DateInserted,
		DateLastUpdated,
		CommissionYear
	)
	select	cs.PendingPaymentID as SourceID,
			cs.CaseID,
			cs.TransactionID,
			cs.ExtPolicyNumber as Policy,
			cs.ProductCode,
			cs.BusinessCode,
			cs.AgentCode as SellerCode,
			0.0 as PointsTotal,
			case
				when BSCpot.ID is not null then 
					--BSC takes the first 0.12 of the ongoing fee %. If the ongoing fee % is 0.12% or less, then 100% of the ongoing fee is allocated to BSC
					case when coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2)) - convert(decimal(8,4),sc.KeyValue2) >= 0.01
						then 
							case when cs.FrequencyCode = 2	--Monthly 
								then (cso.AgentSplit/100) * 12.0 * (isnull(cs.Premium,0)/2.0) * convert(decimal(8,4),sc.KeyValue3) * case when cs.CommissionType in (16,19) then -1 else 1 end
								else (cso.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(cs.Premium,0) * convert(decimal(8,4),sc.KeyValue3) * case when cs.CommissionType in (16,19) then -1 else 1 end
							end			
						else
							case when cs.FrequencyCode = 2	--Monthly 
								then (cso.AgentSplit/100) * 12.0 * (isnull(cs.Premium,0)/2.0) * coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2)) * case when cs.CommissionType in (16,19) then -1 else 1 end
								else (cso.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(cs.Premium,0) * (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))/100.0) * case when cs.CommissionType in (16,19) then -1 else 1 end
							end
					end
				else 0.0
			end as BSC,
			0.0 as MBF,
			0.0 as Initial,
			0.0 as OngoingTotal,
			case
				--WEALTH ONGOING CALCULATION START
				--When the adviser has changed, the AgentSplit can become zero in which case the ELITE points should be zero.
				when cso.AgentSplit = 0 then 0

				--SINGLE start
				--Calculate when BSC and ongoing applies (where ongoing rate is greater than BSC rate) 
				when cs.FrequencyCode = 6 and SFMpot.ID is not null and BSCpot.ID is not null and (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2)) - convert(decimal(8,4),sc.KeyValue2)) >= 0.01 then 
							--(AUM X BSC Rate)...
							((cso.AgentSplit/100) * (isnull(cs.Premium,0) * convert(decimal(8,4),sc.KeyValue3)) 
							--(AUM X OGS Rate X COB FCA Rate)...
							- ((cso.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(cs.Premium,0) * (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))/100.0) * Cfca.FACTOR)
							--(AUM X (OGS Rate - BSC Rate) X COB Retention Rate)...
							+ ((cso.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(cs.Premium,0) * ((coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))-convert(decimal(8,4),sc.KeyValue2))/100.0)) * Crate.FACTOR) 
							--Sign correctly for +ve or clawback payment
							* (case when cs.CommissionType in (16,19) then -1 else 1 end)
				--Calculate when BSC and ongoing applies (where ongoing rate less than BSC rate, then BSC gets all the ongoing available) 
				when cs.FrequencyCode = 6 and SFMpot.ID is not null and BSCpot.ID is not null then
							--(AUM X BSC Rate)...(in this scenario it's all of the OGS rate)
							((cso.AgentSplit/100) * (isnull(cs.Premium,0) * (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))/100.0)) 
							--(AUM X OGS Rate X COB FCA Rate)...
							- ((cso.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(cs.Premium,0) * (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))/100.0) * Cfca.FACTOR)
							--(AUM X (OGS Rate - BSC Rate) X COB Retention Rate)...
							+ (0.0)) --BSC got it all, so this part of the calculation is zero
							--Sign correctly for +ve or clawback payment
							* (case when cs.CommissionType in (16,19) then -1 else 1 end)
				--Calculate when no BSC applies and ongoing applies
				when cs.FrequencyCode = 6 and SFMpot.ID is not null and BSCpot.ID is null then 
							--(AUM X OGS Rate X COB Retention Rate)...
							(((cso.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(cs.Premium,0) * (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))/100.0) * Crate.FACTOR) 
							--(AUM X OGS Rate X COB FCA Rate)...
							- ((cso.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(cs.Premium,0) * (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))/100.0) * Cfca.FACTOR))
							--Sign correctly for +ve or clawback payment
							* (case when cs.CommissionType in (16,19) then -1 else 1 end)
				--SINGLE end
				
				--REGULAR start
				--Calculate when BSC and ongoing applies (where ongoing rate is greater than BSC rate) 
				when cs.FrequencyCode <> 6 and SFMpot.ID is not null and BSCpot.ID is not null and (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2)) - convert(decimal(8,4),sc.KeyValue2)) >= 0.01 then		--AG 04/06/2018 (1)
							--The non-BSC portion (Ave AUM X (OGS Rate - BSC Rate) X COB Retention Rate)...
							((((((cso.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(cs.Premium,0) * (case when cs.FrequencyCode = 2 then 12 else 1 end))/2.0) * (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2)) - convert(decimal(8,4),sc.KeyValue2))/100.0)) * Crate.FACTOR
							--The BSC portion (Ave AUM X BSC Rate)...
							+ case when cs.FrequencyCode = 2	--Monthly 
									then (cso.AgentSplit/100) * 12.0 * (isnull(cs.Premium,0)/2.0) * convert(decimal(8,4),sc.KeyValue3) 
									else (cso.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(cs.Premium,0) * convert(decimal(8,4),sc.KeyValue3) 
							  end
							--FCA Charge (Ave AUM X OGS Rate X FCA Rate)...
							- (case when cs.FrequencyCode = 2	--Monthly 
									then (cso.AgentSplit/100) * 12.0 * (isnull(cs.Premium,0)/2.0) 
									else (cso.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(cs.Premium,0) 
							   end * (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))/100.0) * Cfca.FACTOR))
							--Sign correctly for +ve or clawback payment
							* (case when cs.CommissionType in (16,19) then -1 else 1 end)   
				--Calculate when BSC and ongoing applies (where ongoing rate less than BSC rate, then BSC gets all the ongoing available) 
				when cs.FrequencyCode <> 6 and SFMpot.ID is not null and BSCpot.ID is not null then		--AG 04/06/2018 (1)
							--The non-BSC portion (Ave AUM X (OGS Rate - BSC Rate) X COB Retention Rate)...
							((0.0)	--BSC got it all, so this part of the calculation is zero
							--The BSC portion (Ave AUM X BSC Rate)...(in this scenario it's all of the OGS rate)
							+ case when cs.FrequencyCode = 2	--Monthly 
									then (cso.AgentSplit/100) * 12.0 * (isnull(cs.Premium,0)/2.0) * (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))/100.0) 
									else (cso.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(cs.Premium,0) * (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))/100.0) 
							  end
							--FCA Charge (Ave AUM X OGS Rate X FCA Rate)...
							- (case when cs.FrequencyCode = 2	--Monthly 
									then (cso.AgentSplit/100) * 12.0 * (isnull(cs.Premium,0)/2.0) 
									else (cso.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(cs.Premium,0) 
							   end * (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))/100.0) * Cfca.FACTOR))
							--Sign correctly for +ve or clawback payment
							* (case when cs.CommissionType in (16,19) then -1 else 1 end)   
				--Calculate when no BSC applies, but ongoing servicing applies
				when cs.FrequencyCode <> 6 and SFMpot.ID is not null and BSCpot.ID is null then		--AG 04/06/2018	(1)
							--(Ave AUM X OGS Rate X COB Retention Rate)...
							(((((cso.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(cs.Premium,0) * (case when cs.FrequencyCode = 2 then 12 else 1 end))/2.0) * (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))/100.0) * Crate.FACTOR) 
							--(Ave AUM X OGS Rate X COB FCA Rate)...
							- ((((cso.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(cs.Premium,0) * (case when cs.FrequencyCode = 2 then 12 else 1 end))/2.0) * (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))/100.0) * Cfca.FACTOR))
							--Sign correctly for +ve or clawback payment
							* (case when cs.CommissionType in (16,19) then -1 else 1 end)   
				--REGULAR end
				
				else 0.0

				--WEALTH ONGOING CALCULATION END
			end as OngoingYr01,
			0.0 as OngoingYr02,
			0.0 as OngoingYr03,
			0.0 as OngoingYr04,
			0.0 as OngoingYr05,
			0.0 as OngoingYr06,
			0.0 as OngoingYr07,
			0.0 as OngoingYr08,
			0.0 as OngoingYr09,
			0.0 as OngoingYr10,
			Cfca.FACTOR*100.0 as FCARate,
			Crate.FACTOR*100.0 as RetentionRate,
			0.0 as RetentionRateBroker,
			case when SFMpot.ID is not null
				then coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))
				else null
			end as OngoingServicingRate,
			case when SFMpot.ID is not null
				then case 
						when ogs.OngoingServiceFee is null and ogscli.OngoingServiceFee is null 
							then case
								when ogsdflt.KeyValue = 'ONPLAT' then 'Default - On Plat'
								else 'Default - Off Plat'
							end
						when ogs.OngoingServiceFee is not null then 'Client Product'
						when ogscli.OngoingServiceFee is not null then 'Client Only'
						else 'Unknown'
					 end
				else case when (ph.ProductCategoryCode = 1 or pcc.KeyValue2 = '1')
						then 'No OGS'					--WEALTH, but no OGS
						else null						--Not WEALTH, so OGS is n/a and is therefore null
					 end
			end as OngoingServicingSource,
			pt.CommInitialAmount as DA,
			e.AMOUNT_REC as AmountReceived,
			cs.Premium,
			cso.AgentSplit,								--Use the split from the IC record
			cs.CommissionType,
			left(cs.StandingOrderDesc,50) as CommissionTypeDesc,
			cs.PayBasisCode,
			cs.PayBasisDesc,
			cs.CreateDate as PaymentMatchedDate,
			cs.Month,
			cs.FrequencyCode,
			cs.FrequencyDesc,
			pg.ProductGroupCode as ReassignedProductGroupCode,	--Force the re-assigned products...		
			pg.ProductGroupName as ReassignedProductGroupName,	--...to be processed as investments		
			'VNB-OGS' as RecognitionType,
			'WEALTH-ONGOING' as CalculationType,
			'Openwork 2006' as Source,
			@DateLastUpdated as DateInserted,
			@DateLastUpdated as DateLastUpdated,
			csp.year as CommissionYear
	from	#msit_CommissionStatementONGOING cso
			inner join msit_CommissionStatement cs on cs.PendingPaymentID = cso.MinPendingPaymentID
			inner join mstt_Agents ag on ag.Code = cs.BusinessCode
			inner join mstt_PolicyTransactions pt on pt.ID = cs.TransactionID
			inner join mstt_Policies p on p.POL_NUM = pt.PolicyID
			inner join msit_CommissionStatementPeriods VNBStart on convert(date,pt.CreateDateTime) between VNBStart.PeriodStartDate and VNBStart.PeriodEndDate
			inner join msit_Commissionstatementperiods csp on csp.month = cs.month
			inner join mstt_ProductHierarchy ph on ph.productcode = cs.productcode
			inner join mstt_Expectation e on e.ID = cs.ExpectationID
			left join dbo.owt_MortgageBrokerFees mbf on mbf.PendingPaymentID = cs.PendingPaymentID and mbf.AdviceFeeCharged = 'Yes'
			left join owt_SelectionControl SC
						on SC.Process = 'ElitePoints' 
						and SC.KeyType = 'NSCPotCode' 
						and cs.CreateDate between SC.EffectiveStartDate and SC.EffectiveEndDate
			left join mstt_Commissions BSCpot
						on BSCpot.TransactionID = cs.TransactionID 
						and BSCpot.Agent_Code = sc.KeyValue
						and BSCpot.CommissionType = 10
			left join owt_SelectionControl SFMPC						
						on SFMPC.Process = 'ElitePoints' 
						and SFMPC.KeyType = 'ServicingFeeMarginPotCode' 
						and cs.CreateDate between SFMPC.EffectiveStartDate and SFMPC.EffectiveEndDate
			left join mstt_Commissions SFMpot							
						on SFMpot.TransactionID = cs.TransactionID 
						and SFMpot.Agent_Code = SFMPC.KeyValue
						and SFMpot.CommissionType = 10	
			left join owt_SelectionControl pcc 
						on pcc.Process = 'ElitePoints'
						and pcc.KeyType = 'ProductCategoryCode'
						and pcc.KeyValue = cs.ProductCode	
						and cs.CreateDate between pcc.EffectiveStartDate and pcc.EffectiveEndDate
			left join owt_SelectionControl ogsdflt 
						on ogsdflt.Process = 'ElitePoints'
						and ogsdflt.KeyType = 'DefaultOngoingServicingRate'
						and ogsdflt.SelectionType = 'VNB'
						and ogsdflt.KeyValue = case when ph.RDRType = 'ONPLAT' then 'ONPLAT' else 'OFPLAT' end
						and cs.CreateDate between ogsdflt.EffectiveStartDate and ogsdflt.EffectiveEndDate
			left join mstt_CodeProductGroup pg on pg.ProductGroupCode = case when pcc.KeyValue2 = '1' then 2 else ph.ProductGroupCode end
			left join owt_EliteFactors Cfca on Cfca.FeeType = 'VNB' and Cfca.category = 'COB-FCA-RATE' and csp.year between Cfca.StartYear and Cfca.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors Crate on Crate.FeeType = 'VNB' and Crate.category = 'COB-RETENTION-RATE' and csp.year between Crate.StartYear and Crate.EndYear 
--			left join owt_EliteFactors Mfca on Mfca.FeeType = 'VNB' and Mfca.category = 'MORT-FCA-RATE' and csp.year between Mfca.StartYear and Mfca.EndYear 
--			left join owt_EliteFactors MRproc on MRproc.FeeType = 'VNB' and MRproc.category = 'MORT-RETENTION-RATE-PROC' and csp.year between MRproc.StartYear and MRproc.EndYear 
--			left join owt_EliteFactors MRbkr on MRbkr.FeeType = 'VNB' and MRbkr.category = 'MORT-RETENTION-RATE-BROKER' and csp.year between MRbkr.StartYear and MRbkr.EndYear 
--			left join owt_EliteFactors Pfca on Pfca.FeeType = 'VNB' and Pfca.category = 'PROT-FCA-RATE' and csp.year between Pfca.StartYear and Pfca.EndYear 
--			left join owt_EliteFactors Prate on Prate.FeeType = 'VNB' and Prate.category = 'PROT-RETENTION-RATE' and csp.year between Prate.StartYear and Prate.EndYear 
			left join #OGSLookUp ogs on ogs.CLIENT_NUM = cs.ClientID and ogs.ProductCode = cs.ProductCode
			left join #OGSLookUpClient ogscli on ogscli.CLIENT_NUM = cs.ClientID 	

	select @RowCount = @@rowcount
	set @ProcessMessage = '#owt_Recognition (ongoing yr1) = ' + convert(nvarchar(10), @RowCount)
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseLog, @ProcessMessage, null, @Module, @Client

	/****************************************************************************

		Now calculate the ongoing spread as follows:
		1) Investments: Years 1 to 6
		2) Pensions:	Years 1 to 10
		Note that regular payments get an additional multiplier to uplift the 
		average AUM for each year.
																		
	****************************************************************************/

	update r
		set OngoingYr02 = case when r.FrequencyCode = 2									--Monthly
							then r.OngoingYr01 * YR02.Multiplier * YR02.Factor			--Regular
							else r.OngoingYr01 * YR02.Factor							--Single
						  end,
			OngoingYr03 = case when r.FrequencyCode = 2									--Monthly
							then r.OngoingYr01 * YR03.Multiplier * YR03.Factor			--Regular
							else r.OngoingYr01 * YR03.Factor							--Single
						  end,
			OngoingYr04 = case when r.FrequencyCode = 2									--Monthly
							then r.OngoingYr01 * YR04.Multiplier * YR04.Factor			--Regular
							else r.OngoingYr01 * YR04.Factor							--Single
						  end,
			OngoingYr05 = case when r.FrequencyCode = 2									--Monthly 
							then r.OngoingYr01 * YR05.Multiplier * YR05.Factor			--Regular
							else r.OngoingYr01 * YR05.Factor							--Single
						  end,
			OngoingYr06 = case when r.FrequencyCode = 2									--Monthly 
							then r.OngoingYr01 * YR06.Multiplier * YR06.Factor			--Regular
							else r.OngoingYr01 * YR06.Factor							--Single
						  end,
			OngoingYr07 = case when r.ReassignedProductGroupCode = 5					--Pensions	AG 05/06/2018
							then
								case when r.FrequencyCode = 2							--Monthly 
									then r.OngoingYr01 * YR07.Multiplier * YR07.Factor	--Regular
									else r.OngoingYr01 * YR07.Factor					--Single
								end
							else 
								0.0
						  end,
			OngoingYr08 = case when r.ReassignedProductGroupCode = 5					--Pensions	AG 05/06/2018 
							then
								case when r.FrequencyCode = 2							--Monthly 
									then r.OngoingYr01 * YR08.Multiplier * YR08.Factor	--Regular
									else r.OngoingYr01 * YR08.Factor					--Single
								end
							else 
								0.0
						  end,
			OngoingYr09 = case when r.ReassignedProductGroupCode = 5					--Pensions	AG 05/06/2018 
							then
								case when r.FrequencyCode = 2							--Monthly 
									then r.OngoingYr01 * YR09.Multiplier * YR09.Factor	--Regular
									else r.OngoingYr01 * YR09.Factor					--Single
								end
							else 
								0.0
						  end,
			OngoingYr10 = case when r.ReassignedProductGroupCode = 5					--Pensions	AG 05/06/2018
							then
								case when r.FrequencyCode = 2							--Monthly 
									then r.OngoingYr01 * YR10.Multiplier * YR10.Factor	--Regular
									else r.OngoingYr01 * YR10.Factor					--Single
								end
							else 
								0.0
						  end
	from	#AG_owt_Recognition_SEPARATE_ONGOING r
			left join owt_EliteFactors YR01 on YR01.FeeType = 'VNB' and YR01.Category = 'COB-ONGOING-DISCOUNT-YR01' and r.CommissionYear between YR01.StartYear and YR01.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors YR02 on YR02.FeeType = 'VNB' and YR02.Category = 'COB-ONGOING-DISCOUNT-YR02' and r.CommissionYear between YR02.StartYear and YR02.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors YR03 on YR03.FeeType = 'VNB' and YR03.Category = 'COB-ONGOING-DISCOUNT-YR03' and r.CommissionYear between YR03.StartYear and YR03.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors YR04 on YR04.FeeType = 'VNB' and YR04.Category = 'COB-ONGOING-DISCOUNT-YR04' and r.CommissionYear between YR04.StartYear and YR04.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors YR05 on YR05.FeeType = 'VNB' and YR05.Category = 'COB-ONGOING-DISCOUNT-YR05' and r.CommissionYear between YR05.StartYear and YR05.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors YR06 on YR06.FeeType = 'VNB' and YR06.Category = 'COB-ONGOING-DISCOUNT-YR06' and r.CommissionYear between YR06.StartYear and YR06.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors YR07 on YR07.FeeType = 'VNB' and YR07.Category = 'COB-ONGOING-DISCOUNT-YR07' and r.CommissionYear between YR07.StartYear and YR07.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors YR08 on YR08.FeeType = 'VNB' and YR08.Category = 'COB-ONGOING-DISCOUNT-YR08' and r.CommissionYear between YR08.StartYear and YR08.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors YR09 on YR09.FeeType = 'VNB' and YR09.Category = 'COB-ONGOING-DISCOUNT-YR09' and r.CommissionYear between YR09.StartYear and YR09.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors YR10 on YR10.FeeType = 'VNB' and YR10.Category = 'COB-ONGOING-DISCOUNT-YR10' and r.CommissionYear between YR10.StartYear and YR10.EndYear 
	where	r.CalculationType = 'WEALTH-ONGOING'

	select @RowCount = @@rowcount
	set @ProcessMessage = '#owt_Recognition (ongoing yr2-10) = ' + convert(nvarchar(10), @RowCount)
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseLog, @ProcessMessage, null, @Module, @Client
	
	/****************************************************************************

		Now add up all the numbers
																		
	****************************************************************************/
	
	update r
		set OngoingTotal	=	OngoingYr01 + OngoingYr02 + OngoingYr03 + OngoingYr04 + OngoingYr05 +
								OngoingYr06 + OngoingYr07 + OngoingYr08 + OngoingYr09 + OngoingYr10,
			PointsTotal		=	OngoingYr01 + OngoingYr02 + OngoingYr03 + OngoingYr04 + OngoingYr05 +
								OngoingYr06 + OngoingYr07 + OngoingYr08 + OngoingYr09 + OngoingYr10 +
								Initial + MBF	-- Note BSC is already included in the Ongoing, so don't include it in the Points Total.
	from	#AG_owt_Recognition_SEPARATE_ONGOING r

	select @RowCount = @@rowcount
	set @ProcessMessage = '#owt_Recognition (points total) = ' + convert(nvarchar(10), @RowCount)
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseLog, @ProcessMessage, null, @Module, @Client

	/****************************************************************************

		Merge the temporary table into the permanent table (IC data)
																		
	****************************************************************************/

	BEGIN TRANSACTION

	declare @SummaryOfChanges table (Change varchar(20))
	merge	dbo.AG_owt_Recognition_SEPARATE_ONGOING as trg
	using	#AG_owt_Recognition_SEPARATE_ONGOING as src
	on		trg.SourceID = src.SourceID
	and		trg.Source = src.Source
	when	matched 
	and		isnull(trg.PointsTotal,0) <> isnull(src.PointsTotal,0)
	then	update 
				set trg.CaseID = src.CaseID,
					trg.TransactionID = src.TransactionID,
					trg.Policy = src.Policy,
					trg.ProductCode = src.ProductCode,
					trg.BusinessCode = src.BusinessCode,
					trg.SellerCode = src.SellerCode,					--AG 13/06/2018
					trg.PointsTotal = src.PointsTotal,
					trg.BSC = src.BSC,
					trg.MBF = src.MBF,
					trg.Initial = src.Initial,
					trg.OngoingTotal = src.OngoingTotal,
					trg.OngoingYr01 = src.OngoingYr01,
					trg.OngoingYr02 = src.OngoingYr02,
					trg.OngoingYr03 = src.OngoingYr03,
					trg.OngoingYr04 = src.OngoingYr04,
					trg.OngoingYr05 = src.OngoingYr05,
					trg.OngoingYr06 = src.OngoingYr06,
					trg.OngoingYr07 = src.OngoingYr07,
					trg.OngoingYr08 = src.OngoingYr08,
					trg.OngoingYr09 = src.OngoingYr09,
					trg.OngoingYr10 = src.OngoingYr10,
					trg.FCARate = src.FCARate,
					trg.RetentionRate = src.RetentionRate,
					trg.RetentionRateBroker = src.RetentionRateBroker,
					trg.OngoingServicingRate = src.OngoingServicingRate,
					trg.OngoingServicingSource = src.OngoingServicingSource,
					trg.DA = src.DA,
					trg.AmountReceived = src.AmountReceived,
					trg.Premium = src.Premium,
					trg.AgentSplit = src.AgentSplit,
					trg.CommissionType = src.CommissionType,
					trg.CommissionTypeDesc = src.CommissionTypeDesc,
					trg.PayBasisCode = src.PayBasisCode,				--AG 13/06/2018
					trg.PayBasisDesc = src.PayBasisDesc,				--AG 13/06/2018
					trg.PaymentMatchedDate = src.PaymentMatchedDate,	--AG 13/06/2018	
					trg.Month = src.Month,
					trg.FrequencyCode = src.FrequencyCode,
					trg.FrequencyDesc = src.FrequencyDesc,
					trg.ReassignedProductGroupCode = src.ReassignedProductGroupCode,	--AG 05/06/2018
					trg.ReassignedProductGroupName = src.ReassignedProductGroupName,	--AG 05/06/2018
					trg.RecognitionType = src.RecognitionType,
					trg.CalculationType = src.CalculationType,
					trg.DateLastUpdated = @DateLastUpdated
	when	not matched by target 
	then	insert
			(
				SourceID,
				CaseID,
				TransactionID,
				Policy,
				ProductCode,
				BusinessCode,
				SellerCode,							--AG 13/06/2018
				PointsTotal,
				BSC,
				MBF,
				Initial,
				OngoingTotal,
				OngoingYr01,
				OngoingYr02,
				OngoingYr03,
				OngoingYr04,
				OngoingYr05,
				OngoingYr06,
				OngoingYr07,
				OngoingYr08,
				OngoingYr09,
				OngoingYr10,
				FCARate,
				RetentionRate,
				RetentionRateBroker,
				OngoingServicingRate,
				OngoingServicingSource,
				DA,
				AmountReceived,
				Premium,
				AgentSplit,
				CommissionType,
				CommissionTypeDesc,
				PayBasisCode,						--AG 13/06/2018
				PayBasisDesc,						--AG 13/06/2018
				PaymentMatchedDate,					--AG 13/06/2018
				Month,
				FrequencyCode,
				FrequencyDesc,
				ReassignedProductGroupCode,			--AG 05/06/2018
				ReassignedProductGroupName,			--AG 05/06/2018
				RecognitionType,
				CalculationType,
				Source,
				DateInserted,
				DateLastUpdated
			)		
			values
			(
				src.SourceID,
				src.CaseID,
				src.TransactionID,
				src.Policy,
				src.ProductCode,
				src.BusinessCode,
				src.SellerCode,						--AG 13/06/2018
				src.PointsTotal,
				src.BSC,
				src.MBF,
				src.Initial,
				src.OngoingTotal,
				src.OngoingYr01,
				src.OngoingYr02,
				src.OngoingYr03,
				src.OngoingYr04,
				src.OngoingYr05,
				src.OngoingYr06,
				src.OngoingYr07,
				src.OngoingYr08,
				src.OngoingYr09,
				src.OngoingYr10,
				src.FCARate,
				src.RetentionRate,
				src.RetentionRateBroker,
				src.OngoingServicingRate,
				src.OngoingServicingSource,
				src.DA,
				src.AmountReceived,
				src.Premium,
				src.AgentSplit,
				src.CommissionType,
				src.CommissionTypeDesc,
				src.PayBasisCode,					--AG 13/06/2018
				src.PayBasisDesc,					--AG 13/06/2018
				src.PaymentMatchedDate,				--AG 13/06/2018
				src.Month,
				src.FrequencyCode,
				src.FrequencyDesc,
				src.ReassignedProductGroupCode,		--AG 05/06/2018
				src.ReassignedProductGroupName,		--AG 05/06/2018
				src.RecognitionType,
				src.CalculationType,
				src.Source,
				src.DateInserted,
				src.DateLastUpdated)				--Merge statements must have a ;
	output $action into @SummaryOfChanges;
						
	/****************************************************************************

		Update OpenAccess
																		
	****************************************************************************/

/*	
	--Do not include MBF in the OpenAccess Commission Listing as it is on the MBF download
	--and we don't want MBF double counting.
	update	oal
		set VNB_Points = r.PointsTotal - r.MBF		--AG 04/06/2018 (2)
	from	msit_CommissionStatement cs
/*			inner join (select	distinct PKID
						from	owt_TransformationMovements tm 
						where	tm.DriverTableName = 'sa_swift_S_AGMFIL'
						and		tm.CommissionStatement = 'Y') tm on tm.PKID = cs.PendingPaymentID
*/			inner join msit_OpenworkAdviserListing oal on oal.SourceID = cs.ID and oal.Source = 'Openwork 2006'
			inner join owt_Recognition r 
						on r.SourceID = cs.PendingPaymentID
						and r.Source = oal.Source
	--where	isnull(oal.VNB_Points,0) <> isnull(r.PointsTotal,0)
	
	select @OALRowCount = @@rowcount
*/
	COMMIT TRANSACTION      
	
	select	@RowCount = COUNT(*)
	from	@SummaryOfChanges
	where	Change = 'INSERT'

	set @ProcessMessage = 'owt_Recognition (insert) = ' + convert(nvarchar(10), @RowCount)
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseLog, @ProcessMessage, null, @Module, @Client

	select	@RowCount = COUNT(*)
	from	@SummaryOfChanges
	where	Change = 'UPDATE'

	set @ProcessMessage = 'owt_Recognition (update) = ' + convert(nvarchar(10), @RowCount)
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseLog, @ProcessMessage, null, @Module, @Client
/*
	set @ProcessMessage = 'msit_OpenworkAdviserListing (update) = ' + convert(nvarchar(10), @OALRowCount)
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseLog, @ProcessMessage, null, @Module, @Client
*/
	/****************************************************************************

		T H E   E N D
																		
	****************************************************************************/
	
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseEnd, @ProcName, null, @Module, @Client

END TRY

BEGIN CATCH 

	select @ErrNum = ERROR_NUMBER(), @ErrMsg = ERROR_MESSAGE(), @ErrSev = ERROR_SEVERITY(), @ErrLine = ERROR_LINE(), @ErrState = XACT_STATE()
	set @ErrMsg = REPLACE(@ErrMsg, '.', '') + ' (error no: ' + CAST(@ErrNum AS VARCHAR(10)) + ') on line ' + CAST(@ErrLine AS VARCHAR(10))
	
	-- Test XACT_STATE for 0, 1, or -1.
    -- If 1, the transaction is committable.
    -- If -1, the transaction is uncommittable and should be rolled back.
    -- If 0, there is no transaction and a commit or rollback operation would generate an error.

	if @ErrState = -1			-- Transaction is uncommitable
		rollback transaction

	if @ErrState = 1			
		commit transaction

	-- Error message line 1
	set @ErrMsgBrief = left(@ErrMsg,100)
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseError, @ErrMsgBrief, null, @Module, @Client
	
	-- Error message line 2 - if any text exists
	set @ErrMsgBrief = substring(@ErrMsg,101,100)
	if len(@ErrMsgBrief) > 0
		exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseError, @ErrMsgBrief, null, @Module, @Client

	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseEnd, @ProcName, null, @Module, @Client

	RAISERROR(@ErrMsg, @ErrSev , 1)

END CATCH

/****************************************************************************

			E N D															

****************************************************************************/

return @ErrNum


GO
/****** Object:  StoredProcedure [dbo].[owp_RecognitionSwiftONGOING_Backup20180701AG]    Script Date: 7/3/2026 3:44:25 PM ******/
SET ANSI_NULLS ON
GO
SET QUOTED_IDENTIFIER ON
GO
/*********************************************************************************************************

Program:		owp_RecognitionSwift					
Author:			Alan Groves
Date created:	11/04/2018
											
Description:
===========

This proc populates the new recognition table called "owt_Recognition" with "Value of New Business"
(VNB) points.

This proc handles all of the swift data which includes:
WEALTH - COB business i.e. pensions and investments
MORTGAGES
PROTECTION

Note: There is a separate proc that calculates the GI VNB points from the Paymentshield data.

The approach of this proc is to use the incremental PendingPaymentIDs from the overnight batch
to calculate the VNB points in a temporary table.

The temporary table is then merged with the permanent table to make the calculated (or
re-calculated values) permanent.

Terms
-----
BSC			- Business Service Charge.
MBF			- Mortgage Broker Fee.
OGS			- Ongoing Servicing.
BSC Rate	- 0.12% at the time of writing (24/04/2018). This could be changed by the business, but
				would also require some DEV work in OWS.
DF			- Discount Factor.
DA			- Distribution Allowance (the total amount paid out by the provider to Openwork)
AUM			- Assets Under Management. Basically the amount invested or the premium on investment
				cases.
Average AUM - Average amount invested annually which is equivalent to 6 months' premium.

THE CALCULATIONS
================

There are two potential parts: initial + ongoing (if ongoing applies). If BSC (applies to ongoing 
only) and MBF (applies to mortgages only) apply, then these are also included:

MORTGAGE
--------
Part 1: MBF column = (Advice Fee Amount X Broker Retention Rate) - (Advice Fee Amount X Mort FCA Rate)
Part 2: Initial column = (Proc Fee Amount X Mortgage Retention Rate) - (Proc Fee X Mort FCA Rate) 
Mortgage Points Total = Initial + MBF

PROTECTION
----------
= (DA X Protection Retention Rate) - (DA X Protection FCA Rate) 
Protection Points Total = Initial

WEALTH (COB i.e. pensions and investments)
------
Part 1: Initial column = (DA X Wealth Retention Rate) - (DA X Wealth FCA Rate)

Part 2:

****XXXX****

NOTE: Where the BSC rate is greater than the ongoing rate, then BSC gets ALL of the AVAILABLE 
ongoing.

****XXXX****

REGULAR - BSC applies:
Year 1 column = BSC Points + Non-BSC Points - FCA Points
Non-BSC Points = Ave AUM X (OGS Rate - BSC Rate) X COB Retention Rate
BSC Points = Ave AUM X BSC Rate
FCA Points = Ave AUM X OGS Rate X COB FCA Rate

REGULAR - Non-BSC: 
Year 1 column = (Ave AUM X OGS Rate X COB Retention Rate) - (Ave AUM X OGS Rate X COB FCA Rate)

SINGLE - BSC applies:
Year 1 column = (AUM X BSC Rate) + (AUM X (OGS Rate - BSC Rate) X COB Retention Rate) - (AUM X OGS Rate X COB FCA Rate) 

SINGLE - Non-BSC:
Year 1 column = (AUM X OGS Rate X COB Retention Rate) - (AUM X OGS Rate X COB FCA Rate) 

Then years 2 to 10 are calculated by applying a discount factor
Year  2 = Year 1 X  3 X DF
Year  3 = Year 1 X  5 X DF
Year  4 = Year 1 X  7 X DF
Year  5 = Year 1 X  9 X DF
Year  6 = Year 1 X 11 X DF
Year  7 = Year 1 X 13 X DF
Year  8 = Year 1 X 15 X DF
Year  9 = Year 1 X 17 X DF
Year 10 = Year 1 X 19 X DF

Wealth Points Total =	OngoingYr01 + OngoingYr02 + OngoingYr03 + OngoingYr04 + OngoingYr05 +
						OngoingYr06 + OngoingYr07 + OngoingYr08 + OngoingYr09 + OngoingYr10 +
						Initial

GI
--
See stored proc "owp_RecognitionGIPaymentshield".
 
Notes:
-----

1)	There is a BSC column on table owt_Recognition. However, BSC is already included in the ongoing
	years 1 - 10, so the BSC column does not need to be added in. In fact you will double count if 
	you attempt to do anything with it other than display it.

2)	Occasionally an investment case may receive two or more cheques which
	then go through Swift as two or more SINGLE investments on the SAME
	slice. Although the INITIAL VNB calculation will pro-rata correctly
	because it is based on the amount received, this scenario will cause
	ongoing VNB to be calculated on each of the payment records and so will 
	double count (or worse if there are more than two cheques received).
	Since de-coupling IC from ongoing i.e. they now have separate rows on
	table owt_Recognition, the issue of multiple cheques should no longer
	cause ongoing double counting.


This proc is called as follows:
	declare @rc int
	exec @rc = dbo.owp_RecognitionSwift 'Openwork', 'Recognition'
	select @rc

					
AMENDMENT HISTORY				
=================								

Date		Author		Description
----		------		-----------
26/04/2018	A Groves	Only include rows in the OGS lookups where the OngoingServiceFee > 0.0.
						Negative OGS rates are bad data and at the time of writing, there are
						39 of these.
27/04/2018	A Groves	Additional calculation and condition to handle the scenario where BSC applies
						but the OGS Rate is less than the BSC rate. Previously, this caused the
						total ongoing to be zero. However, there are two components to ongoing VNB 
						points, the BSC share and the non-BSC share. So the BSC share (which takes 
						100% when the OGS rate is less than 0.12%) should still yield ongoing points.
27/04/2018	A Groves	Single ongoing Yr01 corrected by applying outer brackets before signing the result.
03/05/2018	A Groves	Added update of column "msit_OpenworkAdviserListing.VNB_Points".
18/05/2018	A Groves	Changed mortgage calculation to use e.AMOUNT_REC instead of pt.CommInitialAmount
						as Marcus Cossey wanted the actual amount received to be used for the DA.
04/06/2018	A Groves	1) In the REGULAR section of column "OngoingYr01", the condition for cs.FrequencyCode <> 6
							was added to ensure the code differentiates to the SINGLE section.
						2) Exclude MBF from the OpenAccess table (msit_OpenworkAdviserListing) as this
							is shown on the MBF download and would otherwise incur MBF double counting.
05/06/2018	A Groves	1) Marcus Cossey advised that investments should get ongoing for years 1 to 6 and
							pensions for years 1 to 10. Previously, both lines of business got years 1 to 10.
						2) Marcus Cossey asked for split payments (i.e. where multiple cheques are processed
							for a SINGLE investment) to only claculate ongoing VNB on the oldest payment. 
11/06/2018	A Groves	1) PSD processed a protection clawback statement as fee type initial. These clawbacks
							all generated +ve instead of -ve VNB points. A tweak was added to ensure that the 
							absolute value of AMOUNT_REC is used to ensure the VNB is correctly signed. 
						2) Another unknown business rule has surfaced: Previously, only initial, clawbacks and
							adjustments on slices created new from 2017 were included. This rule only applies
							to initial. Clawbacks and adjustments can belong to a slice created at any point
							in the past. However, note that the payment (irrespective of whether it is +ve or 
							-ve), must not pre-date 2017.
13/06/2018	A Groves	Marcus asked for SellerCode and PaymentMatchedDate to be added so he need only use 
							the one table for both the adviser and enterprise leagues. PayBasisCode and 
							PayBasisDesc were also added at the same time as these are used in the calculations.
*************************************************************************************************************/

CREATE PROCEDURE [dbo].[owp_RecognitionSwiftONGOING_Backup20180701AG]
	@Client		varchar(50),
	@Module		Varchar(50)

AS

set nocount on

declare		@PhaseStart				varchar(50),
			@PhaseEnd				varchar(50),
			@PhaseError				varchar(50),
			@PhaseLog				varchar(50),
			@ProcName				varchar(100),
			@ProcessMessage			varchar(100),
			@RowCount				int,
			@OALRowCount			int,
			@ErrMsg					nvarchar(4000),
			@ErrMsgBrief			nvarchar(100),
			@ErrNum					int,
			@ErrSev					int,
			@ErrLine				int,
			@ErrState				int,
			@DateLastUpdated		datetime,
			@OwlManager2Code		nvarchar(10)
			
/****************************************************************************

	Set initial parameters																
																		
****************************************************************************/

set @ProcName			= object_name(@@procid)
set @PhaseStart			= 'START'
set @PhaseEnd			= 'END'
set @PhaseError			= 'ERROR'
set @PhaseLog			= 'LOG'
set @ErrNum				= 0	
set @DateLastUpdated	= getdate()

set @OwlManager2Code = (select cde.Code from msit_MIWarehouseCodesAndDescriptions cde
			where cde.ColumnName = 'Manager2Code' and cde.Description = 'Owl Financial')

-- We want this logging irrespective of whether or not there is a rollback
exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseStart, @ProcName, null, @Module, @Client

/****************************************************************************

	Populate the table																
																		
****************************************************************************/

SET XACT_ABORT ON	-- Needed if XACT_STATE() function is used.

BEGIN TRY

	/****************************************************************************

		Link OWS data to Swift data to enable the ongoing servicng (OGS) rate
		to be looked up.
																		
	****************************************************************************/
	
	select	distinct s.PersonID, swp.Client_Num, p.InternalProductID, swp.ProductCode 
	into	#SwiftOWSClientLink
	from	sa_ows_Sale s
			inner join sa_ows_Policies p on p.SaleID = s.SaleID
			inner join mstt_Policies swp on swp.PolicyRef = p.PolicyID
	where	s.DateSubmitted is not null
	--and		s.PersonID = 146030

	select @RowCount = @@rowcount
	set @ProcessMessage = '#SwiftOWSClientLink = ' + convert(nvarchar(10), @RowCount)
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseLog, @ProcessMessage, null, @Module, @Client

	-- The OGS rate is stored for the client/product combination
	select	link.Client_Num, link.ProductCode, max(ogs.OngoingServiceFee) as OngoingServiceFee
	into	#OGSLookUp
	from	#SwiftOWSClientLink link 
			inner join mstt_ProductHierarchy ph on ph.ProductCode = link.ProductCode
			inner join Submission.sa_ows_SubmittedProductCurrentOngoingServiceFee ogs
							on ogs.PersonID = link.PersonID
							and ogs.InternalProductID = (case when ph.RDRType = 'ONPLAT' 
															then -2 
															else link.InternalProductID 
														 end)
	where	ogs.OngoingServiceFee > 0.0							--AG 26/04/2018
	group	by 	link.Client_Num, link.ProductCode

	select @RowCount = @@rowcount
	set @ProcessMessage = '#OGSLookUp = ' + convert(nvarchar(10), @RowCount)
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseLog, @ProcessMessage, null, @Module, @Client

	create index idx_OGSLookUp on #OGSLookUp (Client_num, ProductCode)

	--This is an additional catch for OGS by storing the client's highest OGS
	--rate against their client number. This lookup will apply if the first
	--look up fails. The first lookup can fail, for example, if the case was 
	--not submitted on OWS i.e. the CaseID has a "17" prefix. 
	select	Client_Num, MAX(OngoingServiceFee) as OngoingServiceFee
	into	#OGSLookUpClient
	from	#OGSLookUp
	group	by Client_Num

	select @RowCount = @@rowcount
	set @ProcessMessage = '#OGSLookUpClient = ' + convert(nvarchar(10), @RowCount)
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseLog, @ProcessMessage, null, @Module, @Client
	
	create index idx_OGSLookUpClient on #OGSLookUpClient (Client_num)

	/****************************************************************************

		Calculate VNB and populate the temporary table with the results
		
		Note that there are oddities like LV protection payments which always
		come in pairs with one large and one much smaller amount (e.g. TransactionID 
		= 6684787.) The system treats both payments in the pair as first payments 
		and the (projected) DA associated with both is the same (because it's on 
		the policy transaction). 
		
		There is also a requirement to front-load VNB points on accrual and level
		payments. This means calculate the VNB for the full amount of the DA and 
		put it on the first payment record and then on all subsequent accrual and 
		level payments, set the VNB to zero.
		
		Thus two different sources of DA are used depending on whether we need the
		full DA amount for accruals and level or the actual amount received for all
		other scenarios including the LV split payment scenario. The two sources are:
		
		mstt_PolicyTransactions.CommInitialAmount - Full (projected) DA amount
		
		mstt_Expectation.AMOUNT_REC - The DA actually received. This handles the
										LV scenario whereby the AMOUNT_REC is 
										proportioned across the two payments received.   
																		
	****************************************************************************/

	select	top 0 
			*, 
			convert(int,NULL) as CommissionYear
	into	#AG_owt_Recognition_SEPARATE_ONGOING
	from	AG_owt_Recognition_SEPARATE_ONGOING

	/****************************************************************************

		Phase 1 - Process all but regular accrual cases with clawbacks/adjustments
		Accruals are front loaded unless their latest payment is a clawback/adjudtment
		in which case they accrue VNB points on a per payment basis and so these
		are dealt with in Phases 2 and 3.
																		
	****************************************************************************/

	insert into #AG_owt_Recognition_SEPARATE_ONGOING
	(
		SourceID,
		CaseID,
		TransactionID,
		Policy,
		ProductCode,
		BusinessCode,
		SellerCode,						--AG 13/06/2018
		PointsTotal,
		BSC,
		MBF,
		Initial,
		OngoingTotal,
		OngoingYr01,
		OngoingYr02,
		OngoingYr03,
		OngoingYr04,
		OngoingYr05,
		OngoingYr06,
		OngoingYr07,
		OngoingYr08,
		OngoingYr09,
		OngoingYr10,
		FCARate,
		RetentionRate,
		RetentionRateBroker,
		OngoingServicingRate,
		OngoingServicingSource,
		DA,
		AmountReceived,
		Premium,
		AgentSplit,
		CommissionType,
		CommissionTypeDesc,
		PayBasisCode,					--AG 13/06/2018
		PayBasisDesc,					--AG 13/06/2018
		PaymentMatchedDate,				--AG 13/06/2018
		Month,
		FrequencyCode,
		FrequencyDesc,
		ReassignedProductGroupCode,		--AG 05/06/2018
		ReassignedProductGroupName,		--AG 05/06/2018
		RecognitionType,
		CalculationType,
		Source,
		DateInserted,
		DateLastUpdated,
		CommissionYear
	)
	select	cs.PendingPaymentID as SourceID,
			cs.CaseID,
			cs.TransactionID,
			cs.ExtPolicyNumber as Policy,
			cs.ProductCode,
			cs.BusinessCode,
			cs.AgentCode as SellerCode,				--AG 13/06/2018
			0.0 as PointsTotal,
			0.0 as BSC,
			case 
				when mbf.MortgageFeeID is not null and cs.INIssued <> 0 then (((mbf.AdviceFeeAmount)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * MRbkr.FACTOR) - ((mbf.AdviceFeeAmount)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * Mfca.FACTOR)) --Note that mbf.AdviceFeeAmount is signed correctly - so no coding for signing is needed here
				else 0.0
			end as MBF,
			case 
				--When the adviser has changed, the AgentSplit can become zero in which case the ELITE points should be zero.
				when cs.AgentSplit = 0 then 0
				
				--WEALTH CALCULATION START
				--Indemnity payments or SINGLEs or IC Clawbacks or IC adjustments Start
				when (ph.ProductCategoryCode = 1 or pcc.KeyValue2 = '1') and (cs.FrequencyCode = 6 or cs.PayBasisCode in ('T') or cs.CommissionType in (2,17)) and cs.commissiontype in (1,2,17) and cs.INIssued <> 0 then (((e.AMOUNT_REC)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * Crate.FACTOR) - ((e.AMOUNT_REC)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * Cfca.FACTOR)) * case when cs.INIssued < 0 then -1 else 1 end
				--Indemnity payments or SINGLEs or IC Clawbacks or IC adjustments End
				--Accruals & Level Start
				when (ph.ProductCategoryCode = 1 or pcc.KeyValue2 = '1') and cs.INIssued <> 0 then (((pt.CommInitialAmount)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * Crate.FACTOR) - ((pt.CommInitialAmount)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * Cfca.FACTOR)) * case when cs.INIssued < 0 then -1 else 1 end
				--Accruals & Level End
				--WEALTH CALCULATION END
				
				--MORTGAGE CALCULATION START
				--Note: The MBF component has its own table column
				--Only 1 payment for mortgages
				when ph.ProductGroupCode = 3 and cs.INIssued <> 0 then (((e.AMOUNT_REC)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * MRproc.FACTOR) - ((e.AMOUNT_REC)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * Mfca.FACTOR)) * case when cs.INIssued < 0 then -1 else 1 end	--AG 18/05/2018
				--MORTGAGE CALCULATION END
				
				--PROTECTION CALCULATION START
				--Indemnity payments or SINGLEs or IC Clawbacks or IC adjustments Start
				when ph.ProductGroupCode = 6 and (cs.FrequencyCode = 6 or cs.PayBasisCode in ('T') or cs.CommissionType in (2,17)) and cs.commissiontype in (1,2,17) and cs.INIssued <> 0 then ((abs(e.AMOUNT_REC)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * Prate.FACTOR) - (abs(e.AMOUNT_REC)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * Pfca.FACTOR)) * case when cs.INIssued < 0 then -1 else 1 end	--AG 11/06/2018 (1)
				--Indemnity payments or SINGLEs or IC Clawbacks or IC adjustments End
				--Accruals & Level Start
				when ph.ProductGroupCode = 6 and cs.INIssued <> 0 then (((pt.CommInitialAmount)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * Prate.FACTOR) - ((pt.CommInitialAmount)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * Pfca.FACTOR)) * case when cs.INIssued < 0 then -1 else 1 end
				--Accruals & Level End
				--PROTECTION CALCULATION END

				else 0.0

			end as Initial,
			0.0 as OngoingTotal,
			0.0 as OngoingYr01,
			0.0 as OngoingYr02,
			0.0 as OngoingYr03,
			0.0 as OngoingYr04,
			0.0 as OngoingYr05,
			0.0 as OngoingYr06,
			0.0 as OngoingYr07,
			0.0 as OngoingYr08,
			0.0 as OngoingYr09,
			0.0 as OngoingYr10,
			case 
				when (ph.ProductCategoryCode = 1 or pcc.KeyValue2 = '1') then Cfca.FACTOR*100.0		--COB
				when ph.ProductGroupCode = 3 then Mfca.FACTOR*100.0		--MORT
				when ph.ProductGroupCode = 6 then Pfca.FACTOR*100.0		--PROT
				else 0.0
			end as FCARate,
			case 
				when (ph.ProductCategoryCode = 1 or pcc.KeyValue2 = '1') then Crate.FACTOR*100.0	--COB
				when ph.ProductGroupCode = 3 then MRproc.FACTOR*100.0	--MORT
				when ph.ProductGroupCode = 6 then Prate.FACTOR*100.0	--PROT
				else 0.0
			end as RetentionRate,
			case 
				when mbf.MortgageFeeID is not null then  MRbkr.FACTOR*100.0	
				else 0.0
			end as RetentionRateBroker,
			null as OngoingServicingRate,
			null as OngoingServicingSource,
			pt.CommInitialAmount as DA,
			e.AMOUNT_REC as AmountReceived,
			cs.Premium,
			cs.AgentSplit,
			cs.CommissionType,
			left(cs.StandingOrderDesc,50) as CommissionTypeDesc,
			cs.PayBasisCode,							--AG 13/06/2018
			cs.PayBasisDesc,							--AG 13/06/2018
			cs.CreateDate as PaymentMatchedDate,		--AG 13/06/2018
			cs.Month,
			cs.FrequencyCode,
			cs.FrequencyDesc,
			pg.ProductGroupCode as ReassignedProductGroupCode,	--Force the re-assigned products...		AG 05/06/2018
			pg.ProductGroupName as ReassignedProductGroupName,	--...to be processed as investments		AG 05/06/2018
			'VNB-INI-PHASE-1' as RecognitionType,
			case 
				when (ph.ProductCategoryCode = 1 or pcc.KeyValue2 = '1') then 'WEALTH-INITIAL'
				when ph.ProductGroupCode = 3 then 'MORTGAGE'
				when ph.ProductGroupCode = 6 then 'PROTECTION'
				else null
			end as CalculationType,
			'Openwork 2006' as Source,
			@DateLastUpdated as DateInserted,
			@DateLastUpdated as DateLastUpdated,
			csp.year as CommissionYear
	--select count(*)
	from	msit_CommissionStatement cs
/*			inner join (select	distinct PKID
						from	owt_TransformationMovements tm 
						where	tm.DriverTableName = 'sa_swift_S_AGMFIL'
						and		tm.CommissionStatement = 'Y') tm on tm.PKID = cs.PendingPaymentID
*/			inner join mstt_Agents ag on ag.Code = cs.BusinessCode
			inner join mstt_PolicyTransactions pt on pt.ID = cs.TransactionID
			inner join mstt_Policies p on p.POL_NUM = pt.PolicyID
			inner join msit_CommissionStatementPeriods VNBStart on convert(date,pt.CreateDateTime) between VNBStart.PeriodStartDate and VNBStart.PeriodEndDate
			inner join msit_Commissionstatementperiods csp on csp.month = cs.month
			inner join mstt_ProductHierarchy ph on ph.productcode = cs.productcode
			inner join mstt_Expectation e on e.ID = cs.ExpectationID
			left join dbo.owt_MortgageBrokerFees mbf on mbf.PendingPaymentID = cs.PendingPaymentID and mbf.AdviceFeeCharged = 'Yes'
			left join owt_SelectionControl SC
						on SC.Process = 'ElitePoints' 
						and SC.KeyType = 'NSCPotCode' 
						and cs.CreateDate between SC.EffectiveStartDate and SC.EffectiveEndDate
			left join mstt_Commissions BSCpot
						on BSCpot.TransactionID = cs.TransactionID 
						and BSCpot.Agent_Code = sc.KeyValue
						and BSCpot.CommissionType = 10
			left join owt_SelectionControl SFMPC						
						on SFMPC.Process = 'ElitePoints' 
						and SFMPC.KeyType = 'ServicingFeeMarginPotCode' 
						and cs.CreateDate between SFMPC.EffectiveStartDate and SFMPC.EffectiveEndDate
			left join mstt_Commissions SFMpot							
						on SFMpot.TransactionID = cs.TransactionID 
						and SFMpot.Agent_Code = SFMPC.KeyValue
						and SFMpot.CommissionType = 10	
			left join owt_SelectionControl pcc 
						on pcc.Process = 'ElitePoints'
						and pcc.KeyType = 'ProductCategoryCode'
						and pcc.KeyValue = cs.ProductCode	
						and cs.CreateDate between pcc.EffectiveStartDate and pcc.EffectiveEndDate
			left join owt_SelectionControl ogsdflt 
						on ogsdflt.Process = 'ElitePoints'
						and ogsdflt.KeyType = 'DefaultOngoingServicingRate'
						and ogsdflt.SelectionType = 'VNB'
						and ogsdflt.KeyValue = case when ph.RDRType = 'ONPLAT' then 'ONPLAT' else 'OFPLAT' end
						and cs.CreateDate between ogsdflt.EffectiveStartDate and ogsdflt.EffectiveEndDate
			left join mstt_CodeProductGroup pg on pg.ProductGroupCode = case when pcc.KeyValue2 = '1' then 2 else ph.ProductGroupCode end
			left join owt_EliteFactors Cfca on Cfca.FeeType = 'VNB' and Cfca.category = 'COB-FCA-RATE' and csp.year between Cfca.StartYear and Cfca.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors Crate on Crate.FeeType = 'VNB' and Crate.category = 'COB-RETENTION-RATE' and csp.year between Crate.StartYear and Crate.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors Mfca on Mfca.FeeType = 'VNB' and Mfca.category = 'MORT-FCA-RATE' and csp.year between Mfca.StartYear and Mfca.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors MRproc on MRproc.FeeType = 'VNB' and MRproc.category = 'MORT-RETENTION-RATE-PROC' and csp.year between MRproc.StartYear and MRproc.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors MRbkr on MRbkr.FeeType = 'VNB' and MRbkr.category = 'MORT-RETENTION-RATE-BROKER' and csp.year between MRbkr.StartYear and MRbkr.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors Pfca on Pfca.FeeType = 'VNB' and Pfca.category = 'PROT-FCA-RATE' and csp.year between Pfca.StartYear and Pfca.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors Prate on Prate.FeeType = 'VNB' and Prate.category = 'PROT-RETENTION-RATE' and csp.year between Prate.StartYear and Prate.EndYear 
			left join msit_CommissionStatement csadj 
						on csadj.TransactionID = cs.TransactionID 
						and csadj.AgentCode = cs.AgentCode 
						and csadj.CommissionType in (2,17)
						and	csadj.PayBasisCode in ('F')				--Accrual
						and	csadj.FrequencyCode <> 6				--Regular 
	where	cs.ReportingClassCode = 1
	and		ag.Manager2Code <> @OwlManager2Code		--Exclude Owl
	and		cs.INIssued <> 0
	and		csp.Year >= 2017						--Ensure in-scope payments are consistent with VNB start
	and		VNBStart.Year >= 2017
	and		cs.CommissionType in (1,2,17)
	and		abs(e.AMOUNT_REC) >= 0.01	
	--and		((VNBStart.Year >= 2017 and cs.CommissionType = 1 and e.AMOUNT_REC >= 0.01)		--VNB to start from new slices in 2017 for +ve payments but...			AG 11/06/2018 (2)
	--		or (cs.CommissionType in (2,17) or e.AMOUNT_REC <= -0.01))						--...for -ve payments, the slice can start from any date in the past	AG 11/06/2018 (2)
	and		csadj.ID is null						--Deal with accrual regular clawbacks/adjustments later

	select @RowCount = @@rowcount
	set @ProcessMessage = '#owt_Recognition (ini ph1 - no accr adj) = ' + convert(nvarchar(10), @RowCount)
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseLog, @ProcessMessage, null, @Module, @Client

	/****************************************************************************

		Now deal with accrual clawbacks and adjustments
																		
	****************************************************************************/

	--drop table #msit_CommissionStatementSUMMARY

	--Find transactions with clawbacks/adj on them
	select	cs.TransactionID,
			cs.AgentCode,
			Min(case when cs.CommissionType = 1 then cs.PendingPaymentID else null end) as MinInitialPendingPaymentID,
			MAX(case when cs.CommissionType = 1 then cs.PendingPaymentID else null end) as MaxInitialPendingPaymentID,
			MAX(case when cs.CommissionType in (2,17) then cs.PendingPaymentID else null end) as MaxAdjPendingPaymentID,
			null as MinInitialAfterAdjPendingPaymentID
	into	#msit_CommissionStatementSUMMARY
	from	msit_CommissionStatement cs
			inner join mstt_Agents ag on ag.Code = cs.BusinessCode
			inner join mstt_PolicyTransactions pt on pt.ID = cs.TransactionID
			inner join mstt_Policies p on p.POL_NUM = pt.PolicyID
			inner join msit_CommissionStatementPeriods VNBStart on convert(date,pt.CreateDateTime) between VNBStart.PeriodStartDate and VNBStart.PeriodEndDate
			inner join msit_Commissionstatementperiods csp on csp.month = cs.month
			inner join mstt_Expectation e on e.ID = cs.ExpectationID
			left join msit_CommissionStatement csadj 
						on csadj.TransactionID = cs.TransactionID 
						and csadj.AgentCode = cs.AgentCode 
						and csadj.CommissionType in (2,17)
						and	csadj.PayBasisCode in ('F')				--Accrual
						and	csadj.FrequencyCode <> 6				--Regular 
	where	cs.ReportingClassCode = 1
	and		cs.CommissionType in (1,2,17)			--We want all the initial payment types (i.e. not trail (ongoing))
	and		ag.Manager2Code <> @OwlManager2Code		--Exclude Owl
	and		csp.Year >= 2017						--Ensure in-scope payments are consistent with VNB start
	and		VNBStart.Year >= 2017 
	and		abs(e.AMOUNT_REC) >= 0.01	
	and		csadj.ID is not null					--select regular accrual transactions with clawbacks/adjustments
	--and cs.TransactionID in (5613333,6296827)
	group by	cs.TransactionID,
				cs.AgentCode

	select @RowCount = @@rowcount
	set @ProcessMessage = '#msit_CommissionStatementSUMMARY (accr adj txns) = ' + convert(nvarchar(10), @RowCount)
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseLog, @ProcessMessage, null, @Module, @Client

	--Get first initial payment after last clawback/adj
	update css
		set MinInitialAfterAdjPendingPaymentID = summ.MinPendingPaymentID 
	from  #msit_CommissionStatementSUMMARY css
			inner join  (
						select cssinner.TransactionID, cssinner.AgentCode, min(cs.PendingPaymentID) as MinPendingPaymentID
						from #msit_CommissionStatementSUMMARY cssinner
								inner join msit_CommissionStatement cs
											on cs.TransactionID = cssinner.TransactionID
											and cs.AgentCode = cssinner.AgentCode
						where cs.PendingPaymentID > cssinner.MaxAdjPendingPaymentID
						group by cssinner.TransactionID, cssinner.AgentCode
						) summ on  summ.TransactionID = css.TransactionID
							   and summ.AgentCode = css.AgentCode

	select @RowCount = @@rowcount
	set @ProcessMessage = '#msit_CommissionStatementSUMMARY (1st IC after adj) = ' + convert(nvarchar(10), @RowCount)
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseLog, @ProcessMessage, null, @Module, @Client

	/****************************************************************************

		Phase 2 - This phase deals with regular accrual cases where there is at 
		least one clawback/adjustment. In this scenario the VNB is changed from 
		front loaded to a per payment basis.
																		
	****************************************************************************/

	insert into #AG_owt_Recognition_SEPARATE_ONGOING
	(
		SourceID,
		CaseID,
		TransactionID,
		Policy,
		ProductCode,
		BusinessCode,
		SellerCode,						
		PointsTotal,
		BSC,
		MBF,
		Initial,
		OngoingTotal,
		OngoingYr01,
		OngoingYr02,
		OngoingYr03,
		OngoingYr04,
		OngoingYr05,
		OngoingYr06,
		OngoingYr07,
		OngoingYr08,
		OngoingYr09,
		OngoingYr10,
		FCARate,
		RetentionRate,
		RetentionRateBroker,
		OngoingServicingRate,
		OngoingServicingSource,
		DA,
		AmountReceived,
		Premium,
		AgentSplit,
		CommissionType,
		CommissionTypeDesc,
		PayBasisCode,					
		PayBasisDesc,					
		PaymentMatchedDate,				
		Month,
		FrequencyCode,
		FrequencyDesc,
		ReassignedProductGroupCode,		
		ReassignedProductGroupName,		
		RecognitionType,
		CalculationType,
		Source,
		DateInserted,
		DateLastUpdated,
		CommissionYear
	)
	select	cs.PendingPaymentID as SourceID,
			cs.CaseID,
			cs.TransactionID,
			cs.ExtPolicyNumber as Policy,
			cs.ProductCode,
			cs.BusinessCode,
			cs.AgentCode as SellerCode,				
			0.0 as PointsTotal,
			0.0 as BSC,
			case 
				when mbf.MortgageFeeID is not null and cs.INIssued <> 0 then (((mbf.AdviceFeeAmount)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * MRbkr.FACTOR) - ((mbf.AdviceFeeAmount)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * Mfca.FACTOR)) --Note that mbf.AdviceFeeAmount is signed correctly - so no coding for signing is needed here
				else 0.0
			end as MBF,
			case 
				--When the adviser has changed, the AgentSplit can become zero in which case the ELITE points should be zero.
				when cs.AgentSplit = 0 then 0
				
				--WEALTH CALCULATION START
				--Indemnity payments or SINGLEs or IC Clawbacks or IC adjustments Start
				--THIS SCENARIO DOESN'T OCCUR IN PHASE 2
				--Indemnity payments or SINGLEs or IC Clawbacks or IC adjustments End
				--Accruals & Level Start
				when (ph.ProductCategoryCode = 1 or pcc.KeyValue2 = '1') then (((e.AMOUNT_REC)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * Crate.FACTOR) - ((e.AMOUNT_REC)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * Cfca.FACTOR)) * case when cs.CommissionType in (2,17) then -1 else 1 end
				--Accruals & Level End
				--WEALTH CALCULATION END
				
				--MORTGAGE CALCULATION START
				--Note: The MBF component has its own table column
				--Only 1 payment for mortgages
				when ph.ProductGroupCode = 3 then (((e.AMOUNT_REC)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * MRproc.FACTOR) - ((e.AMOUNT_REC)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * Mfca.FACTOR)) * case when cs.CommissionType in (2,17) then -1 else 1 end	
				--MORTGAGE CALCULATION END
				
				--PROTECTION CALCULATION START
				--Indemnity payments or SINGLEs or IC Clawbacks or IC adjustments Start
				--THIS SCENARIO DOESN'T OCCUR IN PHASE 2
				--Indemnity payments or SINGLEs or IC Clawbacks or IC adjustments End
				--Accruals & Level Start
				when ph.ProductGroupCode = 6 then (((e.AMOUNT_REC)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * Prate.FACTOR) - ((e.AMOUNT_REC)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * Pfca.FACTOR)) * case when cs.CommissionType in (2,17) then -1 else 1 end
				--Accruals & Level End
				--PROTECTION CALCULATION END

				else 0.0

			end as Initial,
			0.0 as OngoingTotal,
			0.0 as OngoingYr01,
			0.0 as OngoingYr02,
			0.0 as OngoingYr03,
			0.0 as OngoingYr04,
			0.0 as OngoingYr05,
			0.0 as OngoingYr06,
			0.0 as OngoingYr07,
			0.0 as OngoingYr08,
			0.0 as OngoingYr09,
			0.0 as OngoingYr10,
			case 
				when (ph.ProductCategoryCode = 1 or pcc.KeyValue2 = '1') then Cfca.FACTOR*100.0		--COB
				when ph.ProductGroupCode = 3 then Mfca.FACTOR*100.0		--MORT
				when ph.ProductGroupCode = 6 then Pfca.FACTOR*100.0		--PROT
				else 0.0
			end as FCARate,
			case 
				when (ph.ProductCategoryCode = 1 or pcc.KeyValue2 = '1') then Crate.FACTOR*100.0	--COB
				when ph.ProductGroupCode = 3 then MRproc.FACTOR*100.0	--MORT
				when ph.ProductGroupCode = 6 then Prate.FACTOR*100.0	--PROT
				else 0.0
			end as RetentionRate,
			case 
				when mbf.MortgageFeeID is not null then  MRbkr.FACTOR*100.0	
				else 0.0
			end as RetentionRateBroker,
			null as OngoingServicingRate,
			null as OngoingServicingSource,
			pt.CommInitialAmount as DA,
			e.AMOUNT_REC as AmountReceived,
			cs.Premium,
			cs.AgentSplit,
			cs.CommissionType,
			left(cs.StandingOrderDesc,50) as CommissionTypeDesc,
			cs.PayBasisCode,							
			cs.PayBasisDesc,							
			cs.CreateDate as PaymentMatchedDate,		
			cs.Month,
			cs.FrequencyCode,
			cs.FrequencyDesc,
			pg.ProductGroupCode as ReassignedProductGroupCode,	--Force the re-assigned products...		
			pg.ProductGroupName as ReassignedProductGroupName,	--...to be processed as investments		
			'VNB-INI-PHASE-2' as RecognitionType,
			case 
				when (ph.ProductCategoryCode = 1 or pcc.KeyValue2 = '1') then 'WEALTH-INITIAL'
				when ph.ProductGroupCode = 3 then 'MORTGAGE'
				when ph.ProductGroupCode = 6 then 'PROTECTION'
				else null
			end as CalculationType,
			'Openwork 2006' as Source,
			@DateLastUpdated as DateInserted,
			@DateLastUpdated as DateLastUpdated,
			csp.year as CommissionYear
	from	#msit_CommissionStatementSUMMARY css
			inner join msit_CommissionStatement cs
						on cs.TransactionID = css.TransactionID
						and cs.AgentCode = css.AgentCode
			inner join mstt_Agents ag on ag.Code = cs.BusinessCode
			inner join mstt_PolicyTransactions pt on pt.ID = cs.TransactionID
			inner join mstt_Policies p on p.POL_NUM = pt.PolicyID
			inner join msit_CommissionStatementPeriods VNBStart on convert(date,pt.CreateDateTime) between VNBStart.PeriodStartDate and VNBStart.PeriodEndDate
			inner join msit_Commissionstatementperiods csp on csp.month = cs.month
			inner join mstt_ProductHierarchy ph on ph.productcode = cs.productcode
			inner join mstt_Expectation e on e.ID = cs.ExpectationID
			left join dbo.owt_MortgageBrokerFees mbf on mbf.PendingPaymentID = cs.PendingPaymentID and mbf.AdviceFeeCharged = 'Yes'
			left join owt_SelectionControl SC
						on SC.Process = 'ElitePoints' 
						and SC.KeyType = 'NSCPotCode' 
						and cs.CreateDate between SC.EffectiveStartDate and SC.EffectiveEndDate
			left join mstt_Commissions BSCpot
						on BSCpot.TransactionID = cs.TransactionID 
						and BSCpot.Agent_Code = sc.KeyValue
						and BSCpot.CommissionType = 10
			left join owt_SelectionControl SFMPC						
						on SFMPC.Process = 'ElitePoints' 
						and SFMPC.KeyType = 'ServicingFeeMarginPotCode' 
						and cs.CreateDate between SFMPC.EffectiveStartDate and SFMPC.EffectiveEndDate
			left join mstt_Commissions SFMpot							
						on SFMpot.TransactionID = cs.TransactionID 
						and SFMpot.Agent_Code = SFMPC.KeyValue
						and SFMpot.CommissionType = 10	
			left join owt_SelectionControl pcc 
						on pcc.Process = 'ElitePoints'
						and pcc.KeyType = 'ProductCategoryCode'
						and pcc.KeyValue = cs.ProductCode	
						and cs.CreateDate between pcc.EffectiveStartDate and pcc.EffectiveEndDate
			left join owt_SelectionControl ogsdflt 
						on ogsdflt.Process = 'ElitePoints'
						and ogsdflt.KeyType = 'DefaultOngoingServicingRate'
						and ogsdflt.SelectionType = 'VNB'
						and ogsdflt.KeyValue = case when ph.RDRType = 'ONPLAT' then 'ONPLAT' else 'OFPLAT' end
						and cs.CreateDate between ogsdflt.EffectiveStartDate and ogsdflt.EffectiveEndDate
			left join mstt_CodeProductGroup pg on pg.ProductGroupCode = case when pcc.KeyValue2 = '1' then 2 else ph.ProductGroupCode end
			left join owt_EliteFactors Cfca on Cfca.FeeType = 'VNB' and Cfca.category = 'COB-FCA-RATE' and csp.year between Cfca.StartYear and Cfca.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors Crate on Crate.FeeType = 'VNB' and Crate.category = 'COB-RETENTION-RATE' and csp.year between Crate.StartYear and Crate.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors Mfca on Mfca.FeeType = 'VNB' and Mfca.category = 'MORT-FCA-RATE' and csp.year between Mfca.StartYear and Mfca.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors MRproc on MRproc.FeeType = 'VNB' and MRproc.category = 'MORT-RETENTION-RATE-PROC' and csp.year between MRproc.StartYear and MRproc.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors MRbkr on MRbkr.FeeType = 'VNB' and MRbkr.category = 'MORT-RETENTION-RATE-BROKER' and csp.year between MRbkr.StartYear and MRbkr.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors Pfca on Pfca.FeeType = 'VNB' and Pfca.category = 'PROT-FCA-RATE' and csp.year between Pfca.StartYear and Pfca.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors Prate on Prate.FeeType = 'VNB' and Prate.category = 'PROT-RETENTION-RATE' and csp.year between Prate.StartYear and Prate.EndYear 
	where	cs.ReportingClassCode = 1
	and		cs.CommissionType in (1,2,17)			--We want all the initial payment types (i.e. not trail (ongoing))
	and		ag.Manager2Code <> @OwlManager2Code		--Exclude Owl

	select @RowCount = @@rowcount
	set @ProcessMessage = '#owt_Recognition (ini ph2 - accr adj) = ' + convert(nvarchar(10), @RowCount)
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseLog, @ProcessMessage, null, @Module, @Client

	/****************************************************************************

		Initial Phase 3
		1) Add up the +ves and -ves prior to the NEW front loaded amount and
			net them off on the first +ve following the last -ve
		2) Now set all the +ves following the one updated in (1) to zero.
																
	****************************************************************************/

	update r
		set RecognitionType	= case when r.SourceID >= css.MinInitialAfterAdjPendingPaymentID 
								then 'VNB-INI-PHASE-3'
								else r.RecognitionType
							  end,
			Initial = case  when r.SourceID = css.MinInitialAfterAdjPendingPaymentID 
								then (((r.DA)*(r.AgentSplit/100) * (r.RetentionRate/100.0)) - ((r.DA)*(r.AgentSplit/100) * (r.FCARate/100))) - derived.SumInitial
							when r.SourceID > css.MinInitialAfterAdjPendingPaymentID 
								then 0.0
							else r.Initial
					  end,
			DateLastUpdated = @DateLastUpdated
	from	#msit_CommissionStatementSUMMARY css
			inner join #AG_owt_Recognition_SEPARATE_ONGOING r
						on r.TransactionID = css.TransactionID
						and r.SellerCode = css.AgentCode
			inner join (select	r.TransactionID, r.SellerCode, SUM(Initial) as SumInitial
						from	#msit_CommissionStatementSUMMARY s
								inner join #AG_owt_Recognition_SEPARATE_ONGOING r 
											on r.TransactionID = s.TransactionID
											and r.SellerCode = s.AgentCode
						where	r.SourceID <= s.MaxAdjPendingPaymentID
						group	by r.TransactionID, r.SellerCode
						) derived 
							on  derived.TransactionID = r.TransactionID
							and	derived.SellerCode = r.SellerCode 
	where	isnull(css.MaxInitialPendingPaymentID,0) > isnull(css.MaxAdjPendingPaymentID,0)-- An initial payment follows the clawback, so time to revert back to front loading
	--and		r.SourceID = css.MinInitialAfterAdjPendingPaymentID
	--and		css.TransactionID = 5696809

	select @RowCount = @@rowcount
	set @ProcessMessage = '#owt_Recognition (ini ph3 - accr adj) = ' + convert(nvarchar(10), @RowCount)
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseLog, @ProcessMessage, null, @Module, @Client

	/****************************************************************************

		Now do the ongoing.
		
		Build an ongoing summary row for each transaction and mark any row
		that has clawbacks or adjustments (TransactionHasAdjustments).
						
	****************************************************************************/

	--Find transactions with clawbacks/adj on them
	select	cs.TransactionID,
			cs.AgentCode,
			c.Agent_Perc as AgentSplit,
			max(case when csadj.ID is null then 0 else 1 end) as TransactionHasAdjustments,
			Min(case when cs.CommissionType = 10 then cs.PendingPaymentID else null end) as MinOngoingPendingPaymentID,
			MAX(case when cs.CommissionType = 10 then cs.PendingPaymentID else null end) as MaxOngoingPendingPaymentID,
			MAX(case when cs.CommissionType in (16,19) then cs.PendingPaymentID else null end) as MaxAdjOngoingPendingPaymentID,
			null as MinOngoingAfterAdjPendingPaymentID
	into	#msit_CommissionStatementONGOING
	from	msit_CommissionStatement cs
			inner join mstt_Commissions c
						on c.TransactionID = cs.TransactionID
						and c.Agent_Code = cs.AgentCode
						and c.CommissionType = 1
			inner join mstt_Agents ag on ag.Code = cs.BusinessCode
			inner join mstt_PolicyTransactions pt on pt.ID = cs.TransactionID
			inner join mstt_Policies p on p.POL_NUM = pt.PolicyID
			inner join msit_CommissionStatementPeriods VNBStart on convert(date,pt.CreateDateTime) between VNBStart.PeriodStartDate and VNBStart.PeriodEndDate
			inner join msit_Commissionstatementperiods csp on csp.month = cs.month
			inner join mstt_ProductHierarchy ph on ph.productcode = cs.productcode
			inner join mstt_Expectation e on e.ID = cs.ExpectationID
			left join owt_SelectionControl pcc 
						on pcc.Process = 'ElitePoints'
						and pcc.KeyType = 'ProductCategoryCode'
						and pcc.KeyValue = cs.ProductCode	
						and cs.CreateDate between pcc.EffectiveStartDate and pcc.EffectiveEndDate
			left join msit_CommissionStatement csadj 
						on csadj.TransactionID = cs.TransactionID 
						and csadj.AgentCode = cs.AgentCode 
						and csadj.CommissionType in (16,19)
						and	csadj.PayBasisCode in ('F')				--Accrual
						and	csadj.FrequencyCode <> 6				--Regular 
	where	cs.ReportingClassCode = 1
	and		cs.CommissionType in (10,16,19)			--We want all the trail (ongoing) payment types (i.e. not initial)
	and		cs.CommFeeType = 'Ongoing'
	and		(ph.ProductCategoryCode = 1 or pcc.KeyValue2 = '1')
	and		ag.Manager2Code <> @OwlManager2Code		--Exclude Owl
	and		csp.Year >= 2017						--Ensure in-scope payments are consistent with VNB start
	and		VNBStart.Year >= 2017 
	and		abs(e.AMOUNT_REC) >= 0.01
	and		((cs.FrequencyCode = 6 and cs.Premium > 1.00)		--Frequency=6->Single
			or (cs.FrequencyCode <> 6 and cs.Premium > 0.01))	--Frequency<>6->Regular	
	--and		csadj.ID is null									--select regular accrual transactions with NO clawbacks/adjustments
	--and cs.TransactionID in (5613333,6296827)
	group by	cs.TransactionID, 
				cs.AgentCode, 
				c.Agent_Perc

	select @RowCount = @@rowcount
	set @ProcessMessage = '#msit_CommissionStatementONGOING (accr adj txns) = ' + convert(nvarchar(10), @RowCount)
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseLog, @ProcessMessage, null, @Module, @Client

	--Get first ongoing payment after last clawback/adj
	update cso
		set MinOngoingAfterAdjPendingPaymentID = summ.MinPendingPaymentID 
	from  #msit_CommissionStatementONGOING cso
			inner join  (
						select csoinner.TransactionID, csoinner.AgentCode, min(cs.PendingPaymentID) as MinPendingPaymentID
						from #msit_CommissionStatementONGOING csoinner
								inner join msit_CommissionStatement cs
											on cs.TransactionID = csoinner.TransactionID
											and cs.AgentCode = csoinner.AgentCode
						where cs.PendingPaymentID > csoinner.MaxAdjOngoingPendingPaymentID
						group by csoinner.TransactionID, csoinner.AgentCode
						) summ on  summ.TransactionID = cso.TransactionID
							   and summ.AgentCode = cso.AgentCode

	select @RowCount = @@rowcount
	set @ProcessMessage = '#msit_CommissionStatementONGOING (1st ogs after adj) = ' + convert(nvarchar(10), @RowCount)
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseLog, @ProcessMessage, null, @Module, @Client

	/****************************************************************************
		
		Insert the ongoing VNB results for those transactions with no
		clawbacks or adjustments - front loaded.
																		
	****************************************************************************/

	insert into #AG_owt_Recognition_SEPARATE_ONGOING
	(
		SourceID,
		CaseID,
		TransactionID,
		Policy,
		ProductCode,
		BusinessCode,
		SellerCode,
		PointsTotal,
		BSC,
		MBF,
		Initial,
		OngoingTotal,
		OngoingYr01,
		OngoingYr02,
		OngoingYr03,
		OngoingYr04,
		OngoingYr05,
		OngoingYr06,
		OngoingYr07,
		OngoingYr08,
		OngoingYr09,
		OngoingYr10,
		FCARate,
		RetentionRate,
		RetentionRateBroker,
		OngoingServicingRate,
		OngoingServicingSource,
		DA,
		AmountReceived,
		Premium,
		AgentSplit,
		CommissionType,
		CommissionTypeDesc,
		PayBasisCode,
		PayBasisDesc,
		PaymentMatchedDate,
		Month,
		FrequencyCode,
		FrequencyDesc,
		ReassignedProductGroupCode,
		ReassignedProductGroupName,
		RecognitionType,
		CalculationType,
		Source,
		DateInserted,
		DateLastUpdated,
		CommissionYear
	)
	select	cs.PendingPaymentID as SourceID,
			cs.CaseID,
			cs.TransactionID,
			cs.ExtPolicyNumber as Policy,
			cs.ProductCode,
			cs.BusinessCode,
			cs.AgentCode as SellerCode,
			0.0 as PointsTotal,
			case
				when BSCpot.ID is not null then 
					--BSC takes the first 0.12 of the ongoing fee %. If the ongoing fee % is 0.12% or less, then 100% of the ongoing fee is allocated to BSC
					case when coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2)) - convert(decimal(8,4),sc.KeyValue2) >= 0.01
						then 
							case when cs.FrequencyCode = 2	--Monthly 
								then (cso.AgentSplit/100) * 12.0 * (isnull(cs.Premium,0)/2.0) * convert(decimal(8,4),sc.KeyValue3) * case when cs.CommissionType in (16,19) then -1 else 1 end
								else (cso.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(cs.Premium,0) * convert(decimal(8,4),sc.KeyValue3) * case when cs.CommissionType in (16,19) then -1 else 1 end
							end			
						else
							case when cs.FrequencyCode = 2	--Monthly 
								then (cso.AgentSplit/100) * 12.0 * (isnull(cs.Premium,0)/2.0) * coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2)) * case when cs.CommissionType in (16,19) then -1 else 1 end
								else (cso.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(cs.Premium,0) * (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))/100.0) * case when cs.CommissionType in (16,19) then -1 else 1 end
							end
					end
				else 0.0
			end as BSC,
			0.0 as MBF,
			0.0 as Initial,
			0.0 as OngoingTotal,
			case
				--WEALTH ONGOING CALCULATION START
				--When the adviser has changed, the AgentSplit can become zero in which case the ELITE points should be zero.
				when cso.AgentSplit = 0 then 0

				--SINGLE start
				--Calculate when BSC and ongoing applies (where ongoing rate is greater than BSC rate) 
				when cs.FrequencyCode = 6 and SFMpot.ID is not null and BSCpot.ID is not null and (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2)) - convert(decimal(8,4),sc.KeyValue2)) >= 0.01 then 
							--(AUM X BSC Rate)...
							((cso.AgentSplit/100) * (isnull(cs.Premium,0) * convert(decimal(8,4),sc.KeyValue3)) 
							--(AUM X OGS Rate X COB FCA Rate)...
							- ((cso.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(cs.Premium,0) * (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))/100.0) * Cfca.FACTOR)
							--(AUM X (OGS Rate - BSC Rate) X COB Retention Rate)...
							+ ((cso.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(cs.Premium,0) * ((coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))-convert(decimal(8,4),sc.KeyValue2))/100.0)) * Crate.FACTOR) 
							--Sign correctly for +ve or clawback payment
							* (case when cs.CommissionType in (16,19) then -1 else 1 end)
				--Calculate when BSC and ongoing applies (where ongoing rate less than BSC rate, then BSC gets all the ongoing available) 
				when cs.FrequencyCode = 6 and SFMpot.ID is not null and BSCpot.ID is not null then
							--(AUM X BSC Rate)...(in this scenario it's all of the OGS rate)
							((cso.AgentSplit/100) * (isnull(cs.Premium,0) * (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))/100.0)) 
							--(AUM X OGS Rate X COB FCA Rate)...
							- ((cso.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(cs.Premium,0) * (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))/100.0) * Cfca.FACTOR)
							--(AUM X (OGS Rate - BSC Rate) X COB Retention Rate)...
							+ (0.0)) --BSC got it all, so this part of the calculation is zero
							--Sign correctly for +ve or clawback payment
							* (case when cs.CommissionType in (16,19) then -1 else 1 end)
				--Calculate when no BSC applies and ongoing applies
				when cs.FrequencyCode = 6 and SFMpot.ID is not null and BSCpot.ID is null then 
							--(AUM X OGS Rate X COB Retention Rate)...
							(((cso.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(cs.Premium,0) * (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))/100.0) * Crate.FACTOR) 
							--(AUM X OGS Rate X COB FCA Rate)...
							- ((cso.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(cs.Premium,0) * (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))/100.0) * Cfca.FACTOR))
							--Sign correctly for +ve or clawback payment
							* (case when cs.CommissionType in (16,19) then -1 else 1 end)
				--SINGLE end
				
				--REGULAR start
				--Calculate when BSC and ongoing applies (where ongoing rate is greater than BSC rate) 
				when cs.FrequencyCode <> 6 and SFMpot.ID is not null and BSCpot.ID is not null and (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2)) - convert(decimal(8,4),sc.KeyValue2)) >= 0.01 then		--AG 04/06/2018 (1)
							--The non-BSC portion (Ave AUM X (OGS Rate - BSC Rate) X COB Retention Rate)...
							((((((cso.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(cs.Premium,0) * (case when cs.FrequencyCode = 2 then 12 else 1 end))/2.0) * (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2)) - convert(decimal(8,4),sc.KeyValue2))/100.0)) * Crate.FACTOR
							--The BSC portion (Ave AUM X BSC Rate)...
							+ case when cs.FrequencyCode = 2	--Monthly 
									then (cso.AgentSplit/100) * 12.0 * (isnull(cs.Premium,0)/2.0) * convert(decimal(8,4),sc.KeyValue3) 
									else (cso.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(cs.Premium,0) * convert(decimal(8,4),sc.KeyValue3) 
							  end
							--FCA Charge (Ave AUM X OGS Rate X FCA Rate)...
							- (case when cs.FrequencyCode = 2	--Monthly 
									then (cso.AgentSplit/100) * 12.0 * (isnull(cs.Premium,0)/2.0) 
									else (cso.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(cs.Premium,0) 
							   end * (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))/100.0) * Cfca.FACTOR))
							--Sign correctly for +ve or clawback payment
							* (case when cs.CommissionType in (16,19) then -1 else 1 end)   
				--Calculate when BSC and ongoing applies (where ongoing rate less than BSC rate, then BSC gets all the ongoing available) 
				when cs.FrequencyCode <> 6 and SFMpot.ID is not null and BSCpot.ID is not null then		--AG 04/06/2018 (1)
							--The non-BSC portion (Ave AUM X (OGS Rate - BSC Rate) X COB Retention Rate)...
							((0.0)	--BSC got it all, so this part of the calculation is zero
							--The BSC portion (Ave AUM X BSC Rate)...(in this scenario it's all of the OGS rate)
							+ case when cs.FrequencyCode = 2	--Monthly 
									then (cso.AgentSplit/100) * 12.0 * (isnull(cs.Premium,0)/2.0) * (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))/100.0) 
									else (cso.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(cs.Premium,0) * (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))/100.0) 
							  end
							--FCA Charge (Ave AUM X OGS Rate X FCA Rate)...
							- (case when cs.FrequencyCode = 2	--Monthly 
									then (cso.AgentSplit/100) * 12.0 * (isnull(cs.Premium,0)/2.0) 
									else (cso.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(cs.Premium,0) 
							   end * (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))/100.0) * Cfca.FACTOR))
							--Sign correctly for +ve or clawback payment
							* (case when cs.CommissionType in (16,19) then -1 else 1 end)   
				--Calculate when no BSC applies, but ongoing servicing applies
				when cs.FrequencyCode <> 6 and SFMpot.ID is not null and BSCpot.ID is null then		--AG 04/06/2018	(1)
							--(Ave AUM X OGS Rate X COB Retention Rate)...
							(((((cso.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(cs.Premium,0) * (case when cs.FrequencyCode = 2 then 12 else 1 end))/2.0) * (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))/100.0) * Crate.FACTOR) 
							--(Ave AUM X OGS Rate X COB FCA Rate)...
							- ((((cso.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(cs.Premium,0) * (case when cs.FrequencyCode = 2 then 12 else 1 end))/2.0) * (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))/100.0) * Cfca.FACTOR))
							--Sign correctly for +ve or clawback payment
							* (case when cs.CommissionType in (16,19) then -1 else 1 end)   
				--REGULAR end
				
				else 0.0

				--WEALTH ONGOING CALCULATION END
			end as OngoingYr01,
			0.0 as OngoingYr02,
			0.0 as OngoingYr03,
			0.0 as OngoingYr04,
			0.0 as OngoingYr05,
			0.0 as OngoingYr06,
			0.0 as OngoingYr07,
			0.0 as OngoingYr08,
			0.0 as OngoingYr09,
			0.0 as OngoingYr10,
			Cfca.FACTOR*100.0 as FCARate,
			Crate.FACTOR*100.0 as RetentionRate,
			0.0 as RetentionRateBroker,
			case when SFMpot.ID is not null
				then coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))
				else null
			end as OngoingServicingRate,
			case when SFMpot.ID is not null
				then case 
						when ogs.OngoingServiceFee is null and ogscli.OngoingServiceFee is null 
							then case
								when ogsdflt.KeyValue = 'ONPLAT' then 'Default - On Plat'
								else 'Default - Off Plat'
							end
						when ogs.OngoingServiceFee is not null then 'Client Product'
						when ogscli.OngoingServiceFee is not null then 'Client Only'
						else 'Unknown'
					 end
				else case when (ph.ProductCategoryCode = 1 or pcc.KeyValue2 = '1')
						then 'No OGS'					--WEALTH, but no OGS
						else null						--Not WEALTH, so OGS is n/a and is therefore null
					 end
			end as OngoingServicingSource,
			pt.CommInitialAmount as DA,
			e.AMOUNT_REC as AmountReceived,
			cs.Premium,
			cso.AgentSplit,								--Use the split from the IC record
			cs.CommissionType,
			left(cs.StandingOrderDesc,50) as CommissionTypeDesc,
			cs.PayBasisCode,
			cs.PayBasisDesc,
			cs.CreateDate as PaymentMatchedDate,
			cs.Month,
			cs.FrequencyCode,
			cs.FrequencyDesc,
			pg.ProductGroupCode as ReassignedProductGroupCode,	--Force the re-assigned products...		
			pg.ProductGroupName as ReassignedProductGroupName,	--...to be processed as investments		
			'VNB-OGS-PHASE-1' as RecognitionType,
			'WEALTH-ONGOING' as CalculationType,
			'Openwork 2006' as Source,
			@DateLastUpdated as DateInserted,
			@DateLastUpdated as DateLastUpdated,
			csp.year as CommissionYear
	from	#msit_CommissionStatementONGOING cso
			inner join msit_CommissionStatement cs on cs.PendingPaymentID = cso.MinOngoingPendingPaymentID
			inner join mstt_Agents ag on ag.Code = cs.BusinessCode
			inner join mstt_PolicyTransactions pt on pt.ID = cs.TransactionID
			inner join mstt_Policies p on p.POL_NUM = pt.PolicyID
			inner join msit_CommissionStatementPeriods VNBStart on convert(date,pt.CreateDateTime) between VNBStart.PeriodStartDate and VNBStart.PeriodEndDate
			inner join msit_Commissionstatementperiods csp on csp.month = cs.month
			inner join mstt_ProductHierarchy ph on ph.productcode = cs.productcode
			inner join mstt_Expectation e on e.ID = cs.ExpectationID
			left join dbo.owt_MortgageBrokerFees mbf on mbf.PendingPaymentID = cs.PendingPaymentID and mbf.AdviceFeeCharged = 'Yes'
			left join owt_SelectionControl SC
						on SC.Process = 'ElitePoints' 
						and SC.KeyType = 'NSCPotCode' 
						and cs.CreateDate between SC.EffectiveStartDate and SC.EffectiveEndDate
			left join mstt_Commissions BSCpot
						on BSCpot.TransactionID = cs.TransactionID 
						and BSCpot.Agent_Code = sc.KeyValue
						and BSCpot.CommissionType = 10
			left join owt_SelectionControl SFMPC						
						on SFMPC.Process = 'ElitePoints' 
						and SFMPC.KeyType = 'ServicingFeeMarginPotCode' 
						and cs.CreateDate between SFMPC.EffectiveStartDate and SFMPC.EffectiveEndDate
			left join mstt_Commissions SFMpot							
						on SFMpot.TransactionID = cs.TransactionID 
						and SFMpot.Agent_Code = SFMPC.KeyValue
						and SFMpot.CommissionType = 10	
			left join owt_SelectionControl pcc 
						on pcc.Process = 'ElitePoints'
						and pcc.KeyType = 'ProductCategoryCode'
						and pcc.KeyValue = cs.ProductCode	
						and cs.CreateDate between pcc.EffectiveStartDate and pcc.EffectiveEndDate
			left join owt_SelectionControl ogsdflt 
						on ogsdflt.Process = 'ElitePoints'
						and ogsdflt.KeyType = 'DefaultOngoingServicingRate'
						and ogsdflt.SelectionType = 'VNB'
						and ogsdflt.KeyValue = case when ph.RDRType = 'ONPLAT' then 'ONPLAT' else 'OFPLAT' end
						and cs.CreateDate between ogsdflt.EffectiveStartDate and ogsdflt.EffectiveEndDate
			left join mstt_CodeProductGroup pg on pg.ProductGroupCode = case when pcc.KeyValue2 = '1' then 2 else ph.ProductGroupCode end
			left join owt_EliteFactors Cfca on Cfca.FeeType = 'VNB' and Cfca.category = 'COB-FCA-RATE' and csp.year between Cfca.StartYear and Cfca.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors Crate on Crate.FeeType = 'VNB' and Crate.category = 'COB-RETENTION-RATE' and csp.year between Crate.StartYear and Crate.EndYear 
			left join #OGSLookUp ogs on ogs.CLIENT_NUM = cs.ClientID and ogs.ProductCode = cs.ProductCode
			left join #OGSLookUpClient ogscli on ogscli.CLIENT_NUM = cs.ClientID 	
	--where	cso.TransactionHasAdjustments = 0	--No clawbacks or adjustments so front load
	
	select @RowCount = @@rowcount
	set @ProcessMessage = '#owt_Recognition (ogs ph1 yr1) = ' + convert(nvarchar(10), @RowCount)
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseLog, @ProcessMessage, null, @Module, @Client

	/****************************************************************************
		
		Insert the ongoing VNB results for those transactions with
		clawbacks or adjustments - on a per payment basis.
																		
	****************************************************************************/
/*
	insert into #AG_owt_Recognition_SEPARATE_ONGOING
	(
		SourceID,
		CaseID,
		TransactionID,
		Policy,
		ProductCode,
		BusinessCode,
		SellerCode,
		PointsTotal,
		BSC,
		MBF,
		Initial,
		OngoingTotal,
		OngoingYr01,
		OngoingYr02,
		OngoingYr03,
		OngoingYr04,
		OngoingYr05,
		OngoingYr06,
		OngoingYr07,
		OngoingYr08,
		OngoingYr09,
		OngoingYr10,
		FCARate,
		RetentionRate,
		RetentionRateBroker,
		OngoingServicingRate,
		OngoingServicingSource,
		DA,
		AmountReceived,
		Premium,
		AgentSplit,
		CommissionType,
		CommissionTypeDesc,
		PayBasisCode,
		PayBasisDesc,
		PaymentMatchedDate,
		Month,
		FrequencyCode,
		FrequencyDesc,
		ReassignedProductGroupCode,
		ReassignedProductGroupName,
		RecognitionType,
		CalculationType,
		Source,
		DateInserted,
		DateLastUpdated,
		CommissionYear
	)
	select	cs.PendingPaymentID as SourceID,
			cs.CaseID,
			cs.TransactionID,
			cs.ExtPolicyNumber as Policy,
			cs.ProductCode,
			cs.BusinessCode,
			cs.AgentCode as SellerCode,
			0.0 as PointsTotal,
			case
				when BSCpot.ID is not null then 
					--BSC takes the first 0.12 of the ongoing fee %. If the ongoing fee % is 0.12% or less, then 100% of the ongoing fee is allocated to BSC
					case when coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2)) - convert(decimal(8,4),sc.KeyValue2) >= 0.01
						then 
							case when cs.FrequencyCode = 2	--Monthly 
								then (cso.AgentSplit/100) * 12.0 * (isnull(cs.Premium,0)/2.0) * convert(decimal(8,4),sc.KeyValue3) * case when cs.CommissionType in (16,19) then -1 else 1 end
								else (cso.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(cs.Premium,0) * convert(decimal(8,4),sc.KeyValue3) * case when cs.CommissionType in (16,19) then -1 else 1 end
							end			
						else
							case when cs.FrequencyCode = 2	--Monthly 
								then (cso.AgentSplit/100) * 12.0 * (isnull(cs.Premium,0)/2.0) * coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2)) * case when cs.CommissionType in (16,19) then -1 else 1 end
								else (cso.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(cs.Premium,0) * (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))/100.0) * case when cs.CommissionType in (16,19) then -1 else 1 end
							end
					end
				else 0.0
			end as BSC,
			0.0 as MBF,
			0.0 as Initial,
			0.0 as OngoingTotal,
			case
				--WEALTH ONGOING CALCULATION START
				--When the adviser has changed, the AgentSplit can become zero in which case the ELITE points should be zero.
				when cso.AgentSplit = 0 then 0

				--SINGLE start
				--Calculate when BSC and ongoing applies (where ongoing rate is greater than BSC rate) 
				when cs.FrequencyCode = 6 and SFMpot.ID is not null and BSCpot.ID is not null and (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2)) - convert(decimal(8,4),sc.KeyValue2)) >= 0.01 then 
							--(AUM X BSC Rate)...
							((cso.AgentSplit/100) * (isnull(cs.Premium,0) * convert(decimal(8,4),sc.KeyValue3)) 
							--(AUM X OGS Rate X COB FCA Rate)...
							- ((cso.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(cs.Premium,0) * (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))/100.0) * Cfca.FACTOR)
							--(AUM X (OGS Rate - BSC Rate) X COB Retention Rate)...
							+ ((cso.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(cs.Premium,0) * ((coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))-convert(decimal(8,4),sc.KeyValue2))/100.0)) * Crate.FACTOR) 
							--Sign correctly for +ve or clawback payment
							* (case when cs.CommissionType in (16,19) then -1 else 1 end)
				--Calculate when BSC and ongoing applies (where ongoing rate less than BSC rate, then BSC gets all the ongoing available) 
				when cs.FrequencyCode = 6 and SFMpot.ID is not null and BSCpot.ID is not null then
							--(AUM X BSC Rate)...(in this scenario it's all of the OGS rate)
							((cso.AgentSplit/100) * (isnull(cs.Premium,0) * (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))/100.0)) 
							--(AUM X OGS Rate X COB FCA Rate)...
							- ((cso.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(cs.Premium,0) * (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))/100.0) * Cfca.FACTOR)
							--(AUM X (OGS Rate - BSC Rate) X COB Retention Rate)...
							+ (0.0)) --BSC got it all, so this part of the calculation is zero
							--Sign correctly for +ve or clawback payment
							* (case when cs.CommissionType in (16,19) then -1 else 1 end)
				--Calculate when no BSC applies and ongoing applies
				when cs.FrequencyCode = 6 and SFMpot.ID is not null and BSCpot.ID is null then 
							--(AUM X OGS Rate X COB Retention Rate)...
							(((cso.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(cs.Premium,0) * (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))/100.0) * Crate.FACTOR) 
							--(AUM X OGS Rate X COB FCA Rate)...
							- ((cso.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(cs.Premium,0) * (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))/100.0) * Cfca.FACTOR))
							--Sign correctly for +ve or clawback payment
							* (case when cs.CommissionType in (16,19) then -1 else 1 end)
				--SINGLE end
				
				--REGULAR start
				--Calculate when BSC and ongoing applies (where ongoing rate is greater than BSC rate) 
				when cs.FrequencyCode <> 6 and SFMpot.ID is not null and BSCpot.ID is not null and (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2)) - convert(decimal(8,4),sc.KeyValue2)) >= 0.01 then		--AG 04/06/2018 (1)
							--The non-BSC portion (Ave AUM X (OGS Rate - BSC Rate) X COB Retention Rate)...
							((((((cso.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(cs.Premium,0) * (case when cs.FrequencyCode = 2 then 12 else 1 end))/2.0) * (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2)) - convert(decimal(8,4),sc.KeyValue2))/100.0)) * Crate.FACTOR
							--The BSC portion (Ave AUM X BSC Rate)...
							+ case when cs.FrequencyCode = 2	--Monthly 
									then (cso.AgentSplit/100) * 12.0 * (isnull(cs.Premium,0)/2.0) * convert(decimal(8,4),sc.KeyValue3) 
									else (cso.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(cs.Premium,0) * convert(decimal(8,4),sc.KeyValue3) 
							  end
							--FCA Charge (Ave AUM X OGS Rate X FCA Rate)...
							- (case when cs.FrequencyCode = 2	--Monthly 
									then (cso.AgentSplit/100) * 12.0 * (isnull(cs.Premium,0)/2.0) 
									else (cso.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(cs.Premium,0) 
							   end * (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))/100.0) * Cfca.FACTOR))
							--Sign correctly for +ve or clawback payment
							* (case when cs.CommissionType in (16,19) then -1 else 1 end)   
				--Calculate when BSC and ongoing applies (where ongoing rate less than BSC rate, then BSC gets all the ongoing available) 
				when cs.FrequencyCode <> 6 and SFMpot.ID is not null and BSCpot.ID is not null then		--AG 04/06/2018 (1)
							--The non-BSC portion (Ave AUM X (OGS Rate - BSC Rate) X COB Retention Rate)...
							((0.0)	--BSC got it all, so this part of the calculation is zero
							--The BSC portion (Ave AUM X BSC Rate)...(in this scenario it's all of the OGS rate)
							+ case when cs.FrequencyCode = 2	--Monthly 
									then (cso.AgentSplit/100) * 12.0 * (isnull(cs.Premium,0)/2.0) * (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))/100.0) 
									else (cso.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(cs.Premium,0) * (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))/100.0) 
							  end
							--FCA Charge (Ave AUM X OGS Rate X FCA Rate)...
							- (case when cs.FrequencyCode = 2	--Monthly 
									then (cso.AgentSplit/100) * 12.0 * (isnull(cs.Premium,0)/2.0) 
									else (cso.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(cs.Premium,0) 
							   end * (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))/100.0) * Cfca.FACTOR))
							--Sign correctly for +ve or clawback payment
							* (case when cs.CommissionType in (16,19) then -1 else 1 end)   
				--Calculate when no BSC applies, but ongoing servicing applies
				when cs.FrequencyCode <> 6 and SFMpot.ID is not null and BSCpot.ID is null then		--AG 04/06/2018	(1)
							--(Ave AUM X OGS Rate X COB Retention Rate)...
							(((((cso.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(cs.Premium,0) * (case when cs.FrequencyCode = 2 then 12 else 1 end))/2.0) * (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))/100.0) * Crate.FACTOR) 
							--(Ave AUM X OGS Rate X COB FCA Rate)...
							- ((((cso.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(cs.Premium,0) * (case when cs.FrequencyCode = 2 then 12 else 1 end))/2.0) * (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))/100.0) * Cfca.FACTOR))
							--Sign correctly for +ve or clawback payment
							* (case when cs.CommissionType in (16,19) then -1 else 1 end)   
				--REGULAR end
				
				else 0.0

				--WEALTH ONGOING CALCULATION END
			end as OngoingYr01,
			0.0 as OngoingYr02,
			0.0 as OngoingYr03,
			0.0 as OngoingYr04,
			0.0 as OngoingYr05,
			0.0 as OngoingYr06,
			0.0 as OngoingYr07,
			0.0 as OngoingYr08,
			0.0 as OngoingYr09,
			0.0 as OngoingYr10,
			Cfca.FACTOR*100.0 as FCARate,
			Crate.FACTOR*100.0 as RetentionRate,
			0.0 as RetentionRateBroker,
			case when SFMpot.ID is not null
				then coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))
				else null
			end as OngoingServicingRate,
			case when SFMpot.ID is not null
				then case 
						when ogs.OngoingServiceFee is null and ogscli.OngoingServiceFee is null 
							then case
								when ogsdflt.KeyValue = 'ONPLAT' then 'Default - On Plat'
								else 'Default - Off Plat'
							end
						when ogs.OngoingServiceFee is not null then 'Client Product'
						when ogscli.OngoingServiceFee is not null then 'Client Only'
						else 'Unknown'
					 end
				else case when (ph.ProductCategoryCode = 1 or pcc.KeyValue2 = '1')
						then 'No OGS'					--WEALTH, but no OGS
						else null						--Not WEALTH, so OGS is n/a and is therefore null
					 end
			end as OngoingServicingSource,
			pt.CommInitialAmount as DA,
			e.AMOUNT_REC as AmountReceived,
			cs.Premium,
			cso.AgentSplit,								--Use the split from the IC record
			cs.CommissionType,
			left(cs.StandingOrderDesc,50) as CommissionTypeDesc,
			cs.PayBasisCode,
			cs.PayBasisDesc,
			cs.CreateDate as PaymentMatchedDate,
			cs.Month,
			cs.FrequencyCode,
			cs.FrequencyDesc,
			pg.ProductGroupCode as ReassignedProductGroupCode,	--Force the re-assigned products...		
			pg.ProductGroupName as ReassignedProductGroupName,	--...to be processed as investments		
			'VNB-OGS-PHASE-2' as RecognitionType,
			'WEALTH-ONGOING' as CalculationType,
			'Openwork 2006' as Source,
			@DateLastUpdated as DateInserted,
			@DateLastUpdated as DateLastUpdated,
			csp.year as CommissionYear
	from	#msit_CommissionStatementONGOING cso
			inner join msit_CommissionStatement cs 
						on cs.TransactionID = cso.TransactionID
						and cs.AgentCode = cso.AgentCode
			inner join msit_CommissionStatement cs on cs.PendingPaymentID = cso.MinOngoingPendingPaymentID
			inner join mstt_Agents ag on ag.Code = cs.BusinessCode
			inner join mstt_PolicyTransactions pt on pt.ID = cs.TransactionID
			inner join mstt_Policies p on p.POL_NUM = pt.PolicyID
			inner join msit_CommissionStatementPeriods VNBStart on convert(date,pt.CreateDateTime) between VNBStart.PeriodStartDate and VNBStart.PeriodEndDate
			inner join msit_Commissionstatementperiods csp on csp.month = cs.month
			inner join mstt_ProductHierarchy ph on ph.productcode = cs.productcode
			inner join mstt_Expectation e on e.ID = cs.ExpectationID
			left join dbo.owt_MortgageBrokerFees mbf on mbf.PendingPaymentID = cs.PendingPaymentID and mbf.AdviceFeeCharged = 'Yes'
			left join owt_SelectionControl SC
						on SC.Process = 'ElitePoints' 
						and SC.KeyType = 'NSCPotCode' 
						and cs.CreateDate between SC.EffectiveStartDate and SC.EffectiveEndDate
			left join mstt_Commissions BSCpot
						on BSCpot.TransactionID = cs.TransactionID 
						and BSCpot.Agent_Code = sc.KeyValue
						and BSCpot.CommissionType = 10
			left join owt_SelectionControl SFMPC						
						on SFMPC.Process = 'ElitePoints' 
						and SFMPC.KeyType = 'ServicingFeeMarginPotCode' 
						and cs.CreateDate between SFMPC.EffectiveStartDate and SFMPC.EffectiveEndDate
			left join mstt_Commissions SFMpot							
						on SFMpot.TransactionID = cs.TransactionID 
						and SFMpot.Agent_Code = SFMPC.KeyValue
						and SFMpot.CommissionType = 10	
			left join owt_SelectionControl pcc 
						on pcc.Process = 'ElitePoints'
						and pcc.KeyType = 'ProductCategoryCode'
						and pcc.KeyValue = cs.ProductCode	
						and cs.CreateDate between pcc.EffectiveStartDate and pcc.EffectiveEndDate
			left join owt_SelectionControl ogsdflt 
						on ogsdflt.Process = 'ElitePoints'
						and ogsdflt.KeyType = 'DefaultOngoingServicingRate'
						and ogsdflt.SelectionType = 'VNB'
						and ogsdflt.KeyValue = case when ph.RDRType = 'ONPLAT' then 'ONPLAT' else 'OFPLAT' end
						and cs.CreateDate between ogsdflt.EffectiveStartDate and ogsdflt.EffectiveEndDate
			left join mstt_CodeProductGroup pg on pg.ProductGroupCode = case when pcc.KeyValue2 = '1' then 2 else ph.ProductGroupCode end
			left join owt_EliteFactors Cfca on Cfca.FeeType = 'VNB' and Cfca.category = 'COB-FCA-RATE' and csp.year between Cfca.StartYear and Cfca.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors Crate on Crate.FeeType = 'VNB' and Crate.category = 'COB-RETENTION-RATE' and csp.year between Crate.StartYear and Crate.EndYear 
			left join #OGSLookUp ogs on ogs.CLIENT_NUM = cs.ClientID and ogs.ProductCode = cs.ProductCode
			left join #OGSLookUpClient ogscli on ogscli.CLIENT_NUM = cs.ClientID 	
	where	cso.TransactionHasAdjustments = 1	--Clawbacks or adjustments so per payment

	select @RowCount = @@rowcount
	set @ProcessMessage = '#owt_Recognition (ogs ph2 yr1) = ' + convert(nvarchar(10), @RowCount)
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseLog, @ProcessMessage, null, @Module, @Client
*/
	/****************************************************************************

		Ongoing Phase 3
		1) Add up the +ves and -ves prior to the NEW front loaded amount and
			net them off on the first +ve following the last -ve
		2) Now set all the +ves following the one updated in (1) to zero.
																
	****************************************************************************/
/*
	update r
		set RecognitionType	= case when r.SourceID >= css.MinInitialAfterAdjPendingPaymentID 
								then 'VNB-INI-PHASE-3'
								else r.RecognitionType
							  end,
			Initial = case  when r.SourceID = css.MinInitialAfterAdjPendingPaymentID 
								then (((r.DA)*(r.AgentSplit/100) * (r.RetentionRate/100.0)) - ((r.DA)*(r.AgentSplit/100) * (r.FCARate/100))) - derived.SumInitial
							when r.SourceID > css.MinInitialAfterAdjPendingPaymentID 
								then 0.0
							else r.Initial
					  end,
			DateLastUpdated = @DateLastUpdated
	from	#msit_CommissionStatementSUMMARY css
			inner join #AG_owt_Recognition_SEPARATE_ONGOING r
						on r.TransactionID = css.TransactionID
						and r.SellerCode = css.AgentCode
			inner join (select	r.TransactionID, r.SellerCode, SUM(Initial) as SumInitial
						from	#msit_CommissionStatementSUMMARY s
								inner join #AG_owt_Recognition_SEPARATE_ONGOING r 
											on r.TransactionID = s.TransactionID
											and r.SellerCode = s.AgentCode
						where	r.SourceID <= s.MaxAdjPendingPaymentID
						group	by r.TransactionID, r.SellerCode
						) derived 
							on  derived.TransactionID = r.TransactionID
							and	derived.SellerCode = r.SellerCode 
	where	isnull(css.MaxInitialPendingPaymentID,0) > isnull(css.MaxAdjPendingPaymentID,0)-- An initial payment follows the clawback, so time to revert back to front loading
	--and		r.SourceID = css.MinInitialAfterAdjPendingPaymentID
	--and		css.TransactionID = 5696809

	select @RowCount = @@rowcount
	set @ProcessMessage = '#owt_Recognition (ini ph3 - accr adj) = ' + convert(nvarchar(10), @RowCount)
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseLog, @ProcessMessage, null, @Module, @Client
*/
	/****************************************************************************

		Now calculate the ongoing spread as follows:
		1) Investments: Years 1 to 6
		2) Pensions:	Years 1 to 10
		Note that regular payments get an additional multiplier to uplift the 
		average AUM for each year.
																		
	****************************************************************************/

	update r
		set OngoingYr02 = case when r.FrequencyCode = 2									--Monthly
							then r.OngoingYr01 * YR02.Multiplier * YR02.Factor			--Regular
							else r.OngoingYr01 * YR02.Factor							--Single
						  end,
			OngoingYr03 = case when r.FrequencyCode = 2									--Monthly
							then r.OngoingYr01 * YR03.Multiplier * YR03.Factor			--Regular
							else r.OngoingYr01 * YR03.Factor							--Single
						  end,
			OngoingYr04 = case when r.FrequencyCode = 2									--Monthly
							then r.OngoingYr01 * YR04.Multiplier * YR04.Factor			--Regular
							else r.OngoingYr01 * YR04.Factor							--Single
						  end,
			OngoingYr05 = case when r.FrequencyCode = 2									--Monthly 
							then r.OngoingYr01 * YR05.Multiplier * YR05.Factor			--Regular
							else r.OngoingYr01 * YR05.Factor							--Single
						  end,
			OngoingYr06 = case when r.FrequencyCode = 2									--Monthly 
							then r.OngoingYr01 * YR06.Multiplier * YR06.Factor			--Regular
							else r.OngoingYr01 * YR06.Factor							--Single
						  end,
			OngoingYr07 = case when r.ReassignedProductGroupCode = 5					--Pensions	AG 05/06/2018
							then
								case when r.FrequencyCode = 2							--Monthly 
									then r.OngoingYr01 * YR07.Multiplier * YR07.Factor	--Regular
									else r.OngoingYr01 * YR07.Factor					--Single
								end
							else 
								0.0
						  end,
			OngoingYr08 = case when r.ReassignedProductGroupCode = 5					--Pensions	AG 05/06/2018 
							then
								case when r.FrequencyCode = 2							--Monthly 
									then r.OngoingYr01 * YR08.Multiplier * YR08.Factor	--Regular
									else r.OngoingYr01 * YR08.Factor					--Single
								end
							else 
								0.0
						  end,
			OngoingYr09 = case when r.ReassignedProductGroupCode = 5					--Pensions	AG 05/06/2018 
							then
								case when r.FrequencyCode = 2							--Monthly 
									then r.OngoingYr01 * YR09.Multiplier * YR09.Factor	--Regular
									else r.OngoingYr01 * YR09.Factor					--Single
								end
							else 
								0.0
						  end,
			OngoingYr10 = case when r.ReassignedProductGroupCode = 5					--Pensions	AG 05/06/2018
							then
								case when r.FrequencyCode = 2							--Monthly 
									then r.OngoingYr01 * YR10.Multiplier * YR10.Factor	--Regular
									else r.OngoingYr01 * YR10.Factor					--Single
								end
							else 
								0.0
						  end
	from	#AG_owt_Recognition_SEPARATE_ONGOING r
			left join owt_EliteFactors YR01 on YR01.FeeType = 'VNB' and YR01.Category = 'COB-ONGOING-DISCOUNT-YR01' and r.CommissionYear between YR01.StartYear and YR01.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors YR02 on YR02.FeeType = 'VNB' and YR02.Category = 'COB-ONGOING-DISCOUNT-YR02' and r.CommissionYear between YR02.StartYear and YR02.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors YR03 on YR03.FeeType = 'VNB' and YR03.Category = 'COB-ONGOING-DISCOUNT-YR03' and r.CommissionYear between YR03.StartYear and YR03.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors YR04 on YR04.FeeType = 'VNB' and YR04.Category = 'COB-ONGOING-DISCOUNT-YR04' and r.CommissionYear between YR04.StartYear and YR04.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors YR05 on YR05.FeeType = 'VNB' and YR05.Category = 'COB-ONGOING-DISCOUNT-YR05' and r.CommissionYear between YR05.StartYear and YR05.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors YR06 on YR06.FeeType = 'VNB' and YR06.Category = 'COB-ONGOING-DISCOUNT-YR06' and r.CommissionYear between YR06.StartYear and YR06.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors YR07 on YR07.FeeType = 'VNB' and YR07.Category = 'COB-ONGOING-DISCOUNT-YR07' and r.CommissionYear between YR07.StartYear and YR07.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors YR08 on YR08.FeeType = 'VNB' and YR08.Category = 'COB-ONGOING-DISCOUNT-YR08' and r.CommissionYear between YR08.StartYear and YR08.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors YR09 on YR09.FeeType = 'VNB' and YR09.Category = 'COB-ONGOING-DISCOUNT-YR09' and r.CommissionYear between YR09.StartYear and YR09.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors YR10 on YR10.FeeType = 'VNB' and YR10.Category = 'COB-ONGOING-DISCOUNT-YR10' and r.CommissionYear between YR10.StartYear and YR10.EndYear 
	where	r.CalculationType = 'WEALTH-ONGOING'

	select @RowCount = @@rowcount
	set @ProcessMessage = '#owt_Recognition (ongoing yr2-10) = ' + convert(nvarchar(10), @RowCount)
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseLog, @ProcessMessage, null, @Module, @Client
	
	/****************************************************************************

		Now add up all the numbers
																		
	****************************************************************************/
	
	update r
		set OngoingTotal	=	OngoingYr01 + OngoingYr02 + OngoingYr03 + OngoingYr04 + OngoingYr05 +
								OngoingYr06 + OngoingYr07 + OngoingYr08 + OngoingYr09 + OngoingYr10,
			PointsTotal		=	OngoingYr01 + OngoingYr02 + OngoingYr03 + OngoingYr04 + OngoingYr05 +
								OngoingYr06 + OngoingYr07 + OngoingYr08 + OngoingYr09 + OngoingYr10 +
								Initial + MBF	-- Note BSC is already included in the Ongoing, so don't include it in the Points Total.
	from	#AG_owt_Recognition_SEPARATE_ONGOING r

	select @RowCount = @@rowcount
	set @ProcessMessage = '#owt_Recognition (points total) = ' + convert(nvarchar(10), @RowCount)
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseLog, @ProcessMessage, null, @Module, @Client

	/****************************************************************************

		Merge the temporary table into the permanent table (IC data)
																		
	****************************************************************************/

	BEGIN TRANSACTION

	declare @SummaryOfChanges table (Change varchar(20))
	merge	dbo.AG_owt_Recognition_SEPARATE_ONGOING as trg
	using	#AG_owt_Recognition_SEPARATE_ONGOING as src
	on		trg.SourceID = src.SourceID
	and		trg.Source = src.Source
	when	matched 
	and		isnull(trg.PointsTotal,0) <> isnull(src.PointsTotal,0)
	then	update 
				set trg.CaseID = src.CaseID,
					trg.TransactionID = src.TransactionID,
					trg.Policy = src.Policy,
					trg.ProductCode = src.ProductCode,
					trg.BusinessCode = src.BusinessCode,
					trg.SellerCode = src.SellerCode,					--AG 13/06/2018
					trg.PointsTotal = src.PointsTotal,
					trg.BSC = src.BSC,
					trg.MBF = src.MBF,
					trg.Initial = src.Initial,
					trg.OngoingTotal = src.OngoingTotal,
					trg.OngoingYr01 = src.OngoingYr01,
					trg.OngoingYr02 = src.OngoingYr02,
					trg.OngoingYr03 = src.OngoingYr03,
					trg.OngoingYr04 = src.OngoingYr04,
					trg.OngoingYr05 = src.OngoingYr05,
					trg.OngoingYr06 = src.OngoingYr06,
					trg.OngoingYr07 = src.OngoingYr07,
					trg.OngoingYr08 = src.OngoingYr08,
					trg.OngoingYr09 = src.OngoingYr09,
					trg.OngoingYr10 = src.OngoingYr10,
					trg.FCARate = src.FCARate,
					trg.RetentionRate = src.RetentionRate,
					trg.RetentionRateBroker = src.RetentionRateBroker,
					trg.OngoingServicingRate = src.OngoingServicingRate,
					trg.OngoingServicingSource = src.OngoingServicingSource,
					trg.DA = src.DA,
					trg.AmountReceived = src.AmountReceived,
					trg.Premium = src.Premium,
					trg.AgentSplit = src.AgentSplit,
					trg.CommissionType = src.CommissionType,
					trg.CommissionTypeDesc = src.CommissionTypeDesc,
					trg.PayBasisCode = src.PayBasisCode,				--AG 13/06/2018
					trg.PayBasisDesc = src.PayBasisDesc,				--AG 13/06/2018
					trg.PaymentMatchedDate = src.PaymentMatchedDate,	--AG 13/06/2018	
					trg.Month = src.Month,
					trg.FrequencyCode = src.FrequencyCode,
					trg.FrequencyDesc = src.FrequencyDesc,
					trg.ReassignedProductGroupCode = src.ReassignedProductGroupCode,	--AG 05/06/2018
					trg.ReassignedProductGroupName = src.ReassignedProductGroupName,	--AG 05/06/2018
					trg.RecognitionType = src.RecognitionType,
					trg.CalculationType = src.CalculationType,
					trg.DateLastUpdated = @DateLastUpdated
	when	not matched by target 
	then	insert
			(
				SourceID,
				CaseID,
				TransactionID,
				Policy,
				ProductCode,
				BusinessCode,
				SellerCode,							--AG 13/06/2018
				PointsTotal,
				BSC,
				MBF,
				Initial,
				OngoingTotal,
				OngoingYr01,
				OngoingYr02,
				OngoingYr03,
				OngoingYr04,
				OngoingYr05,
				OngoingYr06,
				OngoingYr07,
				OngoingYr08,
				OngoingYr09,
				OngoingYr10,
				FCARate,
				RetentionRate,
				RetentionRateBroker,
				OngoingServicingRate,
				OngoingServicingSource,
				DA,
				AmountReceived,
				Premium,
				AgentSplit,
				CommissionType,
				CommissionTypeDesc,
				PayBasisCode,						--AG 13/06/2018
				PayBasisDesc,						--AG 13/06/2018
				PaymentMatchedDate,					--AG 13/06/2018
				Month,
				FrequencyCode,
				FrequencyDesc,
				ReassignedProductGroupCode,			--AG 05/06/2018
				ReassignedProductGroupName,			--AG 05/06/2018
				RecognitionType,
				CalculationType,
				Source,
				DateInserted,
				DateLastUpdated
			)		
			values
			(
				src.SourceID,
				src.CaseID,
				src.TransactionID,
				src.Policy,
				src.ProductCode,
				src.BusinessCode,
				src.SellerCode,						--AG 13/06/2018
				src.PointsTotal,
				src.BSC,
				src.MBF,
				src.Initial,
				src.OngoingTotal,
				src.OngoingYr01,
				src.OngoingYr02,
				src.OngoingYr03,
				src.OngoingYr04,
				src.OngoingYr05,
				src.OngoingYr06,
				src.OngoingYr07,
				src.OngoingYr08,
				src.OngoingYr09,
				src.OngoingYr10,
				src.FCARate,
				src.RetentionRate,
				src.RetentionRateBroker,
				src.OngoingServicingRate,
				src.OngoingServicingSource,
				src.DA,
				src.AmountReceived,
				src.Premium,
				src.AgentSplit,
				src.CommissionType,
				src.CommissionTypeDesc,
				src.PayBasisCode,					--AG 13/06/2018
				src.PayBasisDesc,					--AG 13/06/2018
				src.PaymentMatchedDate,				--AG 13/06/2018
				src.Month,
				src.FrequencyCode,
				src.FrequencyDesc,
				src.ReassignedProductGroupCode,		--AG 05/06/2018
				src.ReassignedProductGroupName,		--AG 05/06/2018
				src.RecognitionType,
				src.CalculationType,
				src.Source,
				src.DateInserted,
				src.DateLastUpdated)				--Merge statements must have a ;
	output $action into @SummaryOfChanges;
						
	/****************************************************************************

		Update OpenAccess
																		
	****************************************************************************/

/*	
	--Do not include MBF in the OpenAccess Commission Listing as it is on the MBF download
	--and we don't want MBF double counting.
	update	oal
		set VNB_Points = r.PointsTotal - r.MBF		--AG 04/06/2018 (2)
	from	msit_CommissionStatement cs
/*			inner join (select	distinct PKID
						from	owt_TransformationMovements tm 
						where	tm.DriverTableName = 'sa_swift_S_AGMFIL'
						and		tm.CommissionStatement = 'Y') tm on tm.PKID = cs.PendingPaymentID
*/			inner join msit_OpenworkAdviserListing oal on oal.SourceID = cs.ID and oal.Source = 'Openwork 2006'
			inner join owt_Recognition r 
						on r.SourceID = cs.PendingPaymentID
						and r.Source = oal.Source
	--where	isnull(oal.VNB_Points,0) <> isnull(r.PointsTotal,0)
	
	select @OALRowCount = @@rowcount
*/
	COMMIT TRANSACTION      
	
	select	@RowCount = COUNT(*)
	from	@SummaryOfChanges
	where	Change = 'INSERT'

	set @ProcessMessage = 'owt_Recognition (insert) = ' + convert(nvarchar(10), @RowCount)
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseLog, @ProcessMessage, null, @Module, @Client

	select	@RowCount = COUNT(*)
	from	@SummaryOfChanges
	where	Change = 'UPDATE'

	set @ProcessMessage = 'owt_Recognition (update) = ' + convert(nvarchar(10), @RowCount)
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseLog, @ProcessMessage, null, @Module, @Client
/*
	set @ProcessMessage = 'msit_OpenworkAdviserListing (update) = ' + convert(nvarchar(10), @OALRowCount)
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseLog, @ProcessMessage, null, @Module, @Client
*/
	/****************************************************************************

		T H E   E N D
																		
	****************************************************************************/
	
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseEnd, @ProcName, null, @Module, @Client

END TRY

BEGIN CATCH 

	select @ErrNum = ERROR_NUMBER(), @ErrMsg = ERROR_MESSAGE(), @ErrSev = ERROR_SEVERITY(), @ErrLine = ERROR_LINE(), @ErrState = XACT_STATE()
	set @ErrMsg = REPLACE(@ErrMsg, '.', '') + ' (error no: ' + CAST(@ErrNum AS VARCHAR(10)) + ') on line ' + CAST(@ErrLine AS VARCHAR(10))
	
	-- Test XACT_STATE for 0, 1, or -1.
    -- If 1, the transaction is committable.
    -- If -1, the transaction is uncommittable and should be rolled back.
    -- If 0, there is no transaction and a commit or rollback operation would generate an error.

	if @ErrState = -1			-- Transaction is uncommitable
		rollback transaction

	if @ErrState = 1			
		commit transaction

	-- Error message line 1
	set @ErrMsgBrief = left(@ErrMsg,100)
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseError, @ErrMsgBrief, null, @Module, @Client
	
	-- Error message line 2 - if any text exists
	set @ErrMsgBrief = substring(@ErrMsg,101,100)
	if len(@ErrMsgBrief) > 0
		exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseError, @ErrMsgBrief, null, @Module, @Client

	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseEnd, @ProcName, null, @Module, @Client

	RAISERROR(@ErrMsg, @ErrSev , 1)

END CATCH

/****************************************************************************

			E N D															

****************************************************************************/

return @ErrNum


GO
/****** Object:  StoredProcedure [dbo].[owp_RecognitionSwiftONGOING_Backup20180703AG]    Script Date: 7/3/2026 3:44:25 PM ******/
SET ANSI_NULLS ON
GO
SET QUOTED_IDENTIFIER ON
GO
/*********************************************************************************************************

Program:		owp_RecognitionSwift					
Author:			Alan Groves
Date created:	11/04/2018
											
Description:
===========

This proc populates the new recognition table called "owt_Recognition" with "Value of New Business"
(VNB) points.

This proc handles all of the swift data which includes:
WEALTH - COB business i.e. pensions and investments
MORTGAGES
PROTECTION

Note: There is a separate proc that calculates the GI VNB points from the Paymentshield data.

The approach of this proc is to use the incremental PendingPaymentIDs from the overnight batch
to calculate the VNB points in a temporary table.

The temporary table is then merged with the permanent table to make the calculated (or
re-calculated values) permanent.

Terms
-----
BSC			- Business Service Charge.
MBF			- Mortgage Broker Fee.
OGS			- Ongoing Servicing.
BSC Rate	- 0.12% at the time of writing (24/04/2018). This could be changed by the business, but
				would also require some DEV work in OWS.
DF			- Discount Factor.
DA			- Distribution Allowance (the total amount paid out by the provider to Openwork)
AUM			- Assets Under Management. Basically the amount invested or the premium on investment
				cases.
Average AUM - Average amount invested annually which is equivalent to 6 months' premium.

THE CALCULATIONS
================

There are two potential parts: initial + ongoing (if ongoing applies). If BSC (applies to ongoing 
only) and MBF (applies to mortgages only) apply, then these are also included:

MORTGAGE
--------
Part 1: MBF column = (Advice Fee Amount X Broker Retention Rate) - (Advice Fee Amount X Mort FCA Rate)
Part 2: Initial column = (Proc Fee Amount X Mortgage Retention Rate) - (Proc Fee X Mort FCA Rate) 
Mortgage Points Total = Initial + MBF

PROTECTION
----------
= (DA X Protection Retention Rate) - (DA X Protection FCA Rate) 
Protection Points Total = Initial

WEALTH (COB i.e. pensions and investments)
------
Part 1: Initial column = (DA X Wealth Retention Rate) - (DA X Wealth FCA Rate)

Part 2:

****XXXX****

NOTE: Where the BSC rate is greater than the ongoing rate, then BSC gets ALL of the AVAILABLE 
ongoing.

****XXXX****

REGULAR - BSC applies:
Year 1 column = BSC Points + Non-BSC Points - FCA Points
Non-BSC Points = Ave AUM X (OGS Rate - BSC Rate) X COB Retention Rate
BSC Points = Ave AUM X BSC Rate
FCA Points = Ave AUM X OGS Rate X COB FCA Rate

REGULAR - Non-BSC: 
Year 1 column = (Ave AUM X OGS Rate X COB Retention Rate) - (Ave AUM X OGS Rate X COB FCA Rate)

SINGLE - BSC applies:
Year 1 column = (AUM X BSC Rate) + (AUM X (OGS Rate - BSC Rate) X COB Retention Rate) - (AUM X OGS Rate X COB FCA Rate) 

SINGLE - Non-BSC:
Year 1 column = (AUM X OGS Rate X COB Retention Rate) - (AUM X OGS Rate X COB FCA Rate) 

Then years 2 to 10 are calculated by applying a discount factor
Year  2 = Year 1 X  3 X DF
Year  3 = Year 1 X  5 X DF
Year  4 = Year 1 X  7 X DF
Year  5 = Year 1 X  9 X DF
Year  6 = Year 1 X 11 X DF
Year  7 = Year 1 X 13 X DF
Year  8 = Year 1 X 15 X DF
Year  9 = Year 1 X 17 X DF
Year 10 = Year 1 X 19 X DF

Wealth Points Total =	OngoingYr01 + OngoingYr02 + OngoingYr03 + OngoingYr04 + OngoingYr05 +
						OngoingYr06 + OngoingYr07 + OngoingYr08 + OngoingYr09 + OngoingYr10 +
						Initial

GI
--
See stored proc "owp_RecognitionGIPaymentshield".
 
Notes:
-----

1)	There is a BSC column on table owt_Recognition. However, BSC is already included in the ongoing
	years 1 - 10, so the BSC column does not need to be added in. In fact you will double count if 
	you attempt to do anything with it other than display it.

2)	Occasionally an investment case may receive two or more cheques which
	then go through Swift as two or more SINGLE investments on the SAME
	slice. Although the INITIAL VNB calculation will pro-rata correctly
	because it is based on the amount received, this scenario will cause
	ongoing VNB to be calculated on each of the payment records and so will 
	double count (or worse if there are more than two cheques received).
	Since de-coupling IC from ongoing i.e. they now have separate rows on
	table owt_Recognition, the issue of multiple cheques should no longer
	cause ongoing double counting.


This proc is called as follows:
	declare @rc int
	exec @rc = dbo.owp_RecognitionSwift 'Openwork', 'Recognition'
	select @rc

					
AMENDMENT HISTORY				
=================								

Date		Author		Description
----		------		-----------
26/04/2018	A Groves	Only include rows in the OGS lookups where the OngoingServiceFee > 0.0.
						Negative OGS rates are bad data and at the time of writing, there are
						39 of these.
27/04/2018	A Groves	Additional calculation and condition to handle the scenario where BSC applies
						but the OGS Rate is less than the BSC rate. Previously, this caused the
						total ongoing to be zero. However, there are two components to ongoing VNB 
						points, the BSC share and the non-BSC share. So the BSC share (which takes 
						100% when the OGS rate is less than 0.12%) should still yield ongoing points.
27/04/2018	A Groves	Single ongoing Yr01 corrected by applying outer brackets before signing the result.
03/05/2018	A Groves	Added update of column "msit_OpenworkAdviserListing.VNB_Points".
18/05/2018	A Groves	Changed mortgage calculation to use e.AMOUNT_REC instead of pt.CommInitialAmount
						as Marcus Cossey wanted the actual amount received to be used for the DA.
04/06/2018	A Groves	1) In the REGULAR section of column "OngoingYr01", the condition for cs.FrequencyCode <> 6
							was added to ensure the code differentiates to the SINGLE section.
						2) Exclude MBF from the OpenAccess table (msit_OpenworkAdviserListing) as this
							is shown on the MBF download and would otherwise incur MBF double counting.
05/06/2018	A Groves	1) Marcus Cossey advised that investments should get ongoing for years 1 to 6 and
							pensions for years 1 to 10. Previously, both lines of business got years 1 to 10.
						2) Marcus Cossey asked for split payments (i.e. where multiple cheques are processed
							for a SINGLE investment) to only claculate ongoing VNB on the oldest payment. 
11/06/2018	A Groves	1) PSD processed a protection clawback statement as fee type initial. These clawbacks
							all generated +ve instead of -ve VNB points. A tweak was added to ensure that the 
							absolute value of AMOUNT_REC is used to ensure the VNB is correctly signed. 
						2) Another unknown business rule has surfaced: Previously, only initial, clawbacks and
							adjustments on slices created new from 2017 were included. This rule only applies
							to initial. Clawbacks and adjustments can belong to a slice created at any point
							in the past. However, note that the payment (irrespective of whether it is +ve or 
							-ve), must not pre-date 2017.
13/06/2018	A Groves	Marcus asked for SellerCode and PaymentMatchedDate to be added so he need only use 
							the one table for both the adviser and enterprise leagues. PayBasisCode and 
							PayBasisDesc were also added at the same time as these are used in the calculations.
*************************************************************************************************************/

CREATE PROCEDURE [dbo].[owp_RecognitionSwiftONGOING_Backup20180703AG]
	@Client		varchar(50),
	@Module		Varchar(50)

AS

set nocount on

declare		@PhaseStart				varchar(50),
			@PhaseEnd				varchar(50),
			@PhaseError				varchar(50),
			@PhaseLog				varchar(50),
			@ProcName				varchar(100),
			@ProcessMessage			varchar(100),
			@RowCount				int,
			@OALRowCount			int,
			@ErrMsg					nvarchar(4000),
			@ErrMsgBrief			nvarchar(100),
			@ErrNum					int,
			@ErrSev					int,
			@ErrLine				int,
			@ErrState				int,
			@DateLastUpdated		datetime,
			@OwlManager2Code		nvarchar(10)
			
/****************************************************************************

	Set initial parameters																
																		
****************************************************************************/

set @ProcName			= object_name(@@procid)
set @PhaseStart			= 'START'
set @PhaseEnd			= 'END'
set @PhaseError			= 'ERROR'
set @PhaseLog			= 'LOG'
set @ErrNum				= 0	
set @DateLastUpdated	= getdate()

set @OwlManager2Code = (select cde.Code from msit_MIWarehouseCodesAndDescriptions cde
			where cde.ColumnName = 'Manager2Code' and cde.Description = 'Owl Financial')

-- We want this logging irrespective of whether or not there is a rollback
exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseStart, @ProcName, null, @Module, @Client

/****************************************************************************

	Populate the table																
																		
****************************************************************************/

SET XACT_ABORT ON	-- Needed if XACT_STATE() function is used.

BEGIN TRY

	/****************************************************************************

		Link OWS data to Swift data to enable the ongoing servicng (OGS) rate
		to be looked up.
																		
	****************************************************************************/
	
	select	distinct s.PersonID, swp.Client_Num, p.InternalProductID, swp.ProductCode 
	into	#SwiftOWSClientLink
	from	sa_ows_Sale s
			inner join sa_ows_Policies p on p.SaleID = s.SaleID
			inner join mstt_Policies swp on swp.PolicyRef = p.PolicyID
	where	s.DateSubmitted is not null
	--and		s.PersonID = 146030

	select @RowCount = @@rowcount
	set @ProcessMessage = '#SwiftOWSClientLink = ' + convert(nvarchar(10), @RowCount)
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseLog, @ProcessMessage, null, @Module, @Client

	-- The OGS rate is stored for the client/product combination
	select	link.Client_Num, link.ProductCode, max(ogs.OngoingServiceFee) as OngoingServiceFee
	into	#OGSLookUp
	from	#SwiftOWSClientLink link 
			inner join mstt_ProductHierarchy ph on ph.ProductCode = link.ProductCode
			inner join Submission.sa_ows_SubmittedProductCurrentOngoingServiceFee ogs
							on ogs.PersonID = link.PersonID
							and ogs.InternalProductID = (case when ph.RDRType = 'ONPLAT' 
															then -2 
															else link.InternalProductID 
														 end)
	where	ogs.OngoingServiceFee > 0.0							--AG 26/04/2018
	group	by 	link.Client_Num, link.ProductCode

	select @RowCount = @@rowcount
	set @ProcessMessage = '#OGSLookUp = ' + convert(nvarchar(10), @RowCount)
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseLog, @ProcessMessage, null, @Module, @Client

	create index idx_OGSLookUp on #OGSLookUp (Client_num, ProductCode)

	--This is an additional catch for OGS by storing the client's highest OGS
	--rate against their client number. This lookup will apply if the first
	--look up fails. The first lookup can fail, for example, if the case was 
	--not submitted on OWS i.e. the CaseID has a "17" prefix. 
	select	Client_Num, MAX(OngoingServiceFee) as OngoingServiceFee
	into	#OGSLookUpClient
	from	#OGSLookUp
	group	by Client_Num

	select @RowCount = @@rowcount
	set @ProcessMessage = '#OGSLookUpClient = ' + convert(nvarchar(10), @RowCount)
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseLog, @ProcessMessage, null, @Module, @Client
	
	create index idx_OGSLookUpClient on #OGSLookUpClient (Client_num)

	/****************************************************************************

		Calculate VNB and populate the temporary table with the results
		
		Note that there are oddities like LV protection payments which always
		come in pairs with one large and one much smaller amount (e.g. TransactionID 
		= 6684787.) The system treats both payments in the pair as first payments 
		and the (projected) DA associated with both is the same (because it's on 
		the policy transaction). 
		
		There is also a requirement to front-load VNB points on accrual and level
		payments. This means calculate the VNB for the full amount of the DA and 
		put it on the first payment record and then on all subsequent accrual and 
		level payments, set the VNB to zero.
		
		Thus two different sources of DA are used depending on whether we need the
		full DA amount for accruals and level or the actual amount received for all
		other scenarios including the LV split payment scenario. The two sources are:
		
		mstt_PolicyTransactions.CommInitialAmount - Full (projected) DA amount
		
		mstt_Expectation.AMOUNT_REC - The DA actually received. This handles the
										LV scenario whereby the AMOUNT_REC is 
										proportioned across the two payments received.   
																		
	****************************************************************************/

	select	top 0 
			*, 
			convert(int,NULL) as CommissionYear
	into	#AG_owt_Recognition_SEPARATE_ONGOING
	from	AG_owt_Recognition_SEPARATE_ONGOING

	/****************************************************************************

		Phase 1 - Process all but regular accrual cases with clawbacks/adjustments
		Accruals are front loaded unless their latest payment is a clawback/adjudtment
		in which case they accrue VNB points on a per payment basis and so these
		are dealt with in Phases 2 and 3.
																		
	****************************************************************************/

	insert into #AG_owt_Recognition_SEPARATE_ONGOING
	(
		SourceID,
		CaseID,
		TransactionID,
		Policy,
		ProductCode,
		BusinessCode,
		SellerCode,						--AG 13/06/2018
		PointsTotal,
		BSC,
		MBF,
		Initial,
		OngoingTotal,
		OngoingYr01,
		OngoingYr02,
		OngoingYr03,
		OngoingYr04,
		OngoingYr05,
		OngoingYr06,
		OngoingYr07,
		OngoingYr08,
		OngoingYr09,
		OngoingYr10,
		FCARate,
		RetentionRate,
		RetentionRateBroker,
		OngoingServicingRate,
		OngoingServicingSource,
		DA,
		AmountReceived,
		Premium,
		AgentSplit,
		CommissionType,
		CommissionTypeDesc,
		PayBasisCode,					--AG 13/06/2018
		PayBasisDesc,					--AG 13/06/2018
		PaymentMatchedDate,				--AG 13/06/2018
		Month,
		FrequencyCode,
		FrequencyDesc,
		ReassignedProductGroupCode,		--AG 05/06/2018
		ReassignedProductGroupName,		--AG 05/06/2018
		RecognitionType,
		CalculationType,
		Source,
		DateInserted,
		DateLastUpdated,
		CommissionYear
	)
	select	cs.PendingPaymentID as SourceID,
			cs.CaseID,
			cs.TransactionID,
			cs.ExtPolicyNumber as Policy,
			cs.ProductCode,
			cs.BusinessCode,
			cs.AgentCode as SellerCode,				--AG 13/06/2018
			0.0 as PointsTotal,
			0.0 as BSC,
			case 
				when mbf.MortgageFeeID is not null and cs.INIssued <> 0 then (((mbf.AdviceFeeAmount)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * MRbkr.FACTOR) - ((mbf.AdviceFeeAmount)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * Mfca.FACTOR)) --Note that mbf.AdviceFeeAmount is signed correctly - so no coding for signing is needed here
				else 0.0
			end as MBF,
			case 
				--When the adviser has changed, the AgentSplit can become zero in which case the ELITE points should be zero.
				when cs.AgentSplit = 0 then 0
				
				--WEALTH CALCULATION START
				--Indemnity payments or SINGLEs or IC Clawbacks or IC adjustments Start
				when (ph.ProductCategoryCode = 1 or pcc.KeyValue2 = '1') and (cs.FrequencyCode = 6 or cs.PayBasisCode in ('T') or cs.CommissionType in (2,17)) and cs.commissiontype in (1,2,17) and cs.INIssued <> 0 then (((e.AMOUNT_REC)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * Crate.FACTOR) - ((e.AMOUNT_REC)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * Cfca.FACTOR)) * case when cs.INIssued < 0 then -1 else 1 end
				--Indemnity payments or SINGLEs or IC Clawbacks or IC adjustments End
				--Accruals & Level Start
				when (ph.ProductCategoryCode = 1 or pcc.KeyValue2 = '1') and cs.INIssued <> 0 then (((pt.CommInitialAmount)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * Crate.FACTOR) - ((pt.CommInitialAmount)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * Cfca.FACTOR)) * case when cs.INIssued < 0 then -1 else 1 end
				--Accruals & Level End
				--WEALTH CALCULATION END
				
				--MORTGAGE CALCULATION START
				--Note: The MBF component has its own table column
				--Only 1 payment for mortgages
				when ph.ProductGroupCode = 3 and cs.INIssued <> 0 then (((e.AMOUNT_REC)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * MRproc.FACTOR) - ((e.AMOUNT_REC)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * Mfca.FACTOR)) * case when cs.INIssued < 0 then -1 else 1 end	--AG 18/05/2018
				--MORTGAGE CALCULATION END
				
				--PROTECTION CALCULATION START
				--Indemnity payments or SINGLEs or IC Clawbacks or IC adjustments Start
				when ph.ProductGroupCode = 6 and (cs.FrequencyCode = 6 or cs.PayBasisCode in ('T') or cs.CommissionType in (2,17)) and cs.commissiontype in (1,2,17) and cs.INIssued <> 0 then ((abs(e.AMOUNT_REC)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * Prate.FACTOR) - (abs(e.AMOUNT_REC)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * Pfca.FACTOR)) * case when cs.INIssued < 0 then -1 else 1 end	--AG 11/06/2018 (1)
				--Indemnity payments or SINGLEs or IC Clawbacks or IC adjustments End
				--Accruals & Level Start
				when ph.ProductGroupCode = 6 and cs.INIssued <> 0 then (((pt.CommInitialAmount)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * Prate.FACTOR) - ((pt.CommInitialAmount)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * Pfca.FACTOR)) * case when cs.INIssued < 0 then -1 else 1 end
				--Accruals & Level End
				--PROTECTION CALCULATION END

				else 0.0

			end as Initial,
			0.0 as OngoingTotal,
			0.0 as OngoingYr01,
			0.0 as OngoingYr02,
			0.0 as OngoingYr03,
			0.0 as OngoingYr04,
			0.0 as OngoingYr05,
			0.0 as OngoingYr06,
			0.0 as OngoingYr07,
			0.0 as OngoingYr08,
			0.0 as OngoingYr09,
			0.0 as OngoingYr10,
			case 
				when (ph.ProductCategoryCode = 1 or pcc.KeyValue2 = '1') then Cfca.FACTOR*100.0		--COB
				when ph.ProductGroupCode = 3 then Mfca.FACTOR*100.0		--MORT
				when ph.ProductGroupCode = 6 then Pfca.FACTOR*100.0		--PROT
				else 0.0
			end as FCARate,
			case 
				when (ph.ProductCategoryCode = 1 or pcc.KeyValue2 = '1') then Crate.FACTOR*100.0	--COB
				when ph.ProductGroupCode = 3 then MRproc.FACTOR*100.0	--MORT
				when ph.ProductGroupCode = 6 then Prate.FACTOR*100.0	--PROT
				else 0.0
			end as RetentionRate,
			case 
				when mbf.MortgageFeeID is not null then  MRbkr.FACTOR*100.0	
				else 0.0
			end as RetentionRateBroker,
			null as OngoingServicingRate,
			null as OngoingServicingSource,
			pt.CommInitialAmount as DA,
			e.AMOUNT_REC as AmountReceived,
			cs.Premium,
			cs.AgentSplit,
			cs.CommissionType,
			left(cs.StandingOrderDesc,50) as CommissionTypeDesc,
			cs.PayBasisCode,							--AG 13/06/2018
			cs.PayBasisDesc,							--AG 13/06/2018
			cs.CreateDate as PaymentMatchedDate,		--AG 13/06/2018
			cs.Month,
			cs.FrequencyCode,
			cs.FrequencyDesc,
			pg.ProductGroupCode as ReassignedProductGroupCode,	--Force the re-assigned products...		AG 05/06/2018
			pg.ProductGroupName as ReassignedProductGroupName,	--...to be processed as investments		AG 05/06/2018
			'VNB-INI-PHASE-1' as RecognitionType,
			case 
				when (ph.ProductCategoryCode = 1 or pcc.KeyValue2 = '1') then 'WEALTH-INITIAL'
				when ph.ProductGroupCode = 3 then 'MORTGAGE'
				when ph.ProductGroupCode = 6 then 'PROTECTION'
				else null
			end as CalculationType,
			'Openwork 2006' as Source,
			@DateLastUpdated as DateInserted,
			@DateLastUpdated as DateLastUpdated,
			csp.year as CommissionYear
	--select count(*)
	from	msit_CommissionStatement cs
/*			inner join (select	distinct PKID
						from	owt_TransformationMovements tm 
						where	tm.DriverTableName = 'sa_swift_S_AGMFIL'
						and		tm.CommissionStatement = 'Y') tm on tm.PKID = cs.PendingPaymentID
*/			inner join mstt_Agents ag on ag.Code = cs.BusinessCode
			inner join mstt_PolicyTransactions pt on pt.ID = cs.TransactionID
			inner join mstt_Policies p on p.POL_NUM = pt.PolicyID
			inner join msit_CommissionStatementPeriods VNBStart on convert(date,pt.CreateDateTime) between VNBStart.PeriodStartDate and VNBStart.PeriodEndDate
			inner join msit_Commissionstatementperiods csp on csp.month = cs.month
			inner join mstt_ProductHierarchy ph on ph.productcode = cs.productcode
			inner join mstt_Expectation e on e.ID = cs.ExpectationID
			left join dbo.owt_MortgageBrokerFees mbf on mbf.PendingPaymentID = cs.PendingPaymentID and mbf.AdviceFeeCharged = 'Yes'
			left join owt_SelectionControl SC
						on SC.Process = 'ElitePoints' 
						and SC.KeyType = 'NSCPotCode' 
						and cs.CreateDate between SC.EffectiveStartDate and SC.EffectiveEndDate
			left join mstt_Commissions BSCpot
						on BSCpot.TransactionID = cs.TransactionID 
						and BSCpot.Agent_Code = sc.KeyValue
						and BSCpot.CommissionType = 10
			left join owt_SelectionControl SFMPC						
						on SFMPC.Process = 'ElitePoints' 
						and SFMPC.KeyType = 'ServicingFeeMarginPotCode' 
						and cs.CreateDate between SFMPC.EffectiveStartDate and SFMPC.EffectiveEndDate
			left join mstt_Commissions SFMpot							
						on SFMpot.TransactionID = cs.TransactionID 
						and SFMpot.Agent_Code = SFMPC.KeyValue
						and SFMpot.CommissionType = 10	
			left join owt_SelectionControl pcc 
						on pcc.Process = 'ElitePoints'
						and pcc.KeyType = 'ProductCategoryCode'
						and pcc.KeyValue = cs.ProductCode	
						and cs.CreateDate between pcc.EffectiveStartDate and pcc.EffectiveEndDate
			left join owt_SelectionControl ogsdflt 
						on ogsdflt.Process = 'ElitePoints'
						and ogsdflt.KeyType = 'DefaultOngoingServicingRate'
						and ogsdflt.SelectionType = 'VNB'
						and ogsdflt.KeyValue = case when ph.RDRType = 'ONPLAT' then 'ONPLAT' else 'OFPLAT' end
						and cs.CreateDate between ogsdflt.EffectiveStartDate and ogsdflt.EffectiveEndDate
			left join mstt_CodeProductGroup pg on pg.ProductGroupCode = case when pcc.KeyValue2 = '1' then 2 else ph.ProductGroupCode end
			left join owt_EliteFactors Cfca on Cfca.FeeType = 'VNB' and Cfca.category = 'COB-FCA-RATE' and csp.year between Cfca.StartYear and Cfca.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors Crate on Crate.FeeType = 'VNB' and Crate.category = 'COB-RETENTION-RATE' and csp.year between Crate.StartYear and Crate.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors Mfca on Mfca.FeeType = 'VNB' and Mfca.category = 'MORT-FCA-RATE' and csp.year between Mfca.StartYear and Mfca.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors MRproc on MRproc.FeeType = 'VNB' and MRproc.category = 'MORT-RETENTION-RATE-PROC' and csp.year between MRproc.StartYear and MRproc.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors MRbkr on MRbkr.FeeType = 'VNB' and MRbkr.category = 'MORT-RETENTION-RATE-BROKER' and csp.year between MRbkr.StartYear and MRbkr.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors Pfca on Pfca.FeeType = 'VNB' and Pfca.category = 'PROT-FCA-RATE' and csp.year between Pfca.StartYear and Pfca.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors Prate on Prate.FeeType = 'VNB' and Prate.category = 'PROT-RETENTION-RATE' and csp.year between Prate.StartYear and Prate.EndYear 
			left join msit_CommissionStatement csadj 
						on csadj.TransactionID = cs.TransactionID 
						and csadj.AgentCode = cs.AgentCode 
						and csadj.CommissionType in (2,17)
						and	csadj.PayBasisCode in ('F')				--Accrual
						and	csadj.FrequencyCode <> 6				--Regular 
	where	cs.ReportingClassCode = 1
	and		ag.Manager2Code <> @OwlManager2Code		--Exclude Owl
	and		cs.INIssued <> 0
	and		csp.Year >= 2017						--Ensure in-scope payments are consistent with VNB start
	and		VNBStart.Year >= 2017
	and		cs.CommissionType in (1,2,17)
	and		abs(e.AMOUNT_REC) >= 0.01	
	--and		((VNBStart.Year >= 2017 and cs.CommissionType = 1 and e.AMOUNT_REC >= 0.01)		--VNB to start from new slices in 2017 for +ve payments but...			AG 11/06/2018 (2)
	--		or (cs.CommissionType in (2,17) or e.AMOUNT_REC <= -0.01))						--...for -ve payments, the slice can start from any date in the past	AG 11/06/2018 (2)
	and		csadj.ID is null						--Deal with accrual regular clawbacks/adjustments later

	select @RowCount = @@rowcount
	set @ProcessMessage = '#owt_Recognition (ini ph1 - no accr adj) = ' + convert(nvarchar(10), @RowCount)
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseLog, @ProcessMessage, null, @Module, @Client

	/****************************************************************************

		Now deal with accrual clawbacks and adjustments
																		
	****************************************************************************/

	--drop table #msit_CommissionStatementSUMMARY

	--Find transactions with clawbacks/adj on them
	select	cs.TransactionID,
			cs.AgentCode,
			Min(case when cs.CommissionType = 1 then cs.PendingPaymentID else null end) as MinInitialPendingPaymentID,
			MAX(case when cs.CommissionType = 1 then cs.PendingPaymentID else null end) as MaxInitialPendingPaymentID,
			MAX(case when cs.CommissionType in (2,17) then cs.PendingPaymentID else null end) as MaxAdjPendingPaymentID,
			null as MinInitialAfterAdjPendingPaymentID
	into	#msit_CommissionStatementSUMMARY
	from	msit_CommissionStatement cs
			inner join mstt_Agents ag on ag.Code = cs.BusinessCode
			inner join mstt_PolicyTransactions pt on pt.ID = cs.TransactionID
			inner join mstt_Policies p on p.POL_NUM = pt.PolicyID
			inner join msit_CommissionStatementPeriods VNBStart on convert(date,pt.CreateDateTime) between VNBStart.PeriodStartDate and VNBStart.PeriodEndDate
			inner join msit_Commissionstatementperiods csp on csp.month = cs.month
			inner join mstt_Expectation e on e.ID = cs.ExpectationID
			left join msit_CommissionStatement csadj 
						on csadj.TransactionID = cs.TransactionID 
						and csadj.AgentCode = cs.AgentCode 
						and csadj.CommissionType in (2,17)
						and	csadj.PayBasisCode in ('F')				--Accrual
						and	csadj.FrequencyCode <> 6				--Regular 
	where	cs.ReportingClassCode = 1
	and		cs.CommissionType in (1,2,17)			--We want all the initial payment types (i.e. not trail (ongoing))
	and		ag.Manager2Code <> @OwlManager2Code		--Exclude Owl
	and		csp.Year >= 2017						--Ensure in-scope payments are consistent with VNB start
	and		VNBStart.Year >= 2017 
	and		abs(e.AMOUNT_REC) >= 0.01	
	and		csadj.ID is not null					--select regular accrual transactions with clawbacks/adjustments
	--and cs.TransactionID in (5613333,6296827)
	group by	cs.TransactionID,
				cs.AgentCode

	select @RowCount = @@rowcount
	set @ProcessMessage = '#msit_CommissionStatementSUMMARY (accr adj txns) = ' + convert(nvarchar(10), @RowCount)
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseLog, @ProcessMessage, null, @Module, @Client

	--Get first initial payment after last clawback/adj
	update css
		set MinInitialAfterAdjPendingPaymentID = summ.MinPendingPaymentID 
	from  #msit_CommissionStatementSUMMARY css
			inner join  (
						select cssinner.TransactionID, cssinner.AgentCode, min(cs.PendingPaymentID) as MinPendingPaymentID
						from #msit_CommissionStatementSUMMARY cssinner
								inner join msit_CommissionStatement cs
											on cs.TransactionID = cssinner.TransactionID
											and cs.AgentCode = cssinner.AgentCode
						where cs.PendingPaymentID > cssinner.MaxAdjPendingPaymentID
						group by cssinner.TransactionID, cssinner.AgentCode
						) summ on  summ.TransactionID = css.TransactionID
							   and summ.AgentCode = css.AgentCode

	select @RowCount = @@rowcount
	set @ProcessMessage = '#msit_CommissionStatementSUMMARY (1st IC after adj) = ' + convert(nvarchar(10), @RowCount)
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseLog, @ProcessMessage, null, @Module, @Client

	/****************************************************************************

		Phase 2 - This phase deals with regular accrual cases where there is at 
		least one clawback/adjustment. In this scenario the VNB is changed from 
		front loaded to a per payment basis.
																		
	****************************************************************************/

	insert into #AG_owt_Recognition_SEPARATE_ONGOING
	(
		SourceID,
		CaseID,
		TransactionID,
		Policy,
		ProductCode,
		BusinessCode,
		SellerCode,						
		PointsTotal,
		BSC,
		MBF,
		Initial,
		OngoingTotal,
		OngoingYr01,
		OngoingYr02,
		OngoingYr03,
		OngoingYr04,
		OngoingYr05,
		OngoingYr06,
		OngoingYr07,
		OngoingYr08,
		OngoingYr09,
		OngoingYr10,
		FCARate,
		RetentionRate,
		RetentionRateBroker,
		OngoingServicingRate,
		OngoingServicingSource,
		DA,
		AmountReceived,
		Premium,
		AgentSplit,
		CommissionType,
		CommissionTypeDesc,
		PayBasisCode,					
		PayBasisDesc,					
		PaymentMatchedDate,				
		Month,
		FrequencyCode,
		FrequencyDesc,
		ReassignedProductGroupCode,		
		ReassignedProductGroupName,		
		RecognitionType,
		CalculationType,
		Source,
		DateInserted,
		DateLastUpdated,
		CommissionYear
	)
	select	cs.PendingPaymentID as SourceID,
			cs.CaseID,
			cs.TransactionID,
			cs.ExtPolicyNumber as Policy,
			cs.ProductCode,
			cs.BusinessCode,
			cs.AgentCode as SellerCode,				
			0.0 as PointsTotal,
			0.0 as BSC,
			case 
				when mbf.MortgageFeeID is not null and cs.INIssued <> 0 then (((mbf.AdviceFeeAmount)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * MRbkr.FACTOR) - ((mbf.AdviceFeeAmount)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * Mfca.FACTOR)) --Note that mbf.AdviceFeeAmount is signed correctly - so no coding for signing is needed here
				else 0.0
			end as MBF,
			case 
				--When the adviser has changed, the AgentSplit can become zero in which case the ELITE points should be zero.
				when cs.AgentSplit = 0 then 0
				
				--WEALTH CALCULATION START
				--Indemnity payments or SINGLEs or IC Clawbacks or IC adjustments Start
				--THIS SCENARIO DOESN'T OCCUR IN PHASE 2
				--Indemnity payments or SINGLEs or IC Clawbacks or IC adjustments End
				--Accruals & Level Start
				when (ph.ProductCategoryCode = 1 or pcc.KeyValue2 = '1') then (((e.AMOUNT_REC)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * Crate.FACTOR) - ((e.AMOUNT_REC)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * Cfca.FACTOR)) * case when cs.CommissionType in (2,17) then -1 else 1 end
				--Accruals & Level End
				--WEALTH CALCULATION END
				
				--MORTGAGE CALCULATION START
				--Note: The MBF component has its own table column
				--Only 1 payment for mortgages
				when ph.ProductGroupCode = 3 then (((e.AMOUNT_REC)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * MRproc.FACTOR) - ((e.AMOUNT_REC)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * Mfca.FACTOR)) * case when cs.CommissionType in (2,17) then -1 else 1 end	
				--MORTGAGE CALCULATION END
				
				--PROTECTION CALCULATION START
				--Indemnity payments or SINGLEs or IC Clawbacks or IC adjustments Start
				--THIS SCENARIO DOESN'T OCCUR IN PHASE 2
				--Indemnity payments or SINGLEs or IC Clawbacks or IC adjustments End
				--Accruals & Level Start
				when ph.ProductGroupCode = 6 then (((e.AMOUNT_REC)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * Prate.FACTOR) - ((e.AMOUNT_REC)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * Pfca.FACTOR)) * case when cs.CommissionType in (2,17) then -1 else 1 end
				--Accruals & Level End
				--PROTECTION CALCULATION END

				else 0.0

			end as Initial,
			0.0 as OngoingTotal,
			0.0 as OngoingYr01,
			0.0 as OngoingYr02,
			0.0 as OngoingYr03,
			0.0 as OngoingYr04,
			0.0 as OngoingYr05,
			0.0 as OngoingYr06,
			0.0 as OngoingYr07,
			0.0 as OngoingYr08,
			0.0 as OngoingYr09,
			0.0 as OngoingYr10,
			case 
				when (ph.ProductCategoryCode = 1 or pcc.KeyValue2 = '1') then Cfca.FACTOR*100.0		--COB
				when ph.ProductGroupCode = 3 then Mfca.FACTOR*100.0		--MORT
				when ph.ProductGroupCode = 6 then Pfca.FACTOR*100.0		--PROT
				else 0.0
			end as FCARate,
			case 
				when (ph.ProductCategoryCode = 1 or pcc.KeyValue2 = '1') then Crate.FACTOR*100.0	--COB
				when ph.ProductGroupCode = 3 then MRproc.FACTOR*100.0	--MORT
				when ph.ProductGroupCode = 6 then Prate.FACTOR*100.0	--PROT
				else 0.0
			end as RetentionRate,
			case 
				when mbf.MortgageFeeID is not null then  MRbkr.FACTOR*100.0	
				else 0.0
			end as RetentionRateBroker,
			null as OngoingServicingRate,
			null as OngoingServicingSource,
			pt.CommInitialAmount as DA,
			e.AMOUNT_REC as AmountReceived,
			cs.Premium,
			cs.AgentSplit,
			cs.CommissionType,
			left(cs.StandingOrderDesc,50) as CommissionTypeDesc,
			cs.PayBasisCode,							
			cs.PayBasisDesc,							
			cs.CreateDate as PaymentMatchedDate,		
			cs.Month,
			cs.FrequencyCode,
			cs.FrequencyDesc,
			pg.ProductGroupCode as ReassignedProductGroupCode,	--Force the re-assigned products...		
			pg.ProductGroupName as ReassignedProductGroupName,	--...to be processed as investments		
			'VNB-INI-PHASE-2' as RecognitionType,
			case 
				when (ph.ProductCategoryCode = 1 or pcc.KeyValue2 = '1') then 'WEALTH-INITIAL'
				when ph.ProductGroupCode = 3 then 'MORTGAGE'
				when ph.ProductGroupCode = 6 then 'PROTECTION'
				else null
			end as CalculationType,
			'Openwork 2006' as Source,
			@DateLastUpdated as DateInserted,
			@DateLastUpdated as DateLastUpdated,
			csp.year as CommissionYear
	from	#msit_CommissionStatementSUMMARY css
			inner join msit_CommissionStatement cs
						on cs.TransactionID = css.TransactionID
						and cs.AgentCode = css.AgentCode
			inner join mstt_Agents ag on ag.Code = cs.BusinessCode
			inner join mstt_PolicyTransactions pt on pt.ID = cs.TransactionID
			inner join mstt_Policies p on p.POL_NUM = pt.PolicyID
			inner join msit_CommissionStatementPeriods VNBStart on convert(date,pt.CreateDateTime) between VNBStart.PeriodStartDate and VNBStart.PeriodEndDate
			inner join msit_Commissionstatementperiods csp on csp.month = cs.month
			inner join mstt_ProductHierarchy ph on ph.productcode = cs.productcode
			inner join mstt_Expectation e on e.ID = cs.ExpectationID
			left join dbo.owt_MortgageBrokerFees mbf on mbf.PendingPaymentID = cs.PendingPaymentID and mbf.AdviceFeeCharged = 'Yes'
			left join owt_SelectionControl SC
						on SC.Process = 'ElitePoints' 
						and SC.KeyType = 'NSCPotCode' 
						and cs.CreateDate between SC.EffectiveStartDate and SC.EffectiveEndDate
			left join mstt_Commissions BSCpot
						on BSCpot.TransactionID = cs.TransactionID 
						and BSCpot.Agent_Code = sc.KeyValue
						and BSCpot.CommissionType = 10
			left join owt_SelectionControl SFMPC						
						on SFMPC.Process = 'ElitePoints' 
						and SFMPC.KeyType = 'ServicingFeeMarginPotCode' 
						and cs.CreateDate between SFMPC.EffectiveStartDate and SFMPC.EffectiveEndDate
			left join mstt_Commissions SFMpot							
						on SFMpot.TransactionID = cs.TransactionID 
						and SFMpot.Agent_Code = SFMPC.KeyValue
						and SFMpot.CommissionType = 10	
			left join owt_SelectionControl pcc 
						on pcc.Process = 'ElitePoints'
						and pcc.KeyType = 'ProductCategoryCode'
						and pcc.KeyValue = cs.ProductCode	
						and cs.CreateDate between pcc.EffectiveStartDate and pcc.EffectiveEndDate
			left join owt_SelectionControl ogsdflt 
						on ogsdflt.Process = 'ElitePoints'
						and ogsdflt.KeyType = 'DefaultOngoingServicingRate'
						and ogsdflt.SelectionType = 'VNB'
						and ogsdflt.KeyValue = case when ph.RDRType = 'ONPLAT' then 'ONPLAT' else 'OFPLAT' end
						and cs.CreateDate between ogsdflt.EffectiveStartDate and ogsdflt.EffectiveEndDate
			left join mstt_CodeProductGroup pg on pg.ProductGroupCode = case when pcc.KeyValue2 = '1' then 2 else ph.ProductGroupCode end
			left join owt_EliteFactors Cfca on Cfca.FeeType = 'VNB' and Cfca.category = 'COB-FCA-RATE' and csp.year between Cfca.StartYear and Cfca.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors Crate on Crate.FeeType = 'VNB' and Crate.category = 'COB-RETENTION-RATE' and csp.year between Crate.StartYear and Crate.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors Mfca on Mfca.FeeType = 'VNB' and Mfca.category = 'MORT-FCA-RATE' and csp.year between Mfca.StartYear and Mfca.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors MRproc on MRproc.FeeType = 'VNB' and MRproc.category = 'MORT-RETENTION-RATE-PROC' and csp.year between MRproc.StartYear and MRproc.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors MRbkr on MRbkr.FeeType = 'VNB' and MRbkr.category = 'MORT-RETENTION-RATE-BROKER' and csp.year between MRbkr.StartYear and MRbkr.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors Pfca on Pfca.FeeType = 'VNB' and Pfca.category = 'PROT-FCA-RATE' and csp.year between Pfca.StartYear and Pfca.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors Prate on Prate.FeeType = 'VNB' and Prate.category = 'PROT-RETENTION-RATE' and csp.year between Prate.StartYear and Prate.EndYear 
	where	cs.ReportingClassCode = 1
	and		cs.CommissionType in (1,2,17)			--We want all the initial payment types (i.e. not trail (ongoing))
	and		ag.Manager2Code <> @OwlManager2Code		--Exclude Owl

	select @RowCount = @@rowcount
	set @ProcessMessage = '#owt_Recognition (ini ph2 - accr adj) = ' + convert(nvarchar(10), @RowCount)
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseLog, @ProcessMessage, null, @Module, @Client

	/****************************************************************************

		Initial Phase 3
		1) Add up the +ves and -ves prior to the NEW front loaded amount and
			net them off on the first +ve following the last -ve
		2) Now set all the +ves following the one updated in (1) to zero.
																
	****************************************************************************/

	update r
		set RecognitionType	= case when r.SourceID >= css.MinInitialAfterAdjPendingPaymentID 
								then 'VNB-INI-PHASE-3'
								else r.RecognitionType
							  end,
			Initial = case  when r.SourceID = css.MinInitialAfterAdjPendingPaymentID 
								then (((r.DA)*(r.AgentSplit/100) * (r.RetentionRate/100.0)) - ((r.DA)*(r.AgentSplit/100) * (r.FCARate/100))) - derived.SumInitial
							when r.SourceID > css.MinInitialAfterAdjPendingPaymentID 
								then 0.0
							else r.Initial
					  end,
			DateLastUpdated = @DateLastUpdated
	from	#msit_CommissionStatementSUMMARY css
			inner join #AG_owt_Recognition_SEPARATE_ONGOING r
						on r.TransactionID = css.TransactionID
						and r.SellerCode = css.AgentCode
			inner join (select	r.TransactionID, r.SellerCode, SUM(Initial) as SumInitial
						from	#msit_CommissionStatementSUMMARY s
								inner join #AG_owt_Recognition_SEPARATE_ONGOING r 
											on r.TransactionID = s.TransactionID
											and r.SellerCode = s.AgentCode
						where	r.SourceID <= s.MaxAdjPendingPaymentID
						group	by r.TransactionID, r.SellerCode
						) derived 
							on  derived.TransactionID = r.TransactionID
							and	derived.SellerCode = r.SellerCode 
	where	isnull(css.MaxInitialPendingPaymentID,0) > isnull(css.MaxAdjPendingPaymentID,0)-- An initial payment follows the clawback, so time to revert back to front loading
	--and		r.SourceID = css.MinInitialAfterAdjPendingPaymentID
	--and		css.TransactionID = 5696809

	select @RowCount = @@rowcount
	set @ProcessMessage = '#owt_Recognition (ini ph3 - accr adj) = ' + convert(nvarchar(10), @RowCount)
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseLog, @ProcessMessage, null, @Module, @Client

	/****************************************************************************

		Now do the ongoing.
		
		Build an ongoing summary row for each transaction (slice).
		
		Note we do not care about ongoing clawbacks and adjustments for VNB.
		We want VNB to be on the oldest positive payment on each slice for the
		policy (split by adviser if needed).
						
	****************************************************************************/

	select	cs.TransactionID,
			cs.AgentCode,
			c.Agent_Perc as AgentSplit,
			min(PendingPaymentID) as MinPendingPaymentID
	into	#msit_CommissionStatementONGOING
	from 	msit_CommissionStatement cs
			inner join mstt_Commissions c
						on c.TransactionID = cs.TransactionID
						and c.Agent_Code = cs.AgentCode
						and c.CommissionType = 1
			inner join mstt_Agents ag on ag.Code = cs.BusinessCode
			inner join mstt_PolicyTransactions pt on pt.ID = cs.TransactionID
			inner join mstt_Policies p on p.POL_NUM = pt.PolicyID
			inner join msit_CommissionStatementPeriods VNBStart on convert(date,pt.CreateDateTime) between VNBStart.PeriodStartDate and VNBStart.PeriodEndDate
			inner join msit_Commissionstatementperiods csp on csp.month = cs.month
			inner join mstt_ProductHierarchy ph on ph.productcode = cs.productcode
			inner join mstt_Expectation e on e.ID = cs.ExpectationID
			left join owt_SelectionControl pcc 
						on pcc.Process = 'ElitePoints'
						and pcc.KeyType = 'ProductCategoryCode'
						and pcc.KeyValue = cs.ProductCode	
						and cs.CreateDate between pcc.EffectiveStartDate and pcc.EffectiveEndDate
	where	cs.ReportingClassCode = 1
	and		cs.CommissionType = 10					--Choose only where the ongoing payment is positive
	and		cs.CommFeeType = 'Ongoing'
	and		(ph.ProductCategoryCode = 1 or pcc.KeyValue2 = '1')
	and		ag.Manager2Code <> @OwlManager2Code		--Exclude Owl
	and		csp.Year >= 2017						--Ensure in-scope payments are consistent with VNB start
	and		VNBStart.Year >= 2017 
	and		abs(e.AMOUNT_REC) >= 0.01
	and		((cs.FrequencyCode = 6 and cs.Premium > 1.00)		--Frequency=6->Single
			or (cs.FrequencyCode <> 6 and cs.Premium > 0.01))	--Frequency<>6->Regular	
	group by	cs.TransactionID,
				cs.AgentCode,
				c.Agent_Perc

	select @RowCount = @@rowcount
	set @ProcessMessage = '#msit_CommissionStatementONGOING (ogs txn) = ' + convert(nvarchar(10), @RowCount)
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseLog, @ProcessMessage, null, @Module, @Client

	/****************************************************************************
		
		Insert the ongoing VNB results for those transactions with no
		clawbacks or adjustments - front loaded.
																		
	****************************************************************************/

	insert into #AG_owt_Recognition_SEPARATE_ONGOING
	(
		SourceID,
		CaseID,
		TransactionID,
		Policy,
		ProductCode,
		BusinessCode,
		SellerCode,
		PointsTotal,
		BSC,
		MBF,
		Initial,
		OngoingTotal,
		OngoingYr01,
		OngoingYr02,
		OngoingYr03,
		OngoingYr04,
		OngoingYr05,
		OngoingYr06,
		OngoingYr07,
		OngoingYr08,
		OngoingYr09,
		OngoingYr10,
		FCARate,
		RetentionRate,
		RetentionRateBroker,
		OngoingServicingRate,
		OngoingServicingSource,
		DA,
		AmountReceived,
		Premium,
		AgentSplit,
		CommissionType,
		CommissionTypeDesc,
		PayBasisCode,
		PayBasisDesc,
		PaymentMatchedDate,
		Month,
		FrequencyCode,
		FrequencyDesc,
		ReassignedProductGroupCode,
		ReassignedProductGroupName,
		RecognitionType,
		CalculationType,
		Source,
		DateInserted,
		DateLastUpdated,
		CommissionYear
	)
	select	cs.PendingPaymentID as SourceID,
			cs.CaseID,
			cs.TransactionID,
			cs.ExtPolicyNumber as Policy,
			cs.ProductCode,
			cs.BusinessCode,
			cs.AgentCode as SellerCode,
			0.0 as PointsTotal,
			case
				when BSCpot.ID is not null then 
					--BSC takes the first 0.12 of the ongoing fee %. If the ongoing fee % is 0.12% or less, then 100% of the ongoing fee is allocated to BSC
					case when coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2)) - convert(decimal(8,4),sc.KeyValue2) >= 0.01
						then 
							case when cs.FrequencyCode = 2	--Monthly 
								then (cso.AgentSplit/100) * 12.0 * (isnull(cs.Premium,0)/2.0) * convert(decimal(8,4),sc.KeyValue3) * case when cs.CommissionType in (16,19) then -1 else 1 end
								else (cso.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(cs.Premium,0) * convert(decimal(8,4),sc.KeyValue3) * case when cs.CommissionType in (16,19) then -1 else 1 end
							end			
						else
							case when cs.FrequencyCode = 2	--Monthly 
								then (cso.AgentSplit/100) * 12.0 * (isnull(cs.Premium,0)/2.0) * coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2)) * case when cs.CommissionType in (16,19) then -1 else 1 end
								else (cso.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(cs.Premium,0) * (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))/100.0) * case when cs.CommissionType in (16,19) then -1 else 1 end
							end
					end
				else 0.0
			end as BSC,
			0.0 as MBF,
			0.0 as Initial,
			0.0 as OngoingTotal,
			case
				--WEALTH ONGOING CALCULATION START
				--When the adviser has changed, the AgentSplit can become zero in which case the ELITE points should be zero.
				when cso.AgentSplit = 0 then 0

				--SINGLE start
				--Calculate when BSC and ongoing applies (where ongoing rate is greater than BSC rate) 
				when cs.FrequencyCode = 6 and SFMpot.ID is not null and BSCpot.ID is not null and (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2)) - convert(decimal(8,4),sc.KeyValue2)) >= 0.01 then 
							--(AUM X BSC Rate)...
							((cso.AgentSplit/100) * (isnull(cs.Premium,0) * convert(decimal(8,4),sc.KeyValue3)) 
							--(AUM X OGS Rate X COB FCA Rate)...
							- ((cso.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(cs.Premium,0) * (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))/100.0) * Cfca.FACTOR)
							--(AUM X (OGS Rate - BSC Rate) X COB Retention Rate)...
							+ ((cso.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(cs.Premium,0) * ((coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))-convert(decimal(8,4),sc.KeyValue2))/100.0)) * Crate.FACTOR) 
							--Sign correctly for +ve or clawback payment
							* (case when cs.CommissionType in (16,19) then -1 else 1 end)
				--Calculate when BSC and ongoing applies (where ongoing rate less than BSC rate, then BSC gets all the ongoing available) 
				when cs.FrequencyCode = 6 and SFMpot.ID is not null and BSCpot.ID is not null then
							--(AUM X BSC Rate)...(in this scenario it's all of the OGS rate)
							((cso.AgentSplit/100) * (isnull(cs.Premium,0) * (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))/100.0)) 
							--(AUM X OGS Rate X COB FCA Rate)...
							- ((cso.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(cs.Premium,0) * (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))/100.0) * Cfca.FACTOR)
							--(AUM X (OGS Rate - BSC Rate) X COB Retention Rate)...
							+ (0.0)) --BSC got it all, so this part of the calculation is zero
							--Sign correctly for +ve or clawback payment
							* (case when cs.CommissionType in (16,19) then -1 else 1 end)
				--Calculate when no BSC applies and ongoing applies
				when cs.FrequencyCode = 6 and SFMpot.ID is not null and BSCpot.ID is null then 
							--(AUM X OGS Rate X COB Retention Rate)...
							(((cso.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(cs.Premium,0) * (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))/100.0) * Crate.FACTOR) 
							--(AUM X OGS Rate X COB FCA Rate)...
							- ((cso.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(cs.Premium,0) * (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))/100.0) * Cfca.FACTOR))
							--Sign correctly for +ve or clawback payment
							* (case when cs.CommissionType in (16,19) then -1 else 1 end)
				--SINGLE end
				
				--REGULAR start
				--Calculate when BSC and ongoing applies (where ongoing rate is greater than BSC rate) 
				when cs.FrequencyCode <> 6 and SFMpot.ID is not null and BSCpot.ID is not null and (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2)) - convert(decimal(8,4),sc.KeyValue2)) >= 0.01 then		--AG 04/06/2018 (1)
							--The non-BSC portion (Ave AUM X (OGS Rate - BSC Rate) X COB Retention Rate)...
							((((((cso.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(cs.Premium,0) * (case when cs.FrequencyCode = 2 then 12 else 1 end))/2.0) * (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2)) - convert(decimal(8,4),sc.KeyValue2))/100.0)) * Crate.FACTOR
							--The BSC portion (Ave AUM X BSC Rate)...
							+ case when cs.FrequencyCode = 2	--Monthly 
									then (cso.AgentSplit/100) * 12.0 * (isnull(cs.Premium,0)/2.0) * convert(decimal(8,4),sc.KeyValue3) 
									else (cso.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(cs.Premium,0) * convert(decimal(8,4),sc.KeyValue3) 
							  end
							--FCA Charge (Ave AUM X OGS Rate X FCA Rate)...
							- (case when cs.FrequencyCode = 2	--Monthly 
									then (cso.AgentSplit/100) * 12.0 * (isnull(cs.Premium,0)/2.0) 
									else (cso.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(cs.Premium,0) 
							   end * (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))/100.0) * Cfca.FACTOR))
							--Sign correctly for +ve or clawback payment
							* (case when cs.CommissionType in (16,19) then -1 else 1 end)   
				--Calculate when BSC and ongoing applies (where ongoing rate less than BSC rate, then BSC gets all the ongoing available) 
				when cs.FrequencyCode <> 6 and SFMpot.ID is not null and BSCpot.ID is not null then		--AG 04/06/2018 (1)
							--The non-BSC portion (Ave AUM X (OGS Rate - BSC Rate) X COB Retention Rate)...
							((0.0)	--BSC got it all, so this part of the calculation is zero
							--The BSC portion (Ave AUM X BSC Rate)...(in this scenario it's all of the OGS rate)
							+ case when cs.FrequencyCode = 2	--Monthly 
									then (cso.AgentSplit/100) * 12.0 * (isnull(cs.Premium,0)/2.0) * (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))/100.0) 
									else (cso.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(cs.Premium,0) * (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))/100.0) 
							  end
							--FCA Charge (Ave AUM X OGS Rate X FCA Rate)...
							- (case when cs.FrequencyCode = 2	--Monthly 
									then (cso.AgentSplit/100) * 12.0 * (isnull(cs.Premium,0)/2.0) 
									else (cso.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(cs.Premium,0) 
							   end * (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))/100.0) * Cfca.FACTOR))
							--Sign correctly for +ve or clawback payment
							* (case when cs.CommissionType in (16,19) then -1 else 1 end)   
				--Calculate when no BSC applies, but ongoing servicing applies
				when cs.FrequencyCode <> 6 and SFMpot.ID is not null and BSCpot.ID is null then		--AG 04/06/2018	(1)
							--(Ave AUM X OGS Rate X COB Retention Rate)...
							(((((cso.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(cs.Premium,0) * (case when cs.FrequencyCode = 2 then 12 else 1 end))/2.0) * (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))/100.0) * Crate.FACTOR) 
							--(Ave AUM X OGS Rate X COB FCA Rate)...
							- ((((cso.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(cs.Premium,0) * (case when cs.FrequencyCode = 2 then 12 else 1 end))/2.0) * (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))/100.0) * Cfca.FACTOR))
							--Sign correctly for +ve or clawback payment
							* (case when cs.CommissionType in (16,19) then -1 else 1 end)   
				--REGULAR end
				
				else 0.0

				--WEALTH ONGOING CALCULATION END
			end as OngoingYr01,
			0.0 as OngoingYr02,
			0.0 as OngoingYr03,
			0.0 as OngoingYr04,
			0.0 as OngoingYr05,
			0.0 as OngoingYr06,
			0.0 as OngoingYr07,
			0.0 as OngoingYr08,
			0.0 as OngoingYr09,
			0.0 as OngoingYr10,
			Cfca.FACTOR*100.0 as FCARate,
			Crate.FACTOR*100.0 as RetentionRate,
			0.0 as RetentionRateBroker,
			case when SFMpot.ID is not null
				then coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))
				else null
			end as OngoingServicingRate,
			case when SFMpot.ID is not null
				then case 
						when ogs.OngoingServiceFee is null and ogscli.OngoingServiceFee is null 
							then case
								when ogsdflt.KeyValue = 'ONPLAT' then 'Default - On Plat'
								else 'Default - Off Plat'
							end
						when ogs.OngoingServiceFee is not null then 'Client Product'
						when ogscli.OngoingServiceFee is not null then 'Client Only'
						else 'Unknown'
					 end
				else case when (ph.ProductCategoryCode = 1 or pcc.KeyValue2 = '1')
						then 'No OGS'					--WEALTH, but no OGS
						else null						--Not WEALTH, so OGS is n/a and is therefore null
					 end
			end as OngoingServicingSource,
			pt.CommInitialAmount as DA,
			e.AMOUNT_REC as AmountReceived,
			cs.Premium,
			cso.AgentSplit,								--Use the split from the IC record
			cs.CommissionType,
			left(cs.StandingOrderDesc,50) as CommissionTypeDesc,
			cs.PayBasisCode,
			cs.PayBasisDesc,
			cs.CreateDate as PaymentMatchedDate,
			cs.Month,
			cs.FrequencyCode,
			cs.FrequencyDesc,
			pg.ProductGroupCode as ReassignedProductGroupCode,	--Force the re-assigned products...		
			pg.ProductGroupName as ReassignedProductGroupName,	--...to be processed as investments		
			'VNB-OGS-PHASE-1' as RecognitionType,
			'WEALTH-ONGOING' as CalculationType,
			'Openwork 2006' as Source,
			@DateLastUpdated as DateInserted,
			@DateLastUpdated as DateLastUpdated,
			csp.year as CommissionYear
	from	#msit_CommissionStatementONGOING cso
			inner join msit_CommissionStatement cs on cs.PendingPaymentID = cso.MinPendingPaymentID
			inner join mstt_Agents ag on ag.Code = cs.BusinessCode
			inner join mstt_PolicyTransactions pt on pt.ID = cs.TransactionID
			inner join mstt_Policies p on p.POL_NUM = pt.PolicyID
			inner join msit_CommissionStatementPeriods VNBStart on convert(date,pt.CreateDateTime) between VNBStart.PeriodStartDate and VNBStart.PeriodEndDate
			inner join msit_Commissionstatementperiods csp on csp.month = cs.month
			inner join mstt_ProductHierarchy ph on ph.productcode = cs.productcode
			inner join mstt_Expectation e on e.ID = cs.ExpectationID
			left join dbo.owt_MortgageBrokerFees mbf on mbf.PendingPaymentID = cs.PendingPaymentID and mbf.AdviceFeeCharged = 'Yes'
			left join owt_SelectionControl SC
						on SC.Process = 'ElitePoints' 
						and SC.KeyType = 'NSCPotCode' 
						and cs.CreateDate between SC.EffectiveStartDate and SC.EffectiveEndDate
			left join mstt_Commissions BSCpot
						on BSCpot.TransactionID = cs.TransactionID 
						and BSCpot.Agent_Code = sc.KeyValue
						and BSCpot.CommissionType = 10
			left join owt_SelectionControl SFMPC						
						on SFMPC.Process = 'ElitePoints' 
						and SFMPC.KeyType = 'ServicingFeeMarginPotCode' 
						and cs.CreateDate between SFMPC.EffectiveStartDate and SFMPC.EffectiveEndDate
			left join mstt_Commissions SFMpot							
						on SFMpot.TransactionID = cs.TransactionID 
						and SFMpot.Agent_Code = SFMPC.KeyValue
						and SFMpot.CommissionType = 10	
			left join owt_SelectionControl pcc 
						on pcc.Process = 'ElitePoints'
						and pcc.KeyType = 'ProductCategoryCode'
						and pcc.KeyValue = cs.ProductCode	
						and cs.CreateDate between pcc.EffectiveStartDate and pcc.EffectiveEndDate
			left join owt_SelectionControl ogsdflt 
						on ogsdflt.Process = 'ElitePoints'
						and ogsdflt.KeyType = 'DefaultOngoingServicingRate'
						and ogsdflt.SelectionType = 'VNB'
						and ogsdflt.KeyValue = case when ph.RDRType = 'ONPLAT' then 'ONPLAT' else 'OFPLAT' end
						and cs.CreateDate between ogsdflt.EffectiveStartDate and ogsdflt.EffectiveEndDate
			left join mstt_CodeProductGroup pg on pg.ProductGroupCode = case when pcc.KeyValue2 = '1' then 2 else ph.ProductGroupCode end
			left join owt_EliteFactors Cfca on Cfca.FeeType = 'VNB' and Cfca.category = 'COB-FCA-RATE' and csp.year between Cfca.StartYear and Cfca.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors Crate on Crate.FeeType = 'VNB' and Crate.category = 'COB-RETENTION-RATE' and csp.year between Crate.StartYear and Crate.EndYear 
			left join #OGSLookUp ogs on ogs.CLIENT_NUM = cs.ClientID and ogs.ProductCode = cs.ProductCode
			left join #OGSLookUpClient ogscli on ogscli.CLIENT_NUM = cs.ClientID 	
	
	select @RowCount = @@rowcount
	set @ProcessMessage = '#owt_Recognition (ogs ph1 yr1) = ' + convert(nvarchar(10), @RowCount)
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseLog, @ProcessMessage, null, @Module, @Client

	/****************************************************************************
		
		Insert the ongoing VNB results for those transactions with
		clawbacks or adjustments - on a per payment basis.
																		
	****************************************************************************/
/*
	insert into #AG_owt_Recognition_SEPARATE_ONGOING
	(
		SourceID,
		CaseID,
		TransactionID,
		Policy,
		ProductCode,
		BusinessCode,
		SellerCode,
		PointsTotal,
		BSC,
		MBF,
		Initial,
		OngoingTotal,
		OngoingYr01,
		OngoingYr02,
		OngoingYr03,
		OngoingYr04,
		OngoingYr05,
		OngoingYr06,
		OngoingYr07,
		OngoingYr08,
		OngoingYr09,
		OngoingYr10,
		FCARate,
		RetentionRate,
		RetentionRateBroker,
		OngoingServicingRate,
		OngoingServicingSource,
		DA,
		AmountReceived,
		Premium,
		AgentSplit,
		CommissionType,
		CommissionTypeDesc,
		PayBasisCode,
		PayBasisDesc,
		PaymentMatchedDate,
		Month,
		FrequencyCode,
		FrequencyDesc,
		ReassignedProductGroupCode,
		ReassignedProductGroupName,
		RecognitionType,
		CalculationType,
		Source,
		DateInserted,
		DateLastUpdated,
		CommissionYear
	)
	select	cs.PendingPaymentID as SourceID,
			cs.CaseID,
			cs.TransactionID,
			cs.ExtPolicyNumber as Policy,
			cs.ProductCode,
			cs.BusinessCode,
			cs.AgentCode as SellerCode,
			0.0 as PointsTotal,
			case
				when BSCpot.ID is not null then 
					--BSC takes the first 0.12 of the ongoing fee %. If the ongoing fee % is 0.12% or less, then 100% of the ongoing fee is allocated to BSC
					case when coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2)) - convert(decimal(8,4),sc.KeyValue2) >= 0.01
						then 
							case when cs.FrequencyCode = 2	--Monthly 
								then (cso.AgentSplit/100) * 12.0 * (isnull(cs.Premium,0)/2.0) * convert(decimal(8,4),sc.KeyValue3) * case when cs.CommissionType in (16,19) then -1 else 1 end
								else (cso.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(cs.Premium,0) * convert(decimal(8,4),sc.KeyValue3) * case when cs.CommissionType in (16,19) then -1 else 1 end
							end			
						else
							case when cs.FrequencyCode = 2	--Monthly 
								then (cso.AgentSplit/100) * 12.0 * (isnull(cs.Premium,0)/2.0) * coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2)) * case when cs.CommissionType in (16,19) then -1 else 1 end
								else (cso.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(cs.Premium,0) * (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))/100.0) * case when cs.CommissionType in (16,19) then -1 else 1 end
							end
					end
				else 0.0
			end as BSC,
			0.0 as MBF,
			0.0 as Initial,
			0.0 as OngoingTotal,
			case
				--WEALTH ONGOING CALCULATION START
				--When the adviser has changed, the AgentSplit can become zero in which case the ELITE points should be zero.
				when cso.AgentSplit = 0 then 0

				--SINGLE start
				--Calculate when BSC and ongoing applies (where ongoing rate is greater than BSC rate) 
				when cs.FrequencyCode = 6 and SFMpot.ID is not null and BSCpot.ID is not null and (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2)) - convert(decimal(8,4),sc.KeyValue2)) >= 0.01 then 
							--(AUM X BSC Rate)...
							((cso.AgentSplit/100) * (isnull(cs.Premium,0) * convert(decimal(8,4),sc.KeyValue3)) 
							--(AUM X OGS Rate X COB FCA Rate)...
							- ((cso.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(cs.Premium,0) * (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))/100.0) * Cfca.FACTOR)
							--(AUM X (OGS Rate - BSC Rate) X COB Retention Rate)...
							+ ((cso.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(cs.Premium,0) * ((coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))-convert(decimal(8,4),sc.KeyValue2))/100.0)) * Crate.FACTOR) 
							--Sign correctly for +ve or clawback payment
							* (case when cs.CommissionType in (16,19) then -1 else 1 end)
				--Calculate when BSC and ongoing applies (where ongoing rate less than BSC rate, then BSC gets all the ongoing available) 
				when cs.FrequencyCode = 6 and SFMpot.ID is not null and BSCpot.ID is not null then
							--(AUM X BSC Rate)...(in this scenario it's all of the OGS rate)
							((cso.AgentSplit/100) * (isnull(cs.Premium,0) * (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))/100.0)) 
							--(AUM X OGS Rate X COB FCA Rate)...
							- ((cso.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(cs.Premium,0) * (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))/100.0) * Cfca.FACTOR)
							--(AUM X (OGS Rate - BSC Rate) X COB Retention Rate)...
							+ (0.0)) --BSC got it all, so this part of the calculation is zero
							--Sign correctly for +ve or clawback payment
							* (case when cs.CommissionType in (16,19) then -1 else 1 end)
				--Calculate when no BSC applies and ongoing applies
				when cs.FrequencyCode = 6 and SFMpot.ID is not null and BSCpot.ID is null then 
							--(AUM X OGS Rate X COB Retention Rate)...
							(((cso.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(cs.Premium,0) * (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))/100.0) * Crate.FACTOR) 
							--(AUM X OGS Rate X COB FCA Rate)...
							- ((cso.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(cs.Premium,0) * (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))/100.0) * Cfca.FACTOR))
							--Sign correctly for +ve or clawback payment
							* (case when cs.CommissionType in (16,19) then -1 else 1 end)
				--SINGLE end
				
				--REGULAR start
				--Calculate when BSC and ongoing applies (where ongoing rate is greater than BSC rate) 
				when cs.FrequencyCode <> 6 and SFMpot.ID is not null and BSCpot.ID is not null and (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2)) - convert(decimal(8,4),sc.KeyValue2)) >= 0.01 then		--AG 04/06/2018 (1)
							--The non-BSC portion (Ave AUM X (OGS Rate - BSC Rate) X COB Retention Rate)...
							((((((cso.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(cs.Premium,0) * (case when cs.FrequencyCode = 2 then 12 else 1 end))/2.0) * (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2)) - convert(decimal(8,4),sc.KeyValue2))/100.0)) * Crate.FACTOR
							--The BSC portion (Ave AUM X BSC Rate)...
							+ case when cs.FrequencyCode = 2	--Monthly 
									then (cso.AgentSplit/100) * 12.0 * (isnull(cs.Premium,0)/2.0) * convert(decimal(8,4),sc.KeyValue3) 
									else (cso.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(cs.Premium,0) * convert(decimal(8,4),sc.KeyValue3) 
							  end
							--FCA Charge (Ave AUM X OGS Rate X FCA Rate)...
							- (case when cs.FrequencyCode = 2	--Monthly 
									then (cso.AgentSplit/100) * 12.0 * (isnull(cs.Premium,0)/2.0) 
									else (cso.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(cs.Premium,0) 
							   end * (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))/100.0) * Cfca.FACTOR))
							--Sign correctly for +ve or clawback payment
							* (case when cs.CommissionType in (16,19) then -1 else 1 end)   
				--Calculate when BSC and ongoing applies (where ongoing rate less than BSC rate, then BSC gets all the ongoing available) 
				when cs.FrequencyCode <> 6 and SFMpot.ID is not null and BSCpot.ID is not null then		--AG 04/06/2018 (1)
							--The non-BSC portion (Ave AUM X (OGS Rate - BSC Rate) X COB Retention Rate)...
							((0.0)	--BSC got it all, so this part of the calculation is zero
							--The BSC portion (Ave AUM X BSC Rate)...(in this scenario it's all of the OGS rate)
							+ case when cs.FrequencyCode = 2	--Monthly 
									then (cso.AgentSplit/100) * 12.0 * (isnull(cs.Premium,0)/2.0) * (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))/100.0) 
									else (cso.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(cs.Premium,0) * (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))/100.0) 
							  end
							--FCA Charge (Ave AUM X OGS Rate X FCA Rate)...
							- (case when cs.FrequencyCode = 2	--Monthly 
									then (cso.AgentSplit/100) * 12.0 * (isnull(cs.Premium,0)/2.0) 
									else (cso.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(cs.Premium,0) 
							   end * (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))/100.0) * Cfca.FACTOR))
							--Sign correctly for +ve or clawback payment
							* (case when cs.CommissionType in (16,19) then -1 else 1 end)   
				--Calculate when no BSC applies, but ongoing servicing applies
				when cs.FrequencyCode <> 6 and SFMpot.ID is not null and BSCpot.ID is null then		--AG 04/06/2018	(1)
							--(Ave AUM X OGS Rate X COB Retention Rate)...
							(((((cso.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(cs.Premium,0) * (case when cs.FrequencyCode = 2 then 12 else 1 end))/2.0) * (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))/100.0) * Crate.FACTOR) 
							--(Ave AUM X OGS Rate X COB FCA Rate)...
							- ((((cso.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(cs.Premium,0) * (case when cs.FrequencyCode = 2 then 12 else 1 end))/2.0) * (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))/100.0) * Cfca.FACTOR))
							--Sign correctly for +ve or clawback payment
							* (case when cs.CommissionType in (16,19) then -1 else 1 end)   
				--REGULAR end
				
				else 0.0

				--WEALTH ONGOING CALCULATION END
			end as OngoingYr01,
			0.0 as OngoingYr02,
			0.0 as OngoingYr03,
			0.0 as OngoingYr04,
			0.0 as OngoingYr05,
			0.0 as OngoingYr06,
			0.0 as OngoingYr07,
			0.0 as OngoingYr08,
			0.0 as OngoingYr09,
			0.0 as OngoingYr10,
			Cfca.FACTOR*100.0 as FCARate,
			Crate.FACTOR*100.0 as RetentionRate,
			0.0 as RetentionRateBroker,
			case when SFMpot.ID is not null
				then coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))
				else null
			end as OngoingServicingRate,
			case when SFMpot.ID is not null
				then case 
						when ogs.OngoingServiceFee is null and ogscli.OngoingServiceFee is null 
							then case
								when ogsdflt.KeyValue = 'ONPLAT' then 'Default - On Plat'
								else 'Default - Off Plat'
							end
						when ogs.OngoingServiceFee is not null then 'Client Product'
						when ogscli.OngoingServiceFee is not null then 'Client Only'
						else 'Unknown'
					 end
				else case when (ph.ProductCategoryCode = 1 or pcc.KeyValue2 = '1')
						then 'No OGS'					--WEALTH, but no OGS
						else null						--Not WEALTH, so OGS is n/a and is therefore null
					 end
			end as OngoingServicingSource,
			pt.CommInitialAmount as DA,
			e.AMOUNT_REC as AmountReceived,
			cs.Premium,
			cso.AgentSplit,								--Use the split from the IC record
			cs.CommissionType,
			left(cs.StandingOrderDesc,50) as CommissionTypeDesc,
			cs.PayBasisCode,
			cs.PayBasisDesc,
			cs.CreateDate as PaymentMatchedDate,
			cs.Month,
			cs.FrequencyCode,
			cs.FrequencyDesc,
			pg.ProductGroupCode as ReassignedProductGroupCode,	--Force the re-assigned products...		
			pg.ProductGroupName as ReassignedProductGroupName,	--...to be processed as investments		
			'VNB-OGS-PHASE-2' as RecognitionType,
			'WEALTH-ONGOING' as CalculationType,
			'Openwork 2006' as Source,
			@DateLastUpdated as DateInserted,
			@DateLastUpdated as DateLastUpdated,
			csp.year as CommissionYear
	from	#msit_CommissionStatementONGOING cso
			inner join msit_CommissionStatement cs 
						on cs.TransactionID = cso.TransactionID
						and cs.AgentCode = cso.AgentCode
			inner join msit_CommissionStatement cs on cs.PendingPaymentID = cso.MinOngoingPendingPaymentID
			inner join mstt_Agents ag on ag.Code = cs.BusinessCode
			inner join mstt_PolicyTransactions pt on pt.ID = cs.TransactionID
			inner join mstt_Policies p on p.POL_NUM = pt.PolicyID
			inner join msit_CommissionStatementPeriods VNBStart on convert(date,pt.CreateDateTime) between VNBStart.PeriodStartDate and VNBStart.PeriodEndDate
			inner join msit_Commissionstatementperiods csp on csp.month = cs.month
			inner join mstt_ProductHierarchy ph on ph.productcode = cs.productcode
			inner join mstt_Expectation e on e.ID = cs.ExpectationID
			left join dbo.owt_MortgageBrokerFees mbf on mbf.PendingPaymentID = cs.PendingPaymentID and mbf.AdviceFeeCharged = 'Yes'
			left join owt_SelectionControl SC
						on SC.Process = 'ElitePoints' 
						and SC.KeyType = 'NSCPotCode' 
						and cs.CreateDate between SC.EffectiveStartDate and SC.EffectiveEndDate
			left join mstt_Commissions BSCpot
						on BSCpot.TransactionID = cs.TransactionID 
						and BSCpot.Agent_Code = sc.KeyValue
						and BSCpot.CommissionType = 10
			left join owt_SelectionControl SFMPC						
						on SFMPC.Process = 'ElitePoints' 
						and SFMPC.KeyType = 'ServicingFeeMarginPotCode' 
						and cs.CreateDate between SFMPC.EffectiveStartDate and SFMPC.EffectiveEndDate
			left join mstt_Commissions SFMpot							
						on SFMpot.TransactionID = cs.TransactionID 
						and SFMpot.Agent_Code = SFMPC.KeyValue
						and SFMpot.CommissionType = 10	
			left join owt_SelectionControl pcc 
						on pcc.Process = 'ElitePoints'
						and pcc.KeyType = 'ProductCategoryCode'
						and pcc.KeyValue = cs.ProductCode	
						and cs.CreateDate between pcc.EffectiveStartDate and pcc.EffectiveEndDate
			left join owt_SelectionControl ogsdflt 
						on ogsdflt.Process = 'ElitePoints'
						and ogsdflt.KeyType = 'DefaultOngoingServicingRate'
						and ogsdflt.SelectionType = 'VNB'
						and ogsdflt.KeyValue = case when ph.RDRType = 'ONPLAT' then 'ONPLAT' else 'OFPLAT' end
						and cs.CreateDate between ogsdflt.EffectiveStartDate and ogsdflt.EffectiveEndDate
			left join mstt_CodeProductGroup pg on pg.ProductGroupCode = case when pcc.KeyValue2 = '1' then 2 else ph.ProductGroupCode end
			left join owt_EliteFactors Cfca on Cfca.FeeType = 'VNB' and Cfca.category = 'COB-FCA-RATE' and csp.year between Cfca.StartYear and Cfca.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors Crate on Crate.FeeType = 'VNB' and Crate.category = 'COB-RETENTION-RATE' and csp.year between Crate.StartYear and Crate.EndYear 
			left join #OGSLookUp ogs on ogs.CLIENT_NUM = cs.ClientID and ogs.ProductCode = cs.ProductCode
			left join #OGSLookUpClient ogscli on ogscli.CLIENT_NUM = cs.ClientID 	
	where	cso.TransactionHasAdjustments = 1	--Clawbacks or adjustments so per payment

	select @RowCount = @@rowcount
	set @ProcessMessage = '#owt_Recognition (ogs ph2 yr1) = ' + convert(nvarchar(10), @RowCount)
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseLog, @ProcessMessage, null, @Module, @Client
*/
	/****************************************************************************

		Ongoing Phase 3
		1) Add up the +ves and -ves prior to the NEW front loaded amount and
			net them off on the first +ve following the last -ve
		2) Now set all the +ves following the one updated in (1) to zero.
																
	****************************************************************************/
/*
	update r
		set RecognitionType	= case when r.SourceID >= css.MinInitialAfterAdjPendingPaymentID 
								then 'VNB-INI-PHASE-3'
								else r.RecognitionType
							  end,
			Initial = case  when r.SourceID = css.MinInitialAfterAdjPendingPaymentID 
								then (((r.DA)*(r.AgentSplit/100) * (r.RetentionRate/100.0)) - ((r.DA)*(r.AgentSplit/100) * (r.FCARate/100))) - derived.SumInitial
							when r.SourceID > css.MinInitialAfterAdjPendingPaymentID 
								then 0.0
							else r.Initial
					  end,
			DateLastUpdated = @DateLastUpdated
	from	#msit_CommissionStatementSUMMARY css
			inner join #AG_owt_Recognition_SEPARATE_ONGOING r
						on r.TransactionID = css.TransactionID
						and r.SellerCode = css.AgentCode
			inner join (select	r.TransactionID, r.SellerCode, SUM(Initial) as SumInitial
						from	#msit_CommissionStatementSUMMARY s
								inner join #AG_owt_Recognition_SEPARATE_ONGOING r 
											on r.TransactionID = s.TransactionID
											and r.SellerCode = s.AgentCode
						where	r.SourceID <= s.MaxAdjPendingPaymentID
						group	by r.TransactionID, r.SellerCode
						) derived 
							on  derived.TransactionID = r.TransactionID
							and	derived.SellerCode = r.SellerCode 
	where	isnull(css.MaxInitialPendingPaymentID,0) > isnull(css.MaxAdjPendingPaymentID,0)-- An initial payment follows the clawback, so time to revert back to front loading
	--and		r.SourceID = css.MinInitialAfterAdjPendingPaymentID
	--and		css.TransactionID = 5696809

	select @RowCount = @@rowcount
	set @ProcessMessage = '#owt_Recognition (ini ph3 - accr adj) = ' + convert(nvarchar(10), @RowCount)
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseLog, @ProcessMessage, null, @Module, @Client
*/
	/****************************************************************************

		Now calculate the ongoing spread as follows:
		1) Investments: Years 1 to 6
		2) Pensions:	Years 1 to 10
		Note that regular payments get an additional multiplier to uplift the 
		average AUM for each year.
																		
	****************************************************************************/

	update r
		set OngoingYr02 = case when r.FrequencyCode = 2									--Monthly
							then r.OngoingYr01 * YR02.Multiplier * YR02.Factor			--Regular
							else r.OngoingYr01 * YR02.Factor							--Single
						  end,
			OngoingYr03 = case when r.FrequencyCode = 2									--Monthly
							then r.OngoingYr01 * YR03.Multiplier * YR03.Factor			--Regular
							else r.OngoingYr01 * YR03.Factor							--Single
						  end,
			OngoingYr04 = case when r.FrequencyCode = 2									--Monthly
							then r.OngoingYr01 * YR04.Multiplier * YR04.Factor			--Regular
							else r.OngoingYr01 * YR04.Factor							--Single
						  end,
			OngoingYr05 = case when r.FrequencyCode = 2									--Monthly 
							then r.OngoingYr01 * YR05.Multiplier * YR05.Factor			--Regular
							else r.OngoingYr01 * YR05.Factor							--Single
						  end,
			OngoingYr06 = case when r.FrequencyCode = 2									--Monthly 
							then r.OngoingYr01 * YR06.Multiplier * YR06.Factor			--Regular
							else r.OngoingYr01 * YR06.Factor							--Single
						  end,
			OngoingYr07 = case when r.ReassignedProductGroupCode = 5					--Pensions	AG 05/06/2018
							then
								case when r.FrequencyCode = 2							--Monthly 
									then r.OngoingYr01 * YR07.Multiplier * YR07.Factor	--Regular
									else r.OngoingYr01 * YR07.Factor					--Single
								end
							else 
								0.0
						  end,
			OngoingYr08 = case when r.ReassignedProductGroupCode = 5					--Pensions	AG 05/06/2018 
							then
								case when r.FrequencyCode = 2							--Monthly 
									then r.OngoingYr01 * YR08.Multiplier * YR08.Factor	--Regular
									else r.OngoingYr01 * YR08.Factor					--Single
								end
							else 
								0.0
						  end,
			OngoingYr09 = case when r.ReassignedProductGroupCode = 5					--Pensions	AG 05/06/2018 
							then
								case when r.FrequencyCode = 2							--Monthly 
									then r.OngoingYr01 * YR09.Multiplier * YR09.Factor	--Regular
									else r.OngoingYr01 * YR09.Factor					--Single
								end
							else 
								0.0
						  end,
			OngoingYr10 = case when r.ReassignedProductGroupCode = 5					--Pensions	AG 05/06/2018
							then
								case when r.FrequencyCode = 2							--Monthly 
									then r.OngoingYr01 * YR10.Multiplier * YR10.Factor	--Regular
									else r.OngoingYr01 * YR10.Factor					--Single
								end
							else 
								0.0
						  end
	from	#AG_owt_Recognition_SEPARATE_ONGOING r
			left join owt_EliteFactors YR01 on YR01.FeeType = 'VNB' and YR01.Category = 'COB-ONGOING-DISCOUNT-YR01' and r.CommissionYear between YR01.StartYear and YR01.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors YR02 on YR02.FeeType = 'VNB' and YR02.Category = 'COB-ONGOING-DISCOUNT-YR02' and r.CommissionYear between YR02.StartYear and YR02.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors YR03 on YR03.FeeType = 'VNB' and YR03.Category = 'COB-ONGOING-DISCOUNT-YR03' and r.CommissionYear between YR03.StartYear and YR03.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors YR04 on YR04.FeeType = 'VNB' and YR04.Category = 'COB-ONGOING-DISCOUNT-YR04' and r.CommissionYear between YR04.StartYear and YR04.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors YR05 on YR05.FeeType = 'VNB' and YR05.Category = 'COB-ONGOING-DISCOUNT-YR05' and r.CommissionYear between YR05.StartYear and YR05.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors YR06 on YR06.FeeType = 'VNB' and YR06.Category = 'COB-ONGOING-DISCOUNT-YR06' and r.CommissionYear between YR06.StartYear and YR06.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors YR07 on YR07.FeeType = 'VNB' and YR07.Category = 'COB-ONGOING-DISCOUNT-YR07' and r.CommissionYear between YR07.StartYear and YR07.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors YR08 on YR08.FeeType = 'VNB' and YR08.Category = 'COB-ONGOING-DISCOUNT-YR08' and r.CommissionYear between YR08.StartYear and YR08.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors YR09 on YR09.FeeType = 'VNB' and YR09.Category = 'COB-ONGOING-DISCOUNT-YR09' and r.CommissionYear between YR09.StartYear and YR09.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors YR10 on YR10.FeeType = 'VNB' and YR10.Category = 'COB-ONGOING-DISCOUNT-YR10' and r.CommissionYear between YR10.StartYear and YR10.EndYear 
	where	r.CalculationType = 'WEALTH-ONGOING'

	select @RowCount = @@rowcount
	set @ProcessMessage = '#owt_Recognition (ongoing yr2-10) = ' + convert(nvarchar(10), @RowCount)
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseLog, @ProcessMessage, null, @Module, @Client
	
	/****************************************************************************

		Now add up all the numbers
																		
	****************************************************************************/
	
	update r
		set OngoingTotal	=	OngoingYr01 + OngoingYr02 + OngoingYr03 + OngoingYr04 + OngoingYr05 +
								OngoingYr06 + OngoingYr07 + OngoingYr08 + OngoingYr09 + OngoingYr10,
			PointsTotal		=	OngoingYr01 + OngoingYr02 + OngoingYr03 + OngoingYr04 + OngoingYr05 +
								OngoingYr06 + OngoingYr07 + OngoingYr08 + OngoingYr09 + OngoingYr10 +
								Initial + MBF	-- Note BSC is already included in the Ongoing, so don't include it in the Points Total.
	from	#AG_owt_Recognition_SEPARATE_ONGOING r

	select @RowCount = @@rowcount
	set @ProcessMessage = '#owt_Recognition (points total) = ' + convert(nvarchar(10), @RowCount)
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseLog, @ProcessMessage, null, @Module, @Client

	/****************************************************************************

		Merge the temporary table into the permanent table (IC data)
																		
	****************************************************************************/

	BEGIN TRANSACTION

	declare @SummaryOfChanges table (Change varchar(20))
	merge	dbo.AG_owt_Recognition_SEPARATE_ONGOING as trg
	using	#AG_owt_Recognition_SEPARATE_ONGOING as src
	on		trg.SourceID = src.SourceID
	and		trg.Source = src.Source
	when	matched 
	and		isnull(trg.PointsTotal,0) <> isnull(src.PointsTotal,0)
	then	update 
				set trg.CaseID = src.CaseID,
					trg.TransactionID = src.TransactionID,
					trg.Policy = src.Policy,
					trg.ProductCode = src.ProductCode,
					trg.BusinessCode = src.BusinessCode,
					trg.SellerCode = src.SellerCode,					--AG 13/06/2018
					trg.PointsTotal = src.PointsTotal,
					trg.BSC = src.BSC,
					trg.MBF = src.MBF,
					trg.Initial = src.Initial,
					trg.OngoingTotal = src.OngoingTotal,
					trg.OngoingYr01 = src.OngoingYr01,
					trg.OngoingYr02 = src.OngoingYr02,
					trg.OngoingYr03 = src.OngoingYr03,
					trg.OngoingYr04 = src.OngoingYr04,
					trg.OngoingYr05 = src.OngoingYr05,
					trg.OngoingYr06 = src.OngoingYr06,
					trg.OngoingYr07 = src.OngoingYr07,
					trg.OngoingYr08 = src.OngoingYr08,
					trg.OngoingYr09 = src.OngoingYr09,
					trg.OngoingYr10 = src.OngoingYr10,
					trg.FCARate = src.FCARate,
					trg.RetentionRate = src.RetentionRate,
					trg.RetentionRateBroker = src.RetentionRateBroker,
					trg.OngoingServicingRate = src.OngoingServicingRate,
					trg.OngoingServicingSource = src.OngoingServicingSource,
					trg.DA = src.DA,
					trg.AmountReceived = src.AmountReceived,
					trg.Premium = src.Premium,
					trg.AgentSplit = src.AgentSplit,
					trg.CommissionType = src.CommissionType,
					trg.CommissionTypeDesc = src.CommissionTypeDesc,
					trg.PayBasisCode = src.PayBasisCode,				--AG 13/06/2018
					trg.PayBasisDesc = src.PayBasisDesc,				--AG 13/06/2018
					trg.PaymentMatchedDate = src.PaymentMatchedDate,	--AG 13/06/2018	
					trg.Month = src.Month,
					trg.FrequencyCode = src.FrequencyCode,
					trg.FrequencyDesc = src.FrequencyDesc,
					trg.ReassignedProductGroupCode = src.ReassignedProductGroupCode,	--AG 05/06/2018
					trg.ReassignedProductGroupName = src.ReassignedProductGroupName,	--AG 05/06/2018
					trg.RecognitionType = src.RecognitionType,
					trg.CalculationType = src.CalculationType,
					trg.DateLastUpdated = @DateLastUpdated
	when	not matched by target 
	then	insert
			(
				SourceID,
				CaseID,
				TransactionID,
				Policy,
				ProductCode,
				BusinessCode,
				SellerCode,							--AG 13/06/2018
				PointsTotal,
				BSC,
				MBF,
				Initial,
				OngoingTotal,
				OngoingYr01,
				OngoingYr02,
				OngoingYr03,
				OngoingYr04,
				OngoingYr05,
				OngoingYr06,
				OngoingYr07,
				OngoingYr08,
				OngoingYr09,
				OngoingYr10,
				FCARate,
				RetentionRate,
				RetentionRateBroker,
				OngoingServicingRate,
				OngoingServicingSource,
				DA,
				AmountReceived,
				Premium,
				AgentSplit,
				CommissionType,
				CommissionTypeDesc,
				PayBasisCode,						--AG 13/06/2018
				PayBasisDesc,						--AG 13/06/2018
				PaymentMatchedDate,					--AG 13/06/2018
				Month,
				FrequencyCode,
				FrequencyDesc,
				ReassignedProductGroupCode,			--AG 05/06/2018
				ReassignedProductGroupName,			--AG 05/06/2018
				RecognitionType,
				CalculationType,
				Source,
				DateInserted,
				DateLastUpdated
			)		
			values
			(
				src.SourceID,
				src.CaseID,
				src.TransactionID,
				src.Policy,
				src.ProductCode,
				src.BusinessCode,
				src.SellerCode,						--AG 13/06/2018
				src.PointsTotal,
				src.BSC,
				src.MBF,
				src.Initial,
				src.OngoingTotal,
				src.OngoingYr01,
				src.OngoingYr02,
				src.OngoingYr03,
				src.OngoingYr04,
				src.OngoingYr05,
				src.OngoingYr06,
				src.OngoingYr07,
				src.OngoingYr08,
				src.OngoingYr09,
				src.OngoingYr10,
				src.FCARate,
				src.RetentionRate,
				src.RetentionRateBroker,
				src.OngoingServicingRate,
				src.OngoingServicingSource,
				src.DA,
				src.AmountReceived,
				src.Premium,
				src.AgentSplit,
				src.CommissionType,
				src.CommissionTypeDesc,
				src.PayBasisCode,					--AG 13/06/2018
				src.PayBasisDesc,					--AG 13/06/2018
				src.PaymentMatchedDate,				--AG 13/06/2018
				src.Month,
				src.FrequencyCode,
				src.FrequencyDesc,
				src.ReassignedProductGroupCode,		--AG 05/06/2018
				src.ReassignedProductGroupName,		--AG 05/06/2018
				src.RecognitionType,
				src.CalculationType,
				src.Source,
				src.DateInserted,
				src.DateLastUpdated)				--Merge statements must have a ;
	output $action into @SummaryOfChanges;
						
	/****************************************************************************

		Update OpenAccess
																		
	****************************************************************************/

/*	
	--Do not include MBF in the OpenAccess Commission Listing as it is on the MBF download
	--and we don't want MBF double counting.
	update	oal
		set VNB_Points = r.PointsTotal - r.MBF		--AG 04/06/2018 (2)
	from	msit_CommissionStatement cs
/*			inner join (select	distinct PKID
						from	owt_TransformationMovements tm 
						where	tm.DriverTableName = 'sa_swift_S_AGMFIL'
						and		tm.CommissionStatement = 'Y') tm on tm.PKID = cs.PendingPaymentID
*/			inner join msit_OpenworkAdviserListing oal on oal.SourceID = cs.ID and oal.Source = 'Openwork 2006'
			inner join owt_Recognition r 
						on r.SourceID = cs.PendingPaymentID
						and r.Source = oal.Source
	--where	isnull(oal.VNB_Points,0) <> isnull(r.PointsTotal,0)
	
	select @OALRowCount = @@rowcount
*/
	COMMIT TRANSACTION      
	
	select	@RowCount = COUNT(*)
	from	@SummaryOfChanges
	where	Change = 'INSERT'

	set @ProcessMessage = 'owt_Recognition (insert) = ' + convert(nvarchar(10), @RowCount)
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseLog, @ProcessMessage, null, @Module, @Client

	select	@RowCount = COUNT(*)
	from	@SummaryOfChanges
	where	Change = 'UPDATE'

	set @ProcessMessage = 'owt_Recognition (update) = ' + convert(nvarchar(10), @RowCount)
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseLog, @ProcessMessage, null, @Module, @Client
/*
	set @ProcessMessage = 'msit_OpenworkAdviserListing (update) = ' + convert(nvarchar(10), @OALRowCount)
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseLog, @ProcessMessage, null, @Module, @Client
*/
	/****************************************************************************

		T H E   E N D
																		
	****************************************************************************/
	
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseEnd, @ProcName, null, @Module, @Client

END TRY

BEGIN CATCH 

	select @ErrNum = ERROR_NUMBER(), @ErrMsg = ERROR_MESSAGE(), @ErrSev = ERROR_SEVERITY(), @ErrLine = ERROR_LINE(), @ErrState = XACT_STATE()
	set @ErrMsg = REPLACE(@ErrMsg, '.', '') + ' (error no: ' + CAST(@ErrNum AS VARCHAR(10)) + ') on line ' + CAST(@ErrLine AS VARCHAR(10))
	
	-- Test XACT_STATE for 0, 1, or -1.
    -- If 1, the transaction is committable.
    -- If -1, the transaction is uncommittable and should be rolled back.
    -- If 0, there is no transaction and a commit or rollback operation would generate an error.

	if @ErrState = -1			-- Transaction is uncommitable
		rollback transaction

	if @ErrState = 1			
		commit transaction

	-- Error message line 1
	set @ErrMsgBrief = left(@ErrMsg,100)
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseError, @ErrMsgBrief, null, @Module, @Client
	
	-- Error message line 2 - if any text exists
	set @ErrMsgBrief = substring(@ErrMsg,101,100)
	if len(@ErrMsgBrief) > 0
		exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseError, @ErrMsgBrief, null, @Module, @Client

	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseEnd, @ProcName, null, @Module, @Client

	RAISERROR(@ErrMsg, @ErrSev , 1)

END CATCH

/****************************************************************************

			E N D															

****************************************************************************/

return @ErrNum


GO
/****** Object:  StoredProcedure [dbo].[owp_RecognitionSwiftONGOING_Backup20180706AG]    Script Date: 7/3/2026 3:44:25 PM ******/
SET ANSI_NULLS ON
GO
SET QUOTED_IDENTIFIER ON
GO
/*********************************************************************************************************

Program:		owp_RecognitionSwift					
Author:			Alan Groves
Date created:	11/04/2018
											
Description:
===========

This proc populates the new recognition table called "owt_Recognition" with "Value of New Business"
(VNB) points.

This proc handles all of the swift data which includes:
WEALTH - COB business i.e. pensions and investments
MORTGAGES
PROTECTION

Note: There is a separate proc that calculates the GI VNB points from the Paymentshield data.

The approach of this proc is to use the incremental PendingPaymentIDs from the overnight batch
to calculate the VNB points in a temporary table.

The temporary table is then merged with the permanent table to make the calculated (or
re-calculated values) permanent.

Terms
-----
BSC			- Business Service Charge.
MBF			- Mortgage Broker Fee.
OGS			- Ongoing Servicing.
BSC Rate	- 0.12% at the time of writing (24/04/2018). This could be changed by the business, but
				would also require some DEV work in OWS.
DF			- Discount Factor.
DA			- Distribution Allowance (the total amount paid out by the provider to Openwork)
AUM			- Assets Under Management. Basically the amount invested or the premium on investment
				cases.
Average AUM - Average amount invested annually which is equivalent to 6 months' premium.

THE CALCULATIONS
================

There are two potential parts: initial + ongoing (if ongoing applies). If BSC (applies to ongoing 
only) and MBF (applies to mortgages only) apply, then these are also included:

MORTGAGE
--------
Part 1: MBF column = (Advice Fee Amount X Broker Retention Rate) - (Advice Fee Amount X Mort FCA Rate)
Part 2: Initial column = (Proc Fee Amount X Mortgage Retention Rate) - (Proc Fee X Mort FCA Rate) 
Mortgage Points Total = Initial + MBF

PROTECTION
----------
= (DA X Protection Retention Rate) - (DA X Protection FCA Rate) 
Protection Points Total = Initial

WEALTH (COB i.e. pensions and investments)
------
Part 1: Initial column = (DA X Wealth Retention Rate) - (DA X Wealth FCA Rate)

Part 2:

****XXXX****

NOTE: Where the BSC rate is greater than the ongoing rate, then BSC gets ALL of the AVAILABLE 
ongoing.

****XXXX****

REGULAR - BSC applies:
Year 1 column = BSC Points + Non-BSC Points - FCA Points
Non-BSC Points = Ave AUM X (OGS Rate - BSC Rate) X COB Retention Rate
BSC Points = Ave AUM X BSC Rate
FCA Points = Ave AUM X OGS Rate X COB FCA Rate

REGULAR - Non-BSC: 
Year 1 column = (Ave AUM X OGS Rate X COB Retention Rate) - (Ave AUM X OGS Rate X COB FCA Rate)

SINGLE - BSC applies:
Year 1 column = (AUM X BSC Rate) + (AUM X (OGS Rate - BSC Rate) X COB Retention Rate) - (AUM X OGS Rate X COB FCA Rate) 

SINGLE - Non-BSC:
Year 1 column = (AUM X OGS Rate X COB Retention Rate) - (AUM X OGS Rate X COB FCA Rate) 

Then years 2 to 10 are calculated by applying a discount factor
Year  2 = Year 1 X  3 X DF
Year  3 = Year 1 X  5 X DF
Year  4 = Year 1 X  7 X DF
Year  5 = Year 1 X  9 X DF
Year  6 = Year 1 X 11 X DF
Year  7 = Year 1 X 13 X DF
Year  8 = Year 1 X 15 X DF
Year  9 = Year 1 X 17 X DF
Year 10 = Year 1 X 19 X DF

Wealth Points Total =	OngoingYr01 + OngoingYr02 + OngoingYr03 + OngoingYr04 + OngoingYr05 +
						OngoingYr06 + OngoingYr07 + OngoingYr08 + OngoingYr09 + OngoingYr10 +
						Initial

GI
--
See stored proc "owp_RecognitionGIPaymentshield".
 
Notes:
-----

1)	There is a BSC column on table owt_Recognition. However, BSC is already included in the ongoing
	years 1 - 10, so the BSC column does not need to be added in. In fact you will double count if 
	you attempt to do anything with it other than display it.

2)	Occasionally an investment case may receive two or more cheques which
	then go through Swift as two or more SINGLE investments on the SAME
	slice. Although the INITIAL VNB calculation will pro-rata correctly
	because it is based on the amount received, this scenario will cause
	ongoing VNB to be calculated on each of the payment records and so will 
	double count (or worse if there are more than two cheques received).
	Since de-coupling IC from ongoing i.e. they now have separate rows on
	table owt_Recognition, the issue of multiple cheques should no longer
	cause ongoing double counting.


This proc is called as follows:
	declare @rc int
	exec @rc = dbo.owp_RecognitionSwift 'Openwork', 'Recognition'
	select @rc

					
AMENDMENT HISTORY				
=================								

Date		Author		Description
----		------		-----------
26/04/2018	A Groves	Only include rows in the OGS lookups where the OngoingServiceFee > 0.0.
						Negative OGS rates are bad data and at the time of writing, there are
						39 of these.
27/04/2018	A Groves	Additional calculation and condition to handle the scenario where BSC applies
						but the OGS Rate is less than the BSC rate. Previously, this caused the
						total ongoing to be zero. However, there are two components to ongoing VNB 
						points, the BSC share and the non-BSC share. So the BSC share (which takes 
						100% when the OGS rate is less than 0.12%) should still yield ongoing points.
27/04/2018	A Groves	Single ongoing Yr01 corrected by applying outer brackets before signing the result.
03/05/2018	A Groves	Added update of column "msit_OpenworkAdviserListing.VNB_Points".
18/05/2018	A Groves	Changed mortgage calculation to use e.AMOUNT_REC instead of pt.CommInitialAmount
						as Marcus Cossey wanted the actual amount received to be used for the DA.
04/06/2018	A Groves	1) In the REGULAR section of column "OngoingYr01", the condition for cs.FrequencyCode <> 6
							was added to ensure the code differentiates to the SINGLE section.
						2) Exclude MBF from the OpenAccess table (msit_OpenworkAdviserListing) as this
							is shown on the MBF download and would otherwise incur MBF double counting.
05/06/2018	A Groves	1) Marcus Cossey advised that investments should get ongoing for years 1 to 6 and
							pensions for years 1 to 10. Previously, both lines of business got years 1 to 10.
						2) Marcus Cossey asked for split payments (i.e. where multiple cheques are processed
							for a SINGLE investment) to only claculate ongoing VNB on the oldest payment. 
11/06/2018	A Groves	1) PSD processed a protection clawback statement as fee type initial. These clawbacks
							all generated +ve instead of -ve VNB points. A tweak was added to ensure that the 
							absolute value of AMOUNT_REC is used to ensure the VNB is correctly signed. 
						2) Another unknown business rule has surfaced: Previously, only initial, clawbacks and
							adjustments on slices created new from 2017 were included. This rule only applies
							to initial. Clawbacks and adjustments can belong to a slice created at any point
							in the past. However, note that the payment (irrespective of whether it is +ve or 
							-ve), must not pre-date 2017.
13/06/2018	A Groves	Marcus asked for SellerCode and PaymentMatchedDate to be added so he need only use 
							the one table for both the adviser and enterprise leagues. PayBasisCode and 
							PayBasisDesc were also added at the same time as these are used in the calculations.
*************************************************************************************************************/

CREATE PROCEDURE [dbo].[owp_RecognitionSwiftONGOING_Backup20180706AG]
	@Client		varchar(50),
	@Module		Varchar(50)

AS

set nocount on

declare		@PhaseStart				varchar(50),
			@PhaseEnd				varchar(50),
			@PhaseError				varchar(50),
			@PhaseLog				varchar(50),
			@ProcName				varchar(100),
			@ProcessMessage			varchar(100),
			@RowCount				int,
			@OALRowCount			int,
			@ErrMsg					nvarchar(4000),
			@ErrMsgBrief			nvarchar(100),
			@ErrNum					int,
			@ErrSev					int,
			@ErrLine				int,
			@ErrState				int,
			@DateLastUpdated		datetime,
			@OwlManager2Code		nvarchar(10)
			
/****************************************************************************

	Set initial parameters																
																		
****************************************************************************/

set @ProcName			= object_name(@@procid)
set @PhaseStart			= 'START'
set @PhaseEnd			= 'END'
set @PhaseError			= 'ERROR'
set @PhaseLog			= 'LOG'
set @ErrNum				= 0	
set @DateLastUpdated	= getdate()

set @OwlManager2Code = (select cde.Code from msit_MIWarehouseCodesAndDescriptions cde
			where cde.ColumnName = 'Manager2Code' and cde.Description = 'Owl Financial')

-- We want this logging irrespective of whether or not there is a rollback
exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseStart, @ProcName, null, @Module, @Client

/****************************************************************************

	Populate the table																
																		
****************************************************************************/

SET XACT_ABORT ON	-- Needed if XACT_STATE() function is used.

BEGIN TRY

	/****************************************************************************

		Link OWS data to Swift data to enable the ongoing servicng (OGS) rate
		to be looked up.
																		
	****************************************************************************/
	
	select	distinct s.PersonID, swp.Client_Num, p.InternalProductID, swp.ProductCode 
	into	#SwiftOWSClientLink
	from	sa_ows_Sale s
			inner join sa_ows_Policies p on p.SaleID = s.SaleID
			inner join mstt_Policies swp on swp.PolicyRef = p.PolicyID
	where	s.DateSubmitted is not null
	--and		s.PersonID = 146030

	select @RowCount = @@rowcount
	set @ProcessMessage = '#SwiftOWSClientLink = ' + convert(nvarchar(10), @RowCount)
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseLog, @ProcessMessage, null, @Module, @Client

	-- The OGS rate is stored for the client/product combination
	select	link.Client_Num, link.ProductCode, max(ogs.OngoingServiceFee) as OngoingServiceFee
	into	#OGSLookUp
	from	#SwiftOWSClientLink link 
			inner join mstt_ProductHierarchy ph on ph.ProductCode = link.ProductCode
			inner join Submission.sa_ows_SubmittedProductCurrentOngoingServiceFee ogs
							on ogs.PersonID = link.PersonID
							and ogs.InternalProductID = (case when ph.RDRType = 'ONPLAT' 
															then -2 
															else link.InternalProductID 
														 end)
	where	ogs.OngoingServiceFee > 0.0							--AG 26/04/2018
	group	by 	link.Client_Num, link.ProductCode

	select @RowCount = @@rowcount
	set @ProcessMessage = '#OGSLookUp = ' + convert(nvarchar(10), @RowCount)
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseLog, @ProcessMessage, null, @Module, @Client

	create index idx_OGSLookUp on #OGSLookUp (Client_num, ProductCode)

	--This is an additional catch for OGS by storing the client's highest OGS
	--rate against their client number. This lookup will apply if the first
	--look up fails. The first lookup can fail, for example, if the case was 
	--not submitted on OWS i.e. the CaseID has a "17" prefix. 
	select	Client_Num, MAX(OngoingServiceFee) as OngoingServiceFee
	into	#OGSLookUpClient
	from	#OGSLookUp
	group	by Client_Num

	select @RowCount = @@rowcount
	set @ProcessMessage = '#OGSLookUpClient = ' + convert(nvarchar(10), @RowCount)
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseLog, @ProcessMessage, null, @Module, @Client
	
	create index idx_OGSLookUpClient on #OGSLookUpClient (Client_num)

	/****************************************************************************

		Calculate VNB and populate the temporary table with the results
		
		Note that there are oddities like LV protection payments which always
		come in pairs with one large and one much smaller amount (e.g. TransactionID 
		= 6684787.) The system treats both payments in the pair as first payments 
		and the (projected) DA associated with both is the same (because it's on 
		the policy transaction). 
		
		There is also a requirement to front-load VNB points on accrual and level
		payments. This means calculate the VNB for the full amount of the DA and 
		put it on the first payment record and then on all subsequent accrual and 
		level payments, set the VNB to zero.
		
		Thus two different sources of DA are used depending on whether we need the
		full DA amount for accruals and level or the actual amount received for all
		other scenarios including the LV split payment scenario. The two sources are:
		
		mstt_PolicyTransactions.CommInitialAmount - Full (projected) DA amount
		
		mstt_Expectation.AMOUNT_REC - The DA actually received. This handles the
										LV scenario whereby the AMOUNT_REC is 
										proportioned across the two payments received.   
																		
	****************************************************************************/

	select	top 0 
			*, 
			convert(int,NULL) as CommissionYear
	into	#AG_owt_Recognition_SEPARATE_ONGOING
	from	AG_owt_Recognition_SEPARATE_ONGOING

	/****************************************************************************

		Phase 1 - Process all but regular accrual cases with clawbacks/adjustments
		Accruals are front loaded unless their latest payment is a clawback/adjudtment
		in which case they accrue VNB points on a per payment basis and so these
		are dealt with in Phases 2 and 3.
																		
	****************************************************************************/

	insert into #AG_owt_Recognition_SEPARATE_ONGOING
	(
		SourceID,
		CaseID,
		TransactionID,
		Policy,
		ProductCode,
		BusinessCode,
		SellerCode,						--AG 13/06/2018
		PointsTotal,
		BSC,
		MBF,
		Initial,
		OngoingTotal,
		OngoingYr01,
		OngoingYr02,
		OngoingYr03,
		OngoingYr04,
		OngoingYr05,
		OngoingYr06,
		OngoingYr07,
		OngoingYr08,
		OngoingYr09,
		OngoingYr10,
		FCARate,
		RetentionRate,
		RetentionRateBroker,
		OngoingServicingRate,
		OngoingServicingSource,
		DA,
		AmountReceived,
		Premium,
		AgentSplit,
		CommissionType,
		CommissionTypeDesc,
		PayBasisCode,					--AG 13/06/2018
		PayBasisDesc,					--AG 13/06/2018
		PaymentMatchedDate,				--AG 13/06/2018
		Month,
		FrequencyCode,
		FrequencyDesc,
		ReassignedProductGroupCode,		--AG 05/06/2018
		ReassignedProductGroupName,		--AG 05/06/2018
		RecognitionType,
		CalculationType,
		Source,
		DateInserted,
		DateLastUpdated,
		CommissionYear
	)
	select	cs.PendingPaymentID as SourceID,
			cs.CaseID,
			cs.TransactionID,
			cs.ExtPolicyNumber as Policy,
			cs.ProductCode,
			cs.BusinessCode,
			cs.AgentCode as SellerCode,				--AG 13/06/2018
			0.0 as PointsTotal,
			0.0 as BSC,
			case 
				when mbf.MortgageFeeID is not null and cs.INIssued <> 0 then (((mbf.AdviceFeeAmount)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * MRbkr.FACTOR) - ((mbf.AdviceFeeAmount)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * Mfca.FACTOR)) --Note that mbf.AdviceFeeAmount is signed correctly - so no coding for signing is needed here
				else 0.0
			end as MBF,
			case 
				--When the adviser has changed, the AgentSplit can become zero in which case the ELITE points should be zero.
				when cs.AgentSplit = 0 then 0
				
				--WEALTH CALCULATION START
				--Indemnity payments or SINGLEs or IC Clawbacks or IC adjustments Start
				when (ph.ProductCategoryCode = 1 or pcc.KeyValue2 = '1') and (cs.FrequencyCode = 6 or cs.PayBasisCode in ('T') or cs.CommissionType in (2,17)) and cs.commissiontype in (1,2,17) and cs.INIssued <> 0 then (((e.AMOUNT_REC)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * Crate.FACTOR) - ((e.AMOUNT_REC)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * Cfca.FACTOR)) * case when cs.INIssued < 0 then -1 else 1 end
				--Indemnity payments or SINGLEs or IC Clawbacks or IC adjustments End
				--Accruals & Level Start
				when (ph.ProductCategoryCode = 1 or pcc.KeyValue2 = '1') and cs.INIssued <> 0 then (((pt.CommInitialAmount)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * Crate.FACTOR) - ((pt.CommInitialAmount)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * Cfca.FACTOR)) * case when cs.INIssued < 0 then -1 else 1 end
				--Accruals & Level End
				--WEALTH CALCULATION END
				
				--MORTGAGE CALCULATION START
				--Note: The MBF component has its own table column
				--Only 1 payment for mortgages
				when ph.ProductGroupCode = 3 and cs.INIssued <> 0 then (((e.AMOUNT_REC)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * MRproc.FACTOR) - ((e.AMOUNT_REC)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * Mfca.FACTOR)) * case when cs.INIssued < 0 then -1 else 1 end	--AG 18/05/2018
				--MORTGAGE CALCULATION END
				
				--PROTECTION CALCULATION START
				--Indemnity payments or SINGLEs or IC Clawbacks or IC adjustments Start
				when ph.ProductGroupCode = 6 and (cs.FrequencyCode = 6 or cs.PayBasisCode in ('T') or cs.CommissionType in (2,17)) and cs.commissiontype in (1,2,17) and cs.INIssued <> 0 then ((abs(e.AMOUNT_REC)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * Prate.FACTOR) - (abs(e.AMOUNT_REC)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * Pfca.FACTOR)) * case when cs.INIssued < 0 then -1 else 1 end	--AG 11/06/2018 (1)
				--Indemnity payments or SINGLEs or IC Clawbacks or IC adjustments End
				--Accruals & Level Start
				when ph.ProductGroupCode = 6 and cs.INIssued <> 0 then (((pt.CommInitialAmount)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * Prate.FACTOR) - ((pt.CommInitialAmount)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * Pfca.FACTOR)) * case when cs.INIssued < 0 then -1 else 1 end
				--Accruals & Level End
				--PROTECTION CALCULATION END

				else 0.0

			end as Initial,
			0.0 as OngoingTotal,
			0.0 as OngoingYr01,
			0.0 as OngoingYr02,
			0.0 as OngoingYr03,
			0.0 as OngoingYr04,
			0.0 as OngoingYr05,
			0.0 as OngoingYr06,
			0.0 as OngoingYr07,
			0.0 as OngoingYr08,
			0.0 as OngoingYr09,
			0.0 as OngoingYr10,
			case 
				when (ph.ProductCategoryCode = 1 or pcc.KeyValue2 = '1') then Cfca.FACTOR*100.0		--COB
				when ph.ProductGroupCode = 3 then Mfca.FACTOR*100.0		--MORT
				when ph.ProductGroupCode = 6 then Pfca.FACTOR*100.0		--PROT
				else 0.0
			end as FCARate,
			case 
				when (ph.ProductCategoryCode = 1 or pcc.KeyValue2 = '1') then Crate.FACTOR*100.0	--COB
				when ph.ProductGroupCode = 3 then MRproc.FACTOR*100.0	--MORT
				when ph.ProductGroupCode = 6 then Prate.FACTOR*100.0	--PROT
				else 0.0
			end as RetentionRate,
			case 
				when mbf.MortgageFeeID is not null then  MRbkr.FACTOR*100.0	
				else 0.0
			end as RetentionRateBroker,
			null as OngoingServicingRate,
			null as OngoingServicingSource,
			pt.CommInitialAmount as DA,
			e.AMOUNT_REC as AmountReceived,
			cs.Premium,
			cs.AgentSplit,
			cs.CommissionType,
			left(cs.StandingOrderDesc,50) as CommissionTypeDesc,
			cs.PayBasisCode,							--AG 13/06/2018
			cs.PayBasisDesc,							--AG 13/06/2018
			cs.CreateDate as PaymentMatchedDate,		--AG 13/06/2018
			cs.Month,
			cs.FrequencyCode,
			cs.FrequencyDesc,
			pg.ProductGroupCode as ReassignedProductGroupCode,	--Force the re-assigned products...		AG 05/06/2018
			pg.ProductGroupName as ReassignedProductGroupName,	--...to be processed as investments		AG 05/06/2018
			'VNB-INI-PHASE-1' as RecognitionType,
			case 
				when (ph.ProductCategoryCode = 1 or pcc.KeyValue2 = '1') then 'WEALTH-INITIAL'
				when ph.ProductGroupCode = 3 then 'MORTGAGE'
				when ph.ProductGroupCode = 6 then 'PROTECTION'
				else null
			end as CalculationType,
			'Openwork 2006' as Source,
			@DateLastUpdated as DateInserted,
			@DateLastUpdated as DateLastUpdated,
			csp.year as CommissionYear
	--select count(*)
	from	msit_CommissionStatement cs
/*			inner join (select	distinct PKID
						from	owt_TransformationMovements tm 
						where	tm.DriverTableName = 'sa_swift_S_AGMFIL'
						and		tm.CommissionStatement = 'Y') tm on tm.PKID = cs.PendingPaymentID
*/			inner join mstt_Agents ag on ag.Code = cs.BusinessCode
			inner join mstt_PolicyTransactions pt on pt.ID = cs.TransactionID
			inner join mstt_Policies p on p.POL_NUM = pt.PolicyID
			inner join msit_CommissionStatementPeriods VNBStart on convert(date,pt.CreateDateTime) between VNBStart.PeriodStartDate and VNBStart.PeriodEndDate
			inner join msit_Commissionstatementperiods csp on csp.month = cs.month
			inner join mstt_ProductHierarchy ph on ph.productcode = cs.productcode
			inner join mstt_Expectation e on e.ID = cs.ExpectationID
			left join dbo.owt_MortgageBrokerFees mbf on mbf.PendingPaymentID = cs.PendingPaymentID and mbf.AdviceFeeCharged = 'Yes'
			left join owt_SelectionControl SC
						on SC.Process = 'ElitePoints' 
						and SC.KeyType = 'NSCPotCode' 
						and cs.CreateDate between SC.EffectiveStartDate and SC.EffectiveEndDate
			left join mstt_Commissions BSCpot
						on BSCpot.TransactionID = cs.TransactionID 
						and BSCpot.Agent_Code = sc.KeyValue
						and BSCpot.CommissionType = 10
			left join owt_SelectionControl SFMPC						
						on SFMPC.Process = 'ElitePoints' 
						and SFMPC.KeyType = 'ServicingFeeMarginPotCode' 
						and cs.CreateDate between SFMPC.EffectiveStartDate and SFMPC.EffectiveEndDate
			left join mstt_Commissions SFMpot							
						on SFMpot.TransactionID = cs.TransactionID 
						and SFMpot.Agent_Code = SFMPC.KeyValue
						and SFMpot.CommissionType = 10	
			left join owt_SelectionControl pcc 
						on pcc.Process = 'ElitePoints'
						and pcc.KeyType = 'ProductCategoryCode'
						and pcc.KeyValue = cs.ProductCode	
						and cs.CreateDate between pcc.EffectiveStartDate and pcc.EffectiveEndDate
			left join owt_SelectionControl ogsdflt 
						on ogsdflt.Process = 'ElitePoints'
						and ogsdflt.KeyType = 'DefaultOngoingServicingRate'
						and ogsdflt.SelectionType = 'VNB'
						and ogsdflt.KeyValue = case when ph.RDRType = 'ONPLAT' then 'ONPLAT' else 'OFPLAT' end
						and cs.CreateDate between ogsdflt.EffectiveStartDate and ogsdflt.EffectiveEndDate
			left join mstt_CodeProductGroup pg on pg.ProductGroupCode = case when pcc.KeyValue2 = '1' then 2 else ph.ProductGroupCode end
			left join owt_EliteFactors Cfca on Cfca.FeeType = 'VNB' and Cfca.category = 'COB-FCA-RATE' and csp.year between Cfca.StartYear and Cfca.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors Crate on Crate.FeeType = 'VNB' and Crate.category = 'COB-RETENTION-RATE' and csp.year between Crate.StartYear and Crate.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors Mfca on Mfca.FeeType = 'VNB' and Mfca.category = 'MORT-FCA-RATE' and csp.year between Mfca.StartYear and Mfca.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors MRproc on MRproc.FeeType = 'VNB' and MRproc.category = 'MORT-RETENTION-RATE-PROC' and csp.year between MRproc.StartYear and MRproc.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors MRbkr on MRbkr.FeeType = 'VNB' and MRbkr.category = 'MORT-RETENTION-RATE-BROKER' and csp.year between MRbkr.StartYear and MRbkr.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors Pfca on Pfca.FeeType = 'VNB' and Pfca.category = 'PROT-FCA-RATE' and csp.year between Pfca.StartYear and Pfca.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors Prate on Prate.FeeType = 'VNB' and Prate.category = 'PROT-RETENTION-RATE' and csp.year between Prate.StartYear and Prate.EndYear 
			left join msit_CommissionStatement csadj 
						on csadj.TransactionID = cs.TransactionID 
						and csadj.AgentCode = cs.AgentCode 
						and csadj.CommissionType in (2,17)
						and	csadj.PayBasisCode in ('F')				--Accrual
						and	csadj.FrequencyCode <> 6				--Regular 
	where	cs.ReportingClassCode = 1
	and		ag.Manager2Code <> @OwlManager2Code		--Exclude Owl
	and		cs.INIssued <> 0
	and		csp.Year >= 2017						--Ensure in-scope payments are consistent with VNB start
	and		VNBStart.Year >= 2017
	and		cs.CommissionType in (1,2,17)
	and		abs(e.AMOUNT_REC) >= 0.01	
	--and		((VNBStart.Year >= 2017 and cs.CommissionType = 1 and e.AMOUNT_REC >= 0.01)		--VNB to start from new slices in 2017 for +ve payments but...			AG 11/06/2018 (2)
	--		or (cs.CommissionType in (2,17) or e.AMOUNT_REC <= -0.01))						--...for -ve payments, the slice can start from any date in the past	AG 11/06/2018 (2)
	and		csadj.ID is null						--Deal with accrual regular clawbacks/adjustments later

	select @RowCount = @@rowcount
	set @ProcessMessage = '#owt_Recognition (ini ph1 - no accr adj) = ' + convert(nvarchar(10), @RowCount)
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseLog, @ProcessMessage, null, @Module, @Client

	/****************************************************************************

		Now deal with accrual clawbacks and adjustments
																		
	****************************************************************************/

	--drop table #msit_CommissionStatementSUMMARY

	--Find transactions with clawbacks/adj on them
	select	cs.TransactionID,
			cs.AgentCode,
			Min(case when cs.CommissionType = 1 then cs.PendingPaymentID else null end) as MinInitialPendingPaymentID,
			MAX(case when cs.CommissionType = 1 then cs.PendingPaymentID else null end) as MaxInitialPendingPaymentID,
			MAX(case when cs.CommissionType in (2,17) then cs.PendingPaymentID else null end) as MaxAdjPendingPaymentID,
			null as MinInitialAfterAdjPendingPaymentID
	into	#msit_CommissionStatementSUMMARY
	from	msit_CommissionStatement cs
			inner join mstt_Agents ag on ag.Code = cs.BusinessCode
			inner join mstt_PolicyTransactions pt on pt.ID = cs.TransactionID
			inner join mstt_Policies p on p.POL_NUM = pt.PolicyID
			inner join msit_CommissionStatementPeriods VNBStart on convert(date,pt.CreateDateTime) between VNBStart.PeriodStartDate and VNBStart.PeriodEndDate
			inner join msit_Commissionstatementperiods csp on csp.month = cs.month
			inner join mstt_Expectation e on e.ID = cs.ExpectationID
			left join msit_CommissionStatement csadj 
						on csadj.TransactionID = cs.TransactionID 
						and csadj.AgentCode = cs.AgentCode 
						and csadj.CommissionType in (2,17)
						and	csadj.PayBasisCode in ('F')				--Accrual
						and	csadj.FrequencyCode <> 6				--Regular 
	where	cs.ReportingClassCode = 1
	and		cs.CommissionType in (1,2,17)			--We want all the initial payment types (i.e. not trail (ongoing))
	and		ag.Manager2Code <> @OwlManager2Code		--Exclude Owl
	and		csp.Year >= 2017						--Ensure in-scope payments are consistent with VNB start
	and		VNBStart.Year >= 2017 
	and		abs(e.AMOUNT_REC) >= 0.01	
	and		csadj.ID is not null					--select regular accrual transactions with clawbacks/adjustments
	--and cs.TransactionID in (5613333,6296827)
	group by	cs.TransactionID,
				cs.AgentCode

	select @RowCount = @@rowcount
	set @ProcessMessage = '#msit_CommissionStatementSUMMARY (accr adj txns) = ' + convert(nvarchar(10), @RowCount)
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseLog, @ProcessMessage, null, @Module, @Client

	--Get first initial payment after last clawback/adj
	update css
		set MinInitialAfterAdjPendingPaymentID = summ.MinPendingPaymentID 
	from  #msit_CommissionStatementSUMMARY css
			inner join  (
						select cssinner.TransactionID, cssinner.AgentCode, min(cs.PendingPaymentID) as MinPendingPaymentID
						from #msit_CommissionStatementSUMMARY cssinner
								inner join msit_CommissionStatement cs
											on cs.TransactionID = cssinner.TransactionID
											and cs.AgentCode = cssinner.AgentCode
						where cs.PendingPaymentID > cssinner.MaxAdjPendingPaymentID
						group by cssinner.TransactionID, cssinner.AgentCode
						) summ on  summ.TransactionID = css.TransactionID
							   and summ.AgentCode = css.AgentCode

	select @RowCount = @@rowcount
	set @ProcessMessage = '#msit_CommissionStatementSUMMARY (1st IC after adj) = ' + convert(nvarchar(10), @RowCount)
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseLog, @ProcessMessage, null, @Module, @Client

	/****************************************************************************

		Phase 2 - This phase deals with regular accrual cases where there is at 
		least one clawback/adjustment. In this scenario the VNB is changed from 
		front loaded to a per payment basis.
																		
	****************************************************************************/

	insert into #AG_owt_Recognition_SEPARATE_ONGOING
	(
		SourceID,
		CaseID,
		TransactionID,
		Policy,
		ProductCode,
		BusinessCode,
		SellerCode,						
		PointsTotal,
		BSC,
		MBF,
		Initial,
		OngoingTotal,
		OngoingYr01,
		OngoingYr02,
		OngoingYr03,
		OngoingYr04,
		OngoingYr05,
		OngoingYr06,
		OngoingYr07,
		OngoingYr08,
		OngoingYr09,
		OngoingYr10,
		FCARate,
		RetentionRate,
		RetentionRateBroker,
		OngoingServicingRate,
		OngoingServicingSource,
		DA,
		AmountReceived,
		Premium,
		AgentSplit,
		CommissionType,
		CommissionTypeDesc,
		PayBasisCode,					
		PayBasisDesc,					
		PaymentMatchedDate,				
		Month,
		FrequencyCode,
		FrequencyDesc,
		ReassignedProductGroupCode,		
		ReassignedProductGroupName,		
		RecognitionType,
		CalculationType,
		Source,
		DateInserted,
		DateLastUpdated,
		CommissionYear
	)
	select	cs.PendingPaymentID as SourceID,
			cs.CaseID,
			cs.TransactionID,
			cs.ExtPolicyNumber as Policy,
			cs.ProductCode,
			cs.BusinessCode,
			cs.AgentCode as SellerCode,				
			0.0 as PointsTotal,
			0.0 as BSC,
			case 
				when mbf.MortgageFeeID is not null and cs.INIssued <> 0 then (((mbf.AdviceFeeAmount)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * MRbkr.FACTOR) - ((mbf.AdviceFeeAmount)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * Mfca.FACTOR)) --Note that mbf.AdviceFeeAmount is signed correctly - so no coding for signing is needed here
				else 0.0
			end as MBF,
			case 
				--When the adviser has changed, the AgentSplit can become zero in which case the ELITE points should be zero.
				when cs.AgentSplit = 0 then 0
				
				--WEALTH CALCULATION START
				--Indemnity payments or SINGLEs or IC Clawbacks or IC adjustments Start
				--THIS SCENARIO DOESN'T OCCUR IN PHASE 2
				--Indemnity payments or SINGLEs or IC Clawbacks or IC adjustments End
				--Accruals & Level Start
				when (ph.ProductCategoryCode = 1 or pcc.KeyValue2 = '1') then (((e.AMOUNT_REC)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * Crate.FACTOR) - ((e.AMOUNT_REC)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * Cfca.FACTOR)) * case when cs.CommissionType in (2,17) then -1 else 1 end
				--Accruals & Level End
				--WEALTH CALCULATION END
				
				--MORTGAGE CALCULATION START
				--Note: The MBF component has its own table column
				--Only 1 payment for mortgages
				when ph.ProductGroupCode = 3 then (((e.AMOUNT_REC)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * MRproc.FACTOR) - ((e.AMOUNT_REC)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * Mfca.FACTOR)) * case when cs.CommissionType in (2,17) then -1 else 1 end	
				--MORTGAGE CALCULATION END
				
				--PROTECTION CALCULATION START
				--Indemnity payments or SINGLEs or IC Clawbacks or IC adjustments Start
				--THIS SCENARIO DOESN'T OCCUR IN PHASE 2
				--Indemnity payments or SINGLEs or IC Clawbacks or IC adjustments End
				--Accruals & Level Start
				when ph.ProductGroupCode = 6 then (((e.AMOUNT_REC)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * Prate.FACTOR) - ((e.AMOUNT_REC)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * Pfca.FACTOR)) * case when cs.CommissionType in (2,17) then -1 else 1 end
				--Accruals & Level End
				--PROTECTION CALCULATION END

				else 0.0

			end as Initial,
			0.0 as OngoingTotal,
			0.0 as OngoingYr01,
			0.0 as OngoingYr02,
			0.0 as OngoingYr03,
			0.0 as OngoingYr04,
			0.0 as OngoingYr05,
			0.0 as OngoingYr06,
			0.0 as OngoingYr07,
			0.0 as OngoingYr08,
			0.0 as OngoingYr09,
			0.0 as OngoingYr10,
			case 
				when (ph.ProductCategoryCode = 1 or pcc.KeyValue2 = '1') then Cfca.FACTOR*100.0		--COB
				when ph.ProductGroupCode = 3 then Mfca.FACTOR*100.0		--MORT
				when ph.ProductGroupCode = 6 then Pfca.FACTOR*100.0		--PROT
				else 0.0
			end as FCARate,
			case 
				when (ph.ProductCategoryCode = 1 or pcc.KeyValue2 = '1') then Crate.FACTOR*100.0	--COB
				when ph.ProductGroupCode = 3 then MRproc.FACTOR*100.0	--MORT
				when ph.ProductGroupCode = 6 then Prate.FACTOR*100.0	--PROT
				else 0.0
			end as RetentionRate,
			case 
				when mbf.MortgageFeeID is not null then  MRbkr.FACTOR*100.0	
				else 0.0
			end as RetentionRateBroker,
			null as OngoingServicingRate,
			null as OngoingServicingSource,
			pt.CommInitialAmount as DA,
			e.AMOUNT_REC as AmountReceived,
			cs.Premium,
			cs.AgentSplit,
			cs.CommissionType,
			left(cs.StandingOrderDesc,50) as CommissionTypeDesc,
			cs.PayBasisCode,							
			cs.PayBasisDesc,							
			cs.CreateDate as PaymentMatchedDate,		
			cs.Month,
			cs.FrequencyCode,
			cs.FrequencyDesc,
			pg.ProductGroupCode as ReassignedProductGroupCode,	--Force the re-assigned products...		
			pg.ProductGroupName as ReassignedProductGroupName,	--...to be processed as investments		
			'VNB-INI-PHASE-2' as RecognitionType,
			case 
				when (ph.ProductCategoryCode = 1 or pcc.KeyValue2 = '1') then 'WEALTH-INITIAL'
				when ph.ProductGroupCode = 3 then 'MORTGAGE'
				when ph.ProductGroupCode = 6 then 'PROTECTION'
				else null
			end as CalculationType,
			'Openwork 2006' as Source,
			@DateLastUpdated as DateInserted,
			@DateLastUpdated as DateLastUpdated,
			csp.year as CommissionYear
	from	#msit_CommissionStatementSUMMARY css
			inner join msit_CommissionStatement cs
						on cs.TransactionID = css.TransactionID
						and cs.AgentCode = css.AgentCode
			inner join mstt_Agents ag on ag.Code = cs.BusinessCode
			inner join mstt_PolicyTransactions pt on pt.ID = cs.TransactionID
			inner join mstt_Policies p on p.POL_NUM = pt.PolicyID
			inner join msit_CommissionStatementPeriods VNBStart on convert(date,pt.CreateDateTime) between VNBStart.PeriodStartDate and VNBStart.PeriodEndDate
			inner join msit_Commissionstatementperiods csp on csp.month = cs.month
			inner join mstt_ProductHierarchy ph on ph.productcode = cs.productcode
			inner join mstt_Expectation e on e.ID = cs.ExpectationID
			left join dbo.owt_MortgageBrokerFees mbf on mbf.PendingPaymentID = cs.PendingPaymentID and mbf.AdviceFeeCharged = 'Yes'
			left join owt_SelectionControl SC
						on SC.Process = 'ElitePoints' 
						and SC.KeyType = 'NSCPotCode' 
						and cs.CreateDate between SC.EffectiveStartDate and SC.EffectiveEndDate
			left join mstt_Commissions BSCpot
						on BSCpot.TransactionID = cs.TransactionID 
						and BSCpot.Agent_Code = sc.KeyValue
						and BSCpot.CommissionType = 10
			left join owt_SelectionControl SFMPC						
						on SFMPC.Process = 'ElitePoints' 
						and SFMPC.KeyType = 'ServicingFeeMarginPotCode' 
						and cs.CreateDate between SFMPC.EffectiveStartDate and SFMPC.EffectiveEndDate
			left join mstt_Commissions SFMpot							
						on SFMpot.TransactionID = cs.TransactionID 
						and SFMpot.Agent_Code = SFMPC.KeyValue
						and SFMpot.CommissionType = 10	
			left join owt_SelectionControl pcc 
						on pcc.Process = 'ElitePoints'
						and pcc.KeyType = 'ProductCategoryCode'
						and pcc.KeyValue = cs.ProductCode	
						and cs.CreateDate between pcc.EffectiveStartDate and pcc.EffectiveEndDate
			left join owt_SelectionControl ogsdflt 
						on ogsdflt.Process = 'ElitePoints'
						and ogsdflt.KeyType = 'DefaultOngoingServicingRate'
						and ogsdflt.SelectionType = 'VNB'
						and ogsdflt.KeyValue = case when ph.RDRType = 'ONPLAT' then 'ONPLAT' else 'OFPLAT' end
						and cs.CreateDate between ogsdflt.EffectiveStartDate and ogsdflt.EffectiveEndDate
			left join mstt_CodeProductGroup pg on pg.ProductGroupCode = case when pcc.KeyValue2 = '1' then 2 else ph.ProductGroupCode end
			left join owt_EliteFactors Cfca on Cfca.FeeType = 'VNB' and Cfca.category = 'COB-FCA-RATE' and csp.year between Cfca.StartYear and Cfca.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors Crate on Crate.FeeType = 'VNB' and Crate.category = 'COB-RETENTION-RATE' and csp.year between Crate.StartYear and Crate.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors Mfca on Mfca.FeeType = 'VNB' and Mfca.category = 'MORT-FCA-RATE' and csp.year between Mfca.StartYear and Mfca.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors MRproc on MRproc.FeeType = 'VNB' and MRproc.category = 'MORT-RETENTION-RATE-PROC' and csp.year between MRproc.StartYear and MRproc.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors MRbkr on MRbkr.FeeType = 'VNB' and MRbkr.category = 'MORT-RETENTION-RATE-BROKER' and csp.year between MRbkr.StartYear and MRbkr.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors Pfca on Pfca.FeeType = 'VNB' and Pfca.category = 'PROT-FCA-RATE' and csp.year between Pfca.StartYear and Pfca.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors Prate on Prate.FeeType = 'VNB' and Prate.category = 'PROT-RETENTION-RATE' and csp.year between Prate.StartYear and Prate.EndYear 
	where	cs.ReportingClassCode = 1
	and		cs.CommissionType in (1,2,17)			--We want all the initial payment types (i.e. not trail (ongoing))
	and		ag.Manager2Code <> @OwlManager2Code		--Exclude Owl

	select @RowCount = @@rowcount
	set @ProcessMessage = '#owt_Recognition (ini ph2 - accr adj) = ' + convert(nvarchar(10), @RowCount)
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseLog, @ProcessMessage, null, @Module, @Client

	/****************************************************************************

		Initial Phase 3
		1) Add up the +ves and -ves prior to the NEW front loaded amount and
			net them off on the first +ve following the last -ve
		2) Now set all the +ves following the one updated in (1) to zero.
																
	****************************************************************************/

	update r
		set RecognitionType	= case when r.SourceID >= css.MinInitialAfterAdjPendingPaymentID 
								then 'VNB-INI-PHASE-3'
								else r.RecognitionType
							  end,
			Initial = case  when r.SourceID = css.MinInitialAfterAdjPendingPaymentID 
								then (((r.DA)*(r.AgentSplit/100) * (r.RetentionRate/100.0)) - ((r.DA)*(r.AgentSplit/100) * (r.FCARate/100))) - derived.SumInitial
							when r.SourceID > css.MinInitialAfterAdjPendingPaymentID 
								then 0.0
							else r.Initial
					  end,
			DateLastUpdated = @DateLastUpdated
	from	#msit_CommissionStatementSUMMARY css
			inner join #AG_owt_Recognition_SEPARATE_ONGOING r
						on r.TransactionID = css.TransactionID
						and r.SellerCode = css.AgentCode
			inner join (select	r.TransactionID, r.SellerCode, SUM(Initial) as SumInitial
						from	#msit_CommissionStatementSUMMARY s
								inner join #AG_owt_Recognition_SEPARATE_ONGOING r 
											on r.TransactionID = s.TransactionID
											and r.SellerCode = s.AgentCode
						where	r.SourceID <= s.MaxAdjPendingPaymentID
						group	by r.TransactionID, r.SellerCode
						) derived 
							on  derived.TransactionID = r.TransactionID
							and	derived.SellerCode = r.SellerCode 
	where	isnull(css.MaxInitialPendingPaymentID,0) > isnull(css.MaxAdjPendingPaymentID,0)-- An initial payment follows the clawback, so time to revert back to front loading

	select @RowCount = @@rowcount
	set @ProcessMessage = '#owt_Recognition (ini ph3 - accr adj) = ' + convert(nvarchar(10), @RowCount)
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseLog, @ProcessMessage, null, @Module, @Client

	/****************************************************************************

		Now do the ongoing.
		
		Build an ongoing summary row for each transaction (slice).
		
		Note we do not care about ongoing clawbacks and adjustments for VNB.
		We want VNB to be on the oldest positive payment on each slice for the
		policy (split by adviser if needed).
						
	****************************************************************************/

	select	cs.TransactionID,
			cs.AgentCode,
			c.AGENT_PERC as AgentSplit,
			Min(case when cs.CommissionType = 10 then cs.PendingPaymentID else null end) as MinOngoingPendingPaymentID,
			MAX(case when cs.CommissionType = 10 then cs.PendingPaymentID else null end) as MaxOngoingPendingPaymentID,
			MAX(case when cs.CommissionType in (16,19) then cs.PendingPaymentID else null end) as MaxOngoingAdjPendingPaymentID,
			null as MinOngoingAfterAdjPendingPaymentID
	into	#msit_CommissionStatementOGSSUMMARY
	from 	msit_CommissionStatement cs
			inner join mstt_Commissions c
						on c.TransactionID = cs.TransactionID
						and c.Agent_Code = cs.AgentCode
						and c.CommissionType = 1
			inner join mstt_Agents ag on ag.Code = cs.BusinessCode
			inner join mstt_PolicyTransactions pt on pt.ID = cs.TransactionID
			inner join mstt_Policies p on p.POL_NUM = pt.PolicyID
			inner join msit_CommissionStatementPeriods VNBStart on convert(date,pt.CreateDateTime) between VNBStart.PeriodStartDate and VNBStart.PeriodEndDate
			inner join msit_Commissionstatementperiods csp on csp.month = cs.month
			inner join mstt_ProductHierarchy ph on ph.productcode = cs.productcode
			inner join mstt_Expectation e on e.ID = cs.ExpectationID
			left join owt_SelectionControl pcc 
						on pcc.Process = 'ElitePoints'
						and pcc.KeyType = 'ProductCategoryCode'
						and pcc.KeyValue = cs.ProductCode	
						and cs.CreateDate between pcc.EffectiveStartDate and pcc.EffectiveEndDate
	where	cs.ReportingClassCode = 1
	and		cs.CommissionType in (10,16,19)					--Choose only where the ongoing payment is positive
	and		cs.CommFeeType = 'Ongoing'
	and		(ph.ProductCategoryCode = 1 or pcc.KeyValue2 = '1')
	and		ag.Manager2Code <> @OwlManager2Code		--Exclude Owl
	and		csp.Year >= 2017						--Ensure in-scope payments are consistent with VNB start
	and		VNBStart.Year >= 2017 
	and		abs(e.AMOUNT_REC) >= 0.01
	and		((cs.FrequencyCode = 6 and cs.Premium > 1.00)		--Frequency=6->Single
			or (cs.FrequencyCode <> 6 and cs.Premium > 0.01))	--Frequency<>6->Regular	
	group by	cs.TransactionID,
				cs.AgentCode,
				c.Agent_Perc

	select @RowCount = @@rowcount
	set @ProcessMessage = '#msit_CommissionStatementOGSSUMMARY (ogs txn) = ' + convert(nvarchar(10), @RowCount)
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseLog, @ProcessMessage, null, @Module, @Client

	--Get first ongoing payment after last clawback/adj
	update cso
		set MinOngoingAfterAdjPendingPaymentID = summ.MinPendingPaymentID 
	from  #msit_CommissionStatementOGSSUMMARY cso
			inner join  (
						select	csoinner.TransactionID, csoinner.AgentCode, min(cs.PendingPaymentID) as MinPendingPaymentID
						from	#msit_CommissionStatementOGSSUMMARY csoinner
								inner join msit_CommissionStatement cs
											on cs.TransactionID = csoinner.TransactionID
											and cs.AgentCode = csoinner.AgentCode
						where	cs.PendingPaymentID > csoinner.MaxOngoingAdjPendingPaymentID
						and		cs.CommissionType = 10
						group by csoinner.TransactionID, csoinner.AgentCode
						) summ on  summ.TransactionID = cso.TransactionID
							   and summ.AgentCode = cso.AgentCode

	select @RowCount = @@rowcount
	set @ProcessMessage = '#msit_CommissionStatementOGSSUMMARY (ogs latest +ve) = ' + convert(nvarchar(10), @RowCount)
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseLog, @ProcessMessage, null, @Module, @Client

	/****************************************************************************
		
		Using the OGS SUMMARY table, get all the individual payment records that
		will be carriers of VNB points as follows:
		
		SelectionSource 1 - The oldest +ve payment where no clawbacks or 
								adjustments occur for front loading

		SelectionSource 2 - All the +ve payments that will get a spread of the 
								per payment +ve points 		

		SelectionSource 3 - All the -ve payments that will get a spread of the 
								per payment -ve points
								 															
	****************************************************************************/
	
	--Front loaded -> Just the oldest +ve payment
	--Note: These transactions have NO clawbacks or adjustments
	select	1 as SelectionSource,
			cso.TransactionID,
			cso.AgentCode,
			cso.MinOngoingPendingPaymentID as PendingPaymentID,
			cso.AgentSplit,
			1 as SpreadNumber,
			1 as MaxSpread 
	into	#msit_CommissionStatementONGOING
	from	#msit_CommissionStatementOGSSUMMARY cso	
	where	cso.MaxOngoingAdjPendingPaymentID is null	--No clawbacks or adjustments - so front load
	and		cso.MinOngoingPendingPaymentID is not null	--At least one +ve payment on the transaction

	union	--Add in with dedupe
	
	--Per payment -> all +ve payments with max spread also used for divisor
	--Note: ALL these transactions have clawbacks or adjustments
	select	2 as SelectionSource,
			cso.TransactionID,
			cso.AgentCode,
			cs.PendingPaymentID,
			cso.AgentSplit,
			ROW_NUMBER() over (partition by cs.TransactionID, cs.AgentCode order by cs.TransactionID, cs.AgentCode, cs.PendingPaymentID) as SpreadNumber,
			12 as MaxSpread
	from	#msit_CommissionStatementOGSSUMMARY cso	
			inner join msit_CommissionStatement cs 
						on cs.TransactionID = cso.TransactionID
						and cs.AgentCode = cso.AgentCode
	where	cso.MaxOngoingAdjPendingPaymentID is not null	--Clawbacks or adjustments so per payment
	and		cs.CommissionType in (10)	

	union	--Add in with dedupe
	
	--Per payment -> all -ve payments - with max spread also used for divisor
	--Note: ALL these transactions have clawbacks or adjustments
	select	3 as SelectionSource,
			cso.TransactionID,
			cso.AgentCode,
			cs.PendingPaymentID,
			cso.AgentSplit,
			ROW_NUMBER() over (partition by cs.TransactionID, cs.AgentCode order by cs.TransactionID, cs.AgentCode, cs.PendingPaymentID) as SpreadNumber,
			12 as MaxSpread
	from	#msit_CommissionStatementOGSSUMMARY cso	
			inner join msit_CommissionStatement cs 
						on cs.TransactionID = cso.TransactionID
						and cs.AgentCode = cso.AgentCode
	where	cso.MaxOngoingAdjPendingPaymentID is not null	--Clawbacks or adjustments so per payment
	and		cs.CommissionType in (16,19)	

	select @RowCount = @@rowcount
	set @ProcessMessage = '#msit_CommissionStatementONGOING (ogs payments) = ' + convert(nvarchar(10), @RowCount)
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseLog, @ProcessMessage, null, @Module, @Client

	/****************************************************************************
		
		Insert the ongoing VNB results for those transactions 
																		
	****************************************************************************/

	insert into #AG_owt_Recognition_SEPARATE_ONGOING
	(
		SourceID,
		CaseID,
		TransactionID,
		Policy,
		ProductCode,
		BusinessCode,
		SellerCode,
		PointsTotal,
		BSC,
		MBF,
		Initial,
		OngoingTotal,
		OngoingYr01,
		OngoingYr02,
		OngoingYr03,
		OngoingYr04,
		OngoingYr05,
		OngoingYr06,
		OngoingYr07,
		OngoingYr08,
		OngoingYr09,
		OngoingYr10,
		FCARate,
		RetentionRate,
		RetentionRateBroker,
		OngoingServicingRate,
		OngoingServicingSource,
		DA,
		AmountReceived,
		Premium,
		AgentSplit,
		CommissionType,
		CommissionTypeDesc,
		PayBasisCode,
		PayBasisDesc,
		PaymentMatchedDate,
		Month,
		FrequencyCode,
		FrequencyDesc,
		ReassignedProductGroupCode,
		ReassignedProductGroupName,
		RecognitionType,
		CalculationType,
		Source,
		DateInserted,
		DateLastUpdated,
		CommissionYear
	)
	select	cs.PendingPaymentID as SourceID,
			cs.CaseID,
			cs.TransactionID,
			cs.ExtPolicyNumber as Policy,
			cs.ProductCode,
			cs.BusinessCode,
			cs.AgentCode as SellerCode,
			0.0 as PointsTotal,
			case
				when BSCpot.ID is not null then 
					--BSC takes the first 0.12 of the ongoing fee %. If the ongoing fee % is 0.12% or less, then 100% of the ongoing fee is allocated to BSC
					case when coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2)) - convert(decimal(8,4),sc.KeyValue2) >= 0.01
						then 
							case when cs.FrequencyCode = 2	--Monthly 
								then (cso.AgentSplit/100) * 12.0 * (isnull(cs.Premium/cso.MaxSpread,0)/2.0) * convert(decimal(8,4),sc.KeyValue3) * case when cs.CommissionType in (16,19) then -1 else 1 end
								else (cso.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(cs.Premium/cso.MaxSpread,0) * convert(decimal(8,4),sc.KeyValue3) * case when cs.CommissionType in (16,19) then -1 else 1 end
							end			
						else
							case when cs.FrequencyCode = 2	--Monthly 
								then (cso.AgentSplit/100) * 12.0 * (isnull(cs.Premium/cso.MaxSpread,0)/2.0) * coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2)) * case when cs.CommissionType in (16,19) then -1 else 1 end
								else (cso.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(cs.Premium/cso.MaxSpread,0) * (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))/100.0) * case when cs.CommissionType in (16,19) then -1 else 1 end
							end
					end
				else 0.0
			end as BSC,
			0.0 as MBF,
			0.0 as Initial,
			0.0 as OngoingTotal,
			case
				--WEALTH ONGOING CALCULATION START
				--When the adviser has changed, the AgentSplit can become zero in which case the ELITE points should be zero.
				when cso.AgentSplit = 0 then 0

				--SINGLE start
				--Calculate when BSC and ongoing applies (where ongoing rate is greater than BSC rate) 
				when cs.FrequencyCode = 6 and SFMpot.ID is not null and BSCpot.ID is not null and (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2)) - convert(decimal(8,4),sc.KeyValue2)) >= 0.01 then 
							--(AUM X BSC Rate)...
							((cso.AgentSplit/100) * (isnull(cs.Premium/cso.MaxSpread,0) * convert(decimal(8,4),sc.KeyValue3)) 
							--(AUM X OGS Rate X COB FCA Rate)...
							- ((cso.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(cs.Premium/cso.MaxSpread,0) * (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))/100.0) * Cfca.FACTOR)
							--(AUM X (OGS Rate - BSC Rate) X COB Retention Rate)...
							+ ((cso.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(cs.Premium/cso.MaxSpread,0) * ((coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))-convert(decimal(8,4),sc.KeyValue2))/100.0)) * Crate.FACTOR) 
							--Sign correctly for +ve or clawback payment
							* (case when cs.CommissionType in (16,19) then -1 else 1 end)
				--Calculate when BSC and ongoing applies (where ongoing rate less than BSC rate, then BSC gets all the ongoing available) 
				when cs.FrequencyCode = 6 and SFMpot.ID is not null and BSCpot.ID is not null then
							--(AUM X BSC Rate)...(in this scenario it's all of the OGS rate)
							((cso.AgentSplit/100) * (isnull(cs.Premium/cso.MaxSpread,0) * (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))/100.0)) 
							--(AUM X OGS Rate X COB FCA Rate)...
							- ((cso.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(cs.Premium/cso.MaxSpread,0) * (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))/100.0) * Cfca.FACTOR)
							--(AUM X (OGS Rate - BSC Rate) X COB Retention Rate)...
							+ (0.0)) --BSC got it all, so this part of the calculation is zero
							--Sign correctly for +ve or clawback payment
							* (case when cs.CommissionType in (16,19) then -1 else 1 end)
				--Calculate when no BSC applies and ongoing applies
				when cs.FrequencyCode = 6 and SFMpot.ID is not null and BSCpot.ID is null then 
							--(AUM X OGS Rate X COB Retention Rate)...
							(((cso.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(cs.Premium/cso.MaxSpread,0) * (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))/100.0) * Crate.FACTOR) 
							--(AUM X OGS Rate X COB FCA Rate)...
							- ((cso.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(cs.Premium/cso.MaxSpread,0) * (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))/100.0) * Cfca.FACTOR))
							--Sign correctly for +ve or clawback payment
							* (case when cs.CommissionType in (16,19) then -1 else 1 end)
				--SINGLE end
				
				--REGULAR start
				--Calculate when BSC and ongoing applies (where ongoing rate is greater than BSC rate) 
				when cs.FrequencyCode <> 6 and SFMpot.ID is not null and BSCpot.ID is not null and (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2)) - convert(decimal(8,4),sc.KeyValue2)) >= 0.01 then		--AG 04/06/2018 (1)
							--The non-BSC portion (Ave AUM X (OGS Rate - BSC Rate) X COB Retention Rate)...
							((((((cso.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(cs.Premium/cso.MaxSpread,0) * (case when cs.FrequencyCode = 2 then 12 else 1 end))/2.0) * (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2)) - convert(decimal(8,4),sc.KeyValue2))/100.0)) * Crate.FACTOR
							--The BSC portion (Ave AUM X BSC Rate)...
							+ case when cs.FrequencyCode = 2	--Monthly 
									then (cso.AgentSplit/100) * 12.0 * (isnull(cs.Premium/cso.MaxSpread,0)/2.0) * convert(decimal(8,4),sc.KeyValue3) 
									else (cso.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(cs.Premium/cso.MaxSpread,0) * convert(decimal(8,4),sc.KeyValue3) 
							  end
							--FCA Charge (Ave AUM X OGS Rate X FCA Rate)...
							- (case when cs.FrequencyCode = 2	--Monthly 
									then (cso.AgentSplit/100) * 12.0 * (isnull(cs.Premium/cso.MaxSpread,0)/2.0) 
									else (cso.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(cs.Premium/cso.MaxSpread,0) 
							   end * (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))/100.0) * Cfca.FACTOR))
							--Sign correctly for +ve or clawback payment
							* (case when cs.CommissionType in (16,19) then -1 else 1 end)   
				--Calculate when BSC and ongoing applies (where ongoing rate less than BSC rate, then BSC gets all the ongoing available) 
				when cs.FrequencyCode <> 6 and SFMpot.ID is not null and BSCpot.ID is not null then		--AG 04/06/2018 (1)
							--The non-BSC portion (Ave AUM X (OGS Rate - BSC Rate) X COB Retention Rate)...
							((0.0)	--BSC got it all, so this part of the calculation is zero
							--The BSC portion (Ave AUM X BSC Rate)...(in this scenario it's all of the OGS rate)
							+ case when cs.FrequencyCode = 2	--Monthly 
									then (cso.AgentSplit/100) * 12.0 * (isnull(cs.Premium/cso.MaxSpread,0)/2.0) * (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))/100.0) 
									else (cso.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(cs.Premium/cso.MaxSpread,0) * (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))/100.0) 
							  end
							--FCA Charge (Ave AUM X OGS Rate X FCA Rate)...
							- (case when cs.FrequencyCode = 2	--Monthly 
									then (cso.AgentSplit/100) * 12.0 * (isnull(cs.Premium/cso.MaxSpread,0)/2.0) 
									else (cso.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(cs.Premium/cso.MaxSpread,0) 
							   end * (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))/100.0) * Cfca.FACTOR))
							--Sign correctly for +ve or clawback payment
							* (case when cs.CommissionType in (16,19) then -1 else 1 end)   
				--Calculate when no BSC applies, but ongoing servicing applies
				when cs.FrequencyCode <> 6 and SFMpot.ID is not null and BSCpot.ID is null then		--AG 04/06/2018	(1)
							--(Ave AUM X OGS Rate X COB Retention Rate)...
							(((((cso.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(cs.Premium/cso.MaxSpread,0) * (case when cs.FrequencyCode = 2 then 12 else 1 end))/2.0) * (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))/100.0) * Crate.FACTOR) 
							--(Ave AUM X OGS Rate X COB FCA Rate)...
							- ((((cso.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(cs.Premium/cso.MaxSpread,0) * (case when cs.FrequencyCode = 2 then 12 else 1 end))/2.0) * (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))/100.0) * Cfca.FACTOR))
							--Sign correctly for +ve or clawback payment
							* (case when cs.CommissionType in (16,19) then -1 else 1 end)   
				--REGULAR end
				
				else 0.0

				--WEALTH ONGOING CALCULATION END
			end as OngoingYr01,
			0.0 as OngoingYr02,
			0.0 as OngoingYr03,
			0.0 as OngoingYr04,
			0.0 as OngoingYr05,
			0.0 as OngoingYr06,
			0.0 as OngoingYr07,
			0.0 as OngoingYr08,
			0.0 as OngoingYr09,
			0.0 as OngoingYr10,
			Cfca.FACTOR*100.0 as FCARate,
			Crate.FACTOR*100.0 as RetentionRate,
			0.0 as RetentionRateBroker,
			case when SFMpot.ID is not null
				then coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))
				else null
			end as OngoingServicingRate,
			case when SFMpot.ID is not null
				then case 
						when ogs.OngoingServiceFee is null and ogscli.OngoingServiceFee is null 
							then case
								when ogsdflt.KeyValue = 'ONPLAT' then 'Default - On Plat'
								else 'Default - Off Plat'
							end
						when ogs.OngoingServiceFee is not null then 'Client Product'
						when ogscli.OngoingServiceFee is not null then 'Client Only'
						else 'Unknown'
					 end
				else case when (ph.ProductCategoryCode = 1 or pcc.KeyValue2 = '1')
						then 'No OGS'					--WEALTH, but no OGS
						else null						--Not WEALTH, so OGS is n/a and is therefore null
					 end
			end as OngoingServicingSource,
			pt.CommInitialAmount as DA,
			e.AMOUNT_REC as AmountReceived,
			cs.Premium,
			cso.AgentSplit,								--Use the split from the IC record
			cs.CommissionType,
			left(cs.StandingOrderDesc,50) as CommissionTypeDesc,
			cs.PayBasisCode,
			cs.PayBasisDesc,
			cs.CreateDate as PaymentMatchedDate,
			cs.Month,
			cs.FrequencyCode,
			cs.FrequencyDesc,
			pg.ProductGroupCode as ReassignedProductGroupCode,	--Force the re-assigned products...		
			pg.ProductGroupName as ReassignedProductGroupName,	--...to be processed as investments		
			case cso.SelectionSource
				when 1 then 'VNB-OGS-PHASE-1' 
				when 2 then 'VNB-OGS-PHASE-2' 
				when 3 then 'VNB-OGS-PHASE-3' 
			end as RecognitionType,
			'WEALTH-ONGOING' as CalculationType,
			'Openwork 2006' as Source,
			@DateLastUpdated as DateInserted,
			@DateLastUpdated as DateLastUpdated,
			csp.year as CommissionYear
	from	#msit_CommissionStatementONGOING cso
			inner join msit_CommissionStatement cs on cs.PendingPaymentID = cso.PendingPaymentID
			inner join mstt_Agents ag on ag.Code = cs.BusinessCode
			inner join mstt_PolicyTransactions pt on pt.ID = cs.TransactionID
			inner join mstt_Policies p on p.POL_NUM = pt.PolicyID
			inner join msit_CommissionStatementPeriods VNBStart on convert(date,pt.CreateDateTime) between VNBStart.PeriodStartDate and VNBStart.PeriodEndDate
			inner join msit_Commissionstatementperiods csp on csp.month = cs.month
			inner join mstt_ProductHierarchy ph on ph.productcode = cs.productcode
			inner join mstt_Expectation e on e.ID = cs.ExpectationID
			left join dbo.owt_MortgageBrokerFees mbf on mbf.PendingPaymentID = cs.PendingPaymentID and mbf.AdviceFeeCharged = 'Yes'
			left join owt_SelectionControl SC
						on SC.Process = 'ElitePoints' 
						and SC.KeyType = 'NSCPotCode' 
						and cs.CreateDate between SC.EffectiveStartDate and SC.EffectiveEndDate
			left join mstt_Commissions BSCpot
						on BSCpot.TransactionID = cs.TransactionID 
						and BSCpot.Agent_Code = sc.KeyValue
						and BSCpot.CommissionType = 10
			left join owt_SelectionControl SFMPC						
						on SFMPC.Process = 'ElitePoints' 
						and SFMPC.KeyType = 'ServicingFeeMarginPotCode' 
						and cs.CreateDate between SFMPC.EffectiveStartDate and SFMPC.EffectiveEndDate
			left join mstt_Commissions SFMpot							
						on SFMpot.TransactionID = cs.TransactionID 
						and SFMpot.Agent_Code = SFMPC.KeyValue
						and SFMpot.CommissionType = 10	
			left join owt_SelectionControl pcc 
						on pcc.Process = 'ElitePoints'
						and pcc.KeyType = 'ProductCategoryCode'
						and pcc.KeyValue = cs.ProductCode	
						and cs.CreateDate between pcc.EffectiveStartDate and pcc.EffectiveEndDate
			left join owt_SelectionControl ogsdflt 
						on ogsdflt.Process = 'ElitePoints'
						and ogsdflt.KeyType = 'DefaultOngoingServicingRate'
						and ogsdflt.SelectionType = 'VNB'
						and ogsdflt.KeyValue = case when ph.RDRType = 'ONPLAT' then 'ONPLAT' else 'OFPLAT' end
						and cs.CreateDate between ogsdflt.EffectiveStartDate and ogsdflt.EffectiveEndDate
			left join mstt_CodeProductGroup pg on pg.ProductGroupCode = case when pcc.KeyValue2 = '1' then 2 else ph.ProductGroupCode end
			left join owt_EliteFactors Cfca on Cfca.FeeType = 'VNB' and Cfca.category = 'COB-FCA-RATE' and csp.year between Cfca.StartYear and Cfca.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors Crate on Crate.FeeType = 'VNB' and Crate.category = 'COB-RETENTION-RATE' and csp.year between Crate.StartYear and Crate.EndYear 
			left join #OGSLookUp ogs on ogs.CLIENT_NUM = cs.ClientID and ogs.ProductCode = cs.ProductCode
			left join #OGSLookUpClient ogscli on ogscli.CLIENT_NUM = cs.ClientID 	
	where	cso.SpreadNumber <= cso.MaxSpread	-- if per payment spreading, then limit the spread
	
	select @RowCount = @@rowcount
	set @ProcessMessage = '#owt_Recognition (ogs ph1 yr1) = ' + convert(nvarchar(10), @RowCount)
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseLog, @ProcessMessage, null, @Module, @Client

	/****************************************************************************

		Ongoing Phase 3
		1) Add up the +ves and -ves prior to the NEW front loaded amount and
			net them off on the first +ve following the last -ve
		2) Now set all the +ves following the one updated in (1) to zero.
																
	****************************************************************************/

	update r
		set RecognitionType	= case when r.SourceID >= csos.MinOngoingAfterAdjPendingPaymentID 
								then 'VNB-OGS-PHASE-4'
								else r.RecognitionType
							  end,
			OngoingYr01 = case  when r.SourceID = csos.MinOngoingAfterAdjPendingPaymentID 
									then (abs(r.OngoingYr01) * cso.MaxSpread) - derived.SumOngoingYr01
								when r.SourceID > csos.MinOngoingAfterAdjPendingPaymentID 
									then 0.0
								else r.OngoingYr01
						  end,
			DateLastUpdated = @DateLastUpdated
	from	#msit_CommissionStatementONGOING cso 
			inner join #AG_owt_Recognition_SEPARATE_ONGOING r on r.SourceID = cso.PendingPaymentID
			inner join #msit_CommissionStatementOGSSUMMARY csos
						on  csos.TransactionID = cso.TransactionID
						and csos.AgentCode = cso.AgentCode
			inner join (select	r.TransactionID, r.SellerCode, SUM(OngoingYr01) as SumOngoingYr01
						from	#msit_CommissionStatementOGSSUMMARY s
								inner join #AG_owt_Recognition_SEPARATE_ONGOING r 
											on r.TransactionID = s.TransactionID
											and r.SellerCode = s.AgentCode
						where	r.SourceID <= s.MaxOngoingAdjPendingPaymentID
						group	by r.TransactionID, r.SellerCode
						) derived 
							on  derived.TransactionID = r.TransactionID
							and	derived.SellerCode = r.SellerCode 
	where	isnull(csos.MaxOngoingPendingPaymentID,0) > isnull(csos.MaxOngoingAdjPendingPaymentID,0)	--An ongoing +ve payment follows the clawback, so time to revert back to front loading
	and		cso.SpreadNumber <= cso.MaxSpread	--Only payments within the spread period get a portion of the ongoing VNB
	and		cso.SelectionSource <> 1			--Just process the per-payment rows (not the front loaded rows)

	select @RowCount = @@rowcount
	set @ProcessMessage = '#owt_Recognition (ogs ph4 - accr adj) = ' + convert(nvarchar(10), @RowCount)
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseLog, @ProcessMessage, null, @Module, @Client

	/****************************************************************************

		Now calculate the ongoing spread as follows:
		1) Investments: Years 1 to 6
		2) Pensions:	Years 1 to 10
		Note that regular payments get an additional multiplier to uplift the 
		average AUM for each year.
																		
	****************************************************************************/

	update r
		set OngoingYr02 = case when r.FrequencyCode = 2									--Monthly
							then r.OngoingYr01 * YR02.Multiplier * YR02.Factor			--Regular
							else r.OngoingYr01 * YR02.Factor							--Single
						  end,
			OngoingYr03 = case when r.FrequencyCode = 2									--Monthly
							then r.OngoingYr01 * YR03.Multiplier * YR03.Factor			--Regular
							else r.OngoingYr01 * YR03.Factor							--Single
						  end,
			OngoingYr04 = case when r.FrequencyCode = 2									--Monthly
							then r.OngoingYr01 * YR04.Multiplier * YR04.Factor			--Regular
							else r.OngoingYr01 * YR04.Factor							--Single
						  end,
			OngoingYr05 = case when r.FrequencyCode = 2									--Monthly 
							then r.OngoingYr01 * YR05.Multiplier * YR05.Factor			--Regular
							else r.OngoingYr01 * YR05.Factor							--Single
						  end,
			OngoingYr06 = case when r.FrequencyCode = 2									--Monthly 
							then r.OngoingYr01 * YR06.Multiplier * YR06.Factor			--Regular
							else r.OngoingYr01 * YR06.Factor							--Single
						  end,
			OngoingYr07 = case when r.ReassignedProductGroupCode = 5					--Pensions	AG 05/06/2018
							then
								case when r.FrequencyCode = 2							--Monthly 
									then r.OngoingYr01 * YR07.Multiplier * YR07.Factor	--Regular
									else r.OngoingYr01 * YR07.Factor					--Single
								end
							else 
								0.0
						  end,
			OngoingYr08 = case when r.ReassignedProductGroupCode = 5					--Pensions	AG 05/06/2018 
							then
								case when r.FrequencyCode = 2							--Monthly 
									then r.OngoingYr01 * YR08.Multiplier * YR08.Factor	--Regular
									else r.OngoingYr01 * YR08.Factor					--Single
								end
							else 
								0.0
						  end,
			OngoingYr09 = case when r.ReassignedProductGroupCode = 5					--Pensions	AG 05/06/2018 
							then
								case when r.FrequencyCode = 2							--Monthly 
									then r.OngoingYr01 * YR09.Multiplier * YR09.Factor	--Regular
									else r.OngoingYr01 * YR09.Factor					--Single
								end
							else 
								0.0
						  end,
			OngoingYr10 = case when r.ReassignedProductGroupCode = 5					--Pensions	AG 05/06/2018
							then
								case when r.FrequencyCode = 2							--Monthly 
									then r.OngoingYr01 * YR10.Multiplier * YR10.Factor	--Regular
									else r.OngoingYr01 * YR10.Factor					--Single
								end
							else 
								0.0
						  end
	from	#AG_owt_Recognition_SEPARATE_ONGOING r
			left join owt_EliteFactors YR01 on YR01.FeeType = 'VNB' and YR01.Category = 'COB-ONGOING-DISCOUNT-YR01' and r.CommissionYear between YR01.StartYear and YR01.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors YR02 on YR02.FeeType = 'VNB' and YR02.Category = 'COB-ONGOING-DISCOUNT-YR02' and r.CommissionYear between YR02.StartYear and YR02.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors YR03 on YR03.FeeType = 'VNB' and YR03.Category = 'COB-ONGOING-DISCOUNT-YR03' and r.CommissionYear between YR03.StartYear and YR03.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors YR04 on YR04.FeeType = 'VNB' and YR04.Category = 'COB-ONGOING-DISCOUNT-YR04' and r.CommissionYear between YR04.StartYear and YR04.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors YR05 on YR05.FeeType = 'VNB' and YR05.Category = 'COB-ONGOING-DISCOUNT-YR05' and r.CommissionYear between YR05.StartYear and YR05.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors YR06 on YR06.FeeType = 'VNB' and YR06.Category = 'COB-ONGOING-DISCOUNT-YR06' and r.CommissionYear between YR06.StartYear and YR06.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors YR07 on YR07.FeeType = 'VNB' and YR07.Category = 'COB-ONGOING-DISCOUNT-YR07' and r.CommissionYear between YR07.StartYear and YR07.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors YR08 on YR08.FeeType = 'VNB' and YR08.Category = 'COB-ONGOING-DISCOUNT-YR08' and r.CommissionYear between YR08.StartYear and YR08.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors YR09 on YR09.FeeType = 'VNB' and YR09.Category = 'COB-ONGOING-DISCOUNT-YR09' and r.CommissionYear between YR09.StartYear and YR09.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors YR10 on YR10.FeeType = 'VNB' and YR10.Category = 'COB-ONGOING-DISCOUNT-YR10' and r.CommissionYear between YR10.StartYear and YR10.EndYear 
	where	r.CalculationType = 'WEALTH-ONGOING'

	select @RowCount = @@rowcount
	set @ProcessMessage = '#owt_Recognition (ongoing yr2-10) = ' + convert(nvarchar(10), @RowCount)
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseLog, @ProcessMessage, null, @Module, @Client
	
	/****************************************************************************

		Now add up all the numbers
																		
	****************************************************************************/
	
	update r
		set OngoingTotal	=	OngoingYr01 + OngoingYr02 + OngoingYr03 + OngoingYr04 + OngoingYr05 +
								OngoingYr06 + OngoingYr07 + OngoingYr08 + OngoingYr09 + OngoingYr10,
			PointsTotal		=	OngoingYr01 + OngoingYr02 + OngoingYr03 + OngoingYr04 + OngoingYr05 +
								OngoingYr06 + OngoingYr07 + OngoingYr08 + OngoingYr09 + OngoingYr10 +
								Initial + MBF	-- Note BSC is already included in the Ongoing, so don't include it in the Points Total.
	from	#AG_owt_Recognition_SEPARATE_ONGOING r

	select @RowCount = @@rowcount
	set @ProcessMessage = '#owt_Recognition (points total) = ' + convert(nvarchar(10), @RowCount)
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseLog, @ProcessMessage, null, @Module, @Client

	/****************************************************************************

		Merge the temporary table into the permanent table (IC data)
																		
	****************************************************************************/

	BEGIN TRANSACTION

	declare @SummaryOfChanges table (Change varchar(20))
	merge	dbo.AG_owt_Recognition_SEPARATE_ONGOING as trg
	using	#AG_owt_Recognition_SEPARATE_ONGOING as src
	on		trg.SourceID = src.SourceID
	and		trg.Source = src.Source
	when	matched 
	and		isnull(trg.PointsTotal,0) <> isnull(src.PointsTotal,0)
	then	update 
				set trg.CaseID = src.CaseID,
					trg.TransactionID = src.TransactionID,
					trg.Policy = src.Policy,
					trg.ProductCode = src.ProductCode,
					trg.BusinessCode = src.BusinessCode,
					trg.SellerCode = src.SellerCode,					--AG 13/06/2018
					trg.PointsTotal = src.PointsTotal,
					trg.BSC = src.BSC,
					trg.MBF = src.MBF,
					trg.Initial = src.Initial,
					trg.OngoingTotal = src.OngoingTotal,
					trg.OngoingYr01 = src.OngoingYr01,
					trg.OngoingYr02 = src.OngoingYr02,
					trg.OngoingYr03 = src.OngoingYr03,
					trg.OngoingYr04 = src.OngoingYr04,
					trg.OngoingYr05 = src.OngoingYr05,
					trg.OngoingYr06 = src.OngoingYr06,
					trg.OngoingYr07 = src.OngoingYr07,
					trg.OngoingYr08 = src.OngoingYr08,
					trg.OngoingYr09 = src.OngoingYr09,
					trg.OngoingYr10 = src.OngoingYr10,
					trg.FCARate = src.FCARate,
					trg.RetentionRate = src.RetentionRate,
					trg.RetentionRateBroker = src.RetentionRateBroker,
					trg.OngoingServicingRate = src.OngoingServicingRate,
					trg.OngoingServicingSource = src.OngoingServicingSource,
					trg.DA = src.DA,
					trg.AmountReceived = src.AmountReceived,
					trg.Premium = src.Premium,
					trg.AgentSplit = src.AgentSplit,
					trg.CommissionType = src.CommissionType,
					trg.CommissionTypeDesc = src.CommissionTypeDesc,
					trg.PayBasisCode = src.PayBasisCode,				--AG 13/06/2018
					trg.PayBasisDesc = src.PayBasisDesc,				--AG 13/06/2018
					trg.PaymentMatchedDate = src.PaymentMatchedDate,	--AG 13/06/2018	
					trg.Month = src.Month,
					trg.FrequencyCode = src.FrequencyCode,
					trg.FrequencyDesc = src.FrequencyDesc,
					trg.ReassignedProductGroupCode = src.ReassignedProductGroupCode,	--AG 05/06/2018
					trg.ReassignedProductGroupName = src.ReassignedProductGroupName,	--AG 05/06/2018
					trg.RecognitionType = src.RecognitionType,
					trg.CalculationType = src.CalculationType,
					trg.DateLastUpdated = @DateLastUpdated
	when	not matched by target 
	then	insert
			(
				SourceID,
				CaseID,
				TransactionID,
				Policy,
				ProductCode,
				BusinessCode,
				SellerCode,							--AG 13/06/2018
				PointsTotal,
				BSC,
				MBF,
				Initial,
				OngoingTotal,
				OngoingYr01,
				OngoingYr02,
				OngoingYr03,
				OngoingYr04,
				OngoingYr05,
				OngoingYr06,
				OngoingYr07,
				OngoingYr08,
				OngoingYr09,
				OngoingYr10,
				FCARate,
				RetentionRate,
				RetentionRateBroker,
				OngoingServicingRate,
				OngoingServicingSource,
				DA,
				AmountReceived,
				Premium,
				AgentSplit,
				CommissionType,
				CommissionTypeDesc,
				PayBasisCode,						--AG 13/06/2018
				PayBasisDesc,						--AG 13/06/2018
				PaymentMatchedDate,					--AG 13/06/2018
				Month,
				FrequencyCode,
				FrequencyDesc,
				ReassignedProductGroupCode,			--AG 05/06/2018
				ReassignedProductGroupName,			--AG 05/06/2018
				RecognitionType,
				CalculationType,
				Source,
				DateInserted,
				DateLastUpdated
			)		
			values
			(
				src.SourceID,
				src.CaseID,
				src.TransactionID,
				src.Policy,
				src.ProductCode,
				src.BusinessCode,
				src.SellerCode,						--AG 13/06/2018
				src.PointsTotal,
				src.BSC,
				src.MBF,
				src.Initial,
				src.OngoingTotal,
				src.OngoingYr01,
				src.OngoingYr02,
				src.OngoingYr03,
				src.OngoingYr04,
				src.OngoingYr05,
				src.OngoingYr06,
				src.OngoingYr07,
				src.OngoingYr08,
				src.OngoingYr09,
				src.OngoingYr10,
				src.FCARate,
				src.RetentionRate,
				src.RetentionRateBroker,
				src.OngoingServicingRate,
				src.OngoingServicingSource,
				src.DA,
				src.AmountReceived,
				src.Premium,
				src.AgentSplit,
				src.CommissionType,
				src.CommissionTypeDesc,
				src.PayBasisCode,					--AG 13/06/2018
				src.PayBasisDesc,					--AG 13/06/2018
				src.PaymentMatchedDate,				--AG 13/06/2018
				src.Month,
				src.FrequencyCode,
				src.FrequencyDesc,
				src.ReassignedProductGroupCode,		--AG 05/06/2018
				src.ReassignedProductGroupName,		--AG 05/06/2018
				src.RecognitionType,
				src.CalculationType,
				src.Source,
				src.DateInserted,
				src.DateLastUpdated)				--Merge statements must have a ;
	output $action into @SummaryOfChanges;
						
	/****************************************************************************

		Update OpenAccess
																		
	****************************************************************************/

/*	
	--Do not include MBF in the OpenAccess Commission Listing as it is on the MBF download
	--and we don't want MBF double counting.
	update	oal
		set VNB_Points = r.PointsTotal - r.MBF		--AG 04/06/2018 (2)
	from	msit_CommissionStatement cs
/*			inner join (select	distinct PKID
						from	owt_TransformationMovements tm 
						where	tm.DriverTableName = 'sa_swift_S_AGMFIL'
						and		tm.CommissionStatement = 'Y') tm on tm.PKID = cs.PendingPaymentID
*/			inner join msit_OpenworkAdviserListing oal on oal.SourceID = cs.ID and oal.Source = 'Openwork 2006'
			inner join owt_Recognition r 
						on r.SourceID = cs.PendingPaymentID
						and r.Source = oal.Source
	--where	isnull(oal.VNB_Points,0) <> isnull(r.PointsTotal,0)
	
	select @OALRowCount = @@rowcount
*/
	COMMIT TRANSACTION      
	
	select	@RowCount = COUNT(*)
	from	@SummaryOfChanges
	where	Change = 'INSERT'

	set @ProcessMessage = 'owt_Recognition (insert) = ' + convert(nvarchar(10), @RowCount)
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseLog, @ProcessMessage, null, @Module, @Client

	select	@RowCount = COUNT(*)
	from	@SummaryOfChanges
	where	Change = 'UPDATE'

	set @ProcessMessage = 'owt_Recognition (update) = ' + convert(nvarchar(10), @RowCount)
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseLog, @ProcessMessage, null, @Module, @Client
/*
	set @ProcessMessage = 'msit_OpenworkAdviserListing (update) = ' + convert(nvarchar(10), @OALRowCount)
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseLog, @ProcessMessage, null, @Module, @Client
*/
	/****************************************************************************

		T H E   E N D
																		
	****************************************************************************/
	
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseEnd, @ProcName, null, @Module, @Client

END TRY

BEGIN CATCH 

	select @ErrNum = ERROR_NUMBER(), @ErrMsg = ERROR_MESSAGE(), @ErrSev = ERROR_SEVERITY(), @ErrLine = ERROR_LINE(), @ErrState = XACT_STATE()
	set @ErrMsg = REPLACE(@ErrMsg, '.', '') + ' (error no: ' + CAST(@ErrNum AS VARCHAR(10)) + ') on line ' + CAST(@ErrLine AS VARCHAR(10))
	
	-- Test XACT_STATE for 0, 1, or -1.
    -- If 1, the transaction is committable.
    -- If -1, the transaction is uncommittable and should be rolled back.
    -- If 0, there is no transaction and a commit or rollback operation would generate an error.

	if @ErrState = -1			-- Transaction is uncommitable
		rollback transaction

	if @ErrState = 1			
		commit transaction

	-- Error message line 1
	set @ErrMsgBrief = left(@ErrMsg,100)
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseError, @ErrMsgBrief, null, @Module, @Client
	
	-- Error message line 2 - if any text exists
	set @ErrMsgBrief = substring(@ErrMsg,101,100)
	if len(@ErrMsgBrief) > 0
		exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseError, @ErrMsgBrief, null, @Module, @Client

	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseEnd, @ProcName, null, @Module, @Client

	RAISERROR(@ErrMsg, @ErrSev , 1)

END CATCH

/****************************************************************************

			E N D															

****************************************************************************/

return @ErrNum


GO
/****** Object:  StoredProcedure [dbo].[owp_RecognitionSwiftONGOING_Backup20180717AG]    Script Date: 7/3/2026 3:44:25 PM ******/
SET ANSI_NULLS ON
GO
SET QUOTED_IDENTIFIER ON
GO
/*********************************************************************************************************

Program:		owp_RecognitionSwift					
Author:			Alan Groves
Date created:	11/04/2018
											
Description:
===========

This proc populates the new recognition table called "owt_Recognition" with "Value of New Business"
(VNB) points.

This proc handles all of the swift data which includes:
WEALTH - COB business i.e. pensions and investments
MORTGAGES
PROTECTION

Note: There is a separate proc that calculates the GI VNB points from the Paymentshield data.

The approach of this proc is to use the incremental PendingPaymentIDs from the overnight batch
to calculate the VNB points in a temporary table.

The temporary table is then merged with the permanent table to make the calculated (or
re-calculated values) permanent.

Terms
-----
BSC			- Business Service Charge.
MBF			- Mortgage Broker Fee.
OGS			- Ongoing Servicing.
BSC Rate	- 0.12% at the time of writing (24/04/2018). This could be changed by the business, but
				would also require some DEV work in OWS.
DF			- Discount Factor.
DA			- Distribution Allowance (the total amount paid out by the provider to Openwork)
AUM			- Assets Under Management. Basically the amount invested or the premium on investment
				cases.
Average AUM - Average amount invested annually which is equivalent to 6 months' premium.

THE CALCULATIONS
================

There are two potential parts: initial + ongoing (if ongoing applies). If BSC (applies to ongoing 
only) and MBF (applies to mortgages only) apply, then these are also included:

MORTGAGE
--------
Part 1: MBF column = (Advice Fee Amount X Broker Retention Rate) - (Advice Fee Amount X Mort FCA Rate)
Part 2: Initial column = (Proc Fee Amount X Mortgage Retention Rate) - (Proc Fee X Mort FCA Rate) 
Mortgage Points Total = Initial + MBF

PROTECTION
----------
= (DA X Protection Retention Rate) - (DA X Protection FCA Rate) 
Protection Points Total = Initial

WEALTH (COB i.e. pensions and investments)
------
Part 1: Initial column = (DA X Wealth Retention Rate) - (DA X Wealth FCA Rate)

Part 2:

****XXXX****

NOTE: Where the BSC rate is greater than the ongoing rate, then BSC gets ALL of the AVAILABLE 
ongoing.

****XXXX****

REGULAR - BSC applies:
Year 1 column = BSC Points + Non-BSC Points - FCA Points
Non-BSC Points = Ave AUM X (OGS Rate - BSC Rate) X COB Retention Rate
BSC Points = Ave AUM X BSC Rate
FCA Points = Ave AUM X OGS Rate X COB FCA Rate

REGULAR - Non-BSC: 
Year 1 column = (Ave AUM X OGS Rate X COB Retention Rate) - (Ave AUM X OGS Rate X COB FCA Rate)

SINGLE - BSC applies:
Year 1 column = (AUM X BSC Rate) + (AUM X (OGS Rate - BSC Rate) X COB Retention Rate) - (AUM X OGS Rate X COB FCA Rate) 

SINGLE - Non-BSC:
Year 1 column = (AUM X OGS Rate X COB Retention Rate) - (AUM X OGS Rate X COB FCA Rate) 

Then years 2 to 10 are calculated by applying a discount factor
Year  2 = Year 1 X  3 X DF
Year  3 = Year 1 X  5 X DF
Year  4 = Year 1 X  7 X DF
Year  5 = Year 1 X  9 X DF
Year  6 = Year 1 X 11 X DF
Year  7 = Year 1 X 13 X DF
Year  8 = Year 1 X 15 X DF
Year  9 = Year 1 X 17 X DF
Year 10 = Year 1 X 19 X DF

Wealth Points Total =	OngoingYr01 + OngoingYr02 + OngoingYr03 + OngoingYr04 + OngoingYr05 +
						OngoingYr06 + OngoingYr07 + OngoingYr08 + OngoingYr09 + OngoingYr10 +
						Initial

GI
--
See stored proc "owp_RecognitionGIPaymentshield".
 
Notes:
-----

1)	There is a BSC column on table owt_Recognition. However, BSC is already included in the ongoing
	years 1 - 10, so the BSC column does not need to be added in. In fact you will double count if 
	you attempt to do anything with it other than display it.

2)	Occasionally an investment case may receive two or more cheques which
	then go through Swift as two or more SINGLE investments on the SAME
	slice. Although the INITIAL VNB calculation will pro-rata correctly
	because it is based on the amount received, this scenario will cause
	ongoing VNB to be calculated on each of the payment records and so will 
	double count (or worse if there are more than two cheques received).
	Since de-coupling IC from ongoing i.e. they now have separate rows on
	table owt_Recognition, the issue of multiple cheques should no longer
	cause ongoing double counting.


This proc is called as follows:
	declare @rc int
	exec @rc = dbo.owp_RecognitionSwift 'Openwork', 'Recognition'
	select @rc

					
AMENDMENT HISTORY				
=================								

Date		Author		Description
----		------		-----------
26/04/2018	A Groves	Only include rows in the OGS lookups where the OngoingServiceFee > 0.0.
						Negative OGS rates are bad data and at the time of writing, there are
						39 of these.
27/04/2018	A Groves	Additional calculation and condition to handle the scenario where BSC applies
						but the OGS Rate is less than the BSC rate. Previously, this caused the
						total ongoing to be zero. However, there are two components to ongoing VNB 
						points, the BSC share and the non-BSC share. So the BSC share (which takes 
						100% when the OGS rate is less than 0.12%) should still yield ongoing points.
27/04/2018	A Groves	Single ongoing Yr01 corrected by applying outer brackets before signing the result.
03/05/2018	A Groves	Added update of column "msit_OpenworkAdviserListing.VNB_Points".
18/05/2018	A Groves	Changed mortgage calculation to use e.AMOUNT_REC instead of pt.CommInitialAmount
						as Marcus Cossey wanted the actual amount received to be used for the DA.
04/06/2018	A Groves	1) In the REGULAR section of column "OngoingYr01", the condition for cs.FrequencyCode <> 6
							was added to ensure the code differentiates to the SINGLE section.
						2) Exclude MBF from the OpenAccess table (msit_OpenworkAdviserListing) as this
							is shown on the MBF download and would otherwise incur MBF double counting.
05/06/2018	A Groves	1) Marcus Cossey advised that investments should get ongoing for years 1 to 6 and
							pensions for years 1 to 10. Previously, both lines of business got years 1 to 10.
						2) Marcus Cossey asked for split payments (i.e. where multiple cheques are processed
							for a SINGLE investment) to only claculate ongoing VNB on the oldest payment. 
11/06/2018	A Groves	1) PSD processed a protection clawback statement as fee type initial. These clawbacks
							all generated +ve instead of -ve VNB points. A tweak was added to ensure that the 
							absolute value of AMOUNT_REC is used to ensure the VNB is correctly signed. 
						2) Another unknown business rule has surfaced: Previously, only initial, clawbacks and
							adjustments on slices created new from 2017 were included. This rule only applies
							to initial. Clawbacks and adjustments can belong to a slice created at any point
							in the past. However, note that the payment (irrespective of whether it is +ve or 
							-ve), must not pre-date 2017.
13/06/2018	A Groves	Marcus asked for SellerCode and PaymentMatchedDate to be added so he need only use 
							the one table for both the adviser and enterprise leagues. PayBasisCode and 
							PayBasisDesc were also added at the same time as these are used in the calculations.
06/07/2018	A Groves	Replaced the OGS Rate lookup on the fly to using table dbo.owt_OngoingRate. This was 
							done to ensure the rate used at any point in time stays the same, so the onging VNB
							will always give the same result each time the calculation runs.
*************************************************************************************************************/

CREATE PROCEDURE [dbo].[owp_RecognitionSwiftONGOING_Backup20180717AG]
	@Client		varchar(50),
	@Module		Varchar(50)

AS

set nocount on

declare		@PhaseStart				varchar(50),
			@PhaseEnd				varchar(50),
			@PhaseError				varchar(50),
			@PhaseLog				varchar(50),
			@ProcName				varchar(100),
			@ProcessMessage			varchar(100),
			@RowCount				int,
			@OALRowCount			int,
			@ErrMsg					nvarchar(4000),
			@ErrMsgBrief			nvarchar(100),
			@ErrNum					int,
			@ErrSev					int,
			@ErrLine				int,
			@ErrState				int,
			@DateLastUpdated		datetime,
			@OwlManager2Code		nvarchar(10)
			
/****************************************************************************

	Set initial parameters																
																		
****************************************************************************/

set @ProcName			= object_name(@@procid)
set @PhaseStart			= 'START'
set @PhaseEnd			= 'END'
set @PhaseError			= 'ERROR'
set @PhaseLog			= 'LOG'
set @ErrNum				= 0	
set @DateLastUpdated	= getdate()

set @OwlManager2Code = (select cde.Code from msit_MIWarehouseCodesAndDescriptions cde
			where cde.ColumnName = 'Manager2Code' and cde.Description = 'Owl Financial')

-- We want this logging irrespective of whether or not there is a rollback
exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseStart, @ProcName, null, @Module, @Client

/****************************************************************************

	Populate the table																
																		
****************************************************************************/

SET XACT_ABORT ON	-- Needed if XACT_STATE() function is used.

BEGIN TRY

	/****************************************************************************

		Calculate VNB and populate the temporary table with the results
		
		Note that there are oddities like LV protection payments which always
		come in pairs with one large and one much smaller amount (e.g. TransactionID 
		= 6684787.) The system treats both payments in the pair as first payments 
		and the (projected) DA associated with both is the same (because it's on 
		the policy transaction). 
		
		There is also a requirement to front-load VNB points on accrual and level
		payments. This means calculate the VNB for the full amount of the DA and 
		put it on the first payment record and then on all subsequent accrual and 
		level payments, set the VNB to zero.
		
		Thus two different sources of DA are used depending on whether we need the
		full DA amount for accruals and level or the actual amount received for all
		other scenarios including the LV split payment scenario. The two sources are:
		
		mstt_PolicyTransactions.CommInitialAmount - Full (projected) DA amount
		
		mstt_Expectation.AMOUNT_REC - The DA actually received. This handles the
										LV scenario whereby the AMOUNT_REC is 
										proportioned across the two payments received.   
																		
	****************************************************************************/

	select	top 0 
			*, 
			convert(int,NULL) as CommissionYear
	into	#AG_owt_Recognition_SEPARATE_ONGOING
	from	AG_owt_Recognition_SEPARATE_ONGOING

	/****************************************************************************

		Phase 1 - Process all but regular accrual cases with clawbacks/adjustments
		Accruals are front loaded unless their latest payment is a clawback/adjudtment
		in which case they accrue VNB points on a per payment basis and so these
		are dealt with in Phases 2 and 3.
																		
	****************************************************************************/

	insert into #AG_owt_Recognition_SEPARATE_ONGOING
	(
		SourceID,
		CaseID,
		TransactionID,
		Policy,
		ProductCode,
		BusinessCode,
		SellerCode,						--AG 13/06/2018
		PointsTotal,
		BSC,
		MBF,
		Initial,
		OngoingTotal,
		OngoingYr01,
		OngoingYr02,
		OngoingYr03,
		OngoingYr04,
		OngoingYr05,
		OngoingYr06,
		OngoingYr07,
		OngoingYr08,
		OngoingYr09,
		OngoingYr10,
		FCARate,
		RetentionRate,
		RetentionRateBroker,
		OngoingServicingRate,
		OngoingServicingSource,
		DA,
		AmountReceived,
		Premium,
		AgentSplit,
		CommissionType,
		CommissionTypeDesc,
		PayBasisCode,					--AG 13/06/2018
		PayBasisDesc,					--AG 13/06/2018
		PaymentMatchedDate,				--AG 13/06/2018
		Month,
		FrequencyCode,
		FrequencyDesc,
		ReassignedProductGroupCode,		--AG 05/06/2018
		ReassignedProductGroupName,		--AG 05/06/2018
		RecognitionType,
		CalculationType,
		Source,
		DateInserted,
		DateLastUpdated,
		CommissionYear
	)
	select	cs.PendingPaymentID as SourceID,
			cs.CaseID,
			cs.TransactionID,
			cs.ExtPolicyNumber as Policy,
			cs.ProductCode,
			cs.BusinessCode,
			cs.AgentCode as SellerCode,				--AG 13/06/2018
			0.0 as PointsTotal,
			0.0 as BSC,
			case 
				when mbf.MortgageFeeID is not null and cs.INIssued <> 0 then (((mbf.AdviceFeeAmount)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * MRbkr.FACTOR) - ((mbf.AdviceFeeAmount)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * Mfca.FACTOR)) --Note that mbf.AdviceFeeAmount is signed correctly - so no coding for signing is needed here
				else 0.0
			end as MBF,
			case 
				--When the adviser has changed, the AgentSplit can become zero in which case the ELITE points should be zero.
				when cs.AgentSplit = 0 then 0
				
				--WEALTH CALCULATION START
				--Indemnity payments or SINGLEs or IC Clawbacks or IC adjustments Start
				when (ph.ProductCategoryCode = 1 or pcc.KeyValue2 = '1') and (cs.FrequencyCode = 6 or cs.PayBasisCode in ('T') or cs.CommissionType in (2,17)) and cs.commissiontype in (1,2,17) and cs.INIssued <> 0 then (((e.AMOUNT_REC)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * Crate.FACTOR) - ((e.AMOUNT_REC)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * Cfca.FACTOR)) * case when cs.INIssued < 0 then -1 else 1 end
				--Indemnity payments or SINGLEs or IC Clawbacks or IC adjustments End
				--Accruals & Level Start
				when (ph.ProductCategoryCode = 1 or pcc.KeyValue2 = '1') and cs.INIssued <> 0 then (((pt.CommInitialAmount)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * Crate.FACTOR) - ((pt.CommInitialAmount)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * Cfca.FACTOR)) * case when cs.INIssued < 0 then -1 else 1 end
				--Accruals & Level End
				--WEALTH CALCULATION END
				
				--MORTGAGE CALCULATION START
				--Note: The MBF component has its own table column
				--Only 1 payment for mortgages
				when ph.ProductGroupCode = 3 and cs.INIssued <> 0 then (((e.AMOUNT_REC)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * MRproc.FACTOR) - ((e.AMOUNT_REC)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * Mfca.FACTOR)) * case when cs.INIssued < 0 then -1 else 1 end	--AG 18/05/2018
				--MORTGAGE CALCULATION END
				
				--PROTECTION CALCULATION START
				--Indemnity payments or SINGLEs or IC Clawbacks or IC adjustments Start
				when ph.ProductGroupCode = 6 and (cs.FrequencyCode = 6 or cs.PayBasisCode in ('T') or cs.CommissionType in (2,17)) and cs.commissiontype in (1,2,17) and cs.INIssued <> 0 then ((abs(e.AMOUNT_REC)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * Prate.FACTOR) - (abs(e.AMOUNT_REC)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * Pfca.FACTOR)) * case when cs.INIssued < 0 then -1 else 1 end	--AG 11/06/2018 (1)
				--Indemnity payments or SINGLEs or IC Clawbacks or IC adjustments End
				--Accruals & Level Start
				when ph.ProductGroupCode = 6 and cs.INIssued <> 0 then (((pt.CommInitialAmount)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * Prate.FACTOR) - ((pt.CommInitialAmount)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * Pfca.FACTOR)) * case when cs.INIssued < 0 then -1 else 1 end
				--Accruals & Level End
				--PROTECTION CALCULATION END

				else 0.0

			end as Initial,
			0.0 as OngoingTotal,
			0.0 as OngoingYr01,
			0.0 as OngoingYr02,
			0.0 as OngoingYr03,
			0.0 as OngoingYr04,
			0.0 as OngoingYr05,
			0.0 as OngoingYr06,
			0.0 as OngoingYr07,
			0.0 as OngoingYr08,
			0.0 as OngoingYr09,
			0.0 as OngoingYr10,
			case 
				when (ph.ProductCategoryCode = 1 or pcc.KeyValue2 = '1') then Cfca.FACTOR*100.0		--COB
				when ph.ProductGroupCode = 3 then Mfca.FACTOR*100.0		--MORT
				when ph.ProductGroupCode = 6 then Pfca.FACTOR*100.0		--PROT
				else 0.0
			end as FCARate,
			case 
				when (ph.ProductCategoryCode = 1 or pcc.KeyValue2 = '1') then Crate.FACTOR*100.0	--COB
				when ph.ProductGroupCode = 3 then MRproc.FACTOR*100.0	--MORT
				when ph.ProductGroupCode = 6 then Prate.FACTOR*100.0	--PROT
				else 0.0
			end as RetentionRate,
			case 
				when mbf.MortgageFeeID is not null then  MRbkr.FACTOR*100.0	
				else 0.0
			end as RetentionRateBroker,
			null as OngoingServicingRate,
			null as OngoingServicingSource,
			pt.CommInitialAmount as DA,
			e.AMOUNT_REC as AmountReceived,
			cs.Premium,
			cs.AgentSplit,
			cs.CommissionType,
			left(cs.StandingOrderDesc,50) as CommissionTypeDesc,
			cs.PayBasisCode,							--AG 13/06/2018
			cs.PayBasisDesc,							--AG 13/06/2018
			cs.CreateDate as PaymentMatchedDate,		--AG 13/06/2018
			cs.Month,
			cs.FrequencyCode,
			cs.FrequencyDesc,
			pg.ProductGroupCode as ReassignedProductGroupCode,	--Force the re-assigned products...		AG 05/06/2018
			pg.ProductGroupName as ReassignedProductGroupName,	--...to be processed as investments		AG 05/06/2018
			'VNB-INI-PHASE-1' as RecognitionType,
			case 
				when (ph.ProductCategoryCode = 1 or pcc.KeyValue2 = '1') then 'WEALTH-INITIAL'
				when ph.ProductGroupCode = 3 then 'MORTGAGE'
				when ph.ProductGroupCode = 6 then 'PROTECTION'
				else null
			end as CalculationType,
			'Openwork 2006' as Source,
			@DateLastUpdated as DateInserted,
			@DateLastUpdated as DateLastUpdated,
			csp.year as CommissionYear
	--select count(*)
	from	msit_CommissionStatement cs
/*			inner join (select	distinct PKID
						from	owt_TransformationMovements tm 
						where	tm.DriverTableName = 'sa_swift_S_AGMFIL'
						and		tm.CommissionStatement = 'Y') tm on tm.PKID = cs.PendingPaymentID
*/			inner join mstt_Agents ag on ag.Code = cs.BusinessCode
			inner join mstt_PolicyTransactions pt on pt.ID = cs.TransactionID
			inner join mstt_Policies p on p.POL_NUM = pt.PolicyID
			inner join msit_CommissionStatementPeriods VNBStart on convert(date,pt.CreateDateTime) between VNBStart.PeriodStartDate and VNBStart.PeriodEndDate
			inner join msit_Commissionstatementperiods csp on csp.month = cs.month
			inner join mstt_ProductHierarchy ph on ph.productcode = cs.productcode
			inner join mstt_Expectation e on e.ID = cs.ExpectationID
			left join dbo.owt_MortgageBrokerFees mbf on mbf.PendingPaymentID = cs.PendingPaymentID and mbf.AdviceFeeCharged = 'Yes'
			left join owt_SelectionControl SC
						on SC.Process = 'ElitePoints' 
						and SC.KeyType = 'NSCPotCode' 
						and cs.CreateDate between SC.EffectiveStartDate and SC.EffectiveEndDate
			left join mstt_Commissions BSCpot
						on BSCpot.TransactionID = cs.TransactionID 
						and BSCpot.Agent_Code = sc.KeyValue
						and BSCpot.CommissionType = 10
			left join owt_SelectionControl SFMPC						
						on SFMPC.Process = 'ElitePoints' 
						and SFMPC.KeyType = 'ServicingFeeMarginPotCode' 
						and cs.CreateDate between SFMPC.EffectiveStartDate and SFMPC.EffectiveEndDate
			left join mstt_Commissions SFMpot							
						on SFMpot.TransactionID = cs.TransactionID 
						and SFMpot.Agent_Code = SFMPC.KeyValue
						and SFMpot.CommissionType = 10	
			left join owt_SelectionControl pcc 
						on pcc.Process = 'ElitePoints'
						and pcc.KeyType = 'ProductCategoryCode'
						and pcc.KeyValue = cs.ProductCode	
						and cs.CreateDate between pcc.EffectiveStartDate and pcc.EffectiveEndDate
			left join owt_SelectionControl ogsdflt 
						on ogsdflt.Process = 'ElitePoints'
						and ogsdflt.KeyType = 'DefaultOngoingServicingRate'
						and ogsdflt.SelectionType = 'VNB'
						and ogsdflt.KeyValue = case when ph.RDRType = 'ONPLAT' then 'ONPLAT' else 'OFPLAT' end
						and cs.CreateDate between ogsdflt.EffectiveStartDate and ogsdflt.EffectiveEndDate
			left join mstt_CodeProductGroup pg on pg.ProductGroupCode = case when pcc.KeyValue2 = '1' then 2 else ph.ProductGroupCode end
			left join owt_EliteFactors Cfca on Cfca.FeeType = 'VNB' and Cfca.category = 'COB-FCA-RATE' and csp.year between Cfca.StartYear and Cfca.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors Crate on Crate.FeeType = 'VNB' and Crate.category = 'COB-RETENTION-RATE' and csp.year between Crate.StartYear and Crate.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors Mfca on Mfca.FeeType = 'VNB' and Mfca.category = 'MORT-FCA-RATE' and csp.year between Mfca.StartYear and Mfca.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors MRproc on MRproc.FeeType = 'VNB' and MRproc.category = 'MORT-RETENTION-RATE-PROC' and csp.year between MRproc.StartYear and MRproc.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors MRbkr on MRbkr.FeeType = 'VNB' and MRbkr.category = 'MORT-RETENTION-RATE-BROKER' and csp.year between MRbkr.StartYear and MRbkr.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors Pfca on Pfca.FeeType = 'VNB' and Pfca.category = 'PROT-FCA-RATE' and csp.year between Pfca.StartYear and Pfca.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors Prate on Prate.FeeType = 'VNB' and Prate.category = 'PROT-RETENTION-RATE' and csp.year between Prate.StartYear and Prate.EndYear 
			left join msit_CommissionStatement csadj 
						on csadj.TransactionID = cs.TransactionID 
						and csadj.AgentCode = cs.AgentCode 
						and csadj.CommissionType in (2,17)
						and	csadj.PayBasisCode in ('F')				--Accrual
						and	csadj.FrequencyCode <> 6				--Regular 
	where	cs.ReportingClassCode = 1
	and		ag.Manager2Code <> @OwlManager2Code		--Exclude Owl
	and		cs.INIssued <> 0
	and		csp.Year >= 2017						--Ensure in-scope payments are consistent with VNB start
	and		VNBStart.Year >= 2017
	and		cs.CommissionType in (1,2,17)
	and		abs(e.AMOUNT_REC) >= 0.01	
	--and		((VNBStart.Year >= 2017 and cs.CommissionType = 1 and e.AMOUNT_REC >= 0.01)		--VNB to start from new slices in 2017 for +ve payments but...			AG 11/06/2018 (2)
	--		or (cs.CommissionType in (2,17) or e.AMOUNT_REC <= -0.01))						--...for -ve payments, the slice can start from any date in the past	AG 11/06/2018 (2)
	and		csadj.ID is null						--Deal with accrual regular clawbacks/adjustments later

	select @RowCount = @@rowcount
	set @ProcessMessage = '#owt_Recognition (ini ph1 - no accr adj) = ' + convert(nvarchar(10), @RowCount)
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseLog, @ProcessMessage, null, @Module, @Client

	/****************************************************************************

		Now deal with accrual clawbacks and adjustments
																		
	****************************************************************************/

	--drop table #msit_CommissionStatementSUMMARY

	--Find transactions with clawbacks/adj on them
	select	cs.TransactionID,
			cs.AgentCode,
			Min(case when cs.CommissionType = 1 then cs.PendingPaymentID else null end) as MinInitialPendingPaymentID,
			MAX(case when cs.CommissionType = 1 then cs.PendingPaymentID else null end) as MaxInitialPendingPaymentID,
			MAX(case when cs.CommissionType in (2,17) then cs.PendingPaymentID else null end) as MaxAdjPendingPaymentID,
			null as MinInitialAfterAdjPendingPaymentID
	into	#msit_CommissionStatementSUMMARY
	from	msit_CommissionStatement cs
			inner join mstt_Agents ag on ag.Code = cs.BusinessCode
			inner join mstt_PolicyTransactions pt on pt.ID = cs.TransactionID
			inner join mstt_Policies p on p.POL_NUM = pt.PolicyID
			inner join msit_CommissionStatementPeriods VNBStart on convert(date,pt.CreateDateTime) between VNBStart.PeriodStartDate and VNBStart.PeriodEndDate
			inner join msit_Commissionstatementperiods csp on csp.month = cs.month
			inner join mstt_Expectation e on e.ID = cs.ExpectationID
			left join msit_CommissionStatement csadj 
						on csadj.TransactionID = cs.TransactionID 
						and csadj.AgentCode = cs.AgentCode 
						and csadj.CommissionType in (2,17)
						and	csadj.PayBasisCode in ('F')				--Accrual
						and	csadj.FrequencyCode <> 6				--Regular 
	where	cs.ReportingClassCode = 1
	and		cs.CommissionType in (1,2,17)			--We want all the initial payment types (i.e. not trail (ongoing))
	and		ag.Manager2Code <> @OwlManager2Code		--Exclude Owl
	and		csp.Year >= 2017						--Ensure in-scope payments are consistent with VNB start
	and		VNBStart.Year >= 2017 
	and		abs(e.AMOUNT_REC) >= 0.01	
	and		csadj.ID is not null					--select regular accrual transactions with clawbacks/adjustments
	--and cs.TransactionID in (5613333,6296827)
	group by	cs.TransactionID,
				cs.AgentCode

	select @RowCount = @@rowcount
	set @ProcessMessage = '#msit_CommissionStatementSUMMARY (accr adj txns) = ' + convert(nvarchar(10), @RowCount)
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseLog, @ProcessMessage, null, @Module, @Client

	--Get first initial payment after last clawback/adj
	update css
		set MinInitialAfterAdjPendingPaymentID = summ.MinPendingPaymentID 
	from  #msit_CommissionStatementSUMMARY css
			inner join  (
						select cssinner.TransactionID, cssinner.AgentCode, min(cs.PendingPaymentID) as MinPendingPaymentID
						from #msit_CommissionStatementSUMMARY cssinner
								inner join msit_CommissionStatement cs
											on cs.TransactionID = cssinner.TransactionID
											and cs.AgentCode = cssinner.AgentCode
						where cs.PendingPaymentID > cssinner.MaxAdjPendingPaymentID
						group by cssinner.TransactionID, cssinner.AgentCode
						) summ on  summ.TransactionID = css.TransactionID
							   and summ.AgentCode = css.AgentCode

	select @RowCount = @@rowcount
	set @ProcessMessage = '#msit_CommissionStatementSUMMARY (1st IC after adj) = ' + convert(nvarchar(10), @RowCount)
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseLog, @ProcessMessage, null, @Module, @Client

	/****************************************************************************

		Phase 2 - This phase deals with regular accrual cases where there is at 
		least one clawback/adjustment. In this scenario the VNB is changed from 
		front loaded to a per payment basis.
																		
	****************************************************************************/

	insert into #AG_owt_Recognition_SEPARATE_ONGOING
	(
		SourceID,
		CaseID,
		TransactionID,
		Policy,
		ProductCode,
		BusinessCode,
		SellerCode,						
		PointsTotal,
		BSC,
		MBF,
		Initial,
		OngoingTotal,
		OngoingYr01,
		OngoingYr02,
		OngoingYr03,
		OngoingYr04,
		OngoingYr05,
		OngoingYr06,
		OngoingYr07,
		OngoingYr08,
		OngoingYr09,
		OngoingYr10,
		FCARate,
		RetentionRate,
		RetentionRateBroker,
		OngoingServicingRate,
		OngoingServicingSource,
		DA,
		AmountReceived,
		Premium,
		AgentSplit,
		CommissionType,
		CommissionTypeDesc,
		PayBasisCode,					
		PayBasisDesc,					
		PaymentMatchedDate,				
		Month,
		FrequencyCode,
		FrequencyDesc,
		ReassignedProductGroupCode,		
		ReassignedProductGroupName,		
		RecognitionType,
		CalculationType,
		Source,
		DateInserted,
		DateLastUpdated,
		CommissionYear
	)
	select	cs.PendingPaymentID as SourceID,
			cs.CaseID,
			cs.TransactionID,
			cs.ExtPolicyNumber as Policy,
			cs.ProductCode,
			cs.BusinessCode,
			cs.AgentCode as SellerCode,				
			0.0 as PointsTotal,
			0.0 as BSC,
			case 
				when mbf.MortgageFeeID is not null and cs.INIssued <> 0 then (((mbf.AdviceFeeAmount)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * MRbkr.FACTOR) - ((mbf.AdviceFeeAmount)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * Mfca.FACTOR)) --Note that mbf.AdviceFeeAmount is signed correctly - so no coding for signing is needed here
				else 0.0
			end as MBF,
			case 
				--When the adviser has changed, the AgentSplit can become zero in which case the ELITE points should be zero.
				when cs.AgentSplit = 0 then 0
				
				--WEALTH CALCULATION START
				--Indemnity payments or SINGLEs or IC Clawbacks or IC adjustments Start
				--THIS SCENARIO DOESN'T OCCUR IN PHASE 2
				--Indemnity payments or SINGLEs or IC Clawbacks or IC adjustments End
				--Accruals & Level Start
				when (ph.ProductCategoryCode = 1 or pcc.KeyValue2 = '1') then (((e.AMOUNT_REC)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * Crate.FACTOR) - ((e.AMOUNT_REC)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * Cfca.FACTOR)) * case when cs.CommissionType in (2,17) then -1 else 1 end
				--Accruals & Level End
				--WEALTH CALCULATION END
				
				--MORTGAGE CALCULATION START
				--Note: The MBF component has its own table column
				--Only 1 payment for mortgages
				when ph.ProductGroupCode = 3 then (((e.AMOUNT_REC)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * MRproc.FACTOR) - ((e.AMOUNT_REC)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * Mfca.FACTOR)) * case when cs.CommissionType in (2,17) then -1 else 1 end	
				--MORTGAGE CALCULATION END
				
				--PROTECTION CALCULATION START
				--Indemnity payments or SINGLEs or IC Clawbacks or IC adjustments Start
				--THIS SCENARIO DOESN'T OCCUR IN PHASE 2
				--Indemnity payments or SINGLEs or IC Clawbacks or IC adjustments End
				--Accruals & Level Start
				when ph.ProductGroupCode = 6 then (((e.AMOUNT_REC)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * Prate.FACTOR) - ((e.AMOUNT_REC)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * Pfca.FACTOR)) * case when cs.CommissionType in (2,17) then -1 else 1 end
				--Accruals & Level End
				--PROTECTION CALCULATION END

				else 0.0

			end as Initial,
			0.0 as OngoingTotal,
			0.0 as OngoingYr01,
			0.0 as OngoingYr02,
			0.0 as OngoingYr03,
			0.0 as OngoingYr04,
			0.0 as OngoingYr05,
			0.0 as OngoingYr06,
			0.0 as OngoingYr07,
			0.0 as OngoingYr08,
			0.0 as OngoingYr09,
			0.0 as OngoingYr10,
			case 
				when (ph.ProductCategoryCode = 1 or pcc.KeyValue2 = '1') then Cfca.FACTOR*100.0		--COB
				when ph.ProductGroupCode = 3 then Mfca.FACTOR*100.0		--MORT
				when ph.ProductGroupCode = 6 then Pfca.FACTOR*100.0		--PROT
				else 0.0
			end as FCARate,
			case 
				when (ph.ProductCategoryCode = 1 or pcc.KeyValue2 = '1') then Crate.FACTOR*100.0	--COB
				when ph.ProductGroupCode = 3 then MRproc.FACTOR*100.0	--MORT
				when ph.ProductGroupCode = 6 then Prate.FACTOR*100.0	--PROT
				else 0.0
			end as RetentionRate,
			case 
				when mbf.MortgageFeeID is not null then  MRbkr.FACTOR*100.0	
				else 0.0
			end as RetentionRateBroker,
			null as OngoingServicingRate,
			null as OngoingServicingSource,
			pt.CommInitialAmount as DA,
			e.AMOUNT_REC as AmountReceived,
			cs.Premium,
			cs.AgentSplit,
			cs.CommissionType,
			left(cs.StandingOrderDesc,50) as CommissionTypeDesc,
			cs.PayBasisCode,							
			cs.PayBasisDesc,							
			cs.CreateDate as PaymentMatchedDate,		
			cs.Month,
			cs.FrequencyCode,
			cs.FrequencyDesc,
			pg.ProductGroupCode as ReassignedProductGroupCode,	--Force the re-assigned products...		
			pg.ProductGroupName as ReassignedProductGroupName,	--...to be processed as investments		
			'VNB-INI-PHASE-2' as RecognitionType,
			case 
				when (ph.ProductCategoryCode = 1 or pcc.KeyValue2 = '1') then 'WEALTH-INITIAL'
				when ph.ProductGroupCode = 3 then 'MORTGAGE'
				when ph.ProductGroupCode = 6 then 'PROTECTION'
				else null
			end as CalculationType,
			'Openwork 2006' as Source,
			@DateLastUpdated as DateInserted,
			@DateLastUpdated as DateLastUpdated,
			csp.year as CommissionYear
	from	#msit_CommissionStatementSUMMARY css
			inner join msit_CommissionStatement cs
						on cs.TransactionID = css.TransactionID
						and cs.AgentCode = css.AgentCode
			inner join mstt_Agents ag on ag.Code = cs.BusinessCode
			inner join mstt_PolicyTransactions pt on pt.ID = cs.TransactionID
			inner join mstt_Policies p on p.POL_NUM = pt.PolicyID
			inner join msit_CommissionStatementPeriods VNBStart on convert(date,pt.CreateDateTime) between VNBStart.PeriodStartDate and VNBStart.PeriodEndDate
			inner join msit_Commissionstatementperiods csp on csp.month = cs.month
			inner join mstt_ProductHierarchy ph on ph.productcode = cs.productcode
			inner join mstt_Expectation e on e.ID = cs.ExpectationID
			left join dbo.owt_MortgageBrokerFees mbf on mbf.PendingPaymentID = cs.PendingPaymentID and mbf.AdviceFeeCharged = 'Yes'
			left join owt_SelectionControl SC
						on SC.Process = 'ElitePoints' 
						and SC.KeyType = 'NSCPotCode' 
						and cs.CreateDate between SC.EffectiveStartDate and SC.EffectiveEndDate
			left join mstt_Commissions BSCpot
						on BSCpot.TransactionID = cs.TransactionID 
						and BSCpot.Agent_Code = sc.KeyValue
						and BSCpot.CommissionType = 10
			left join owt_SelectionControl SFMPC						
						on SFMPC.Process = 'ElitePoints' 
						and SFMPC.KeyType = 'ServicingFeeMarginPotCode' 
						and cs.CreateDate between SFMPC.EffectiveStartDate and SFMPC.EffectiveEndDate
			left join mstt_Commissions SFMpot							
						on SFMpot.TransactionID = cs.TransactionID 
						and SFMpot.Agent_Code = SFMPC.KeyValue
						and SFMpot.CommissionType = 10	
			left join owt_SelectionControl pcc 
						on pcc.Process = 'ElitePoints'
						and pcc.KeyType = 'ProductCategoryCode'
						and pcc.KeyValue = cs.ProductCode	
						and cs.CreateDate between pcc.EffectiveStartDate and pcc.EffectiveEndDate
			left join owt_SelectionControl ogsdflt 
						on ogsdflt.Process = 'ElitePoints'
						and ogsdflt.KeyType = 'DefaultOngoingServicingRate'
						and ogsdflt.SelectionType = 'VNB'
						and ogsdflt.KeyValue = case when ph.RDRType = 'ONPLAT' then 'ONPLAT' else 'OFPLAT' end
						and cs.CreateDate between ogsdflt.EffectiveStartDate and ogsdflt.EffectiveEndDate
			left join mstt_CodeProductGroup pg on pg.ProductGroupCode = case when pcc.KeyValue2 = '1' then 2 else ph.ProductGroupCode end
			left join owt_EliteFactors Cfca on Cfca.FeeType = 'VNB' and Cfca.category = 'COB-FCA-RATE' and csp.year between Cfca.StartYear and Cfca.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors Crate on Crate.FeeType = 'VNB' and Crate.category = 'COB-RETENTION-RATE' and csp.year between Crate.StartYear and Crate.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors Mfca on Mfca.FeeType = 'VNB' and Mfca.category = 'MORT-FCA-RATE' and csp.year between Mfca.StartYear and Mfca.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors MRproc on MRproc.FeeType = 'VNB' and MRproc.category = 'MORT-RETENTION-RATE-PROC' and csp.year between MRproc.StartYear and MRproc.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors MRbkr on MRbkr.FeeType = 'VNB' and MRbkr.category = 'MORT-RETENTION-RATE-BROKER' and csp.year between MRbkr.StartYear and MRbkr.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors Pfca on Pfca.FeeType = 'VNB' and Pfca.category = 'PROT-FCA-RATE' and csp.year between Pfca.StartYear and Pfca.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors Prate on Prate.FeeType = 'VNB' and Prate.category = 'PROT-RETENTION-RATE' and csp.year between Prate.StartYear and Prate.EndYear 
	where	cs.ReportingClassCode = 1
	and		cs.CommissionType in (1,2,17)			--We want all the initial payment types (i.e. not trail (ongoing))
	and		ag.Manager2Code <> @OwlManager2Code		--Exclude Owl

	select @RowCount = @@rowcount
	set @ProcessMessage = '#owt_Recognition (ini ph2 - accr adj) = ' + convert(nvarchar(10), @RowCount)
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseLog, @ProcessMessage, null, @Module, @Client

	/****************************************************************************

		Initial Phase 3
		1) Add up the +ves and -ves prior to the NEW front loaded amount and
			net them off on the first +ve following the last -ve
		2) Now set all the +ves following the one updated in (1) to zero.
																
	****************************************************************************/

	update r
		set RecognitionType	= case when r.SourceID >= css.MinInitialAfterAdjPendingPaymentID 
								then 'VNB-INI-PHASE-3'
								else r.RecognitionType
							  end,
			Initial = case  when r.SourceID = css.MinInitialAfterAdjPendingPaymentID 
								then (((r.DA)*(r.AgentSplit/100) * (r.RetentionRate/100.0)) - ((r.DA)*(r.AgentSplit/100) * (r.FCARate/100))) - derived.SumInitial
							when r.SourceID > css.MinInitialAfterAdjPendingPaymentID 
								then 0.0
							else r.Initial
					  end,
			DateLastUpdated = @DateLastUpdated
	from	#msit_CommissionStatementSUMMARY css
			inner join #AG_owt_Recognition_SEPARATE_ONGOING r
						on r.TransactionID = css.TransactionID
						and r.SellerCode = css.AgentCode
			inner join (select	r.TransactionID, r.SellerCode, SUM(Initial) as SumInitial
						from	#msit_CommissionStatementSUMMARY s
								inner join #AG_owt_Recognition_SEPARATE_ONGOING r 
											on r.TransactionID = s.TransactionID
											and r.SellerCode = s.AgentCode
						where	r.SourceID <= s.MaxAdjPendingPaymentID
						group	by r.TransactionID, r.SellerCode
						) derived 
							on  derived.TransactionID = r.TransactionID
							and	derived.SellerCode = r.SellerCode 
	where	isnull(css.MaxInitialPendingPaymentID,0) > isnull(css.MaxAdjPendingPaymentID,0)-- An initial payment follows the clawback, so time to revert back to front loading

	select @RowCount = @@rowcount
	set @ProcessMessage = '#owt_Recognition (ini ph3 - accr adj) = ' + convert(nvarchar(10), @RowCount)
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseLog, @ProcessMessage, null, @Module, @Client

	/****************************************************************************

		Now do the ongoing.
		
		Build an ongoing summary row for each transaction (slice).
		
		Note we do not care about ongoing clawbacks and adjustments for VNB.
		We want VNB to be on the oldest positive payment on each slice for the
		policy (split by adviser if needed).
						
	****************************************************************************/

	select	cs.TransactionID,
			cs.AgentCode,
			c.AGENT_PERC as AgentSplit,
			Min(case when cs.CommissionType = 10 then cs.PendingPaymentID else null end) as MinOngoingPendingPaymentID,
			MAX(case when cs.CommissionType = 10 then cs.PendingPaymentID else null end) as MaxOngoingPendingPaymentID,
			MAX(case when cs.CommissionType in (16,19) then cs.PendingPaymentID else null end) as MaxOngoingAdjPendingPaymentID,
			null as MinOngoingAfterAdjPendingPaymentID
	into	#msit_CommissionStatementOGSSUMMARY
	from 	msit_CommissionStatement cs
			inner join mstt_Commissions c
						on c.TransactionID = cs.TransactionID
						and c.Agent_Code = cs.AgentCode
						and c.CommissionType = 1
			inner join mstt_Agents ag on ag.Code = cs.BusinessCode
			inner join mstt_PolicyTransactions pt on pt.ID = cs.TransactionID
			inner join mstt_Policies p on p.POL_NUM = pt.PolicyID
			inner join msit_CommissionStatementPeriods VNBStart on convert(date,pt.CreateDateTime) between VNBStart.PeriodStartDate and VNBStart.PeriodEndDate
			inner join msit_Commissionstatementperiods csp on csp.month = cs.month
			inner join mstt_ProductHierarchy ph on ph.productcode = cs.productcode
			inner join mstt_Expectation e on e.ID = cs.ExpectationID
			left join owt_SelectionControl pcc 
						on pcc.Process = 'ElitePoints'
						and pcc.KeyType = 'ProductCategoryCode'
						and pcc.KeyValue = cs.ProductCode	
						and cs.CreateDate between pcc.EffectiveStartDate and pcc.EffectiveEndDate
	where	cs.ReportingClassCode = 1
	and		cs.CommissionType in (10,16,19)					--Choose only where the ongoing payment is positive
	and		cs.CommFeeType = 'Ongoing'
	and		(ph.ProductCategoryCode = 1 or pcc.KeyValue2 = '1')
	and		ag.Manager2Code <> @OwlManager2Code		--Exclude Owl
	and		csp.Year >= 2017						--Ensure in-scope payments are consistent with VNB start
	and		VNBStart.Year >= 2017 
	and		abs(e.AMOUNT_REC) >= 0.01
	and		((cs.FrequencyCode = 6 and cs.Premium > 1.00)		--Frequency=6->Single
			or (cs.FrequencyCode <> 6 and cs.Premium > 0.01))	--Frequency<>6->Regular	
	group by	cs.TransactionID,
				cs.AgentCode,
				c.Agent_Perc

	select @RowCount = @@rowcount
	set @ProcessMessage = '#msit_CommissionStatementOGSSUMMARY (ogs txn) = ' + convert(nvarchar(10), @RowCount)
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseLog, @ProcessMessage, null, @Module, @Client

	--Get first ongoing payment after last clawback/adj
	update cso
		set MinOngoingAfterAdjPendingPaymentID = summ.MinPendingPaymentID 
	from  #msit_CommissionStatementOGSSUMMARY cso
			inner join  (
						select	csoinner.TransactionID, csoinner.AgentCode, min(cs.PendingPaymentID) as MinPendingPaymentID
						from	#msit_CommissionStatementOGSSUMMARY csoinner
								inner join msit_CommissionStatement cs
											on cs.TransactionID = csoinner.TransactionID
											and cs.AgentCode = csoinner.AgentCode
						where	cs.PendingPaymentID > csoinner.MaxOngoingAdjPendingPaymentID
						and		cs.CommissionType = 10
						group by csoinner.TransactionID, csoinner.AgentCode
						) summ on  summ.TransactionID = cso.TransactionID
							   and summ.AgentCode = cso.AgentCode

	select @RowCount = @@rowcount
	set @ProcessMessage = '#msit_CommissionStatementOGSSUMMARY (ogs latest +ve) = ' + convert(nvarchar(10), @RowCount)
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseLog, @ProcessMessage, null, @Module, @Client

	/****************************************************************************
		
		Using the OGS SUMMARY table, get all the individual payment records that
		will be carriers of VNB points as follows:
		
		SelectionSource 1 - The oldest +ve payment where no clawbacks or 
								adjustments occur for front loading

		SelectionSource 2 - All the +ve payments that will get a spread of the 
								per payment +ve points 		

		SelectionSource 3 - All the -ve payments that will get a spread of the 
								per payment -ve points
								 															
	****************************************************************************/
	
	--Front loaded -> Just the oldest +ve payment
	--Note: These transactions have NO clawbacks or adjustments
	select	1 as SelectionSource,
			cso.TransactionID,
			cso.AgentCode,
			cso.MinOngoingPendingPaymentID as PendingPaymentID,
			cso.AgentSplit,
			1 as SpreadNumber,
			1 as MaxSpread 
	into	#msit_CommissionStatementONGOING
	from	#msit_CommissionStatementOGSSUMMARY cso	
	where	cso.MaxOngoingAdjPendingPaymentID is null	--No clawbacks or adjustments - so front load
	and		cso.MinOngoingPendingPaymentID is not null	--At least one +ve payment on the transaction

	union	--Add in with dedupe
	
	--Per payment -> all +ve payments with max spread also used for divisor
	--Note: ALL these transactions have clawbacks or adjustments
	select	2 as SelectionSource,
			cso.TransactionID,
			cso.AgentCode,
			cs.PendingPaymentID,
			cso.AgentSplit,
			ROW_NUMBER() over (partition by cs.TransactionID, cs.AgentCode order by cs.TransactionID, cs.AgentCode, cs.PendingPaymentID) as SpreadNumber,
			12 as MaxSpread
	from	#msit_CommissionStatementOGSSUMMARY cso	
			inner join msit_CommissionStatement cs 
						on cs.TransactionID = cso.TransactionID
						and cs.AgentCode = cso.AgentCode
	where	cso.MaxOngoingAdjPendingPaymentID is not null	--Clawbacks or adjustments so per payment
	and		cs.CommissionType in (10)	

	union	--Add in with dedupe
	
	--Per payment -> all -ve payments - with max spread also used for divisor
	--Note: ALL these transactions have clawbacks or adjustments
	select	3 as SelectionSource,
			cso.TransactionID,
			cso.AgentCode,
			cs.PendingPaymentID,
			cso.AgentSplit,
			ROW_NUMBER() over (partition by cs.TransactionID, cs.AgentCode order by cs.TransactionID, cs.AgentCode, cs.PendingPaymentID) as SpreadNumber,
			12 as MaxSpread
	from	#msit_CommissionStatementOGSSUMMARY cso	
			inner join msit_CommissionStatement cs 
						on cs.TransactionID = cso.TransactionID
						and cs.AgentCode = cso.AgentCode
	where	cso.MaxOngoingAdjPendingPaymentID is not null	--Clawbacks or adjustments so per payment
	and		cs.CommissionType in (16,19)	

	select @RowCount = @@rowcount
	set @ProcessMessage = '#msit_CommissionStatementONGOING (ogs payments) = ' + convert(nvarchar(10), @RowCount)
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseLog, @ProcessMessage, null, @Module, @Client

	/****************************************************************************
		
		Insert the ongoing VNB results for those transactions 
																		
	****************************************************************************/

	insert into #AG_owt_Recognition_SEPARATE_ONGOING
	(
		SourceID,
		CaseID,
		TransactionID,
		Policy,
		ProductCode,
		BusinessCode,
		SellerCode,
		PointsTotal,
		BSC,
		MBF,
		Initial,
		OngoingTotal,
		OngoingYr01,
		OngoingYr02,
		OngoingYr03,
		OngoingYr04,
		OngoingYr05,
		OngoingYr06,
		OngoingYr07,
		OngoingYr08,
		OngoingYr09,
		OngoingYr10,
		FCARate,
		RetentionRate,
		RetentionRateBroker,
		OngoingServicingRate,
		OngoingServicingSource,
		DA,
		AmountReceived,
		Premium,
		AgentSplit,
		CommissionType,
		CommissionTypeDesc,
		PayBasisCode,
		PayBasisDesc,
		PaymentMatchedDate,
		Month,
		FrequencyCode,
		FrequencyDesc,
		ReassignedProductGroupCode,
		ReassignedProductGroupName,
		RecognitionType,
		CalculationType,
		Source,
		DateInserted,
		DateLastUpdated,
		CommissionYear
	)
	select	cs.PendingPaymentID as SourceID,
			cs.CaseID,
			cs.TransactionID,
			cs.ExtPolicyNumber as Policy,
			cs.ProductCode,
			cs.BusinessCode,
			cs.AgentCode as SellerCode,
			0.0 as PointsTotal,
			case
				when BSCpot.ID is not null then 
					--BSC takes the first 0.12 of the ongoing fee %. If the ongoing fee % is 0.12% or less, then 100% of the ongoing fee is allocated to BSC
					case when coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2)) - convert(decimal(8,4),sc.KeyValue2) >= 0.01
						then 
							case when cs.FrequencyCode = 2	--Monthly 
								then (cso.AgentSplit/100) * 12.0 * (isnull(cs.Premium/cso.MaxSpread,0)/2.0) * convert(decimal(8,4),sc.KeyValue3) * case when cs.CommissionType in (16,19) then -1 else 1 end
								else (cso.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(cs.Premium/cso.MaxSpread,0) * convert(decimal(8,4),sc.KeyValue3) * case when cs.CommissionType in (16,19) then -1 else 1 end
							end			
						else
							case when cs.FrequencyCode = 2	--Monthly 
								then (cso.AgentSplit/100) * 12.0 * (isnull(cs.Premium/cso.MaxSpread,0)/2.0) * coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2)) * case when cs.CommissionType in (16,19) then -1 else 1 end
								else (cso.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(cs.Premium/cso.MaxSpread,0) * (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))/100.0) * case when cs.CommissionType in (16,19) then -1 else 1 end
							end
					end
				else 0.0
			end as BSC,
			0.0 as MBF,
			0.0 as Initial,
			0.0 as OngoingTotal,
			case
				--WEALTH ONGOING CALCULATION START
				--When the adviser has changed, the AgentSplit can become zero in which case the ELITE points should be zero.
				when cso.AgentSplit = 0 then 0

				--SINGLE start
				--Calculate when BSC and ongoing applies (where ongoing rate is greater than BSC rate) 
				when cs.FrequencyCode = 6 and SFMpot.ID is not null and BSCpot.ID is not null and (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2)) - convert(decimal(8,4),sc.KeyValue2)) >= 0.01 then 
							--(AUM X BSC Rate)...
							((cso.AgentSplit/100) * (isnull(cs.Premium/cso.MaxSpread,0) * convert(decimal(8,4),sc.KeyValue3)) 
							--(AUM X OGS Rate X COB FCA Rate)...
							- ((cso.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(cs.Premium/cso.MaxSpread,0) * (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))/100.0) * Cfca.FACTOR)
							--(AUM X (OGS Rate - BSC Rate) X COB Retention Rate)...
							+ ((cso.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(cs.Premium/cso.MaxSpread,0) * ((coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))-convert(decimal(8,4),sc.KeyValue2))/100.0)) * Crate.FACTOR) 
							--Sign correctly for +ve or clawback payment
							* (case when cs.CommissionType in (16,19) then -1 else 1 end)
				--Calculate when BSC and ongoing applies (where ongoing rate less than BSC rate, then BSC gets all the ongoing available) 
				when cs.FrequencyCode = 6 and SFMpot.ID is not null and BSCpot.ID is not null then
							--(AUM X BSC Rate)...(in this scenario it's all of the OGS rate)
							((cso.AgentSplit/100) * (isnull(cs.Premium/cso.MaxSpread,0) * (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))/100.0)) 
							--(AUM X OGS Rate X COB FCA Rate)...
							- ((cso.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(cs.Premium/cso.MaxSpread,0) * (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))/100.0) * Cfca.FACTOR)
							--(AUM X (OGS Rate - BSC Rate) X COB Retention Rate)...
							+ (0.0)) --BSC got it all, so this part of the calculation is zero
							--Sign correctly for +ve or clawback payment
							* (case when cs.CommissionType in (16,19) then -1 else 1 end)
				--Calculate when no BSC applies and ongoing applies
				when cs.FrequencyCode = 6 and SFMpot.ID is not null and BSCpot.ID is null then 
							--(AUM X OGS Rate X COB Retention Rate)...
							(((cso.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(cs.Premium/cso.MaxSpread,0) * (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))/100.0) * Crate.FACTOR) 
							--(AUM X OGS Rate X COB FCA Rate)...
							- ((cso.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(cs.Premium/cso.MaxSpread,0) * (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))/100.0) * Cfca.FACTOR))
							--Sign correctly for +ve or clawback payment
							* (case when cs.CommissionType in (16,19) then -1 else 1 end)
				--SINGLE end
				
				--REGULAR start
				--Calculate when BSC and ongoing applies (where ongoing rate is greater than BSC rate) 
				when cs.FrequencyCode <> 6 and SFMpot.ID is not null and BSCpot.ID is not null and (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2)) - convert(decimal(8,4),sc.KeyValue2)) >= 0.01 then		--AG 04/06/2018 (1)
							--The non-BSC portion (Ave AUM X (OGS Rate - BSC Rate) X COB Retention Rate)...
							((((((cso.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(cs.Premium/cso.MaxSpread,0) * (case when cs.FrequencyCode = 2 then 12 else 1 end))/2.0) * (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2)) - convert(decimal(8,4),sc.KeyValue2))/100.0)) * Crate.FACTOR
							--The BSC portion (Ave AUM X BSC Rate)...
							+ case when cs.FrequencyCode = 2	--Monthly 
									then (cso.AgentSplit/100) * 12.0 * (isnull(cs.Premium/cso.MaxSpread,0)/2.0) * convert(decimal(8,4),sc.KeyValue3) 
									else (cso.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(cs.Premium/cso.MaxSpread,0) * convert(decimal(8,4),sc.KeyValue3) 
							  end
							--FCA Charge (Ave AUM X OGS Rate X FCA Rate)...
							- (case when cs.FrequencyCode = 2	--Monthly 
									then (cso.AgentSplit/100) * 12.0 * (isnull(cs.Premium/cso.MaxSpread,0)/2.0) 
									else (cso.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(cs.Premium/cso.MaxSpread,0) 
							   end * (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))/100.0) * Cfca.FACTOR))
							--Sign correctly for +ve or clawback payment
							* (case when cs.CommissionType in (16,19) then -1 else 1 end)   
				--Calculate when BSC and ongoing applies (where ongoing rate less than BSC rate, then BSC gets all the ongoing available) 
				when cs.FrequencyCode <> 6 and SFMpot.ID is not null and BSCpot.ID is not null then		--AG 04/06/2018 (1)
							--The non-BSC portion (Ave AUM X (OGS Rate - BSC Rate) X COB Retention Rate)...
							((0.0)	--BSC got it all, so this part of the calculation is zero
							--The BSC portion (Ave AUM X BSC Rate)...(in this scenario it's all of the OGS rate)
							+ case when cs.FrequencyCode = 2	--Monthly 
									then (cso.AgentSplit/100) * 12.0 * (isnull(cs.Premium/cso.MaxSpread,0)/2.0) * (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))/100.0) 
									else (cso.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(cs.Premium/cso.MaxSpread,0) * (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))/100.0) 
							  end
							--FCA Charge (Ave AUM X OGS Rate X FCA Rate)...
							- (case when cs.FrequencyCode = 2	--Monthly 
									then (cso.AgentSplit/100) * 12.0 * (isnull(cs.Premium/cso.MaxSpread,0)/2.0) 
									else (cso.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(cs.Premium/cso.MaxSpread,0) 
							   end * (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))/100.0) * Cfca.FACTOR))
							--Sign correctly for +ve or clawback payment
							* (case when cs.CommissionType in (16,19) then -1 else 1 end)   
				--Calculate when no BSC applies, but ongoing servicing applies
				when cs.FrequencyCode <> 6 and SFMpot.ID is not null and BSCpot.ID is null then		--AG 04/06/2018	(1)
							--(Ave AUM X OGS Rate X COB Retention Rate)...
							(((((cso.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(cs.Premium/cso.MaxSpread,0) * (case when cs.FrequencyCode = 2 then 12 else 1 end))/2.0) * (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))/100.0) * Crate.FACTOR) 
							--(Ave AUM X OGS Rate X COB FCA Rate)...
							- ((((cso.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(cs.Premium/cso.MaxSpread,0) * (case when cs.FrequencyCode = 2 then 12 else 1 end))/2.0) * (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))/100.0) * Cfca.FACTOR))
							--Sign correctly for +ve or clawback payment
							* (case when cs.CommissionType in (16,19) then -1 else 1 end)   
				--REGULAR end
				
				else 0.0

				--WEALTH ONGOING CALCULATION END
			end as OngoingYr01,
			0.0 as OngoingYr02,
			0.0 as OngoingYr03,
			0.0 as OngoingYr04,
			0.0 as OngoingYr05,
			0.0 as OngoingYr06,
			0.0 as OngoingYr07,
			0.0 as OngoingYr08,
			0.0 as OngoingYr09,
			0.0 as OngoingYr10,
			Cfca.FACTOR*100.0 as FCARate,
			Crate.FACTOR*100.0 as RetentionRate,
			0.0 as RetentionRateBroker,
			case when SFMpot.ID is not null
				then coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))
				else null
			end as OngoingServicingRate,
			case when SFMpot.ID is not null
				then case 
						when ogs.OngoingServiceFee is null and ogscli.OngoingServiceFee is null 
							then case
								when ogsdflt.KeyValue = 'ONPLAT' then 'Default - On Plat'
								else 'Default - Off Plat'
							end
						when ogs.OngoingServiceFee is not null then 'Client Product'
						when ogscli.OngoingServiceFee is not null then 'Client Only'
						else 'Unknown'
					 end
				else case when (ph.ProductCategoryCode = 1 or pcc.KeyValue2 = '1')
						then 'No OGS'					--WEALTH, but no OGS
						else null						--Not WEALTH, so OGS is n/a and is therefore null
					 end
			end as OngoingServicingSource,
			pt.CommInitialAmount as DA,
			e.AMOUNT_REC as AmountReceived,
			cs.Premium,
			cso.AgentSplit,								--Use the split from the IC record
			cs.CommissionType,
			left(cs.StandingOrderDesc,50) as CommissionTypeDesc,
			cs.PayBasisCode,
			cs.PayBasisDesc,
			cs.CreateDate as PaymentMatchedDate,
			cs.Month,
			cs.FrequencyCode,
			cs.FrequencyDesc,
			pg.ProductGroupCode as ReassignedProductGroupCode,	--Force the re-assigned products...		
			pg.ProductGroupName as ReassignedProductGroupName,	--...to be processed as investments		
			case cso.SelectionSource
				when 1 then 'VNB-OGS-PHASE-1' 
				when 2 then 'VNB-OGS-PHASE-2' 
				when 3 then 'VNB-OGS-PHASE-3' 
			end as RecognitionType,
			'WEALTH-ONGOING' as CalculationType,
			'Openwork 2006' as Source,
			@DateLastUpdated as DateInserted,
			@DateLastUpdated as DateLastUpdated,
			csp.year as CommissionYear
	from	#msit_CommissionStatementONGOING cso
			inner join msit_CommissionStatement cs on cs.PendingPaymentID = cso.PendingPaymentID
			inner join mstt_Agents ag on ag.Code = cs.BusinessCode
			inner join mstt_PolicyTransactions pt on pt.ID = cs.TransactionID
			inner join mstt_Policies p on p.POL_NUM = pt.PolicyID
			inner join msit_CommissionStatementPeriods VNBStart on convert(date,pt.CreateDateTime) between VNBStart.PeriodStartDate and VNBStart.PeriodEndDate
			inner join msit_Commissionstatementperiods csp on csp.month = cs.month
			inner join mstt_ProductHierarchy ph on ph.productcode = cs.productcode
			inner join mstt_Expectation e on e.ID = cs.ExpectationID
			left join dbo.owt_MortgageBrokerFees mbf on mbf.PendingPaymentID = cs.PendingPaymentID and mbf.AdviceFeeCharged = 'Yes'
			left join owt_SelectionControl SC
						on SC.Process = 'ElitePoints' 
						and SC.KeyType = 'NSCPotCode' 
						and cs.CreateDate between SC.EffectiveStartDate and SC.EffectiveEndDate
			left join mstt_Commissions BSCpot
						on BSCpot.TransactionID = cs.TransactionID 
						and BSCpot.Agent_Code = sc.KeyValue
						and BSCpot.CommissionType = 10
			left join owt_SelectionControl SFMPC						
						on SFMPC.Process = 'ElitePoints' 
						and SFMPC.KeyType = 'ServicingFeeMarginPotCode' 
						and cs.CreateDate between SFMPC.EffectiveStartDate and SFMPC.EffectiveEndDate
			left join mstt_Commissions SFMpot							
						on SFMpot.TransactionID = cs.TransactionID 
						and SFMpot.Agent_Code = SFMPC.KeyValue
						and SFMpot.CommissionType = 10	
			left join owt_SelectionControl pcc 
						on pcc.Process = 'ElitePoints'
						and pcc.KeyType = 'ProductCategoryCode'
						and pcc.KeyValue = cs.ProductCode	
						and cs.CreateDate between pcc.EffectiveStartDate and pcc.EffectiveEndDate
			left join owt_SelectionControl ogsdflt 
						on ogsdflt.Process = 'ElitePoints'
						and ogsdflt.KeyType = 'DefaultOngoingServicingRate'
						and ogsdflt.SelectionType = 'VNB'
						and ogsdflt.KeyValue = case when ph.RDRType = 'ONPLAT' then 'ONPLAT' else 'OFPLAT' end
						and cs.CreateDate between ogsdflt.EffectiveStartDate and ogsdflt.EffectiveEndDate
			left join mstt_CodeProductGroup pg on pg.ProductGroupCode = case when pcc.KeyValue2 = '1' then 2 else ph.ProductGroupCode end
			left join owt_EliteFactors Cfca on Cfca.FeeType = 'VNB' and Cfca.category = 'COB-FCA-RATE' and csp.year between Cfca.StartYear and Cfca.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors Crate on Crate.FeeType = 'VNB' and Crate.category = 'COB-RETENTION-RATE' and csp.year between Crate.StartYear and Crate.EndYear 
			left join dbo.owt_OngoingRate ogs 
						on  ogs.CLIENT_NUM = cs.ClientID 
						and ogs.ProductCode = cs.ProductCode
						and convert(date,pt.CreateDateTime) between ogs.EffectiveStartDate and ogs.EffectiveEndDate
			left join dbo.owt_OngoingRate ogscli 
						on  ogscli.CLIENT_NUM = cs.ClientID 
						and ogscli.ProductCode = '(CLIENT)'
						and convert(date,pt.CreateDateTime) between ogscli.EffectiveStartDate and ogscli.EffectiveEndDate
	where	cso.SpreadNumber <= cso.MaxSpread	-- if per payment spreading, then limit the spread
	
	select @RowCount = @@rowcount
	set @ProcessMessage = '#owt_Recognition (ogs ph1 yr1) = ' + convert(nvarchar(10), @RowCount)
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseLog, @ProcessMessage, null, @Module, @Client

	/****************************************************************************

		Ongoing Phase 3
		1) Add up the +ves and -ves prior to the NEW front loaded amount and
			net them off on the first +ve following the last -ve
		2) Now set all the +ves following the one updated in (1) to zero.
																
	****************************************************************************/

	update r
		set RecognitionType	= case when r.SourceID >= csos.MinOngoingAfterAdjPendingPaymentID 
								then 'VNB-OGS-PHASE-4'
								else r.RecognitionType
							  end,
			OngoingYr01 = case  when r.SourceID = csos.MinOngoingAfterAdjPendingPaymentID 
									then (abs(r.OngoingYr01) * cso.MaxSpread) - derived.SumOngoingYr01
								when r.SourceID > csos.MinOngoingAfterAdjPendingPaymentID 
									then 0.0
								else r.OngoingYr01
						  end,
			DateLastUpdated = @DateLastUpdated
	from	#msit_CommissionStatementONGOING cso 
			inner join #AG_owt_Recognition_SEPARATE_ONGOING r on r.SourceID = cso.PendingPaymentID
			inner join #msit_CommissionStatementOGSSUMMARY csos
						on  csos.TransactionID = cso.TransactionID
						and csos.AgentCode = cso.AgentCode
			inner join (select	r.TransactionID, r.SellerCode, SUM(OngoingYr01) as SumOngoingYr01
						from	#msit_CommissionStatementOGSSUMMARY s
								inner join #AG_owt_Recognition_SEPARATE_ONGOING r 
											on r.TransactionID = s.TransactionID
											and r.SellerCode = s.AgentCode
						where	r.SourceID <= s.MaxOngoingAdjPendingPaymentID
						group	by r.TransactionID, r.SellerCode
						) derived 
							on  derived.TransactionID = r.TransactionID
							and	derived.SellerCode = r.SellerCode 
	where	isnull(csos.MaxOngoingPendingPaymentID,0) > isnull(csos.MaxOngoingAdjPendingPaymentID,0)	--An ongoing +ve payment follows the clawback, so time to revert back to front loading
	and		cso.SpreadNumber <= cso.MaxSpread	--Only payments within the spread period get a portion of the ongoing VNB
	and		cso.SelectionSource <> 1			--Just process the per-payment rows (not the front loaded rows)

	select @RowCount = @@rowcount
	set @ProcessMessage = '#owt_Recognition (ogs ph4 - accr adj) = ' + convert(nvarchar(10), @RowCount)
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseLog, @ProcessMessage, null, @Module, @Client

	/****************************************************************************

		Now calculate the ongoing spread as follows:
		1) Investments: Years 1 to 6
		2) Pensions:	Years 1 to 10
		Note that regular payments get an additional multiplier to uplift the 
		average AUM for each year.
																		
	****************************************************************************/

	update r
		set OngoingYr02 = case when r.FrequencyCode = 2									--Monthly
							then r.OngoingYr01 * YR02.Multiplier * YR02.Factor			--Regular
							else r.OngoingYr01 * YR02.Factor							--Single
						  end,
			OngoingYr03 = case when r.FrequencyCode = 2									--Monthly
							then r.OngoingYr01 * YR03.Multiplier * YR03.Factor			--Regular
							else r.OngoingYr01 * YR03.Factor							--Single
						  end,
			OngoingYr04 = case when r.FrequencyCode = 2									--Monthly
							then r.OngoingYr01 * YR04.Multiplier * YR04.Factor			--Regular
							else r.OngoingYr01 * YR04.Factor							--Single
						  end,
			OngoingYr05 = case when r.FrequencyCode = 2									--Monthly 
							then r.OngoingYr01 * YR05.Multiplier * YR05.Factor			--Regular
							else r.OngoingYr01 * YR05.Factor							--Single
						  end,
			OngoingYr06 = case when r.FrequencyCode = 2									--Monthly 
							then r.OngoingYr01 * YR06.Multiplier * YR06.Factor			--Regular
							else r.OngoingYr01 * YR06.Factor							--Single
						  end,
			OngoingYr07 = case when r.ReassignedProductGroupCode = 5					--Pensions	AG 05/06/2018
							then
								case when r.FrequencyCode = 2							--Monthly 
									then r.OngoingYr01 * YR07.Multiplier * YR07.Factor	--Regular
									else r.OngoingYr01 * YR07.Factor					--Single
								end
							else 
								0.0
						  end,
			OngoingYr08 = case when r.ReassignedProductGroupCode = 5					--Pensions	AG 05/06/2018 
							then
								case when r.FrequencyCode = 2							--Monthly 
									then r.OngoingYr01 * YR08.Multiplier * YR08.Factor	--Regular
									else r.OngoingYr01 * YR08.Factor					--Single
								end
							else 
								0.0
						  end,
			OngoingYr09 = case when r.ReassignedProductGroupCode = 5					--Pensions	AG 05/06/2018 
							then
								case when r.FrequencyCode = 2							--Monthly 
									then r.OngoingYr01 * YR09.Multiplier * YR09.Factor	--Regular
									else r.OngoingYr01 * YR09.Factor					--Single
								end
							else 
								0.0
						  end,
			OngoingYr10 = case when r.ReassignedProductGroupCode = 5					--Pensions	AG 05/06/2018
							then
								case when r.FrequencyCode = 2							--Monthly 
									then r.OngoingYr01 * YR10.Multiplier * YR10.Factor	--Regular
									else r.OngoingYr01 * YR10.Factor					--Single
								end
							else 
								0.0
						  end
	from	#AG_owt_Recognition_SEPARATE_ONGOING r
			left join owt_EliteFactors YR01 on YR01.FeeType = 'VNB' and YR01.Category = 'COB-ONGOING-DISCOUNT-YR01' and r.CommissionYear between YR01.StartYear and YR01.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors YR02 on YR02.FeeType = 'VNB' and YR02.Category = 'COB-ONGOING-DISCOUNT-YR02' and r.CommissionYear between YR02.StartYear and YR02.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors YR03 on YR03.FeeType = 'VNB' and YR03.Category = 'COB-ONGOING-DISCOUNT-YR03' and r.CommissionYear between YR03.StartYear and YR03.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors YR04 on YR04.FeeType = 'VNB' and YR04.Category = 'COB-ONGOING-DISCOUNT-YR04' and r.CommissionYear between YR04.StartYear and YR04.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors YR05 on YR05.FeeType = 'VNB' and YR05.Category = 'COB-ONGOING-DISCOUNT-YR05' and r.CommissionYear between YR05.StartYear and YR05.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors YR06 on YR06.FeeType = 'VNB' and YR06.Category = 'COB-ONGOING-DISCOUNT-YR06' and r.CommissionYear between YR06.StartYear and YR06.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors YR07 on YR07.FeeType = 'VNB' and YR07.Category = 'COB-ONGOING-DISCOUNT-YR07' and r.CommissionYear between YR07.StartYear and YR07.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors YR08 on YR08.FeeType = 'VNB' and YR08.Category = 'COB-ONGOING-DISCOUNT-YR08' and r.CommissionYear between YR08.StartYear and YR08.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors YR09 on YR09.FeeType = 'VNB' and YR09.Category = 'COB-ONGOING-DISCOUNT-YR09' and r.CommissionYear between YR09.StartYear and YR09.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors YR10 on YR10.FeeType = 'VNB' and YR10.Category = 'COB-ONGOING-DISCOUNT-YR10' and r.CommissionYear between YR10.StartYear and YR10.EndYear 
	where	r.CalculationType = 'WEALTH-ONGOING'

	select @RowCount = @@rowcount
	set @ProcessMessage = '#owt_Recognition (ongoing yr2-10) = ' + convert(nvarchar(10), @RowCount)
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseLog, @ProcessMessage, null, @Module, @Client
	
	/****************************************************************************

		Now add up all the numbers
																		
	****************************************************************************/
	
	update r
		set OngoingTotal	=	OngoingYr01 + OngoingYr02 + OngoingYr03 + OngoingYr04 + OngoingYr05 +
								OngoingYr06 + OngoingYr07 + OngoingYr08 + OngoingYr09 + OngoingYr10,
			PointsTotal		=	OngoingYr01 + OngoingYr02 + OngoingYr03 + OngoingYr04 + OngoingYr05 +
								OngoingYr06 + OngoingYr07 + OngoingYr08 + OngoingYr09 + OngoingYr10 +
								Initial + MBF	-- Note BSC is already included in the Ongoing, so don't include it in the Points Total.
	from	#AG_owt_Recognition_SEPARATE_ONGOING r

	select @RowCount = @@rowcount
	set @ProcessMessage = '#owt_Recognition (points total) = ' + convert(nvarchar(10), @RowCount)
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseLog, @ProcessMessage, null, @Module, @Client

	/****************************************************************************

		Merge the temporary table into the permanent table (IC data)
																		
	****************************************************************************/

	BEGIN TRANSACTION

	declare @SummaryOfChanges table (Change varchar(20))
	merge	dbo.AG_owt_Recognition_SEPARATE_ONGOING as trg
	using	#AG_owt_Recognition_SEPARATE_ONGOING as src
	on		trg.SourceID = src.SourceID
	and		trg.Source = src.Source
	when	matched 
	and		isnull(trg.PointsTotal,0) <> isnull(src.PointsTotal,0)
	then	update 
				set trg.CaseID = src.CaseID,
					trg.TransactionID = src.TransactionID,
					trg.Policy = src.Policy,
					trg.ProductCode = src.ProductCode,
					trg.BusinessCode = src.BusinessCode,
					trg.SellerCode = src.SellerCode,					--AG 13/06/2018
					trg.PointsTotal = src.PointsTotal,
					trg.BSC = src.BSC,
					trg.MBF = src.MBF,
					trg.Initial = src.Initial,
					trg.OngoingTotal = src.OngoingTotal,
					trg.OngoingYr01 = src.OngoingYr01,
					trg.OngoingYr02 = src.OngoingYr02,
					trg.OngoingYr03 = src.OngoingYr03,
					trg.OngoingYr04 = src.OngoingYr04,
					trg.OngoingYr05 = src.OngoingYr05,
					trg.OngoingYr06 = src.OngoingYr06,
					trg.OngoingYr07 = src.OngoingYr07,
					trg.OngoingYr08 = src.OngoingYr08,
					trg.OngoingYr09 = src.OngoingYr09,
					trg.OngoingYr10 = src.OngoingYr10,
					trg.FCARate = src.FCARate,
					trg.RetentionRate = src.RetentionRate,
					trg.RetentionRateBroker = src.RetentionRateBroker,
					trg.OngoingServicingRate = src.OngoingServicingRate,
					trg.OngoingServicingSource = src.OngoingServicingSource,
					trg.DA = src.DA,
					trg.AmountReceived = src.AmountReceived,
					trg.Premium = src.Premium,
					trg.AgentSplit = src.AgentSplit,
					trg.CommissionType = src.CommissionType,
					trg.CommissionTypeDesc = src.CommissionTypeDesc,
					trg.PayBasisCode = src.PayBasisCode,				--AG 13/06/2018
					trg.PayBasisDesc = src.PayBasisDesc,				--AG 13/06/2018
					trg.PaymentMatchedDate = src.PaymentMatchedDate,	--AG 13/06/2018	
					trg.Month = src.Month,
					trg.FrequencyCode = src.FrequencyCode,
					trg.FrequencyDesc = src.FrequencyDesc,
					trg.ReassignedProductGroupCode = src.ReassignedProductGroupCode,	--AG 05/06/2018
					trg.ReassignedProductGroupName = src.ReassignedProductGroupName,	--AG 05/06/2018
					trg.RecognitionType = src.RecognitionType,
					trg.CalculationType = src.CalculationType,
					trg.DateLastUpdated = @DateLastUpdated
	when	not matched by target 
	then	insert
			(
				SourceID,
				CaseID,
				TransactionID,
				Policy,
				ProductCode,
				BusinessCode,
				SellerCode,							--AG 13/06/2018
				PointsTotal,
				BSC,
				MBF,
				Initial,
				OngoingTotal,
				OngoingYr01,
				OngoingYr02,
				OngoingYr03,
				OngoingYr04,
				OngoingYr05,
				OngoingYr06,
				OngoingYr07,
				OngoingYr08,
				OngoingYr09,
				OngoingYr10,
				FCARate,
				RetentionRate,
				RetentionRateBroker,
				OngoingServicingRate,
				OngoingServicingSource,
				DA,
				AmountReceived,
				Premium,
				AgentSplit,
				CommissionType,
				CommissionTypeDesc,
				PayBasisCode,						--AG 13/06/2018
				PayBasisDesc,						--AG 13/06/2018
				PaymentMatchedDate,					--AG 13/06/2018
				Month,
				FrequencyCode,
				FrequencyDesc,
				ReassignedProductGroupCode,			--AG 05/06/2018
				ReassignedProductGroupName,			--AG 05/06/2018
				RecognitionType,
				CalculationType,
				Source,
				DateInserted,
				DateLastUpdated
			)		
			values
			(
				src.SourceID,
				src.CaseID,
				src.TransactionID,
				src.Policy,
				src.ProductCode,
				src.BusinessCode,
				src.SellerCode,						--AG 13/06/2018
				src.PointsTotal,
				src.BSC,
				src.MBF,
				src.Initial,
				src.OngoingTotal,
				src.OngoingYr01,
				src.OngoingYr02,
				src.OngoingYr03,
				src.OngoingYr04,
				src.OngoingYr05,
				src.OngoingYr06,
				src.OngoingYr07,
				src.OngoingYr08,
				src.OngoingYr09,
				src.OngoingYr10,
				src.FCARate,
				src.RetentionRate,
				src.RetentionRateBroker,
				src.OngoingServicingRate,
				src.OngoingServicingSource,
				src.DA,
				src.AmountReceived,
				src.Premium,
				src.AgentSplit,
				src.CommissionType,
				src.CommissionTypeDesc,
				src.PayBasisCode,					--AG 13/06/2018
				src.PayBasisDesc,					--AG 13/06/2018
				src.PaymentMatchedDate,				--AG 13/06/2018
				src.Month,
				src.FrequencyCode,
				src.FrequencyDesc,
				src.ReassignedProductGroupCode,		--AG 05/06/2018
				src.ReassignedProductGroupName,		--AG 05/06/2018
				src.RecognitionType,
				src.CalculationType,
				src.Source,
				src.DateInserted,
				src.DateLastUpdated)				--Merge statements must have a ;
	output $action into @SummaryOfChanges;
						
	/****************************************************************************

		Update OpenAccess
																		
	****************************************************************************/

/*	
	--Do not include MBF in the OpenAccess Commission Listing as it is on the MBF download
	--and we don't want MBF double counting.
	update	oal
		set VNB_Points = r.PointsTotal - r.MBF		--AG 04/06/2018 (2)
	from	msit_CommissionStatement cs
/*			inner join (select	distinct PKID
						from	owt_TransformationMovements tm 
						where	tm.DriverTableName = 'sa_swift_S_AGMFIL'
						and		tm.CommissionStatement = 'Y') tm on tm.PKID = cs.PendingPaymentID
*/			inner join msit_OpenworkAdviserListing oal on oal.SourceID = cs.ID and oal.Source = 'Openwork 2006'
			inner join owt_Recognition r 
						on r.SourceID = cs.PendingPaymentID
						and r.Source = oal.Source
	--where	isnull(oal.VNB_Points,0) <> isnull(r.PointsTotal,0)
	
	select @OALRowCount = @@rowcount
*/
	COMMIT TRANSACTION      
	
	select	@RowCount = COUNT(*)
	from	@SummaryOfChanges
	where	Change = 'INSERT'

	set @ProcessMessage = 'owt_Recognition (insert) = ' + convert(nvarchar(10), @RowCount)
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseLog, @ProcessMessage, null, @Module, @Client

	select	@RowCount = COUNT(*)
	from	@SummaryOfChanges
	where	Change = 'UPDATE'

	set @ProcessMessage = 'owt_Recognition (update) = ' + convert(nvarchar(10), @RowCount)
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseLog, @ProcessMessage, null, @Module, @Client
/*
	set @ProcessMessage = 'msit_OpenworkAdviserListing (update) = ' + convert(nvarchar(10), @OALRowCount)
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseLog, @ProcessMessage, null, @Module, @Client
*/
	/****************************************************************************

		T H E   E N D
																		
	****************************************************************************/
	
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseEnd, @ProcName, null, @Module, @Client

END TRY

BEGIN CATCH 

	select @ErrNum = ERROR_NUMBER(), @ErrMsg = ERROR_MESSAGE(), @ErrSev = ERROR_SEVERITY(), @ErrLine = ERROR_LINE(), @ErrState = XACT_STATE()
	set @ErrMsg = REPLACE(@ErrMsg, '.', '') + ' (error no: ' + CAST(@ErrNum AS VARCHAR(10)) + ') on line ' + CAST(@ErrLine AS VARCHAR(10))
	
	-- Test XACT_STATE for 0, 1, or -1.
    -- If 1, the transaction is committable.
    -- If -1, the transaction is uncommittable and should be rolled back.
    -- If 0, there is no transaction and a commit or rollback operation would generate an error.

	if @ErrState = -1			-- Transaction is uncommitable
		rollback transaction

	if @ErrState = 1			
		commit transaction

	-- Error message line 1
	set @ErrMsgBrief = left(@ErrMsg,100)
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseError, @ErrMsgBrief, null, @Module, @Client
	
	-- Error message line 2 - if any text exists
	set @ErrMsgBrief = substring(@ErrMsg,101,100)
	if len(@ErrMsgBrief) > 0
		exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseError, @ErrMsgBrief, null, @Module, @Client

	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseEnd, @ProcName, null, @Module, @Client

	RAISERROR(@ErrMsg, @ErrSev , 1)

END CATCH

/****************************************************************************

			E N D															

****************************************************************************/

return @ErrNum


GO
/****** Object:  StoredProcedure [dbo].[owp_RecognitionSwiftONGOING_Backup20180719AG]    Script Date: 7/3/2026 3:44:25 PM ******/
SET ANSI_NULLS ON
GO
SET QUOTED_IDENTIFIER ON
GO
/*********************************************************************************************************

Program:		owp_RecognitionSwift					
Author:			Alan Groves
Date created:	11/04/2018
											
Description:
===========

This proc populates the new recognition table called "owt_Recognition" with "Value of New Business"
(VNB) points.

This proc handles all of the swift data which includes:
WEALTH - COB business i.e. pensions and investments
MORTGAGES
PROTECTION

Note: There is a separate proc that calculates the GI VNB points from the Paymentshield data.

The approach of this proc is to use the incremental PendingPaymentIDs from the overnight batch
to calculate the VNB points in a temporary table.

The temporary table is then merged with the permanent table to make the calculated (or
re-calculated values) permanent.

Terms
-----
BSC			- Business Service Charge.
MBF			- Mortgage Broker Fee.
OGS			- Ongoing Servicing.
BSC Rate	- 0.12% at the time of writing (24/04/2018). This could be changed by the business, but
				would also require some DEV work in OWS.
DF			- Discount Factor.
DA			- Distribution Allowance (the total amount paid out by the provider to Openwork)
AUM			- Assets Under Management. Basically the amount invested or the premium on investment
				cases.
Average AUM - Average amount invested annually which is equivalent to 6 months' premium.

THE CALCULATIONS
================

There are two potential parts: initial + ongoing (if ongoing applies). If BSC (applies to ongoing 
only) and MBF (applies to mortgages only) apply, then these are also included:

MORTGAGE
--------
Part 1: MBF column = (Advice Fee Amount X Broker Retention Rate) - (Advice Fee Amount X Mort FCA Rate)
Part 2: Initial column = (Proc Fee Amount X Mortgage Retention Rate) - (Proc Fee X Mort FCA Rate) 
Mortgage Points Total = Initial + MBF

PROTECTION
----------
= (DA X Protection Retention Rate) - (DA X Protection FCA Rate) 
Protection Points Total = Initial

WEALTH (COB i.e. pensions and investments)
------
Part 1: Initial column = (DA X Wealth Retention Rate) - (DA X Wealth FCA Rate)

Part 2:

****XXXX****

NOTE: Where the BSC rate is greater than the ongoing rate, then BSC gets ALL of the AVAILABLE 
ongoing.

****XXXX****

REGULAR - BSC applies:
Year 1 column = BSC Points + Non-BSC Points - FCA Points
Non-BSC Points = Ave AUM X (OGS Rate - BSC Rate) X COB Retention Rate
BSC Points = Ave AUM X BSC Rate
FCA Points = Ave AUM X OGS Rate X COB FCA Rate

REGULAR - Non-BSC: 
Year 1 column = (Ave AUM X OGS Rate X COB Retention Rate) - (Ave AUM X OGS Rate X COB FCA Rate)

SINGLE - BSC applies:
Year 1 column = (AUM X BSC Rate) + (AUM X (OGS Rate - BSC Rate) X COB Retention Rate) - (AUM X OGS Rate X COB FCA Rate) 

SINGLE - Non-BSC:
Year 1 column = (AUM X OGS Rate X COB Retention Rate) - (AUM X OGS Rate X COB FCA Rate) 

Then years 2 to 10 are calculated by applying a discount factor
Year  2 = Year 1 X  3 X DF
Year  3 = Year 1 X  5 X DF
Year  4 = Year 1 X  7 X DF
Year  5 = Year 1 X  9 X DF
Year  6 = Year 1 X 11 X DF
Year  7 = Year 1 X 13 X DF
Year  8 = Year 1 X 15 X DF
Year  9 = Year 1 X 17 X DF
Year 10 = Year 1 X 19 X DF

Wealth Points Total =	OngoingYr01 + OngoingYr02 + OngoingYr03 + OngoingYr04 + OngoingYr05 +
						OngoingYr06 + OngoingYr07 + OngoingYr08 + OngoingYr09 + OngoingYr10 +
						Initial

GI
--
See stored proc "owp_RecognitionGIPaymentshield".
 
Notes:
-----

1)	There is a BSC column on table owt_Recognition. However, BSC is already included in the ongoing
	years 1 - 10, so the BSC column does not need to be added in. In fact you will double count if 
	you attempt to do anything with it other than display it.

2)	Occasionally an investment case may receive two or more cheques which
	then go through Swift as two or more SINGLE investments on the SAME
	slice. Although the INITIAL VNB calculation will pro-rata correctly
	because it is based on the amount received, this scenario will cause
	ongoing VNB to be calculated on each of the payment records and so will 
	double count (or worse if there are more than two cheques received).
	Since de-coupling IC from ongoing i.e. they now have separate rows on
	table owt_Recognition, the issue of multiple cheques should no longer
	cause ongoing double counting.


This proc is called as follows:
	declare @rc int
	exec @rc = dbo.owp_RecognitionSwift 'Openwork', 'Recognition'
	select @rc

					
AMENDMENT HISTORY				
=================								

Date		Author		Description
----		------		-----------
26/04/2018	A Groves	Only include rows in the OGS lookups where the OngoingServiceFee > 0.0.
						Negative OGS rates are bad data and at the time of writing, there are
						39 of these.
27/04/2018	A Groves	Additional calculation and condition to handle the scenario where BSC applies
						but the OGS Rate is less than the BSC rate. Previously, this caused the
						total ongoing to be zero. However, there are two components to ongoing VNB 
						points, the BSC share and the non-BSC share. So the BSC share (which takes 
						100% when the OGS rate is less than 0.12%) should still yield ongoing points.
27/04/2018	A Groves	Single ongoing Yr01 corrected by applying outer brackets before signing the result.
03/05/2018	A Groves	Added update of column "msit_OpenworkAdviserListing.VNB_Points".
18/05/2018	A Groves	Changed mortgage calculation to use e.AMOUNT_REC instead of pt.CommInitialAmount
						as Marcus Cossey wanted the actual amount received to be used for the DA.
04/06/2018	A Groves	1) In the REGULAR section of column "OngoingYr01", the condition for cs.FrequencyCode <> 6
							was added to ensure the code differentiates to the SINGLE section.
						2) Exclude MBF from the OpenAccess table (msit_OpenworkAdviserListing) as this
							is shown on the MBF download and would otherwise incur MBF double counting.
05/06/2018	A Groves	1) Marcus Cossey advised that investments should get ongoing for years 1 to 6 and
							pensions for years 1 to 10. Previously, both lines of business got years 1 to 10.
						2) Marcus Cossey asked for split payments (i.e. where multiple cheques are processed
							for a SINGLE investment) to only claculate ongoing VNB on the oldest payment. 
11/06/2018	A Groves	1) PSD processed a protection clawback statement as fee type initial. These clawbacks
							all generated +ve instead of -ve VNB points. A tweak was added to ensure that the 
							absolute value of AMOUNT_REC is used to ensure the VNB is correctly signed. 
						2) Another unknown business rule has surfaced: Previously, only initial, clawbacks and
							adjustments on slices created new from 2017 were included. This rule only applies
							to initial. Clawbacks and adjustments can belong to a slice created at any point
							in the past. However, note that the payment (irrespective of whether it is +ve or 
							-ve), must not pre-date 2017.
13/06/2018	A Groves	Marcus asked for SellerCode and PaymentMatchedDate to be added so he need only use 
							the one table for both the adviser and enterprise leagues. PayBasisCode and 
							PayBasisDesc were also added at the same time as these are used in the calculations.
06/07/2018	A Groves	Replaced the OGS Rate lookup on the fly to using table dbo.owt_OngoingRate. This was 
							done to ensure the rate used at any point in time stays the same, so the onging VNB
							will always give the same result each time the calculation runs.
17/07/2018	A Groves	Marcus asked for the ongoing calculation to be based on the sum of premium across
							all the initial transactions where an initial fee has been paid.
*************************************************************************************************************/

CREATE PROCEDURE [dbo].[owp_RecognitionSwiftONGOING_Backup20180719AG]
	@Client		varchar(50),
	@Module		Varchar(50)

AS

set nocount on

declare		@PhaseStart				varchar(50),
			@PhaseEnd				varchar(50),
			@PhaseError				varchar(50),
			@PhaseLog				varchar(50),
			@ProcName				varchar(100),
			@ProcessMessage			varchar(100),
			@RowCount				int,
			@OALRowCount			int,
			@ErrMsg					nvarchar(4000),
			@ErrMsgBrief			nvarchar(100),
			@ErrNum					int,
			@ErrSev					int,
			@ErrLine				int,
			@ErrState				int,
			@DateLastUpdated		datetime,
			@OwlManager2Code		nvarchar(10)
			
/****************************************************************************

	Set initial parameters																
																		
****************************************************************************/

set @ProcName			= object_name(@@procid)
set @PhaseStart			= 'START'
set @PhaseEnd			= 'END'
set @PhaseError			= 'ERROR'
set @PhaseLog			= 'LOG'
set @ErrNum				= 0	
set @DateLastUpdated	= getdate()

set @OwlManager2Code = (select cde.Code from msit_MIWarehouseCodesAndDescriptions cde
			where cde.ColumnName = 'Manager2Code' and cde.Description = 'Owl Financial')

-- We want this logging irrespective of whether or not there is a rollback
exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseStart, @ProcName, null, @Module, @Client

/****************************************************************************

	Populate the table																
																		
****************************************************************************/

SET XACT_ABORT ON	-- Needed if XACT_STATE() function is used.

BEGIN TRY

	/****************************************************************************

		Calculate VNB and populate the temporary table with the results
		
		Note that there are oddities like LV protection payments which always
		come in pairs with one large and one much smaller amount (e.g. TransactionID 
		= 6684787.) The system treats both payments in the pair as first payments 
		and the (projected) DA associated with both is the same (because it's on 
		the policy transaction). 
		
		There is also a requirement to front-load VNB points on accrual and level
		payments. This means calculate the VNB for the full amount of the DA and 
		put it on the first payment record and then on all subsequent accrual and 
		level payments, set the VNB to zero.
		
		Thus two different sources of DA are used depending on whether we need the
		full DA amount for accruals and level or the actual amount received for all
		other scenarios including the LV split payment scenario. The two sources are:
		
		mstt_PolicyTransactions.CommInitialAmount - Full (projected) DA amount
		
		mstt_Expectation.AMOUNT_REC - The DA actually received. This handles the
										LV scenario whereby the AMOUNT_REC is 
										proportioned across the two payments received.   
																		
	****************************************************************************/

	select	top 0 
			*, 
			convert(int,NULL) as CommissionYear
	into	#AG_owt_Recognition_SEPARATE_ONGOING
	from	AG_owt_Recognition_SEPARATE_ONGOING

	/****************************************************************************

		Phase 1 - Process all but regular accrual cases with clawbacks/adjustments
		Accruals are front loaded unless their latest payment is a clawback/adjudtment
		in which case they accrue VNB points on a per payment basis and so these
		are dealt with in Phases 2 and 3.
																		
	****************************************************************************/

	insert into #AG_owt_Recognition_SEPARATE_ONGOING
	(
		SourceID,
		CaseID,
		TransactionID,
		Policy,
		ProductCode,
		BusinessCode,
		SellerCode,						--AG 13/06/2018
		PointsTotal,
		BSC,
		MBF,
		Initial,
		OngoingTotal,
		OngoingYr01,
		OngoingYr02,
		OngoingYr03,
		OngoingYr04,
		OngoingYr05,
		OngoingYr06,
		OngoingYr07,
		OngoingYr08,
		OngoingYr09,
		OngoingYr10,
		FCARate,
		RetentionRate,
		RetentionRateBroker,
		OngoingServicingRate,
		OngoingServicingSource,
		DA,
		AmountReceived,
		Premium,
		AgentSplit,
		CommissionType,
		CommissionTypeDesc,
		PayBasisCode,					--AG 13/06/2018
		PayBasisDesc,					--AG 13/06/2018
		PaymentMatchedDate,				--AG 13/06/2018
		Month,
		FrequencyCode,
		FrequencyDesc,
		ReassignedProductGroupCode,		--AG 05/06/2018
		ReassignedProductGroupName,		--AG 05/06/2018
		RecognitionType,
		CalculationType,
		Source,
		DateInserted,
		DateLastUpdated,
		CommissionYear
	)
	select	cs.PendingPaymentID as SourceID,
			cs.CaseID,
			cs.TransactionID,
			cs.ExtPolicyNumber as Policy,
			cs.ProductCode,
			cs.BusinessCode,
			cs.AgentCode as SellerCode,				--AG 13/06/2018
			0.0 as PointsTotal,
			0.0 as BSC,
			case 
				when mbf.MortgageFeeID is not null and cs.INIssued <> 0 then (((mbf.AdviceFeeAmount)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * MRbkr.FACTOR) - ((mbf.AdviceFeeAmount)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * Mfca.FACTOR)) --Note that mbf.AdviceFeeAmount is signed correctly - so no coding for signing is needed here
				else 0.0
			end as MBF,
			case 
				--When the adviser has changed, the AgentSplit can become zero in which case the ELITE points should be zero.
				when cs.AgentSplit = 0 then 0
				
				--WEALTH CALCULATION START
				--Indemnity payments or SINGLEs or IC Clawbacks or IC adjustments Start
				when (ph.ProductCategoryCode = 1 or pcc.KeyValue2 = '1') and (cs.FrequencyCode = 6 or cs.PayBasisCode in ('T') or cs.CommissionType in (2,17)) and cs.commissiontype in (1,2,17) and cs.INIssued <> 0 then (((e.AMOUNT_REC)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * Crate.FACTOR) - ((e.AMOUNT_REC)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * Cfca.FACTOR)) * case when cs.INIssued < 0 then -1 else 1 end
				--Indemnity payments or SINGLEs or IC Clawbacks or IC adjustments End
				--Accruals & Level Start
				when (ph.ProductCategoryCode = 1 or pcc.KeyValue2 = '1') and cs.INIssued <> 0 then (((pt.CommInitialAmount)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * Crate.FACTOR) - ((pt.CommInitialAmount)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * Cfca.FACTOR)) * case when cs.INIssued < 0 then -1 else 1 end
				--Accruals & Level End
				--WEALTH CALCULATION END
				
				--MORTGAGE CALCULATION START
				--Note: The MBF component has its own table column
				--Only 1 payment for mortgages
				when ph.ProductGroupCode = 3 and cs.INIssued <> 0 then (((e.AMOUNT_REC)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * MRproc.FACTOR) - ((e.AMOUNT_REC)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * Mfca.FACTOR)) * case when cs.INIssued < 0 then -1 else 1 end	--AG 18/05/2018
				--MORTGAGE CALCULATION END
				
				--PROTECTION CALCULATION START
				--Indemnity payments or SINGLEs or IC Clawbacks or IC adjustments Start
				when ph.ProductGroupCode = 6 and (cs.FrequencyCode = 6 or cs.PayBasisCode in ('T') or cs.CommissionType in (2,17)) and cs.commissiontype in (1,2,17) and cs.INIssued <> 0 then ((abs(e.AMOUNT_REC)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * Prate.FACTOR) - (abs(e.AMOUNT_REC)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * Pfca.FACTOR)) * case when cs.INIssued < 0 then -1 else 1 end	--AG 11/06/2018 (1)
				--Indemnity payments or SINGLEs or IC Clawbacks or IC adjustments End
				--Accruals & Level Start
				when ph.ProductGroupCode = 6 and cs.INIssued <> 0 then (((pt.CommInitialAmount)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * Prate.FACTOR) - ((pt.CommInitialAmount)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * Pfca.FACTOR)) * case when cs.INIssued < 0 then -1 else 1 end
				--Accruals & Level End
				--PROTECTION CALCULATION END

				else 0.0

			end as Initial,
			0.0 as OngoingTotal,
			0.0 as OngoingYr01,
			0.0 as OngoingYr02,
			0.0 as OngoingYr03,
			0.0 as OngoingYr04,
			0.0 as OngoingYr05,
			0.0 as OngoingYr06,
			0.0 as OngoingYr07,
			0.0 as OngoingYr08,
			0.0 as OngoingYr09,
			0.0 as OngoingYr10,
			case 
				when (ph.ProductCategoryCode = 1 or pcc.KeyValue2 = '1') then Cfca.FACTOR*100.0		--COB
				when ph.ProductGroupCode = 3 then Mfca.FACTOR*100.0		--MORT
				when ph.ProductGroupCode = 6 then Pfca.FACTOR*100.0		--PROT
				else 0.0
			end as FCARate,
			case 
				when (ph.ProductCategoryCode = 1 or pcc.KeyValue2 = '1') then Crate.FACTOR*100.0	--COB
				when ph.ProductGroupCode = 3 then MRproc.FACTOR*100.0	--MORT
				when ph.ProductGroupCode = 6 then Prate.FACTOR*100.0	--PROT
				else 0.0
			end as RetentionRate,
			case 
				when mbf.MortgageFeeID is not null then  MRbkr.FACTOR*100.0	
				else 0.0
			end as RetentionRateBroker,
			null as OngoingServicingRate,
			null as OngoingServicingSource,
			pt.CommInitialAmount as DA,
			e.AMOUNT_REC as AmountReceived,
			cs.Premium,
			cs.AgentSplit,
			cs.CommissionType,
			left(cs.StandingOrderDesc,50) as CommissionTypeDesc,
			cs.PayBasisCode,							--AG 13/06/2018
			cs.PayBasisDesc,							--AG 13/06/2018
			cs.CreateDate as PaymentMatchedDate,		--AG 13/06/2018
			cs.Month,
			cs.FrequencyCode,
			cs.FrequencyDesc,
			pg.ProductGroupCode as ReassignedProductGroupCode,	--Force the re-assigned products...		AG 05/06/2018
			pg.ProductGroupName as ReassignedProductGroupName,	--...to be processed as investments		AG 05/06/2018
			'VNB-INI-PHASE-1' as RecognitionType,
			case 
				when (ph.ProductCategoryCode = 1 or pcc.KeyValue2 = '1') then 'WEALTH-INITIAL'
				when ph.ProductGroupCode = 3 then 'MORTGAGE'
				when ph.ProductGroupCode = 6 then 'PROTECTION'
				else null
			end as CalculationType,
			'Openwork 2006' as Source,
			@DateLastUpdated as DateInserted,
			@DateLastUpdated as DateLastUpdated,
			csp.year as CommissionYear
	--select count(*)
	from	msit_CommissionStatement cs
/*			inner join (select	distinct PKID
						from	owt_TransformationMovements tm 
						where	tm.DriverTableName = 'sa_swift_S_AGMFIL'
						and		tm.CommissionStatement = 'Y') tm on tm.PKID = cs.PendingPaymentID
*/			inner join mstt_Agents ag on ag.Code = cs.BusinessCode
			inner join mstt_PolicyTransactions pt on pt.ID = cs.TransactionID
			inner join mstt_Policies p on p.POL_NUM = pt.PolicyID
			inner join msit_CommissionStatementPeriods VNBStart on convert(date,pt.CreateDateTime) between VNBStart.PeriodStartDate and VNBStart.PeriodEndDate
			inner join msit_Commissionstatementperiods csp on csp.month = cs.month
			inner join mstt_ProductHierarchy ph on ph.productcode = cs.productcode
			inner join mstt_Expectation e on e.ID = cs.ExpectationID
			left join dbo.owt_MortgageBrokerFees mbf on mbf.PendingPaymentID = cs.PendingPaymentID and mbf.AdviceFeeCharged = 'Yes'
			left join owt_SelectionControl SC
						on SC.Process = 'ElitePoints' 
						and SC.KeyType = 'NSCPotCode' 
						and cs.CreateDate between SC.EffectiveStartDate and SC.EffectiveEndDate
			left join mstt_Commissions BSCpot
						on BSCpot.TransactionID = cs.TransactionID 
						and BSCpot.Agent_Code = sc.KeyValue
						and BSCpot.CommissionType = 10
			left join owt_SelectionControl SFMPC						
						on SFMPC.Process = 'ElitePoints' 
						and SFMPC.KeyType = 'ServicingFeeMarginPotCode' 
						and cs.CreateDate between SFMPC.EffectiveStartDate and SFMPC.EffectiveEndDate
			left join mstt_Commissions SFMpot							
						on SFMpot.TransactionID = cs.TransactionID 
						and SFMpot.Agent_Code = SFMPC.KeyValue
						and SFMpot.CommissionType = 10	
			left join owt_SelectionControl pcc 
						on pcc.Process = 'ElitePoints'
						and pcc.KeyType = 'ProductCategoryCode'
						and pcc.KeyValue = cs.ProductCode	
						and cs.CreateDate between pcc.EffectiveStartDate and pcc.EffectiveEndDate
			left join owt_SelectionControl ogsdflt 
						on ogsdflt.Process = 'ElitePoints'
						and ogsdflt.KeyType = 'DefaultOngoingServicingRate'
						and ogsdflt.SelectionType = 'VNB'
						and ogsdflt.KeyValue = case when ph.RDRType = 'ONPLAT' then 'ONPLAT' else 'OFPLAT' end
						and cs.CreateDate between ogsdflt.EffectiveStartDate and ogsdflt.EffectiveEndDate
			left join mstt_CodeProductGroup pg on pg.ProductGroupCode = case when pcc.KeyValue2 = '1' then 2 else ph.ProductGroupCode end
			left join owt_EliteFactors Cfca on Cfca.FeeType = 'VNB' and Cfca.category = 'COB-FCA-RATE' and csp.year between Cfca.StartYear and Cfca.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors Crate on Crate.FeeType = 'VNB' and Crate.category = 'COB-RETENTION-RATE' and csp.year between Crate.StartYear and Crate.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors Mfca on Mfca.FeeType = 'VNB' and Mfca.category = 'MORT-FCA-RATE' and csp.year between Mfca.StartYear and Mfca.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors MRproc on MRproc.FeeType = 'VNB' and MRproc.category = 'MORT-RETENTION-RATE-PROC' and csp.year between MRproc.StartYear and MRproc.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors MRbkr on MRbkr.FeeType = 'VNB' and MRbkr.category = 'MORT-RETENTION-RATE-BROKER' and csp.year between MRbkr.StartYear and MRbkr.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors Pfca on Pfca.FeeType = 'VNB' and Pfca.category = 'PROT-FCA-RATE' and csp.year between Pfca.StartYear and Pfca.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors Prate on Prate.FeeType = 'VNB' and Prate.category = 'PROT-RETENTION-RATE' and csp.year between Prate.StartYear and Prate.EndYear 
			left join msit_CommissionStatement csadj 
						on csadj.TransactionID = cs.TransactionID 
						and csadj.AgentCode = cs.AgentCode 
						and csadj.CommissionType in (2,17)
						and	csadj.PayBasisCode in ('F')				--Accrual
						and	csadj.FrequencyCode <> 6				--Regular 
	where	cs.ReportingClassCode = 1
	and		ag.Manager2Code <> @OwlManager2Code		--Exclude Owl
	and		cs.INIssued <> 0
	and		csp.Year >= 2017						--Ensure in-scope payments are consistent with VNB start
	and		VNBStart.Year >= 2017
	and		cs.CommissionType in (1,2,17)
	and		abs(e.AMOUNT_REC) >= 0.01	
	--and		((VNBStart.Year >= 2017 and cs.CommissionType = 1 and e.AMOUNT_REC >= 0.01)		--VNB to start from new slices in 2017 for +ve payments but...			AG 11/06/2018 (2)
	--		or (cs.CommissionType in (2,17) or e.AMOUNT_REC <= -0.01))						--...for -ve payments, the slice can start from any date in the past	AG 11/06/2018 (2)
	and		csadj.ID is null						--Deal with accrual regular clawbacks/adjustments later

	select @RowCount = @@rowcount
	set @ProcessMessage = '#owt_Recognition (ini ph1 - no accr adj) = ' + convert(nvarchar(10), @RowCount)
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseLog, @ProcessMessage, null, @Module, @Client

	/****************************************************************************

		Now deal with accrual clawbacks and adjustments
																		
	****************************************************************************/

	--drop table #msit_CommissionStatementSUMMARY

	--Find transactions with clawbacks/adj on them
	select	cs.TransactionID,
			cs.AgentCode,
			Min(case when cs.CommissionType = 1 then cs.PendingPaymentID else null end) as MinInitialPendingPaymentID,
			MAX(case when cs.CommissionType = 1 then cs.PendingPaymentID else null end) as MaxInitialPendingPaymentID,
			MAX(case when cs.CommissionType in (2,17) then cs.PendingPaymentID else null end) as MaxAdjPendingPaymentID,
			null as MinInitialAfterAdjPendingPaymentID
	into	#msit_CommissionStatementSUMMARY
	from	msit_CommissionStatement cs
			inner join mstt_Agents ag on ag.Code = cs.BusinessCode
			inner join mstt_PolicyTransactions pt on pt.ID = cs.TransactionID
			inner join mstt_Policies p on p.POL_NUM = pt.PolicyID
			inner join msit_CommissionStatementPeriods VNBStart on convert(date,pt.CreateDateTime) between VNBStart.PeriodStartDate and VNBStart.PeriodEndDate
			inner join msit_Commissionstatementperiods csp on csp.month = cs.month
			inner join mstt_Expectation e on e.ID = cs.ExpectationID
			left join msit_CommissionStatement csadj 
						on csadj.TransactionID = cs.TransactionID 
						and csadj.AgentCode = cs.AgentCode 
						and csadj.CommissionType in (2,17)
						and	csadj.PayBasisCode in ('F')				--Accrual
						and	csadj.FrequencyCode <> 6				--Regular 
	where	cs.ReportingClassCode = 1
	and		cs.CommissionType in (1,2,17)			--We want all the initial payment types (i.e. not trail (ongoing))
	and		ag.Manager2Code <> @OwlManager2Code		--Exclude Owl
	and		csp.Year >= 2017						--Ensure in-scope payments are consistent with VNB start
	and		VNBStart.Year >= 2017 
	and		abs(e.AMOUNT_REC) >= 0.01	
	and		csadj.ID is not null					--select regular accrual transactions with clawbacks/adjustments
	--and cs.TransactionID in (5613333,6296827)
	group by	cs.TransactionID,
				cs.AgentCode

	select @RowCount = @@rowcount
	set @ProcessMessage = '#msit_CommissionStatementSUMMARY (accr adj txns) = ' + convert(nvarchar(10), @RowCount)
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseLog, @ProcessMessage, null, @Module, @Client

	--Get first initial payment after last clawback/adj
	update css
		set MinInitialAfterAdjPendingPaymentID = summ.MinPendingPaymentID 
	from  #msit_CommissionStatementSUMMARY css
			inner join  (
						select cssinner.TransactionID, cssinner.AgentCode, min(cs.PendingPaymentID) as MinPendingPaymentID
						from #msit_CommissionStatementSUMMARY cssinner
								inner join msit_CommissionStatement cs
											on cs.TransactionID = cssinner.TransactionID
											and cs.AgentCode = cssinner.AgentCode
						where cs.PendingPaymentID > cssinner.MaxAdjPendingPaymentID
						group by cssinner.TransactionID, cssinner.AgentCode
						) summ on  summ.TransactionID = css.TransactionID
							   and summ.AgentCode = css.AgentCode

	select @RowCount = @@rowcount
	set @ProcessMessage = '#msit_CommissionStatementSUMMARY (1st IC after adj) = ' + convert(nvarchar(10), @RowCount)
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseLog, @ProcessMessage, null, @Module, @Client

	/****************************************************************************

		Phase 2 - This phase deals with regular accrual cases where there is at 
		least one clawback/adjustment. In this scenario the VNB is changed from 
		front loaded to a per payment basis.
																		
	****************************************************************************/

	insert into #AG_owt_Recognition_SEPARATE_ONGOING
	(
		SourceID,
		CaseID,
		TransactionID,
		Policy,
		ProductCode,
		BusinessCode,
		SellerCode,						
		PointsTotal,
		BSC,
		MBF,
		Initial,
		OngoingTotal,
		OngoingYr01,
		OngoingYr02,
		OngoingYr03,
		OngoingYr04,
		OngoingYr05,
		OngoingYr06,
		OngoingYr07,
		OngoingYr08,
		OngoingYr09,
		OngoingYr10,
		FCARate,
		RetentionRate,
		RetentionRateBroker,
		OngoingServicingRate,
		OngoingServicingSource,
		DA,
		AmountReceived,
		Premium,
		AgentSplit,
		CommissionType,
		CommissionTypeDesc,
		PayBasisCode,					
		PayBasisDesc,					
		PaymentMatchedDate,				
		Month,
		FrequencyCode,
		FrequencyDesc,
		ReassignedProductGroupCode,		
		ReassignedProductGroupName,		
		RecognitionType,
		CalculationType,
		Source,
		DateInserted,
		DateLastUpdated,
		CommissionYear
	)
	select	cs.PendingPaymentID as SourceID,
			cs.CaseID,
			cs.TransactionID,
			cs.ExtPolicyNumber as Policy,
			cs.ProductCode,
			cs.BusinessCode,
			cs.AgentCode as SellerCode,				
			0.0 as PointsTotal,
			0.0 as BSC,
			case 
				when mbf.MortgageFeeID is not null and cs.INIssued <> 0 then (((mbf.AdviceFeeAmount)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * MRbkr.FACTOR) - ((mbf.AdviceFeeAmount)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * Mfca.FACTOR)) --Note that mbf.AdviceFeeAmount is signed correctly - so no coding for signing is needed here
				else 0.0
			end as MBF,
			case 
				--When the adviser has changed, the AgentSplit can become zero in which case the ELITE points should be zero.
				when cs.AgentSplit = 0 then 0
				
				--WEALTH CALCULATION START
				--Indemnity payments or SINGLEs or IC Clawbacks or IC adjustments Start
				--THIS SCENARIO DOESN'T OCCUR IN PHASE 2
				--Indemnity payments or SINGLEs or IC Clawbacks or IC adjustments End
				--Accruals & Level Start
				when (ph.ProductCategoryCode = 1 or pcc.KeyValue2 = '1') then (((e.AMOUNT_REC)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * Crate.FACTOR) - ((e.AMOUNT_REC)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * Cfca.FACTOR)) * case when cs.CommissionType in (2,17) then -1 else 1 end
				--Accruals & Level End
				--WEALTH CALCULATION END
				
				--MORTGAGE CALCULATION START
				--Note: The MBF component has its own table column
				--Only 1 payment for mortgages
				when ph.ProductGroupCode = 3 then (((e.AMOUNT_REC)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * MRproc.FACTOR) - ((e.AMOUNT_REC)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * Mfca.FACTOR)) * case when cs.CommissionType in (2,17) then -1 else 1 end	
				--MORTGAGE CALCULATION END
				
				--PROTECTION CALCULATION START
				--Indemnity payments or SINGLEs or IC Clawbacks or IC adjustments Start
				--THIS SCENARIO DOESN'T OCCUR IN PHASE 2
				--Indemnity payments or SINGLEs or IC Clawbacks or IC adjustments End
				--Accruals & Level Start
				when ph.ProductGroupCode = 6 then (((e.AMOUNT_REC)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * Prate.FACTOR) - ((e.AMOUNT_REC)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * Pfca.FACTOR)) * case when cs.CommissionType in (2,17) then -1 else 1 end
				--Accruals & Level End
				--PROTECTION CALCULATION END

				else 0.0

			end as Initial,
			0.0 as OngoingTotal,
			0.0 as OngoingYr01,
			0.0 as OngoingYr02,
			0.0 as OngoingYr03,
			0.0 as OngoingYr04,
			0.0 as OngoingYr05,
			0.0 as OngoingYr06,
			0.0 as OngoingYr07,
			0.0 as OngoingYr08,
			0.0 as OngoingYr09,
			0.0 as OngoingYr10,
			case 
				when (ph.ProductCategoryCode = 1 or pcc.KeyValue2 = '1') then Cfca.FACTOR*100.0		--COB
				when ph.ProductGroupCode = 3 then Mfca.FACTOR*100.0		--MORT
				when ph.ProductGroupCode = 6 then Pfca.FACTOR*100.0		--PROT
				else 0.0
			end as FCARate,
			case 
				when (ph.ProductCategoryCode = 1 or pcc.KeyValue2 = '1') then Crate.FACTOR*100.0	--COB
				when ph.ProductGroupCode = 3 then MRproc.FACTOR*100.0	--MORT
				when ph.ProductGroupCode = 6 then Prate.FACTOR*100.0	--PROT
				else 0.0
			end as RetentionRate,
			case 
				when mbf.MortgageFeeID is not null then  MRbkr.FACTOR*100.0	
				else 0.0
			end as RetentionRateBroker,
			null as OngoingServicingRate,
			null as OngoingServicingSource,
			pt.CommInitialAmount as DA,
			e.AMOUNT_REC as AmountReceived,
			cs.Premium,
			cs.AgentSplit,
			cs.CommissionType,
			left(cs.StandingOrderDesc,50) as CommissionTypeDesc,
			cs.PayBasisCode,							
			cs.PayBasisDesc,							
			cs.CreateDate as PaymentMatchedDate,		
			cs.Month,
			cs.FrequencyCode,
			cs.FrequencyDesc,
			pg.ProductGroupCode as ReassignedProductGroupCode,	--Force the re-assigned products...		
			pg.ProductGroupName as ReassignedProductGroupName,	--...to be processed as investments		
			'VNB-INI-PHASE-2' as RecognitionType,
			case 
				when (ph.ProductCategoryCode = 1 or pcc.KeyValue2 = '1') then 'WEALTH-INITIAL'
				when ph.ProductGroupCode = 3 then 'MORTGAGE'
				when ph.ProductGroupCode = 6 then 'PROTECTION'
				else null
			end as CalculationType,
			'Openwork 2006' as Source,
			@DateLastUpdated as DateInserted,
			@DateLastUpdated as DateLastUpdated,
			csp.year as CommissionYear
	from	#msit_CommissionStatementSUMMARY css
			inner join msit_CommissionStatement cs
						on cs.TransactionID = css.TransactionID
						and cs.AgentCode = css.AgentCode
			inner join mstt_Agents ag on ag.Code = cs.BusinessCode
			inner join mstt_PolicyTransactions pt on pt.ID = cs.TransactionID
			inner join mstt_Policies p on p.POL_NUM = pt.PolicyID
			inner join msit_CommissionStatementPeriods VNBStart on convert(date,pt.CreateDateTime) between VNBStart.PeriodStartDate and VNBStart.PeriodEndDate
			inner join msit_Commissionstatementperiods csp on csp.month = cs.month
			inner join mstt_ProductHierarchy ph on ph.productcode = cs.productcode
			inner join mstt_Expectation e on e.ID = cs.ExpectationID
			left join dbo.owt_MortgageBrokerFees mbf on mbf.PendingPaymentID = cs.PendingPaymentID and mbf.AdviceFeeCharged = 'Yes'
			left join owt_SelectionControl SC
						on SC.Process = 'ElitePoints' 
						and SC.KeyType = 'NSCPotCode' 
						and cs.CreateDate between SC.EffectiveStartDate and SC.EffectiveEndDate
			left join mstt_Commissions BSCpot
						on BSCpot.TransactionID = cs.TransactionID 
						and BSCpot.Agent_Code = sc.KeyValue
						and BSCpot.CommissionType = 10
			left join owt_SelectionControl SFMPC						
						on SFMPC.Process = 'ElitePoints' 
						and SFMPC.KeyType = 'ServicingFeeMarginPotCode' 
						and cs.CreateDate between SFMPC.EffectiveStartDate and SFMPC.EffectiveEndDate
			left join mstt_Commissions SFMpot							
						on SFMpot.TransactionID = cs.TransactionID 
						and SFMpot.Agent_Code = SFMPC.KeyValue
						and SFMpot.CommissionType = 10	
			left join owt_SelectionControl pcc 
						on pcc.Process = 'ElitePoints'
						and pcc.KeyType = 'ProductCategoryCode'
						and pcc.KeyValue = cs.ProductCode	
						and cs.CreateDate between pcc.EffectiveStartDate and pcc.EffectiveEndDate
			left join owt_SelectionControl ogsdflt 
						on ogsdflt.Process = 'ElitePoints'
						and ogsdflt.KeyType = 'DefaultOngoingServicingRate'
						and ogsdflt.SelectionType = 'VNB'
						and ogsdflt.KeyValue = case when ph.RDRType = 'ONPLAT' then 'ONPLAT' else 'OFPLAT' end
						and cs.CreateDate between ogsdflt.EffectiveStartDate and ogsdflt.EffectiveEndDate
			left join mstt_CodeProductGroup pg on pg.ProductGroupCode = case when pcc.KeyValue2 = '1' then 2 else ph.ProductGroupCode end
			left join owt_EliteFactors Cfca on Cfca.FeeType = 'VNB' and Cfca.category = 'COB-FCA-RATE' and csp.year between Cfca.StartYear and Cfca.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors Crate on Crate.FeeType = 'VNB' and Crate.category = 'COB-RETENTION-RATE' and csp.year between Crate.StartYear and Crate.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors Mfca on Mfca.FeeType = 'VNB' and Mfca.category = 'MORT-FCA-RATE' and csp.year between Mfca.StartYear and Mfca.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors MRproc on MRproc.FeeType = 'VNB' and MRproc.category = 'MORT-RETENTION-RATE-PROC' and csp.year between MRproc.StartYear and MRproc.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors MRbkr on MRbkr.FeeType = 'VNB' and MRbkr.category = 'MORT-RETENTION-RATE-BROKER' and csp.year between MRbkr.StartYear and MRbkr.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors Pfca on Pfca.FeeType = 'VNB' and Pfca.category = 'PROT-FCA-RATE' and csp.year between Pfca.StartYear and Pfca.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors Prate on Prate.FeeType = 'VNB' and Prate.category = 'PROT-RETENTION-RATE' and csp.year between Prate.StartYear and Prate.EndYear 
	where	cs.ReportingClassCode = 1
	and		cs.CommissionType in (1,2,17)			--We want all the initial payment types (i.e. not trail (ongoing))
	and		ag.Manager2Code <> @OwlManager2Code		--Exclude Owl

	select @RowCount = @@rowcount
	set @ProcessMessage = '#owt_Recognition (ini ph2 - accr adj) = ' + convert(nvarchar(10), @RowCount)
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseLog, @ProcessMessage, null, @Module, @Client

	/****************************************************************************

		Initial Phase 3
		1) Add up the +ves and -ves prior to the NEW front loaded amount and
			net them off on the first +ve following the last -ve
		2) Now set all the +ves following the one updated in (1) to zero.
																
	****************************************************************************/

	update r
		set RecognitionType	= case when r.SourceID >= css.MinInitialAfterAdjPendingPaymentID 
								then 'VNB-INI-PHASE-3'
								else r.RecognitionType
							  end,
			Initial = case  when r.SourceID = css.MinInitialAfterAdjPendingPaymentID 
								then (((r.DA)*(r.AgentSplit/100) * (r.RetentionRate/100.0)) - ((r.DA)*(r.AgentSplit/100) * (r.FCARate/100))) - derived.SumInitial
							when r.SourceID > css.MinInitialAfterAdjPendingPaymentID 
								then 0.0
							else r.Initial
					  end,
			DateLastUpdated = @DateLastUpdated
	from	#msit_CommissionStatementSUMMARY css
			inner join #AG_owt_Recognition_SEPARATE_ONGOING r
						on r.TransactionID = css.TransactionID
						and r.SellerCode = css.AgentCode
			inner join (select	r.TransactionID, r.SellerCode, SUM(Initial) as SumInitial
						from	#msit_CommissionStatementSUMMARY s
								inner join #AG_owt_Recognition_SEPARATE_ONGOING r 
											on r.TransactionID = s.TransactionID
											and r.SellerCode = s.AgentCode
						where	r.SourceID <= s.MaxAdjPendingPaymentID
						group	by r.TransactionID, r.SellerCode
						) derived 
							on  derived.TransactionID = r.TransactionID
							and	derived.SellerCode = r.SellerCode 
	where	isnull(css.MaxInitialPendingPaymentID,0) > isnull(css.MaxAdjPendingPaymentID,0)-- An initial payment follows the clawback, so time to revert back to front loading

	select @RowCount = @@rowcount
	set @ProcessMessage = '#owt_Recognition (ini ph3 - accr adj) = ' + convert(nvarchar(10), @RowCount)
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseLog, @ProcessMessage, null, @Module, @Client

	/****************************************************************************

		Now do the ongoing.
		
		Build an ongoing summary row for each transaction (slice).
		
		Note we do not care about ongoing clawbacks and adjustments for VNB.
		We want VNB to be on the oldest positive payment on each slice for the
		policy (split by adviser if needed).
						
	****************************************************************************/

	select	cs.TransactionID,
			cs.AgentCode,
			c.AGENT_PERC as AgentSplit,
			min(case when cs.CommissionType = 10 then cs.PendingPaymentID else null end) as MinOngoingPendingPaymentID,
			max(case when cs.CommissionType = 10 then cs.PendingPaymentID else null end) as MaxOngoingPendingPaymentID,
			max(case when cs.CommissionType in (16,19) then cs.PendingPaymentID else null end) as MaxOngoingAdjPendingPaymentID,
			null as MinOngoingAfterAdjPendingPaymentID,
			cs.Premium,			--AG 17/07/2018
			cs.FrequencyCode,	--AG 17/07/2018
			cs.FrequencyDesc	--AG 17/07/2018
	into	#msit_CommissionStatementOGSSUMMARY
	from 	msit_CommissionStatement cs
			inner join mstt_Commissions c
						on c.TransactionID = cs.TransactionID
						and c.Agent_Code = cs.AgentCode
						and c.CommissionType = 1
			inner join mstt_Agents ag on ag.Code = cs.BusinessCode
			inner join mstt_PolicyTransactions pt on pt.ID = cs.TransactionID
			inner join mstt_Policies p on p.POL_NUM = pt.PolicyID
			inner join msit_CommissionStatementPeriods VNBStart on convert(date,pt.CreateDateTime) between VNBStart.PeriodStartDate and VNBStart.PeriodEndDate
			inner join msit_Commissionstatementperiods csp on csp.month = cs.month
			inner join mstt_ProductHierarchy ph on ph.productcode = cs.productcode
			inner join mstt_Expectation e on e.ID = cs.ExpectationID
			left join owt_SelectionControl pcc 
						on pcc.Process = 'ElitePoints'
						and pcc.KeyType = 'ProductCategoryCode'
						and pcc.KeyValue = cs.ProductCode	
						and cs.CreateDate between pcc.EffectiveStartDate and pcc.EffectiveEndDate
	where	cs.ReportingClassCode = 1
	and		cs.CommissionType in (10,16,19)					--Choose only where the ongoing payment is positive
	and		cs.CommFeeType = 'Ongoing'
	and		(ph.ProductCategoryCode = 1 or pcc.KeyValue2 = '1')
	and		ag.Manager2Code <> @OwlManager2Code		--Exclude Owl
	and		csp.Year >= 2017						--Ensure in-scope payments are consistent with VNB start
	and		VNBStart.Year >= 2017 
	and		abs(e.AMOUNT_REC) >= 0.01
	and		((cs.FrequencyCode = 6 and cs.Premium > 1.00)		--Frequency=6->Single
			or (cs.FrequencyCode <> 6 and cs.Premium > 0.01))	--Frequency<>6->Regular	
	group by	cs.TransactionID,
				cs.AgentCode,
				c.Agent_Perc,
				cs.Premium,			--AG 17/07/2018
				cs.FrequencyCode,	--AG 17/07/2018
				cs.FrequencyDesc	--AG 17/07/2018

	select @RowCount = @@rowcount
	set @ProcessMessage = '#msit_CommissionStatementOGSSUMMARY (ogs txn) = ' + convert(nvarchar(10), @RowCount)
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseLog, @ProcessMessage, null, @Module, @Client

	--Get first ongoing payment after last clawback/adj
	update cso
		set MinOngoingAfterAdjPendingPaymentID = summ.MinPendingPaymentID 
	from  #msit_CommissionStatementOGSSUMMARY cso
			inner join  (
						select	csoinner.TransactionID, csoinner.AgentCode, min(cs.PendingPaymentID) as MinPendingPaymentID
						from	#msit_CommissionStatementOGSSUMMARY csoinner
								inner join msit_CommissionStatement cs
											on cs.TransactionID = csoinner.TransactionID
											and cs.AgentCode = csoinner.AgentCode
						where	cs.PendingPaymentID > csoinner.MaxOngoingAdjPendingPaymentID
						and		cs.CommissionType = 10
						group by csoinner.TransactionID, csoinner.AgentCode
						) summ on  summ.TransactionID = cso.TransactionID
							   and summ.AgentCode = cso.AgentCode

	select @RowCount = @@rowcount
	set @ProcessMessage = '#msit_CommissionStatementOGSSUMMARY (ogs latest +ve) = ' + convert(nvarchar(10), @RowCount)
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseLog, @ProcessMessage, null, @Module, @Client

	/****************************************************************************
		
		Using the OGS SUMMARY table, get all the individual payment records that
		will be carriers of VNB points as follows:
		
		SelectionSource 1 - The oldest +ve payment where no clawbacks or 
								adjustments occur for front loading

		SelectionSource 2 - All the +ve payments that will get a spread of the 
								per payment +ve points 		

		SelectionSource 3 - All the -ve payments that will get a spread of the 
								per payment -ve points
								 															
	****************************************************************************/
	
	--AG 17/07/2018
	--Combine the premium on all the transactions (slices) for each case and seller
	--In case of mixed frequencies, force the sum to be a single
	select	CaseID,
			SellerCode,
			sum(case when FrequencyCode = 2 then Premium * 12.0 * (AgentSplit/100) else Premium * (AgentSplit/100) end) as SumOfPremium,
			convert(tinyint,6) as FrequencyCode			--single
	into	#OngoingPremiumTotal
	from	#AG_owt_Recognition_SEPARATE_ONGOING
	where	CalculationType = 'WEALTH-INITIAL'
	group	by CaseID, SellerCode

	select @RowCount = @@rowcount
	set @ProcessMessage = '#OngoingPremiumTotal = ' + convert(nvarchar(10), @RowCount)
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseLog, @ProcessMessage, null, @Module, @Client
		
	--Front loaded -> Just the oldest +ve payment
	--Note: These transactions have NO clawbacks or adjustments
	select	1 as SelectionSource,
			cso.TransactionID,
			cso.AgentCode,
			cso.MinOngoingPendingPaymentID as PendingPaymentID,
			cso.AgentSplit,
			case when opt.CaseID is null
				then cso.Premium
				else opt.SumOfPremium
			end as Premium,
			case when opt.CaseID is null
				then cso.FrequencyCode
				else opt.FrequencyCode
			end as FrequencyCode,
			1 as SpreadNumber,
			1 as MaxSpread 
	into	#msit_CommissionStatementONGOING
	from	#msit_CommissionStatementOGSSUMMARY cso	
			left join mstt_PolicyTransactions pt on pt.ID = cso.TransactionID
			left join mstt_Policies p on p.POL_NUM = pt.PolicyID
			left join #OngoingPremiumTotal opt			--When NO clawbacks or adjustments, the seller gets credit for the combined premium
						on opt.CaseID = p.PolicyRef
						and opt.SellerCode = cso.AgentCode
	where	cso.MaxOngoingAdjPendingPaymentID is null	--No clawbacks or adjustments - so front load
	and		cso.MinOngoingPendingPaymentID is not null	--At least one +ve payment on the transaction

	union	--Add in with dedupe
	
	--Per payment -> all +ve payments with max spread also used for divisor
	--Note: ALL these transactions have clawbacks or adjustments
	select	2 as SelectionSource,
			cso.TransactionID,
			cso.AgentCode,
			cs.PendingPaymentID,
			cso.AgentSplit,
			cso.Premium,
			cso.FrequencyCode,
			ROW_NUMBER() over (partition by cs.TransactionID, cs.AgentCode order by cs.TransactionID, cs.AgentCode, cs.PendingPaymentID) as SpreadNumber,
			12 as MaxSpread
	from	#msit_CommissionStatementOGSSUMMARY cso	
			inner join msit_CommissionStatement cs 
						on cs.TransactionID = cso.TransactionID
						and cs.AgentCode = cso.AgentCode
	where	cso.MaxOngoingAdjPendingPaymentID is not null	--Clawbacks or adjustments so per payment
	and		cs.CommissionType in (10)	

	union	--Add in with dedupe
	
	--Per payment -> all -ve payments - with max spread also used for divisor
	--Note: ALL these transactions have clawbacks or adjustments
	select	3 as SelectionSource,
			cso.TransactionID,
			cso.AgentCode,
			cs.PendingPaymentID,
			cso.AgentSplit,
			cso.Premium,
			cso.FrequencyCode,
			ROW_NUMBER() over (partition by cs.TransactionID, cs.AgentCode order by cs.TransactionID, cs.AgentCode, cs.PendingPaymentID) as SpreadNumber,
			12 as MaxSpread
	from	#msit_CommissionStatementOGSSUMMARY cso	
			inner join msit_CommissionStatement cs 
						on cs.TransactionID = cso.TransactionID
						and cs.AgentCode = cso.AgentCode
	where	cso.MaxOngoingAdjPendingPaymentID is not null	--Clawbacks or adjustments so per payment
	and		cs.CommissionType in (16,19)	

	select @RowCount = @@rowcount
	set @ProcessMessage = '#msit_CommissionStatementONGOING (ogs payments) = ' + convert(nvarchar(10), @RowCount)
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseLog, @ProcessMessage, null, @Module, @Client

	/****************************************************************************
		
		Insert the ongoing VNB results for those transactions 
																		
	****************************************************************************/

	insert into #AG_owt_Recognition_SEPARATE_ONGOING
	(
		SourceID,
		CaseID,
		TransactionID,
		Policy,
		ProductCode,
		BusinessCode,
		SellerCode,
		PointsTotal,
		BSC,
		MBF,
		Initial,
		OngoingTotal,
		OngoingYr01,
		OngoingYr02,
		OngoingYr03,
		OngoingYr04,
		OngoingYr05,
		OngoingYr06,
		OngoingYr07,
		OngoingYr08,
		OngoingYr09,
		OngoingYr10,
		FCARate,
		RetentionRate,
		RetentionRateBroker,
		OngoingServicingRate,
		OngoingServicingSource,
		DA,
		AmountReceived,
		Premium,
		AgentSplit,
		CommissionType,
		CommissionTypeDesc,
		PayBasisCode,
		PayBasisDesc,
		PaymentMatchedDate,
		Month,
		FrequencyCode,
		FrequencyDesc,
		ReassignedProductGroupCode,
		ReassignedProductGroupName,
		RecognitionType,
		CalculationType,
		Source,
		DateInserted,
		DateLastUpdated,
		CommissionYear
	)
	select	cs.PendingPaymentID as SourceID,
			cs.CaseID,
			cs.TransactionID,
			cs.ExtPolicyNumber as Policy,
			cs.ProductCode,
			cs.BusinessCode,
			cs.AgentCode as SellerCode,
			0.0 as PointsTotal,
			case
				when BSCpot.ID is not null then 
					--BSC takes the first 0.12 of the ongoing fee %. If the ongoing fee % is 0.12% or less, then 100% of the ongoing fee is allocated to BSC
					case when coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2)) - convert(decimal(8,4),sc.KeyValue2) >= 0.01
						then 
							case when cso.FrequencyCode = 2	--Monthly 
								then (cso.AgentSplit/100) * 12.0 * (isnull(cso.Premium/cso.MaxSpread,0)/2.0) * convert(decimal(8,4),sc.KeyValue3) * case when cs.CommissionType in (16,19) then -1 else 1 end
								else (cso.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(cso.Premium/cso.MaxSpread,0) * convert(decimal(8,4),sc.KeyValue3) * case when cs.CommissionType in (16,19) then -1 else 1 end
							end			
						else
							case when cso.FrequencyCode = 2	--Monthly 
								then (cso.AgentSplit/100) * 12.0 * (isnull(cso.Premium/cso.MaxSpread,0)/2.0) * coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2)) * case when cs.CommissionType in (16,19) then -1 else 1 end
								else (cso.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(cso.Premium/cso.MaxSpread,0) * (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))/100.0) * case when cs.CommissionType in (16,19) then -1 else 1 end
							end
					end
				else 0.0
			end as BSC,
			0.0 as MBF,
			0.0 as Initial,
			0.0 as OngoingTotal,
			case
				--WEALTH ONGOING CALCULATION START
				--When the adviser has changed, the AgentSplit can become zero in which case the ELITE points should be zero.
				when cso.AgentSplit = 0 then 0

				--SINGLE start
				--Calculate when BSC and ongoing applies (where ongoing rate is greater than BSC rate) 
				when cso.FrequencyCode = 6 and SFMpot.ID is not null and BSCpot.ID is not null and (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2)) - convert(decimal(8,4),sc.KeyValue2)) >= 0.01 then 
							--(AUM X BSC Rate)...
							((cso.AgentSplit/100) * (isnull(cso.Premium/cso.MaxSpread,0) * convert(decimal(8,4),sc.KeyValue3)) 
							--(AUM X OGS Rate X COB FCA Rate)...
							- ((cso.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(cso.Premium/cso.MaxSpread,0) * (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))/100.0) * Cfca.FACTOR)
							--(AUM X (OGS Rate - BSC Rate) X COB Retention Rate)...
							+ ((cso.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(cso.Premium/cso.MaxSpread,0) * ((coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))-convert(decimal(8,4),sc.KeyValue2))/100.0)) * Crate.FACTOR) 
							--Sign correctly for +ve or clawback payment
							* (case when cs.CommissionType in (16,19) then -1 else 1 end)
				--Calculate when BSC and ongoing applies (where ongoing rate less than BSC rate, then BSC gets all the ongoing available) 
				when cso.FrequencyCode = 6 and SFMpot.ID is not null and BSCpot.ID is not null then
							--(AUM X BSC Rate)...(in this scenario it's all of the OGS rate)
							((cso.AgentSplit/100) * (isnull(cso.Premium/cso.MaxSpread,0) * (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))/100.0)) 
							--(AUM X OGS Rate X COB FCA Rate)...
							- ((cso.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(cso.Premium/cso.MaxSpread,0) * (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))/100.0) * Cfca.FACTOR)
							--(AUM X (OGS Rate - BSC Rate) X COB Retention Rate)...
							+ (0.0)) --BSC got it all, so this part of the calculation is zero
							--Sign correctly for +ve or clawback payment
							* (case when cs.CommissionType in (16,19) then -1 else 1 end)
				--Calculate when no BSC applies and ongoing applies
				when cso.FrequencyCode = 6 and SFMpot.ID is not null and BSCpot.ID is null then 
							--(AUM X OGS Rate X COB Retention Rate)...
							(((cso.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(cso.Premium/cso.MaxSpread,0) * (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))/100.0) * Crate.FACTOR) 
							--(AUM X OGS Rate X COB FCA Rate)...
							- ((cso.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(cso.Premium/cso.MaxSpread,0) * (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))/100.0) * Cfca.FACTOR))
							--Sign correctly for +ve or clawback payment
							* (case when cs.CommissionType in (16,19) then -1 else 1 end)
				--SINGLE end
				
				--REGULAR start
				--Calculate when BSC and ongoing applies (where ongoing rate is greater than BSC rate) 
				when cso.FrequencyCode <> 6 and SFMpot.ID is not null and BSCpot.ID is not null and (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2)) - convert(decimal(8,4),sc.KeyValue2)) >= 0.01 then		--AG 04/06/2018 (1)
							--The non-BSC portion (Ave AUM X (OGS Rate - BSC Rate) X COB Retention Rate)...
							((((((cso.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(cso.Premium/cso.MaxSpread,0) * (case when cso.FrequencyCode = 2 then 12 else 1 end))/2.0) * (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2)) - convert(decimal(8,4),sc.KeyValue2))/100.0)) * Crate.FACTOR
							--The BSC portion (Ave AUM X BSC Rate)...
							+ case when cso.FrequencyCode = 2	--Monthly 
									then (cso.AgentSplit/100) * 12.0 * (isnull(cso.Premium/cso.MaxSpread,0)/2.0) * convert(decimal(8,4),sc.KeyValue3) 
									else (cso.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(cso.Premium/cso.MaxSpread,0) * convert(decimal(8,4),sc.KeyValue3) 
							  end
							--FCA Charge (Ave AUM X OGS Rate X FCA Rate)...
							- (case when cso.FrequencyCode = 2	--Monthly 
									then (cso.AgentSplit/100) * 12.0 * (isnull(cso.Premium/cso.MaxSpread,0)/2.0) 
									else (cso.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(cso.Premium/cso.MaxSpread,0) 
							   end * (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))/100.0) * Cfca.FACTOR))
							--Sign correctly for +ve or clawback payment
							* (case when cs.CommissionType in (16,19) then -1 else 1 end)   
				--Calculate when BSC and ongoing applies (where ongoing rate less than BSC rate, then BSC gets all the ongoing available) 
				when cso.FrequencyCode <> 6 and SFMpot.ID is not null and BSCpot.ID is not null then		--AG 04/06/2018 (1)
							--The non-BSC portion (Ave AUM X (OGS Rate - BSC Rate) X COB Retention Rate)...
							((0.0)	--BSC got it all, so this part of the calculation is zero
							--The BSC portion (Ave AUM X BSC Rate)...(in this scenario it's all of the OGS rate)
							+ case when cso.FrequencyCode = 2	--Monthly 
									then (cso.AgentSplit/100) * 12.0 * (isnull(cso.Premium/cso.MaxSpread,0)/2.0) * (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))/100.0) 
									else (cso.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(cso.Premium/cso.MaxSpread,0) * (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))/100.0) 
							  end
							--FCA Charge (Ave AUM X OGS Rate X FCA Rate)...
							- (case when cso.FrequencyCode = 2	--Monthly 
									then (cso.AgentSplit/100) * 12.0 * (isnull(cso.Premium/cso.MaxSpread,0)/2.0) 
									else (cso.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(cso.Premium/cso.MaxSpread,0) 
							   end * (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))/100.0) * Cfca.FACTOR))
							--Sign correctly for +ve or clawback payment
							* (case when cs.CommissionType in (16,19) then -1 else 1 end)   
				--Calculate when no BSC applies, but ongoing servicing applies
				when cso.FrequencyCode <> 6 and SFMpot.ID is not null and BSCpot.ID is null then		--AG 04/06/2018	(1)
							--(Ave AUM X OGS Rate X COB Retention Rate)...
							(((((cso.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(cso.Premium/cso.MaxSpread,0) * (case when cso.FrequencyCode = 2 then 12 else 1 end))/2.0) * (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))/100.0) * Crate.FACTOR) 
							--(Ave AUM X OGS Rate X COB FCA Rate)...
							- ((((cso.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(cso.Premium/cso.MaxSpread,0) * (case when cso.FrequencyCode = 2 then 12 else 1 end))/2.0) * (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))/100.0) * Cfca.FACTOR))
							--Sign correctly for +ve or clawback payment
							* (case when cs.CommissionType in (16,19) then -1 else 1 end)   
				--REGULAR end
				
				else 0.0

				--WEALTH ONGOING CALCULATION END
			end as OngoingYr01,
			0.0 as OngoingYr02,
			0.0 as OngoingYr03,
			0.0 as OngoingYr04,
			0.0 as OngoingYr05,
			0.0 as OngoingYr06,
			0.0 as OngoingYr07,
			0.0 as OngoingYr08,
			0.0 as OngoingYr09,
			0.0 as OngoingYr10,
			Cfca.FACTOR*100.0 as FCARate,
			Crate.FACTOR*100.0 as RetentionRate,
			0.0 as RetentionRateBroker,
			case when SFMpot.ID is not null
				then coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))
				else null
			end as OngoingServicingRate,
			case when SFMpot.ID is not null
				then case 
						when ogs.OngoingServiceFee is null and ogscli.OngoingServiceFee is null 
							then case
								when ogsdflt.KeyValue = 'ONPLAT' then 'Default - On Plat'
								else 'Default - Off Plat'
							end
						when ogs.OngoingServiceFee is not null then 'Client Product'
						when ogscli.OngoingServiceFee is not null then 'Client Only'
						else 'Unknown'
					 end
				else case when (ph.ProductCategoryCode = 1 or pcc.KeyValue2 = '1')
						then 'No OGS'					--WEALTH, but no OGS
						else null						--Not WEALTH, so OGS is n/a and is therefore null
					 end
			end as OngoingServicingSource,
			pt.CommInitialAmount as DA,
			e.AMOUNT_REC as AmountReceived,
			cso.Premium,								--AG 17/07/2018
			cso.AgentSplit,								--Use the split from the IC record
			cs.CommissionType,
			left(cs.StandingOrderDesc,50) as CommissionTypeDesc,
			cs.PayBasisCode,
			cs.PayBasisDesc,
			cs.CreateDate as PaymentMatchedDate,
			cs.Month,
			cso.FrequencyCode,							--AG 17/07/2018
			case when cso.FrequencyCode = 6
				then 'Single'
				else 'Monthly'
			end as FrequencyDesc,						--AG 17/07/2018
			pg.ProductGroupCode as ReassignedProductGroupCode,	--Force the re-assigned products...		
			pg.ProductGroupName as ReassignedProductGroupName,	--...to be processed as investments		
			case cso.SelectionSource
				when 1 then 'VNB-OGS-PHASE-1' 
				when 2 then 'VNB-OGS-PHASE-2' 
				when 3 then 'VNB-OGS-PHASE-3' 
			end as RecognitionType,
			'WEALTH-ONGOING' as CalculationType,
			'Openwork 2006' as Source,
			@DateLastUpdated as DateInserted,
			@DateLastUpdated as DateLastUpdated,
			csp.year as CommissionYear
	from	#msit_CommissionStatementONGOING cso
			inner join msit_CommissionStatement cs on cs.PendingPaymentID = cso.PendingPaymentID
			inner join mstt_Agents ag on ag.Code = cs.BusinessCode
			inner join mstt_PolicyTransactions pt on pt.ID = cs.TransactionID
			inner join mstt_Policies p on p.POL_NUM = pt.PolicyID
			inner join msit_CommissionStatementPeriods VNBStart on convert(date,pt.CreateDateTime) between VNBStart.PeriodStartDate and VNBStart.PeriodEndDate
			inner join msit_Commissionstatementperiods csp on csp.month = cs.month
			inner join mstt_ProductHierarchy ph on ph.productcode = cs.productcode
			inner join mstt_Expectation e on e.ID = cs.ExpectationID
			left join dbo.owt_MortgageBrokerFees mbf on mbf.PendingPaymentID = cs.PendingPaymentID and mbf.AdviceFeeCharged = 'Yes'
			left join owt_SelectionControl SC
						on SC.Process = 'ElitePoints' 
						and SC.KeyType = 'NSCPotCode' 
						and cs.CreateDate between SC.EffectiveStartDate and SC.EffectiveEndDate
			left join mstt_Commissions BSCpot
						on BSCpot.TransactionID = cs.TransactionID 
						and BSCpot.Agent_Code = sc.KeyValue
						and BSCpot.CommissionType = 10
			left join owt_SelectionControl SFMPC						
						on SFMPC.Process = 'ElitePoints' 
						and SFMPC.KeyType = 'ServicingFeeMarginPotCode' 
						and cs.CreateDate between SFMPC.EffectiveStartDate and SFMPC.EffectiveEndDate
			left join mstt_Commissions SFMpot							
						on SFMpot.TransactionID = cs.TransactionID 
						and SFMpot.Agent_Code = SFMPC.KeyValue
						and SFMpot.CommissionType = 10	
			left join owt_SelectionControl pcc 
						on pcc.Process = 'ElitePoints'
						and pcc.KeyType = 'ProductCategoryCode'
						and pcc.KeyValue = cs.ProductCode	
						and cs.CreateDate between pcc.EffectiveStartDate and pcc.EffectiveEndDate
			left join owt_SelectionControl ogsdflt 
						on ogsdflt.Process = 'ElitePoints'
						and ogsdflt.KeyType = 'DefaultOngoingServicingRate'
						and ogsdflt.SelectionType = 'VNB'
						and ogsdflt.KeyValue = case when ph.RDRType = 'ONPLAT' then 'ONPLAT' else 'OFPLAT' end
						and cs.CreateDate between ogsdflt.EffectiveStartDate and ogsdflt.EffectiveEndDate
			left join mstt_CodeProductGroup pg on pg.ProductGroupCode = case when pcc.KeyValue2 = '1' then 2 else ph.ProductGroupCode end
			left join owt_EliteFactors Cfca on Cfca.FeeType = 'VNB' and Cfca.category = 'COB-FCA-RATE' and csp.year between Cfca.StartYear and Cfca.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors Crate on Crate.FeeType = 'VNB' and Crate.category = 'COB-RETENTION-RATE' and csp.year between Crate.StartYear and Crate.EndYear 
			left join dbo.owt_OngoingRate ogs 
						on  ogs.CLIENT_NUM = cs.ClientID 
						and ogs.ProductCode = cs.ProductCode
						and convert(date,pt.CreateDateTime) between ogs.EffectiveStartDate and ogs.EffectiveEndDate
			left join dbo.owt_OngoingRate ogscli 
						on  ogscli.CLIENT_NUM = cs.ClientID 
						and ogscli.ProductCode = '(CLIENT)'
						and convert(date,pt.CreateDateTime) between ogscli.EffectiveStartDate and ogscli.EffectiveEndDate
	where	cso.SpreadNumber <= cso.MaxSpread	-- if per payment spreading, then limit the spread
	
	select @RowCount = @@rowcount
	set @ProcessMessage = '#owt_Recognition (ogs ph1 yr1) = ' + convert(nvarchar(10), @RowCount)
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseLog, @ProcessMessage, null, @Module, @Client

	/****************************************************************************

		Ongoing Phase 3
		1) Add up the +ves and -ves prior to the NEW front loaded amount and
			net them off on the first +ve following the last -ve
		2) Now set all the +ves following the one updated in (1) to zero.
																
	****************************************************************************/

	update r
		set RecognitionType	= case when r.SourceID >= csos.MinOngoingAfterAdjPendingPaymentID 
								then 'VNB-OGS-PHASE-4'
								else r.RecognitionType
							  end,
			OngoingYr01 = case  when r.SourceID = csos.MinOngoingAfterAdjPendingPaymentID 
									then (abs(r.OngoingYr01) * cso.MaxSpread) - derived.SumOngoingYr01
								when r.SourceID > csos.MinOngoingAfterAdjPendingPaymentID 
									then 0.0
								else r.OngoingYr01
						  end,
			DateLastUpdated = @DateLastUpdated
	from	#msit_CommissionStatementONGOING cso 
			inner join #AG_owt_Recognition_SEPARATE_ONGOING r on r.SourceID = cso.PendingPaymentID
			inner join #msit_CommissionStatementOGSSUMMARY csos
						on  csos.TransactionID = cso.TransactionID
						and csos.AgentCode = cso.AgentCode
			inner join (select	r.TransactionID, r.SellerCode, SUM(OngoingYr01) as SumOngoingYr01
						from	#msit_CommissionStatementOGSSUMMARY s
								inner join #AG_owt_Recognition_SEPARATE_ONGOING r 
											on r.TransactionID = s.TransactionID
											and r.SellerCode = s.AgentCode
						where	r.SourceID <= s.MaxOngoingAdjPendingPaymentID
						group	by r.TransactionID, r.SellerCode
						) derived 
							on  derived.TransactionID = r.TransactionID
							and	derived.SellerCode = r.SellerCode 
	where	isnull(csos.MaxOngoingPendingPaymentID,0) > isnull(csos.MaxOngoingAdjPendingPaymentID,0)	--An ongoing +ve payment follows the clawback, so time to revert back to front loading
	and		cso.SpreadNumber <= cso.MaxSpread	--Only payments within the spread period get a portion of the ongoing VNB
	and		cso.SelectionSource <> 1			--Just process the per-payment rows (not the front loaded rows)

	select @RowCount = @@rowcount
	set @ProcessMessage = '#owt_Recognition (ogs ph4 - accr adj) = ' + convert(nvarchar(10), @RowCount)
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseLog, @ProcessMessage, null, @Module, @Client

	/****************************************************************************

		Now calculate the ongoing spread as follows:
		1) Investments: Years 1 to 6
		2) Pensions:	Years 1 to 10
		Note that regular payments get an additional multiplier to uplift the 
		average AUM for each year.
																		
	****************************************************************************/

	update r
		set OngoingYr02 = case when r.FrequencyCode = 2									--Monthly
							then r.OngoingYr01 * YR02.Multiplier * YR02.Factor			--Regular
							else r.OngoingYr01 * YR02.Factor							--Single
						  end,
			OngoingYr03 = case when r.FrequencyCode = 2									--Monthly
							then r.OngoingYr01 * YR03.Multiplier * YR03.Factor			--Regular
							else r.OngoingYr01 * YR03.Factor							--Single
						  end,
			OngoingYr04 = case when r.FrequencyCode = 2									--Monthly
							then r.OngoingYr01 * YR04.Multiplier * YR04.Factor			--Regular
							else r.OngoingYr01 * YR04.Factor							--Single
						  end,
			OngoingYr05 = case when r.FrequencyCode = 2									--Monthly 
							then r.OngoingYr01 * YR05.Multiplier * YR05.Factor			--Regular
							else r.OngoingYr01 * YR05.Factor							--Single
						  end,
			OngoingYr06 = case when r.FrequencyCode = 2									--Monthly 
							then r.OngoingYr01 * YR06.Multiplier * YR06.Factor			--Regular
							else r.OngoingYr01 * YR06.Factor							--Single
						  end,
			OngoingYr07 = case when r.ReassignedProductGroupCode = 5					--Pensions	AG 05/06/2018
							then
								case when r.FrequencyCode = 2							--Monthly 
									then r.OngoingYr01 * YR07.Multiplier * YR07.Factor	--Regular
									else r.OngoingYr01 * YR07.Factor					--Single
								end
							else 
								0.0
						  end,
			OngoingYr08 = case when r.ReassignedProductGroupCode = 5					--Pensions	AG 05/06/2018 
							then
								case when r.FrequencyCode = 2							--Monthly 
									then r.OngoingYr01 * YR08.Multiplier * YR08.Factor	--Regular
									else r.OngoingYr01 * YR08.Factor					--Single
								end
							else 
								0.0
						  end,
			OngoingYr09 = case when r.ReassignedProductGroupCode = 5					--Pensions	AG 05/06/2018 
							then
								case when r.FrequencyCode = 2							--Monthly 
									then r.OngoingYr01 * YR09.Multiplier * YR09.Factor	--Regular
									else r.OngoingYr01 * YR09.Factor					--Single
								end
							else 
								0.0
						  end,
			OngoingYr10 = case when r.ReassignedProductGroupCode = 5					--Pensions	AG 05/06/2018
							then
								case when r.FrequencyCode = 2							--Monthly 
									then r.OngoingYr01 * YR10.Multiplier * YR10.Factor	--Regular
									else r.OngoingYr01 * YR10.Factor					--Single
								end
							else 
								0.0
						  end
	from	#AG_owt_Recognition_SEPARATE_ONGOING r
			left join owt_EliteFactors YR01 on YR01.FeeType = 'VNB' and YR01.Category = 'COB-ONGOING-DISCOUNT-YR01' and r.CommissionYear between YR01.StartYear and YR01.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors YR02 on YR02.FeeType = 'VNB' and YR02.Category = 'COB-ONGOING-DISCOUNT-YR02' and r.CommissionYear between YR02.StartYear and YR02.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors YR03 on YR03.FeeType = 'VNB' and YR03.Category = 'COB-ONGOING-DISCOUNT-YR03' and r.CommissionYear between YR03.StartYear and YR03.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors YR04 on YR04.FeeType = 'VNB' and YR04.Category = 'COB-ONGOING-DISCOUNT-YR04' and r.CommissionYear between YR04.StartYear and YR04.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors YR05 on YR05.FeeType = 'VNB' and YR05.Category = 'COB-ONGOING-DISCOUNT-YR05' and r.CommissionYear between YR05.StartYear and YR05.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors YR06 on YR06.FeeType = 'VNB' and YR06.Category = 'COB-ONGOING-DISCOUNT-YR06' and r.CommissionYear between YR06.StartYear and YR06.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors YR07 on YR07.FeeType = 'VNB' and YR07.Category = 'COB-ONGOING-DISCOUNT-YR07' and r.CommissionYear between YR07.StartYear and YR07.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors YR08 on YR08.FeeType = 'VNB' and YR08.Category = 'COB-ONGOING-DISCOUNT-YR08' and r.CommissionYear between YR08.StartYear and YR08.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors YR09 on YR09.FeeType = 'VNB' and YR09.Category = 'COB-ONGOING-DISCOUNT-YR09' and r.CommissionYear between YR09.StartYear and YR09.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors YR10 on YR10.FeeType = 'VNB' and YR10.Category = 'COB-ONGOING-DISCOUNT-YR10' and r.CommissionYear between YR10.StartYear and YR10.EndYear 
	where	r.CalculationType = 'WEALTH-ONGOING'

	select @RowCount = @@rowcount
	set @ProcessMessage = '#owt_Recognition (ongoing yr2-10) = ' + convert(nvarchar(10), @RowCount)
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseLog, @ProcessMessage, null, @Module, @Client
	
	/****************************************************************************

		Now add up all the numbers
																		
	****************************************************************************/
	
	update r
		set OngoingTotal	=	OngoingYr01 + OngoingYr02 + OngoingYr03 + OngoingYr04 + OngoingYr05 +
								OngoingYr06 + OngoingYr07 + OngoingYr08 + OngoingYr09 + OngoingYr10,
			PointsTotal		=	OngoingYr01 + OngoingYr02 + OngoingYr03 + OngoingYr04 + OngoingYr05 +
								OngoingYr06 + OngoingYr07 + OngoingYr08 + OngoingYr09 + OngoingYr10 +
								Initial + MBF	-- Note BSC is already included in the Ongoing, so don't include it in the Points Total.
	from	#AG_owt_Recognition_SEPARATE_ONGOING r

	select @RowCount = @@rowcount
	set @ProcessMessage = '#owt_Recognition (points total) = ' + convert(nvarchar(10), @RowCount)
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseLog, @ProcessMessage, null, @Module, @Client

	/****************************************************************************

		Merge the temporary table into the permanent table (IC data)
																		
	****************************************************************************/

	BEGIN TRANSACTION

	declare @SummaryOfChanges table (Change varchar(20))
	merge	dbo.AG_owt_Recognition_SEPARATE_ONGOING as trg
	using	#AG_owt_Recognition_SEPARATE_ONGOING as src
	on		trg.SourceID = src.SourceID
	and		trg.Source = src.Source
	when	matched 
	and		isnull(trg.PointsTotal,0) <> isnull(src.PointsTotal,0)
	then	update 
				set trg.CaseID = src.CaseID,
					trg.TransactionID = src.TransactionID,
					trg.Policy = src.Policy,
					trg.ProductCode = src.ProductCode,
					trg.BusinessCode = src.BusinessCode,
					trg.SellerCode = src.SellerCode,					--AG 13/06/2018
					trg.PointsTotal = src.PointsTotal,
					trg.BSC = src.BSC,
					trg.MBF = src.MBF,
					trg.Initial = src.Initial,
					trg.OngoingTotal = src.OngoingTotal,
					trg.OngoingYr01 = src.OngoingYr01,
					trg.OngoingYr02 = src.OngoingYr02,
					trg.OngoingYr03 = src.OngoingYr03,
					trg.OngoingYr04 = src.OngoingYr04,
					trg.OngoingYr05 = src.OngoingYr05,
					trg.OngoingYr06 = src.OngoingYr06,
					trg.OngoingYr07 = src.OngoingYr07,
					trg.OngoingYr08 = src.OngoingYr08,
					trg.OngoingYr09 = src.OngoingYr09,
					trg.OngoingYr10 = src.OngoingYr10,
					trg.FCARate = src.FCARate,
					trg.RetentionRate = src.RetentionRate,
					trg.RetentionRateBroker = src.RetentionRateBroker,
					trg.OngoingServicingRate = src.OngoingServicingRate,
					trg.OngoingServicingSource = src.OngoingServicingSource,
					trg.DA = src.DA,
					trg.AmountReceived = src.AmountReceived,
					trg.Premium = src.Premium,
					trg.AgentSplit = src.AgentSplit,
					trg.CommissionType = src.CommissionType,
					trg.CommissionTypeDesc = src.CommissionTypeDesc,
					trg.PayBasisCode = src.PayBasisCode,				--AG 13/06/2018
					trg.PayBasisDesc = src.PayBasisDesc,				--AG 13/06/2018
					trg.PaymentMatchedDate = src.PaymentMatchedDate,	--AG 13/06/2018	
					trg.Month = src.Month,
					trg.FrequencyCode = src.FrequencyCode,
					trg.FrequencyDesc = src.FrequencyDesc,
					trg.ReassignedProductGroupCode = src.ReassignedProductGroupCode,	--AG 05/06/2018
					trg.ReassignedProductGroupName = src.ReassignedProductGroupName,	--AG 05/06/2018
					trg.RecognitionType = src.RecognitionType,
					trg.CalculationType = src.CalculationType,
					trg.DateLastUpdated = @DateLastUpdated
	when	not matched by target 
	then	insert
			(
				SourceID,
				CaseID,
				TransactionID,
				Policy,
				ProductCode,
				BusinessCode,
				SellerCode,							--AG 13/06/2018
				PointsTotal,
				BSC,
				MBF,
				Initial,
				OngoingTotal,
				OngoingYr01,
				OngoingYr02,
				OngoingYr03,
				OngoingYr04,
				OngoingYr05,
				OngoingYr06,
				OngoingYr07,
				OngoingYr08,
				OngoingYr09,
				OngoingYr10,
				FCARate,
				RetentionRate,
				RetentionRateBroker,
				OngoingServicingRate,
				OngoingServicingSource,
				DA,
				AmountReceived,
				Premium,
				AgentSplit,
				CommissionType,
				CommissionTypeDesc,
				PayBasisCode,						--AG 13/06/2018
				PayBasisDesc,						--AG 13/06/2018
				PaymentMatchedDate,					--AG 13/06/2018
				Month,
				FrequencyCode,
				FrequencyDesc,
				ReassignedProductGroupCode,			--AG 05/06/2018
				ReassignedProductGroupName,			--AG 05/06/2018
				RecognitionType,
				CalculationType,
				Source,
				DateInserted,
				DateLastUpdated
			)		
			values
			(
				src.SourceID,
				src.CaseID,
				src.TransactionID,
				src.Policy,
				src.ProductCode,
				src.BusinessCode,
				src.SellerCode,						--AG 13/06/2018
				src.PointsTotal,
				src.BSC,
				src.MBF,
				src.Initial,
				src.OngoingTotal,
				src.OngoingYr01,
				src.OngoingYr02,
				src.OngoingYr03,
				src.OngoingYr04,
				src.OngoingYr05,
				src.OngoingYr06,
				src.OngoingYr07,
				src.OngoingYr08,
				src.OngoingYr09,
				src.OngoingYr10,
				src.FCARate,
				src.RetentionRate,
				src.RetentionRateBroker,
				src.OngoingServicingRate,
				src.OngoingServicingSource,
				src.DA,
				src.AmountReceived,
				src.Premium,
				src.AgentSplit,
				src.CommissionType,
				src.CommissionTypeDesc,
				src.PayBasisCode,					--AG 13/06/2018
				src.PayBasisDesc,					--AG 13/06/2018
				src.PaymentMatchedDate,				--AG 13/06/2018
				src.Month,
				src.FrequencyCode,
				src.FrequencyDesc,
				src.ReassignedProductGroupCode,		--AG 05/06/2018
				src.ReassignedProductGroupName,		--AG 05/06/2018
				src.RecognitionType,
				src.CalculationType,
				src.Source,
				src.DateInserted,
				src.DateLastUpdated)				--Merge statements must have a ;
	output $action into @SummaryOfChanges;
						
	/****************************************************************************

		Update OpenAccess
																		
	****************************************************************************/

/*	
	--Do not include MBF in the OpenAccess Commission Listing as it is on the MBF download
	--and we don't want MBF double counting.
	update	oal
		set VNB_Points = r.PointsTotal - r.MBF		--AG 04/06/2018 (2)
	from	msit_CommissionStatement cs
/*			inner join (select	distinct PKID
						from	owt_TransformationMovements tm 
						where	tm.DriverTableName = 'sa_swift_S_AGMFIL'
						and		tm.CommissionStatement = 'Y') tm on tm.PKID = cs.PendingPaymentID
*/			inner join msit_OpenworkAdviserListing oal on oal.SourceID = cs.ID and oal.Source = 'Openwork 2006'
			inner join owt_Recognition r 
						on r.SourceID = cs.PendingPaymentID
						and r.Source = oal.Source
	--where	isnull(oal.VNB_Points,0) <> isnull(r.PointsTotal,0)
	
	select @OALRowCount = @@rowcount
*/
	COMMIT TRANSACTION      
	
	select	@RowCount = COUNT(*)
	from	@SummaryOfChanges
	where	Change = 'INSERT'

	set @ProcessMessage = 'owt_Recognition (insert) = ' + convert(nvarchar(10), @RowCount)
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseLog, @ProcessMessage, null, @Module, @Client

	select	@RowCount = COUNT(*)
	from	@SummaryOfChanges
	where	Change = 'UPDATE'

	set @ProcessMessage = 'owt_Recognition (update) = ' + convert(nvarchar(10), @RowCount)
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseLog, @ProcessMessage, null, @Module, @Client
/*
	set @ProcessMessage = 'msit_OpenworkAdviserListing (update) = ' + convert(nvarchar(10), @OALRowCount)
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseLog, @ProcessMessage, null, @Module, @Client
*/
	/****************************************************************************

		T H E   E N D
																		
	****************************************************************************/
	
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseEnd, @ProcName, null, @Module, @Client

END TRY

BEGIN CATCH 

	select @ErrNum = ERROR_NUMBER(), @ErrMsg = ERROR_MESSAGE(), @ErrSev = ERROR_SEVERITY(), @ErrLine = ERROR_LINE(), @ErrState = XACT_STATE()
	set @ErrMsg = REPLACE(@ErrMsg, '.', '') + ' (error no: ' + CAST(@ErrNum AS VARCHAR(10)) + ') on line ' + CAST(@ErrLine AS VARCHAR(10))
	
	-- Test XACT_STATE for 0, 1, or -1.
    -- If 1, the transaction is committable.
    -- If -1, the transaction is uncommittable and should be rolled back.
    -- If 0, there is no transaction and a commit or rollback operation would generate an error.

	if @ErrState = -1			-- Transaction is uncommitable
		rollback transaction

	if @ErrState = 1			
		commit transaction

	-- Error message line 1
	set @ErrMsgBrief = left(@ErrMsg,100)
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseError, @ErrMsgBrief, null, @Module, @Client
	
	-- Error message line 2 - if any text exists
	set @ErrMsgBrief = substring(@ErrMsg,101,100)
	if len(@ErrMsgBrief) > 0
		exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseError, @ErrMsgBrief, null, @Module, @Client

	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseEnd, @ProcName, null, @Module, @Client

	RAISERROR(@ErrMsg, @ErrSev , 1)

END CATCH

/****************************************************************************

			E N D															

****************************************************************************/

return @ErrNum


GO
/****** Object:  StoredProcedure [dbo].[owp_RecognitionSwiftONGOING_Backup20180724AG]    Script Date: 7/3/2026 3:44:25 PM ******/
SET ANSI_NULLS ON
GO
SET QUOTED_IDENTIFIER ON
GO
/*********************************************************************************************************

Program:		owp_RecognitionSwift					
Author:			Alan Groves
Date created:	11/04/2018
											
Description:
===========

This proc populates the new recognition table called "owt_Recognition" with "Value of New Business"
(VNB) points.

This proc handles all of the swift data which includes:
WEALTH - COB business i.e. pensions and investments
MORTGAGES
PROTECTION

Note: There is a separate proc that calculates the GI VNB points from the Paymentshield data.

The approach of this proc is to use the incremental PendingPaymentIDs from the overnight batch
to calculate the VNB points in a temporary table.

The temporary table is then merged with the permanent table to make the calculated (or
re-calculated values) permanent.

Terms
-----
BSC			- Business Service Charge.
MBF			- Mortgage Broker Fee.
OGS			- Ongoing Servicing.
BSC Rate	- 0.12% at the time of writing (24/04/2018). This could be changed by the business, but
				would also require some DEV work in OWS.
DF			- Discount Factor.
DA			- Distribution Allowance (the total amount paid out by the provider to Openwork)
AUM			- Assets Under Management. Basically the amount invested or the premium on investment
				cases.
Average AUM - Average amount invested annually which is equivalent to 6 months' premium.

THE CALCULATIONS
================

There are two potential parts: initial + ongoing (if ongoing applies). If BSC (applies to ongoing 
only) and MBF (applies to mortgages only) apply, then these are also included:

MORTGAGE
--------
Part 1: MBF column = (Advice Fee Amount X Broker Retention Rate) - (Advice Fee Amount X Mort FCA Rate)
Part 2: Initial column = (Proc Fee Amount X Mortgage Retention Rate) - (Proc Fee X Mort FCA Rate) 
Mortgage Points Total = Initial + MBF

PROTECTION
----------
= (DA X Protection Retention Rate) - (DA X Protection FCA Rate) 
Protection Points Total = Initial

WEALTH (COB i.e. pensions and investments)
------
Part 1: Initial column = (DA X Wealth Retention Rate) - (DA X Wealth FCA Rate)

Part 2:

****XXXX****

NOTE: Where the BSC rate is greater than the ongoing rate, then BSC gets ALL of the AVAILABLE 
ongoing.

****XXXX****

REGULAR - BSC applies:
Year 1 column = BSC Points + Non-BSC Points - FCA Points
Non-BSC Points = Ave AUM X (OGS Rate - BSC Rate) X COB Retention Rate
BSC Points = Ave AUM X BSC Rate
FCA Points = Ave AUM X OGS Rate X COB FCA Rate

REGULAR - Non-BSC: 
Year 1 column = (Ave AUM X OGS Rate X COB Retention Rate) - (Ave AUM X OGS Rate X COB FCA Rate)

SINGLE - BSC applies:
Year 1 column = (AUM X BSC Rate) + (AUM X (OGS Rate - BSC Rate) X COB Retention Rate) - (AUM X OGS Rate X COB FCA Rate) 

SINGLE - Non-BSC:
Year 1 column = (AUM X OGS Rate X COB Retention Rate) - (AUM X OGS Rate X COB FCA Rate) 

Then years 2 to 10 are calculated by applying a discount factor
Year  2 = Year 1 X  3 X DF
Year  3 = Year 1 X  5 X DF
Year  4 = Year 1 X  7 X DF
Year  5 = Year 1 X  9 X DF
Year  6 = Year 1 X 11 X DF
Year  7 = Year 1 X 13 X DF
Year  8 = Year 1 X 15 X DF
Year  9 = Year 1 X 17 X DF
Year 10 = Year 1 X 19 X DF

Wealth Points Total =	OngoingYr01 + OngoingYr02 + OngoingYr03 + OngoingYr04 + OngoingYr05 +
						OngoingYr06 + OngoingYr07 + OngoingYr08 + OngoingYr09 + OngoingYr10 +
						Initial

GI
--
See stored proc "owp_RecognitionGIPaymentshield".
 
Notes:
-----

1)	There is a BSC column on table owt_Recognition. However, BSC is already included in the ongoing
	years 1 - 10, so the BSC column does not need to be added in. In fact you will double count if 
	you attempt to do anything with it other than display it.

2)	Occasionally an investment case may receive two or more cheques which
	then go through Swift as two or more SINGLE investments on the SAME
	slice. Although the INITIAL VNB calculation will pro-rata correctly
	because it is based on the amount received, this scenario will cause
	ongoing VNB to be calculated on each of the payment records and so will 
	double count (or worse if there are more than two cheques received).
	Since de-coupling IC from ongoing i.e. they now have separate rows on
	table owt_Recognition, the issue of multiple cheques should no longer
	cause ongoing double counting.


This proc is called as follows:
	declare @rc int
	exec @rc = dbo.owp_RecognitionSwift 'Openwork', 'Recognition'
	select @rc

					
AMENDMENT HISTORY				
=================								

Date		Author		Description
----		------		-----------
26/04/2018	A Groves	Only include rows in the OGS lookups where the OngoingServiceFee > 0.0.
						Negative OGS rates are bad data and at the time of writing, there are
						39 of these.
27/04/2018	A Groves	Additional calculation and condition to handle the scenario where BSC applies
						but the OGS Rate is less than the BSC rate. Previously, this caused the
						total ongoing to be zero. However, there are two components to ongoing VNB 
						points, the BSC share and the non-BSC share. So the BSC share (which takes 
						100% when the OGS rate is less than 0.12%) should still yield ongoing points.
27/04/2018	A Groves	Single ongoing Yr01 corrected by applying outer brackets before signing the result.
03/05/2018	A Groves	Added update of column "msit_OpenworkAdviserListing.VNB_Points".
18/05/2018	A Groves	Changed mortgage calculation to use e.AMOUNT_REC instead of pt.CommInitialAmount
						as Marcus Cossey wanted the actual amount received to be used for the DA.
04/06/2018	A Groves	1) In the REGULAR section of column "OngoingYr01", the condition for cs.FrequencyCode <> 6
							was added to ensure the code differentiates to the SINGLE section.
						2) Exclude MBF from the OpenAccess table (msit_OpenworkAdviserListing) as this
							is shown on the MBF download and would otherwise incur MBF double counting.
05/06/2018	A Groves	1) Marcus Cossey advised that investments should get ongoing for years 1 to 6 and
							pensions for years 1 to 10. Previously, both lines of business got years 1 to 10.
						2) Marcus Cossey asked for split payments (i.e. where multiple cheques are processed
							for a SINGLE investment) to only claculate ongoing VNB on the oldest payment. 
11/06/2018	A Groves	1) PSD processed a protection clawback statement as fee type initial. These clawbacks
							all generated +ve instead of -ve VNB points. A tweak was added to ensure that the 
							absolute value of AMOUNT_REC is used to ensure the VNB is correctly signed. 
						2) Another unknown business rule has surfaced: Previously, only initial, clawbacks and
							adjustments on slices created new from 2017 were included. This rule only applies
							to initial. Clawbacks and adjustments can belong to a slice created at any point
							in the past. However, note that the payment (irrespective of whether it is +ve or 
							-ve), must not pre-date 2017.
13/06/2018	A Groves	Marcus asked for SellerCode and PaymentMatchedDate to be added so he need only use 
							the one table for both the adviser and enterprise leagues. PayBasisCode and 
							PayBasisDesc were also added at the same time as these are used in the calculations.
06/07/2018	A Groves	Replaced the OGS Rate lookup on the fly to using table dbo.owt_OngoingRate. This was 
							done to ensure the rate used at any point in time stays the same, so the onging VNB
							will always give the same result each time the calculation runs.
17/07/2018	A Groves	Marcus asked for the ongoing calculation to be based on the sum of premium across
							all the initial transactions where an initial fee has been paid.
19/07/2018	A Groves	Agreed with Marcus that any initial premium that isn't covered by ongoing slices
							needs to be added to the OGS calculation to ensure advisers are not under
							rewarded. The missing OGS premium is added to the oldest OGS payment.
*************************************************************************************************************/

CREATE PROCEDURE [dbo].[owp_RecognitionSwiftONGOING_Backup20180724AG]
	@Client		varchar(50),
	@Module		Varchar(50)

AS

set nocount on

declare		@PhaseStart				varchar(50),
			@PhaseEnd				varchar(50),
			@PhaseError				varchar(50),
			@PhaseLog				varchar(50),
			@ProcName				varchar(100),
			@ProcessMessage			varchar(100),
			@RowCount				int,
			@OALRowCount			int,
			@ErrMsg					nvarchar(4000),
			@ErrMsgBrief			nvarchar(100),
			@ErrNum					int,
			@ErrSev					int,
			@ErrLine				int,
			@ErrState				int,
			@DateLastUpdated		datetime,
			@OwlManager2Code		nvarchar(10)
			
/****************************************************************************

	Set initial parameters																
																		
****************************************************************************/

set @ProcName			= object_name(@@procid)
set @PhaseStart			= 'START'
set @PhaseEnd			= 'END'
set @PhaseError			= 'ERROR'
set @PhaseLog			= 'LOG'
set @ErrNum				= 0	
set @DateLastUpdated	= getdate()

set @OwlManager2Code = (select cde.Code from msit_MIWarehouseCodesAndDescriptions cde
			where cde.ColumnName = 'Manager2Code' and cde.Description = 'Owl Financial')

-- We want this logging irrespective of whether or not there is a rollback
exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseStart, @ProcName, null, @Module, @Client

/****************************************************************************

	Populate the table																
																		
****************************************************************************/

SET XACT_ABORT ON	-- Needed if XACT_STATE() function is used.

BEGIN TRY

	/****************************************************************************

		Calculate VNB and populate the temporary table with the results
		
		Note that there are oddities like LV protection payments which always
		come in pairs with one large and one much smaller amount (e.g. TransactionID 
		= 6684787.) The system treats both payments in the pair as first payments 
		and the (projected) DA associated with both is the same (because it's on 
		the policy transaction). 
		
		There is also a requirement to front-load VNB points on accrual and level
		payments. This means calculate the VNB for the full amount of the DA and 
		put it on the first payment record and then on all subsequent accrual and 
		level payments, set the VNB to zero.
		
		Thus two different sources of DA are used depending on whether we need the
		full DA amount for accruals and level or the actual amount received for all
		other scenarios including the LV split payment scenario. The two sources are:
		
		mstt_PolicyTransactions.CommInitialAmount - Full (projected) DA amount
		
		mstt_Expectation.AMOUNT_REC - The DA actually received. This handles the
										LV scenario whereby the AMOUNT_REC is 
										proportioned across the two payments received.   
																		
	****************************************************************************/
/*
	select	top 0 
			*, 
			convert(int,NULL) as CommissionYear
	into	#AG_owt_Recognition_SEPARATE_ONGOING
	from	AG_owt_Recognition_SEPARATE_ONGOING
*/
	create table [dbo].[#AG_owt_Recognition_SEPARATE_ONGOING]
	(
		[ID] [bigint] IDENTITY(1,1) NOT NULL,
		[SourceID] [int] NULL,
		[CaseID] [int] NULL,
		[TransactionID] [int] NULL,
		[Policy] [varchar](25) NULL,
		[ProductCode] [varchar](8) NULL,
		[BusinessCode] [varchar](7) NULL,
		[SellerCode] [varchar](7) NULL,
		[PointsTotal] [decimal](16, 4) NULL,
		[BSC] [decimal](16, 4) NULL,
		[MBF] [decimal](16, 4) NULL,
		[Initial] [decimal](16, 4) NULL,
		[OngoingTotal] [decimal](16, 4) NULL,
		[OngoingYr01] [decimal](16, 4) NULL,
		[OngoingYr02] [decimal](16, 4) NULL,
		[OngoingYr03] [decimal](16, 4) NULL,
		[OngoingYr04] [decimal](16, 4) NULL,
		[OngoingYr05] [decimal](16, 4) NULL,
		[OngoingYr06] [decimal](16, 4) NULL,
		[OngoingYr07] [decimal](16, 4) NULL,
		[OngoingYr08] [decimal](16, 4) NULL,
		[OngoingYr09] [decimal](16, 4) NULL,
		[OngoingYr10] [decimal](16, 4) NULL,
		[FCARate] [decimal](8, 4) NULL,
		[RetentionRate] [decimal](8, 4) NULL,
		[RetentionRateBroker] [decimal](8, 4) NULL,
		[OngoingServicingRate] [decimal](8, 4) NULL,
		[OngoingServicingSource] [varchar](20) NULL,
		[DA] [decimal](16, 2) NULL,
		[AmountReceived] [decimal](16, 2) NULL,
		[Premium] [decimal](16, 2) NULL,
		[AgentSplit] [decimal](8, 4) NULL,
		[CommissionType] [int] NULL,
		[CommissionTypeDesc] [varchar](50) NULL,
		[PayBasisCode] [varchar](20) NULL,
		[PayBasisDesc] [varchar](20) NULL,
		[PaymentMatchedDate] [datetime] NULL,
		[Month] [datetime] NULL,
		[FrequencyCode] [tinyint] NULL,
		[FrequencyDesc] [varchar](20) NULL,
		[ReassignedProductGroupCode] [int] NULL,
		[ReassignedProductGroupName] [varchar](50) NULL,
		[RecognitionType] [varchar](15) NULL,
		[CalculationType] [varchar](20) NULL,
		[Source] [varchar](15) NULL,
		[DateInserted] [datetime] NULL,
		[DateLastUpdated] [datetime] NULL,
		[CommissionYear] [int] NULL
	)

	/****************************************************************************

		Phase 1 - Process all but regular accrual cases with clawbacks/adjustments
		Accruals are front loaded unless their latest payment is a clawback/adjudtment
		in which case they accrue VNB points on a per payment basis and so these
		are dealt with in Phases 2 and 3.
																		
	****************************************************************************/

	insert into #AG_owt_Recognition_SEPARATE_ONGOING
	(
		SourceID,
		CaseID,
		TransactionID,
		Policy,
		ProductCode,
		BusinessCode,
		SellerCode,						--AG 13/06/2018
		PointsTotal,
		BSC,
		MBF,
		Initial,
		OngoingTotal,
		OngoingYr01,
		OngoingYr02,
		OngoingYr03,
		OngoingYr04,
		OngoingYr05,
		OngoingYr06,
		OngoingYr07,
		OngoingYr08,
		OngoingYr09,
		OngoingYr10,
		FCARate,
		RetentionRate,
		RetentionRateBroker,
		OngoingServicingRate,
		OngoingServicingSource,
		DA,
		AmountReceived,
		Premium,
		AgentSplit,
		CommissionType,
		CommissionTypeDesc,
		PayBasisCode,					--AG 13/06/2018
		PayBasisDesc,					--AG 13/06/2018
		PaymentMatchedDate,				--AG 13/06/2018
		Month,
		FrequencyCode,
		FrequencyDesc,
		ReassignedProductGroupCode,		--AG 05/06/2018
		ReassignedProductGroupName,		--AG 05/06/2018
		RecognitionType,
		CalculationType,
		Source,
		DateInserted,
		DateLastUpdated,
		CommissionYear
	)
	select	cs.PendingPaymentID as SourceID,
			cs.CaseID,
			cs.TransactionID,
			cs.ExtPolicyNumber as Policy,
			cs.ProductCode,
			cs.BusinessCode,
			cs.AgentCode as SellerCode,				--AG 13/06/2018
			0.0 as PointsTotal,
			0.0 as BSC,
			case 
				when mbf.MortgageFeeID is not null and cs.INIssued <> 0 then (((mbf.AdviceFeeAmount)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * MRbkr.FACTOR) - ((mbf.AdviceFeeAmount)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * Mfca.FACTOR)) --Note that mbf.AdviceFeeAmount is signed correctly - so no coding for signing is needed here
				else 0.0
			end as MBF,
			case 
				--When the adviser has changed, the AgentSplit can become zero in which case the ELITE points should be zero.
				when cs.AgentSplit = 0 then 0
				
				--WEALTH CALCULATION START
				--Indemnity payments or SINGLEs or IC Clawbacks or IC adjustments Start
				when (ph.ProductCategoryCode = 1 or pcc.KeyValue2 = '1') and (cs.FrequencyCode = 6 or cs.PayBasisCode in ('T') or cs.CommissionType in (2,17)) and cs.commissiontype in (1,2,17) and cs.INIssued <> 0 then (((e.AMOUNT_REC)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * Crate.FACTOR) - ((e.AMOUNT_REC)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * Cfca.FACTOR)) * case when cs.INIssued < 0 then -1 else 1 end
				--Indemnity payments or SINGLEs or IC Clawbacks or IC adjustments End
				--Accruals & Level Start
				when (ph.ProductCategoryCode = 1 or pcc.KeyValue2 = '1') and cs.INIssued <> 0 then (((pt.CommInitialAmount)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * Crate.FACTOR) - ((pt.CommInitialAmount)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * Cfca.FACTOR)) * case when cs.INIssued < 0 then -1 else 1 end
				--Accruals & Level End
				--WEALTH CALCULATION END
				
				--MORTGAGE CALCULATION START
				--Note: The MBF component has its own table column
				--Only 1 payment for mortgages
				when ph.ProductGroupCode = 3 and cs.INIssued <> 0 then (((e.AMOUNT_REC)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * MRproc.FACTOR) - ((e.AMOUNT_REC)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * Mfca.FACTOR)) * case when cs.INIssued < 0 then -1 else 1 end	--AG 18/05/2018
				--MORTGAGE CALCULATION END
				
				--PROTECTION CALCULATION START
				--Indemnity payments or SINGLEs or IC Clawbacks or IC adjustments Start
				when ph.ProductGroupCode = 6 and (cs.FrequencyCode = 6 or cs.PayBasisCode in ('T') or cs.CommissionType in (2,17)) and cs.commissiontype in (1,2,17) and cs.INIssued <> 0 then ((abs(e.AMOUNT_REC)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * Prate.FACTOR) - (abs(e.AMOUNT_REC)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * Pfca.FACTOR)) * case when cs.INIssued < 0 then -1 else 1 end	--AG 11/06/2018 (1)
				--Indemnity payments or SINGLEs or IC Clawbacks or IC adjustments End
				--Accruals & Level Start
				when ph.ProductGroupCode = 6 and cs.INIssued <> 0 then (((pt.CommInitialAmount)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * Prate.FACTOR) - ((pt.CommInitialAmount)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * Pfca.FACTOR)) * case when cs.INIssued < 0 then -1 else 1 end
				--Accruals & Level End
				--PROTECTION CALCULATION END

				else 0.0

			end as Initial,
			0.0 as OngoingTotal,
			0.0 as OngoingYr01,
			0.0 as OngoingYr02,
			0.0 as OngoingYr03,
			0.0 as OngoingYr04,
			0.0 as OngoingYr05,
			0.0 as OngoingYr06,
			0.0 as OngoingYr07,
			0.0 as OngoingYr08,
			0.0 as OngoingYr09,
			0.0 as OngoingYr10,
			case 
				when (ph.ProductCategoryCode = 1 or pcc.KeyValue2 = '1') then Cfca.FACTOR*100.0		--COB
				when ph.ProductGroupCode = 3 then Mfca.FACTOR*100.0		--MORT
				when ph.ProductGroupCode = 6 then Pfca.FACTOR*100.0		--PROT
				else 0.0
			end as FCARate,
			case 
				when (ph.ProductCategoryCode = 1 or pcc.KeyValue2 = '1') then Crate.FACTOR*100.0	--COB
				when ph.ProductGroupCode = 3 then MRproc.FACTOR*100.0	--MORT
				when ph.ProductGroupCode = 6 then Prate.FACTOR*100.0	--PROT
				else 0.0
			end as RetentionRate,
			case 
				when mbf.MortgageFeeID is not null then  MRbkr.FACTOR*100.0	
				else 0.0
			end as RetentionRateBroker,
			null as OngoingServicingRate,
			null as OngoingServicingSource,
			pt.CommInitialAmount as DA,
			e.AMOUNT_REC as AmountReceived,
			cs.Premium,
			cs.AgentSplit,
			cs.CommissionType,
			left(cs.StandingOrderDesc,50) as CommissionTypeDesc,
			cs.PayBasisCode,							--AG 13/06/2018
			cs.PayBasisDesc,							--AG 13/06/2018
			cs.CreateDate as PaymentMatchedDate,		--AG 13/06/2018
			cs.Month,
			cs.FrequencyCode,
			cs.FrequencyDesc,
			pg.ProductGroupCode as ReassignedProductGroupCode,	--Force the re-assigned products...		AG 05/06/2018
			pg.ProductGroupName as ReassignedProductGroupName,	--...to be processed as investments		AG 05/06/2018
			'VNB-INI-PHASE-1' as RecognitionType,
			case 
				when (ph.ProductCategoryCode = 1 or pcc.KeyValue2 = '1') then 'WEALTH-INITIAL'
				when ph.ProductGroupCode = 3 then 'MORTGAGE'
				when ph.ProductGroupCode = 6 then 'PROTECTION'
				else null
			end as CalculationType,
			'Openwork 2006' as Source,
			@DateLastUpdated as DateInserted,
			@DateLastUpdated as DateLastUpdated,
			csp.year as CommissionYear
	--select count(*)
	from	msit_CommissionStatement cs
/*			inner join (select	distinct PKID
						from	owt_TransformationMovements tm 
						where	tm.DriverTableName = 'sa_swift_S_AGMFIL'
						and		tm.CommissionStatement = 'Y') tm on tm.PKID = cs.PendingPaymentID
*/			inner join mstt_Agents ag on ag.Code = cs.BusinessCode
			inner join mstt_PolicyTransactions pt on pt.ID = cs.TransactionID
			inner join mstt_Policies p on p.POL_NUM = pt.PolicyID
			inner join msit_CommissionStatementPeriods VNBStart on convert(date,pt.CreateDateTime) between VNBStart.PeriodStartDate and VNBStart.PeriodEndDate
			inner join msit_Commissionstatementperiods csp on csp.month = cs.month
			inner join mstt_ProductHierarchy ph on ph.productcode = cs.productcode
			inner join mstt_Expectation e on e.ID = cs.ExpectationID
			left join dbo.owt_MortgageBrokerFees mbf on mbf.PendingPaymentID = cs.PendingPaymentID and mbf.AdviceFeeCharged = 'Yes'
			left join owt_SelectionControl SC
						on SC.Process = 'ElitePoints' 
						and SC.KeyType = 'NSCPotCode' 
						and cs.CreateDate between SC.EffectiveStartDate and SC.EffectiveEndDate
			left join mstt_Commissions BSCpot
						on BSCpot.TransactionID = cs.TransactionID 
						and BSCpot.Agent_Code = sc.KeyValue
						and BSCpot.CommissionType = 10
			left join owt_SelectionControl SFMPC						
						on SFMPC.Process = 'ElitePoints' 
						and SFMPC.KeyType = 'ServicingFeeMarginPotCode' 
						and cs.CreateDate between SFMPC.EffectiveStartDate and SFMPC.EffectiveEndDate
			left join mstt_Commissions SFMpot							
						on SFMpot.TransactionID = cs.TransactionID 
						and SFMpot.Agent_Code = SFMPC.KeyValue
						and SFMpot.CommissionType = 10	
			left join owt_SelectionControl pcc 
						on pcc.Process = 'ElitePoints'
						and pcc.KeyType = 'ProductCategoryCode'
						and pcc.KeyValue = cs.ProductCode	
						and cs.CreateDate between pcc.EffectiveStartDate and pcc.EffectiveEndDate
			left join owt_SelectionControl ogsdflt 
						on ogsdflt.Process = 'ElitePoints'
						and ogsdflt.KeyType = 'DefaultOngoingServicingRate'
						and ogsdflt.SelectionType = 'VNB'
						and ogsdflt.KeyValue = case when ph.RDRType = 'ONPLAT' then 'ONPLAT' else 'OFPLAT' end
						and cs.CreateDate between ogsdflt.EffectiveStartDate and ogsdflt.EffectiveEndDate
			left join mstt_CodeProductGroup pg on pg.ProductGroupCode = case when pcc.KeyValue2 = '1' then 2 else ph.ProductGroupCode end
			left join owt_EliteFactors Cfca on Cfca.FeeType = 'VNB' and Cfca.category = 'COB-FCA-RATE' and csp.year between Cfca.StartYear and Cfca.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors Crate on Crate.FeeType = 'VNB' and Crate.category = 'COB-RETENTION-RATE' and csp.year between Crate.StartYear and Crate.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors Mfca on Mfca.FeeType = 'VNB' and Mfca.category = 'MORT-FCA-RATE' and csp.year between Mfca.StartYear and Mfca.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors MRproc on MRproc.FeeType = 'VNB' and MRproc.category = 'MORT-RETENTION-RATE-PROC' and csp.year between MRproc.StartYear and MRproc.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors MRbkr on MRbkr.FeeType = 'VNB' and MRbkr.category = 'MORT-RETENTION-RATE-BROKER' and csp.year between MRbkr.StartYear and MRbkr.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors Pfca on Pfca.FeeType = 'VNB' and Pfca.category = 'PROT-FCA-RATE' and csp.year between Pfca.StartYear and Pfca.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors Prate on Prate.FeeType = 'VNB' and Prate.category = 'PROT-RETENTION-RATE' and csp.year between Prate.StartYear and Prate.EndYear 
			left join msit_CommissionStatement csadj 
						on csadj.TransactionID = cs.TransactionID 
						and csadj.AgentCode = cs.AgentCode 
						and csadj.CommissionType in (2,17)
						and	csadj.PayBasisCode in ('F')				--Accrual
						and	csadj.FrequencyCode <> 6				--Regular 
	where	cs.ReportingClassCode = 1
	and		ag.Manager2Code <> @OwlManager2Code		--Exclude Owl
	and		cs.INIssued <> 0
	and		csp.Year >= 2017						--Ensure in-scope payments are consistent with VNB start
	and		VNBStart.Year >= 2017
	and		cs.CommissionType in (1,2,17)
	and		abs(e.AMOUNT_REC) >= 0.01	
	--and		((VNBStart.Year >= 2017 and cs.CommissionType = 1 and e.AMOUNT_REC >= 0.01)		--VNB to start from new slices in 2017 for +ve payments but...			AG 11/06/2018 (2)
	--		or (cs.CommissionType in (2,17) or e.AMOUNT_REC <= -0.01))						--...for -ve payments, the slice can start from any date in the past	AG 11/06/2018 (2)
	and		csadj.ID is null						--Deal with accrual regular clawbacks/adjustments later

	select @RowCount = @@rowcount
	set @ProcessMessage = '#owt_Recognition (ini ph1 - no accr adj) = ' + convert(nvarchar(10), @RowCount)
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseLog, @ProcessMessage, null, @Module, @Client

	/****************************************************************************

		Now deal with accrual clawbacks and adjustments
																		
	****************************************************************************/

	--drop table #msit_CommissionStatementSUMMARY

	create table #msit_CommissionStatementSUMMARY
	(
		TransactionID						int,
		AgentCode							varchar(7),
		MinInitialPendingPaymentID			varchar(10),
		MaxInitialPendingPaymentID			varchar(10),	
		MaxAdjPendingPaymentID				varchar(10),
		MinInitialAfterAdjPendingPaymentID	varchar(10)
	)

	--Find transactions with clawbacks/adj on them
	insert into #msit_CommissionStatementSUMMARY
	(
		TransactionID,
		AgentCode,
		MinInitialPendingPaymentID,
		MaxInitialPendingPaymentID,	
		MaxAdjPendingPaymentID,
		MinInitialAfterAdjPendingPaymentID
	)
	select	cs.TransactionID,
			cs.AgentCode,
			Min(case when cs.CommissionType = 1 then cs.PendingPaymentID else null end) as MinInitialPendingPaymentID,
			MAX(case when cs.CommissionType = 1 then cs.PendingPaymentID else null end) as MaxInitialPendingPaymentID,
			MAX(case when cs.CommissionType in (2,17) then cs.PendingPaymentID else null end) as MaxAdjPendingPaymentID,
			null as MinInitialAfterAdjPendingPaymentID
	--into	#msit_CommissionStatementSUMMARY
	from	msit_CommissionStatement cs
			inner join mstt_Agents ag on ag.Code = cs.BusinessCode
			inner join mstt_PolicyTransactions pt on pt.ID = cs.TransactionID
			inner join mstt_Policies p on p.POL_NUM = pt.PolicyID
			inner join msit_CommissionStatementPeriods VNBStart on convert(date,pt.CreateDateTime) between VNBStart.PeriodStartDate and VNBStart.PeriodEndDate
			inner join msit_Commissionstatementperiods csp on csp.month = cs.month
			inner join mstt_Expectation e on e.ID = cs.ExpectationID
			left join msit_CommissionStatement csadj 
						on csadj.TransactionID = cs.TransactionID 
						and csadj.AgentCode = cs.AgentCode 
						and csadj.CommissionType in (2,17)
						and	csadj.PayBasisCode in ('F')				--Accrual
						and	csadj.FrequencyCode <> 6				--Regular 
	where	cs.ReportingClassCode = 1
	and		cs.CommissionType in (1,2,17)			--We want all the initial payment types (i.e. not trail (ongoing))
	and		ag.Manager2Code <> @OwlManager2Code		--Exclude Owl
	and		csp.Year >= 2017						--Ensure in-scope payments are consistent with VNB start
	and		VNBStart.Year >= 2017 
	and		abs(e.AMOUNT_REC) >= 0.01	
	and		csadj.ID is not null					--select regular accrual transactions with clawbacks/adjustments
	--and cs.TransactionID in (5613333,6296827)
	group by	cs.TransactionID,
				cs.AgentCode

	select @RowCount = @@rowcount
	set @ProcessMessage = '#msit_CommissionStatementSUMMARY (accr adj txns) = ' + convert(nvarchar(10), @RowCount)
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseLog, @ProcessMessage, null, @Module, @Client

	--Get first initial payment after last clawback/adj
	update css
		set MinInitialAfterAdjPendingPaymentID = summ.MinPendingPaymentID 
	from  #msit_CommissionStatementSUMMARY css
			inner join  (
						select cssinner.TransactionID, cssinner.AgentCode, min(cs.PendingPaymentID) as MinPendingPaymentID
						from #msit_CommissionStatementSUMMARY cssinner
								inner join msit_CommissionStatement cs
											on cs.TransactionID = cssinner.TransactionID
											and cs.AgentCode = cssinner.AgentCode
						where cs.PendingPaymentID > cssinner.MaxAdjPendingPaymentID
						group by cssinner.TransactionID, cssinner.AgentCode
						) summ on  summ.TransactionID = css.TransactionID
							   and summ.AgentCode = css.AgentCode

	select @RowCount = @@rowcount
	set @ProcessMessage = '#msit_CommissionStatementSUMMARY (1st IC after adj) = ' + convert(nvarchar(10), @RowCount)
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseLog, @ProcessMessage, null, @Module, @Client

	/****************************************************************************

		Phase 2 - This phase deals with regular accrual cases where there is at 
		least one clawback/adjustment. In this scenario the VNB is changed from 
		front loaded to a per payment basis.
																		
	****************************************************************************/

	insert into #AG_owt_Recognition_SEPARATE_ONGOING
	(
		SourceID,
		CaseID,
		TransactionID,
		Policy,
		ProductCode,
		BusinessCode,
		SellerCode,						
		PointsTotal,
		BSC,
		MBF,
		Initial,
		OngoingTotal,
		OngoingYr01,
		OngoingYr02,
		OngoingYr03,
		OngoingYr04,
		OngoingYr05,
		OngoingYr06,
		OngoingYr07,
		OngoingYr08,
		OngoingYr09,
		OngoingYr10,
		FCARate,
		RetentionRate,
		RetentionRateBroker,
		OngoingServicingRate,
		OngoingServicingSource,
		DA,
		AmountReceived,
		Premium,
		AgentSplit,
		CommissionType,
		CommissionTypeDesc,
		PayBasisCode,					
		PayBasisDesc,					
		PaymentMatchedDate,				
		Month,
		FrequencyCode,
		FrequencyDesc,
		ReassignedProductGroupCode,		
		ReassignedProductGroupName,		
		RecognitionType,
		CalculationType,
		Source,
		DateInserted,
		DateLastUpdated,
		CommissionYear
	)
	select	cs.PendingPaymentID as SourceID,
			cs.CaseID,
			cs.TransactionID,
			cs.ExtPolicyNumber as Policy,
			cs.ProductCode,
			cs.BusinessCode,
			cs.AgentCode as SellerCode,				
			0.0 as PointsTotal,
			0.0 as BSC,
			case 
				when mbf.MortgageFeeID is not null and cs.INIssued <> 0 then (((mbf.AdviceFeeAmount)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * MRbkr.FACTOR) - ((mbf.AdviceFeeAmount)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * Mfca.FACTOR)) --Note that mbf.AdviceFeeAmount is signed correctly - so no coding for signing is needed here
				else 0.0
			end as MBF,
			case 
				--When the adviser has changed, the AgentSplit can become zero in which case the ELITE points should be zero.
				when cs.AgentSplit = 0 then 0
				
				--WEALTH CALCULATION START
				--Indemnity payments or SINGLEs or IC Clawbacks or IC adjustments Start
				--THIS SCENARIO DOESN'T OCCUR IN PHASE 2
				--Indemnity payments or SINGLEs or IC Clawbacks or IC adjustments End
				--Accruals & Level Start
				when (ph.ProductCategoryCode = 1 or pcc.KeyValue2 = '1') then (((e.AMOUNT_REC)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * Crate.FACTOR) - ((e.AMOUNT_REC)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * Cfca.FACTOR)) * case when cs.CommissionType in (2,17) then -1 else 1 end
				--Accruals & Level End
				--WEALTH CALCULATION END
				
				--MORTGAGE CALCULATION START
				--Note: The MBF component has its own table column
				--Only 1 payment for mortgages
				when ph.ProductGroupCode = 3 then (((e.AMOUNT_REC)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * MRproc.FACTOR) - ((e.AMOUNT_REC)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * Mfca.FACTOR)) * case when cs.CommissionType in (2,17) then -1 else 1 end	
				--MORTGAGE CALCULATION END
				
				--PROTECTION CALCULATION START
				--Indemnity payments or SINGLEs or IC Clawbacks or IC adjustments Start
				--THIS SCENARIO DOESN'T OCCUR IN PHASE 2
				--Indemnity payments or SINGLEs or IC Clawbacks or IC adjustments End
				--Accruals & Level Start
				when ph.ProductGroupCode = 6 then (((e.AMOUNT_REC)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * Prate.FACTOR) - ((e.AMOUNT_REC)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * Pfca.FACTOR)) * case when cs.CommissionType in (2,17) then -1 else 1 end
				--Accruals & Level End
				--PROTECTION CALCULATION END

				else 0.0

			end as Initial,
			0.0 as OngoingTotal,
			0.0 as OngoingYr01,
			0.0 as OngoingYr02,
			0.0 as OngoingYr03,
			0.0 as OngoingYr04,
			0.0 as OngoingYr05,
			0.0 as OngoingYr06,
			0.0 as OngoingYr07,
			0.0 as OngoingYr08,
			0.0 as OngoingYr09,
			0.0 as OngoingYr10,
			case 
				when (ph.ProductCategoryCode = 1 or pcc.KeyValue2 = '1') then Cfca.FACTOR*100.0		--COB
				when ph.ProductGroupCode = 3 then Mfca.FACTOR*100.0		--MORT
				when ph.ProductGroupCode = 6 then Pfca.FACTOR*100.0		--PROT
				else 0.0
			end as FCARate,
			case 
				when (ph.ProductCategoryCode = 1 or pcc.KeyValue2 = '1') then Crate.FACTOR*100.0	--COB
				when ph.ProductGroupCode = 3 then MRproc.FACTOR*100.0	--MORT
				when ph.ProductGroupCode = 6 then Prate.FACTOR*100.0	--PROT
				else 0.0
			end as RetentionRate,
			case 
				when mbf.MortgageFeeID is not null then  MRbkr.FACTOR*100.0	
				else 0.0
			end as RetentionRateBroker,
			null as OngoingServicingRate,
			null as OngoingServicingSource,
			pt.CommInitialAmount as DA,
			e.AMOUNT_REC as AmountReceived,
			cs.Premium,
			cs.AgentSplit,
			cs.CommissionType,
			left(cs.StandingOrderDesc,50) as CommissionTypeDesc,
			cs.PayBasisCode,							
			cs.PayBasisDesc,							
			cs.CreateDate as PaymentMatchedDate,		
			cs.Month,
			cs.FrequencyCode,
			cs.FrequencyDesc,
			pg.ProductGroupCode as ReassignedProductGroupCode,	--Force the re-assigned products...		
			pg.ProductGroupName as ReassignedProductGroupName,	--...to be processed as investments		
			'VNB-INI-PHASE-2' as RecognitionType,
			case 
				when (ph.ProductCategoryCode = 1 or pcc.KeyValue2 = '1') then 'WEALTH-INITIAL'
				when ph.ProductGroupCode = 3 then 'MORTGAGE'
				when ph.ProductGroupCode = 6 then 'PROTECTION'
				else null
			end as CalculationType,
			'Openwork 2006' as Source,
			@DateLastUpdated as DateInserted,
			@DateLastUpdated as DateLastUpdated,
			csp.year as CommissionYear
	from	#msit_CommissionStatementSUMMARY css
			inner join msit_CommissionStatement cs
						on cs.TransactionID = css.TransactionID
						and cs.AgentCode = css.AgentCode
			inner join mstt_Agents ag on ag.Code = cs.BusinessCode
			inner join mstt_PolicyTransactions pt on pt.ID = cs.TransactionID
			inner join mstt_Policies p on p.POL_NUM = pt.PolicyID
			inner join msit_CommissionStatementPeriods VNBStart on convert(date,pt.CreateDateTime) between VNBStart.PeriodStartDate and VNBStart.PeriodEndDate
			inner join msit_Commissionstatementperiods csp on csp.month = cs.month
			inner join mstt_ProductHierarchy ph on ph.productcode = cs.productcode
			inner join mstt_Expectation e on e.ID = cs.ExpectationID
			left join dbo.owt_MortgageBrokerFees mbf on mbf.PendingPaymentID = cs.PendingPaymentID and mbf.AdviceFeeCharged = 'Yes'
			left join owt_SelectionControl SC
						on SC.Process = 'ElitePoints' 
						and SC.KeyType = 'NSCPotCode' 
						and cs.CreateDate between SC.EffectiveStartDate and SC.EffectiveEndDate
			left join mstt_Commissions BSCpot
						on BSCpot.TransactionID = cs.TransactionID 
						and BSCpot.Agent_Code = sc.KeyValue
						and BSCpot.CommissionType = 10
			left join owt_SelectionControl SFMPC						
						on SFMPC.Process = 'ElitePoints' 
						and SFMPC.KeyType = 'ServicingFeeMarginPotCode' 
						and cs.CreateDate between SFMPC.EffectiveStartDate and SFMPC.EffectiveEndDate
			left join mstt_Commissions SFMpot							
						on SFMpot.TransactionID = cs.TransactionID 
						and SFMpot.Agent_Code = SFMPC.KeyValue
						and SFMpot.CommissionType = 10	
			left join owt_SelectionControl pcc 
						on pcc.Process = 'ElitePoints'
						and pcc.KeyType = 'ProductCategoryCode'
						and pcc.KeyValue = cs.ProductCode	
						and cs.CreateDate between pcc.EffectiveStartDate and pcc.EffectiveEndDate
			left join owt_SelectionControl ogsdflt 
						on ogsdflt.Process = 'ElitePoints'
						and ogsdflt.KeyType = 'DefaultOngoingServicingRate'
						and ogsdflt.SelectionType = 'VNB'
						and ogsdflt.KeyValue = case when ph.RDRType = 'ONPLAT' then 'ONPLAT' else 'OFPLAT' end
						and cs.CreateDate between ogsdflt.EffectiveStartDate and ogsdflt.EffectiveEndDate
			left join mstt_CodeProductGroup pg on pg.ProductGroupCode = case when pcc.KeyValue2 = '1' then 2 else ph.ProductGroupCode end
			left join owt_EliteFactors Cfca on Cfca.FeeType = 'VNB' and Cfca.category = 'COB-FCA-RATE' and csp.year between Cfca.StartYear and Cfca.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors Crate on Crate.FeeType = 'VNB' and Crate.category = 'COB-RETENTION-RATE' and csp.year between Crate.StartYear and Crate.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors Mfca on Mfca.FeeType = 'VNB' and Mfca.category = 'MORT-FCA-RATE' and csp.year between Mfca.StartYear and Mfca.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors MRproc on MRproc.FeeType = 'VNB' and MRproc.category = 'MORT-RETENTION-RATE-PROC' and csp.year between MRproc.StartYear and MRproc.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors MRbkr on MRbkr.FeeType = 'VNB' and MRbkr.category = 'MORT-RETENTION-RATE-BROKER' and csp.year between MRbkr.StartYear and MRbkr.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors Pfca on Pfca.FeeType = 'VNB' and Pfca.category = 'PROT-FCA-RATE' and csp.year between Pfca.StartYear and Pfca.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors Prate on Prate.FeeType = 'VNB' and Prate.category = 'PROT-RETENTION-RATE' and csp.year between Prate.StartYear and Prate.EndYear 
	where	cs.ReportingClassCode = 1
	and		cs.CommissionType in (1,2,17)			--We want all the initial payment types (i.e. not trail (ongoing))
	and		ag.Manager2Code <> @OwlManager2Code		--Exclude Owl

	select @RowCount = @@rowcount
	set @ProcessMessage = '#owt_Recognition (ini ph2 - accr adj) = ' + convert(nvarchar(10), @RowCount)
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseLog, @ProcessMessage, null, @Module, @Client

	/****************************************************************************

		Initial Phase 3
		1) Add up the +ves and -ves prior to the NEW front loaded amount and
			net them off on the first +ve following the last -ve
		2) Now set all the +ves following the one updated in (1) to zero.
																
	****************************************************************************/

	update r
		set RecognitionType	= case when r.SourceID >= css.MinInitialAfterAdjPendingPaymentID 
								then 'VNB-INI-PHASE-3'
								else r.RecognitionType
							  end,
			Initial = case  when r.SourceID = css.MinInitialAfterAdjPendingPaymentID 
								then (((r.DA)*(r.AgentSplit/100) * (r.RetentionRate/100.0)) - ((r.DA)*(r.AgentSplit/100) * (r.FCARate/100))) - derived.SumInitial
							when r.SourceID > css.MinInitialAfterAdjPendingPaymentID 
								then 0.0
							else r.Initial
					  end,
			DateLastUpdated = @DateLastUpdated
	from	#msit_CommissionStatementSUMMARY css
			inner join #AG_owt_Recognition_SEPARATE_ONGOING r
						on r.TransactionID = css.TransactionID
						and r.SellerCode = css.AgentCode
			inner join (select	r.TransactionID, r.SellerCode, SUM(Initial) as SumInitial
						from	#msit_CommissionStatementSUMMARY s
								inner join #AG_owt_Recognition_SEPARATE_ONGOING r 
											on r.TransactionID = s.TransactionID
											and r.SellerCode = s.AgentCode
						where	r.SourceID <= s.MaxAdjPendingPaymentID
						group	by r.TransactionID, r.SellerCode
						) derived 
							on  derived.TransactionID = r.TransactionID
							and	derived.SellerCode = r.SellerCode 
	where	isnull(css.MaxInitialPendingPaymentID,0) > isnull(css.MaxAdjPendingPaymentID,0)-- An initial payment follows the clawback, so time to revert back to front loading

	select @RowCount = @@rowcount
	set @ProcessMessage = '#owt_Recognition (ini ph3 - accr adj) = ' + convert(nvarchar(10), @RowCount)
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseLog, @ProcessMessage, null, @Module, @Client

	/****************************************************************************

		Now do the ongoing.
		
		Build an ongoing summary row for each transaction (slice).
		
		Note we do not care about ongoing clawbacks and adjustments for VNB.
		We want VNB to be on the oldest positive payment on each slice for the
		policy (split by adviser if needed).
						
	****************************************************************************/

	create table #msit_CommissionStatementOGSSUMMARY
	(
		CaseID								varchar(10),
		TransactionID						varchar(10),
		AgentCode							varchar(7),
		AgentSplit							float,
		MinOngoingPendingPaymentID			varchar(10),
		MaxOngoingPendingPaymentID			varchar(10),
		MaxOngoingAdjPendingPaymentID		varchar(10),
		MaxPremium							float,
		MinOngoingAfterAdjPendingPaymentID	varchar(10),
		Premium								float,						
		FrequencyCode						tinyint,
		FrequencyDesc						varchar(20)
	)

	insert into #msit_CommissionStatementOGSSUMMARY
	(
		CaseID,
		TransactionID,
		AgentCode,
		AgentSplit,
		MinOngoingPendingPaymentID,
		MaxOngoingPendingPaymentID,
		MaxOngoingAdjPendingPaymentID,
		MaxPremium,
		MinOngoingAfterAdjPendingPaymentID,
		Premium,						
		FrequencyCode,
		FrequencyDesc
	)
	select	cs.CaseID,
			cs.TransactionID,
			cs.AgentCode,
			c.AGENT_PERC as AgentSplit,
			min(case when cs.CommissionType = 10 then cs.PendingPaymentID else null end) as MinOngoingPendingPaymentID,
			max(case when cs.CommissionType = 10 then cs.PendingPaymentID else null end) as MaxOngoingPendingPaymentID,
			max(case when cs.CommissionType in (16,19) then cs.PendingPaymentID else null end) as MaxOngoingAdjPendingPaymentID,
			max(case when cs.CommissionType = 10 then case when cs.FrequencyCode <> 6 then (cs.Premium * 12.0 * (c.Agent_Perc/100)) else (cs.Premium * (c.Agent_Perc/100)) end else 0.0 end) as MaxPremium,	--AG 19/07/2018
			null as MinOngoingAfterAdjPendingPaymentID,
			cs.Premium,			--AG 17/07/2018
			cs.FrequencyCode,	--AG 17/07/2018
			cs.FrequencyDesc	--AG 17/07/2018
	--into	#msit_CommissionStatementOGSSUMMARY
	from 	msit_CommissionStatement cs
			inner join mstt_Commissions c
						on c.TransactionID = cs.TransactionID
						and c.Agent_Code = cs.AgentCode
						and c.CommissionType = 1
			inner join mstt_Agents ag on ag.Code = cs.BusinessCode
			inner join mstt_PolicyTransactions pt on pt.ID = cs.TransactionID
			inner join mstt_Policies p on p.POL_NUM = pt.PolicyID
			inner join msit_CommissionStatementPeriods VNBStart on convert(date,pt.CreateDateTime) between VNBStart.PeriodStartDate and VNBStart.PeriodEndDate
			inner join msit_Commissionstatementperiods csp on csp.month = cs.month
			inner join mstt_ProductHierarchy ph on ph.productcode = cs.productcode
			inner join mstt_Expectation e on e.ID = cs.ExpectationID
			left join owt_SelectionControl pcc 
						on pcc.Process = 'ElitePoints'
						and pcc.KeyType = 'ProductCategoryCode'
						and pcc.KeyValue = cs.ProductCode	
						and cs.CreateDate between pcc.EffectiveStartDate and pcc.EffectiveEndDate
	where	cs.ReportingClassCode = 1
	and		cs.CommissionType in (10,16,19)					--Choose only where the ongoing payment is positive
	and		cs.CommFeeType = 'Ongoing'
	and		(ph.ProductCategoryCode = 1 or pcc.KeyValue2 = '1')
	and		ag.Manager2Code <> @OwlManager2Code		--Exclude Owl
	and		csp.Year >= 2017						--Ensure in-scope payments are consistent with VNB start
	and		VNBStart.Year >= 2017 
	and		abs(e.AMOUNT_REC) >= 0.01
	and		((cs.FrequencyCode = 6 and cs.Premium > 1.00)		--Frequency=6->Single
			or (cs.FrequencyCode <> 6 and cs.Premium > 0.01))	--Frequency<>6->Regular	
	group by	cs.CaseID,
				cs.TransactionID,
				cs.AgentCode,
				c.Agent_Perc,
				cs.Premium,			--AG 17/07/2018
				cs.FrequencyCode,	--AG 17/07/2018
				cs.FrequencyDesc	--AG 17/07/2018

	select @RowCount = @@rowcount
	set @ProcessMessage = '#msit_CommissionStatementOGSSUMMARY (ogs txn) = ' + convert(nvarchar(10), @RowCount)
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseLog, @ProcessMessage, null, @Module, @Client

	--Get first ongoing payment after last clawback/adj
	update cso
		set MinOngoingAfterAdjPendingPaymentID = summ.MinPendingPaymentID 
	from  #msit_CommissionStatementOGSSUMMARY cso
			inner join  (
						select	csoinner.TransactionID, csoinner.AgentCode, min(cs.PendingPaymentID) as MinPendingPaymentID
						from	#msit_CommissionStatementOGSSUMMARY csoinner
								inner join msit_CommissionStatement cs
											on cs.TransactionID = csoinner.TransactionID
											and cs.AgentCode = csoinner.AgentCode
						where	cs.PendingPaymentID > csoinner.MaxOngoingAdjPendingPaymentID
						and		cs.CommissionType = 10
						group by csoinner.TransactionID, csoinner.AgentCode
						) summ on  summ.TransactionID = cso.TransactionID
							   and summ.AgentCode = cso.AgentCode

	select @RowCount = @@rowcount
	set @ProcessMessage = '#msit_CommissionStatementOGSSUMMARY (ogs latest +ve) = ' + convert(nvarchar(10), @RowCount)
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseLog, @ProcessMessage, null, @Module, @Client

	/****************************************************************************
		
		Using the OGS SUMMARY table, get all the individual payment records that
		will be carriers of VNB points as follows:
		
		SelectionSource 1 - The oldest +ve payment where no clawbacks or 
								adjustments occur for front loading

		SelectionSource 2 - All the +ve payments that will get a spread of the 
								per payment +ve points 		

		SelectionSource 3 - All the -ve payments that will get a spread of the 
								per payment -ve points
								 															
	****************************************************************************/
	
	--AG 19/07/2018
	--Combine the premium on all the transactions (slices) for each case and seller
	--In case of mixed frequencies, force the sum to be a single
	create table #PremiumTotal
	(
		CaseID						int,
		SellerCode					varchar(7),
		InitialSumOfPremium			float,
		OngoingSumOfPremium			float,	
		MinOngoingPendingPaymentID	varchar(10)
	)

	insert into #PremiumTotal
	(
		CaseID,
		SellerCode,
		InitialSumOfPremium,
		OngoingSumOfPremium,	
		MinOngoingPendingPaymentID
	)
	select	CaseID,
			SellerCode,
			sum(case when CommissionType = 1 then SumOfPremium else 0 end) as InitialSumOfPremium,
			sum(case when CommissionType = 10 then SumOfPremium else 0 end) as OngoingSumOfPremium,
			min(case when CommissionType = 10 then MinOngoingPendingPaymentID end) as MinOngoingPendingPaymentID
	--into	#PremiumTotal
	from
		(
		select	CaseID,
				SellerCode,
				1 as CommissionType,						--IC
				min(SourceID) as MinOngoingPendingPaymentID,
				sum(case when FrequencyCode <> 6 then Premium * 12.0 * (AgentSplit/100) else Premium * (AgentSplit/100) end) as SumOfPremium
		from	#AG_owt_Recognition_SEPARATE_ONGOING
		where	CalculationType = 'WEALTH-INITIAL'
		and		CommissionType = 1
		group	by CaseID, SellerCode
		
		union
		
		select	CaseID,
				AgentCode as SellerCode,
				10 as CommissionType,						--Trail (OGS)
				min(MinOngoingPendingPaymentID) as MinOngoingPendingPaymentID,
				sum(MaxPremium) as SumOfPremium
		from	#msit_CommissionStatementOGSSUMMARY
		group	by CaseID, AgentCode
		) a
	group by CaseID, SellerCode

	select @RowCount = @@rowcount
	set @ProcessMessage = '#PremiumTotal = ' + convert(nvarchar(10), @RowCount)
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseLog, @ProcessMessage, null, @Module, @Client
	
	create table #msit_CommissionStatementONGOING
	(
		SelectionSource		int,
		TransactionID		varchar(10),
		AgentCode			varchar(7),
		PendingPaymentID	varchar(10),
		AgentSplit			decimal(8,4),
		Premium				decimal(16,2),
		FrequencyCode		tinyint,
		SpreadNumber		int,
		MaxSpread			int
	)
	
	--Front loaded -> Just the oldest +ve payment
	--Note: These transactions have NO clawbacks or adjustments
	insert into #msit_CommissionStatementONGOING
	(
		SelectionSource,
		TransactionID,
		AgentCode,
		PendingPaymentID,
		AgentSplit,
		Premium,
		FrequencyCode,
		SpreadNumber,
		MaxSpread
	)
	select	1 as SelectionSource,
			cso.TransactionID,
			cso.AgentCode,
			cso.MinOngoingPendingPaymentID as PendingPaymentID,
			cso.AgentSplit,
			case when ptot.CaseID is null
				then cso.Premium
				else	case when	ptot.MinOngoingPendingPaymentID = cso.MinOngoingPendingPaymentID 
									and ptot.InitialSumOfPremium - ptot.OngoingSumOfPremium > 0.0 
							then	cso.Premium + ptot.InitialSumOfPremium - ptot.OngoingSumOfPremium 
							else	cso.Premium 
						end	--AG 19/07/2018
			end as Premium,
			case when ptot.CaseID is null
				then cso.FrequencyCode
				else 6					--Single - had to be hardcoded because proc kept failing when column was used. Weird but true.
			end as FrequencyCode,
			1 as SpreadNumber,
			1 as MaxSpread 
	--into	#msit_CommissionStatementONGOING
	from	#msit_CommissionStatementOGSSUMMARY cso	
			left join mstt_PolicyTransactions pt on pt.ID = cso.TransactionID
			left join mstt_Policies p on p.POL_NUM = pt.PolicyID
			left join #PremiumTotal ptot				--When NO clawbacks or adjustments, the seller gets credit for the combined premium
						on ptot.CaseID = p.PolicyRef
						and ptot.SellerCode = cso.AgentCode
	where	cso.MaxOngoingAdjPendingPaymentID is null	--No clawbacks or adjustments - so front load
	and		cso.MinOngoingPendingPaymentID is not null	--At least one +ve payment on the transaction

	union	--Add in with dedupe
	
	--Per payment -> all +ve payments with max spread also used for divisor
	--Note: ALL these transactions have clawbacks or adjustments
	select	2 as SelectionSource,
			cso.TransactionID,
			cso.AgentCode,
			cs.PendingPaymentID,
			cso.AgentSplit,
			cso.Premium,
			cso.FrequencyCode,
			ROW_NUMBER() over (partition by cs.TransactionID, cs.AgentCode order by cs.TransactionID, cs.AgentCode, cs.PendingPaymentID) as SpreadNumber,
			12 as MaxSpread
	from	#msit_CommissionStatementOGSSUMMARY cso	
			inner join msit_CommissionStatement cs 
						on cs.TransactionID = cso.TransactionID
						and cs.AgentCode = cso.AgentCode
	where	cso.MaxOngoingAdjPendingPaymentID is not null	--Clawbacks or adjustments so per payment
	and		cs.CommissionType in (10)	

	union	--Add in with dedupe
	
	--Per payment -> all -ve payments - with max spread also used for divisor
	--Note: ALL these transactions have clawbacks or adjustments
	select	3 as SelectionSource,
			cso.TransactionID,
			cso.AgentCode,
			cs.PendingPaymentID,
			cso.AgentSplit,
			cso.Premium,
			cso.FrequencyCode,
			ROW_NUMBER() over (partition by cs.TransactionID, cs.AgentCode order by cs.TransactionID, cs.AgentCode, cs.PendingPaymentID) as SpreadNumber,
			12 as MaxSpread
	from	#msit_CommissionStatementOGSSUMMARY cso	
			inner join msit_CommissionStatement cs 
						on cs.TransactionID = cso.TransactionID
						and cs.AgentCode = cso.AgentCode
	where	cso.MaxOngoingAdjPendingPaymentID is not null	--Clawbacks or adjustments so per payment
	and		cs.CommissionType in (16,19)	

	select @RowCount = @@rowcount
	set @ProcessMessage = '#msit_CommissionStatementONGOING (ogs payments) = ' + convert(nvarchar(10), @RowCount)
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseLog, @ProcessMessage, null, @Module, @Client

	/****************************************************************************
		
		Insert the ongoing VNB results for those transactions 
																		
	****************************************************************************/

	insert into #AG_owt_Recognition_SEPARATE_ONGOING
	(
		SourceID,
		CaseID,
		TransactionID,
		Policy,
		ProductCode,
		BusinessCode,
		SellerCode,
		PointsTotal,
		BSC,
		MBF,
		Initial,
		OngoingTotal,
		OngoingYr01,
		OngoingYr02,
		OngoingYr03,
		OngoingYr04,
		OngoingYr05,
		OngoingYr06,
		OngoingYr07,
		OngoingYr08,
		OngoingYr09,
		OngoingYr10,
		FCARate,
		RetentionRate,
		RetentionRateBroker,
		OngoingServicingRate,
		OngoingServicingSource,
		DA,
		AmountReceived,
		Premium,
		AgentSplit,
		CommissionType,
		CommissionTypeDesc,
		PayBasisCode,
		PayBasisDesc,
		PaymentMatchedDate,
		Month,
		FrequencyCode,
		FrequencyDesc,
		ReassignedProductGroupCode,
		ReassignedProductGroupName,
		RecognitionType,
		CalculationType,
		Source,
		DateInserted,
		DateLastUpdated,
		CommissionYear
	)
	select	cs.PendingPaymentID as SourceID,
			cs.CaseID,
			cs.TransactionID,
			cs.ExtPolicyNumber as Policy,
			cs.ProductCode,
			cs.BusinessCode,
			cs.AgentCode as SellerCode,
			0.0 as PointsTotal,
			case
				when BSCpot.ID is not null then 
					--BSC takes the first 0.12 of the ongoing fee %. If the ongoing fee % is 0.12% or less, then 100% of the ongoing fee is allocated to BSC
					case when coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2)) - convert(decimal(8,4),sc.KeyValue2) >= 0.01
						then 
							case when cso.FrequencyCode = 2	--Monthly 
								then (cso.AgentSplit/100) * 12.0 * (isnull(cso.Premium/cso.MaxSpread,0)/2.0) * convert(decimal(8,4),sc.KeyValue3) * case when cs.CommissionType in (16,19) then -1 else 1 end
								else (cso.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(cso.Premium/cso.MaxSpread,0) * convert(decimal(8,4),sc.KeyValue3) * case when cs.CommissionType in (16,19) then -1 else 1 end
							end			
						else
							case when cso.FrequencyCode = 2	--Monthly 
								then (cso.AgentSplit/100) * 12.0 * (isnull(cso.Premium/cso.MaxSpread,0)/2.0) * coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2)) * case when cs.CommissionType in (16,19) then -1 else 1 end
								else (cso.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(cso.Premium/cso.MaxSpread,0) * (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))/100.0) * case when cs.CommissionType in (16,19) then -1 else 1 end
							end
					end
				else 0.0
			end as BSC,
			0.0 as MBF,
			0.0 as Initial,
			0.0 as OngoingTotal,
			case
				--WEALTH ONGOING CALCULATION START
				--When the adviser has changed, the AgentSplit can become zero in which case the ELITE points should be zero.
				when cso.AgentSplit = 0 then 0

				--SINGLE start
				--Calculate when BSC and ongoing applies (where ongoing rate is greater than BSC rate) 
				when cso.FrequencyCode = 6 and SFMpot.ID is not null and BSCpot.ID is not null and (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2)) - convert(decimal(8,4),sc.KeyValue2)) >= 0.01 then 
							--(AUM X BSC Rate)...
							((cso.AgentSplit/100) * (isnull(cso.Premium/cso.MaxSpread,0) * convert(decimal(8,4),sc.KeyValue3)) 
							--(AUM X OGS Rate X COB FCA Rate)...
							- ((cso.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(cso.Premium/cso.MaxSpread,0) * (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))/100.0) * Cfca.FACTOR)
							--(AUM X (OGS Rate - BSC Rate) X COB Retention Rate)...
							+ ((cso.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(cso.Premium/cso.MaxSpread,0) * ((coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))-convert(decimal(8,4),sc.KeyValue2))/100.0)) * Crate.FACTOR) 
							--Sign correctly for +ve or clawback payment
							* (case when cs.CommissionType in (16,19) then -1 else 1 end)
				--Calculate when BSC and ongoing applies (where ongoing rate less than BSC rate, then BSC gets all the ongoing available) 
				when cso.FrequencyCode = 6 and SFMpot.ID is not null and BSCpot.ID is not null then
							--(AUM X BSC Rate)...(in this scenario it's all of the OGS rate)
							((cso.AgentSplit/100) * (isnull(cso.Premium/cso.MaxSpread,0) * (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))/100.0)) 
							--(AUM X OGS Rate X COB FCA Rate)...
							- ((cso.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(cso.Premium/cso.MaxSpread,0) * (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))/100.0) * Cfca.FACTOR)
							--(AUM X (OGS Rate - BSC Rate) X COB Retention Rate)...
							+ (0.0)) --BSC got it all, so this part of the calculation is zero
							--Sign correctly for +ve or clawback payment
							* (case when cs.CommissionType in (16,19) then -1 else 1 end)
				--Calculate when no BSC applies and ongoing applies
				when cso.FrequencyCode = 6 and SFMpot.ID is not null and BSCpot.ID is null then 
							--(AUM X OGS Rate X COB Retention Rate)...
							(((cso.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(cso.Premium/cso.MaxSpread,0) * (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))/100.0) * Crate.FACTOR) 
							--(AUM X OGS Rate X COB FCA Rate)...
							- ((cso.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(cso.Premium/cso.MaxSpread,0) * (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))/100.0) * Cfca.FACTOR))
							--Sign correctly for +ve or clawback payment
							* (case when cs.CommissionType in (16,19) then -1 else 1 end)
				--SINGLE end
				
				--REGULAR start
				--Calculate when BSC and ongoing applies (where ongoing rate is greater than BSC rate) 
				when cso.FrequencyCode <> 6 and SFMpot.ID is not null and BSCpot.ID is not null and (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2)) - convert(decimal(8,4),sc.KeyValue2)) >= 0.01 then		--AG 04/06/2018 (1)
							--The non-BSC portion (Ave AUM X (OGS Rate - BSC Rate) X COB Retention Rate)...
							((((((cso.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(cso.Premium/cso.MaxSpread,0) * (case when cso.FrequencyCode = 2 then 12 else 1 end))/2.0) * (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2)) - convert(decimal(8,4),sc.KeyValue2))/100.0)) * Crate.FACTOR
							--The BSC portion (Ave AUM X BSC Rate)...
							+ case when cso.FrequencyCode = 2	--Monthly 
									then (cso.AgentSplit/100) * 12.0 * (isnull(cso.Premium/cso.MaxSpread,0)/2.0) * convert(decimal(8,4),sc.KeyValue3) 
									else (cso.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(cso.Premium/cso.MaxSpread,0) * convert(decimal(8,4),sc.KeyValue3) 
							  end
							--FCA Charge (Ave AUM X OGS Rate X FCA Rate)...
							- (case when cso.FrequencyCode = 2	--Monthly 
									then (cso.AgentSplit/100) * 12.0 * (isnull(cso.Premium/cso.MaxSpread,0)/2.0) 
									else (cso.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(cso.Premium/cso.MaxSpread,0) 
							   end * (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))/100.0) * Cfca.FACTOR))
							--Sign correctly for +ve or clawback payment
							* (case when cs.CommissionType in (16,19) then -1 else 1 end)   
				--Calculate when BSC and ongoing applies (where ongoing rate less than BSC rate, then BSC gets all the ongoing available) 
				when cso.FrequencyCode <> 6 and SFMpot.ID is not null and BSCpot.ID is not null then		--AG 04/06/2018 (1)
							--The non-BSC portion (Ave AUM X (OGS Rate - BSC Rate) X COB Retention Rate)...
							((0.0)	--BSC got it all, so this part of the calculation is zero
							--The BSC portion (Ave AUM X BSC Rate)...(in this scenario it's all of the OGS rate)
							+ case when cso.FrequencyCode = 2	--Monthly 
									then (cso.AgentSplit/100) * 12.0 * (isnull(cso.Premium/cso.MaxSpread,0)/2.0) * (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))/100.0) 
									else (cso.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(cso.Premium/cso.MaxSpread,0) * (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))/100.0) 
							  end
							--FCA Charge (Ave AUM X OGS Rate X FCA Rate)...
							- (case when cso.FrequencyCode = 2	--Monthly 
									then (cso.AgentSplit/100) * 12.0 * (isnull(cso.Premium/cso.MaxSpread,0)/2.0) 
									else (cso.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(cso.Premium/cso.MaxSpread,0) 
							   end * (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))/100.0) * Cfca.FACTOR))
							--Sign correctly for +ve or clawback payment
							* (case when cs.CommissionType in (16,19) then -1 else 1 end)   
				--Calculate when no BSC applies, but ongoing servicing applies
				when cso.FrequencyCode <> 6 and SFMpot.ID is not null and BSCpot.ID is null then		--AG 04/06/2018	(1)
							--(Ave AUM X OGS Rate X COB Retention Rate)...
							(((((cso.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(cso.Premium/cso.MaxSpread,0) * (case when cso.FrequencyCode = 2 then 12 else 1 end))/2.0) * (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))/100.0) * Crate.FACTOR) 
							--(Ave AUM X OGS Rate X COB FCA Rate)...
							- ((((cso.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(cso.Premium/cso.MaxSpread,0) * (case when cso.FrequencyCode = 2 then 12 else 1 end))/2.0) * (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))/100.0) * Cfca.FACTOR))
							--Sign correctly for +ve or clawback payment
							* (case when cs.CommissionType in (16,19) then -1 else 1 end)   
				--REGULAR end
				
				else 0.0

				--WEALTH ONGOING CALCULATION END
			end as OngoingYr01,
			0.0 as OngoingYr02,
			0.0 as OngoingYr03,
			0.0 as OngoingYr04,
			0.0 as OngoingYr05,
			0.0 as OngoingYr06,
			0.0 as OngoingYr07,
			0.0 as OngoingYr08,
			0.0 as OngoingYr09,
			0.0 as OngoingYr10,
			Cfca.FACTOR*100.0 as FCARate,
			Crate.FACTOR*100.0 as RetentionRate,
			0.0 as RetentionRateBroker,
			case when SFMpot.ID is not null
				then coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))
				else null
			end as OngoingServicingRate,
			case when SFMpot.ID is not null
				then case 
						when ogs.OngoingServiceFee is null and ogscli.OngoingServiceFee is null 
							then case
								when ogsdflt.KeyValue = 'ONPLAT' then 'Default - On Plat'
								else 'Default - Off Plat'
							end
						when ogs.OngoingServiceFee is not null then 'Client Product'
						when ogscli.OngoingServiceFee is not null then 'Client Only'
						else 'Unknown'
					 end
				else case when (ph.ProductCategoryCode = 1 or pcc.KeyValue2 = '1')
						then 'No OGS'					--WEALTH, but no OGS
						else null						--Not WEALTH, so OGS is n/a and is therefore null
					 end
			end as OngoingServicingSource,
			pt.CommInitialAmount as DA,
			e.AMOUNT_REC as AmountReceived,
			cso.Premium,								--AG 17/07/2018
			cso.AgentSplit,								--Use the split from the IC record
			cs.CommissionType,
			left(cs.StandingOrderDesc,50) as CommissionTypeDesc,
			cs.PayBasisCode,
			cs.PayBasisDesc,
			cs.CreateDate as PaymentMatchedDate,
			cs.Month,
			cso.FrequencyCode,							--AG 17/07/2018
			case when cso.FrequencyCode = 6
				then 'Single'
				else 'Monthly'
			end as FrequencyDesc,						--AG 17/07/2018
			pg.ProductGroupCode as ReassignedProductGroupCode,	--Force the re-assigned products...		
			pg.ProductGroupName as ReassignedProductGroupName,	--...to be processed as investments		
			case cso.SelectionSource
				when 1 then 'VNB-OGS-PHASE-1' 
				when 2 then 'VNB-OGS-PHASE-2' 
				when 3 then 'VNB-OGS-PHASE-3' 
			end as RecognitionType,
			'WEALTH-ONGOING' as CalculationType,
			'Openwork 2006' as Source,
			@DateLastUpdated as DateInserted,
			@DateLastUpdated as DateLastUpdated,
			csp.year as CommissionYear
	from	#msit_CommissionStatementONGOING cso
			inner join msit_CommissionStatement cs on cs.PendingPaymentID = cso.PendingPaymentID
			inner join mstt_Agents ag on ag.Code = cs.BusinessCode
			inner join mstt_PolicyTransactions pt on pt.ID = cs.TransactionID
			inner join mstt_Policies p on p.POL_NUM = pt.PolicyID
			inner join msit_CommissionStatementPeriods VNBStart on convert(date,pt.CreateDateTime) between VNBStart.PeriodStartDate and VNBStart.PeriodEndDate
			inner join msit_Commissionstatementperiods csp on csp.month = cs.month
			inner join mstt_ProductHierarchy ph on ph.productcode = cs.productcode
			inner join mstt_Expectation e on e.ID = cs.ExpectationID
			left join dbo.owt_MortgageBrokerFees mbf on mbf.PendingPaymentID = cs.PendingPaymentID and mbf.AdviceFeeCharged = 'Yes'
			left join owt_SelectionControl SC
						on SC.Process = 'ElitePoints' 
						and SC.KeyType = 'NSCPotCode' 
						and cs.CreateDate between SC.EffectiveStartDate and SC.EffectiveEndDate
			left join mstt_Commissions BSCpot
						on BSCpot.TransactionID = cs.TransactionID 
						and BSCpot.Agent_Code = sc.KeyValue
						and BSCpot.CommissionType = 10
			left join owt_SelectionControl SFMPC						
						on SFMPC.Process = 'ElitePoints' 
						and SFMPC.KeyType = 'ServicingFeeMarginPotCode' 
						and cs.CreateDate between SFMPC.EffectiveStartDate and SFMPC.EffectiveEndDate
			left join mstt_Commissions SFMpot							
						on SFMpot.TransactionID = cs.TransactionID 
						and SFMpot.Agent_Code = SFMPC.KeyValue
						and SFMpot.CommissionType = 10	
			left join owt_SelectionControl pcc 
						on pcc.Process = 'ElitePoints'
						and pcc.KeyType = 'ProductCategoryCode'
						and pcc.KeyValue = cs.ProductCode	
						and cs.CreateDate between pcc.EffectiveStartDate and pcc.EffectiveEndDate
			left join owt_SelectionControl ogsdflt 
						on ogsdflt.Process = 'ElitePoints'
						and ogsdflt.KeyType = 'DefaultOngoingServicingRate'
						and ogsdflt.SelectionType = 'VNB'
						and ogsdflt.KeyValue = case when ph.RDRType = 'ONPLAT' then 'ONPLAT' else 'OFPLAT' end
						and cs.CreateDate between ogsdflt.EffectiveStartDate and ogsdflt.EffectiveEndDate
			left join mstt_CodeProductGroup pg on pg.ProductGroupCode = case when pcc.KeyValue2 = '1' then 2 else ph.ProductGroupCode end
			left join owt_EliteFactors Cfca on Cfca.FeeType = 'VNB' and Cfca.category = 'COB-FCA-RATE' and csp.year between Cfca.StartYear and Cfca.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors Crate on Crate.FeeType = 'VNB' and Crate.category = 'COB-RETENTION-RATE' and csp.year between Crate.StartYear and Crate.EndYear 
			left join dbo.owt_OngoingRate ogs 
						on  ogs.CLIENT_NUM = cs.ClientID 
						and ogs.ProductCode = cs.ProductCode
						and convert(date,pt.CreateDateTime) between ogs.EffectiveStartDate and ogs.EffectiveEndDate
			left join dbo.owt_OngoingRate ogscli 
						on  ogscli.CLIENT_NUM = cs.ClientID 
						and ogscli.ProductCode = '(CLIENT)'
						and convert(date,pt.CreateDateTime) between ogscli.EffectiveStartDate and ogscli.EffectiveEndDate
	where	cso.SpreadNumber <= cso.MaxSpread	-- if per payment spreading, then limit the spread
	
	select @RowCount = @@rowcount
	set @ProcessMessage = '#owt_Recognition (ogs ph1 yr1) = ' + convert(nvarchar(10), @RowCount)
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseLog, @ProcessMessage, null, @Module, @Client

	/****************************************************************************

		Ongoing Phase 3
		1) Add up the +ves and -ves prior to the NEW front loaded amount and
			net them off on the first +ve following the last -ve
		2) Now set all the +ves following the one updated in (1) to zero.
																
	****************************************************************************/

	update r
		set RecognitionType	= case when r.SourceID >= csos.MinOngoingAfterAdjPendingPaymentID 
								then 'VNB-OGS-PHASE-4'
								else r.RecognitionType
							  end,
			OngoingYr01 = case  when r.SourceID = csos.MinOngoingAfterAdjPendingPaymentID 
									then (abs(r.OngoingYr01) * cso.MaxSpread) - derived.SumOngoingYr01
								when r.SourceID > csos.MinOngoingAfterAdjPendingPaymentID 
									then 0.0
								else r.OngoingYr01
						  end,
			DateLastUpdated = @DateLastUpdated
	from	#msit_CommissionStatementONGOING cso 
			inner join #AG_owt_Recognition_SEPARATE_ONGOING r on r.SourceID = cso.PendingPaymentID
			inner join #msit_CommissionStatementOGSSUMMARY csos
						on  csos.TransactionID = cso.TransactionID
						and csos.AgentCode = cso.AgentCode
			inner join (select	r.TransactionID, r.SellerCode, SUM(OngoingYr01) as SumOngoingYr01
						from	#msit_CommissionStatementOGSSUMMARY s
								inner join #AG_owt_Recognition_SEPARATE_ONGOING r 
											on r.TransactionID = s.TransactionID
											and r.SellerCode = s.AgentCode
						where	r.SourceID <= s.MaxOngoingAdjPendingPaymentID
						group	by r.TransactionID, r.SellerCode
						) derived 
							on  derived.TransactionID = r.TransactionID
							and	derived.SellerCode = r.SellerCode 
	where	isnull(csos.MaxOngoingPendingPaymentID,0) > isnull(csos.MaxOngoingAdjPendingPaymentID,0)	--An ongoing +ve payment follows the clawback, so time to revert back to front loading
	and		cso.SpreadNumber <= cso.MaxSpread	--Only payments within the spread period get a portion of the ongoing VNB
	and		cso.SelectionSource <> 1			--Just process the per-payment rows (not the front loaded rows)

	select @RowCount = @@rowcount
	set @ProcessMessage = '#owt_Recognition (ogs ph4 - accr adj) = ' + convert(nvarchar(10), @RowCount)
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseLog, @ProcessMessage, null, @Module, @Client

	/****************************************************************************

		Now calculate the ongoing spread as follows:
		1) Investments: Years 1 to 6
		2) Pensions:	Years 1 to 10
		Note that regular payments get an additional multiplier to uplift the 
		average AUM for each year.
																		
	****************************************************************************/

	update r
		set OngoingYr02 = case when r.FrequencyCode = 2									--Monthly
							then r.OngoingYr01 * YR02.Multiplier * YR02.Factor			--Regular
							else r.OngoingYr01 * YR02.Factor							--Single
						  end,
			OngoingYr03 = case when r.FrequencyCode = 2									--Monthly
							then r.OngoingYr01 * YR03.Multiplier * YR03.Factor			--Regular
							else r.OngoingYr01 * YR03.Factor							--Single
						  end,
			OngoingYr04 = case when r.FrequencyCode = 2									--Monthly
							then r.OngoingYr01 * YR04.Multiplier * YR04.Factor			--Regular
							else r.OngoingYr01 * YR04.Factor							--Single
						  end,
			OngoingYr05 = case when r.FrequencyCode = 2									--Monthly 
							then r.OngoingYr01 * YR05.Multiplier * YR05.Factor			--Regular
							else r.OngoingYr01 * YR05.Factor							--Single
						  end,
			OngoingYr06 = case when r.FrequencyCode = 2									--Monthly 
							then r.OngoingYr01 * YR06.Multiplier * YR06.Factor			--Regular
							else r.OngoingYr01 * YR06.Factor							--Single
						  end,
			OngoingYr07 = case when r.ReassignedProductGroupCode = 5					--Pensions	AG 05/06/2018
							then
								case when r.FrequencyCode = 2							--Monthly 
									then r.OngoingYr01 * YR07.Multiplier * YR07.Factor	--Regular
									else r.OngoingYr01 * YR07.Factor					--Single
								end
							else 
								0.0
						  end,
			OngoingYr08 = case when r.ReassignedProductGroupCode = 5					--Pensions	AG 05/06/2018 
							then
								case when r.FrequencyCode = 2							--Monthly 
									then r.OngoingYr01 * YR08.Multiplier * YR08.Factor	--Regular
									else r.OngoingYr01 * YR08.Factor					--Single
								end
							else 
								0.0
						  end,
			OngoingYr09 = case when r.ReassignedProductGroupCode = 5					--Pensions	AG 05/06/2018 
							then
								case when r.FrequencyCode = 2							--Monthly 
									then r.OngoingYr01 * YR09.Multiplier * YR09.Factor	--Regular
									else r.OngoingYr01 * YR09.Factor					--Single
								end
							else 
								0.0
						  end,
			OngoingYr10 = case when r.ReassignedProductGroupCode = 5					--Pensions	AG 05/06/2018
							then
								case when r.FrequencyCode = 2							--Monthly 
									then r.OngoingYr01 * YR10.Multiplier * YR10.Factor	--Regular
									else r.OngoingYr01 * YR10.Factor					--Single
								end
							else 
								0.0
						  end
	from	#AG_owt_Recognition_SEPARATE_ONGOING r
			left join owt_EliteFactors YR01 on YR01.FeeType = 'VNB' and YR01.Category = 'COB-ONGOING-DISCOUNT-YR01' and r.CommissionYear between YR01.StartYear and YR01.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors YR02 on YR02.FeeType = 'VNB' and YR02.Category = 'COB-ONGOING-DISCOUNT-YR02' and r.CommissionYear between YR02.StartYear and YR02.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors YR03 on YR03.FeeType = 'VNB' and YR03.Category = 'COB-ONGOING-DISCOUNT-YR03' and r.CommissionYear between YR03.StartYear and YR03.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors YR04 on YR04.FeeType = 'VNB' and YR04.Category = 'COB-ONGOING-DISCOUNT-YR04' and r.CommissionYear between YR04.StartYear and YR04.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors YR05 on YR05.FeeType = 'VNB' and YR05.Category = 'COB-ONGOING-DISCOUNT-YR05' and r.CommissionYear between YR05.StartYear and YR05.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors YR06 on YR06.FeeType = 'VNB' and YR06.Category = 'COB-ONGOING-DISCOUNT-YR06' and r.CommissionYear between YR06.StartYear and YR06.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors YR07 on YR07.FeeType = 'VNB' and YR07.Category = 'COB-ONGOING-DISCOUNT-YR07' and r.CommissionYear between YR07.StartYear and YR07.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors YR08 on YR08.FeeType = 'VNB' and YR08.Category = 'COB-ONGOING-DISCOUNT-YR08' and r.CommissionYear between YR08.StartYear and YR08.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors YR09 on YR09.FeeType = 'VNB' and YR09.Category = 'COB-ONGOING-DISCOUNT-YR09' and r.CommissionYear between YR09.StartYear and YR09.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors YR10 on YR10.FeeType = 'VNB' and YR10.Category = 'COB-ONGOING-DISCOUNT-YR10' and r.CommissionYear between YR10.StartYear and YR10.EndYear 
	where	r.CalculationType = 'WEALTH-ONGOING'

	select @RowCount = @@rowcount
	set @ProcessMessage = '#owt_Recognition (ongoing yr2-10) = ' + convert(nvarchar(10), @RowCount)
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseLog, @ProcessMessage, null, @Module, @Client
	
	/****************************************************************************

		Now add up all the numbers
																		
	****************************************************************************/
	
	update r
		set OngoingTotal	=	OngoingYr01 + OngoingYr02 + OngoingYr03 + OngoingYr04 + OngoingYr05 +
								OngoingYr06 + OngoingYr07 + OngoingYr08 + OngoingYr09 + OngoingYr10,
			PointsTotal		=	OngoingYr01 + OngoingYr02 + OngoingYr03 + OngoingYr04 + OngoingYr05 +
								OngoingYr06 + OngoingYr07 + OngoingYr08 + OngoingYr09 + OngoingYr10 +
								Initial + MBF	-- Note BSC is already included in the Ongoing, so don't include it in the Points Total.
	from	#AG_owt_Recognition_SEPARATE_ONGOING r

	select @RowCount = @@rowcount
	set @ProcessMessage = '#owt_Recognition (points total) = ' + convert(nvarchar(10), @RowCount)
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseLog, @ProcessMessage, null, @Module, @Client

	/****************************************************************************

		Merge the temporary table into the permanent table (IC data)
																		
	****************************************************************************/

	BEGIN TRANSACTION

	declare @SummaryOfChanges table (Change varchar(20))
	merge	dbo.AG_owt_Recognition_SEPARATE_ONGOING as trg
	using	#AG_owt_Recognition_SEPARATE_ONGOING as src
	on		trg.SourceID = src.SourceID
	and		trg.Source = src.Source
	when	matched 
	and		isnull(trg.PointsTotal,0) <> isnull(src.PointsTotal,0)
	then	update 
				set trg.CaseID = src.CaseID,
					trg.TransactionID = src.TransactionID,
					trg.Policy = src.Policy,
					trg.ProductCode = src.ProductCode,
					trg.BusinessCode = src.BusinessCode,
					trg.SellerCode = src.SellerCode,					--AG 13/06/2018
					trg.PointsTotal = src.PointsTotal,
					trg.BSC = src.BSC,
					trg.MBF = src.MBF,
					trg.Initial = src.Initial,
					trg.OngoingTotal = src.OngoingTotal,
					trg.OngoingYr01 = src.OngoingYr01,
					trg.OngoingYr02 = src.OngoingYr02,
					trg.OngoingYr03 = src.OngoingYr03,
					trg.OngoingYr04 = src.OngoingYr04,
					trg.OngoingYr05 = src.OngoingYr05,
					trg.OngoingYr06 = src.OngoingYr06,
					trg.OngoingYr07 = src.OngoingYr07,
					trg.OngoingYr08 = src.OngoingYr08,
					trg.OngoingYr09 = src.OngoingYr09,
					trg.OngoingYr10 = src.OngoingYr10,
					trg.FCARate = src.FCARate,
					trg.RetentionRate = src.RetentionRate,
					trg.RetentionRateBroker = src.RetentionRateBroker,
					trg.OngoingServicingRate = src.OngoingServicingRate,
					trg.OngoingServicingSource = src.OngoingServicingSource,
					trg.DA = src.DA,
					trg.AmountReceived = src.AmountReceived,
					trg.Premium = src.Premium,
					trg.AgentSplit = src.AgentSplit,
					trg.CommissionType = src.CommissionType,
					trg.CommissionTypeDesc = src.CommissionTypeDesc,
					trg.PayBasisCode = src.PayBasisCode,				--AG 13/06/2018
					trg.PayBasisDesc = src.PayBasisDesc,				--AG 13/06/2018
					trg.PaymentMatchedDate = src.PaymentMatchedDate,	--AG 13/06/2018	
					trg.Month = src.Month,
					trg.FrequencyCode = src.FrequencyCode,
					trg.FrequencyDesc = src.FrequencyDesc,
					trg.ReassignedProductGroupCode = src.ReassignedProductGroupCode,	--AG 05/06/2018
					trg.ReassignedProductGroupName = src.ReassignedProductGroupName,	--AG 05/06/2018
					trg.RecognitionType = src.RecognitionType,
					trg.CalculationType = src.CalculationType,
					trg.DateLastUpdated = @DateLastUpdated
	when	not matched by target 
	then	insert
			(
				SourceID,
				CaseID,
				TransactionID,
				Policy,
				ProductCode,
				BusinessCode,
				SellerCode,							--AG 13/06/2018
				PointsTotal,
				BSC,
				MBF,
				Initial,
				OngoingTotal,
				OngoingYr01,
				OngoingYr02,
				OngoingYr03,
				OngoingYr04,
				OngoingYr05,
				OngoingYr06,
				OngoingYr07,
				OngoingYr08,
				OngoingYr09,
				OngoingYr10,
				FCARate,
				RetentionRate,
				RetentionRateBroker,
				OngoingServicingRate,
				OngoingServicingSource,
				DA,
				AmountReceived,
				Premium,
				AgentSplit,
				CommissionType,
				CommissionTypeDesc,
				PayBasisCode,						--AG 13/06/2018
				PayBasisDesc,						--AG 13/06/2018
				PaymentMatchedDate,					--AG 13/06/2018
				Month,
				FrequencyCode,
				FrequencyDesc,
				ReassignedProductGroupCode,			--AG 05/06/2018
				ReassignedProductGroupName,			--AG 05/06/2018
				RecognitionType,
				CalculationType,
				Source,
				DateInserted,
				DateLastUpdated
			)		
			values
			(
				src.SourceID,
				src.CaseID,
				src.TransactionID,
				src.Policy,
				src.ProductCode,
				src.BusinessCode,
				src.SellerCode,						--AG 13/06/2018
				src.PointsTotal,
				src.BSC,
				src.MBF,
				src.Initial,
				src.OngoingTotal,
				src.OngoingYr01,
				src.OngoingYr02,
				src.OngoingYr03,
				src.OngoingYr04,
				src.OngoingYr05,
				src.OngoingYr06,
				src.OngoingYr07,
				src.OngoingYr08,
				src.OngoingYr09,
				src.OngoingYr10,
				src.FCARate,
				src.RetentionRate,
				src.RetentionRateBroker,
				src.OngoingServicingRate,
				src.OngoingServicingSource,
				src.DA,
				src.AmountReceived,
				src.Premium,
				src.AgentSplit,
				src.CommissionType,
				src.CommissionTypeDesc,
				src.PayBasisCode,					--AG 13/06/2018
				src.PayBasisDesc,					--AG 13/06/2018
				src.PaymentMatchedDate,				--AG 13/06/2018
				src.Month,
				src.FrequencyCode,
				src.FrequencyDesc,
				src.ReassignedProductGroupCode,		--AG 05/06/2018
				src.ReassignedProductGroupName,		--AG 05/06/2018
				src.RecognitionType,
				src.CalculationType,
				src.Source,
				src.DateInserted,
				src.DateLastUpdated)				--Merge statements must have a ;
	output $action into @SummaryOfChanges;
						
	/****************************************************************************

		Update OpenAccess
																		
	****************************************************************************/

/*	
	--Do not include MBF in the OpenAccess Commission Listing as it is on the MBF download
	--and we don't want MBF double counting.
	update	oal
		set VNB_Points = r.PointsTotal - r.MBF		--AG 04/06/2018 (2)
	from	msit_CommissionStatement cs
/*			inner join (select	distinct PKID
						from	owt_TransformationMovements tm 
						where	tm.DriverTableName = 'sa_swift_S_AGMFIL'
						and		tm.CommissionStatement = 'Y') tm on tm.PKID = cs.PendingPaymentID
*/			inner join msit_OpenworkAdviserListing oal on oal.SourceID = cs.ID and oal.Source = 'Openwork 2006'
			inner join owt_Recognition r 
						on r.SourceID = cs.PendingPaymentID
						and r.Source = oal.Source
	--where	isnull(oal.VNB_Points,0) <> isnull(r.PointsTotal,0)
	
	select @OALRowCount = @@rowcount
*/
	COMMIT TRANSACTION      
	
	select	@RowCount = COUNT(*)
	from	@SummaryOfChanges
	where	Change = 'INSERT'

	set @ProcessMessage = 'owt_Recognition (insert) = ' + convert(nvarchar(10), @RowCount)
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseLog, @ProcessMessage, null, @Module, @Client

	select	@RowCount = COUNT(*)
	from	@SummaryOfChanges
	where	Change = 'UPDATE'

	set @ProcessMessage = 'owt_Recognition (update) = ' + convert(nvarchar(10), @RowCount)
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseLog, @ProcessMessage, null, @Module, @Client
/*
	set @ProcessMessage = 'msit_OpenworkAdviserListing (update) = ' + convert(nvarchar(10), @OALRowCount)
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseLog, @ProcessMessage, null, @Module, @Client
*/
	/****************************************************************************

		T H E   E N D
																		
	****************************************************************************/
	
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseEnd, @ProcName, null, @Module, @Client

END TRY

BEGIN CATCH 

	select @ErrNum = ERROR_NUMBER(), @ErrMsg = ERROR_MESSAGE(), @ErrSev = ERROR_SEVERITY(), @ErrLine = ERROR_LINE(), @ErrState = XACT_STATE()
	set @ErrMsg = REPLACE(@ErrMsg, '.', '') + ' (error no: ' + CAST(@ErrNum AS VARCHAR(10)) + ') on line ' + CAST(@ErrLine AS VARCHAR(10))
	
	-- Test XACT_STATE for 0, 1, or -1.
    -- If 1, the transaction is committable.
    -- If -1, the transaction is uncommittable and should be rolled back.
    -- If 0, there is no transaction and a commit or rollback operation would generate an error.

	if @ErrState = -1			-- Transaction is uncommitable
		rollback transaction

	if @ErrState = 1			
		commit transaction

	-- Error message line 1
	set @ErrMsgBrief = left(@ErrMsg,100)
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseError, @ErrMsgBrief, null, @Module, @Client
	
	-- Error message line 2 - if any text exists
	set @ErrMsgBrief = substring(@ErrMsg,101,100)
	if len(@ErrMsgBrief) > 0
		exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseError, @ErrMsgBrief, null, @Module, @Client

	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseEnd, @ProcName, null, @Module, @Client

	RAISERROR(@ErrMsg, @ErrSev , 1)

END CATCH

/****************************************************************************

			E N D															

****************************************************************************/

return @ErrNum


GO
/****** Object:  StoredProcedure [dbo].[owp_RecognitionSwiftONGOING_Backup20180724AG-2]    Script Date: 7/3/2026 3:44:25 PM ******/
SET ANSI_NULLS ON
GO
SET QUOTED_IDENTIFIER ON
GO
/*********************************************************************************************************

Program:		owp_RecognitionSwift					
Author:			Alan Groves
Date created:	11/04/2018
											
Description:
===========

This proc populates the new recognition table called "owt_Recognition" with "Value of New Business"
(VNB) points.

This proc handles all of the swift data which includes:
WEALTH - COB business i.e. pensions and investments
MORTGAGES
PROTECTION

Note: There is a separate proc that calculates the GI VNB points from the Paymentshield data.

The approach of this proc is to use the incremental PendingPaymentIDs from the overnight batch
to calculate the VNB points in a temporary table.

The temporary table is then merged with the permanent table to make the calculated (or
re-calculated values) permanent.

Terms
-----
BSC			- Business Service Charge.
MBF			- Mortgage Broker Fee.
OGS			- Ongoing Servicing.
BSC Rate	- 0.12% at the time of writing (24/04/2018). This could be changed by the business, but
				would also require some DEV work in OWS.
DF			- Discount Factor.
DA			- Distribution Allowance (the total amount paid out by the provider to Openwork)
AUM			- Assets Under Management. Basically the amount invested or the premium on investment
				cases.
Average AUM - Average amount invested annually which is equivalent to 6 months' premium.

THE CALCULATIONS
================

There are two potential parts: initial + ongoing (if ongoing applies). If BSC (applies to ongoing 
only) and MBF (applies to mortgages only) apply, then these are also included:

MORTGAGE
--------
Part 1: MBF column = (Advice Fee Amount X Broker Retention Rate) - (Advice Fee Amount X Mort FCA Rate)
Part 2: Initial column = (Proc Fee Amount X Mortgage Retention Rate) - (Proc Fee X Mort FCA Rate) 
Mortgage Points Total = Initial + MBF

PROTECTION
----------
= (DA X Protection Retention Rate) - (DA X Protection FCA Rate) 
Protection Points Total = Initial

WEALTH (COB i.e. pensions and investments)
------
Part 1: Initial column = (DA X Wealth Retention Rate) - (DA X Wealth FCA Rate)

Part 2:

****XXXX****

NOTE: Where the BSC rate is greater than the ongoing rate, then BSC gets ALL of the AVAILABLE 
ongoing.

****XXXX****

REGULAR - BSC applies:
Year 1 column = BSC Points + Non-BSC Points - FCA Points
Non-BSC Points = Ave AUM X (OGS Rate - BSC Rate) X COB Retention Rate
BSC Points = Ave AUM X BSC Rate
FCA Points = Ave AUM X OGS Rate X COB FCA Rate

REGULAR - Non-BSC: 
Year 1 column = (Ave AUM X OGS Rate X COB Retention Rate) - (Ave AUM X OGS Rate X COB FCA Rate)

SINGLE - BSC applies:
Year 1 column = (AUM X BSC Rate) + (AUM X (OGS Rate - BSC Rate) X COB Retention Rate) - (AUM X OGS Rate X COB FCA Rate) 

SINGLE - Non-BSC:
Year 1 column = (AUM X OGS Rate X COB Retention Rate) - (AUM X OGS Rate X COB FCA Rate) 

Then years 2 to 10 are calculated by applying a discount factor
Year  2 = Year 1 X  3 X DF
Year  3 = Year 1 X  5 X DF
Year  4 = Year 1 X  7 X DF
Year  5 = Year 1 X  9 X DF
Year  6 = Year 1 X 11 X DF
Year  7 = Year 1 X 13 X DF
Year  8 = Year 1 X 15 X DF
Year  9 = Year 1 X 17 X DF
Year 10 = Year 1 X 19 X DF

Wealth Points Total =	OngoingYr01 + OngoingYr02 + OngoingYr03 + OngoingYr04 + OngoingYr05 +
						OngoingYr06 + OngoingYr07 + OngoingYr08 + OngoingYr09 + OngoingYr10 +
						Initial

GI
--
See stored proc "owp_RecognitionGIPaymentshield".
 
Notes:
-----

1)	There is a BSC column on table owt_Recognition. However, BSC is already included in the ongoing
	years 1 - 10, so the BSC column does not need to be added in. In fact you will double count if 
	you attempt to do anything with it other than display it.

2)	Occasionally an investment case may receive two or more cheques which
	then go through Swift as two or more SINGLE investments on the SAME
	slice. Although the INITIAL VNB calculation will pro-rata correctly
	because it is based on the amount received, this scenario will cause
	ongoing VNB to be calculated on each of the payment records and so will 
	double count (or worse if there are more than two cheques received).
	Since de-coupling IC from ongoing i.e. they now have separate rows on
	table owt_Recognition, the issue of multiple cheques should no longer
	cause ongoing double counting.


This proc is called as follows:
	declare @rc int
	exec @rc = dbo.owp_RecognitionSwift 'Openwork', 'Recognition'
	select @rc

					
AMENDMENT HISTORY				
=================								

Date		Author		Description
----		------		-----------
26/04/2018	A Groves	Only include rows in the OGS lookups where the OngoingServiceFee > 0.0.
						Negative OGS rates are bad data and at the time of writing, there are
						39 of these.
27/04/2018	A Groves	Additional calculation and condition to handle the scenario where BSC applies
						but the OGS Rate is less than the BSC rate. Previously, this caused the
						total ongoing to be zero. However, there are two components to ongoing VNB 
						points, the BSC share and the non-BSC share. So the BSC share (which takes 
						100% when the OGS rate is less than 0.12%) should still yield ongoing points.
27/04/2018	A Groves	Single ongoing Yr01 corrected by applying outer brackets before signing the result.
03/05/2018	A Groves	Added update of column "msit_OpenworkAdviserListing.VNB_Points".
18/05/2018	A Groves	Changed mortgage calculation to use e.AMOUNT_REC instead of pt.CommInitialAmount
						as Marcus Cossey wanted the actual amount received to be used for the DA.
04/06/2018	A Groves	1) In the REGULAR section of column "OngoingYr01", the condition for cs.FrequencyCode <> 6
							was added to ensure the code differentiates to the SINGLE section.
						2) Exclude MBF from the OpenAccess table (msit_OpenworkAdviserListing) as this
							is shown on the MBF download and would otherwise incur MBF double counting.
05/06/2018	A Groves	1) Marcus Cossey advised that investments should get ongoing for years 1 to 6 and
							pensions for years 1 to 10. Previously, both lines of business got years 1 to 10.
						2) Marcus Cossey asked for split payments (i.e. where multiple cheques are processed
							for a SINGLE investment) to only claculate ongoing VNB on the oldest payment. 
11/06/2018	A Groves	1) PSD processed a protection clawback statement as fee type initial. These clawbacks
							all generated +ve instead of -ve VNB points. A tweak was added to ensure that the 
							absolute value of AMOUNT_REC is used to ensure the VNB is correctly signed. 
						2) Another unknown business rule has surfaced: Previously, only initial, clawbacks and
							adjustments on slices created new from 2017 were included. This rule only applies
							to initial. Clawbacks and adjustments can belong to a slice created at any point
							in the past. However, note that the payment (irrespective of whether it is +ve or 
							-ve), must not pre-date 2017.
13/06/2018	A Groves	Marcus asked for SellerCode and PaymentMatchedDate to be added so he need only use 
							the one table for both the adviser and enterprise leagues. PayBasisCode and 
							PayBasisDesc were also added at the same time as these are used in the calculations.
06/07/2018	A Groves	Replaced the OGS Rate lookup on the fly to using table dbo.owt_OngoingRate. This was 
							done to ensure the rate used at any point in time stays the same, so the onging VNB
							will always give the same result each time the calculation runs.
17/07/2018	A Groves	Marcus asked for the ongoing calculation to be based on the sum of premium across
							all the initial transactions where an initial fee has been paid.
19/07/2018	A Groves	Agreed with Marcus that any initial premium that isn't covered by ongoing slices
							needs to be added to the OGS calculation to ensure advisers are not under
							rewarded. The missing OGS premium is added to the oldest OGS payment.
*************************************************************************************************************/

CREATE PROCEDURE [dbo].[owp_RecognitionSwiftONGOING_Backup20180724AG-2]
	@Client		varchar(50),
	@Module		Varchar(50)

AS

set nocount on

declare		@PhaseStart				varchar(50),
			@PhaseEnd				varchar(50),
			@PhaseError				varchar(50),
			@PhaseLog				varchar(50),
			@ProcName				varchar(100),
			@ProcessMessage			varchar(100),
			@RowCount				int,
			@OALRowCount			int,
			@ErrMsg					nvarchar(4000),
			@ErrMsgBrief			nvarchar(100),
			@ErrNum					int,
			@ErrSev					int,
			@ErrLine				int,
			@ErrState				int,
			@DateLastUpdated		datetime,
			@OwlManager2Code		nvarchar(10)
			
/****************************************************************************

	Set initial parameters																
																		
****************************************************************************/

set @ProcName			= object_name(@@procid)
set @PhaseStart			= 'START'
set @PhaseEnd			= 'END'
set @PhaseError			= 'ERROR'
set @PhaseLog			= 'LOG'
set @ErrNum				= 0	
set @DateLastUpdated	= getdate()

set @OwlManager2Code = (select cde.Code from msit_MIWarehouseCodesAndDescriptions cde
			where cde.ColumnName = 'Manager2Code' and cde.Description = 'Owl Financial')

-- We want this logging irrespective of whether or not there is a rollback
exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseStart, @ProcName, null, @Module, @Client

/****************************************************************************

	Populate the table																
																		
****************************************************************************/

SET XACT_ABORT ON	-- Needed if XACT_STATE() function is used.

BEGIN TRY

	/****************************************************************************

		Calculate VNB and populate the temporary table with the results
		
		Note that there are oddities like LV protection payments which always
		come in pairs with one large and one much smaller amount (e.g. TransactionID 
		= 6684787.) The system treats both payments in the pair as first payments 
		and the (projected) DA associated with both is the same (because it's on 
		the policy transaction). 
		
		There is also a requirement to front-load VNB points on accrual and level
		payments. This means calculate the VNB for the full amount of the DA and 
		put it on the first payment record and then on all subsequent accrual and 
		level payments, set the VNB to zero.
		
		Thus two different sources of DA are used depending on whether we need the
		full DA amount for accruals and level or the actual amount received for all
		other scenarios including the LV split payment scenario. The two sources are:
		
		mstt_PolicyTransactions.CommInitialAmount - Full (projected) DA amount
		
		mstt_Expectation.AMOUNT_REC - The DA actually received. This handles the
										LV scenario whereby the AMOUNT_REC is 
										proportioned across the two payments received.   
																		
	****************************************************************************/
/*
	select	top 0 
			*, 
			convert(int,NULL) as CommissionYear
	into	#AG_owt_Recognition_SEPARATE_ONGOING
	from	AG_owt_Recognition_SEPARATE_ONGOING
*/
	create table [dbo].[#AG_owt_Recognition_SEPARATE_ONGOING]
	(
		[ID] [bigint] IDENTITY(1,1) NOT NULL,
		[SourceID] [int] NULL,
		[CaseID] [int] NULL,
		[TransactionID] [int] NULL,
		[Policy] [varchar](25) NULL,
		[ProductCode] [varchar](8) NULL,
		[BusinessCode] [varchar](7) NULL,
		[SellerCode] [varchar](7) NULL,
		[PointsTotal] [decimal](16, 4) NULL,
		[BSC] [decimal](16, 4) NULL,
		[MBF] [decimal](16, 4) NULL,
		[Initial] [decimal](16, 4) NULL,
		[OngoingTotal] [decimal](16, 4) NULL,
		[OngoingYr01] [decimal](16, 4) NULL,
		[OngoingYr02] [decimal](16, 4) NULL,
		[OngoingYr03] [decimal](16, 4) NULL,
		[OngoingYr04] [decimal](16, 4) NULL,
		[OngoingYr05] [decimal](16, 4) NULL,
		[OngoingYr06] [decimal](16, 4) NULL,
		[OngoingYr07] [decimal](16, 4) NULL,
		[OngoingYr08] [decimal](16, 4) NULL,
		[OngoingYr09] [decimal](16, 4) NULL,
		[OngoingYr10] [decimal](16, 4) NULL,
		[FCARate] [decimal](8, 4) NULL,
		[RetentionRate] [decimal](8, 4) NULL,
		[RetentionRateBroker] [decimal](8, 4) NULL,
		[OngoingServicingRate] [decimal](8, 4) NULL,
		[OngoingServicingSource] [varchar](20) NULL,
		[DA] [decimal](16, 2) NULL,
		[AmountReceived] [decimal](16, 2) NULL,
		[Premium] [decimal](16, 2) NULL,
		[AgentSplit] [decimal](8, 4) NULL,
		[CommissionType] [int] NULL,
		[CommissionTypeDesc] [varchar](50) NULL,
		[PayBasisCode] [varchar](20) NULL,
		[PayBasisDesc] [varchar](20) NULL,
		[PaymentMatchedDate] [datetime] NULL,
		[Month] [datetime] NULL,
		[FrequencyCode] [tinyint] NULL,
		[FrequencyDesc] [varchar](20) NULL,
		[ReassignedProductGroupCode] [int] NULL,
		[ReassignedProductGroupName] [varchar](50) NULL,
		[RecognitionType] [varchar](15) NULL,
		[CalculationType] [varchar](20) NULL,
		[Source] [varchar](15) NULL,
		[DateInserted] [datetime] NULL,
		[DateLastUpdated] [datetime] NULL,
		[CommissionYear] [int] NULL
	)

	/****************************************************************************

		Phase 1 - Process all but regular accrual cases with clawbacks/adjustments
		Accruals are front loaded unless their latest payment is a clawback/adjudtment
		in which case they accrue VNB points on a per payment basis and so these
		are dealt with in Phases 2 and 3.
																		
	****************************************************************************/

	insert into #AG_owt_Recognition_SEPARATE_ONGOING
	(
		SourceID,
		CaseID,
		TransactionID,
		Policy,
		ProductCode,
		BusinessCode,
		SellerCode,						--AG 13/06/2018
		PointsTotal,
		BSC,
		MBF,
		Initial,
		OngoingTotal,
		OngoingYr01,
		OngoingYr02,
		OngoingYr03,
		OngoingYr04,
		OngoingYr05,
		OngoingYr06,
		OngoingYr07,
		OngoingYr08,
		OngoingYr09,
		OngoingYr10,
		FCARate,
		RetentionRate,
		RetentionRateBroker,
		OngoingServicingRate,
		OngoingServicingSource,
		DA,
		AmountReceived,
		Premium,
		AgentSplit,
		CommissionType,
		CommissionTypeDesc,
		PayBasisCode,					--AG 13/06/2018
		PayBasisDesc,					--AG 13/06/2018
		PaymentMatchedDate,				--AG 13/06/2018
		Month,
		FrequencyCode,
		FrequencyDesc,
		ReassignedProductGroupCode,		--AG 05/06/2018
		ReassignedProductGroupName,		--AG 05/06/2018
		RecognitionType,
		CalculationType,
		Source,
		DateInserted,
		DateLastUpdated,
		CommissionYear
	)
	select	cs.PendingPaymentID as SourceID,
			cs.CaseID,
			cs.TransactionID,
			cs.ExtPolicyNumber as Policy,
			cs.ProductCode,
			cs.BusinessCode,
			cs.AgentCode as SellerCode,				--AG 13/06/2018
			0.0 as PointsTotal,
			0.0 as BSC,
			case 
				when mbf.MortgageFeeID is not null and cs.INIssued <> 0 then (((mbf.AdviceFeeAmount)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * MRbkr.FACTOR) - ((mbf.AdviceFeeAmount)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * Mfca.FACTOR)) --Note that mbf.AdviceFeeAmount is signed correctly - so no coding for signing is needed here
				else 0.0
			end as MBF,
			case 
				--When the adviser has changed, the AgentSplit can become zero in which case the ELITE points should be zero.
				when cs.AgentSplit = 0 then 0
				
				--WEALTH CALCULATION START
				--Indemnity payments or SINGLEs or IC Clawbacks or IC adjustments Start
				when (ph.ProductCategoryCode = 1 or pcc.KeyValue2 = '1') and (cs.FrequencyCode = 6 or cs.PayBasisCode in ('T') or cs.CommissionType in (2,17)) and cs.commissiontype in (1,2,17) and cs.INIssued <> 0 then (((e.AMOUNT_REC)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * Crate.FACTOR) - ((e.AMOUNT_REC)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * Cfca.FACTOR)) * case when cs.INIssued < 0 then -1 else 1 end
				--Indemnity payments or SINGLEs or IC Clawbacks or IC adjustments End
				--Accruals & Level Start
				when (ph.ProductCategoryCode = 1 or pcc.KeyValue2 = '1') and cs.INIssued <> 0 then (((pt.CommInitialAmount)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * Crate.FACTOR) - ((pt.CommInitialAmount)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * Cfca.FACTOR)) * case when cs.INIssued < 0 then -1 else 1 end
				--Accruals & Level End
				--WEALTH CALCULATION END
				
				--MORTGAGE CALCULATION START
				--Note: The MBF component has its own table column
				--Only 1 payment for mortgages
				when ph.ProductGroupCode = 3 and cs.INIssued <> 0 then (((e.AMOUNT_REC)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * MRproc.FACTOR) - ((e.AMOUNT_REC)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * Mfca.FACTOR)) * case when cs.INIssued < 0 then -1 else 1 end	--AG 18/05/2018
				--MORTGAGE CALCULATION END
				
				--PROTECTION CALCULATION START
				--Indemnity payments or SINGLEs or IC Clawbacks or IC adjustments Start
				when ph.ProductGroupCode = 6 and (cs.FrequencyCode = 6 or cs.PayBasisCode in ('T') or cs.CommissionType in (2,17)) and cs.commissiontype in (1,2,17) and cs.INIssued <> 0 then ((abs(e.AMOUNT_REC)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * Prate.FACTOR) - (abs(e.AMOUNT_REC)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * Pfca.FACTOR)) * case when cs.INIssued < 0 then -1 else 1 end	--AG 11/06/2018 (1)
				--Indemnity payments or SINGLEs or IC Clawbacks or IC adjustments End
				--Accruals & Level Start
				when ph.ProductGroupCode = 6 and cs.INIssued <> 0 then (((pt.CommInitialAmount)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * Prate.FACTOR) - ((pt.CommInitialAmount)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * Pfca.FACTOR)) * case when cs.INIssued < 0 then -1 else 1 end
				--Accruals & Level End
				--PROTECTION CALCULATION END

				else 0.0

			end as Initial,
			0.0 as OngoingTotal,
			0.0 as OngoingYr01,
			0.0 as OngoingYr02,
			0.0 as OngoingYr03,
			0.0 as OngoingYr04,
			0.0 as OngoingYr05,
			0.0 as OngoingYr06,
			0.0 as OngoingYr07,
			0.0 as OngoingYr08,
			0.0 as OngoingYr09,
			0.0 as OngoingYr10,
			case 
				when (ph.ProductCategoryCode = 1 or pcc.KeyValue2 = '1') then Cfca.FACTOR*100.0		--COB
				when ph.ProductGroupCode = 3 then Mfca.FACTOR*100.0		--MORT
				when ph.ProductGroupCode = 6 then Pfca.FACTOR*100.0		--PROT
				else 0.0
			end as FCARate,
			case 
				when (ph.ProductCategoryCode = 1 or pcc.KeyValue2 = '1') then Crate.FACTOR*100.0	--COB
				when ph.ProductGroupCode = 3 then MRproc.FACTOR*100.0	--MORT
				when ph.ProductGroupCode = 6 then Prate.FACTOR*100.0	--PROT
				else 0.0
			end as RetentionRate,
			case 
				when mbf.MortgageFeeID is not null then  MRbkr.FACTOR*100.0	
				else 0.0
			end as RetentionRateBroker,
			null as OngoingServicingRate,
			null as OngoingServicingSource,
			pt.CommInitialAmount as DA,
			e.AMOUNT_REC as AmountReceived,
			cs.Premium,
			cs.AgentSplit,
			cs.CommissionType,
			left(cs.StandingOrderDesc,50) as CommissionTypeDesc,
			cs.PayBasisCode,							--AG 13/06/2018
			cs.PayBasisDesc,							--AG 13/06/2018
			cs.CreateDate as PaymentMatchedDate,		--AG 13/06/2018
			cs.Month,
			cs.FrequencyCode,
			cs.FrequencyDesc,
			pg.ProductGroupCode as ReassignedProductGroupCode,	--Force the re-assigned products...		AG 05/06/2018
			pg.ProductGroupName as ReassignedProductGroupName,	--...to be processed as investments		AG 05/06/2018
			'VNB-INI-PHASE-1' as RecognitionType,
			case 
				when (ph.ProductCategoryCode = 1 or pcc.KeyValue2 = '1') then 'WEALTH-INITIAL'
				when ph.ProductGroupCode = 3 then 'MORTGAGE'
				when ph.ProductGroupCode = 6 then 'PROTECTION'
				else null
			end as CalculationType,
			'Openwork 2006' as Source,
			@DateLastUpdated as DateInserted,
			@DateLastUpdated as DateLastUpdated,
			csp.year as CommissionYear
	--select count(*)
	from	msit_CommissionStatement cs
/*			inner join (select	distinct PKID
						from	owt_TransformationMovements tm 
						where	tm.DriverTableName = 'sa_swift_S_AGMFIL'
						and		tm.CommissionStatement = 'Y') tm on tm.PKID = cs.PendingPaymentID
*/			inner join mstt_Agents ag on ag.Code = cs.BusinessCode
			inner join mstt_PolicyTransactions pt on pt.ID = cs.TransactionID
			inner join mstt_Policies p on p.POL_NUM = pt.PolicyID
			inner join msit_CommissionStatementPeriods VNBStart on convert(date,pt.CreateDateTime) between VNBStart.PeriodStartDate and VNBStart.PeriodEndDate
			inner join msit_Commissionstatementperiods csp on csp.month = cs.month
			inner join mstt_ProductHierarchy ph on ph.productcode = cs.productcode
			inner join mstt_Expectation e on e.ID = cs.ExpectationID
			left join dbo.owt_MortgageBrokerFees mbf on mbf.PendingPaymentID = cs.PendingPaymentID and mbf.AdviceFeeCharged = 'Yes'
			left join owt_SelectionControl SC
						on SC.Process = 'ElitePoints' 
						and SC.KeyType = 'NSCPotCode' 
						and cs.CreateDate between SC.EffectiveStartDate and SC.EffectiveEndDate
			left join mstt_Commissions BSCpot
						on BSCpot.TransactionID = cs.TransactionID 
						and BSCpot.Agent_Code = sc.KeyValue
						and BSCpot.CommissionType = 10
			left join owt_SelectionControl SFMPC						
						on SFMPC.Process = 'ElitePoints' 
						and SFMPC.KeyType = 'ServicingFeeMarginPotCode' 
						and cs.CreateDate between SFMPC.EffectiveStartDate and SFMPC.EffectiveEndDate
			left join mstt_Commissions SFMpot							
						on SFMpot.TransactionID = cs.TransactionID 
						and SFMpot.Agent_Code = SFMPC.KeyValue
						and SFMpot.CommissionType = 10	
			left join owt_SelectionControl pcc 
						on pcc.Process = 'ElitePoints'
						and pcc.KeyType = 'ProductCategoryCode'
						and pcc.KeyValue = cs.ProductCode	
						and cs.CreateDate between pcc.EffectiveStartDate and pcc.EffectiveEndDate
			left join owt_SelectionControl ogsdflt 
						on ogsdflt.Process = 'ElitePoints'
						and ogsdflt.KeyType = 'DefaultOngoingServicingRate'
						and ogsdflt.SelectionType = 'VNB'
						and ogsdflt.KeyValue = case when ph.RDRType = 'ONPLAT' then 'ONPLAT' else 'OFPLAT' end
						and cs.CreateDate between ogsdflt.EffectiveStartDate and ogsdflt.EffectiveEndDate
			left join mstt_CodeProductGroup pg on pg.ProductGroupCode = case when pcc.KeyValue2 = '1' then 2 else ph.ProductGroupCode end
			left join owt_EliteFactors Cfca on Cfca.FeeType = 'VNB' and Cfca.category = 'COB-FCA-RATE' and csp.year between Cfca.StartYear and Cfca.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors Crate on Crate.FeeType = 'VNB' and Crate.category = 'COB-RETENTION-RATE' and csp.year between Crate.StartYear and Crate.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors Mfca on Mfca.FeeType = 'VNB' and Mfca.category = 'MORT-FCA-RATE' and csp.year between Mfca.StartYear and Mfca.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors MRproc on MRproc.FeeType = 'VNB' and MRproc.category = 'MORT-RETENTION-RATE-PROC' and csp.year between MRproc.StartYear and MRproc.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors MRbkr on MRbkr.FeeType = 'VNB' and MRbkr.category = 'MORT-RETENTION-RATE-BROKER' and csp.year between MRbkr.StartYear and MRbkr.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors Pfca on Pfca.FeeType = 'VNB' and Pfca.category = 'PROT-FCA-RATE' and csp.year between Pfca.StartYear and Pfca.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors Prate on Prate.FeeType = 'VNB' and Prate.category = 'PROT-RETENTION-RATE' and csp.year between Prate.StartYear and Prate.EndYear 
			left join msit_CommissionStatement csadj 
						on csadj.TransactionID = cs.TransactionID 
						and csadj.AgentCode = cs.AgentCode 
						and csadj.CommissionType in (2,17)
						and	csadj.PayBasisCode in ('F')				--Accrual
						and	csadj.FrequencyCode <> 6				--Regular 
	where	cs.ReportingClassCode = 1
	and		ag.Manager2Code <> @OwlManager2Code		--Exclude Owl
	and		cs.INIssued <> 0
	and		csp.Year >= 2017						--Ensure in-scope payments are consistent with VNB start
	and		VNBStart.Year >= 2017
	and		cs.CommissionType in (1,2,17)
	and		abs(e.AMOUNT_REC) >= 0.01	
	--and		((VNBStart.Year >= 2017 and cs.CommissionType = 1 and e.AMOUNT_REC >= 0.01)		--VNB to start from new slices in 2017 for +ve payments but...			AG 11/06/2018 (2)
	--		or (cs.CommissionType in (2,17) or e.AMOUNT_REC <= -0.01))						--...for -ve payments, the slice can start from any date in the past	AG 11/06/2018 (2)
	and		csadj.ID is null						--Deal with accrual regular clawbacks/adjustments later

	select @RowCount = @@rowcount
	set @ProcessMessage = '#owt_Recognition (ini ph1 - no accr adj) = ' + convert(nvarchar(10), @RowCount)
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseLog, @ProcessMessage, null, @Module, @Client

	/****************************************************************************

		Now deal with accrual clawbacks and adjustments
																		
	****************************************************************************/

	--drop table #msit_CommissionStatementSUMMARY

	create table #msit_CommissionStatementSUMMARY
	(
		TransactionID						int,
		AgentCode							varchar(7),
		MinInitialPendingPaymentID			varchar(10),
		MaxInitialPendingPaymentID			varchar(10),	
		MaxAdjPendingPaymentID				varchar(10),
		MinInitialAfterAdjPendingPaymentID	varchar(10)
	)

	--Find transactions with clawbacks/adj on them
	insert into #msit_CommissionStatementSUMMARY
	(
		TransactionID,
		AgentCode,
		MinInitialPendingPaymentID,
		MaxInitialPendingPaymentID,	
		MaxAdjPendingPaymentID,
		MinInitialAfterAdjPendingPaymentID
	)
	select	cs.TransactionID,
			cs.AgentCode,
			Min(case when cs.CommissionType = 1 then cs.PendingPaymentID else null end) as MinInitialPendingPaymentID,
			MAX(case when cs.CommissionType = 1 then cs.PendingPaymentID else null end) as MaxInitialPendingPaymentID,
			MAX(case when cs.CommissionType in (2,17) then cs.PendingPaymentID else null end) as MaxAdjPendingPaymentID,
			null as MinInitialAfterAdjPendingPaymentID
	--into	#msit_CommissionStatementSUMMARY
	from	msit_CommissionStatement cs
			inner join mstt_Agents ag on ag.Code = cs.BusinessCode
			inner join mstt_PolicyTransactions pt on pt.ID = cs.TransactionID
			inner join mstt_Policies p on p.POL_NUM = pt.PolicyID
			inner join msit_CommissionStatementPeriods VNBStart on convert(date,pt.CreateDateTime) between VNBStart.PeriodStartDate and VNBStart.PeriodEndDate
			inner join msit_Commissionstatementperiods csp on csp.month = cs.month
			inner join mstt_Expectation e on e.ID = cs.ExpectationID
			left join msit_CommissionStatement csadj 
						on csadj.TransactionID = cs.TransactionID 
						and csadj.AgentCode = cs.AgentCode 
						and csadj.CommissionType in (2,17)
						and	csadj.PayBasisCode in ('F')				--Accrual
						and	csadj.FrequencyCode <> 6				--Regular 
	where	cs.ReportingClassCode = 1
	and		cs.CommissionType in (1,2,17)			--We want all the initial payment types (i.e. not trail (ongoing))
	and		ag.Manager2Code <> @OwlManager2Code		--Exclude Owl
	and		csp.Year >= 2017						--Ensure in-scope payments are consistent with VNB start
	and		VNBStart.Year >= 2017 
	and		abs(e.AMOUNT_REC) >= 0.01	
	and		csadj.ID is not null					--select regular accrual transactions with clawbacks/adjustments
	--and cs.TransactionID in (5613333,6296827)
	group by	cs.TransactionID,
				cs.AgentCode

	select @RowCount = @@rowcount
	set @ProcessMessage = '#msit_CommissionStatementSUMMARY (accr adj txns) = ' + convert(nvarchar(10), @RowCount)
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseLog, @ProcessMessage, null, @Module, @Client

	--Get first initial payment after last clawback/adj
	update css
		set MinInitialAfterAdjPendingPaymentID = summ.MinPendingPaymentID 
	from  #msit_CommissionStatementSUMMARY css
			inner join  (
						select cssinner.TransactionID, cssinner.AgentCode, min(cs.PendingPaymentID) as MinPendingPaymentID
						from #msit_CommissionStatementSUMMARY cssinner
								inner join msit_CommissionStatement cs
											on cs.TransactionID = cssinner.TransactionID
											and cs.AgentCode = cssinner.AgentCode
						where cs.PendingPaymentID > cssinner.MaxAdjPendingPaymentID
						group by cssinner.TransactionID, cssinner.AgentCode
						) summ on  summ.TransactionID = css.TransactionID
							   and summ.AgentCode = css.AgentCode

	select @RowCount = @@rowcount
	set @ProcessMessage = '#msit_CommissionStatementSUMMARY (1st IC after adj) = ' + convert(nvarchar(10), @RowCount)
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseLog, @ProcessMessage, null, @Module, @Client

	/****************************************************************************

		Phase 2 - This phase deals with regular accrual cases where there is at 
		least one clawback/adjustment. In this scenario the VNB is changed from 
		front loaded to a per payment basis.
																		
	****************************************************************************/

	insert into #AG_owt_Recognition_SEPARATE_ONGOING
	(
		SourceID,
		CaseID,
		TransactionID,
		Policy,
		ProductCode,
		BusinessCode,
		SellerCode,						
		PointsTotal,
		BSC,
		MBF,
		Initial,
		OngoingTotal,
		OngoingYr01,
		OngoingYr02,
		OngoingYr03,
		OngoingYr04,
		OngoingYr05,
		OngoingYr06,
		OngoingYr07,
		OngoingYr08,
		OngoingYr09,
		OngoingYr10,
		FCARate,
		RetentionRate,
		RetentionRateBroker,
		OngoingServicingRate,
		OngoingServicingSource,
		DA,
		AmountReceived,
		Premium,
		AgentSplit,
		CommissionType,
		CommissionTypeDesc,
		PayBasisCode,					
		PayBasisDesc,					
		PaymentMatchedDate,				
		Month,
		FrequencyCode,
		FrequencyDesc,
		ReassignedProductGroupCode,		
		ReassignedProductGroupName,		
		RecognitionType,
		CalculationType,
		Source,
		DateInserted,
		DateLastUpdated,
		CommissionYear
	)
	select	cs.PendingPaymentID as SourceID,
			cs.CaseID,
			cs.TransactionID,
			cs.ExtPolicyNumber as Policy,
			cs.ProductCode,
			cs.BusinessCode,
			cs.AgentCode as SellerCode,				
			0.0 as PointsTotal,
			0.0 as BSC,
			case 
				when mbf.MortgageFeeID is not null and cs.INIssued <> 0 then (((mbf.AdviceFeeAmount)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * MRbkr.FACTOR) - ((mbf.AdviceFeeAmount)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * Mfca.FACTOR)) --Note that mbf.AdviceFeeAmount is signed correctly - so no coding for signing is needed here
				else 0.0
			end as MBF,
			case 
				--When the adviser has changed, the AgentSplit can become zero in which case the ELITE points should be zero.
				when cs.AgentSplit = 0 then 0
				
				--WEALTH CALCULATION START
				--Indemnity payments or SINGLEs or IC Clawbacks or IC adjustments Start
				--THIS SCENARIO DOESN'T OCCUR IN PHASE 2
				--Indemnity payments or SINGLEs or IC Clawbacks or IC adjustments End
				--Accruals & Level Start
				when (ph.ProductCategoryCode = 1 or pcc.KeyValue2 = '1') then (((e.AMOUNT_REC)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * Crate.FACTOR) - ((e.AMOUNT_REC)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * Cfca.FACTOR)) * case when cs.CommissionType in (2,17) then -1 else 1 end
				--Accruals & Level End
				--WEALTH CALCULATION END
				
				--MORTGAGE CALCULATION START
				--Note: The MBF component has its own table column
				--Only 1 payment for mortgages
				when ph.ProductGroupCode = 3 then (((e.AMOUNT_REC)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * MRproc.FACTOR) - ((e.AMOUNT_REC)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * Mfca.FACTOR)) * case when cs.CommissionType in (2,17) then -1 else 1 end	
				--MORTGAGE CALCULATION END
				
				--PROTECTION CALCULATION START
				--Indemnity payments or SINGLEs or IC Clawbacks or IC adjustments Start
				--THIS SCENARIO DOESN'T OCCUR IN PHASE 2
				--Indemnity payments or SINGLEs or IC Clawbacks or IC adjustments End
				--Accruals & Level Start
				when ph.ProductGroupCode = 6 then (((e.AMOUNT_REC)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * Prate.FACTOR) - ((e.AMOUNT_REC)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * Pfca.FACTOR)) * case when cs.CommissionType in (2,17) then -1 else 1 end
				--Accruals & Level End
				--PROTECTION CALCULATION END

				else 0.0

			end as Initial,
			0.0 as OngoingTotal,
			0.0 as OngoingYr01,
			0.0 as OngoingYr02,
			0.0 as OngoingYr03,
			0.0 as OngoingYr04,
			0.0 as OngoingYr05,
			0.0 as OngoingYr06,
			0.0 as OngoingYr07,
			0.0 as OngoingYr08,
			0.0 as OngoingYr09,
			0.0 as OngoingYr10,
			case 
				when (ph.ProductCategoryCode = 1 or pcc.KeyValue2 = '1') then Cfca.FACTOR*100.0		--COB
				when ph.ProductGroupCode = 3 then Mfca.FACTOR*100.0		--MORT
				when ph.ProductGroupCode = 6 then Pfca.FACTOR*100.0		--PROT
				else 0.0
			end as FCARate,
			case 
				when (ph.ProductCategoryCode = 1 or pcc.KeyValue2 = '1') then Crate.FACTOR*100.0	--COB
				when ph.ProductGroupCode = 3 then MRproc.FACTOR*100.0	--MORT
				when ph.ProductGroupCode = 6 then Prate.FACTOR*100.0	--PROT
				else 0.0
			end as RetentionRate,
			case 
				when mbf.MortgageFeeID is not null then  MRbkr.FACTOR*100.0	
				else 0.0
			end as RetentionRateBroker,
			null as OngoingServicingRate,
			null as OngoingServicingSource,
			pt.CommInitialAmount as DA,
			e.AMOUNT_REC as AmountReceived,
			cs.Premium,
			cs.AgentSplit,
			cs.CommissionType,
			left(cs.StandingOrderDesc,50) as CommissionTypeDesc,
			cs.PayBasisCode,							
			cs.PayBasisDesc,							
			cs.CreateDate as PaymentMatchedDate,		
			cs.Month,
			cs.FrequencyCode,
			cs.FrequencyDesc,
			pg.ProductGroupCode as ReassignedProductGroupCode,	--Force the re-assigned products...		
			pg.ProductGroupName as ReassignedProductGroupName,	--...to be processed as investments		
			'VNB-INI-PHASE-2' as RecognitionType,
			case 
				when (ph.ProductCategoryCode = 1 or pcc.KeyValue2 = '1') then 'WEALTH-INITIAL'
				when ph.ProductGroupCode = 3 then 'MORTGAGE'
				when ph.ProductGroupCode = 6 then 'PROTECTION'
				else null
			end as CalculationType,
			'Openwork 2006' as Source,
			@DateLastUpdated as DateInserted,
			@DateLastUpdated as DateLastUpdated,
			csp.year as CommissionYear
	from	#msit_CommissionStatementSUMMARY css
			inner join msit_CommissionStatement cs
						on cs.TransactionID = css.TransactionID
						and cs.AgentCode = css.AgentCode
			inner join mstt_Agents ag on ag.Code = cs.BusinessCode
			inner join mstt_PolicyTransactions pt on pt.ID = cs.TransactionID
			inner join mstt_Policies p on p.POL_NUM = pt.PolicyID
			inner join msit_CommissionStatementPeriods VNBStart on convert(date,pt.CreateDateTime) between VNBStart.PeriodStartDate and VNBStart.PeriodEndDate
			inner join msit_Commissionstatementperiods csp on csp.month = cs.month
			inner join mstt_ProductHierarchy ph on ph.productcode = cs.productcode
			inner join mstt_Expectation e on e.ID = cs.ExpectationID
			left join dbo.owt_MortgageBrokerFees mbf on mbf.PendingPaymentID = cs.PendingPaymentID and mbf.AdviceFeeCharged = 'Yes'
			left join owt_SelectionControl SC
						on SC.Process = 'ElitePoints' 
						and SC.KeyType = 'NSCPotCode' 
						and cs.CreateDate between SC.EffectiveStartDate and SC.EffectiveEndDate
			left join mstt_Commissions BSCpot
						on BSCpot.TransactionID = cs.TransactionID 
						and BSCpot.Agent_Code = sc.KeyValue
						and BSCpot.CommissionType = 10
			left join owt_SelectionControl SFMPC						
						on SFMPC.Process = 'ElitePoints' 
						and SFMPC.KeyType = 'ServicingFeeMarginPotCode' 
						and cs.CreateDate between SFMPC.EffectiveStartDate and SFMPC.EffectiveEndDate
			left join mstt_Commissions SFMpot							
						on SFMpot.TransactionID = cs.TransactionID 
						and SFMpot.Agent_Code = SFMPC.KeyValue
						and SFMpot.CommissionType = 10	
			left join owt_SelectionControl pcc 
						on pcc.Process = 'ElitePoints'
						and pcc.KeyType = 'ProductCategoryCode'
						and pcc.KeyValue = cs.ProductCode	
						and cs.CreateDate between pcc.EffectiveStartDate and pcc.EffectiveEndDate
			left join owt_SelectionControl ogsdflt 
						on ogsdflt.Process = 'ElitePoints'
						and ogsdflt.KeyType = 'DefaultOngoingServicingRate'
						and ogsdflt.SelectionType = 'VNB'
						and ogsdflt.KeyValue = case when ph.RDRType = 'ONPLAT' then 'ONPLAT' else 'OFPLAT' end
						and cs.CreateDate between ogsdflt.EffectiveStartDate and ogsdflt.EffectiveEndDate
			left join mstt_CodeProductGroup pg on pg.ProductGroupCode = case when pcc.KeyValue2 = '1' then 2 else ph.ProductGroupCode end
			left join owt_EliteFactors Cfca on Cfca.FeeType = 'VNB' and Cfca.category = 'COB-FCA-RATE' and csp.year between Cfca.StartYear and Cfca.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors Crate on Crate.FeeType = 'VNB' and Crate.category = 'COB-RETENTION-RATE' and csp.year between Crate.StartYear and Crate.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors Mfca on Mfca.FeeType = 'VNB' and Mfca.category = 'MORT-FCA-RATE' and csp.year between Mfca.StartYear and Mfca.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors MRproc on MRproc.FeeType = 'VNB' and MRproc.category = 'MORT-RETENTION-RATE-PROC' and csp.year between MRproc.StartYear and MRproc.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors MRbkr on MRbkr.FeeType = 'VNB' and MRbkr.category = 'MORT-RETENTION-RATE-BROKER' and csp.year between MRbkr.StartYear and MRbkr.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors Pfca on Pfca.FeeType = 'VNB' and Pfca.category = 'PROT-FCA-RATE' and csp.year between Pfca.StartYear and Pfca.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors Prate on Prate.FeeType = 'VNB' and Prate.category = 'PROT-RETENTION-RATE' and csp.year between Prate.StartYear and Prate.EndYear 
	where	cs.ReportingClassCode = 1
	and		cs.CommissionType in (1,2,17)			--We want all the initial payment types (i.e. not trail (ongoing))
	and		ag.Manager2Code <> @OwlManager2Code		--Exclude Owl

	select @RowCount = @@rowcount
	set @ProcessMessage = '#owt_Recognition (ini ph2 - accr adj) = ' + convert(nvarchar(10), @RowCount)
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseLog, @ProcessMessage, null, @Module, @Client

	/****************************************************************************

		Initial Phase 3
		1) Add up the +ves and -ves prior to the NEW front loaded amount and
			net them off on the first +ve following the last -ve
		2) Now set all the +ves following the one updated in (1) to zero.
																
	****************************************************************************/

	update r
		set RecognitionType	= case when r.SourceID >= css.MinInitialAfterAdjPendingPaymentID 
								then 'VNB-INI-PHASE-3'
								else r.RecognitionType
							  end,
			Initial = case  when r.SourceID = css.MinInitialAfterAdjPendingPaymentID 
								then (((r.DA)*(r.AgentSplit/100) * (r.RetentionRate/100.0)) - ((r.DA)*(r.AgentSplit/100) * (r.FCARate/100))) - derived.SumInitial
							when r.SourceID > css.MinInitialAfterAdjPendingPaymentID 
								then 0.0
							else r.Initial
					  end,
			DateLastUpdated = @DateLastUpdated
	from	#msit_CommissionStatementSUMMARY css
			inner join #AG_owt_Recognition_SEPARATE_ONGOING r
						on r.TransactionID = css.TransactionID
						and r.SellerCode = css.AgentCode
			inner join (select	r.TransactionID, r.SellerCode, SUM(Initial) as SumInitial
						from	#msit_CommissionStatementSUMMARY s
								inner join #AG_owt_Recognition_SEPARATE_ONGOING r 
											on r.TransactionID = s.TransactionID
											and r.SellerCode = s.AgentCode
						where	r.SourceID <= s.MaxAdjPendingPaymentID
						group	by r.TransactionID, r.SellerCode
						) derived 
							on  derived.TransactionID = r.TransactionID
							and	derived.SellerCode = r.SellerCode 
	where	isnull(css.MaxInitialPendingPaymentID,0) > isnull(css.MaxAdjPendingPaymentID,0)-- An initial payment follows the clawback, so time to revert back to front loading

	select @RowCount = @@rowcount
	set @ProcessMessage = '#owt_Recognition (ini ph3 - accr adj) = ' + convert(nvarchar(10), @RowCount)
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseLog, @ProcessMessage, null, @Module, @Client

	/****************************************************************************

		Now do the ongoing.
		
		Build an ongoing summary row for each transaction (slice).
		
		Note we do not care about ongoing clawbacks and adjustments for VNB.
		We want VNB to be on the oldest positive payment on each slice for the
		policy (split by adviser if needed).
						
	****************************************************************************/

	create table #msit_CommissionStatementOGSSUMMARY
	(
		CaseID								varchar(10),
		TransactionID						varchar(10),
		AgentCode							varchar(7),
		AgentSplit							float,
		MinOngoingPendingPaymentID			varchar(10),
		MaxOngoingPendingPaymentID			varchar(10),
		MaxOngoingAdjPendingPaymentID		varchar(10),
		MaxPremium							float,
		MinOngoingAfterAdjPendingPaymentID	varchar(10),
		Premium								float,						
		FrequencyCode						tinyint,
		FrequencyDesc						varchar(20)
	)

	insert into #msit_CommissionStatementOGSSUMMARY
	(
		CaseID,
		TransactionID,
		AgentCode,
		AgentSplit,
		MinOngoingPendingPaymentID,
		MaxOngoingPendingPaymentID,
		MaxOngoingAdjPendingPaymentID,
		MaxPremium,
		MinOngoingAfterAdjPendingPaymentID,
		Premium,						
		FrequencyCode,
		FrequencyDesc
	)
	select	cs.CaseID,
			cs.TransactionID,
			cs.AgentCode,
			c.AGENT_PERC as AgentSplit,
			min(case when cs.CommissionType = 10 then cs.PendingPaymentID else null end) as MinOngoingPendingPaymentID,
			max(case when cs.CommissionType = 10 then cs.PendingPaymentID else null end) as MaxOngoingPendingPaymentID,
			max(case when cs.CommissionType in (16,19) then cs.PendingPaymentID else null end) as MaxOngoingAdjPendingPaymentID,
			max(case when cs.CommissionType = 10 then case when cs.FrequencyCode <> 6 then (cs.Premium * 12.0 * (c.Agent_Perc/100)) else (cs.Premium * (c.Agent_Perc/100)) end else 0.0 end) as MaxPremium,	--AG 19/07/2018
			null as MinOngoingAfterAdjPendingPaymentID,
			cs.Premium,			--AG 17/07/2018
			cs.FrequencyCode,	--AG 17/07/2018
			cs.FrequencyDesc	--AG 17/07/2018
	--into	#msit_CommissionStatementOGSSUMMARY
	from 	msit_CommissionStatement cs
			inner join mstt_Commissions c
						on c.TransactionID = cs.TransactionID
						and c.Agent_Code = cs.AgentCode
						and c.CommissionType = 1
			inner join mstt_Agents ag on ag.Code = cs.BusinessCode
			inner join mstt_PolicyTransactions pt on pt.ID = cs.TransactionID
			inner join mstt_Policies p on p.POL_NUM = pt.PolicyID
			inner join msit_CommissionStatementPeriods VNBStart on convert(date,pt.CreateDateTime) between VNBStart.PeriodStartDate and VNBStart.PeriodEndDate
			inner join msit_Commissionstatementperiods csp on csp.month = cs.month
			inner join mstt_ProductHierarchy ph on ph.productcode = cs.productcode
			inner join mstt_Expectation e on e.ID = cs.ExpectationID
			left join owt_SelectionControl pcc 
						on pcc.Process = 'ElitePoints'
						and pcc.KeyType = 'ProductCategoryCode'
						and pcc.KeyValue = cs.ProductCode	
						and cs.CreateDate between pcc.EffectiveStartDate and pcc.EffectiveEndDate
	where	cs.ReportingClassCode = 1
	and		cs.CommissionType in (10,16,19)					--Choose only where the ongoing payment is positive
	and		cs.CommFeeType = 'Ongoing'
	and		(ph.ProductCategoryCode = 1 or pcc.KeyValue2 = '1')
	and		ag.Manager2Code <> @OwlManager2Code		--Exclude Owl
	and		csp.Year >= 2017						--Ensure in-scope payments are consistent with VNB start
	and		VNBStart.Year >= 2017 
	and		abs(e.AMOUNT_REC) >= 0.01
	and		((cs.FrequencyCode = 6 and cs.Premium > 1.00)		--Frequency=6->Single
			or (cs.FrequencyCode <> 6 and cs.Premium > 0.01))	--Frequency<>6->Regular	
	group by	cs.CaseID,
				cs.TransactionID,
				cs.AgentCode,
				c.Agent_Perc,
				cs.Premium,			--AG 17/07/2018
				cs.FrequencyCode,	--AG 17/07/2018
				cs.FrequencyDesc	--AG 17/07/2018

	select @RowCount = @@rowcount
	set @ProcessMessage = '#msit_CommissionStatementOGSSUMMARY (ogs txn) = ' + convert(nvarchar(10), @RowCount)
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseLog, @ProcessMessage, null, @Module, @Client

	--Get first ongoing payment after last clawback/adj
	update cso
		set MinOngoingAfterAdjPendingPaymentID = summ.MinPendingPaymentID 
	from  #msit_CommissionStatementOGSSUMMARY cso
			inner join  (
						select	csoinner.TransactionID, csoinner.AgentCode, min(cs.PendingPaymentID) as MinPendingPaymentID
						from	#msit_CommissionStatementOGSSUMMARY csoinner
								inner join msit_CommissionStatement cs
											on cs.TransactionID = csoinner.TransactionID
											and cs.AgentCode = csoinner.AgentCode
						where	cs.PendingPaymentID > csoinner.MaxOngoingAdjPendingPaymentID
						and		cs.CommissionType = 10
						group by csoinner.TransactionID, csoinner.AgentCode
						) summ on  summ.TransactionID = cso.TransactionID
							   and summ.AgentCode = cso.AgentCode

	select @RowCount = @@rowcount
	set @ProcessMessage = '#msit_CommissionStatementOGSSUMMARY (ogs latest +ve) = ' + convert(nvarchar(10), @RowCount)
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseLog, @ProcessMessage, null, @Module, @Client

	/****************************************************************************
		
		Using the OGS SUMMARY table, get all the individual payment records that
		will be carriers of VNB points as follows:
		
		SelectionSource 1 - The oldest +ve payment where no clawbacks or 
								adjustments occur for front loading

		SelectionSource 2 - All the +ve payments that will get a spread of the 
								per payment +ve points 		

		SelectionSource 3 - All the -ve payments that will get a spread of the 
								per payment -ve points
								 															
	****************************************************************************/
	
	--AG 19/07/2018
	--Combine the premium on all the transactions (slices) for each case and seller
	--In case of mixed frequencies, force the sum to be a single
	create table #PremiumTotal
	(
		CaseID						int,
		SellerCode					varchar(7),
		InitialSumOfPremium			float,
		OngoingSumOfPremium			float,	
		MinOngoingPendingPaymentID	varchar(10)
	)

	insert into #PremiumTotal
	(
		CaseID,
		SellerCode,
		InitialSumOfPremium,
		OngoingSumOfPremium,	
		MinOngoingPendingPaymentID
	)
	select	CaseID,
			SellerCode,
			sum(case when CommissionType = 1 then SumOfPremium else 0 end) as InitialSumOfPremium,
			sum(case when CommissionType = 10 then SumOfPremium else 0 end) as OngoingSumOfPremium,
			min(case when CommissionType = 10 then MinOngoingPendingPaymentID end) as MinOngoingPendingPaymentID
	--into	#PremiumTotal
	from
		(
		select	CaseID,
				SellerCode,
				1 as CommissionType,						--IC
				min(SourceID) as MinOngoingPendingPaymentID,
				sum(case when FrequencyCode <> 6 then Premium * 12.0 * (AgentSplit/100) else Premium * (AgentSplit/100) end) as SumOfPremium
		from	#AG_owt_Recognition_SEPARATE_ONGOING
		where	CalculationType = 'WEALTH-INITIAL'
		and		CommissionType = 1
		group	by CaseID, SellerCode
		
		union
		
		select	CaseID,
				AgentCode as SellerCode,
				10 as CommissionType,						--Trail (OGS)
				min(MinOngoingPendingPaymentID) as MinOngoingPendingPaymentID,
				sum(MaxPremium) as SumOfPremium
		from	#msit_CommissionStatementOGSSUMMARY
		group	by CaseID, AgentCode
		) a
	group by CaseID, SellerCode

	select @RowCount = @@rowcount
	set @ProcessMessage = '#PremiumTotal = ' + convert(nvarchar(10), @RowCount)
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseLog, @ProcessMessage, null, @Module, @Client
	
	create table #msit_CommissionStatementONGOING
	(
		SelectionSource		int,
		TransactionID		varchar(10),
		AgentCode			varchar(7),
		PendingPaymentID	varchar(10),
		AgentSplit			decimal(8,4),
		Premium				decimal(16,2),
		FrequencyCode		tinyint,
		SpreadNumber		int,
		MaxSpread			int
	)
	
	--Front loaded -> Just the oldest +ve payment
	--Note: These transactions have NO clawbacks or adjustments
	insert into #msit_CommissionStatementONGOING
	(
		SelectionSource,
		TransactionID,
		AgentCode,
		PendingPaymentID,
		AgentSplit,
		Premium,
		FrequencyCode,
		SpreadNumber,
		MaxSpread
	)
	select	1 as SelectionSource,
			cso.TransactionID,
			cso.AgentCode,
			cso.MinOngoingPendingPaymentID as PendingPaymentID,
			cso.AgentSplit,
			case when ptot.CaseID is null
				then cso.Premium
				else	case when	ptot.MinOngoingPendingPaymentID = cso.MinOngoingPendingPaymentID 
									and ptot.InitialSumOfPremium - ptot.OngoingSumOfPremium > 0.0 
							then	cso.Premium + ptot.InitialSumOfPremium - ptot.OngoingSumOfPremium 
							else	cso.Premium 
						end	--AG 19/07/2018
			end as Premium,
			case when ptot.CaseID is null
				then cso.FrequencyCode
				else 6					--Single - had to be hardcoded because proc kept failing when column was used. Weird but true.
			end as FrequencyCode,
			1 as SpreadNumber,
			1 as MaxSpread 
	--into	#msit_CommissionStatementONGOING
	from	#msit_CommissionStatementOGSSUMMARY cso	
			left join mstt_PolicyTransactions pt on pt.ID = cso.TransactionID
			left join mstt_Policies p on p.POL_NUM = pt.PolicyID
			left join #PremiumTotal ptot				--When NO clawbacks or adjustments, the seller gets credit for the combined premium
						on ptot.CaseID = p.PolicyRef
						and ptot.SellerCode = cso.AgentCode
	where	cso.MaxOngoingAdjPendingPaymentID is null	--No clawbacks or adjustments - so front load
	and		cso.MinOngoingPendingPaymentID is not null	--At least one +ve payment on the transaction

	union	--Add in with dedupe
	
	--Per payment -> all +ve payments with max spread also used for divisor
	--Note: ALL these transactions have clawbacks or adjustments
	select	2 as SelectionSource,
			cso.TransactionID,
			cso.AgentCode,
			cs.PendingPaymentID,
			cso.AgentSplit,
			cso.Premium,
			cso.FrequencyCode,
			ROW_NUMBER() over (partition by cs.TransactionID, cs.AgentCode order by cs.TransactionID, cs.AgentCode, cs.PendingPaymentID) as SpreadNumber,
			12 as MaxSpread
	from	#msit_CommissionStatementOGSSUMMARY cso	
			inner join msit_CommissionStatement cs 
						on cs.TransactionID = cso.TransactionID
						and cs.AgentCode = cso.AgentCode
	where	cso.MaxOngoingAdjPendingPaymentID is not null	--Clawbacks or adjustments so per payment
	and		cs.CommissionType in (10)	

	union	--Add in with dedupe
	
	--Per payment -> all -ve payments - with max spread also used for divisor
	--Note: ALL these transactions have clawbacks or adjustments
	select	3 as SelectionSource,
			cso.TransactionID,
			cso.AgentCode,
			cs.PendingPaymentID,
			cso.AgentSplit,
			cso.Premium,
			cso.FrequencyCode,
			ROW_NUMBER() over (partition by cs.TransactionID, cs.AgentCode order by cs.TransactionID, cs.AgentCode, cs.PendingPaymentID) as SpreadNumber,
			12 as MaxSpread
	from	#msit_CommissionStatementOGSSUMMARY cso	
			inner join msit_CommissionStatement cs 
						on cs.TransactionID = cso.TransactionID
						and cs.AgentCode = cso.AgentCode
	where	cso.MaxOngoingAdjPendingPaymentID is not null	--Clawbacks or adjustments so per payment
	and		cs.CommissionType in (16,19)	

	select @RowCount = @@rowcount
	set @ProcessMessage = '#msit_CommissionStatementONGOING (ogs payments) = ' + convert(nvarchar(10), @RowCount)
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseLog, @ProcessMessage, null, @Module, @Client

	/****************************************************************************
		
		Insert the ongoing VNB results for those transactions 
																		
	****************************************************************************/

	insert into #AG_owt_Recognition_SEPARATE_ONGOING
	(
		SourceID,
		CaseID,
		TransactionID,
		Policy,
		ProductCode,
		BusinessCode,
		SellerCode,
		PointsTotal,
		BSC,
		MBF,
		Initial,
		OngoingTotal,
		OngoingYr01,
		OngoingYr02,
		OngoingYr03,
		OngoingYr04,
		OngoingYr05,
		OngoingYr06,
		OngoingYr07,
		OngoingYr08,
		OngoingYr09,
		OngoingYr10,
		FCARate,
		RetentionRate,
		RetentionRateBroker,
		OngoingServicingRate,
		OngoingServicingSource,
		DA,
		AmountReceived,
		Premium,
		AgentSplit,
		CommissionType,
		CommissionTypeDesc,
		PayBasisCode,
		PayBasisDesc,
		PaymentMatchedDate,
		Month,
		FrequencyCode,
		FrequencyDesc,
		ReassignedProductGroupCode,
		ReassignedProductGroupName,
		RecognitionType,
		CalculationType,
		Source,
		DateInserted,
		DateLastUpdated,
		CommissionYear
	)
	select	cs.PendingPaymentID as SourceID,
			cs.CaseID,
			cs.TransactionID,
			cs.ExtPolicyNumber as Policy,
			cs.ProductCode,
			cs.BusinessCode,
			cs.AgentCode as SellerCode,
			0.0 as PointsTotal,
			case
				when BSCpot.ID is not null then 
					--BSC takes the first 0.12 of the ongoing fee %. If the ongoing fee % is 0.12% or less, then 100% of the ongoing fee is allocated to BSC
					case when coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2)) - convert(decimal(8,4),sc.KeyValue2) >= 0.01
						then 
							case when cso.FrequencyCode = 2	--Monthly 
								then (cso.AgentSplit/100) * 12.0 * (isnull(cso.Premium/cso.MaxSpread,0)/2.0) * convert(decimal(8,4),sc.KeyValue3) * case when cs.CommissionType in (16,19) then -1 else 1 end
								else (cso.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(cso.Premium/cso.MaxSpread,0) * convert(decimal(8,4),sc.KeyValue3) * case when cs.CommissionType in (16,19) then -1 else 1 end
							end			
						else
							case when cso.FrequencyCode = 2	--Monthly 
								then (cso.AgentSplit/100) * 12.0 * (isnull(cso.Premium/cso.MaxSpread,0)/2.0) * coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2)) * case when cs.CommissionType in (16,19) then -1 else 1 end
								else (cso.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(cso.Premium/cso.MaxSpread,0) * (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))/100.0) * case when cs.CommissionType in (16,19) then -1 else 1 end
							end
					end
				else 0.0
			end as BSC,
			0.0 as MBF,
			0.0 as Initial,
			0.0 as OngoingTotal,
			case
				--WEALTH ONGOING CALCULATION START
				--When the adviser has changed, the AgentSplit can become zero in which case the ELITE points should be zero.
				when cso.AgentSplit = 0 then 0

				--SINGLE start
				--Calculate when BSC and ongoing applies (where ongoing rate is greater than BSC rate) 
				when cso.FrequencyCode = 6 and SFMpot.ID is not null and BSCpot.ID is not null and (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2)) - convert(decimal(8,4),sc.KeyValue2)) >= 0.01 then 
							--(AUM X BSC Rate)...
							((cso.AgentSplit/100) * (isnull(cso.Premium/cso.MaxSpread,0) * convert(decimal(8,4),sc.KeyValue3)) 
							--(AUM X OGS Rate X COB FCA Rate)...
							- ((cso.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(cso.Premium/cso.MaxSpread,0) * (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))/100.0) * Cfca.FACTOR)
							--(AUM X (OGS Rate - BSC Rate) X COB Retention Rate)...
							+ ((cso.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(cso.Premium/cso.MaxSpread,0) * ((coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))-convert(decimal(8,4),sc.KeyValue2))/100.0)) * Crate.FACTOR) 
							--Sign correctly for +ve or clawback payment
							* (case when cs.CommissionType in (16,19) then -1 else 1 end)
				--Calculate when BSC and ongoing applies (where ongoing rate less than BSC rate, then BSC gets all the ongoing available) 
				when cso.FrequencyCode = 6 and SFMpot.ID is not null and BSCpot.ID is not null then
							--(AUM X BSC Rate)...(in this scenario it's all of the OGS rate)
							((cso.AgentSplit/100) * (isnull(cso.Premium/cso.MaxSpread,0) * (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))/100.0)) 
							--(AUM X OGS Rate X COB FCA Rate)...
							- ((cso.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(cso.Premium/cso.MaxSpread,0) * (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))/100.0) * Cfca.FACTOR)
							--(AUM X (OGS Rate - BSC Rate) X COB Retention Rate)...
							+ (0.0)) --BSC got it all, so this part of the calculation is zero
							--Sign correctly for +ve or clawback payment
							* (case when cs.CommissionType in (16,19) then -1 else 1 end)
				--Calculate when no BSC applies and ongoing applies
				when cso.FrequencyCode = 6 and SFMpot.ID is not null and BSCpot.ID is null then 
							--(AUM X OGS Rate X COB Retention Rate)...
							(((cso.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(cso.Premium/cso.MaxSpread,0) * (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))/100.0) * Crate.FACTOR) 
							--(AUM X OGS Rate X COB FCA Rate)...
							- ((cso.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(cso.Premium/cso.MaxSpread,0) * (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))/100.0) * Cfca.FACTOR))
							--Sign correctly for +ve or clawback payment
							* (case when cs.CommissionType in (16,19) then -1 else 1 end)
				--SINGLE end
				
				--REGULAR start
				--Calculate when BSC and ongoing applies (where ongoing rate is greater than BSC rate) 
				when cso.FrequencyCode <> 6 and SFMpot.ID is not null and BSCpot.ID is not null and (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2)) - convert(decimal(8,4),sc.KeyValue2)) >= 0.01 then		--AG 04/06/2018 (1)
							--The non-BSC portion (Ave AUM X (OGS Rate - BSC Rate) X COB Retention Rate)...
							((((((cso.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(cso.Premium/cso.MaxSpread,0) * (case when cso.FrequencyCode = 2 then 12 else 1 end))/2.0) * (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2)) - convert(decimal(8,4),sc.KeyValue2))/100.0)) * Crate.FACTOR
							--The BSC portion (Ave AUM X BSC Rate)...
							+ case when cso.FrequencyCode = 2	--Monthly 
									then (cso.AgentSplit/100) * 12.0 * (isnull(cso.Premium/cso.MaxSpread,0)/2.0) * convert(decimal(8,4),sc.KeyValue3) 
									else (cso.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(cso.Premium/cso.MaxSpread,0) * convert(decimal(8,4),sc.KeyValue3) 
							  end
							--FCA Charge (Ave AUM X OGS Rate X FCA Rate)...
							- (case when cso.FrequencyCode = 2	--Monthly 
									then (cso.AgentSplit/100) * 12.0 * (isnull(cso.Premium/cso.MaxSpread,0)/2.0) 
									else (cso.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(cso.Premium/cso.MaxSpread,0) 
							   end * (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))/100.0) * Cfca.FACTOR))
							--Sign correctly for +ve or clawback payment
							* (case when cs.CommissionType in (16,19) then -1 else 1 end)   
				--Calculate when BSC and ongoing applies (where ongoing rate less than BSC rate, then BSC gets all the ongoing available) 
				when cso.FrequencyCode <> 6 and SFMpot.ID is not null and BSCpot.ID is not null then		--AG 04/06/2018 (1)
							--The non-BSC portion (Ave AUM X (OGS Rate - BSC Rate) X COB Retention Rate)...
							((0.0)	--BSC got it all, so this part of the calculation is zero
							--The BSC portion (Ave AUM X BSC Rate)...(in this scenario it's all of the OGS rate)
							+ case when cso.FrequencyCode = 2	--Monthly 
									then (cso.AgentSplit/100) * 12.0 * (isnull(cso.Premium/cso.MaxSpread,0)/2.0) * (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))/100.0) 
									else (cso.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(cso.Premium/cso.MaxSpread,0) * (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))/100.0) 
							  end
							--FCA Charge (Ave AUM X OGS Rate X FCA Rate)...
							- (case when cso.FrequencyCode = 2	--Monthly 
									then (cso.AgentSplit/100) * 12.0 * (isnull(cso.Premium/cso.MaxSpread,0)/2.0) 
									else (cso.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(cso.Premium/cso.MaxSpread,0) 
							   end * (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))/100.0) * Cfca.FACTOR))
							--Sign correctly for +ve or clawback payment
							* (case when cs.CommissionType in (16,19) then -1 else 1 end)   
				--Calculate when no BSC applies, but ongoing servicing applies
				when cso.FrequencyCode <> 6 and SFMpot.ID is not null and BSCpot.ID is null then		--AG 04/06/2018	(1)
							--(Ave AUM X OGS Rate X COB Retention Rate)...
							(((((cso.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(cso.Premium/cso.MaxSpread,0) * (case when cso.FrequencyCode = 2 then 12 else 1 end))/2.0) * (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))/100.0) * Crate.FACTOR) 
							--(Ave AUM X OGS Rate X COB FCA Rate)...
							- ((((cso.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(cso.Premium/cso.MaxSpread,0) * (case when cso.FrequencyCode = 2 then 12 else 1 end))/2.0) * (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))/100.0) * Cfca.FACTOR))
							--Sign correctly for +ve or clawback payment
							* (case when cs.CommissionType in (16,19) then -1 else 1 end)   
				--REGULAR end
				
				else 0.0

				--WEALTH ONGOING CALCULATION END
			end as OngoingYr01,
			0.0 as OngoingYr02,
			0.0 as OngoingYr03,
			0.0 as OngoingYr04,
			0.0 as OngoingYr05,
			0.0 as OngoingYr06,
			0.0 as OngoingYr07,
			0.0 as OngoingYr08,
			0.0 as OngoingYr09,
			0.0 as OngoingYr10,
			Cfca.FACTOR*100.0 as FCARate,
			Crate.FACTOR*100.0 as RetentionRate,
			0.0 as RetentionRateBroker,
			case when SFMpot.ID is not null
				then coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))
				else null
			end as OngoingServicingRate,
			case when SFMpot.ID is not null
				then case 
						when ogs.OngoingServiceFee is null and ogscli.OngoingServiceFee is null 
							then case
								when ogsdflt.KeyValue = 'ONPLAT' then 'Default - On Plat'
								else 'Default - Off Plat'
							end
						when ogs.OngoingServiceFee is not null then 'Client Product'
						when ogscli.OngoingServiceFee is not null then 'Client Only'
						else 'Unknown'
					 end
				else case when (ph.ProductCategoryCode = 1 or pcc.KeyValue2 = '1')
						then 'No OGS'					--WEALTH, but no OGS
						else null						--Not WEALTH, so OGS is n/a and is therefore null
					 end
			end as OngoingServicingSource,
			pt.CommInitialAmount as DA,
			e.AMOUNT_REC as AmountReceived,
			cso.Premium,								--AG 17/07/2018
			cso.AgentSplit,								--Use the split from the IC record
			cs.CommissionType,
			left(cs.StandingOrderDesc,50) as CommissionTypeDesc,
			cs.PayBasisCode,
			cs.PayBasisDesc,
			cs.CreateDate as PaymentMatchedDate,
			cs.Month,
			cso.FrequencyCode,							--AG 17/07/2018
			case when cso.FrequencyCode = 6
				then 'Single'
				else 'Monthly'
			end as FrequencyDesc,						--AG 17/07/2018
			pg.ProductGroupCode as ReassignedProductGroupCode,	--Force the re-assigned products...		
			pg.ProductGroupName as ReassignedProductGroupName,	--...to be processed as investments		
			case cso.SelectionSource
				when 1 then 'VNB-OGS-PHASE-1' 
				when 2 then 'VNB-OGS-PHASE-2' 
				when 3 then 'VNB-OGS-PHASE-3' 
			end as RecognitionType,
			'WEALTH-ONGOING' as CalculationType,
			'Openwork 2006' as Source,
			@DateLastUpdated as DateInserted,
			@DateLastUpdated as DateLastUpdated,
			csp.year as CommissionYear
	from	#msit_CommissionStatementONGOING cso
			inner join msit_CommissionStatement cs on cs.PendingPaymentID = cso.PendingPaymentID
			inner join mstt_Agents ag on ag.Code = cs.BusinessCode
			inner join mstt_PolicyTransactions pt on pt.ID = cs.TransactionID
			inner join mstt_Policies p on p.POL_NUM = pt.PolicyID
			inner join msit_CommissionStatementPeriods VNBStart on convert(date,pt.CreateDateTime) between VNBStart.PeriodStartDate and VNBStart.PeriodEndDate
			inner join msit_Commissionstatementperiods csp on csp.month = cs.month
			inner join mstt_ProductHierarchy ph on ph.productcode = cs.productcode
			inner join mstt_Expectation e on e.ID = cs.ExpectationID
			left join dbo.owt_MortgageBrokerFees mbf on mbf.PendingPaymentID = cs.PendingPaymentID and mbf.AdviceFeeCharged = 'Yes'
			left join owt_SelectionControl SC
						on SC.Process = 'ElitePoints' 
						and SC.KeyType = 'NSCPotCode' 
						and cs.CreateDate between SC.EffectiveStartDate and SC.EffectiveEndDate
			left join mstt_Commissions BSCpot
						on BSCpot.TransactionID = cs.TransactionID 
						and BSCpot.Agent_Code = sc.KeyValue
						and BSCpot.CommissionType = 10
			left join owt_SelectionControl SFMPC						
						on SFMPC.Process = 'ElitePoints' 
						and SFMPC.KeyType = 'ServicingFeeMarginPotCode' 
						and cs.CreateDate between SFMPC.EffectiveStartDate and SFMPC.EffectiveEndDate
			left join mstt_Commissions SFMpot							
						on SFMpot.TransactionID = cs.TransactionID 
						and SFMpot.Agent_Code = SFMPC.KeyValue
						and SFMpot.CommissionType = 10	
			left join owt_SelectionControl pcc 
						on pcc.Process = 'ElitePoints'
						and pcc.KeyType = 'ProductCategoryCode'
						and pcc.KeyValue = cs.ProductCode	
						and cs.CreateDate between pcc.EffectiveStartDate and pcc.EffectiveEndDate
			left join owt_SelectionControl ogsdflt 
						on ogsdflt.Process = 'ElitePoints'
						and ogsdflt.KeyType = 'DefaultOngoingServicingRate'
						and ogsdflt.SelectionType = 'VNB'
						and ogsdflt.KeyValue = case when ph.RDRType = 'ONPLAT' then 'ONPLAT' else 'OFPLAT' end
						and cs.CreateDate between ogsdflt.EffectiveStartDate and ogsdflt.EffectiveEndDate
			left join mstt_CodeProductGroup pg on pg.ProductGroupCode = case when pcc.KeyValue2 = '1' then 2 else ph.ProductGroupCode end
			left join owt_EliteFactors Cfca on Cfca.FeeType = 'VNB' and Cfca.category = 'COB-FCA-RATE' and csp.year between Cfca.StartYear and Cfca.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors Crate on Crate.FeeType = 'VNB' and Crate.category = 'COB-RETENTION-RATE' and csp.year between Crate.StartYear and Crate.EndYear 
			left join dbo.owt_OngoingRate ogs 
						on  ogs.CLIENT_NUM = cs.ClientID 
						and ogs.ProductCode = cs.ProductCode
						and convert(date,pt.CreateDateTime) between ogs.EffectiveStartDate and ogs.EffectiveEndDate
			left join dbo.owt_OngoingRate ogscli 
						on  ogscli.CLIENT_NUM = cs.ClientID 
						and ogscli.ProductCode = '(CLIENT)'
						and convert(date,pt.CreateDateTime) between ogscli.EffectiveStartDate and ogscli.EffectiveEndDate
	where	cso.SpreadNumber <= cso.MaxSpread	-- if per payment spreading, then limit the spread
	
	select @RowCount = @@rowcount
	set @ProcessMessage = '#owt_Recognition (ogs ph1 yr1) = ' + convert(nvarchar(10), @RowCount)
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseLog, @ProcessMessage, null, @Module, @Client

	/****************************************************************************

		Ongoing Phase 3
		1) Add up the +ves and -ves prior to the NEW front loaded amount and
			net them off on the first +ve following the last -ve
		2) Now set all the +ves following the one updated in (1) to zero.
																
	****************************************************************************/

	update r
		set RecognitionType	= case when r.SourceID >= csos.MinOngoingAfterAdjPendingPaymentID 
								then 'VNB-OGS-PHASE-4'
								else r.RecognitionType
							  end,
			OngoingYr01 = case  when r.SourceID = csos.MinOngoingAfterAdjPendingPaymentID 
									then (abs(r.OngoingYr01) * cso.MaxSpread) - derived.SumOngoingYr01
								when r.SourceID > csos.MinOngoingAfterAdjPendingPaymentID 
									then 0.0
								else r.OngoingYr01
						  end,
			DateLastUpdated = @DateLastUpdated
	from	#msit_CommissionStatementONGOING cso 
			inner join #AG_owt_Recognition_SEPARATE_ONGOING r on r.SourceID = cso.PendingPaymentID
			inner join #msit_CommissionStatementOGSSUMMARY csos
						on  csos.TransactionID = cso.TransactionID
						and csos.AgentCode = cso.AgentCode
			inner join (select	r.TransactionID, r.SellerCode, SUM(OngoingYr01) as SumOngoingYr01
						from	#msit_CommissionStatementOGSSUMMARY s
								inner join #AG_owt_Recognition_SEPARATE_ONGOING r 
											on r.TransactionID = s.TransactionID
											and r.SellerCode = s.AgentCode
						where	r.SourceID <= s.MaxOngoingAdjPendingPaymentID
						group	by r.TransactionID, r.SellerCode
						) derived 
							on  derived.TransactionID = r.TransactionID
							and	derived.SellerCode = r.SellerCode 
	where	isnull(csos.MaxOngoingPendingPaymentID,0) > isnull(csos.MaxOngoingAdjPendingPaymentID,0)	--An ongoing +ve payment follows the clawback, so time to revert back to front loading
	and		cso.SpreadNumber <= cso.MaxSpread	--Only payments within the spread period get a portion of the ongoing VNB
	and		cso.SelectionSource <> 1			--Just process the per-payment rows (not the front loaded rows)

	select @RowCount = @@rowcount
	set @ProcessMessage = '#owt_Recognition (ogs ph4 - accr adj) = ' + convert(nvarchar(10), @RowCount)
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseLog, @ProcessMessage, null, @Module, @Client

	/****************************************************************************

		Now calculate the ongoing spread as follows:
		1) Investments: Years 1 to 6
		2) Pensions:	Years 1 to 10
		Note that regular payments get an additional multiplier to uplift the 
		average AUM for each year.
																		
	****************************************************************************/

	update r
		set OngoingYr02 = case when r.FrequencyCode = 2									--Monthly
							then r.OngoingYr01 * YR02.Multiplier * YR02.Factor			--Regular
							else r.OngoingYr01 * YR02.Factor							--Single
						  end,
			OngoingYr03 = case when r.FrequencyCode = 2									--Monthly
							then r.OngoingYr01 * YR03.Multiplier * YR03.Factor			--Regular
							else r.OngoingYr01 * YR03.Factor							--Single
						  end,
			OngoingYr04 = case when r.FrequencyCode = 2									--Monthly
							then r.OngoingYr01 * YR04.Multiplier * YR04.Factor			--Regular
							else r.OngoingYr01 * YR04.Factor							--Single
						  end,
			OngoingYr05 = case when r.FrequencyCode = 2									--Monthly 
							then r.OngoingYr01 * YR05.Multiplier * YR05.Factor			--Regular
							else r.OngoingYr01 * YR05.Factor							--Single
						  end,
			OngoingYr06 = case when r.FrequencyCode = 2									--Monthly 
							then r.OngoingYr01 * YR06.Multiplier * YR06.Factor			--Regular
							else r.OngoingYr01 * YR06.Factor							--Single
						  end,
			OngoingYr07 = case when r.ReassignedProductGroupCode = 5					--Pensions	AG 05/06/2018
							then
								case when r.FrequencyCode = 2							--Monthly 
									then r.OngoingYr01 * YR07.Multiplier * YR07.Factor	--Regular
									else r.OngoingYr01 * YR07.Factor					--Single
								end
							else 
								0.0
						  end,
			OngoingYr08 = case when r.ReassignedProductGroupCode = 5					--Pensions	AG 05/06/2018 
							then
								case when r.FrequencyCode = 2							--Monthly 
									then r.OngoingYr01 * YR08.Multiplier * YR08.Factor	--Regular
									else r.OngoingYr01 * YR08.Factor					--Single
								end
							else 
								0.0
						  end,
			OngoingYr09 = case when r.ReassignedProductGroupCode = 5					--Pensions	AG 05/06/2018 
							then
								case when r.FrequencyCode = 2							--Monthly 
									then r.OngoingYr01 * YR09.Multiplier * YR09.Factor	--Regular
									else r.OngoingYr01 * YR09.Factor					--Single
								end
							else 
								0.0
						  end,
			OngoingYr10 = case when r.ReassignedProductGroupCode = 5					--Pensions	AG 05/06/2018
							then
								case when r.FrequencyCode = 2							--Monthly 
									then r.OngoingYr01 * YR10.Multiplier * YR10.Factor	--Regular
									else r.OngoingYr01 * YR10.Factor					--Single
								end
							else 
								0.0
						  end
	from	#AG_owt_Recognition_SEPARATE_ONGOING r
			left join owt_EliteFactors YR01 on YR01.FeeType = 'VNB' and YR01.Category = 'COB-ONGOING-DISCOUNT-YR01' and r.CommissionYear between YR01.StartYear and YR01.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors YR02 on YR02.FeeType = 'VNB' and YR02.Category = 'COB-ONGOING-DISCOUNT-YR02' and r.CommissionYear between YR02.StartYear and YR02.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors YR03 on YR03.FeeType = 'VNB' and YR03.Category = 'COB-ONGOING-DISCOUNT-YR03' and r.CommissionYear between YR03.StartYear and YR03.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors YR04 on YR04.FeeType = 'VNB' and YR04.Category = 'COB-ONGOING-DISCOUNT-YR04' and r.CommissionYear between YR04.StartYear and YR04.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors YR05 on YR05.FeeType = 'VNB' and YR05.Category = 'COB-ONGOING-DISCOUNT-YR05' and r.CommissionYear between YR05.StartYear and YR05.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors YR06 on YR06.FeeType = 'VNB' and YR06.Category = 'COB-ONGOING-DISCOUNT-YR06' and r.CommissionYear between YR06.StartYear and YR06.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors YR07 on YR07.FeeType = 'VNB' and YR07.Category = 'COB-ONGOING-DISCOUNT-YR07' and r.CommissionYear between YR07.StartYear and YR07.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors YR08 on YR08.FeeType = 'VNB' and YR08.Category = 'COB-ONGOING-DISCOUNT-YR08' and r.CommissionYear between YR08.StartYear and YR08.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors YR09 on YR09.FeeType = 'VNB' and YR09.Category = 'COB-ONGOING-DISCOUNT-YR09' and r.CommissionYear between YR09.StartYear and YR09.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors YR10 on YR10.FeeType = 'VNB' and YR10.Category = 'COB-ONGOING-DISCOUNT-YR10' and r.CommissionYear between YR10.StartYear and YR10.EndYear 
	where	r.CalculationType = 'WEALTH-ONGOING'

	select @RowCount = @@rowcount
	set @ProcessMessage = '#owt_Recognition (ongoing yr2-10) = ' + convert(nvarchar(10), @RowCount)
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseLog, @ProcessMessage, null, @Module, @Client
	
	/****************************************************************************

		Now add up all the numbers
																		
	****************************************************************************/
	
	update r
		set OngoingTotal	=	OngoingYr01 + OngoingYr02 + OngoingYr03 + OngoingYr04 + OngoingYr05 +
								OngoingYr06 + OngoingYr07 + OngoingYr08 + OngoingYr09 + OngoingYr10,
			PointsTotal		=	OngoingYr01 + OngoingYr02 + OngoingYr03 + OngoingYr04 + OngoingYr05 +
								OngoingYr06 + OngoingYr07 + OngoingYr08 + OngoingYr09 + OngoingYr10 +
								Initial + MBF	-- Note BSC is already included in the Ongoing, so don't include it in the Points Total.
	from	#AG_owt_Recognition_SEPARATE_ONGOING r

	select @RowCount = @@rowcount
	set @ProcessMessage = '#owt_Recognition (points total) = ' + convert(nvarchar(10), @RowCount)
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseLog, @ProcessMessage, null, @Module, @Client

	/****************************************************************************

		Merge the temporary table into the permanent table (IC data)
																		
	****************************************************************************/

	BEGIN TRANSACTION

	declare @SummaryOfChanges table (Change varchar(20))
	merge	dbo.AG_owt_Recognition_SEPARATE_ONGOING as trg
	using	#AG_owt_Recognition_SEPARATE_ONGOING as src
	on		trg.SourceID = src.SourceID
	and		trg.Source = src.Source
	when	matched 
	and		isnull(trg.PointsTotal,0) <> isnull(src.PointsTotal,0)
	then	update 
				set trg.CaseID = src.CaseID,
					trg.TransactionID = src.TransactionID,
					trg.Policy = src.Policy,
					trg.ProductCode = src.ProductCode,
					trg.BusinessCode = src.BusinessCode,
					trg.SellerCode = src.SellerCode,					--AG 13/06/2018
					trg.PointsTotal = src.PointsTotal,
					trg.BSC = src.BSC,
					trg.MBF = src.MBF,
					trg.Initial = src.Initial,
					trg.OngoingTotal = src.OngoingTotal,
					trg.OngoingYr01 = src.OngoingYr01,
					trg.OngoingYr02 = src.OngoingYr02,
					trg.OngoingYr03 = src.OngoingYr03,
					trg.OngoingYr04 = src.OngoingYr04,
					trg.OngoingYr05 = src.OngoingYr05,
					trg.OngoingYr06 = src.OngoingYr06,
					trg.OngoingYr07 = src.OngoingYr07,
					trg.OngoingYr08 = src.OngoingYr08,
					trg.OngoingYr09 = src.OngoingYr09,
					trg.OngoingYr10 = src.OngoingYr10,
					trg.FCARate = src.FCARate,
					trg.RetentionRate = src.RetentionRate,
					trg.RetentionRateBroker = src.RetentionRateBroker,
					trg.OngoingServicingRate = src.OngoingServicingRate,
					trg.OngoingServicingSource = src.OngoingServicingSource,
					trg.DA = src.DA,
					trg.AmountReceived = src.AmountReceived,
					trg.Premium = src.Premium,
					trg.AgentSplit = src.AgentSplit,
					trg.CommissionType = src.CommissionType,
					trg.CommissionTypeDesc = src.CommissionTypeDesc,
					trg.PayBasisCode = src.PayBasisCode,				--AG 13/06/2018
					trg.PayBasisDesc = src.PayBasisDesc,				--AG 13/06/2018
					trg.PaymentMatchedDate = src.PaymentMatchedDate,	--AG 13/06/2018	
					trg.Month = src.Month,
					trg.FrequencyCode = src.FrequencyCode,
					trg.FrequencyDesc = src.FrequencyDesc,
					trg.ReassignedProductGroupCode = src.ReassignedProductGroupCode,	--AG 05/06/2018
					trg.ReassignedProductGroupName = src.ReassignedProductGroupName,	--AG 05/06/2018
					trg.RecognitionType = src.RecognitionType,
					trg.CalculationType = src.CalculationType,
					trg.DateLastUpdated = @DateLastUpdated
	when	not matched by source
	then	delete
	when	not matched by target 
	then	insert
			(
				SourceID,
				CaseID,
				TransactionID,
				Policy,
				ProductCode,
				BusinessCode,
				SellerCode,							--AG 13/06/2018
				PointsTotal,
				BSC,
				MBF,
				Initial,
				OngoingTotal,
				OngoingYr01,
				OngoingYr02,
				OngoingYr03,
				OngoingYr04,
				OngoingYr05,
				OngoingYr06,
				OngoingYr07,
				OngoingYr08,
				OngoingYr09,
				OngoingYr10,
				FCARate,
				RetentionRate,
				RetentionRateBroker,
				OngoingServicingRate,
				OngoingServicingSource,
				DA,
				AmountReceived,
				Premium,
				AgentSplit,
				CommissionType,
				CommissionTypeDesc,
				PayBasisCode,						--AG 13/06/2018
				PayBasisDesc,						--AG 13/06/2018
				PaymentMatchedDate,					--AG 13/06/2018
				Month,
				FrequencyCode,
				FrequencyDesc,
				ReassignedProductGroupCode,			--AG 05/06/2018
				ReassignedProductGroupName,			--AG 05/06/2018
				RecognitionType,
				CalculationType,
				Source,
				DateInserted,
				DateLastUpdated
			)		
			values
			(
				src.SourceID,
				src.CaseID,
				src.TransactionID,
				src.Policy,
				src.ProductCode,
				src.BusinessCode,
				src.SellerCode,						--AG 13/06/2018
				src.PointsTotal,
				src.BSC,
				src.MBF,
				src.Initial,
				src.OngoingTotal,
				src.OngoingYr01,
				src.OngoingYr02,
				src.OngoingYr03,
				src.OngoingYr04,
				src.OngoingYr05,
				src.OngoingYr06,
				src.OngoingYr07,
				src.OngoingYr08,
				src.OngoingYr09,
				src.OngoingYr10,
				src.FCARate,
				src.RetentionRate,
				src.RetentionRateBroker,
				src.OngoingServicingRate,
				src.OngoingServicingSource,
				src.DA,
				src.AmountReceived,
				src.Premium,
				src.AgentSplit,
				src.CommissionType,
				src.CommissionTypeDesc,
				src.PayBasisCode,					--AG 13/06/2018
				src.PayBasisDesc,					--AG 13/06/2018
				src.PaymentMatchedDate,				--AG 13/06/2018
				src.Month,
				src.FrequencyCode,
				src.FrequencyDesc,
				src.ReassignedProductGroupCode,		--AG 05/06/2018
				src.ReassignedProductGroupName,		--AG 05/06/2018
				src.RecognitionType,
				src.CalculationType,
				src.Source,
				src.DateInserted,
				src.DateLastUpdated)				--Merge statements must have a ;
	output $action into @SummaryOfChanges;
						
	/****************************************************************************

		Update OpenAccess
																		
	****************************************************************************/

/*	
	--Do not include MBF in the OpenAccess Commission Listing as it is on the MBF download
	--and we don't want MBF double counting.
	update	oal
		set VNB_Points = r.PointsTotal - r.MBF		--AG 04/06/2018 (2)
	from	msit_CommissionStatement cs
/*			inner join (select	distinct PKID
						from	owt_TransformationMovements tm 
						where	tm.DriverTableName = 'sa_swift_S_AGMFIL'
						and		tm.CommissionStatement = 'Y') tm on tm.PKID = cs.PendingPaymentID
*/			inner join msit_OpenworkAdviserListing oal on oal.SourceID = cs.ID and oal.Source = 'Openwork 2006'
			inner join owt_Recognition r 
						on r.SourceID = cs.PendingPaymentID
						and r.Source = oal.Source
	--where	isnull(oal.VNB_Points,0) <> isnull(r.PointsTotal,0)
	
	select @OALRowCount = @@rowcount
*/
	COMMIT TRANSACTION      
	
	select	@RowCount = COUNT(*)
	from	@SummaryOfChanges
	where	Change = 'INSERT'

	set @ProcessMessage = 'owt_Recognition (insert) = ' + convert(nvarchar(10), @RowCount)
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseLog, @ProcessMessage, null, @Module, @Client

	select	@RowCount = COUNT(*)
	from	@SummaryOfChanges
	where	Change = 'UPDATE'

	set @ProcessMessage = 'owt_Recognition (update) = ' + convert(nvarchar(10), @RowCount)
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseLog, @ProcessMessage, null, @Module, @Client
	
	select	@RowCount = COUNT(*)
	from	@SummaryOfChanges
	where	Change = 'DELETE'

	set @ProcessMessage = 'owt_Recognition (delete) = ' + convert(nvarchar(10), @RowCount)
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseLog, @ProcessMessage, null, @Module, @Client

/*
	set @ProcessMessage = 'msit_OpenworkAdviserListing (update) = ' + convert(nvarchar(10), @OALRowCount)
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseLog, @ProcessMessage, null, @Module, @Client
*/
	/****************************************************************************

		T H E   E N D
																		
	****************************************************************************/
	
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseEnd, @ProcName, null, @Module, @Client

END TRY

BEGIN CATCH 

	select @ErrNum = ERROR_NUMBER(), @ErrMsg = ERROR_MESSAGE(), @ErrSev = ERROR_SEVERITY(), @ErrLine = ERROR_LINE(), @ErrState = XACT_STATE()
	set @ErrMsg = REPLACE(@ErrMsg, '.', '') + ' (error no: ' + CAST(@ErrNum AS VARCHAR(10)) + ') on line ' + CAST(@ErrLine AS VARCHAR(10))
	
	-- Test XACT_STATE for 0, 1, or -1.
    -- If 1, the transaction is committable.
    -- If -1, the transaction is uncommittable and should be rolled back.
    -- If 0, there is no transaction and a commit or rollback operation would generate an error.

	if @ErrState = -1			-- Transaction is uncommitable
		rollback transaction

	if @ErrState = 1			
		commit transaction

	-- Error message line 1
	set @ErrMsgBrief = left(@ErrMsg,100)
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseError, @ErrMsgBrief, null, @Module, @Client
	
	-- Error message line 2 - if any text exists
	set @ErrMsgBrief = substring(@ErrMsg,101,100)
	if len(@ErrMsgBrief) > 0
		exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseError, @ErrMsgBrief, null, @Module, @Client

	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseEnd, @ProcName, null, @Module, @Client

	RAISERROR(@ErrMsg, @ErrSev , 1)

END CATCH

/****************************************************************************

			E N D															

****************************************************************************/

return @ErrNum


GO
/****** Object:  StoredProcedure [dbo].[owp_RecognitionSwiftONGOINGVER2]    Script Date: 7/3/2026 3:44:25 PM ******/
SET ANSI_NULLS ON
GO
SET QUOTED_IDENTIFIER ON
GO
/*********************************************************************************************************

Program:		owp_RecognitionSwift					
Author:			Alan Groves
Date created:	11/04/2018
											
Description:
===========

This proc populates the new recognition table called "owt_Recognition" with "Value of New Business"
(VNB) points.

This proc handles all of the swift data which includes:
WEALTH - COB business i.e. pensions and investments
MORTGAGES
PROTECTION

Note: There is a separate proc that calculates the GI VNB points from the Paymentshield data.

The approach of this proc is to use the incremental PendingPaymentIDs from the overnight batch
to calculate the VNB points in a temporary table.

The temporary table is then merged with the permanent table to make the calculated (or
re-calculated values) permanent.

Terms
-----
BSC			- Business Service Charge.
MBF			- Mortgage Broker Fee.
OGS			- Ongoing Servicing.
BSC Rate	- 0.12% at the time of writing (24/04/2018). This could be changed by the business, but
				would also require some DEV work in OWS.
DF			- Discount Factor.
DA			- Distribution Allowance (the total amount paid out by the provider to Openwork)
AUM			- Assets Under Management. Basically the amount invested or the premium on investment
				cases.
Average AUM - Average amount invested annually which is equivalent to 6 months' premium.

THE CALCULATIONS
================

There are two potential parts: initial + ongoing (if ongoing applies). If BSC (applies to ongoing 
only) and MBF (applies to mortgages only) apply, then these are also included:

MORTGAGE
--------
Part 1: MBF column = (Advice Fee Amount X Broker Retention Rate) - (Advice Fee Amount X Mort FCA Rate)
Part 2: Initial column = (Proc Fee Amount X Mortgage Retention Rate) - (Proc Fee X Mort FCA Rate) 
Mortgage Points Total = Initial + MBF

PROTECTION
----------
= (DA X Protection Retention Rate) - (DA X Protection FCA Rate) 
Protection Points Total = Initial

WEALTH (COB i.e. pensions and investments)
------
Part 1: Initial column = (DA X Wealth Retention Rate) - (DA X Wealth FCA Rate)

Part 2:

****XXXX****

NOTE: Where the BSC rate is greater than the ongoing rate, then BSC gets ALL of the AVAILABLE 
ongoing.

****XXXX****

REGULAR - BSC applies:
Year 1 column = BSC Points + Non-BSC Points - FCA Points
Non-BSC Points = Ave AUM X (OGS Rate - BSC Rate) X COB Retention Rate
BSC Points = Ave AUM X BSC Rate
FCA Points = Ave AUM X OGS Rate X COB FCA Rate

REGULAR - Non-BSC: 
Year 1 column = (Ave AUM X OGS Rate X COB Retention Rate) - (Ave AUM X OGS Rate X COB FCA Rate)

SINGLE - BSC applies:
Year 1 column = (AUM X BSC Rate) + (AUM X (OGS Rate - BSC Rate) X COB Retention Rate) - (AUM X OGS Rate X COB FCA Rate) 

SINGLE - Non-BSC:
Year 1 column = (AUM X OGS Rate X COB Retention Rate) - (AUM X OGS Rate X COB FCA Rate) 

Then years 2 to 10 are calculated by applying a discount factor
Year  2 = Year 1 X  3 X DF
Year  3 = Year 1 X  5 X DF
Year  4 = Year 1 X  7 X DF
Year  5 = Year 1 X  9 X DF
Year  6 = Year 1 X 11 X DF
Year  7 = Year 1 X 13 X DF
Year  8 = Year 1 X 15 X DF
Year  9 = Year 1 X 17 X DF
Year 10 = Year 1 X 19 X DF

Wealth Points Total =	OngoingYr01 + OngoingYr02 + OngoingYr03 + OngoingYr04 + OngoingYr05 +
						OngoingYr06 + OngoingYr07 + OngoingYr08 + OngoingYr09 + OngoingYr10 +
						Initial

GI
--
See stored proc "owp_RecognitionGIPaymentshield".
 
Notes:
-----

1)	There is a BSC column on table owt_Recognition. However, BSC is already included in the ongoing
	years 1 - 10, so the BSC column does not need to be added in. In fact you will double count if 
	you attempt to do anything with it other than display it.

2)	Occasionally an investment case may receive two or more cheques which
	then go through Swift as two or more SINGLE investments on the SAME
	slice. Although the INITIAL VNB calculation will pro-rata correctly
	because it is based on the amount received, this scenario will cause
	ongoing VNB to be calculated on each of the payment records and so will 
	double count (or worse if there are more than two cheques received).
	Since de-coupling IC from ongoing i.e. they now have separate rows on
	table owt_Recognition, the issue of multiple cheques should no longer
	cause ongoing double counting.


This proc is called as follows:
	declare @rc int
	exec @rc = dbo.owp_RecognitionSwift 'Openwork', 'Recognition'
	select @rc

					
AMENDMENT HISTORY				
=================								

Date		Author		Description
----		------		-----------
26/04/2018	A Groves	Only include rows in the OGS lookups where the OngoingServiceFee > 0.0.
						Negative OGS rates are bad data and at the time of writing, there are
						39 of these.
27/04/2018	A Groves	Additional calculation and condition to handle the scenario where BSC applies
						but the OGS Rate is less than the BSC rate. Previously, this caused the
						total ongoing to be zero. However, there are two components to ongoing VNB 
						points, the BSC share and the non-BSC share. So the BSC share (which takes 
						100% when the OGS rate is less than 0.12%) should still yield ongoing points.
27/04/2018	A Groves	Single ongoing Yr01 corrected by applying outer brackets before signing the result.
03/05/2018	A Groves	Added update of column "msit_OpenworkAdviserListing.VNB_Points".
18/05/2018	A Groves	Changed mortgage calculation to use e.AMOUNT_REC instead of pt.CommInitialAmount
						as Marcus Cossey wanted the actual amount received to be used for the DA.
04/06/2018	A Groves	1) In the REGULAR section of column "OngoingYr01", the condition for cs.FrequencyCode <> 6
							was added to ensure the code differentiates to the SINGLE section.
						2) Exclude MBF from the OpenAccess table (msit_OpenworkAdviserListing) as this
							is shown on the MBF download and would otherwise incur MBF double counting.
05/06/2018	A Groves	1) Marcus Cossey advised that investments should get ongoing for years 1 to 6 and
							pensions for years 1 to 10. Previously, both lines of business got years 1 to 10.
						2) Marcus Cossey asked for split payments (i.e. where multiple cheques are processed
							for a SINGLE investment) to only claculate ongoing VNB on the oldest payment. 
11/06/2018	A Groves	1) PSD processed a protection clawback statement as fee type initial. These clawbacks
							all generated +ve instead of -ve VNB points. A tweak was added to ensure that the 
							absolute value of AMOUNT_REC is used to ensure the VNB is correctly signed. 
						2) Another unknown business rule has surfaced: Previously, only initial, clawbacks and
							adjustments on slices created new from 2017 were included. This rule only applies
							to initial. Clawbacks and adjustments can belong to a slice created at any point
							in the past. However, note that the payment (irrespective of whether it is +ve or 
							-ve), must not pre-date 2017.
13/06/2018	A Groves	Marcus asked for SellerCode and PaymentMatchedDate to be added so he need only use 
							the one table for both the adviser and enterprise leagues. PayBasisCode and 
							PayBasisDesc were also added at the same time as these are used in the calculations.
06/07/2018	A Groves	Replaced the OGS Rate lookup on the fly to using table dbo.owt_OngoingRate. This was 
							done to ensure the rate used at any point in time stays the same, so the onging VNB
							will always give the same result each time the calculation runs.
17/07/2018	A Groves	Marcus asked for the ongoing calculation to be based on the sum of premium across
							all the initial transactions where an initial fee has been paid.
*************************************************************************************************************/

CREATE PROCEDURE [dbo].[owp_RecognitionSwiftONGOINGVER2]
	@Client		varchar(50),
	@Module		Varchar(50)

with recompile

AS

set nocount on

declare		@PhaseStart				varchar(50),
			@PhaseEnd				varchar(50),
			@PhaseError				varchar(50),
			@PhaseLog				varchar(50),
			@ProcName				varchar(100),
			@ProcessMessage			varchar(100),
			@RowCount				int,
			@OALRowCount			int,
			@ErrMsg					nvarchar(4000),
			@ErrMsgBrief			nvarchar(100),
			@ErrNum					int,
			@ErrSev					int,
			@ErrLine				int,
			@ErrState				int,
			@DateLastUpdated		datetime,
			@OwlManager2Code		nvarchar(10)
			
/****************************************************************************

	Set initial parameters																
																		
****************************************************************************/

set @ProcName			= object_name(@@procid)
set @PhaseStart			= 'START'
set @PhaseEnd			= 'END'
set @PhaseError			= 'ERROR'
set @PhaseLog			= 'LOG'
set @ErrNum				= 0	
set @DateLastUpdated	= getdate()

set @OwlManager2Code = (select cde.Code from msit_MIWarehouseCodesAndDescriptions cde
			where cde.ColumnName = 'Manager2Code' and cde.Description = 'Owl Financial')

-- We want this logging irrespective of whether or not there is a rollback
exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseStart, @ProcName, null, @Module, @Client

/****************************************************************************

	Populate the table																
																		
****************************************************************************/

SET XACT_ABORT ON	-- Needed if XACT_STATE() function is used.

BEGIN TRY

	/****************************************************************************

		Calculate VNB and populate the temporary table with the results
		
		Note that there are oddities like LV protection payments which always
		come in pairs with one large and one much smaller amount (e.g. TransactionID 
		= 6684787.) The system treats both payments in the pair as first payments 
		and the (projected) DA associated with both is the same (because it's on 
		the policy transaction). 
		
		There is also a requirement to front-load VNB points on accrual and level
		payments. This means calculate the VNB for the full amount of the DA and 
		put it on the first payment record and then on all subsequent accrual and 
		level payments, set the VNB to zero.
		
		Thus two different sources of DA are used depending on whether we need the
		full DA amount for accruals and level or the actual amount received for all
		other scenarios including the LV split payment scenario. The two sources are:
		
		mstt_PolicyTransactions.CommInitialAmount - Full (projected) DA amount
		
		mstt_Expectation.AMOUNT_REC - The DA actually received. This handles the
										LV scenario whereby the AMOUNT_REC is 
										proportioned across the two payments received.   
																		
	****************************************************************************/

	select	top 0 
			*, 
			convert(int,NULL) as CommissionYear
	into	#AG_owt_Recognition_SEPARATE_ONGOING
	from	AG_owt_Recognition_SEPARATE_ONGOING

	/****************************************************************************

		Phase 1 - Process all but regular accrual cases with clawbacks/adjustments
		Accruals are front loaded unless their latest payment is a clawback/adjudtment
		in which case they accrue VNB points on a per payment basis and so these
		are dealt with in Phases 2 and 3.
																		
	****************************************************************************/

	insert into #AG_owt_Recognition_SEPARATE_ONGOING
	(
		SourceID,
		CaseID,
		TransactionID,
		Policy,
		ProductCode,
		BusinessCode,
		SellerCode,						--AG 13/06/2018
		PointsTotal,
		BSC,
		MBF,
		Initial,
		OngoingTotal,
		OngoingYr01,
		OngoingYr02,
		OngoingYr03,
		OngoingYr04,
		OngoingYr05,
		OngoingYr06,
		OngoingYr07,
		OngoingYr08,
		OngoingYr09,
		OngoingYr10,
		FCARate,
		RetentionRate,
		RetentionRateBroker,
		OngoingServicingRate,
		OngoingServicingSource,
		DA,
		AmountReceived,
		Premium,
		AgentSplit,
		CommissionType,
		CommissionTypeDesc,
		PayBasisCode,					--AG 13/06/2018
		PayBasisDesc,					--AG 13/06/2018
		PaymentMatchedDate,				--AG 13/06/2018
		Month,
		FrequencyCode,
		FrequencyDesc,
		ReassignedProductGroupCode,		--AG 05/06/2018
		ReassignedProductGroupName,		--AG 05/06/2018
		RecognitionType,
		CalculationType,
		Source,
		DateInserted,
		DateLastUpdated,
		CommissionYear
	)
	select	cs.PendingPaymentID as SourceID,
			cs.CaseID,
			cs.TransactionID,
			cs.ExtPolicyNumber as Policy,
			cs.ProductCode,
			cs.BusinessCode,
			cs.AgentCode as SellerCode,				--AG 13/06/2018
			0.0 as PointsTotal,
			0.0 as BSC,
			case 
				when mbf.MortgageFeeID is not null and cs.INIssued <> 0 then (((mbf.AdviceFeeAmount)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * MRbkr.FACTOR) - ((mbf.AdviceFeeAmount)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * Mfca.FACTOR)) --Note that mbf.AdviceFeeAmount is signed correctly - so no coding for signing is needed here
				else 0.0
			end as MBF,
			case 
				--When the adviser has changed, the AgentSplit can become zero in which case the ELITE points should be zero.
				when cs.AgentSplit = 0 then 0
				
				--WEALTH CALCULATION START
				--Indemnity payments or SINGLEs or IC Clawbacks or IC adjustments Start
				when (ph.ProductCategoryCode = 1 or pcc.KeyValue2 = '1') and (cs.FrequencyCode = 6 or cs.PayBasisCode in ('T') or cs.CommissionType in (2,17)) and cs.commissiontype in (1,2,17) and cs.INIssued <> 0 then (((e.AMOUNT_REC)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * Crate.FACTOR) - ((e.AMOUNT_REC)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * Cfca.FACTOR)) * case when cs.INIssued < 0 then -1 else 1 end
				--Indemnity payments or SINGLEs or IC Clawbacks or IC adjustments End
				--Accruals & Level Start
				when (ph.ProductCategoryCode = 1 or pcc.KeyValue2 = '1') and cs.INIssued <> 0 then (((pt.CommInitialAmount)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * Crate.FACTOR) - ((pt.CommInitialAmount)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * Cfca.FACTOR)) * case when cs.INIssued < 0 then -1 else 1 end
				--Accruals & Level End
				--WEALTH CALCULATION END
				
				--MORTGAGE CALCULATION START
				--Note: The MBF component has its own table column
				--Only 1 payment for mortgages
				when ph.ProductGroupCode = 3 and cs.INIssued <> 0 then (((e.AMOUNT_REC)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * MRproc.FACTOR) - ((e.AMOUNT_REC)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * Mfca.FACTOR)) * case when cs.INIssued < 0 then -1 else 1 end	--AG 18/05/2018
				--MORTGAGE CALCULATION END
				
				--PROTECTION CALCULATION START
				--Indemnity payments or SINGLEs or IC Clawbacks or IC adjustments Start
				when ph.ProductGroupCode = 6 and (cs.FrequencyCode = 6 or cs.PayBasisCode in ('T') or cs.CommissionType in (2,17)) and cs.commissiontype in (1,2,17) and cs.INIssued <> 0 then ((abs(e.AMOUNT_REC)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * Prate.FACTOR) - (abs(e.AMOUNT_REC)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * Pfca.FACTOR)) * case when cs.INIssued < 0 then -1 else 1 end	--AG 11/06/2018 (1)
				--Indemnity payments or SINGLEs or IC Clawbacks or IC adjustments End
				--Accruals & Level Start
				when ph.ProductGroupCode = 6 and cs.INIssued <> 0 then (((pt.CommInitialAmount)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * Prate.FACTOR) - ((pt.CommInitialAmount)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * Pfca.FACTOR)) * case when cs.INIssued < 0 then -1 else 1 end
				--Accruals & Level End
				--PROTECTION CALCULATION END

				else 0.0

			end as Initial,
			0.0 as OngoingTotal,
			0.0 as OngoingYr01,
			0.0 as OngoingYr02,
			0.0 as OngoingYr03,
			0.0 as OngoingYr04,
			0.0 as OngoingYr05,
			0.0 as OngoingYr06,
			0.0 as OngoingYr07,
			0.0 as OngoingYr08,
			0.0 as OngoingYr09,
			0.0 as OngoingYr10,
			case 
				when (ph.ProductCategoryCode = 1 or pcc.KeyValue2 = '1') then Cfca.FACTOR*100.0		--COB
				when ph.ProductGroupCode = 3 then Mfca.FACTOR*100.0		--MORT
				when ph.ProductGroupCode = 6 then Pfca.FACTOR*100.0		--PROT
				else 0.0
			end as FCARate,
			case 
				when (ph.ProductCategoryCode = 1 or pcc.KeyValue2 = '1') then Crate.FACTOR*100.0	--COB
				when ph.ProductGroupCode = 3 then MRproc.FACTOR*100.0	--MORT
				when ph.ProductGroupCode = 6 then Prate.FACTOR*100.0	--PROT
				else 0.0
			end as RetentionRate,
			case 
				when mbf.MortgageFeeID is not null then  MRbkr.FACTOR*100.0	
				else 0.0
			end as RetentionRateBroker,
			null as OngoingServicingRate,
			null as OngoingServicingSource,
			pt.CommInitialAmount as DA,
			e.AMOUNT_REC as AmountReceived,
			cs.Premium,
			cs.AgentSplit,
			cs.CommissionType,
			left(cs.StandingOrderDesc,50) as CommissionTypeDesc,
			cs.PayBasisCode,							--AG 13/06/2018
			cs.PayBasisDesc,							--AG 13/06/2018
			cs.CreateDate as PaymentMatchedDate,		--AG 13/06/2018
			cs.Month,
			cs.FrequencyCode,
			cs.FrequencyDesc,
			pg.ProductGroupCode as ReassignedProductGroupCode,	--Force the re-assigned products...		AG 05/06/2018
			pg.ProductGroupName as ReassignedProductGroupName,	--...to be processed as investments		AG 05/06/2018
			'VNB-INI-PHASE-1' as RecognitionType,
			case 
				when (ph.ProductCategoryCode = 1 or pcc.KeyValue2 = '1') then 'WEALTH-INITIAL'
				when ph.ProductGroupCode = 3 then 'MORTGAGE'
				when ph.ProductGroupCode = 6 then 'PROTECTION'
				else null
			end as CalculationType,
			'Openwork 2006' as Source,
			@DateLastUpdated as DateInserted,
			@DateLastUpdated as DateLastUpdated,
			csp.year as CommissionYear
	--select count(*)
	from	msit_CommissionStatement cs
/*			inner join (select	distinct PKID
						from	owt_TransformationMovements tm 
						where	tm.DriverTableName = 'sa_swift_S_AGMFIL'
						and		tm.CommissionStatement = 'Y') tm on tm.PKID = cs.PendingPaymentID
*/			inner join mstt_Agents ag on ag.Code = cs.BusinessCode
			inner join mstt_PolicyTransactions pt on pt.ID = cs.TransactionID
			inner join mstt_Policies p on p.POL_NUM = pt.PolicyID
			inner join msit_CommissionStatementPeriods VNBStart on convert(date,pt.CreateDateTime) between VNBStart.PeriodStartDate and VNBStart.PeriodEndDate
			inner join msit_Commissionstatementperiods csp on csp.month = cs.month
			inner join mstt_ProductHierarchy ph on ph.productcode = cs.productcode
			inner join mstt_Expectation e on e.ID = cs.ExpectationID
			left join dbo.owt_MortgageBrokerFees mbf on mbf.PendingPaymentID = cs.PendingPaymentID and mbf.AdviceFeeCharged = 'Yes'
			left join owt_SelectionControl SC
						on SC.Process = 'ElitePoints' 
						and SC.KeyType = 'NSCPotCode' 
						and cs.CreateDate between SC.EffectiveStartDate and SC.EffectiveEndDate
			left join mstt_Commissions BSCpot
						on BSCpot.TransactionID = cs.TransactionID 
						and BSCpot.Agent_Code = sc.KeyValue
						and BSCpot.CommissionType = 10
			left join owt_SelectionControl SFMPC						
						on SFMPC.Process = 'ElitePoints' 
						and SFMPC.KeyType = 'ServicingFeeMarginPotCode' 
						and cs.CreateDate between SFMPC.EffectiveStartDate and SFMPC.EffectiveEndDate
			left join mstt_Commissions SFMpot							
						on SFMpot.TransactionID = cs.TransactionID 
						and SFMpot.Agent_Code = SFMPC.KeyValue
						and SFMpot.CommissionType = 10	
			left join owt_SelectionControl pcc 
						on pcc.Process = 'ElitePoints'
						and pcc.KeyType = 'ProductCategoryCode'
						and pcc.KeyValue = cs.ProductCode	
						and cs.CreateDate between pcc.EffectiveStartDate and pcc.EffectiveEndDate
			left join owt_SelectionControl ogsdflt 
						on ogsdflt.Process = 'ElitePoints'
						and ogsdflt.KeyType = 'DefaultOngoingServicingRate'
						and ogsdflt.SelectionType = 'VNB'
						and ogsdflt.KeyValue = case when ph.RDRType = 'ONPLAT' then 'ONPLAT' else 'OFPLAT' end
						and cs.CreateDate between ogsdflt.EffectiveStartDate and ogsdflt.EffectiveEndDate
			left join mstt_CodeProductGroup pg on pg.ProductGroupCode = case when pcc.KeyValue2 = '1' then 2 else ph.ProductGroupCode end
			left join owt_EliteFactors Cfca on Cfca.FeeType = 'VNB' and Cfca.category = 'COB-FCA-RATE' and csp.year between Cfca.StartYear and Cfca.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors Crate on Crate.FeeType = 'VNB' and Crate.category = 'COB-RETENTION-RATE' and csp.year between Crate.StartYear and Crate.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors Mfca on Mfca.FeeType = 'VNB' and Mfca.category = 'MORT-FCA-RATE' and csp.year between Mfca.StartYear and Mfca.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors MRproc on MRproc.FeeType = 'VNB' and MRproc.category = 'MORT-RETENTION-RATE-PROC' and csp.year between MRproc.StartYear and MRproc.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors MRbkr on MRbkr.FeeType = 'VNB' and MRbkr.category = 'MORT-RETENTION-RATE-BROKER' and csp.year between MRbkr.StartYear and MRbkr.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors Pfca on Pfca.FeeType = 'VNB' and Pfca.category = 'PROT-FCA-RATE' and csp.year between Pfca.StartYear and Pfca.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors Prate on Prate.FeeType = 'VNB' and Prate.category = 'PROT-RETENTION-RATE' and csp.year between Prate.StartYear and Prate.EndYear 
			left join msit_CommissionStatement csadj 
						on csadj.TransactionID = cs.TransactionID 
						and csadj.AgentCode = cs.AgentCode 
						and csadj.CommissionType in (2,17)
						and	csadj.PayBasisCode in ('F')				--Accrual
						and	csadj.FrequencyCode <> 6				--Regular 
	where	cs.ReportingClassCode = 1
	and		ag.Manager2Code <> @OwlManager2Code		--Exclude Owl
	and		cs.INIssued <> 0
	and		csp.Year >= 2017						--Ensure in-scope payments are consistent with VNB start
	and		VNBStart.Year >= 2017
	and		cs.CommissionType in (1,2,17)
	and		abs(e.AMOUNT_REC) >= 0.01	
	--and		((VNBStart.Year >= 2017 and cs.CommissionType = 1 and e.AMOUNT_REC >= 0.01)		--VNB to start from new slices in 2017 for +ve payments but...			AG 11/06/2018 (2)
	--		or (cs.CommissionType in (2,17) or e.AMOUNT_REC <= -0.01))						--...for -ve payments, the slice can start from any date in the past	AG 11/06/2018 (2)
	and		csadj.ID is null						--Deal with accrual regular clawbacks/adjustments later

	select @RowCount = @@rowcount
	set @ProcessMessage = '#owt_Recognition (ini ph1 - no accr adj) = ' + convert(nvarchar(10), @RowCount)
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseLog, @ProcessMessage, null, @Module, @Client

	/****************************************************************************

		Now deal with accrual clawbacks and adjustments
																		
	****************************************************************************/

	--drop table #msit_CommissionStatementSUMMARY

	--Find transactions with clawbacks/adj on them
	select	cs.TransactionID,
			cs.AgentCode,
			Min(case when cs.CommissionType = 1 then cs.PendingPaymentID else null end) as MinInitialPendingPaymentID,
			MAX(case when cs.CommissionType = 1 then cs.PendingPaymentID else null end) as MaxInitialPendingPaymentID,
			MAX(case when cs.CommissionType in (2,17) then cs.PendingPaymentID else null end) as MaxAdjPendingPaymentID,
			null as MinInitialAfterAdjPendingPaymentID
	into	#msit_CommissionStatementSUMMARY
	from	msit_CommissionStatement cs
			inner join mstt_Agents ag on ag.Code = cs.BusinessCode
			inner join mstt_PolicyTransactions pt on pt.ID = cs.TransactionID
			inner join mstt_Policies p on p.POL_NUM = pt.PolicyID
			inner join msit_CommissionStatementPeriods VNBStart on convert(date,pt.CreateDateTime) between VNBStart.PeriodStartDate and VNBStart.PeriodEndDate
			inner join msit_Commissionstatementperiods csp on csp.month = cs.month
			inner join mstt_Expectation e on e.ID = cs.ExpectationID
			left join msit_CommissionStatement csadj 
						on csadj.TransactionID = cs.TransactionID 
						and csadj.AgentCode = cs.AgentCode 
						and csadj.CommissionType in (2,17)
						and	csadj.PayBasisCode in ('F')				--Accrual
						and	csadj.FrequencyCode <> 6				--Regular 
	where	cs.ReportingClassCode = 1
	and		cs.CommissionType in (1,2,17)			--We want all the initial payment types (i.e. not trail (ongoing))
	and		ag.Manager2Code <> @OwlManager2Code		--Exclude Owl
	and		csp.Year >= 2017						--Ensure in-scope payments are consistent with VNB start
	and		VNBStart.Year >= 2017 
	and		abs(e.AMOUNT_REC) >= 0.01	
	and		csadj.ID is not null					--select regular accrual transactions with clawbacks/adjustments
	--and cs.TransactionID in (5613333,6296827)
	group by	cs.TransactionID,
				cs.AgentCode

	select @RowCount = @@rowcount
	set @ProcessMessage = '#msit_CommissionStatementSUMMARY (accr adj txns) = ' + convert(nvarchar(10), @RowCount)
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseLog, @ProcessMessage, null, @Module, @Client

	--Get first initial payment after last clawback/adj
	update css
		set MinInitialAfterAdjPendingPaymentID = summ.MinPendingPaymentID 
	from  #msit_CommissionStatementSUMMARY css
			inner join  (
						select cssinner.TransactionID, cssinner.AgentCode, min(cs.PendingPaymentID) as MinPendingPaymentID
						from #msit_CommissionStatementSUMMARY cssinner
								inner join msit_CommissionStatement cs
											on cs.TransactionID = cssinner.TransactionID
											and cs.AgentCode = cssinner.AgentCode
						where cs.PendingPaymentID > cssinner.MaxAdjPendingPaymentID
						group by cssinner.TransactionID, cssinner.AgentCode
						) summ on  summ.TransactionID = css.TransactionID
							   and summ.AgentCode = css.AgentCode

	select @RowCount = @@rowcount
	set @ProcessMessage = '#msit_CommissionStatementSUMMARY (1st IC after adj) = ' + convert(nvarchar(10), @RowCount)
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseLog, @ProcessMessage, null, @Module, @Client

	/****************************************************************************

		Phase 2 - This phase deals with regular accrual cases where there is at 
		least one clawback/adjustment. In this scenario the VNB is changed from 
		front loaded to a per payment basis.
																		
	****************************************************************************/

	insert into #AG_owt_Recognition_SEPARATE_ONGOING
	(
		SourceID,
		CaseID,
		TransactionID,
		Policy,
		ProductCode,
		BusinessCode,
		SellerCode,						
		PointsTotal,
		BSC,
		MBF,
		Initial,
		OngoingTotal,
		OngoingYr01,
		OngoingYr02,
		OngoingYr03,
		OngoingYr04,
		OngoingYr05,
		OngoingYr06,
		OngoingYr07,
		OngoingYr08,
		OngoingYr09,
		OngoingYr10,
		FCARate,
		RetentionRate,
		RetentionRateBroker,
		OngoingServicingRate,
		OngoingServicingSource,
		DA,
		AmountReceived,
		Premium,
		AgentSplit,
		CommissionType,
		CommissionTypeDesc,
		PayBasisCode,					
		PayBasisDesc,					
		PaymentMatchedDate,				
		Month,
		FrequencyCode,
		FrequencyDesc,
		ReassignedProductGroupCode,		
		ReassignedProductGroupName,		
		RecognitionType,
		CalculationType,
		Source,
		DateInserted,
		DateLastUpdated,
		CommissionYear
	)
	select	cs.PendingPaymentID as SourceID,
			cs.CaseID,
			cs.TransactionID,
			cs.ExtPolicyNumber as Policy,
			cs.ProductCode,
			cs.BusinessCode,
			cs.AgentCode as SellerCode,				
			0.0 as PointsTotal,
			0.0 as BSC,
			case 
				when mbf.MortgageFeeID is not null and cs.INIssued <> 0 then (((mbf.AdviceFeeAmount)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * MRbkr.FACTOR) - ((mbf.AdviceFeeAmount)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * Mfca.FACTOR)) --Note that mbf.AdviceFeeAmount is signed correctly - so no coding for signing is needed here
				else 0.0
			end as MBF,
			case 
				--When the adviser has changed, the AgentSplit can become zero in which case the ELITE points should be zero.
				when cs.AgentSplit = 0 then 0
				
				--WEALTH CALCULATION START
				--Indemnity payments or SINGLEs or IC Clawbacks or IC adjustments Start
				--THIS SCENARIO DOESN'T OCCUR IN PHASE 2
				--Indemnity payments or SINGLEs or IC Clawbacks or IC adjustments End
				--Accruals & Level Start
				when (ph.ProductCategoryCode = 1 or pcc.KeyValue2 = '1') then (((e.AMOUNT_REC)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * Crate.FACTOR) - ((e.AMOUNT_REC)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * Cfca.FACTOR)) * case when cs.CommissionType in (2,17) then -1 else 1 end
				--Accruals & Level End
				--WEALTH CALCULATION END
				
				--MORTGAGE CALCULATION START
				--Note: The MBF component has its own table column
				--Only 1 payment for mortgages
				when ph.ProductGroupCode = 3 then (((e.AMOUNT_REC)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * MRproc.FACTOR) - ((e.AMOUNT_REC)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * Mfca.FACTOR)) * case when cs.CommissionType in (2,17) then -1 else 1 end	
				--MORTGAGE CALCULATION END
				
				--PROTECTION CALCULATION START
				--Indemnity payments or SINGLEs or IC Clawbacks or IC adjustments Start
				--THIS SCENARIO DOESN'T OCCUR IN PHASE 2
				--Indemnity payments or SINGLEs or IC Clawbacks or IC adjustments End
				--Accruals & Level Start
				when ph.ProductGroupCode = 6 then (((e.AMOUNT_REC)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * Prate.FACTOR) - ((e.AMOUNT_REC)*(cs.AgentSplit/100) * Pfca.FACTOR)) * case when cs.CommissionType in (2,17) then -1 else 1 end
				--Accruals & Level End
				--PROTECTION CALCULATION END

				else 0.0

			end as Initial,
			0.0 as OngoingTotal,
			0.0 as OngoingYr01,
			0.0 as OngoingYr02,
			0.0 as OngoingYr03,
			0.0 as OngoingYr04,
			0.0 as OngoingYr05,
			0.0 as OngoingYr06,
			0.0 as OngoingYr07,
			0.0 as OngoingYr08,
			0.0 as OngoingYr09,
			0.0 as OngoingYr10,
			case 
				when (ph.ProductCategoryCode = 1 or pcc.KeyValue2 = '1') then Cfca.FACTOR*100.0		--COB
				when ph.ProductGroupCode = 3 then Mfca.FACTOR*100.0		--MORT
				when ph.ProductGroupCode = 6 then Pfca.FACTOR*100.0		--PROT
				else 0.0
			end as FCARate,
			case 
				when (ph.ProductCategoryCode = 1 or pcc.KeyValue2 = '1') then Crate.FACTOR*100.0	--COB
				when ph.ProductGroupCode = 3 then MRproc.FACTOR*100.0	--MORT
				when ph.ProductGroupCode = 6 then Prate.FACTOR*100.0	--PROT
				else 0.0
			end as RetentionRate,
			case 
				when mbf.MortgageFeeID is not null then  MRbkr.FACTOR*100.0	
				else 0.0
			end as RetentionRateBroker,
			null as OngoingServicingRate,
			null as OngoingServicingSource,
			pt.CommInitialAmount as DA,
			e.AMOUNT_REC as AmountReceived,
			cs.Premium,
			cs.AgentSplit,
			cs.CommissionType,
			left(cs.StandingOrderDesc,50) as CommissionTypeDesc,
			cs.PayBasisCode,							
			cs.PayBasisDesc,							
			cs.CreateDate as PaymentMatchedDate,		
			cs.Month,
			cs.FrequencyCode,
			cs.FrequencyDesc,
			pg.ProductGroupCode as ReassignedProductGroupCode,	--Force the re-assigned products...		
			pg.ProductGroupName as ReassignedProductGroupName,	--...to be processed as investments		
			'VNB-INI-PHASE-2' as RecognitionType,
			case 
				when (ph.ProductCategoryCode = 1 or pcc.KeyValue2 = '1') then 'WEALTH-INITIAL'
				when ph.ProductGroupCode = 3 then 'MORTGAGE'
				when ph.ProductGroupCode = 6 then 'PROTECTION'
				else null
			end as CalculationType,
			'Openwork 2006' as Source,
			@DateLastUpdated as DateInserted,
			@DateLastUpdated as DateLastUpdated,
			csp.year as CommissionYear
	from	#msit_CommissionStatementSUMMARY css
			inner join msit_CommissionStatement cs
						on cs.TransactionID = css.TransactionID
						and cs.AgentCode = css.AgentCode
			inner join mstt_Agents ag on ag.Code = cs.BusinessCode
			inner join mstt_PolicyTransactions pt on pt.ID = cs.TransactionID
			inner join mstt_Policies p on p.POL_NUM = pt.PolicyID
			inner join msit_CommissionStatementPeriods VNBStart on convert(date,pt.CreateDateTime) between VNBStart.PeriodStartDate and VNBStart.PeriodEndDate
			inner join msit_Commissionstatementperiods csp on csp.month = cs.month
			inner join mstt_ProductHierarchy ph on ph.productcode = cs.productcode
			inner join mstt_Expectation e on e.ID = cs.ExpectationID
			left join dbo.owt_MortgageBrokerFees mbf on mbf.PendingPaymentID = cs.PendingPaymentID and mbf.AdviceFeeCharged = 'Yes'
			left join owt_SelectionControl SC
						on SC.Process = 'ElitePoints' 
						and SC.KeyType = 'NSCPotCode' 
						and cs.CreateDate between SC.EffectiveStartDate and SC.EffectiveEndDate
			left join mstt_Commissions BSCpot
						on BSCpot.TransactionID = cs.TransactionID 
						and BSCpot.Agent_Code = sc.KeyValue
						and BSCpot.CommissionType = 10
			left join owt_SelectionControl SFMPC						
						on SFMPC.Process = 'ElitePoints' 
						and SFMPC.KeyType = 'ServicingFeeMarginPotCode' 
						and cs.CreateDate between SFMPC.EffectiveStartDate and SFMPC.EffectiveEndDate
			left join mstt_Commissions SFMpot							
						on SFMpot.TransactionID = cs.TransactionID 
						and SFMpot.Agent_Code = SFMPC.KeyValue
						and SFMpot.CommissionType = 10	
			left join owt_SelectionControl pcc 
						on pcc.Process = 'ElitePoints'
						and pcc.KeyType = 'ProductCategoryCode'
						and pcc.KeyValue = cs.ProductCode	
						and cs.CreateDate between pcc.EffectiveStartDate and pcc.EffectiveEndDate
			left join owt_SelectionControl ogsdflt 
						on ogsdflt.Process = 'ElitePoints'
						and ogsdflt.KeyType = 'DefaultOngoingServicingRate'
						and ogsdflt.SelectionType = 'VNB'
						and ogsdflt.KeyValue = case when ph.RDRType = 'ONPLAT' then 'ONPLAT' else 'OFPLAT' end
						and cs.CreateDate between ogsdflt.EffectiveStartDate and ogsdflt.EffectiveEndDate
			left join mstt_CodeProductGroup pg on pg.ProductGroupCode = case when pcc.KeyValue2 = '1' then 2 else ph.ProductGroupCode end
			left join owt_EliteFactors Cfca on Cfca.FeeType = 'VNB' and Cfca.category = 'COB-FCA-RATE' and csp.year between Cfca.StartYear and Cfca.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors Crate on Crate.FeeType = 'VNB' and Crate.category = 'COB-RETENTION-RATE' and csp.year between Crate.StartYear and Crate.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors Mfca on Mfca.FeeType = 'VNB' and Mfca.category = 'MORT-FCA-RATE' and csp.year between Mfca.StartYear and Mfca.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors MRproc on MRproc.FeeType = 'VNB' and MRproc.category = 'MORT-RETENTION-RATE-PROC' and csp.year between MRproc.StartYear and MRproc.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors MRbkr on MRbkr.FeeType = 'VNB' and MRbkr.category = 'MORT-RETENTION-RATE-BROKER' and csp.year between MRbkr.StartYear and MRbkr.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors Pfca on Pfca.FeeType = 'VNB' and Pfca.category = 'PROT-FCA-RATE' and csp.year between Pfca.StartYear and Pfca.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors Prate on Prate.FeeType = 'VNB' and Prate.category = 'PROT-RETENTION-RATE' and csp.year between Prate.StartYear and Prate.EndYear 
	where	cs.ReportingClassCode = 1
	and		cs.CommissionType in (1,2,17)			--We want all the initial payment types (i.e. not trail (ongoing))
	and		ag.Manager2Code <> @OwlManager2Code		--Exclude Owl

	select @RowCount = @@rowcount
	set @ProcessMessage = '#owt_Recognition (ini ph2 - accr adj) = ' + convert(nvarchar(10), @RowCount)
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseLog, @ProcessMessage, null, @Module, @Client

	/****************************************************************************

		Initial Phase 3
		1) Add up the +ves and -ves prior to the NEW front loaded amount and
			net them off on the first +ve following the last -ve
		2) Now set all the +ves following the one updated in (1) to zero.
																
	****************************************************************************/

	update r
		set RecognitionType	= case when r.SourceID >= css.MinInitialAfterAdjPendingPaymentID 
								then 'VNB-INI-PHASE-3'
								else r.RecognitionType
							  end,
			Initial = case  when r.SourceID = css.MinInitialAfterAdjPendingPaymentID 
								then (((r.DA)*(r.AgentSplit/100) * (r.RetentionRate/100.0)) - ((r.DA)*(r.AgentSplit/100) * (r.FCARate/100))) - derived.SumInitial
							when r.SourceID > css.MinInitialAfterAdjPendingPaymentID 
								then 0.0
							else r.Initial
					  end,
			DateLastUpdated = @DateLastUpdated
	from	#msit_CommissionStatementSUMMARY css
			inner join #AG_owt_Recognition_SEPARATE_ONGOING r
						on r.TransactionID = css.TransactionID
						and r.SellerCode = css.AgentCode
			inner join (select	r.TransactionID, r.SellerCode, SUM(Initial) as SumInitial
						from	#msit_CommissionStatementSUMMARY s
								inner join #AG_owt_Recognition_SEPARATE_ONGOING r 
											on r.TransactionID = s.TransactionID
											and r.SellerCode = s.AgentCode
						where	r.SourceID <= s.MaxAdjPendingPaymentID
						group	by r.TransactionID, r.SellerCode
						) derived 
							on  derived.TransactionID = r.TransactionID
							and	derived.SellerCode = r.SellerCode 
	where	isnull(css.MaxInitialPendingPaymentID,0) > isnull(css.MaxAdjPendingPaymentID,0)-- An initial payment follows the clawback, so time to revert back to front loading

	select @RowCount = @@rowcount
	set @ProcessMessage = '#owt_Recognition (ini ph3 - accr adj) = ' + convert(nvarchar(10), @RowCount)
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseLog, @ProcessMessage, null, @Module, @Client

	/****************************************************************************

		Now do the ongoing.
		
		Build an ongoing summary row for each transaction (slice).
		
		Note we do not care about ongoing clawbacks and adjustments for VNB.
		We want VNB to be on the oldest positive payment on each slice for the
		policy (split by adviser if needed).
						
	****************************************************************************/

	select	cs.TransactionID,
			cs.AgentCode,
			c.AGENT_PERC as AgentSplit,
			min(case when cs.CommissionType = 10 then cs.PendingPaymentID else null end) as MinOngoingPendingPaymentID,
			max(case when cs.CommissionType = 10 then cs.PendingPaymentID else null end) as MaxOngoingPendingPaymentID,
			max(case when cs.CommissionType in (16,19) then cs.PendingPaymentID else null end) as MaxOngoingAdjPendingPaymentID,
			null as MinOngoingAfterAdjPendingPaymentID,
			cs.Premium,			--AG 17/07/2018
			cs.FrequencyCode,	--AG 17/07/2018
			cs.FrequencyDesc	--AG 17/07/2018
	into	#msit_CommissionStatementOGSSUMMARY
	from 	msit_CommissionStatement cs
			inner join mstt_Commissions c
						on c.TransactionID = cs.TransactionID
						and c.Agent_Code = cs.AgentCode
						and c.CommissionType = 1
			inner join mstt_Agents ag on ag.Code = cs.BusinessCode
			inner join mstt_PolicyTransactions pt on pt.ID = cs.TransactionID
			inner join mstt_Policies p on p.POL_NUM = pt.PolicyID
			inner join msit_CommissionStatementPeriods VNBStart on convert(date,pt.CreateDateTime) between VNBStart.PeriodStartDate and VNBStart.PeriodEndDate
			inner join msit_Commissionstatementperiods csp on csp.month = cs.month
			inner join mstt_ProductHierarchy ph on ph.productcode = cs.productcode
			inner join mstt_Expectation e on e.ID = cs.ExpectationID
			left join owt_SelectionControl pcc 
						on pcc.Process = 'ElitePoints'
						and pcc.KeyType = 'ProductCategoryCode'
						and pcc.KeyValue = cs.ProductCode	
						and cs.CreateDate between pcc.EffectiveStartDate and pcc.EffectiveEndDate
	where	cs.ReportingClassCode = 1
	and		cs.CommissionType in (10,16,19)					--Choose only where the ongoing payment is positive
	and		cs.CommFeeType = 'Ongoing'
	and		(ph.ProductCategoryCode = 1 or pcc.KeyValue2 = '1')
	and		ag.Manager2Code <> @OwlManager2Code		--Exclude Owl
	and		csp.Year >= 2017						--Ensure in-scope payments are consistent with VNB start
	and		VNBStart.Year >= 2017 
	and		abs(e.AMOUNT_REC) >= 0.01
	and		((cs.FrequencyCode = 6 and cs.Premium > 1.00)		--Frequency=6->Single
			or (cs.FrequencyCode <> 6 and cs.Premium > 0.01))	--Frequency<>6->Regular	
	group by	cs.TransactionID,
				cs.AgentCode,
				c.Agent_Perc,
				cs.Premium,			--AG 17/07/2018
				cs.FrequencyCode,	--AG 17/07/2018
				cs.FrequencyDesc	--AG 17/07/2018

	select @RowCount = @@rowcount
	set @ProcessMessage = '#msit_CommissionStatementOGSSUMMARY (ogs txn) = ' + convert(nvarchar(10), @RowCount)
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseLog, @ProcessMessage, null, @Module, @Client

	--Get first ongoing payment after last clawback/adj
	update cso
		set MinOngoingAfterAdjPendingPaymentID = summ.MinPendingPaymentID 
	from  #msit_CommissionStatementOGSSUMMARY cso
			inner join  (
						select	csoinner.TransactionID, csoinner.AgentCode, min(cs.PendingPaymentID) as MinPendingPaymentID
						from	#msit_CommissionStatementOGSSUMMARY csoinner
								inner join msit_CommissionStatement cs
											on cs.TransactionID = csoinner.TransactionID
											and cs.AgentCode = csoinner.AgentCode
						where	cs.PendingPaymentID > csoinner.MaxOngoingAdjPendingPaymentID
						and		cs.CommissionType = 10
						group by csoinner.TransactionID, csoinner.AgentCode
						) summ on  summ.TransactionID = cso.TransactionID
							   and summ.AgentCode = cso.AgentCode

	select @RowCount = @@rowcount
	set @ProcessMessage = '#msit_CommissionStatementOGSSUMMARY (ogs latest +ve) = ' + convert(nvarchar(10), @RowCount)
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseLog, @ProcessMessage, null, @Module, @Client

	/****************************************************************************
		
		Using the OGS SUMMARY table, get all the individual payment records that
		will be carriers of VNB points as follows:
		
		SelectionSource 1 - The oldest +ve payment where no clawbacks or 
								adjustments occur for front loading

		SelectionSource 2 - All the +ve payments that will get a spread of the 
								per payment +ve points 		

		SelectionSource 3 - All the -ve payments that will get a spread of the 
								per payment -ve points
								 															
	****************************************************************************/
	
	--AG 17/07/2018
	--Combine the premium on all the transactions (slices) for each case and seller
	--In case of mixed frequencies, force the sum to be a single
	select	CaseID,
			SellerCode,
			sum(case when FrequencyCode = 2 then Premium * 12.0 * (AgentSplit/100) else Premium * (AgentSplit/100) end) as SumOfPremium,
			convert(tinyint,6) as FrequencyCode,			--single
			convert(varchar(20),'Single') as FrequencyDesc
	into	#OngoingPremiumTotal
	from	#AG_owt_Recognition_SEPARATE_ONGOING
	where	CalculationType = 'WEALTH-INITIAL'
	group	by CaseID, SellerCode

	select @RowCount = @@rowcount
	set @ProcessMessage = '#OngoingPremiumTotal = ' + convert(nvarchar(10), @RowCount)
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseLog, @ProcessMessage, null, @Module, @Client
		
	--Front loaded -> Just the oldest +ve payment
	--Note: These transactions have NO clawbacks or adjustments
	select	1 as SelectionSource,
			cso.TransactionID,
			cso.AgentCode,
			cso.MinOngoingPendingPaymentID as PendingPaymentID,
			cso.AgentSplit,
			case when opt.CaseID is null
				then cso.Premium
				else opt.SumOfPremium
			end as Premium,
			case when opt.CaseID is null
				then cso.FrequencyCode
				else opt.FrequencyCode
			end as FrequencyCode,
			case when opt.CaseID is null
				then cso.FrequencyDesc
				else opt.FrequencyDesc
			end as FrequencyDesc,
			1 as SpreadNumber,
			1 as MaxSpread 
	into	#msit_CommissionStatementONGOING
	from	#msit_CommissionStatementOGSSUMMARY cso	
			left join mstt_PolicyTransactions pt on pt.ID = cso.TransactionID
			left join mstt_Policies p on p.POL_NUM = pt.PolicyID
			left join #OngoingPremiumTotal opt			--When NO clawbacks or adjustments, the seller gets credit for the combined premium
						on opt.CaseID = p.PolicyRef
						and opt.SellerCode = cso.AgentCode
	where	cso.MaxOngoingAdjPendingPaymentID is null	--No clawbacks or adjustments - so front load
	and		cso.MinOngoingPendingPaymentID is not null	--At least one +ve payment on the transaction

	union	--Add in with dedupe
	
	--Per payment -> all +ve payments with max spread also used for divisor
	--Note: ALL these transactions have clawbacks or adjustments
	select	2 as SelectionSource,
			cso.TransactionID,
			cso.AgentCode,
			cs.PendingPaymentID,
			cso.AgentSplit,
			cso.Premium,
			cso.FrequencyCode,
			cso.FrequencyDesc,
			ROW_NUMBER() over (partition by cs.TransactionID, cs.AgentCode order by cs.TransactionID, cs.AgentCode, cs.PendingPaymentID) as SpreadNumber,
			12 as MaxSpread
	from	#msit_CommissionStatementOGSSUMMARY cso	
			inner join msit_CommissionStatement cs 
						on cs.TransactionID = cso.TransactionID
						and cs.AgentCode = cso.AgentCode
	where	cso.MaxOngoingAdjPendingPaymentID is not null	--Clawbacks or adjustments so per payment
	and		cs.CommissionType in (10)	

	union	--Add in with dedupe
	
	--Per payment -> all -ve payments - with max spread also used for divisor
	--Note: ALL these transactions have clawbacks or adjustments
	select	3 as SelectionSource,
			cso.TransactionID,
			cso.AgentCode,
			cs.PendingPaymentID,
			cso.AgentSplit,
			cso.Premium,
			cso.FrequencyCode,
			cso.FrequencyDesc,
			ROW_NUMBER() over (partition by cs.TransactionID, cs.AgentCode order by cs.TransactionID, cs.AgentCode, cs.PendingPaymentID) as SpreadNumber,
			12 as MaxSpread
	from	#msit_CommissionStatementOGSSUMMARY cso	
			inner join msit_CommissionStatement cs 
						on cs.TransactionID = cso.TransactionID
						and cs.AgentCode = cso.AgentCode
	where	cso.MaxOngoingAdjPendingPaymentID is not null	--Clawbacks or adjustments so per payment
	and		cs.CommissionType in (16,19)	

	select @RowCount = @@rowcount
	set @ProcessMessage = '#msit_CommissionStatementONGOING (ogs payments) = ' + convert(nvarchar(10), @RowCount)
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseLog, @ProcessMessage, null, @Module, @Client

	/****************************************************************************
		
		Insert the ongoing VNB results for those transactions 
																		
	****************************************************************************/

	insert into #AG_owt_Recognition_SEPARATE_ONGOING
	(
		SourceID,
		CaseID,
		TransactionID,
		Policy,
		ProductCode,
		BusinessCode,
		SellerCode,
		PointsTotal,
		BSC,
		MBF,
		Initial,
		OngoingTotal,
		OngoingYr01,
		OngoingYr02,
		OngoingYr03,
		OngoingYr04,
		OngoingYr05,
		OngoingYr06,
		OngoingYr07,
		OngoingYr08,
		OngoingYr09,
		OngoingYr10,
		FCARate,
		RetentionRate,
		RetentionRateBroker,
		OngoingServicingRate,
		OngoingServicingSource,
		DA,
		AmountReceived,
		Premium,
		AgentSplit,
		CommissionType,
		CommissionTypeDesc,
		PayBasisCode,
		PayBasisDesc,
		PaymentMatchedDate,
		Month,
		FrequencyCode,
		FrequencyDesc,
		ReassignedProductGroupCode,
		ReassignedProductGroupName,
		RecognitionType,
		CalculationType,
		Source,
		DateInserted,
		DateLastUpdated,
		CommissionYear
	)
	select	cs.PendingPaymentID as SourceID,
			cs.CaseID,
			cs.TransactionID,
			cs.ExtPolicyNumber as Policy,
			cs.ProductCode,
			cs.BusinessCode,
			cs.AgentCode as SellerCode,
			0.0 as PointsTotal,
			case
				when BSCpot.ID is not null then 
					--BSC takes the first 0.12 of the ongoing fee %. If the ongoing fee % is 0.12% or less, then 100% of the ongoing fee is allocated to BSC
					case when coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2)) - convert(decimal(8,4),sc.KeyValue2) >= 0.01
						then 
							case when cso.FrequencyCode = 2	--Monthly 
								then (cso.AgentSplit/100) * 12.0 * (isnull(cso.Premium/cso.MaxSpread,0)/2.0) * convert(decimal(8,4),sc.KeyValue3) * case when cs.CommissionType in (16,19) then -1 else 1 end
								else (cso.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(cso.Premium/cso.MaxSpread,0) * convert(decimal(8,4),sc.KeyValue3) * case when cs.CommissionType in (16,19) then -1 else 1 end
							end			
						else
							case when cso.FrequencyCode = 2	--Monthly 
								then (cso.AgentSplit/100) * 12.0 * (isnull(cso.Premium/cso.MaxSpread,0)/2.0) * coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2)) * case when cs.CommissionType in (16,19) then -1 else 1 end
								else (cso.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(cso.Premium/cso.MaxSpread,0) * (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))/100.0) * case when cs.CommissionType in (16,19) then -1 else 1 end
							end
					end
				else 0.0
			end as BSC,
			0.0 as MBF,
			0.0 as Initial,
			0.0 as OngoingTotal,
			case
				--WEALTH ONGOING CALCULATION START
				--When the adviser has changed, the AgentSplit can become zero in which case the ELITE points should be zero.
				when cso.AgentSplit = 0 then 0

				--SINGLE start
				--Calculate when BSC and ongoing applies (where ongoing rate is greater than BSC rate) 
				when cso.FrequencyCode = 6 and SFMpot.ID is not null and BSCpot.ID is not null and (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2)) - convert(decimal(8,4),sc.KeyValue2)) >= 0.01 then 
							--(AUM X BSC Rate)...
							((cso.AgentSplit/100) * (isnull(cso.Premium/cso.MaxSpread,0) * convert(decimal(8,4),sc.KeyValue3)) 
							--(AUM X OGS Rate X COB FCA Rate)...
							- ((cso.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(cso.Premium/cso.MaxSpread,0) * (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))/100.0) * Cfca.FACTOR)
							--(AUM X (OGS Rate - BSC Rate) X COB Retention Rate)...
							+ ((cso.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(cso.Premium/cso.MaxSpread,0) * ((coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))-convert(decimal(8,4),sc.KeyValue2))/100.0)) * Crate.FACTOR) 
							--Sign correctly for +ve or clawback payment
							* (case when cs.CommissionType in (16,19) then -1 else 1 end)
				--Calculate when BSC and ongoing applies (where ongoing rate less than BSC rate, then BSC gets all the ongoing available) 
				when cso.FrequencyCode = 6 and SFMpot.ID is not null and BSCpot.ID is not null then
							--(AUM X BSC Rate)...(in this scenario it's all of the OGS rate)
							((cso.AgentSplit/100) * (isnull(cso.Premium/cso.MaxSpread,0) * (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))/100.0)) 
							--(AUM X OGS Rate X COB FCA Rate)...
							- ((cso.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(cso.Premium/cso.MaxSpread,0) * (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))/100.0) * Cfca.FACTOR)
							--(AUM X (OGS Rate - BSC Rate) X COB Retention Rate)...
							+ (0.0)) --BSC got it all, so this part of the calculation is zero
							--Sign correctly for +ve or clawback payment
							* (case when cs.CommissionType in (16,19) then -1 else 1 end)
				--Calculate when no BSC applies and ongoing applies
				when cso.FrequencyCode = 6 and SFMpot.ID is not null and BSCpot.ID is null then 
							--(AUM X OGS Rate X COB Retention Rate)...
							(((cso.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(cso.Premium/cso.MaxSpread,0) * (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))/100.0) * Crate.FACTOR) 
							--(AUM X OGS Rate X COB FCA Rate)...
							- ((cso.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(cso.Premium/cso.MaxSpread,0) * (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))/100.0) * Cfca.FACTOR))
							--Sign correctly for +ve or clawback payment
							* (case when cs.CommissionType in (16,19) then -1 else 1 end)
				--SINGLE end
				
				--REGULAR start
				--Calculate when BSC and ongoing applies (where ongoing rate is greater than BSC rate) 
				when cso.FrequencyCode <> 6 and SFMpot.ID is not null and BSCpot.ID is not null and (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2)) - convert(decimal(8,4),sc.KeyValue2)) >= 0.01 then		--AG 04/06/2018 (1)
							--The non-BSC portion (Ave AUM X (OGS Rate - BSC Rate) X COB Retention Rate)...
							((((((cso.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(cso.Premium/cso.MaxSpread,0) * (case when cso.FrequencyCode = 2 then 12 else 1 end))/2.0) * (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2)) - convert(decimal(8,4),sc.KeyValue2))/100.0)) * Crate.FACTOR
							--The BSC portion (Ave AUM X BSC Rate)...
							+ case when cso.FrequencyCode = 2	--Monthly 
									then (cso.AgentSplit/100) * 12.0 * (isnull(cso.Premium/cso.MaxSpread,0)/2.0) * convert(decimal(8,4),sc.KeyValue3) 
									else (cso.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(cso.Premium/cso.MaxSpread,0) * convert(decimal(8,4),sc.KeyValue3) 
							  end
							--FCA Charge (Ave AUM X OGS Rate X FCA Rate)...
							- (case when cso.FrequencyCode = 2	--Monthly 
									then (cso.AgentSplit/100) * 12.0 * (isnull(cso.Premium/cso.MaxSpread,0)/2.0) 
									else (cso.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(cso.Premium/cso.MaxSpread,0) 
							   end * (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))/100.0) * Cfca.FACTOR))
							--Sign correctly for +ve or clawback payment
							* (case when cs.CommissionType in (16,19) then -1 else 1 end)   
				--Calculate when BSC and ongoing applies (where ongoing rate less than BSC rate, then BSC gets all the ongoing available) 
				when cso.FrequencyCode <> 6 and SFMpot.ID is not null and BSCpot.ID is not null then		--AG 04/06/2018 (1)
							--The non-BSC portion (Ave AUM X (OGS Rate - BSC Rate) X COB Retention Rate)...
							((0.0)	--BSC got it all, so this part of the calculation is zero
							--The BSC portion (Ave AUM X BSC Rate)...(in this scenario it's all of the OGS rate)
							+ case when cso.FrequencyCode = 2	--Monthly 
									then (cso.AgentSplit/100) * 12.0 * (isnull(cso.Premium/cso.MaxSpread,0)/2.0) * (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))/100.0) 
									else (cso.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(cso.Premium/cso.MaxSpread,0) * (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))/100.0) 
							  end
							--FCA Charge (Ave AUM X OGS Rate X FCA Rate)...
							- (case when cso.FrequencyCode = 2	--Monthly 
									then (cso.AgentSplit/100) * 12.0 * (isnull(cso.Premium/cso.MaxSpread,0)/2.0) 
									else (cso.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(cso.Premium/cso.MaxSpread,0) 
							   end * (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))/100.0) * Cfca.FACTOR))
							--Sign correctly for +ve or clawback payment
							* (case when cs.CommissionType in (16,19) then -1 else 1 end)   
				--Calculate when no BSC applies, but ongoing servicing applies
				when cso.FrequencyCode <> 6 and SFMpot.ID is not null and BSCpot.ID is null then		--AG 04/06/2018	(1)
							--(Ave AUM X OGS Rate X COB Retention Rate)...
							(((((cso.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(cso.Premium/cso.MaxSpread,0) * (case when cso.FrequencyCode = 2 then 12 else 1 end))/2.0) * (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))/100.0) * Crate.FACTOR) 
							--(Ave AUM X OGS Rate X COB FCA Rate)...
							- ((((cso.AgentSplit/100) * isnull(cso.Premium/cso.MaxSpread,0) * (case when cso.FrequencyCode = 2 then 12 else 1 end))/2.0) * (coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))/100.0) * Cfca.FACTOR))
							--Sign correctly for +ve or clawback payment
							* (case when cs.CommissionType in (16,19) then -1 else 1 end)   
				--REGULAR end
				
				else 0.0

				--WEALTH ONGOING CALCULATION END
			end as OngoingYr01,
			0.0 as OngoingYr02,
			0.0 as OngoingYr03,
			0.0 as OngoingYr04,
			0.0 as OngoingYr05,
			0.0 as OngoingYr06,
			0.0 as OngoingYr07,
			0.0 as OngoingYr08,
			0.0 as OngoingYr09,
			0.0 as OngoingYr10,
			Cfca.FACTOR*100.0 as FCARate,
			Crate.FACTOR*100.0 as RetentionRate,
			0.0 as RetentionRateBroker,
			case when SFMpot.ID is not null
				then coalesce(ogs.OngoingServiceFee,ogscli.OngoingServiceFee,convert(decimal(8,4),ogsdflt.KeyValue2))
				else null
			end as OngoingServicingRate,
			case when SFMpot.ID is not null
				then case 
						when ogs.OngoingServiceFee is null and ogscli.OngoingServiceFee is null 
							then case
								when ogsdflt.KeyValue = 'ONPLAT' then 'Default - On Plat'
								else 'Default - Off Plat'
							end
						when ogs.OngoingServiceFee is not null then 'Client Product'
						when ogscli.OngoingServiceFee is not null then 'Client Only'
						else 'Unknown'
					 end
				else case when (ph.ProductCategoryCode = 1 or pcc.KeyValue2 = '1')
						then 'No OGS'					--WEALTH, but no OGS
						else null						--Not WEALTH, so OGS is n/a and is therefore null
					 end
			end as OngoingServicingSource,
			pt.CommInitialAmount as DA,
			e.AMOUNT_REC as AmountReceived,
			cso.Premium,								--AG 17/07/2018
			cso.AgentSplit,								--Use the split from the IC record
			cs.CommissionType,
			left(cs.StandingOrderDesc,50) as CommissionTypeDesc,
			cs.PayBasisCode,
			cs.PayBasisDesc,
			cs.CreateDate as PaymentMatchedDate,
			cs.Month,
			cso.FrequencyCode,							--AG 17/07/2018
			cso.FrequencyDesc,							--AG 17/07/2018
			pg.ProductGroupCode as ReassignedProductGroupCode,	--Force the re-assigned products...		
			pg.ProductGroupName as ReassignedProductGroupName,	--...to be processed as investments		
			case cso.SelectionSource
				when 1 then 'VNB-OGS-PHASE-1' 
				when 2 then 'VNB-OGS-PHASE-2' 
				when 3 then 'VNB-OGS-PHASE-3' 
			end as RecognitionType,
			'WEALTH-ONGOING' as CalculationType,
			'Openwork 2006' as Source,
			@DateLastUpdated as DateInserted,
			@DateLastUpdated as DateLastUpdated,
			csp.year as CommissionYear
	from	#msit_CommissionStatementONGOING cso
			inner join msit_CommissionStatement cs on cs.PendingPaymentID = cso.PendingPaymentID
			inner join mstt_Agents ag on ag.Code = cs.BusinessCode
			inner join mstt_PolicyTransactions pt on pt.ID = cs.TransactionID
			inner join mstt_Policies p on p.POL_NUM = pt.PolicyID
			inner join msit_CommissionStatementPeriods VNBStart on convert(date,pt.CreateDateTime) between VNBStart.PeriodStartDate and VNBStart.PeriodEndDate
			inner join msit_Commissionstatementperiods csp on csp.month = cs.month
			inner join mstt_ProductHierarchy ph on ph.productcode = cs.productcode
			inner join mstt_Expectation e on e.ID = cs.ExpectationID
			left join dbo.owt_MortgageBrokerFees mbf on mbf.PendingPaymentID = cs.PendingPaymentID and mbf.AdviceFeeCharged = 'Yes'
			left join owt_SelectionControl SC
						on SC.Process = 'ElitePoints' 
						and SC.KeyType = 'NSCPotCode' 
						and cs.CreateDate between SC.EffectiveStartDate and SC.EffectiveEndDate
			left join mstt_Commissions BSCpot
						on BSCpot.TransactionID = cs.TransactionID 
						and BSCpot.Agent_Code = sc.KeyValue
						and BSCpot.CommissionType = 10
			left join owt_SelectionControl SFMPC						
						on SFMPC.Process = 'ElitePoints' 
						and SFMPC.KeyType = 'ServicingFeeMarginPotCode' 
						and cs.CreateDate between SFMPC.EffectiveStartDate and SFMPC.EffectiveEndDate
			left join mstt_Commissions SFMpot							
						on SFMpot.TransactionID = cs.TransactionID 
						and SFMpot.Agent_Code = SFMPC.KeyValue
						and SFMpot.CommissionType = 10	
			left join owt_SelectionControl pcc 
						on pcc.Process = 'ElitePoints'
						and pcc.KeyType = 'ProductCategoryCode'
						and pcc.KeyValue = cs.ProductCode	
						and cs.CreateDate between pcc.EffectiveStartDate and pcc.EffectiveEndDate
			left join owt_SelectionControl ogsdflt 
						on ogsdflt.Process = 'ElitePoints'
						and ogsdflt.KeyType = 'DefaultOngoingServicingRate'
						and ogsdflt.SelectionType = 'VNB'
						and ogsdflt.KeyValue = case when ph.RDRType = 'ONPLAT' then 'ONPLAT' else 'OFPLAT' end
						and cs.CreateDate between ogsdflt.EffectiveStartDate and ogsdflt.EffectiveEndDate
			left join mstt_CodeProductGroup pg on pg.ProductGroupCode = case when pcc.KeyValue2 = '1' then 2 else ph.ProductGroupCode end
			left join owt_EliteFactors Cfca on Cfca.FeeType = 'VNB' and Cfca.category = 'COB-FCA-RATE' and csp.year between Cfca.StartYear and Cfca.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors Crate on Crate.FeeType = 'VNB' and Crate.category = 'COB-RETENTION-RATE' and csp.year between Crate.StartYear and Crate.EndYear 
			left join dbo.owt_OngoingRate ogs 
						on  ogs.CLIENT_NUM = cs.ClientID 
						and ogs.ProductCode = cs.ProductCode
						and convert(date,pt.CreateDateTime) between ogs.EffectiveStartDate and ogs.EffectiveEndDate
			left join dbo.owt_OngoingRate ogscli 
						on  ogscli.CLIENT_NUM = cs.ClientID 
						and ogscli.ProductCode = '(CLIENT)'
						and convert(date,pt.CreateDateTime) between ogscli.EffectiveStartDate and ogscli.EffectiveEndDate
	where	cso.SpreadNumber <= cso.MaxSpread	-- if per payment spreading, then limit the spread
	
	select @RowCount = @@rowcount
	set @ProcessMessage = '#owt_Recognition (ogs ph1 yr1) = ' + convert(nvarchar(10), @RowCount)
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseLog, @ProcessMessage, null, @Module, @Client

	/****************************************************************************

		Ongoing Phase 3
		1) Add up the +ves and -ves prior to the NEW front loaded amount and
			net them off on the first +ve following the last -ve
		2) Now set all the +ves following the one updated in (1) to zero.
																
	****************************************************************************/

	update r
		set RecognitionType	= case when r.SourceID >= csos.MinOngoingAfterAdjPendingPaymentID 
								then 'VNB-OGS-PHASE-4'
								else r.RecognitionType
							  end,
			OngoingYr01 = case  when r.SourceID = csos.MinOngoingAfterAdjPendingPaymentID 
									then (abs(r.OngoingYr01) * cso.MaxSpread) - derived.SumOngoingYr01
								when r.SourceID > csos.MinOngoingAfterAdjPendingPaymentID 
									then 0.0
								else r.OngoingYr01
						  end,
			DateLastUpdated = @DateLastUpdated
	from	#msit_CommissionStatementONGOING cso 
			inner join #AG_owt_Recognition_SEPARATE_ONGOING r on r.SourceID = cso.PendingPaymentID
			inner join #msit_CommissionStatementOGSSUMMARY csos
						on  csos.TransactionID = cso.TransactionID
						and csos.AgentCode = cso.AgentCode
			inner join (select	r.TransactionID, r.SellerCode, SUM(OngoingYr01) as SumOngoingYr01
						from	#msit_CommissionStatementOGSSUMMARY s
								inner join #AG_owt_Recognition_SEPARATE_ONGOING r 
											on r.TransactionID = s.TransactionID
											and r.SellerCode = s.AgentCode
						where	r.SourceID <= s.MaxOngoingAdjPendingPaymentID
						group	by r.TransactionID, r.SellerCode
						) derived 
							on  derived.TransactionID = r.TransactionID
							and	derived.SellerCode = r.SellerCode 
	where	isnull(csos.MaxOngoingPendingPaymentID,0) > isnull(csos.MaxOngoingAdjPendingPaymentID,0)	--An ongoing +ve payment follows the clawback, so time to revert back to front loading
	and		cso.SpreadNumber <= cso.MaxSpread	--Only payments within the spread period get a portion of the ongoing VNB
	and		cso.SelectionSource <> 1			--Just process the per-payment rows (not the front loaded rows)

	select @RowCount = @@rowcount
	set @ProcessMessage = '#owt_Recognition (ogs ph4 - accr adj) = ' + convert(nvarchar(10), @RowCount)
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseLog, @ProcessMessage, null, @Module, @Client

	/****************************************************************************

		Now calculate the ongoing spread as follows:
		1) Investments: Years 1 to 6
		2) Pensions:	Years 1 to 10
		Note that regular payments get an additional multiplier to uplift the 
		average AUM for each year.
																		
	****************************************************************************/

	update r
		set OngoingYr02 = case when r.FrequencyCode = 2									--Monthly
							then r.OngoingYr01 * YR02.Multiplier * YR02.Factor			--Regular
							else r.OngoingYr01 * YR02.Factor							--Single
						  end,
			OngoingYr03 = case when r.FrequencyCode = 2									--Monthly
							then r.OngoingYr01 * YR03.Multiplier * YR03.Factor			--Regular
							else r.OngoingYr01 * YR03.Factor							--Single
						  end,
			OngoingYr04 = case when r.FrequencyCode = 2									--Monthly
							then r.OngoingYr01 * YR04.Multiplier * YR04.Factor			--Regular
							else r.OngoingYr01 * YR04.Factor							--Single
						  end,
			OngoingYr05 = case when r.FrequencyCode = 2									--Monthly 
							then r.OngoingYr01 * YR05.Multiplier * YR05.Factor			--Regular
							else r.OngoingYr01 * YR05.Factor							--Single
						  end,
			OngoingYr06 = case when r.FrequencyCode = 2									--Monthly 
							then r.OngoingYr01 * YR06.Multiplier * YR06.Factor			--Regular
							else r.OngoingYr01 * YR06.Factor							--Single
						  end,
			OngoingYr07 = case when r.ReassignedProductGroupCode = 5					--Pensions	AG 05/06/2018
							then
								case when r.FrequencyCode = 2							--Monthly 
									then r.OngoingYr01 * YR07.Multiplier * YR07.Factor	--Regular
									else r.OngoingYr01 * YR07.Factor					--Single
								end
							else 
								0.0
						  end,
			OngoingYr08 = case when r.ReassignedProductGroupCode = 5					--Pensions	AG 05/06/2018 
							then
								case when r.FrequencyCode = 2							--Monthly 
									then r.OngoingYr01 * YR08.Multiplier * YR08.Factor	--Regular
									else r.OngoingYr01 * YR08.Factor					--Single
								end
							else 
								0.0
						  end,
			OngoingYr09 = case when r.ReassignedProductGroupCode = 5					--Pensions	AG 05/06/2018 
							then
								case when r.FrequencyCode = 2							--Monthly 
									then r.OngoingYr01 * YR09.Multiplier * YR09.Factor	--Regular
									else r.OngoingYr01 * YR09.Factor					--Single
								end
							else 
								0.0
						  end,
			OngoingYr10 = case when r.ReassignedProductGroupCode = 5					--Pensions	AG 05/06/2018
							then
								case when r.FrequencyCode = 2							--Monthly 
									then r.OngoingYr01 * YR10.Multiplier * YR10.Factor	--Regular
									else r.OngoingYr01 * YR10.Factor					--Single
								end
							else 
								0.0
						  end
	from	#AG_owt_Recognition_SEPARATE_ONGOING r
			left join owt_EliteFactors YR01 on YR01.FeeType = 'VNB' and YR01.Category = 'COB-ONGOING-DISCOUNT-YR01' and r.CommissionYear between YR01.StartYear and YR01.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors YR02 on YR02.FeeType = 'VNB' and YR02.Category = 'COB-ONGOING-DISCOUNT-YR02' and r.CommissionYear between YR02.StartYear and YR02.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors YR03 on YR03.FeeType = 'VNB' and YR03.Category = 'COB-ONGOING-DISCOUNT-YR03' and r.CommissionYear between YR03.StartYear and YR03.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors YR04 on YR04.FeeType = 'VNB' and YR04.Category = 'COB-ONGOING-DISCOUNT-YR04' and r.CommissionYear between YR04.StartYear and YR04.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors YR05 on YR05.FeeType = 'VNB' and YR05.Category = 'COB-ONGOING-DISCOUNT-YR05' and r.CommissionYear between YR05.StartYear and YR05.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors YR06 on YR06.FeeType = 'VNB' and YR06.Category = 'COB-ONGOING-DISCOUNT-YR06' and r.CommissionYear between YR06.StartYear and YR06.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors YR07 on YR07.FeeType = 'VNB' and YR07.Category = 'COB-ONGOING-DISCOUNT-YR07' and r.CommissionYear between YR07.StartYear and YR07.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors YR08 on YR08.FeeType = 'VNB' and YR08.Category = 'COB-ONGOING-DISCOUNT-YR08' and r.CommissionYear between YR08.StartYear and YR08.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors YR09 on YR09.FeeType = 'VNB' and YR09.Category = 'COB-ONGOING-DISCOUNT-YR09' and r.CommissionYear between YR09.StartYear and YR09.EndYear 
			left join owt_EliteFactors YR10 on YR10.FeeType = 'VNB' and YR10.Category = 'COB-ONGOING-DISCOUNT-YR10' and r.CommissionYear between YR10.StartYear and YR10.EndYear 
	where	r.CalculationType = 'WEALTH-ONGOING'

	select @RowCount = @@rowcount
	set @ProcessMessage = '#owt_Recognition (ongoing yr2-10) = ' + convert(nvarchar(10), @RowCount)
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseLog, @ProcessMessage, null, @Module, @Client
	
	/****************************************************************************

		Now add up all the numbers
																		
	****************************************************************************/
	
	update r
		set OngoingTotal	=	OngoingYr01 + OngoingYr02 + OngoingYr03 + OngoingYr04 + OngoingYr05 +
								OngoingYr06 + OngoingYr07 + OngoingYr08 + OngoingYr09 + OngoingYr10,
			PointsTotal		=	OngoingYr01 + OngoingYr02 + OngoingYr03 + OngoingYr04 + OngoingYr05 +
								OngoingYr06 + OngoingYr07 + OngoingYr08 + OngoingYr09 + OngoingYr10 +
								Initial + MBF	-- Note BSC is already included in the Ongoing, so don't include it in the Points Total.
	from	#AG_owt_Recognition_SEPARATE_ONGOING r

	select @RowCount = @@rowcount
	set @ProcessMessage = '#owt_Recognition (points total) = ' + convert(nvarchar(10), @RowCount)
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseLog, @ProcessMessage, null, @Module, @Client

	/****************************************************************************

		Merge the temporary table into the permanent table (IC data)
																		
	****************************************************************************/

	BEGIN TRANSACTION

	declare @SummaryOfChanges table (Change varchar(20))
	merge	dbo.AG_owt_Recognition_SEPARATE_ONGOING as trg
	using	#AG_owt_Recognition_SEPARATE_ONGOING as src
	on		trg.SourceID = src.SourceID
	and		trg.Source = src.Source
	when	matched 
	and		isnull(trg.PointsTotal,0) <> isnull(src.PointsTotal,0)
	then	update 
				set trg.CaseID = src.CaseID,
					trg.TransactionID = src.TransactionID,
					trg.Policy = src.Policy,
					trg.ProductCode = src.ProductCode,
					trg.BusinessCode = src.BusinessCode,
					trg.SellerCode = src.SellerCode,					--AG 13/06/2018
					trg.PointsTotal = src.PointsTotal,
					trg.BSC = src.BSC,
					trg.MBF = src.MBF,
					trg.Initial = src.Initial,
					trg.OngoingTotal = src.OngoingTotal,
					trg.OngoingYr01 = src.OngoingYr01,
					trg.OngoingYr02 = src.OngoingYr02,
					trg.OngoingYr03 = src.OngoingYr03,
					trg.OngoingYr04 = src.OngoingYr04,
					trg.OngoingYr05 = src.OngoingYr05,
					trg.OngoingYr06 = src.OngoingYr06,
					trg.OngoingYr07 = src.OngoingYr07,
					trg.OngoingYr08 = src.OngoingYr08,
					trg.OngoingYr09 = src.OngoingYr09,
					trg.OngoingYr10 = src.OngoingYr10,
					trg.FCARate = src.FCARate,
					trg.RetentionRate = src.RetentionRate,
					trg.RetentionRateBroker = src.RetentionRateBroker,
					trg.OngoingServicingRate = src.OngoingServicingRate,
					trg.OngoingServicingSource = src.OngoingServicingSource,
					trg.DA = src.DA,
					trg.AmountReceived = src.AmountReceived,
					trg.Premium = src.Premium,
					trg.AgentSplit = src.AgentSplit,
					trg.CommissionType = src.CommissionType,
					trg.CommissionTypeDesc = src.CommissionTypeDesc,
					trg.PayBasisCode = src.PayBasisCode,				--AG 13/06/2018
					trg.PayBasisDesc = src.PayBasisDesc,				--AG 13/06/2018
					trg.PaymentMatchedDate = src.PaymentMatchedDate,	--AG 13/06/2018	
					trg.Month = src.Month,
					trg.FrequencyCode = src.FrequencyCode,
					trg.FrequencyDesc = src.FrequencyDesc,
					trg.ReassignedProductGroupCode = src.ReassignedProductGroupCode,	--AG 05/06/2018
					trg.ReassignedProductGroupName = src.ReassignedProductGroupName,	--AG 05/06/2018
					trg.RecognitionType = src.RecognitionType,
					trg.CalculationType = src.CalculationType,
					trg.DateLastUpdated = @DateLastUpdated
	when	not matched by target 
	then	insert
			(
				SourceID,
				CaseID,
				TransactionID,
				Policy,
				ProductCode,
				BusinessCode,
				SellerCode,							--AG 13/06/2018
				PointsTotal,
				BSC,
				MBF,
				Initial,
				OngoingTotal,
				OngoingYr01,
				OngoingYr02,
				OngoingYr03,
				OngoingYr04,
				OngoingYr05,
				OngoingYr06,
				OngoingYr07,
				OngoingYr08,
				OngoingYr09,
				OngoingYr10,
				FCARate,
				RetentionRate,
				RetentionRateBroker,
				OngoingServicingRate,
				OngoingServicingSource,
				DA,
				AmountReceived,
				Premium,
				AgentSplit,
				CommissionType,
				CommissionTypeDesc,
				PayBasisCode,						--AG 13/06/2018
				PayBasisDesc,						--AG 13/06/2018
				PaymentMatchedDate,					--AG 13/06/2018
				Month,
				FrequencyCode,
				FrequencyDesc,
				ReassignedProductGroupCode,			--AG 05/06/2018
				ReassignedProductGroupName,			--AG 05/06/2018
				RecognitionType,
				CalculationType,
				Source,
				DateInserted,
				DateLastUpdated
			)		
			values
			(
				src.SourceID,
				src.CaseID,
				src.TransactionID,
				src.Policy,
				src.ProductCode,
				src.BusinessCode,
				src.SellerCode,						--AG 13/06/2018
				src.PointsTotal,
				src.BSC,
				src.MBF,
				src.Initial,
				src.OngoingTotal,
				src.OngoingYr01,
				src.OngoingYr02,
				src.OngoingYr03,
				src.OngoingYr04,
				src.OngoingYr05,
				src.OngoingYr06,
				src.OngoingYr07,
				src.OngoingYr08,
				src.OngoingYr09,
				src.OngoingYr10,
				src.FCARate,
				src.RetentionRate,
				src.RetentionRateBroker,
				src.OngoingServicingRate,
				src.OngoingServicingSource,
				src.DA,
				src.AmountReceived,
				src.Premium,
				src.AgentSplit,
				src.CommissionType,
				src.CommissionTypeDesc,
				src.PayBasisCode,					--AG 13/06/2018
				src.PayBasisDesc,					--AG 13/06/2018
				src.PaymentMatchedDate,				--AG 13/06/2018
				src.Month,
				src.FrequencyCode,
				src.FrequencyDesc,
				src.ReassignedProductGroupCode,		--AG 05/06/2018
				src.ReassignedProductGroupName,		--AG 05/06/2018
				src.RecognitionType,
				src.CalculationType,
				src.Source,
				src.DateInserted,
				src.DateLastUpdated)				--Merge statements must have a ;
	output $action into @SummaryOfChanges;
						
	/****************************************************************************

		Update OpenAccess
																		
	****************************************************************************/

/*	
	--Do not include MBF in the OpenAccess Commission Listing as it is on the MBF download
	--and we don't want MBF double counting.
	update	oal
		set VNB_Points = r.PointsTotal - r.MBF		--AG 04/06/2018 (2)
	from	msit_CommissionStatement cs
/*			inner join (select	distinct PKID
						from	owt_TransformationMovements tm 
						where	tm.DriverTableName = 'sa_swift_S_AGMFIL'
						and		tm.CommissionStatement = 'Y') tm on tm.PKID = cs.PendingPaymentID
*/			inner join msit_OpenworkAdviserListing oal on oal.SourceID = cs.ID and oal.Source = 'Openwork 2006'
			inner join owt_Recognition r 
						on r.SourceID = cs.PendingPaymentID
						and r.Source = oal.Source
	--where	isnull(oal.VNB_Points,0) <> isnull(r.PointsTotal,0)
	
	select @OALRowCount = @@rowcount
*/
	COMMIT TRANSACTION      
	
	select	@RowCount = COUNT(*)
	from	@SummaryOfChanges
	where	Change = 'INSERT'

	set @ProcessMessage = 'owt_Recognition (insert) = ' + convert(nvarchar(10), @RowCount)
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseLog, @ProcessMessage, null, @Module, @Client

	select	@RowCount = COUNT(*)
	from	@SummaryOfChanges
	where	Change = 'UPDATE'

	set @ProcessMessage = 'owt_Recognition (update) = ' + convert(nvarchar(10), @RowCount)
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseLog, @ProcessMessage, null, @Module, @Client
/*
	set @ProcessMessage = 'msit_OpenworkAdviserListing (update) = ' + convert(nvarchar(10), @OALRowCount)
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseLog, @ProcessMessage, null, @Module, @Client
*/
	/****************************************************************************

		T H E   E N D
																		
	****************************************************************************/
	
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseEnd, @ProcName, null, @Module, @Client

END TRY

BEGIN CATCH 

	select @ErrNum = ERROR_NUMBER(), @ErrMsg = ERROR_MESSAGE(), @ErrSev = ERROR_SEVERITY(), @ErrLine = ERROR_LINE(), @ErrState = XACT_STATE()
	set @ErrMsg = REPLACE(@ErrMsg, '.', '') + ' (error no: ' + CAST(@ErrNum AS VARCHAR(10)) + ') on line ' + CAST(@ErrLine AS VARCHAR(10))
	
	-- Test XACT_STATE for 0, 1, or -1.
    -- If 1, the transaction is committable.
    -- If -1, the transaction is uncommittable and should be rolled back.
    -- If 0, there is no transaction and a commit or rollback operation would generate an error.

	if @ErrState = -1			-- Transaction is uncommitable
		rollback transaction

	if @ErrState = 1			
		commit transaction

	-- Error message line 1
	set @ErrMsgBrief = left(@ErrMsg,100)
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseError, @ErrMsgBrief, null, @Module, @Client
	
	-- Error message line 2 - if any text exists
	set @ErrMsgBrief = substring(@ErrMsg,101,100)
	if len(@ErrMsgBrief) > 0
		exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseError, @ErrMsgBrief, null, @Module, @Client

	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseEnd, @ProcName, null, @Module, @Client

	RAISERROR(@ErrMsg, @ErrSev , 1)

END CATCH

/****************************************************************************

			E N D															

****************************************************************************/

return @ErrNum


GO
/****** Object:  StoredProcedure [dbo].[owp_RemoveLatestMonthNonSwiftFeeListings]    Script Date: 7/3/2026 3:44:25 PM ******/
SET ANSI_NULLS OFF
GO
SET QUOTED_IDENTIFIER OFF
GO
/****************************************************************************
     Program:   owp_RemoveLatestMonthNonSwiftFeeListings            
    Author: A Groves
Date created: 08/04/2008              
                      
 Description:   This procedure can be called after the Fee Listing data
        has been loaded as part of the Month End process to remove 
        the Fee Listing Data - JUST for this most recent month
        and ONLY non-Swift data.

        This will enable corrections to be made so that the data
        can be re-loaded.

        It is called as follows:

        exec owp_RemoveLatestMonthNonSwiftFeeListings 'dd/mm/yyyy'
        
        For example, to delete March 08 Month End data call as follows:

        exec owp_RemoveLatestMonthNonSwiftFeeListings '01/04/2008'


  Amendment History               
  -----------------               
                      
  Date    Who     Description       
  ----    ---     -----------     
  10/04/08  A Groves  Remove call to "exec mscp_NSRefreshCurrentData" 
              and replace with truncate of 
              msit_FeesPreSwiftCurrentListing to make back out
              work properly.
****************************************************************************/

CREATE PROCEDURE [dbo].[owp_RemoveLatestMonthNonSwiftFeeListings] @MonthToDelete varchar(10) 
  
AS
BEGIN
  
delete  from msit_FeesNonSWIFTFeeListing      --This would delete March 08 Month End figures
where month = convert(datetime,@MonthToDelete,103)--Only Main/ScottEq/Sterling – so source not needed 
                  
exec mscp_NSRefreshNonSwiftUserAccessControl

truncate table msit_FeesPreSwiftCurrentListing 

delete  from msit_OpenworkAdviserListing
where   source = 'Openwork 2005'
and   month = convert(datetime,@MonthToDelete,103)

delete from msit_ZANAdviserListing
where month = convert(datetime,@MonthToDelete,103)  --Only ZAN - so source not needed)
  
exec mstp_OpenworkAdviserListingBusinesses

END

GO
/****** Object:  StoredProcedure [dbo].[owp_SelectAgentsbyPanelforLastNWorkingDays]    Script Date: 7/3/2026 3:44:25 PM ******/
SET ANSI_NULLS ON
GO
SET QUOTED_IDENTIFIER ON
GO
/****************************************************************************
Program:  	    owp_SelectAgentsbyPanelforLastNWorkingDays
Author:	        Mike Cawood
Date Created:	  05/04/2011							
											
Description:	

This procedure extracts all users with the following Job Titles whose Section
code (UPS_Section on sa_insight_UserPosition) matches the input value.

- 03: Non-Advising Seller
- 04: Financial Adviser
- 05: Practice Principal
- 39: DA Principal
- 42: Schedule E Seller

Only those sa_insight_UserPosition entries updated within the last N workings
days (this supplied as input parameter) are output.

For default run (Cases since previous working day for Section 3) it should be 
called as follows:
		exec owp_SelectAgentsbyPanelforLastNWorkingDays '0','3'

For ALL Cases (for Section 3) it should be called as follows:
		exec owp_SelectAgentsbyPanelforLastNWorkingDays '9999','3'
			
Amendment History								
-----------------								
											
Date  		    Who		    	  Description				
----	    	  --- 			    -----------			


****************************************************************************/
CREATE PROCEDURE [dbo].[owp_SelectAgentsbyPanelforLastNWorkingDays]
	@Days     int = 0,
	@Section  int = 0
AS

declare @Yesterday datetime;
set @Yesterday = dateadd(dd,-1,datediff(dd,0,getdate()));

declare @ExtractDate datetime;
set @ExtractDate = (select dbo.owf_CalcDateNWorkingDaysEarlierthanDate(@Yesterday,@Days));

select DISTINCT
u1.USR_ExternalID as AgentUID,u1.USR_Name as AgentName,CD1.Code_Description as UserType,
CD3.Code_Description as JobTitle,CD2.Code_Description as PanelName,ups_Section as SectionCode,
UPS_CreatedDate as DateCreated,u2.USR_Name as CreatedBy,
UPS_UpdatedDate as LastUpdated,u3.USR_Name as UpdatedBy
from dbo.sa_insight_UserPosition
inner join dbo.sa_insight_UserDetails u1 on u1.USR_ID = UPS_UserId
inner join dbo.sa_insight_CodeDescription CD1 on CD1.Code_Code = UPS_UserType and CD1.Code_CodeType = 11   --UserType
inner join dbo.sa_insight_CodeDescription CD2 on CD2.Code_Code = UPS_Section and CD2.Code_CodeType = 53   --Panel
inner join dbo.sa_insight_CodeDescription CD3 on CD3.Code_Code = UPS_JobTitle and CD3.Code_CodeType = 54   --JobTitle
inner join dbo.sa_insight_UserDetails u2 on u2.USR_ID = UPS_CreatedBy
inner join dbo.sa_insight_UserDetails u3 on u3.USR_ID = UPS_UpdatedBy
where @ExtractDate <= UPS_UpdatedDate
and UPS_Section = @Section
and UPS_JobTitle in (3,4,5,39,42) --Non-Advising Seller/FA/Principal/DA Principal/Sched E Seller
order by u1.USR_ExternalID;
GO
/****** Object:  StoredProcedure [dbo].[owp_ServicesCalculateStandingOrders]    Script Date: 7/3/2026 3:44:25 PM ******/
SET ANSI_NULLS ON
GO
SET QUOTED_IDENTIFIER ON
GO
/*********************************************************************************************************

Program:		[dbo].[owp_ServicesCalculateStandingOrders]			
Author:			Alan Groves
Date created:	14/08/2019
											
Description:
===========

This proc generates standing orders for the services introduced by Project Concert. The first service
is the electronic ID&V service through TransUnion. Openwork pays TransUnion directly and then recovers 
the costs via Swift Standing Orders to each enterprise. This proc populates table 
"owt_ServicesStandingOrders" which has a very similar layout to the Swift table CommAgentStandingOrders. 

Note that this proc should always be generic. It processes the "owoa_Services" table which has been 
designed to be generic. If you're tempted to put any source specific coding in this proc, then I would
say that you've not followed the system design principles.

There is an "Exported" indicator on the table which is set when the standing orders are exported to Swift. 

This proc is called as follows:
	
	exec [dbo].[owp_ServicesCalculateStandingOrders] 'Openwork', 'Services'
			
AMENDMENT HISTORY				
=================								

Date		Author		Description
----		------		-----------
*************************************************************************************************************/

CREATE PROCEDURE [dbo].[owp_ServicesCalculateStandingOrders] 
	@Client		varchar(50),
	@Module		varchar(50)
as

set nocount on
set xact_abort on	-- Ensures all SQL statements are rolled back in the event of an error.

declare @PhaseStart					varchar(50),
		@PhaseEnd					varchar(50),
		@PhaseLog					varchar(50),
		@PhaseError					varchar(50),
		@Process					varchar(100),
		@ProcessMessage				varchar(100),
		@RowCount					int,
		@ErrMsg						varchar(400),
		@ErrMsgBrief				varchar(100), 
		@Severity 					int,			
		@DateLastUpdated			datetime,
		@StandingOrderDate			datetime

/****************************************************************************

	Set initial parameters																
																		
****************************************************************************/

set @PhaseStart				= 'START'
set @PhaseEnd   			= 'END'
set @PhaseLog				= 'LOG'
set @PhaseError				= 'ERROR'
set @Process				= object_name(@@procid)
set @DateLastUpdated		= getdate()
set @StandingOrderDate		= dateadd(dd,0,datediff(dd,0,@DateLastUpdated))

/****************************************************************************

	Log start - we want this whether or not a rollback occurs
																		
****************************************************************************/

exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseStart, @Process, null, @Module, @Client

/****************************************************************************

	Processing start - beyond this point everything should be capable of rollback
																		
****************************************************************************/

BEGIN TRY

	/****************************************************************************

		Start transaction
																			
	****************************************************************************/

	BEGIN TRANSACTION
	
	/****************************************************************************
	
	Accumulate all the fees that have not yet been drawn off for the services
	standing orders. 
	
	****************************************************************************/

	insert into dbo.owt_ServicesStandingOrders
	(
		AgentCode,
		StandingOrderCode,
		Description,
		StartDate,
		EndDate,
		NextPaymentDue,
		Frequency,
		PaymentAmount,
		TotalPaymentAmount,
		AmountPaidToDate,
		Suspend,
		SubjectToVAT,
		CreatedBy,
		CreatedDate,
		Authorised,
		AuthorisedBy,
		AuthorisedDate,
		Exported,
		ExportedDateTime,
		Source,
		SourceType,
		DateInserted,
		DateLastUpdated
	)
	select	StdOrd.EnterpriseUID as AgentCode,
			StdOrd.StandingOrderCode,
			StdOrd.StandingOrderDescription + ' ' + convert(varchar(10),@StandingOrderDate,103) as Description,
			@StandingOrderDate as StartDate,
			null as EndDate,									--This must be null for the SO to take
			@StandingOrderDate as NextPaymentDue,
			6 as Frequency,										--6=Single
			StdOrd.StandingOrderAmount as PaymentAmount,
			StdOrd.StandingOrderAmount as TotalPaymentAmount,
			null as AmountPaidToDate,							--This must be null for the SO to take
			null as Suspend,
			1 as SubjectToVAT,
			2 as CreatedBy,
			@StandingOrderDate as CreatedDate,
			0 as Authorised,
			null as AuthorisedBy,
			@StandingOrderDate as AuthorisedDate,
			0 as Exported,										--Not yet exported
			null as ExportedDateTime,							--Not yet exported
			StdOrd.Source,
			StdOrd.SourceType,
			@DateLastUpdated as DateInserted,
			@DateLastUpdated as DateLastUpdated
	from	(select EnterpriseUID, StandingOrderCode, StandingOrderDescription, Source, SourceType, sum(-GrossAmount) as StandingOrderAmount
			 from	dbo.owoa_Services
			 where	PaymentCollected = 0			--Collect any uncollected fees
			 and	EnterpriseUID is not null		--The enterprise must be valid (should have been checked already)
			 group	by EnterpriseUID, StandingOrderCode, StandingOrderDescription, Source, SourceType
			 having	sum(GrossAmount) <> 0.0) StdOrd	--Only create a standing order if the amount is non-zero.
	
	set @RowCount = @@rowcount
	set @ProcessMessage = 'Insert into owt_ServicesStandingOrders = ' + convert(varchar(20),@RowCount)	
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseLog, @ProcessMessage, null, @Module, @Client

	/****************************************************************************

		Now link the standing orders back to the services fees
																		
	****************************************************************************/

	update	s
		set StandingOrderDescription = sso.Description,		--The description now has the date appended to it
			PaymentCollected = 1,
			PaymentCollectedDate = @StandingOrderDate,
			StandingOrderID = sso.StandingOrderID,
			DateLastUpdated = @DateLastUpdated
	from	dbo.owoa_Services s
			inner join dbo.owt_ServicesStandingOrders sso 
							on  sso.AgentCode = s.EnterpriseUID
							and sso.StandingOrderCode = s.StandingOrderCode
							and sso.Source = s.Source
							and sso.SourceType = s.SourceType
							and sso.DateInserted = @DateLastUpdated			--Get standing order just created
	where	s.PaymentCollected = 0	
	and		s.EnterpriseUID is not null

	set @RowCount = @@rowcount
	set @ProcessMessage = 'Update owoa_Services = ' + convert(varchar(20),@RowCount)	
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseLog, @ProcessMessage, null, @Module, @Client

	/****************************************************************************

		Processing end
																		
	****************************************************************************/
	
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseEnd, @Process, null, @Module, @Client

	/****************************************************************************

		End transaction
																			
	****************************************************************************/

	COMMIT TRANSACTION   

END TRY

BEGIN CATCH 

	IF @@TRANCOUNT <> 0
		ROLLBACK TRANSACTION
		
	SET @ErrMsg = @Process + ' failed.' + REPLACE(ERROR_MESSAGE(), '.', '') + ' (error no: ' + CAST(ERROR_NUMBER() AS VARCHAR(10)) + ') on line ' + CAST(ERROR_LINE() AS VARCHAR(10)) + CASE WHEN ERROR_PROCEDURE() IS NOT NULL THEN ' in ' + ERROR_PROCEDURE() ELSE '' END
	SET @Severity = ERROR_SEVERITY()
	set @ErrMsgBrief = left(@ErrMsg,100)

	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseError, @ErrMsgBrief, null, @Module, @Client
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseEnd, @Process, null, @Module, @Client

	RAISERROR(@ErrMsg, @Severity , 1)

END CATCH

/****************************************************************************

			E N D															

****************************************************************************/
GO
/****** Object:  StoredProcedure [dbo].[owp_ServicesExportStandingOrdersSSIS]    Script Date: 7/3/2026 3:44:25 PM ******/
SET ANSI_NULLS ON
GO
SET QUOTED_IDENTIFIER ON
GO
/*********************************************************************************************************

Program:		[dbo].[owp_ServicesExportStandingOrdersSSIS]			
Author:			Alan Groves
Date created:	16/08/2019
											
Description:
===========

This proc is called by a SSIS script to export the standing orders.

The standing orders are initially staged in table:

SwiftLogging.Services.sa_swift_CommAgentStandingOrders

Then stored procedure SwiftLogging.Services.xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx is run to fetch the URNs
from Swift to use and then finally the standing Orders are inserted into Swift table
SwiftProd.CommAgentStandingOrders.

When Swift "Start Of Day" is next invoked, the standing orders are collected by Swift
and written to Swift table S_AGMFIL. These will then flush back through to the Data Warehouse
overnight and will appear on the OpenAccess Account Statements of the affected enterprises.

This proc is called as follows:
	
	exec [dbo].[owp_ServicesExportStandingOrdersSSIS] 'Openwork', 'Services'
			
AMENDMENT HISTORY				
=================								

Date		Author		Description
----		------		-----------
*************************************************************************************************************/

CREATE PROCEDURE [dbo].[owp_ServicesExportStandingOrdersSSIS] 
	@Client		varchar(50),
	@Module		varchar(50)
as

set nocount on
set xact_abort on	-- Ensures all SQL statements are rolled back in the event of an error.

declare @PhaseStart					varchar(50),
		@PhaseEnd					varchar(50),
		@PhaseLog					varchar(50),
		@PhaseError					varchar(50),
		@Process					varchar(100),
		@ProcessMessage				varchar(100),
		@RowCount					int,
		@ErrMsg						varchar(400),
		@ErrMsgBrief				varchar(100), 
		@Severity 					int,			
		@DateLastUpdated			datetime
		
/****************************************************************************

	Set initial parameters																
																		
****************************************************************************/

set @PhaseStart				= 'START'
set @PhaseEnd   			= 'END'
set @PhaseLog				= 'LOG'
set @PhaseError				= 'ERROR'
set @Process				= object_name(@@procid)
set @DateLastUpdated		= getdate()

/****************************************************************************

	Log start - we want this whether or not a rollback occurs
																		
****************************************************************************/

exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseStart, @Process, null, @Module, @Client

/****************************************************************************

	Processing start - beyond this point everything should be capable of rollback
																		
****************************************************************************/

BEGIN TRY

	/****************************************************************************

		Start transaction
																			
	****************************************************************************/

	BEGIN TRANSACTION
	
	/****************************************************************************

		Update the standing orders to indicate that they have been exported.
		Note that this occurs first because SSIS needs the results set last.
																		
	****************************************************************************/

	update	sso
		set Exported = 1,
			ExportedDateTime = @DateLastUpdated,
			DateLastUpdated = @DateLastUpdated
	from	dbo.owt_ServicesStandingOrders sso
	where	sso.Exported = 0
	and		sso.AgentCode is not null

	set @RowCount = @@rowcount
	set @ProcessMessage = 'Update owt_ServicesStandingOrders exported = ' + convert(varchar(20),@RowCount)	
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseLog, @ProcessMessage, null, @Module, @Client

	/****************************************************************************
	
		Select any unexported standing orders for export.
	
	****************************************************************************/

	select	sso.StandingOrderID,
			null as ID,
			sso.AgentCode,
			sso.StandingOrderCode,
			sso.Description,
			sso.StartDate,
			sso.EndDate,
			sso.NextPaymentDue,
			sso.Frequency,
			sso.PaymentAmount,
			sso.TotalPaymentAmount,
			sso.AmountPaidToDate,
			sso.Suspend,
			sso.SubjectToVAT,
			sso.CreatedBy,
			sso.CreatedDate,
			sso.Authorised,
			sso.AuthorisedBy,
			sso.AuthorisedDate,
			0 as Exported,				--This must be left reset because it is set by the SwiftLogging export to Swift proc
			null as ExportedDateTime,	--This must be left reset because it is set by the SwiftLogging export to Swift proc
			sso.Source,
			sso.SourceType,
			@DateLastUpdated as DateInserted,
			@DateLastUpdated as DateLastUpdated
	from	dbo.owt_ServicesStandingOrders sso
	where	sso.ExportedDateTime = @DateLastUpdated
	and		sso.AgentCode is not null

	set @RowCount = @@rowcount
	set @ProcessMessage = 'Select owt_ServicesStandingOrders exported = ' + convert(varchar(20),@RowCount)	
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseLog, @ProcessMessage, null, @Module, @Client

	/****************************************************************************

		Processing end
																		
	****************************************************************************/
	
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseEnd, @Process, null, @Module, @Client

	/****************************************************************************

		End transaction
																			
	****************************************************************************/

	COMMIT TRANSACTION   

END TRY

BEGIN CATCH 

	IF @@TRANCOUNT <> 0
		ROLLBACK TRANSACTION
		
	SET @ErrMsg = @Process + ' failed.' + REPLACE(ERROR_MESSAGE(), '.', '') + ' (error no: ' + CAST(ERROR_NUMBER() AS VARCHAR(10)) + ') on line ' + CAST(ERROR_LINE() AS VARCHAR(10)) + CASE WHEN ERROR_PROCEDURE() IS NOT NULL THEN ' in ' + ERROR_PROCEDURE() ELSE '' END
	SET @Severity = ERROR_SEVERITY()
	set @ErrMsgBrief = left(@ErrMsg,100)

	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseError, @ErrMsgBrief, null, @Module, @Client
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseEnd, @Process, null, @Module, @Client

	RAISERROR(@ErrMsg, @Severity , 1)

END CATCH

/****************************************************************************

			E N D															

****************************************************************************/
GO
/****** Object:  StoredProcedure [dbo].[owp_SQCheckCachedPermissions]    Script Date: 7/3/2026 3:44:25 PM ******/
SET ANSI_NULLS ON
GO
SET QUOTED_IDENTIFIER ON
GO

create Procedure [dbo].[owp_SQCheckCachedPermissions]

    @UserId              nvarchar(50) = ''
   ,@AgentCode           nvarchar(50) = ''
   ,@Level               nvarchar(50) = ''
   ,@HierarchyTypeCode   nvarchar(50) = ''
   ,@SummaryPeriod       int = 0
   ,@Retval      nvarchar(50) output

as

/*
  OW/RH 20 Feb 2007
  Wraps existing span checking/validation function with cache wrapper for performance


*/

set nocount on


select  @RetVal = Result
from  owft_QualityPermissionCache
where UserID = @UserID
  and AgentCode = @AgentCode
  and [Level] = @Level
  and HierarchyTypeCode = @HierarchyTypeCode
  and SummaryPeriod = @SummaryPeriod
  and RunDate = convert(datetime,convert(varchar,getdate(),106))

    
IF @RetVal is not null
  return 0

-- nothing cached for today so carry on
select @Retval = dbo.msf_SQCheckPermissions (@UserId, @AgentCode, @Level, @HierarchyTypeCode, @SummaryPeriod)


-- cache value for next time
insert  owft_QualityPermissionCache(
  UserID,
  AgentCode,
  [Level],
  HierarchyTypeCode,
  SummaryPeriod,
  Result,
  RunDate)
select  @UserID,
  @AgentCode,
  @Level,
  @HierarchyTypeCode,
  @SummaryPeriod,
  @RetVal,
  convert(datetime,convert(varchar,getdate(),106))

return 0




GO
/****** Object:  StoredProcedure [dbo].[owp_Suspense_APE_Extract]    Script Date: 7/3/2026 3:44:25 PM ******/
SET ANSI_NULLS ON
GO
SET QUOTED_IDENTIFIER ON
GO


CREATE procedure [dbo].[owp_Suspense_APE_Extract]
@RunYear int
WITH RECOMPILE 
as

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
-- Mike Cawood Dec 2007
-- Generates Suspense APE/NBI Adjustments from owt_SuspenseMovements table.
-- Operates on Commission Year basis (supplied as parameter).
-- Deletes all previous adjustments on mstt_ProductionAdjustments table.
-- Generates 'Credit' adjustment for the Create Year if movement not matched.
-- Generates 'Credit' adjustment for the Create Year if movement matched in later year.
-- Generates 'Contra' adjustment for the Create Year plus 1 if 'Credit' created.
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

declare @Today datetime set @Today = CAST(CONVERT(NVARCHAR, getdate(), 112) AS DATETIME)

declare @CurrYear int
set @CurrYear = (select Year from msit_Commissionstatementperiods 
                 where @Today between periodstartdate and periodenddate)

---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
-- Create Original Suspense Movement in Create Year for unmatched entries 
-- REMOVED (or for entries where Match Year > Create Year)
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

select 
  sus.SuspMoveID,
  sus.BusinessCode,
  sus.SellerCode,
  rtrim(cl.firstnames) + ' ' + rtrim(cl.Name) as Client,
  sus.PolicyNumber,
  sus.ProductCode,
  pr.ProductID,
  sus.CreateDate,
  sus.CreateMonth as Month,
  sus.CreateYear as Year,
  sus.ProviderCode,
  sus.NBI,
  sus.APE,
  (rtrim(sus.PolicyNumber) 
   + ' / Product - ' + rtrim(sus.ProductCode)
   + ' / ID ' + rtrim(sus.SuspMoveID) 
   + ' / Provider - ' + rtrim(sus.ProviderCode) 
   + ' / Seller - ' + sus.SellerCode 
   + ' / Date - ' + CAST(CONVERT(NVARCHAR, sus.createdate, 103) AS varchar(10))
   + ' / Client - ' + rtrim(cl.Name)) as Notes
into #Suspense_Original
from owt_SuspenseMovements sus
left outer join msdt_products pr on pr.productcode = sus.productcode
left outer join mstt_clients cl on cl.client_num = sus.clientid
where sus.MatchYear is null and sus.CreateYear = @RunYear
--or (sus.MatchYear is not null and sus.MatchYear > sus.CreateYear)

---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
-- For unmatched entries where CreateYear = @RunYear and CurrYear = @RunYear+1 
-- create Contra adjustment for Create Year + 1
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
select 
  sus.SuspMoveID,
  sus.BusinessCode,
  sus.SellerCode,
  rtrim(cl.firstnames) + ' ' + rtrim(cl.Name) as Client,
  sus.PolicyNumber,
  sus.ProductCode,
  pr.ProductID,
  sus.CreateDate,
  sus.CreateMonth as Month,
  sus.CreateYear + 1 as Year,
  sus.ProviderCode,
  (sus.NBI * -1) as NBI,
  (sus.APE * -1) as APE,
  ('CONTRA' 
   + ' / ' + rtrim(sus.PolicyNumber) 
   + ' / Product - ' + rtrim(sus.ProductCode)
   + ' / ID ' + rtrim(sus.SuspMoveID) 
   + ' / Provider - ' + rtrim(sus.ProviderCode) 
   + ' / Seller - ' + sus.SellerCode 
   + ' / Date - ' + CAST(CONVERT(NVARCHAR, sus.createdate, 103) AS varchar(10))
   + ' / Client - ' + rtrim(cl.Name)) as Notes
into #Suspense_Contra
from owt_SuspenseMovements sus
left outer join msdt_products pr on pr.productcode = sus.productcode
left outer join mstt_clients cl on cl.client_num = sus.clientid
where sus.MatchYear is null and sus.CreateYear = @RunYear and @CurrYear = @RunYear+1
--sus.MatchYear is not null and sus.MatchYear > sus.CreateYear

-- Create single list of adjustments
select * into #Suspense_APE from #Suspense_Original
UNION ALL
select * from #Suspense_Contra

---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
-- Delete all existing Suspense APE/NBI Adjustment rows on the Production Adjustments table
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

delete from mstt_ProductionAdjustments 
where productcode like 'SUSP_%' and transactionid = -9

---------------------------------------------------------------------------------
-- insert Suspense APE records into mstt_ProductionAdjustments
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Insert into mstt_ProductionAdjustments 
select
  -9,
  t1.BusinessCode, 
  -9,
  -99,
  (select AdviserID from msdt_Adviser where AgentCode = t1.BusinessCode),
  2,
  (case when t1.ProductID is not null then t1.ProductID else -99 end),
  -99,
  (select DateID from msdt_CalendarTime where DateTime = t1.Month and EntryTypeID = 2),
  (select DateID from msdt_CalendarTime where DateTime = t1.Month and EntryTypeID = 2),
  2,
  -99,
  isnull((select FranchiseSizeID from msdt_FranchiseSize where FranchiseSize = (select case when MIN(FranchiseSize) < 1000 then MIN(FranchiseSize) else 1000 end from mstt_Agents where CODE = t1.BusinessCode )), -1),
  -99,
  1,
  -99,
  -99,
  2,
  -99,
  cast(t1.APE as decimal(15,2)),
  cast(t1.APE as decimal(15,2)),
  cast(t1.NBI as decimal(15,2)),
  0,
  0,
  case when t1.APE > 0 then 1 when t1.APE < 0 then -1 else 0 end,
  0,
  ('SUSP_' + t1.ProductCode),
  0,
  left(t1.Notes,255),
  'Y',
  t1.Year

from #suspense_ape t1

---------------------------------------------------------------------------------
-- clear down temp tables
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------
drop table #Suspense_Original
drop table #Suspense_Contra
drop table #Suspense_APE
GO
/****** Object:  StoredProcedure [dbo].[owp_suspenseedilist_wh]    Script Date: 7/3/2026 3:44:25 PM ******/
SET ANSI_NULLS ON
GO
SET QUOTED_IDENTIFIER ON
GO

CREATE PROCEDURE [dbo].[owp_suspenseedilist_wh] AS

set nocount on

select 
ED.ID as ID,ED.policyid as DupCase,ED.policynumber as EDIPolicy,ED.initials as EDInits,
ED.Surname as EDISurname,ed.PremiumType as EDIPremTyp,ed.PremiumAmount as EDIPremium,
ed.amountreceived as EDIAmount,
case 
when ed.amountreceived < 0 then 'Negative'
when ed.amountreceived >= 0 and ed.amountreceived < 10 then 'Less Than 10'
when ed.amountreceived >= 10 and ed.amountreceived < 100 then 'Less Than 100' 
when ed.amountreceived >= 100 and ed.amountreceived < 500 then 'Less Than 500'
when ed.amountreceived >= 500 and ed.amountreceived < 1000 then 'Less Than 1000'
when ed.amountreceived >= 1000 then 'More Than 1000'
end as ValueBand,
ed.commissionduedate as EDIDueDate,
ed.commissionreceiveddate as EDIRecDate,
case datepart(mm,ed.commissionreceiveddate)
when 01 then 'JAN'
when 02 then 'FEB'
when 03 then 'MAR'
when 04 then 'APR'
when 05 then 'MAY'
when 06 then 'JUN'
when 07 then 'JUL'
when 08 then 'AUG'
when 09 then 'SEP'
when 10 then 'OCT'
when 11 then 'NOV'
when 12 then 'DEC'
end as EDIRecMonth,
ed.IFAReference as EDIAgent,ed.IFAReferenceNumber as EDICaseID,
case ed.paymentfrequency 
when 'X' then 'IT'
when 'M' then 'Mth'
when 'A' then 'Ann'
when 'S' then 'Sin'
--else 'Unk'
end as EDIPayFreq,
case ed.paymenttype 
when 1 then 'Comm'
when 4 then 'Claw'
when 99 then 'Adj'
--else 'Unk'
end as EDIPayType,
--ed.transactionid as EDITxn,

st.statement as Statement,st.stmnt_date as StateDate,
case st.state 
when 1 then 'Unproc'
when 2 then 'Proc'
end as Process,
st.comp_code as Provider,

ex.unallocatedreasoncode as Unalloc, 
--ex.amount_rec as SuspAmount,ex.date_recv as SuspDate,
--ex.type as SuspType,ex.status as Status,ex.adjust as Adj,

p.policyref as CaseID,p.cont_num as ExtPolNo,p.productcode as Product,
coalesce(p.createdate,p.prop_date) as CreatedDate,
case
when coalesce(p.createdate,p.prop_date) is not null then 'Loaded'
end as OnSwift,
--p.client_num as Client1,p.joint_num as Client2

case q.replacement 
when 1 then 'RepA'
when 2 then 'RepB'
when 3 then 'RepC'
end as Repl,
case q.originatingsourceid
when 0 then 'Man'
when 1 then 'ETi'
when 2 then 'ETr'
when 3 then 'MBL'
when 4 then 'Tri'
when 5 then 'CTP'
--else 'Unk'
end as Source,
coalesce(pa.servicingagentcode,pa.sellingagentcode) as AgentUID,
a1.descn as AgentName,
case
when pa.sellingagentcode is null and pa.servicingagentcode is not null then 'Serv'
when pa.servicingagentcode is null and pa.sellingagentcode is not null then 'Sell'
when pa.sellingagentcode is not null and pa.servicingagentcode is not null
and pa.sellingagentcode = pa.servicingagentcode then 'Sell'
when pa.sellingagentcode is not null and pa.servicingagentcode is not null
and pa.sellingagentcode <> pa.servicingagentcode then 'Serv'
end as AgentRole,
a1.firm as AgentBusUID,
coalesce (a2.tradingname,a2.descn) as AgentBusName,
a2.manager2code as RSMUID,a3.descn as RSMName,
a2.manager4code as ASDUID,a4.descn as ASDName

,case when p.pol_num is not null then 'Issued'
when p.pol_num is not null then 'Not Issued' 
else 'No Policy' end as PolicyStatus

FROM  msit_EDIFACTCommissionStatementContents ed 
INNER JOIN msit_S_PACC ex ON ed.Pacc_ID = ex.ID 
left outer join msit_s_STMTCT st on st.statement = ex.statement 
left outer join msit_s_polmai p on p.cont_num = ed.policynumber
left outer join msit_policyqualitycheckb30 q on q.policyid = p.pol_num
left outer join msit_policyagentsb30 pa on pa.policyid = p.pol_num
left outer join msit_s_agents a1 on a1.code = coalesce(pa.servicingagentcode,pa.sellingagentcode)
left outer join msit_s_agents a2 on a2.code = a1.firm
left outer join msit_s_agents a3 on a3.code = a2.manager2code
left outer join msit_s_agents a4 on a4.code = a2.manager4code

where ex.TYPE IN (5, 6) AND ex.ID NOT IN (SELECT susp_id FROM msit_s_paccsu)

ORDER BY ed.ID,ed.PolicyNumber,p.policyref,st.STATEMENT

GO
/****** Object:  StoredProcedure [dbo].[owp_SuspenseMovementExtract]    Script Date: 7/3/2026 3:44:25 PM ******/
SET ANSI_NULLS ON
GO
SET QUOTED_IDENTIFIER ON
GO


CREATE procedure [dbo].[owp_SuspenseMovementExtract]
with recompile
as

/*
Suspense Movements Scan
=======================
This processing is designed to run daily or on an ad hoc basis and maintain the Suspense Movements 
table. This table is an audit table and is not truncated at the start of each run as is standard 
for Warehouse tables. The table is designed to be used to generate Production Adjustments for Proposal 
Transactions that have yet to be issued but for which unmatched commission receipts are held in 
Suspense. All Movements are held at transaction level and hold indicative APE and NBI values as 
derived for the Open Access Pipeline report. 

Active movements are those where the MatchDate has not been set. If an active Suspense Movement is not 
found in the current Pipeline table (meaning either it has been issued through commission matching or
it has been excluded by the Pipeline cut off rules) then it is marked as closed (by setting MatchDate).

*/

-- START of Processing

-- Define parameters for use in subsequent processing
-- @Today = yesterday as Warehouse data extracted overnight so is effectively 1 day in arrears.

declare @Today datetime set @Today = CAST(CONVERT(NVARCHAR, dateadd(dd,-1,getdate()), 112) AS DATETIME)

declare @Month datetime 
set @Month = (select Month from msit_Commissionstatementperiods 
              where @Today between periodstartdate and periodenddate)

declare @Year int
set @Year = (select Year from msit_Commissionstatementperiods 
              where @Today between periodstartdate and periodenddate)

-- First identify the current set of Proposals from the Open Access Pipeline table

CREATE TABLE [#CurrSusp] (
  [BusinessCode] [varchar] (7),
  [SellerCode] [varchar] (7),
  [PropTranID] [int],
  [PolicyID] [int],
  [ClientID] [int],
  [CaseID] [int],
  [PolicyNumber] [varchar] (25),
  [StatusDate] [datetime],
  [WrittenDate] [datetime],
  [ProviderCode] [varchar] (10),
  [ProductCode] [varchar] (8),
  [ProdGroupCode] [varchar] (2),
  [PolicySuspend] [varchar] (1),
  [UpliftRate] [float],
  [SellerSplit] [float],
  [NBI] [float],
  [APE] [float],
  [SuspenseCount] [int],
  [SuspenseAmount] [float] NULL)

insert into #CurrSusp
(BusinessCode,SellerCode,PropTranID,PolicyID,ClientID,CaseID,PolicyNumber,StatusDate,WrittenDate,
 ProviderCode,ProductCode,ProdGroupCode,PolicySuspend,UpliftRate,SellerSplit,NBI,APE,SuspenseCount,
 SuspenseAmount)
select BusinessCode,SellerCode,PropTranID,PolicyID,ClientID,CaseID,
PolicyNumber,StatusDate,WrittenDate,ProviderCode,ProductCode,ProdGroupcode,PolicySuspend,
UpliftRate,SellerSplit,NBI,APE,SuspenseCount,SuspenseAmount
from owoa_pipeline
where statuscode = 2      -- Proposal in Pipeline with UnmatchedSuspense
and nbi is not null and ape is not null -- Proposal with Commission Splits

-- Insert new 'Suspense' Movements not already held on table

insert into owt_SuspenseMovements
(BusinessCode,SellerCode,PropTranID,PolicyID,ClientID,CaseID,PolicyNumber,StatusDate,WrittenDate,
 ProviderCode,ProductCode,ProdGroupCode,PolicySuspend,UpliftRate,SellerSplit,NBI,APE,SuspenseCount,
 SuspenseAmount,CreateDate,CreateMonth,CreateYear,MoveStatus,MatchDate,MatchMonth,MatchYear,
 MoveType,NextYearID)

select t1.*,getdate() as CreateDate,@Month as CreateMonth,@Year as CreateYear,
'Suspense' as MoveStatus,Null as MatchDate,Null as MatchMonth,Null as MatchYear,
'Suspense' as MoveType,Null as NextYearID
from #currsusp t1
left outer join owt_SuspenseMovements su on su.proptranid = t1.proptranid
where su.suspmoveid is NULL

-- Derive matched dates for unmatched Movements on table linked to Written transaction
select ex.TransactionID,pt.WrittenTranid,pt.Policyid,min(ex.Date_recv) as MatchDate
into #WrittenMatches
from mstt_expectation ex
inner join mstt_policytransactions pt on pt.id = ex.transactionid
where ex.type not in (5,6) and ex.status in (2,3)
and pt.writtentranid in (select proptranid from owt_SuspenseMovements where matchdate is null)
group by ex.transactionid,pt.writtentranid,pt.policyid
order by pt.writtentranid

-- For other unmatched Movements find MatchDate for each transaction linked to policy
select ex.TransactionID,pt.WrittenTranid,pt.Policyid,min(ex.Date_recv) as MatchDate
into #IssuedMatches
from mstt_expectation ex
inner join mstt_policytransactions pt on pt.id = ex.transactionid
inner join owt_SuspenseMovements su on su.policyid = pt.policyid
where ex.type not in (5,6) and ex.status in (2,3)
and pt.id not in (select TransactionID from #WrittenMatches)
and su.MatchDate is null
group by ex.transactionid,pt.writtentranid,pt.policyid
order by pt.policyid,ex.TransactionID

-- Find earliest MatchDate after StatusDate of Movement
select t1.PolicyID,min(t1.MatchDate) as MatchDate
into #FirstMatches
from #IssuedMatches t1
inner join owt_SuspenseMovements su on su.policyid = t1.policyid
where CAST(CONVERT(NVARCHAR,su.statusdate, 112) AS DATETIME) <= CAST(CONVERT(NVARCHAR,t1.matchdate, 112) AS DATETIME)
group by t1.PolicyID
order by t1.PolicyID

-- Close movements as 'Matched' if no longer on Pipeline table

update owt_SuspenseMovements
set MatchDate   = coalesce(t2.MatchDate,t3.MatchDate,@Today),
    MoveStatus  = 'Matched'
from owt_SuspenseMovements su 
left outer join #currsusp t1 on su.proptranid = t1.proptranid
left outer join #WrittenMatches t2 on t2.writtentranid = su.proptranid
left outer join #FirstMatches t3 on t3.policyid = su.policyid
where t1.proptranid is null and su.MatchDate is null

update owt_SuspenseMovements
set MatchMonth = (select Month from msit_CommissionStatementPeriods
      where CAST(CONVERT(NVARCHAR,matchdate, 112) AS DATETIME) between PeriodStartDate and PeriodEndDate),
    MatchYear  = (select Year from msit_CommissionStatementPeriods
      where CAST(CONVERT(NVARCHAR,matchdate, 112) AS DATETIME) between PeriodStartDate and PeriodEndDate)
from owt_SuspenseMovements su
where MatchDate is not null and MatchMonth is null

drop table #WrittenMatches
drop table #IssuedMatches
drop table #FirstMatches
drop table #currsusp

-- END of Processing


GO
/****** Object:  StoredProcedure [dbo].[owp_tranlistsellerfranchise]    Script Date: 7/3/2026 3:44:25 PM ******/
SET ANSI_NULLS OFF
GO
SET QUOTED_IDENTIFIER OFF
GO
CREATE PROCEDURE [dbo].[owp_tranlistsellerfranchise] AS

set nocount on
select po.cont_num as ProviderRef,po.policyref as CaseID,co.agent_code as SellerUID,a2.descn as SellerName,
coalesce(co.franchiseagentcode,co.accessagentcode,co.directlyauthorisedagentcode,co.agent_code) as BusinessUID,
coalesce(a.tradingname,a.descn) as BusinessName,po.comp_code as Provider,
c.firstnames as Forenames,c.name as Surname,c.refer as ClientRef

from mstt_policies po
inner join mstt_policytransactions pt on pt.policyid = po.pol_num
inner join mstt_commissions co on co.transactionid = pt.id and co.commissiontype = 1 and co.grossornet = 'G'
inner join mstt_clients c on c.client_num = po.client_num
left outer join mstt_agents a on 
coalesce(co.franchiseagentcode,co.accessagentcode,co.directlyauthorisedagentcode,co.agent_code) = a.code
left outer join mstt_agents a2 on co.agent_code = a2.code

--where coalesce(a.tradingname,a.descn) like 'newcastle %'  
--po.cont_num like 'S-515606%'

group by 
po.cont_num,po.policyref,co.agent_code,a2.descn,
coalesce(co.franchiseagentcode,co.accessagentcode,co.directlyauthorisedagentcode,co.agent_code),
coalesce(a.tradingname,a.descn),po.comp_code,c.firstnames,c.name,c.refer

order by 
coalesce(co.franchiseagentcode,co.accessagentcode,co.directlyauthorisedagentcode,co.agent_code),
po.cont_num


GO
/****** Object:  StoredProcedure [dbo].[owp_TransformationMovements]    Script Date: 7/3/2026 3:44:25 PM ******/
SET ANSI_NULLS ON
GO
SET QUOTED_IDENTIFIER ON
GO
/********************************************************************************************
 Object  : procedure
 Name    : owp_TransformationMovements
 Author  : M. Cawood
 Created : 22/01/2010

 Call as 
    declare @StartDate datetime, @Days int;
    set @Days = 0
    set @StartDate = dateadd(dd,0,datediff(dd,0,getdate()-@Days))
    exec owp_TransformationMovements 'Openwork', 'Movements', @StartDate


MPC : 21 Jan 2010

This procedure identifies movements on underlying Staging tables that can be used by
Transformation processes in "Movements" mode. Previously, all such transformations
have operated in 'FULL' mode by truncating the transformed table and reloading the
table each run. Run times have increased in line with data volumes.

Movements are identified using the X_MOVEMENTS tables where X is the name of the 
Swift or OMS staging table (e.g. sa_swift_S_AGMFIL_MOVEMENTS). The Start Date input
to this procedure is used to select all movements whose MovementDate is on or after
the input date. If no valid date is provided the procedure defaults to Today's date.

Movements are also generated from related tables for the driver staging table. For
example, sa_swift_S_AGMFIL movements are generated from movements in the
sa_swift_S_AGMPAY table for use in the msp_CommissionStatement transformation.

The owt_TransformationMovements table is truncated in each run and repopulated with
movements for the period selected. The table is designed to operate with the 'MOVE'
mode input to relevant transformations. When the 'FULL' mode is used by these
transformations this table is not used.

Movements are stored for the following Staging tables:
  sa_swift_S_AGMFIL
  sa_swift_ReportBACSExport


